WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.339
Scholastic audio presents Wings of Fire.

00:00:17.399 --> 00:00:22.500
Book 9, Talons of Power, by Tooey T

00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:23.160
Sutherland.

00:00:23.219 --> 00:00:25.980
Read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:51.060
The Jade Mountain Prophecy.

00:00:51.119 --> 00:00:55.200
Beware the darkness of dragons.

00:00:55.259 --> 00:00:58.320
Beware the stalker of dreams.

00:00:58.380 --> 00:01:01.920
Beware the talons of power and fire.

00:01:01.979 --> 00:01:05.519
Beware one who is not what she seems.

00:01:05.579 --> 00:01:09.299
Something is coming to shake the earth.

00:01:09.359 --> 00:01:12.000
Something is coming to scorch the

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:12.480
ground.

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.780
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

00:01:15.780 --> 00:01:16.500
and ice.

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:19.439
Unless the lost city of night can be

00:01:19.439 --> 00:01:19.739
found.

00:01:31.799 --> 00:01:35.040
Prologue.

00:01:35.159 --> 00:01:36.719
Three years ago.

00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:40.799
The royal hatchery was supposed to be a

00:01:40.799 --> 00:01:43.799
warm, safe, peaceful place for eggs to

00:01:43.799 --> 00:01:46.079
rest quietly until it was time to hatch.

00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:48.780
It was not supposed to be a death trap

00:01:48.780 --> 00:01:49.859
that gave you the creeps.

00:01:49.920 --> 00:01:53.879
It's not a death trap, Coral would

00:01:53.879 --> 00:01:54.359
protest.

00:01:54.420 --> 00:01:55.739
Whenever Gil brought this up.

00:01:55.859 --> 00:01:59.579
Seawing princesses and princes have been

00:01:59.579 --> 00:02:02.040
hatching there for 1000s of years, I

00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:04.799
hatched there, and it was safe and

00:02:04.799 --> 00:02:05.280
beautiful.

00:02:05.340 --> 00:02:07.500
It's part of our heritage.

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:09.360
It's a sea wing tradition.

00:02:09.419 --> 00:02:11.339
There's nothing wrong with the hatchery.

00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:13.199
The problem is our useless guards.

00:02:13.259 --> 00:02:15.539
They're doing their best.

00:02:15.599 --> 00:02:16.919
Gail objected.

00:02:16.979 --> 00:02:20.219
You can only expect so much of a dragon.

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:24.120
I'm not expecting the 3 moons in a bowl

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:25.979
Coral growled.

00:02:26.039 --> 00:02:28.139
All they have to do is protect my eggs

00:02:28.139 --> 00:02:30.419
until an air hatches.

00:02:30.479 --> 00:02:32.159
Why is that so hard?

00:02:32.219 --> 00:02:35.099
Gil didn't know the answer to that.

00:02:35.159 --> 00:02:37.979
He didn't know why they'd lost 6 female

00:02:37.979 --> 00:02:39.419
eggs in the last 5 years.

00:02:39.479 --> 00:02:42.240
He didn't know how his other 3 daughters

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:42.599
had died.

00:02:42.659 --> 00:02:45.780
Coral was sure there was an assassin in

00:02:45.780 --> 00:02:48.240
the palace, but Gil didn't understand who

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:49.680
would want to kill so many little

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:50.340
princesses.

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:53.580
His heart ached as he swam through the

00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:55.500
deep palace, thinking about all the

00:02:55.500 --> 00:02:56.759
dragonettes they had lost.

00:02:56.879 --> 00:02:59.939
Coral was trying so hard to hatch an air

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:02.280
that she was having eggs every year now.

00:03:02.340 --> 00:03:05.219
The palaces were overflowing with all the

00:03:05.219 --> 00:03:07.800
sons who had survived the many hatchings

00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:10.860
sea wing princes were everywhere, to the

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:12.659
point where an entire wing of the deep

00:03:12.659 --> 00:03:14.819
palace had been set aside for them to

00:03:14.819 --> 00:03:15.240
live in.

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:18.000
Gil tried hard to remember all their

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.860
names and tell them apart.

00:03:19.919 --> 00:03:21.599
Coral didn't bother.

00:03:21.659 --> 00:03:25.259
But there were 24 of them already, +3

00:03:25.259 --> 00:03:26.400
more waiting to hatch.

00:03:26.520 --> 00:03:28.979
He sometimes wished they didn't have the

00:03:28.979 --> 00:03:31.620
animus touched balance that indicated

00:03:31.620 --> 00:03:33.060
male versus female eggs.

00:03:33.180 --> 00:03:35.520
He wondered if they were making it easier

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:38.520
for the assassin, separating the eggs so

00:03:38.520 --> 00:03:39.719
clearly in the hatchery.

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.639
But then he wondered if it didn't

00:03:41.639 --> 00:03:41.819
matter.

00:03:41.879 --> 00:03:45.060
Without a way to tell them apart, perhaps

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:47.039
the assassin would just have destroyed

00:03:47.039 --> 00:03:47.879
all the eggs.

00:03:47.939 --> 00:03:51.780
His wings took him toward the hatchery as

00:03:51.780 --> 00:03:54.360
they did all the time now, sometimes 5

00:03:54.360 --> 00:03:54.960
times a day.

00:03:55.020 --> 00:03:58.319
So far, Carl's latest plan had been

00:03:58.319 --> 00:03:58.500
working.

00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:00.780
It wouldn't be much longer before the

00:04:00.780 --> 00:04:02.939
eggs hatched, safe and sound.

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:05.460
And then they could be taken out of the

00:04:05.460 --> 00:04:07.680
royal hatchery, which would be a relief

00:04:07.680 --> 00:04:08.159
to Gil.

00:04:08.219 --> 00:04:11.099
Although, given what happened to the

00:04:11.099 --> 00:04:13.560
other princesses, he wasn't really sure

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:14.639
they would be safe anywhere.

00:04:14.699 --> 00:04:18.420
The new council chief of Dragonette Care

00:04:18.420 --> 00:04:20.459
was nervous but dedicated.

00:04:20.519 --> 00:04:23.519
Abalone had a deputy chief to help him

00:04:23.519 --> 00:04:26.099
and together they rotated in and out of

00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:28.499
the hatchery, so someone was watching the

00:04:28.499 --> 00:04:30.359
2 princess eggs at every moment.

00:04:30.420 --> 00:04:34.259
Abalone and Snapper were 2 of Gil's most

00:04:34.259 --> 00:04:35.160
loyal soldiers.

00:04:35.220 --> 00:04:37.680
He had talon picked them himself.

00:04:37.740 --> 00:04:39.360
And yet.

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:43.019
And yet, he couldn't stop checking on

00:04:43.019 --> 00:04:46.019
them, just to be sure, just to be safe.

00:04:46.079 --> 00:04:49.439
He slid open the door and swam inside the

00:04:49.439 --> 00:04:50.819
dark, egg shaped room.

00:04:50.939 --> 00:04:53.939
His wings fluttered in the bursts of warm

00:04:53.939 --> 00:04:56.220
water that bubbled through the hatchery

00:04:56.220 --> 00:04:58.560
keeping it at the perfect temperature for

00:04:58.560 --> 00:04:59.579
the eggs.

00:04:59.639 --> 00:05:01.019
Abalone?

00:05:01.079 --> 00:05:02.459
He flashed an aquatic.

00:05:02.519 --> 00:05:04.079
It was very quiet.

00:05:04.199 --> 00:05:07.500
The marble statue of his daughter Orca

00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:10.379
loomed over the nests, watching over her

00:05:10.379 --> 00:05:11.699
future brothers and sisters.

00:05:11.819 --> 00:05:14.699
Gil wished the statue could protect them

00:05:14.699 --> 00:05:16.980
as fiercely as her face suggested.

00:05:17.040 --> 00:05:20.339
He wished Orca were still alive, so she

00:05:20.339 --> 00:05:21.360
could protect them herself.

00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:24.660
But if she were alive, Coral would be

00:05:24.660 --> 00:05:24.899
dead.

00:05:24.959 --> 00:05:26.639
He shook his head.

00:05:26.699 --> 00:05:29.399
He would never understand why Orca

00:05:29.399 --> 00:05:31.199
challenged her mother for the throne at

00:05:31.199 --> 00:05:32.040
such a young age.

00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:34.319
If she had only waited.

00:05:34.379 --> 00:05:36.420
They could have had so many more years

00:05:36.420 --> 00:05:37.800
together as a family.

00:05:37.860 --> 00:05:40.560
Unless the assassin killed her too.

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:43.980
He shivered, and swam farther into the

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:44.160
room.

00:05:44.220 --> 00:05:47.759
Abalone was slumped over the nest with

00:05:47.759 --> 00:05:50.100
the 2 princess eggs in it, his wings

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:50.699
covering them.

00:05:50.819 --> 00:05:52.620
Abalone?

00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:54.899
Gil hurried over, worried.

00:05:54.959 --> 00:05:57.300
Abalone never slummed.

00:05:57.360 --> 00:05:58.980
He hardly ever even sat down.

00:05:59.040 --> 00:06:02.040
He was always on full alert, always a

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:02.819
model soldier.

00:06:02.879 --> 00:06:05.399
Gil shook his friend's shoulder.

00:06:05.459 --> 00:06:07.139
With a soft groan.

00:06:07.199 --> 00:06:10.920
Abalone sat up, and Gil realized that the

00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:13.560
council chief was a strange white color

00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:14.459
around his gills.

00:06:14.579 --> 00:06:17.459
His eyes were bloodshot, and there were

00:06:17.459 --> 00:06:19.620
flecks of foam rising from his scales.

00:06:19.620 --> 00:06:23.939
I'm sorry, Avalone flashed, with a

00:06:23.939 --> 00:06:25.620
phosphorescent scales under his wings.

00:06:25.680 --> 00:06:28.019
I've been waiting for someone to come.

00:06:28.079 --> 00:06:29.939
But I won't leave the eggs.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:31.139
I won't.

00:06:31.259 --> 00:06:32.879
They'll be safe.

00:06:32.939 --> 00:06:34.620
I promise.

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:37.439
He reached to cover them with his wings

00:06:37.439 --> 00:06:39.600
again, and staggered sideways.

00:06:39.720 --> 00:06:43.439
You're sick, said Gil, catching him

00:06:43.439 --> 00:06:44.759
before he could land on the eggs.

00:06:44.819 --> 00:06:46.319
You shouldn't be here.

00:06:46.379 --> 00:06:47.399
I'll go get help.

00:06:47.459 --> 00:06:48.839
Yes.

00:06:48.899 --> 00:06:49.560
No.

00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:51.240
Avalone flashed.

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:54.060
Afraid I'll drift off.

00:06:54.120 --> 00:06:56.759
Everything, spinning.

00:06:56.879 --> 00:06:59.279
Can you make it to the healing room on

00:06:59.279 --> 00:06:59.579
your own?

00:06:59.639 --> 00:07:00.899
Gil asked.

00:07:00.959 --> 00:07:02.939
If I stay here to guard the X?

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:04.439
Maybe.

00:07:04.560 --> 00:07:08.100
Abalone tried to paddle forward, shifting

00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:10.980
his wings, and instantly violent tremors

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:11.939
shook his whole body.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:15.720
He gasped and curled into a small ball on

00:07:15.720 --> 00:07:17.339
the smooth floor of the hatchery.

00:07:17.399 --> 00:07:19.560
All right, stay here.

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:22.019
Watch the eggs and don't fall asleep.

00:07:22.079 --> 00:07:24.000
I'll grab someone and send for help.

00:07:24.060 --> 00:07:27.180
Gil swam to the door as fast as he could

00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:29.579
and powered up the ramp to the main floor

00:07:29.579 --> 00:07:30.360
of the palace.

00:07:30.480 --> 00:07:34.199
Three little dragonettes, all about 2

00:07:34.199 --> 00:07:36.060
years old, were wrestling in the entrance

00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:38.579
hall, kicking and squeaking gleefully.

00:07:38.699 --> 00:07:42.600
Three of his sons, Gil realized, the ones

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:43.800
from 2 hatchings ago.

00:07:43.860 --> 00:07:46.439
There was only one female egg in that

00:07:46.439 --> 00:07:48.240
group, and she didn't even make it

00:07:48.240 --> 00:07:50.699
halfway through incubating, he remembered

00:07:50.699 --> 00:07:52.620
with a fresh stab of grief.

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:55.439
He flashed his scales at full brightness

00:07:55.439 --> 00:07:56.519
to get their attention.

00:07:56.579 --> 00:07:59.639
They turned toward him, blinking, and he

00:07:59.639 --> 00:08:01.019
flashed, I need help.

00:08:01.079 --> 00:08:02.220
Who's going to help me?

00:08:02.279 --> 00:08:04.920
The princess glanced at one another

00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:07.319
nervously, and then one of them paddled

00:08:07.319 --> 00:08:08.040
forward a little bit.

00:08:08.160 --> 00:08:10.439
Me, he flashed.

00:08:10.560 --> 00:08:11.879
I'll do it, Father.

00:08:11.939 --> 00:08:14.160
Good, said Gil.

00:08:14.220 --> 00:08:15.120
Thank you.

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:16.680
He hesitated.

00:08:16.740 --> 00:08:18.480
Turtle.

00:08:18.540 --> 00:08:19.980
The dragonette flashed.

00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:21.120
I'm turtle.

00:08:21.180 --> 00:08:22.860
I know.

00:08:22.920 --> 00:08:25.139
Gil answered, although he hadn't been

00:08:25.139 --> 00:08:25.439
sure.

00:08:25.500 --> 00:08:26.759
Turtle.

00:08:26.819 --> 00:08:28.019
This is very important.

00:08:28.079 --> 00:08:31.319
I need you to go find Snapper and send

00:08:31.319 --> 00:08:32.580
her to the Royal Hatchery.

00:08:32.639 --> 00:08:34.980
Tell her to hurry as fast as her wings

00:08:34.980 --> 00:08:35.399
can swim.

00:08:35.460 --> 00:08:36.419
Can you do that?

00:08:36.480 --> 00:08:40.500
Sure, Turtle nodded, his green eyes

00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:41.039
wide.

00:08:41.100 --> 00:08:44.279
I'm counting on you, turtle, Gil said

00:08:44.279 --> 00:08:46.139
touching his son's shoulder.

00:08:46.259 --> 00:08:47.159
It's really important.

00:08:47.220 --> 00:08:48.779
I know you can do this.

00:08:48.899 --> 00:08:50.100
I'll be waiting.

00:08:50.159 --> 00:08:50.879
All right?

00:08:50.940 --> 00:08:54.659
Yes, sir, turtle answered, shivering a

00:08:54.659 --> 00:08:54.840
little.

00:08:54.899 --> 00:08:56.220
Go then.

00:08:56.279 --> 00:08:57.120
Hurry.

00:08:57.240 --> 00:09:00.779
Turtle swam away toward the kitchens with

00:09:00.779 --> 00:09:02.820
what felt like agonizing slowness.

00:09:02.940 --> 00:09:05.519
Gil reminded himself that Turtle was a

00:09:05.519 --> 00:09:05.759
prince.

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:07.500
He wouldn't fail.

00:09:07.620 --> 00:09:11.460
He'd find Snapper, abalone's deputy chief

00:09:11.460 --> 00:09:13.559
who could watch the eggs while Gil took

00:09:13.559 --> 00:09:14.759
abalone to the healing room.

00:09:14.820 --> 00:09:17.580
Gil rushed back down to the hatchery.

00:09:17.639 --> 00:09:20.879
Abalone was still awake, crouched by the

00:09:20.879 --> 00:09:22.860
eggs with his front talons pinned across

00:09:22.860 --> 00:09:26.399
his chest, Gil realized with alarm that

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:28.679
there was now a growth on abalone's neck

00:09:28.679 --> 00:09:32.100
a large, round lump that hadn't been

00:09:32.100 --> 00:09:32.820
there a few moments ago.

00:09:32.879 --> 00:09:35.700
He touched it lightly, and abalone

00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:36.419
flinched away.

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:38.460
It was blazingly hot.

00:09:38.519 --> 00:09:42.000
Gil had no idea what kind of disease this

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:42.360
was.

00:09:42.419 --> 00:09:44.580
Is it safe for him to be here?

00:09:44.639 --> 00:09:46.379
Could he infect the eggs?

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:49.259
He needed to get abalone out of the

00:09:49.259 --> 00:09:49.860
hatchery.

00:09:49.919 --> 00:09:52.559
For the safety of the eggs, but also

00:09:52.559 --> 00:09:55.139
because abalone looked closer and closer

00:09:55.139 --> 00:09:56.220
to death every moment.

00:09:56.279 --> 00:09:58.799
Hurry up, turtle.

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:01.740
They waited in painful silence.

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:04.139
Was the growth getting bigger?

00:10:04.259 --> 00:10:06.779
Turtle, where are you?

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:08.159
Come on, come on.

00:10:08.220 --> 00:10:11.879
The lump was expanding, little by

00:10:11.879 --> 00:10:12.179
little.

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:15.120
Pushing abalones, silvery blue scales

00:10:15.120 --> 00:10:17.220
into strange, jagged shapes.

00:10:17.340 --> 00:10:19.919
It looked as if it might explode any

00:10:19.919 --> 00:10:20.460
moment now.

00:10:20.519 --> 00:10:23.100
You'll be all right.

00:10:23.220 --> 00:10:25.259
Gil flashed at Avaloni.

00:10:25.320 --> 00:10:26.460
Hope is coming.

00:10:26.519 --> 00:10:29.100
Help didn't come.

00:10:29.159 --> 00:10:33.120
Time crept by, dragging its long, long

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:33.779
tale.

00:10:33.840 --> 00:10:35.039
Nobody came.

00:10:35.100 --> 00:10:38.820
Abalone started making a low, whimpering

00:10:38.820 --> 00:10:42.360
sound, ragged, like claws scrabbling up

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:43.320
the inside of his throat.

00:10:43.379 --> 00:10:46.799
His gaze was fixed on the eggs, and he

00:10:46.799 --> 00:10:49.019
kept his wings tucked in close to him

00:10:49.019 --> 00:10:50.340
rocking softly.

00:10:50.399 --> 00:10:54.720
Turtle, Gil thought, with helpless fury.

00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:56.820
This was his own fault.

00:10:56.879 --> 00:10:59.100
What a useless command he'd given.

00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:01.740
He should have sent all 3 dragonettes to

00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:02.580
find Snapper.

00:11:02.639 --> 00:11:03.600
No.

00:11:03.659 --> 00:11:05.940
He should have told them to find any

00:11:05.940 --> 00:11:08.820
other adult dragon, or to summon one of

00:11:08.820 --> 00:11:11.039
the healers, or he should have swum

00:11:11.039 --> 00:11:12.779
straight to the healing chambers the

00:11:12.779 --> 00:11:14.519
moment he saw that Abalone was ill.

00:11:14.580 --> 00:11:16.919
Now he could see there would have been

00:11:16.919 --> 00:11:18.720
time to make it there and back with a

00:11:18.720 --> 00:11:19.200
healer.

00:11:19.259 --> 00:11:22.559
But with each moment that passed, Abalone

00:11:22.559 --> 00:11:24.480
looked closer and closer to collapse.

00:11:24.539 --> 00:11:27.659
The truth was, he should have done

00:11:27.659 --> 00:11:29.039
anything other than what he did.

00:11:29.100 --> 00:11:31.379
He'd made a terrible mistake.

00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:34.139
But where was Turtle?

00:11:34.259 --> 00:11:36.720
Couldn't he figure out a smarter option?

00:11:36.779 --> 00:11:38.759
If he couldn't find Snapper?

00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:40.259
Somebody come.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:42.840
Please, please, somebody.

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:45.539
Finally, it became unbearable.

00:11:45.600 --> 00:11:48.179
Abalone would die if he didn't reach a

00:11:48.179 --> 00:11:48.779
healer soon.

00:11:48.840 --> 00:11:51.059
It might already be too late.

00:11:51.120 --> 00:11:53.159
Gil couldn't wait any longer.

00:11:53.220 --> 00:11:55.980
Oh, leave.

00:11:56.039 --> 00:11:58.980
Abalone flashed weekly. as Gil moved

00:11:58.980 --> 00:11:59.580
toward the door.

00:11:59.639 --> 00:12:01.980
I can't let you die like this.

00:12:02.039 --> 00:12:03.360
Gil flashed back.

00:12:03.419 --> 00:12:05.340
Just stay awake until I get back.

00:12:05.399 --> 00:12:08.759
He hesitated in the doorway, worrying.

00:12:08.820 --> 00:12:11.879
Abalone was no match for an assassin in

00:12:11.879 --> 00:12:12.299
this condition.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:15.000
McGill would only be gone a short time.

00:12:15.059 --> 00:12:18.120
It would be truly uncanny, terrible luck

00:12:18.120 --> 00:12:20.519
for the assassin to show up during those

00:12:20.519 --> 00:12:21.299
few moments.

00:12:21.360 --> 00:12:22.679
He swam.

00:12:22.799 --> 00:12:25.679
He swam for Abalone's life and his

00:12:25.679 --> 00:12:26.100
daughters.

00:12:26.159 --> 00:12:28.559
He burst through the palace like a

00:12:28.559 --> 00:12:30.720
typhoon, swooping up to the healing

00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:31.139
chambers.

00:12:31.200 --> 00:12:33.659
His sons were gone from the main

00:12:33.659 --> 00:12:34.139
hallway.

00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:36.840
He saw no sign of turtle or snapper

00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:37.200
anywhere.

00:12:37.259 --> 00:12:38.940
Help!

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:41.580
He flashed at full brightness as he

00:12:41.580 --> 00:12:42.600
reached the healing floor.

00:12:42.659 --> 00:12:45.120
Dragons came pouring into the hall

00:12:45.120 --> 00:12:48.179
curious, and a flurry of bubbling gasps

00:12:48.179 --> 00:12:50.700
went up as he explained abalone's

00:12:50.700 --> 00:12:51.779
condition to the healers.

00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:54.720
Three of them grabbed their kits and swam

00:12:54.720 --> 00:12:55.200
after him.

00:12:55.259 --> 00:12:58.559
Back down, down, down to the royal

00:12:58.559 --> 00:12:59.220
hatchery.

00:12:59.220 --> 00:13:02.580
They found abalone unconscious, his wings

00:13:02.580 --> 00:13:04.259
drifting in the current of the jets.

00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:05.580
For a moment.

00:13:05.639 --> 00:13:07.860
Gil thought his neck had been slashed.

00:13:07.919 --> 00:13:10.919
Then he realized that the blood running

00:13:10.919 --> 00:13:13.679
down abalone scales came from the growth

00:13:13.679 --> 00:13:15.120
which had burst.

00:13:15.179 --> 00:13:18.360
The healers hurried toward him, then

00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:21.059
stopped, turning heartbroken faces to

00:13:21.059 --> 00:13:21.419
Gil.

00:13:21.480 --> 00:13:23.220
No.

00:13:23.279 --> 00:13:25.799
Gill's scales flashed without him

00:13:25.799 --> 00:13:26.519
realizing it.

00:13:26.580 --> 00:13:27.539
No.

00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:28.559
No.

00:13:28.620 --> 00:13:32.519
The 2 eggs had been crushed, apparently

00:13:32.519 --> 00:13:34.379
by huge, heavy talons.

00:13:34.440 --> 00:13:36.720
The dragonettes inside were dead.

00:13:36.840 --> 00:13:39.659
Two more lost princesses.

00:13:39.720 --> 00:13:44.039
Gil roared his pain and fury, roared

00:13:44.039 --> 00:13:46.500
until his throat gave out, and then he

00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:47.460
whirled and swam away.

00:13:47.519 --> 00:13:50.279
He never wanted to see the royal hatchery

00:13:50.279 --> 00:13:50.519
again.

00:13:50.580 --> 00:13:55.440
Find my son turtle, he snarled, at one of

00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:57.120
the gawking dragons in the hallway.

00:13:57.179 --> 00:14:00.179
Upstairs, he saw a group of dragons

00:14:00.179 --> 00:14:02.220
approaching through the gardens, Queen

00:14:02.220 --> 00:14:04.919
Coral, returning from the summer palace

00:14:04.919 --> 00:14:06.120
and are meeting with blister.

00:14:06.179 --> 00:14:08.700
How could he tell her what had happened?

00:14:08.759 --> 00:14:10.559
What had happened again?

00:14:10.620 --> 00:14:14.460
But she saw it on his face as he swam out

00:14:14.460 --> 00:14:15.120
the door toward her.

00:14:15.179 --> 00:14:19.019
She sank suddenly, as if a boulder had

00:14:19.019 --> 00:14:19.679
been dropped on her.

00:14:19.740 --> 00:14:21.960
Touching down amid the coral and

00:14:21.960 --> 00:14:22.620
anemones.

00:14:22.679 --> 00:14:25.559
Her wings came forward, and she covered

00:14:25.559 --> 00:14:26.639
her eyes with her talons.

00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:29.279
She didn't want to see him spell it out

00:14:29.279 --> 00:14:30.000
in aquatic.

00:14:30.059 --> 00:14:33.419
I'm sorry, he flashed anyway.

00:14:33.480 --> 00:14:34.919
I'm sorry.

00:14:35.039 --> 00:14:36.960
She didn't move.

00:14:37.019 --> 00:14:38.220
Didn't look up.

00:14:38.279 --> 00:14:41.100
A movement caught Gil's eye, and he

00:14:41.100 --> 00:14:41.460
turned.

00:14:41.519 --> 00:14:45.059
Some distance away, there was turtle

00:14:45.059 --> 00:14:47.340
swimming slowly through the garden of the

00:14:47.340 --> 00:14:49.740
wounded, peering at each recuperating

00:14:49.740 --> 00:14:52.139
dragon's face, his brothers were behind

00:14:52.139 --> 00:14:55.200
him, joking and laughing, and shoving one

00:14:55.200 --> 00:14:56.039
another back and forth.

00:14:56.100 --> 00:15:00.059
Gil tore across the gardens, seized

00:15:00.059 --> 00:15:02.460
Turtle's wing, and flung him around to

00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:02.700
face him.

00:15:02.759 --> 00:15:04.259
Where have you been?

00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:05.879
Gil roared.

00:15:05.940 --> 00:15:09.000
Turtle flinched, and shielded his eyes

00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:10.980
from the intensity of gills scales.

00:15:11.039 --> 00:15:12.779
I can't find her.

00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:14.460
He flashed nervously.

00:15:14.519 --> 00:15:16.200
I'm still looking.

00:15:16.259 --> 00:15:18.240
Out here?

00:15:18.299 --> 00:15:21.120
Gil waved his talons at the nearly empty

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:23.460
section of the coral reef where injured

00:15:23.460 --> 00:15:25.799
soldiers were taken to rest and recover

00:15:25.799 --> 00:15:27.419
surrounded by color and beauty.

00:15:27.480 --> 00:15:30.539
Gil wanted to rip that beauty to shreds.

00:15:30.659 --> 00:15:33.299
He wanted to tear apart the coral reef

00:15:33.299 --> 00:15:35.340
and kill all the creatures that lived on

00:15:35.340 --> 00:15:35.519
it.

00:15:35.580 --> 00:15:40.080
Well, I I couldn't find her in the palace

00:15:40.080 --> 00:15:42.120
so I I didn't know where to look.

00:15:42.179 --> 00:15:43.019
I'm trying.

00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:46.320
It's too late, Gil growled.

00:15:46.440 --> 00:15:49.440
Your new sisters are dead, and it's your

00:15:49.440 --> 00:15:49.799
fault.

00:15:49.860 --> 00:15:51.960
Turtle blanched.

00:15:52.019 --> 00:15:55.500
But how I didn't.

00:15:56.220 --> 00:15:57.419
You were too slow.

00:15:57.480 --> 00:15:59.399
Gil backed away.

00:15:59.460 --> 00:16:02.399
Glaring at the other 2 princes, who were

00:16:02.399 --> 00:16:04.139
huddling behind an outcropping to watch

00:16:04.139 --> 00:16:04.919
with wide eyes.

00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:06.960
I'm sorry.

00:16:07.019 --> 00:16:10.200
Turtle bowed his head, fiddling with a

00:16:10.200 --> 00:16:11.759
piece of coral in his claws.

00:16:11.820 --> 00:16:15.539
I, I don't know what snapper looks like

00:16:15.539 --> 00:16:17.220
and nobody knew where she was.

00:16:17.279 --> 00:16:20.340
You shouldn't volunteer for things you're

00:16:20.340 --> 00:16:21.120
incapable of doing.

00:16:21.179 --> 00:16:22.860
Gil said harshly.

00:16:22.919 --> 00:16:25.019
You shouldn't offer to help if you're

00:16:25.019 --> 00:16:25.799
going to be useless.

00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:29.580
I really tried, Turtles said.

00:16:29.639 --> 00:16:31.080
Ringing his talons.

00:16:31.139 --> 00:16:33.120
I really really did.

00:16:33.179 --> 00:16:34.860
I promise, daddy.

00:16:34.919 --> 00:16:37.019
You failed.

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:39.840
Gil stared down at him.

00:16:39.899 --> 00:16:43.200
He felt a small pang of guilt at the

00:16:43.200 --> 00:16:45.419
crushing despair on the dragonette's face

00:16:45.419 --> 00:16:47.820
but his anger was too strong to hold back

00:16:47.820 --> 00:16:48.240
right now.

00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:52.860
I am very disappointed in you, he said.

00:16:52.919 --> 00:16:56.279
Maybe one day he would forgive Turtle.

00:16:56.399 --> 00:16:58.919
Maybe one day he'd be able to think

00:16:58.919 --> 00:16:59.879
clearly again.

00:16:59.940 --> 00:17:03.659
Even now, he knew deep down that blaming

00:17:03.659 --> 00:17:05.640
a 2 year old dragonette, for his own

00:17:05.640 --> 00:17:06.660
mistakes, was wrong.

00:17:06.720 --> 00:17:10.079
One day, when his grief had subsided

00:17:10.079 --> 00:17:12.420
maybe he could find the words to tell his

00:17:12.420 --> 00:17:13.079
son that.

00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:14.759
But not today.

00:17:14.880 --> 00:17:18.480
Gil turned away from Turtle's stricken

00:17:18.480 --> 00:17:20.700
face and swam back to Coral.

00:17:20.759 --> 00:17:23.819
She was watching him with vacant, sad

00:17:23.819 --> 00:17:24.539
eyes.

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:26.159
What did he do?

00:17:26.220 --> 00:17:28.019
She asked dimly.

00:17:28.079 --> 00:17:31.439
I sent him for help, and instead he

00:17:31.439 --> 00:17:33.059
flapped around, looking in all the wrong

00:17:33.059 --> 00:17:34.439
places and goofing off.

00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:37.980
He's only a prince, she said.

00:17:38.039 --> 00:17:39.960
What can you expect?

00:17:40.019 --> 00:17:43.440
She reached out and seized one of Gil's

00:17:43.440 --> 00:17:43.920
talons.

00:17:43.980 --> 00:17:46.559
The next one is going to live, Gil.

00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:49.559
Oh, Carl, he said.

00:17:49.619 --> 00:17:50.880
Maybe we shouldn't.

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:54.180
I'll stay with her this time, Carl said

00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:54.720
fiercely.

00:17:54.779 --> 00:17:57.000
No one else can do it except me.

00:17:57.059 --> 00:17:59.940
I was right about our incompetent

00:17:59.940 --> 00:18:00.299
guards.

00:18:00.359 --> 00:18:04.140
It wasn't Abalone's fault, Gil

00:18:04.140 --> 00:18:04.559
protested.

00:18:04.619 --> 00:18:08.700
Doesn't matter. she said, flicking a claw

00:18:08.700 --> 00:18:09.359
at the palace.

00:18:09.420 --> 00:18:11.940
I sent word to have him and Snapper both

00:18:11.940 --> 00:18:12.599
executed.

00:18:12.720 --> 00:18:14.700
Coral!

00:18:14.759 --> 00:18:16.859
Gil cried, appalled.

00:18:16.920 --> 00:18:19.500
He tried to pull away, but she gripped

00:18:19.500 --> 00:18:20.579
his talons even tighter.

00:18:20.700 --> 00:18:23.640
I'm going to keep our next daughter alive

00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:25.019
Coral said.

00:18:25.079 --> 00:18:27.660
I'll stay in the hatchery with the egg to

00:18:27.660 --> 00:18:30.059
keep it safe, but I need you to run the

00:18:30.059 --> 00:18:30.599
kingdom for me.

00:18:30.660 --> 00:18:33.000
I'll do anything.

00:18:33.059 --> 00:18:35.160
He promised sadly.

00:18:35.220 --> 00:18:37.319
He couldn't argue with her in this

00:18:37.319 --> 00:18:37.619
state.

00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:38.579
Not right now.

00:18:38.640 --> 00:18:42.779
I'll keep her by my side all the time, her

00:18:42.779 --> 00:18:43.680
whole life if I have to.

00:18:43.740 --> 00:18:47.279
Coral's eyes glowed, reflecting her

00:18:47.279 --> 00:18:48.359
scales as she spoke.

00:18:48.480 --> 00:18:50.160
I'll never leave her alone.

00:18:50.220 --> 00:18:52.619
She's going to be perfect, Gil.

00:18:52.680 --> 00:18:53.460
You'll see.

00:18:53.519 --> 00:18:56.279
She glanced down at the spot where she

00:18:56.279 --> 00:18:59.099
had landed, at the sea anemones waving

00:18:59.099 --> 00:19:01.200
long, pinkish blue tendrils over her

00:19:01.200 --> 00:19:01.559
claws.

00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:04.019
And we're going to call her.

00:19:04.079 --> 00:19:05.759
Anemone.

00:19:05.819 --> 00:19:09.960
Part one.

00:19:10.019 --> 00:19:12.240
A dragon awakes.

00:19:12.299 --> 00:19:16.019
Chapter one.

00:19:16.079 --> 00:19:20.400
The nightmare rose out of the mountain

00:19:20.400 --> 00:19:22.079
vast and glittering.

00:19:22.140 --> 00:19:25.559
Turtle had never seen a dragon so large.

00:19:25.619 --> 00:19:28.079
He never seen eyes so sharp.

00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:31.559
He knew instantly that this dragon could

00:19:31.559 --> 00:19:34.200
and would happily kill him in a

00:19:34.200 --> 00:19:34.920
heartbeat.

00:19:35.099 --> 00:19:38.400
Terror pounded through him like waves in

00:19:38.400 --> 00:19:40.920
a storm, building higher and higher.

00:19:40.980 --> 00:19:42.779
I need to hide.

00:19:42.839 --> 00:19:43.859
I need to hide.

00:19:43.920 --> 00:19:47.700
He desperately wanted to disappear, to

00:19:47.700 --> 00:19:49.980
vanish into the dark sky as if he'd never

00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:50.519
been there.

00:19:50.579 --> 00:19:53.160
He wished he could melt away, like a

00:19:53.160 --> 00:19:54.599
camouflaged rain wing.

00:19:54.660 --> 00:19:58.140
Why did I ever let anyone notice me?

00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:00.480
I'd be safe if I'd stayed boring and

00:20:00.480 --> 00:20:01.019
forgettable.

00:20:01.079 --> 00:20:04.380
This is what happens when someone sees

00:20:04.380 --> 00:20:04.559
you.

00:20:04.619 --> 00:20:06.779
Soon everyone will see you.

00:20:06.839 --> 00:20:11.279
And one day, that everyone will include a

00:20:11.279 --> 00:20:12.420
dragon who wants to kill you.

00:20:12.480 --> 00:20:15.660
He couldn't have explained how he was so

00:20:15.660 --> 00:20:16.019
sure.

00:20:16.079 --> 00:20:18.839
Dark Stalker was smiling at the

00:20:18.839 --> 00:20:19.799
dragonettes below him.

00:20:19.859 --> 00:20:23.099
In fact, he looked absolutely delighted

00:20:23.099 --> 00:20:25.259
not particularly murderous.

00:20:25.380 --> 00:20:29.880
And yet, as his eyes darted past Turtle

00:20:29.880 --> 00:20:32.700
Turtle thought he saw a flash of hatred

00:20:32.700 --> 00:20:34.440
there, deep and fierce.

00:20:34.559 --> 00:20:38.400
For some reason, this legendary dragon

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:40.799
the most powerful night wing who'd ever

00:20:40.799 --> 00:20:43.559
lived, loathed turtle with all his

00:20:43.559 --> 00:20:44.220
heart.

00:20:44.279 --> 00:20:45.720
Turtle was sure of it.

00:20:45.779 --> 00:20:49.319
He's going to kill me the 1st chance he

00:20:49.319 --> 00:20:49.619
gets.

00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:53.339
This wasn't how he'd expected his story

00:20:53.339 --> 00:20:53.819
to end.

00:20:53.880 --> 00:20:56.819
Turtle had always loved stories.

00:20:56.940 --> 00:21:00.539
He loved histories, and animus tales, and

00:21:00.539 --> 00:21:04.019
stories of war, of skyfaring pirates, or

00:21:04.019 --> 00:21:06.839
enchanted treasure, of scavengers who

00:21:06.839 --> 00:21:09.240
could speak the language of dragons, of

00:21:09.240 --> 00:21:11.279
lost tribes and faraway lands.

00:21:11.400 --> 00:21:14.279
But his favorite stories were about

00:21:14.279 --> 00:21:14.940
heroes.

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:17.339
Especially the ones in the scrolls his

00:21:17.339 --> 00:21:17.759
mother wrote.

00:21:17.819 --> 00:21:20.400
Since she was so busy with running the

00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:22.920
kingdom, writing her scrolls, and

00:21:22.920 --> 00:21:25.680
protecting her heirs, Queen Coral didn't

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:27.720
have much time or interest to spare for

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:29.160
any of her 32 sons.

00:21:29.279 --> 00:21:32.339
Reading her stories was as close as

00:21:32.339 --> 00:21:33.480
Turtle could ever get to her.

00:21:33.539 --> 00:21:37.440
He loved scrolls about brave dragons who

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:39.900
saved the day and stopped the forces of

00:21:39.900 --> 00:21:40.259
evil.

00:21:40.319 --> 00:21:43.680
One of his favorites was about a dragon

00:21:43.680 --> 00:21:46.380
named Indigo, who'd rescued the entire

00:21:46.380 --> 00:21:48.660
tribe from a deranged killer.

00:21:48.779 --> 00:21:52.140
Another starred an insignificant gardener

00:21:52.140 --> 00:21:54.779
named Droplet, who'd discovered a secret

00:21:54.779 --> 00:21:57.240
invasion of Mudwings and fought them off

00:21:57.240 --> 00:21:59.099
before they found the hidden palaces.

00:21:59.160 --> 00:22:02.700
The more Turtle read these stories, the

00:22:02.700 --> 00:22:05.339
more he imagined a story of his own, a

00:22:05.339 --> 00:22:08.279
story where Turtle was the hero, a story

00:22:08.279 --> 00:22:10.500
where Turtle battled squadrons of sky

00:22:10.500 --> 00:22:13.380
wings and storms of sand wings all on his

00:22:13.380 --> 00:22:16.200
own, a story where turtles stood at the

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:18.480
gates of the palace and swung his spear

00:22:18.480 --> 00:22:21.720
in ferocious arks, stabbing their enemies

00:22:21.720 --> 00:22:23.279
as strong as a whale.

00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:25.799
While his older brothers and the rest of

00:22:25.799 --> 00:22:27.539
the tribe cowered inside.

00:22:27.539 --> 00:22:29.819
A story that ended with his parents

00:22:29.819 --> 00:22:32.400
cheering and hugging him, and then his

00:22:32.400 --> 00:22:34.019
mother would ride a scroll that was all

00:22:34.019 --> 00:22:35.579
about him.

00:22:35.640 --> 00:22:38.940
Turtle, the strong and mighty.

00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:42.720
Turtle, a tale of a hero, heroically

00:22:42.720 --> 00:22:44.400
doing hero type things.

00:22:44.460 --> 00:22:47.880
How turtles saved the entire kingdom with

00:22:47.880 --> 00:22:48.839
his awesomeness.

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:52.859
Sometimes, when Turtle had a moment alone

00:22:52.859 --> 00:22:55.259
or when he wasn't paying attention in

00:22:55.259 --> 00:22:57.720
class, he would secretly write pieces of

00:22:57.720 --> 00:23:00.119
this story on scraps of slate, he kept

00:23:00.119 --> 00:23:00.900
hidden in his room.

00:23:01.019 --> 00:23:04.680
He dreamed that one day he'd have a whole

00:23:04.680 --> 00:23:06.960
manuscript to show his mother, and then

00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:10.680
she might say, oh, son, I know one of my

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:11.880
daughters will run the kingdom

00:23:11.880 --> 00:23:12.480
eventually.

00:23:12.539 --> 00:23:15.299
But you are the true heir I've been

00:23:15.299 --> 00:23:18.119
waiting for, the next rider in the

00:23:18.119 --> 00:23:18.359
family.

00:23:18.420 --> 00:23:21.839
A hero or a writer?

00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:23.279
Or both?

00:23:23.339 --> 00:23:24.000
Why not?

00:23:24.059 --> 00:23:26.400
That would be Turtle's place in the

00:23:26.400 --> 00:23:26.640
world.

00:23:26.700 --> 00:23:31.140
But then, too soon and disguised in a

00:23:31.140 --> 00:23:33.420
confusing shape, his chance came.

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:37.079
His one opportunity to save the day, and

00:23:37.079 --> 00:23:38.519
be a hero in his parents' eyes.

00:23:38.579 --> 00:23:41.220
But he didn't even know it until it was

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:43.140
over, and he'd failed.

00:23:43.200 --> 00:23:46.859
He failed, and they hated him.

00:23:46.920 --> 00:23:49.079
And he'd never get that chance again.

00:23:49.140 --> 00:23:53.220
That night, when he'd failed to find

00:23:53.220 --> 00:23:56.220
Snapper and save his unhatched sisters

00:23:56.220 --> 00:23:58.380
Turtle destroyed every bit of writing

00:23:58.380 --> 00:24:01.079
he'd ever done. and swore he would never

00:24:01.079 --> 00:24:01.559
write again.

00:24:01.619 --> 00:24:03.839
He'd stop dreaming.

00:24:03.900 --> 00:24:06.720
He'd stop imagining that a useless dragon

00:24:06.720 --> 00:24:07.319
like him.

00:24:07.380 --> 00:24:09.660
Could ever save the day, or make

00:24:09.660 --> 00:24:10.319
something wonderful.

00:24:10.440 --> 00:24:12.599
He wasn't the hero.

00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:15.059
And he wasn't the storyteller.

00:24:15.119 --> 00:24:18.839
He was the idiot, who fell over his claws

00:24:18.839 --> 00:24:21.420
in the 1st chapter, had to be rescued in

00:24:21.420 --> 00:24:24.180
the 4th, nearly ruined the whole plan in

00:24:24.180 --> 00:24:27.180
the ninth, and ran away at the end, or

00:24:27.180 --> 00:24:29.400
died, if he was really extra stupid.

00:24:29.460 --> 00:24:33.240
So he hid his one power, and stayed

00:24:33.240 --> 00:24:35.579
exactly where he was supposed to, under

00:24:35.579 --> 00:24:36.660
the surface of the water.

00:24:36.720 --> 00:24:39.299
In the middle of his pack of brothers

00:24:39.299 --> 00:24:42.420
ordinary, unmemorable.

00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:45.119
A dragon nobody would expect anything

00:24:45.119 --> 00:24:47.700
from, and so nobody could ever be

00:24:47.700 --> 00:24:49.019
disappointed by him again.

00:24:49.079 --> 00:24:52.680
And that had worked for quite a long time

00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:55.200
until he made the mistake of caring about

00:24:55.200 --> 00:24:57.480
some other dragons, and trying to do a

00:24:57.480 --> 00:24:59.759
couple of little things to help them, and

00:24:59.759 --> 00:25:01.500
where did that lead him?

00:25:01.559 --> 00:25:04.680
Right to the feet of the most terrifying

00:25:04.680 --> 00:25:06.359
dragon the world had ever known.

00:25:06.420 --> 00:25:10.319
This is the part where I die pointlessly

00:25:10.319 --> 00:25:13.500
the one who gets sacrificed, so the real

00:25:13.500 --> 00:25:15.299
heroes can get on with saving the day.

00:25:15.359 --> 00:25:18.960
His wings were shaking so hard, he

00:25:18.960 --> 00:25:19.799
couldn't stay in the air.

00:25:19.920 --> 00:25:23.099
He dropped down beside Moon and Kibley

00:25:23.099 --> 00:25:24.960
clutching the ground with his talons.

00:25:25.019 --> 00:25:27.599
Winter and peril were still hovering in

00:25:27.599 --> 00:25:30.660
the sky, their wings beating, silver and

00:25:30.660 --> 00:25:32.220
gold flashing in the moonlight.

00:25:32.279 --> 00:25:35.460
I need to hide, turtle thought.

00:25:35.519 --> 00:25:38.339
But how could anyone hide from the most

00:25:38.339 --> 00:25:41.160
dangerous dragon in the world, a mind

00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:44.700
reader, an animus, and a seer who knew

00:25:44.700 --> 00:25:45.059
the future?

00:25:45.119 --> 00:25:48.059
He can't read my mind, though.

00:25:48.180 --> 00:25:51.720
Turtle's gaze dropped to the 3 remaining

00:25:51.720 --> 00:25:54.420
Skyfire stones in his armband, which

00:25:54.420 --> 00:25:55.980
shielded him from mind readers.

00:25:56.039 --> 00:25:59.160
Maybe he had a millisecond to do

00:25:59.160 --> 00:26:01.920
something, anything, before dark stalker

00:26:01.920 --> 00:26:03.180
foresaw it and stopped him.

00:26:03.240 --> 00:26:05.940
He scrabbled his talons along the

00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:06.240
ground.

00:26:06.299 --> 00:26:08.700
Keeping his eyes on the towering night

00:26:08.700 --> 00:26:09.119
wing.

00:26:09.180 --> 00:26:11.819
His claws closed around something small

00:26:11.819 --> 00:26:15.059
and rough, a broken stick, from one of

00:26:15.059 --> 00:26:16.619
the trees that had fallen when the

00:26:16.619 --> 00:26:18.299
mountain cracked open.

00:26:18.359 --> 00:26:21.299
Hide me, Turtle thought at it

00:26:21.299 --> 00:26:22.079
frantically.

00:26:22.140 --> 00:26:24.059
Hide me from dark stalker.

00:26:24.119 --> 00:26:28.799
Dark Stalker stretched his vast wings and

00:26:28.799 --> 00:26:30.059
grinned at peril.

00:26:30.119 --> 00:26:31.500
Oh.

00:26:31.559 --> 00:26:34.619
That's infinitely better, he said.

00:26:34.680 --> 00:26:36.720
Nice to finally meet you, Parel.

00:26:36.779 --> 00:26:39.119
Thank you so much for your help.

00:26:39.180 --> 00:26:43.740
Peril roared furiously, and threw herself

00:26:43.740 --> 00:26:46.799
at him, claws outstretched, and flames

00:26:46.799 --> 00:26:48.059
blazing from her mouth.

00:26:48.119 --> 00:26:52.500
Carol, moon shrieked, as fire engulfed

00:26:52.500 --> 00:26:53.640
dark stalker's face.

00:26:53.700 --> 00:26:56.099
Oh, no, no, no.

00:26:56.160 --> 00:26:58.920
Dark Stalker said, waving away the

00:26:58.920 --> 00:26:59.160
smoke.

00:26:59.220 --> 00:27:01.799
He pressed one of his front talons into

00:27:01.799 --> 00:27:04.259
Parel's chest, and held her at arms

00:27:04.259 --> 00:27:06.180
length, while she struggled and tried to

00:27:06.180 --> 00:27:06.539
bite him.

00:27:06.599 --> 00:27:08.160
Peril.

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:10.559
Very brave, but tisk, tisk.

00:27:10.619 --> 00:27:12.359
First of all, I'm your friend.

00:27:12.420 --> 00:27:15.000
Although I realize you're new to that

00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:15.900
whole concept.

00:27:15.960 --> 00:27:18.720
Second of all, invulnerable scales over

00:27:18.720 --> 00:27:20.279
here. didn't you know that?

00:27:20.339 --> 00:27:23.279
Surely that detail came up at some point

00:27:23.279 --> 00:27:25.799
in the great scary legend of Dark

00:27:25.799 --> 00:27:26.279
Stalker.

00:27:26.339 --> 00:27:28.380
There's nothing you can do to me, little

00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:31.380
fire scales, so settle down, and let's

00:27:31.380 --> 00:27:31.619
start over.

00:27:31.680 --> 00:27:35.339
Peril fell back, breathing heavily and

00:27:35.339 --> 00:27:37.200
brushing at her scales, where Dark

00:27:37.200 --> 00:27:38.160
Stalker had touched her.

00:27:38.220 --> 00:27:41.700
The smoke rising from her wings, twisted

00:27:41.700 --> 00:27:43.259
into the thin clouds in the sky

00:27:43.259 --> 00:27:43.740
overhead.

00:27:43.799 --> 00:27:46.619
Turtle's heart was still pounding.

00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:50.220
Dark Stalker turned toward Moon, and his

00:27:50.220 --> 00:27:52.500
eyes went right past Turtle, as though

00:27:52.500 --> 00:27:53.880
the sea wing prince was not there.

00:27:53.940 --> 00:27:57.599
But turtle still didn't feel safe, not

00:27:57.599 --> 00:27:59.279
completely hidden, not yet.

00:27:59.339 --> 00:28:02.759
Dark stalker paused with a slight frown.

00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:04.680
Weren't there?

00:28:04.740 --> 00:28:09.059
More of you, he asked, touching his

00:28:09.059 --> 00:28:09.420
temple.

00:28:09.480 --> 00:28:13.079
Wasn't there someone I particularly

00:28:13.079 --> 00:28:13.799
wanted to see?

00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:17.339
Moon glanced around, confused.

00:28:17.400 --> 00:28:19.920
Particularly wanted to see.

00:28:19.980 --> 00:28:21.839
Does he mean me?

00:28:21.900 --> 00:28:23.700
I need a better spell.

00:28:23.759 --> 00:28:25.740
Turtle thought in a panic.

00:28:25.799 --> 00:28:27.480
He gripped the stick harder.

00:28:27.599 --> 00:28:30.420
As long as this dick is near me or

00:28:30.420 --> 00:28:30.900
touching me.

00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:34.019
I enchant it to hide my entire existence

00:28:34.019 --> 00:28:35.460
from Dark Stalker.

00:28:35.519 --> 00:28:38.400
That means he cannot see me or hear me.

00:28:38.460 --> 00:28:40.740
He cannot remember that he's ever heard

00:28:40.740 --> 00:28:41.160
of me.

00:28:41.220 --> 00:28:44.039
He cannot hear about me in other people's

00:28:44.039 --> 00:28:47.099
minds or conversations, and he cannot see

00:28:47.099 --> 00:28:48.599
me anywhere in his futures.

00:28:48.660 --> 00:28:52.619
I enchant this stick, to completely erase

00:28:52.619 --> 00:28:55.200
the dragon holding it from dark stalker's

00:28:55.200 --> 00:28:55.799
awareness.

00:28:55.859 --> 00:28:58.680
The furrow disappeared from dark

00:28:58.680 --> 00:28:59.759
stalker's forehead.

00:28:59.819 --> 00:29:03.660
Moon, he cried, beaming at her.

00:29:03.720 --> 00:29:05.460
We're finally meeting.

00:29:05.579 --> 00:29:07.259
Isn't this amazing?

00:29:07.319 --> 00:29:08.400
Wow.

00:29:08.460 --> 00:29:10.440
You were a lot smaller than I thought

00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:10.859
you'd be.

00:29:10.980 --> 00:29:13.140
That's you, actually.

00:29:13.200 --> 00:29:16.440
Kibley said, finally finding his voice.

00:29:16.500 --> 00:29:19.559
You're a lot bigger than you probably

00:29:19.559 --> 00:29:20.039
remember.

00:29:20.099 --> 00:29:23.279
Dark stalker looked down at the ground

00:29:23.279 --> 00:29:26.220
held out his talons, and flicked his

00:29:26.220 --> 00:29:28.740
massive tail, knocking a shower of

00:29:28.740 --> 00:29:30.299
boulders down the slope.

00:29:30.359 --> 00:29:32.759
He wasn't really as big as the entire

00:29:32.759 --> 00:29:35.339
mountain, although it had seemed that way

00:29:35.339 --> 00:29:38.160
to turtle at first, but he was at least 3

00:29:38.160 --> 00:29:40.799
times as big as the biggest full grown

00:29:40.799 --> 00:29:42.420
dragons turtle had ever seen.

00:29:42.480 --> 00:29:44.460
I really am.

00:29:44.519 --> 00:29:49.140
Dark Stalker said, delighted. 2000 years

00:29:49.140 --> 00:29:50.819
of slowly growing.

00:29:50.940 --> 00:29:53.700
I must be the hugest dragon that ever

00:29:53.700 --> 00:29:54.000
lived.

00:29:54.059 --> 00:29:56.160
Also, the oldest.

00:29:56.279 --> 00:29:58.619
By all the shining moons.

00:29:58.680 --> 00:30:01.740
I'm ancient, aren't I?

00:30:01.799 --> 00:30:06.480
Beware the darkness of dragons, Moon said

00:30:06.480 --> 00:30:07.799
taking a step back.

00:30:07.859 --> 00:30:10.500
Beware the stalker of dreams.

00:30:10.559 --> 00:30:14.519
Oh, that's not me, Dark Stalker said.

00:30:14.579 --> 00:30:15.839
Moon, come on.

00:30:15.900 --> 00:30:16.980
You know that.

00:30:17.039 --> 00:30:19.619
I don't slither about in the dreams of

00:30:19.619 --> 00:30:20.460
other dragons.

00:30:20.579 --> 00:30:22.740
Apart from fixing your nightmares.

00:30:22.799 --> 00:30:25.500
I'm guessing that part of the prophecy

00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:29.160
was about Queen Scarlet, who, you might

00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:32.039
remember, was chalk full of darkness.

00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:33.660
On the other talent.

00:30:33.779 --> 00:30:36.480
Something is coming to shake the earth.

00:30:36.539 --> 00:30:38.220
That's totally me.

00:30:38.279 --> 00:30:39.420
Watch this.

00:30:39.480 --> 00:30:42.119
He stomped one foot on the ground so hard

00:30:42.119 --> 00:30:44.279
that tremors shuddered out in all

00:30:44.279 --> 00:30:44.759
directions.

00:30:44.819 --> 00:30:47.640
Turtles stumbled and the closest small

00:30:47.640 --> 00:30:48.480
tree fell over.

00:30:48.539 --> 00:30:51.480
Dark Stalker grinned at Moon.

00:30:51.539 --> 00:30:53.220
Pretty impressive.

00:30:53.279 --> 00:30:53.700
Right?

00:30:53.819 --> 00:30:58.140
He paused, thinking, I guess being this

00:30:58.140 --> 00:31:00.900
big is the upside of being alive for 2000

00:31:00.900 --> 00:31:01.200
years.

00:31:01.259 --> 00:31:03.539
Even if I slept through it all.

00:31:03.599 --> 00:31:07.440
By the claw shaped moons, I am so

00:31:07.440 --> 00:31:08.099
hungry.

00:31:08.220 --> 00:31:10.619
Does anyone have any food?

00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:12.539
How did you get out?

00:31:12.599 --> 00:31:14.039
Winter demanded.

00:31:14.099 --> 00:31:17.220
The look Dark Stalker shot at Winter was

00:31:17.220 --> 00:31:18.960
as unfriendly as the one he'd given

00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:19.380
Turtle.

00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:22.319
He doesn't like ice wings either.

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:24.000
Turtle realized.

00:31:24.059 --> 00:31:26.880
But Dark Stalker's answer was cordial.

00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:31.859
Oh, that was all peril here, he said.

00:31:31.920 --> 00:31:33.839
Tapping the sky wing on the head.

00:31:33.900 --> 00:31:37.380
Harold blue eyes were blinking fast, and

00:31:37.380 --> 00:31:38.819
her claws kept clenching and

00:31:38.819 --> 00:31:39.539
unclenching.

00:31:39.599 --> 00:31:43.680
When she set my scroll on fire.

00:31:43.799 --> 00:31:45.720
Dark Stalker explained.

00:31:45.839 --> 00:31:47.759
All my magic returned to me.

00:31:47.819 --> 00:31:49.680
So I could use it to free myself.

00:31:49.740 --> 00:31:51.900
Wasn't that kind of her?

00:31:51.960 --> 00:31:54.539
Pearl's wings slumped.

00:31:54.599 --> 00:31:57.180
She looked as though she'd just rescued a

00:31:57.180 --> 00:31:59.640
baby dragonette from a trap, only to

00:31:59.640 --> 00:32:01.559
watch it immediately get eaten by a great

00:32:01.559 --> 00:32:02.339
white shark.

00:32:02.460 --> 00:32:04.980
Turtle wished he could make her feel

00:32:04.980 --> 00:32:05.220
better.

00:32:05.279 --> 00:32:07.859
He wanted to fly up and tell her this

00:32:07.859 --> 00:32:10.200
wasn't her fault, but his wings were

00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:11.700
still shaking too hard for him to take

00:32:11.700 --> 00:32:12.000
off.

00:32:12.059 --> 00:32:15.180
Also, he hadn't completely convinced

00:32:15.180 --> 00:32:16.980
himself that the magic was working.

00:32:17.039 --> 00:32:19.680
What if Dark Stalker could see him after

00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:19.859
all?

00:32:19.920 --> 00:32:22.619
He didn't want to draw the night wing's

00:32:22.619 --> 00:32:24.059
attention, just in case.

00:32:24.119 --> 00:32:27.119
Wait, Moon said.

00:32:27.180 --> 00:32:30.539
That means, You lied to me.

00:32:30.599 --> 00:32:33.420
She unfurled her wings and pointed at

00:32:33.420 --> 00:32:34.200
Dark Stalker.

00:32:34.259 --> 00:32:37.079
You told me to destroy the scroll.

00:32:37.140 --> 00:32:39.359
If it looked like it would fall into evil

00:32:39.359 --> 00:32:41.819
talents, you made it sound like then

00:32:41.819 --> 00:32:42.960
you'd be trapped forever.

00:32:43.019 --> 00:32:45.000
But it would be worth it to protect

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:47.819
everyone else, but you wanted me to

00:32:47.819 --> 00:32:49.380
destroy the scroll all along.

00:32:49.440 --> 00:32:52.200
You knew that would send your power back

00:32:52.200 --> 00:32:52.500
to you.

00:32:52.559 --> 00:32:54.299
You were tricking me.

00:32:54.359 --> 00:32:56.700
Yes.

00:32:56.759 --> 00:32:59.819
That's true, said Dark Stalker.

00:32:59.880 --> 00:33:01.920
But lucky for me that I did, right?

00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:04.259
Otherwise, you might never freed me.

00:33:04.319 --> 00:33:06.299
Not very kind, Moon.

00:33:06.359 --> 00:33:08.519
I'd say, I did the right thing.

00:33:08.579 --> 00:33:11.339
He looked at her without a smile for the

00:33:11.339 --> 00:33:11.819
1st time.

00:33:11.940 --> 00:33:14.160
His eyes odd and glittering.

00:33:14.220 --> 00:33:18.720
You called us friends, men said, in a low

00:33:18.720 --> 00:33:18.960
voice.

00:33:19.079 --> 00:33:21.779
You shouldn't trick your friends.

00:33:21.839 --> 00:33:23.460
Yes.

00:33:23.519 --> 00:33:26.460
Well, you also should leave your friends

00:33:26.460 --> 00:33:28.440
trapped under a mountain for the rest of

00:33:28.440 --> 00:33:29.099
their immortal lives.

00:33:29.160 --> 00:33:31.619
Dark soccer said briskly.

00:33:31.680 --> 00:33:33.359
Good point.

00:33:33.480 --> 00:33:35.039
Dog stalker.

00:33:35.099 --> 00:33:37.319
Listen, I can't even talk anymore.

00:33:37.380 --> 00:33:38.039
I'm so hungry.

00:33:38.099 --> 00:33:40.859
Let's all catch something to eat, and

00:33:40.859 --> 00:33:42.299
then you can show me around Jade

00:33:42.299 --> 00:33:42.720
Mountain.

00:33:42.779 --> 00:33:45.480
There are some dragons there.

00:33:45.539 --> 00:33:46.440
I can't wait.

00:33:46.440 --> 00:33:47.640
To me.

00:33:47.700 --> 00:33:51.420
He lifted off into the air, then turned

00:33:51.420 --> 00:33:52.380
to beckon at moon.

00:33:52.440 --> 00:33:53.940
Come on, Moon.

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:56.819
I just want to have friends again, to use

00:33:56.819 --> 00:33:59.400
my voice, to hunt and fly.

00:33:59.460 --> 00:34:01.500
Can't we save thee?

00:34:01.559 --> 00:34:04.559
Oh no, but you're so sinister and evil.

00:34:04.619 --> 00:34:06.539
Talon ringing for later.

00:34:06.599 --> 00:34:07.799
What do you say?

00:34:07.859 --> 00:34:09.480
Give me a chance.

00:34:09.539 --> 00:34:13.139
Moon glanced at Kibley, looking torn.

00:34:13.199 --> 00:34:16.919
I'm not going with you, Peril said.

00:34:16.980 --> 00:34:18.599
You're not the queen of me.

00:34:18.659 --> 00:34:21.539
Me neither, said Winter.

00:34:21.659 --> 00:34:23.879
The ice wings have legends about you.

00:34:23.940 --> 00:34:27.000
We know what you did to us, and I don't

00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:30.119
take orders from, I'm not ordering you to

00:34:30.119 --> 00:34:31.920
do anything, Prince Winter.

00:34:32.039 --> 00:34:34.800
Dark Stalker said, turning to look at

00:34:34.800 --> 00:34:35.099
Winter.

00:34:35.159 --> 00:34:36.839
The ice wing fell silent.

00:34:36.900 --> 00:34:40.260
But I think you know that those old

00:34:40.260 --> 00:34:42.179
legends don't tell the whole truth.

00:34:42.239 --> 00:34:45.419
You know that a dragon should not be

00:34:45.419 --> 00:34:47.879
judged by what other dragons say about

00:34:47.879 --> 00:34:48.119
him.

00:34:48.179 --> 00:34:51.359
And the more time you spend with me, the

00:34:51.359 --> 00:34:52.919
more I think you'll find that I'm really

00:34:52.919 --> 00:34:55.139
an absolutely wonderful dragon.

00:34:55.199 --> 00:34:58.739
He smiled, with all his teeth.

00:34:58.860 --> 00:35:02.099
Winter touched his temples for a moment

00:35:02.099 --> 00:35:04.739
then stared at Dark Stalker with

00:35:04.739 --> 00:35:05.880
something new in his blue eyes.

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:09.239
You're right, he said.

00:35:09.300 --> 00:35:10.920
Let's start over.

00:35:10.980 --> 00:35:13.079
Winter?

00:35:13.139 --> 00:35:14.699
Kibley said sharply.

00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:17.280
He darted into the sky and up beside

00:35:17.280 --> 00:35:19.800
winter, brushing the silver dragon's

00:35:19.800 --> 00:35:20.340
wings with his own.

00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:21.840
Are you all right?

00:35:21.900 --> 00:35:24.960
Of course, said Winter.

00:35:25.019 --> 00:35:27.420
He tipped his head toward Dark Stalker.

00:35:27.480 --> 00:35:30.539
I am trying not to judge dragons too

00:35:30.539 --> 00:35:31.260
quickly anymore.

00:35:31.320 --> 00:35:32.639
Let's hear him out.

00:35:32.699 --> 00:35:36.059
That doesn't sound like the winter I know

00:35:36.059 --> 00:35:37.800
Kibley said to Moon.

00:35:37.860 --> 00:35:39.539
Does this seem weird to you?

00:35:39.599 --> 00:35:42.480
You don't know me that.

00:35:42.539 --> 00:35:44.639
Well, Winter objected.

00:35:44.699 --> 00:35:47.280
Snorting a tiny cloud of ice crystals.

00:35:47.340 --> 00:35:49.019
Dragons can change.

00:35:49.079 --> 00:35:50.460
I've changed.

00:35:50.519 --> 00:35:51.599
Maybe he has too.

00:35:51.659 --> 00:35:56.159
Without question, Dark Stalker said

00:35:56.159 --> 00:35:56.579
nodding.

00:35:56.699 --> 00:35:59.280
I've had a lot of time to think about my

00:35:59.280 --> 00:35:59.760
mistakes.

00:35:59.820 --> 00:36:03.420
Kibli backed away from them, worry

00:36:03.420 --> 00:36:04.739
spilling across his face.

00:36:04.800 --> 00:36:09.539
Moon, he said carefully, as though he

00:36:09.539 --> 00:36:11.699
were reaching for the only island in a

00:36:11.699 --> 00:36:14.880
vast empty sea, she flew up beside him

00:36:14.880 --> 00:36:17.099
ducking her head to look into Winter's

00:36:17.099 --> 00:36:17.460
eyes.

00:36:17.519 --> 00:36:19.739
Did you do something to him?

00:36:19.800 --> 00:36:22.139
Moon asked Dark Stalker.

00:36:22.199 --> 00:36:24.119
Of course I didn't.

00:36:24.179 --> 00:36:28.800
Dark Stalker protested, and no, he didn't

00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:30.599
cried Winter at the same time.

00:36:30.659 --> 00:36:34.019
Dark Stalker, Moon said.

00:36:34.079 --> 00:36:35.820
You have to promise me.

00:36:35.880 --> 00:36:38.280
You cannot put spells on my friends.

00:36:38.340 --> 00:36:43.800
I'm really offended by this, Winter said

00:36:43.800 --> 00:36:44.400
haughtily.

00:36:44.460 --> 00:36:47.159
I'm such an open minded dragon.

00:36:47.219 --> 00:36:50.460
Peril and Kibley snorted in unison.

00:36:50.519 --> 00:36:52.440
Moon.

00:36:52.500 --> 00:36:54.659
Dark Stalker said reasonably.

00:36:54.719 --> 00:36:58.619
I wouldn't waste my animus magic, and my

00:36:58.619 --> 00:36:59.340
soul.

00:36:59.400 --> 00:37:02.699
On some tiny hush up and ice wing spell.

00:37:02.760 --> 00:37:04.139
I mean, seriously.

00:37:04.260 --> 00:37:06.719
Don't you remember the whole point of my

00:37:06.719 --> 00:37:08.880
scroll, that I made?

00:37:08.940 --> 00:37:12.300
To keep your soul safe.

00:37:12.420 --> 00:37:14.820
Moon said hesitantly.

00:37:14.880 --> 00:37:17.579
She swooped around winter, studying him.

00:37:17.639 --> 00:37:21.119
But stop worrying so much.

00:37:21.179 --> 00:37:24.059
Dark Stalker nudged her with one of his

00:37:24.059 --> 00:37:24.900
giant wings.

00:37:24.960 --> 00:37:28.440
Boy, you remind me of someone I used to

00:37:28.440 --> 00:37:28.619
know.

00:37:28.679 --> 00:37:30.659
Can't you be excited for me?

00:37:30.719 --> 00:37:32.519
This is a great day.

00:37:32.579 --> 00:37:34.320
Let's go celebrate.

00:37:34.380 --> 00:37:37.739
Tell you what, I promise, if I feel the

00:37:37.739 --> 00:37:40.800
need to use animus magic, I'll let you

00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:40.980
know.

00:37:41.039 --> 00:37:44.880
And you promise not to hurt my friends.

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:46.320
Moon asked.

00:37:46.380 --> 00:37:50.039
Dark Stalker sighed gustily, sending a

00:37:50.039 --> 00:37:51.960
hurricane of leaves swirling around

00:37:51.960 --> 00:37:55.679
turtle's feet, I'm hurt, that you even

00:37:55.679 --> 00:37:56.400
need to ask me that.

00:37:56.519 --> 00:37:57.659
He said.

00:37:57.719 --> 00:38:01.019
But of course, if it makes you feel

00:38:01.019 --> 00:38:04.980
better, I promise that these 3 are

00:38:04.980 --> 00:38:08.340
officially the safest dragons in Pyria.

00:38:08.340 --> 00:38:12.059
He waved his talons at Kibli, winter, and

00:38:12.059 --> 00:38:12.659
peril.

00:38:12.719 --> 00:38:15.539
Moon opened her mouth, then closed it.

00:38:15.659 --> 00:38:18.659
She and Kibley simultaneously looked down

00:38:18.659 --> 00:38:19.320
at Turtle.

00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:22.380
Turtle crouched lower, pressing his

00:38:22.380 --> 00:38:24.360
underbelly into the ground, and shook his

00:38:24.360 --> 00:38:24.719
head at them.

00:38:24.780 --> 00:38:29.340
Let's hunt now, as Dark Stalker suggests

00:38:29.340 --> 00:38:32.820
Kibley said, nudging Moon, and figure out

00:38:32.820 --> 00:38:33.780
what to do next after that.

00:38:33.900 --> 00:38:37.019
He shot a significant glance at Turtle.

00:38:37.079 --> 00:38:38.579
Oh no.

00:38:38.639 --> 00:38:41.820
That glance had a meaning, a message.

00:38:41.880 --> 00:38:44.219
Kibley was expecting Turtle to do

00:38:44.219 --> 00:38:46.500
something, and Turtle had a bad feeling

00:38:46.500 --> 00:38:49.619
that something wasn't turtle flying all

00:38:49.619 --> 00:38:51.420
the way back to the kingdom of the sea

00:38:51.420 --> 00:38:53.699
finding a deep trench and staying there

00:38:53.699 --> 00:38:54.000
forever.

00:38:54.059 --> 00:38:58.019
A queasy, tense feeling started bubbling

00:38:58.019 --> 00:38:59.099
through turtle's stomach.

00:38:59.159 --> 00:39:02.219
Good idea, said winter.

00:39:02.280 --> 00:39:06.059
Moon nodded, and then she gave Turtle a

00:39:06.059 --> 00:39:06.900
meaningful look too.

00:39:07.019 --> 00:39:08.880
By all the moons.

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:10.800
What did they think he was going to do?

00:39:10.860 --> 00:39:14.039
Attack a dark stalker, like peril had?

00:39:14.099 --> 00:39:15.539
Obviously that wouldn't work.

00:39:15.659 --> 00:39:17.460
If peril couldn't hurt him?

00:39:17.519 --> 00:39:19.199
Turtles certainly wouldn't be able to.

00:39:19.260 --> 00:39:21.900
Did they want him to hide them as well?

00:39:22.019 --> 00:39:23.639
He winced.

00:39:23.699 --> 00:39:25.500
He should have thought of that sooner.

00:39:25.559 --> 00:39:27.960
A good friend, a better dragon.

00:39:28.019 --> 00:39:31.019
A hero would have thought to protect

00:39:31.019 --> 00:39:33.420
everyone instead of just hiding himself.

00:39:33.480 --> 00:39:36.659
But they all wanted to talk to Dark

00:39:36.659 --> 00:39:37.619
Stalker, didn't they?

00:39:37.679 --> 00:39:39.300
I just wanted to hide.

00:39:39.360 --> 00:39:41.219
That's what I always do.

00:39:41.340 --> 00:39:44.940
As the dragons flew away, veering

00:39:44.940 --> 00:39:47.820
southwest, Kibli twisted in a spiral

00:39:47.820 --> 00:39:50.340
looked at Turtle again, and flicked his

00:39:50.340 --> 00:39:52.380
tail in the direction of Jade Mountain.

00:39:52.440 --> 00:39:53.579
Oh.

00:39:53.639 --> 00:39:55.260
Turtle realized.

00:39:55.320 --> 00:39:57.539
They want me to go warn the school.

00:39:57.599 --> 00:40:00.420
I can probably do that without messing it

00:40:00.420 --> 00:40:00.599
up.

00:40:00.659 --> 00:40:01.920
I think.

00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:05.579
For a moment, Peril hovered mutinously in

00:40:05.579 --> 00:40:07.860
the sky behind them, and then she swooped

00:40:07.860 --> 00:40:08.460
down to Turtle.

00:40:08.519 --> 00:40:10.199
Aren't you coming too?

00:40:10.320 --> 00:40:11.579
She asked.

00:40:11.639 --> 00:40:13.619
Don't we all have to follow his grand

00:40:13.619 --> 00:40:15.480
mighty lordship's sinister face?

00:40:15.539 --> 00:40:18.000
Turtle shook his head and held out the

00:40:18.000 --> 00:40:18.179
stick.

00:40:18.300 --> 00:40:21.420
He can't see me, he whispered.

00:40:21.480 --> 00:40:23.340
I hid myself from him.

00:40:23.400 --> 00:40:25.619
Pearl's face lit up.

00:40:25.679 --> 00:40:27.840
Of course, she said.

00:40:27.900 --> 00:40:29.039
That's awesome.

00:40:29.099 --> 00:40:30.960
You have animus magic.

00:40:31.019 --> 00:40:31.980
You can kill him.

00:40:32.099 --> 00:40:35.519
Oh, said Turtle, flustered.

00:40:35.579 --> 00:40:39.900
No, I, I don't really kill anyone.

00:40:39.960 --> 00:40:43.739
A brief flash of scales and blood darted

00:40:43.739 --> 00:40:46.139
through his mind, and when he looked down

00:40:46.139 --> 00:40:48.420
he saw his claws curling dangerously.

00:40:48.480 --> 00:40:51.719
He jumped and shook them out until they

00:40:51.719 --> 00:40:53.159
looked like his own talons again.

00:40:53.219 --> 00:40:58.079
That's not my thing, he said. tamping

00:40:58.079 --> 00:40:59.280
down a wave of panic.

00:40:59.340 --> 00:41:01.800
I know, I know.

00:41:01.860 --> 00:41:04.079
It's my thing, Pearl said.

00:41:04.139 --> 00:41:06.780
But I can't kill him because of his

00:41:06.780 --> 00:41:09.420
stupid magic growl.

00:41:09.480 --> 00:41:10.260
So you have to.

00:41:10.380 --> 00:41:12.900
Don't worry, it's not that hard, and it

00:41:12.900 --> 00:41:14.219
would be such a relief.

00:41:14.219 --> 00:41:17.340
For me, I mean, because I'm having this

00:41:17.340 --> 00:41:19.739
feeling, I don't know what to call it, but

00:41:19.739 --> 00:41:22.559
it's kind of big and heavy and annoying.

00:41:22.619 --> 00:41:25.380
And it's filling me all up inside, like

00:41:25.380 --> 00:41:27.420
everything is awful and it's all my

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:28.380
fault.

00:41:28.440 --> 00:41:30.119
Like maybe all the bad things in the

00:41:30.119 --> 00:41:31.440
world are my fault.

00:41:31.500 --> 00:41:33.059
I really don't like it.

00:41:33.119 --> 00:41:35.219
So if you can make it stop, that would be

00:41:35.219 --> 00:41:36.059
the greatest.

00:41:36.119 --> 00:41:39.960
I think what you're describing is what we

00:41:39.960 --> 00:41:42.239
call guilt, said Turtle.

00:41:42.300 --> 00:41:44.820
But it's not your fault he tricked us.

00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:46.920
I still think you did the right thing.

00:41:47.039 --> 00:41:48.360
Burning the scroll.

00:41:48.420 --> 00:41:52.559
Well, thanks, but the universe disagrees

00:41:52.559 --> 00:41:54.300
with you, Peril said.

00:41:54.360 --> 00:41:56.880
Jerking her head at the enormous crack in

00:41:56.880 --> 00:41:57.599
the side of the mountain.

00:41:57.719 --> 00:42:01.619
Peril, called one of the dragons in the

00:42:01.619 --> 00:42:02.039
distance.

00:42:02.099 --> 00:42:05.039
Good luck, peril whispered.

00:42:05.099 --> 00:42:07.860
Make it something really cool, like his

00:42:07.860 --> 00:42:09.059
insides exploding.

00:42:09.119 --> 00:42:11.159
Or his face falling off.

00:42:11.280 --> 00:42:12.480
I'm kidding.

00:42:12.599 --> 00:42:14.400
I'm a little bit kidding.

00:42:14.460 --> 00:42:17.039
I mean, insides exploding would be pretty

00:42:17.039 --> 00:42:17.460
cool, right?

00:42:17.579 --> 00:42:19.500
Never mind, it's up to you.

00:42:19.559 --> 00:42:21.659
Destroy him and save the world.

00:42:21.719 --> 00:42:23.039
Three moons.

00:42:23.099 --> 00:42:24.300
I wish I could do it.

00:42:24.360 --> 00:42:27.840
She took off and flashed away, fast as a

00:42:27.840 --> 00:42:28.260
firework.

00:42:28.320 --> 00:42:30.420
Turtles shivered.

00:42:30.480 --> 00:42:32.340
Save the world?

00:42:32.400 --> 00:42:34.440
That's not my thing either.

00:42:34.500 --> 00:42:36.960
I would definitely mess it up.

00:42:37.019 --> 00:42:39.840
That's way, way too much pressure.

00:42:39.900 --> 00:42:42.480
I'm clearly not a hero.

00:42:42.599 --> 00:42:46.079
He raised his eyes to the shadowy peaks

00:42:46.079 --> 00:42:46.860
of Jade Mountain.

00:42:46.920 --> 00:42:49.380
But I know where I can find some.

00:42:49.500 --> 00:42:53.760
Chapter 2.

00:42:54.000 --> 00:42:57.780
The sun was starting to sneak over the

00:42:57.780 --> 00:42:59.820
mountains, nervously spilling little

00:42:59.820 --> 00:43:02.099
beams around the peaks, as if it were

00:43:02.099 --> 00:43:04.079
making sure Dark Stalker was gone.

00:43:04.079 --> 00:43:07.320
Clouds were visible in the north, with a

00:43:07.320 --> 00:43:10.019
gray haze of distant rain below them, but

00:43:10.019 --> 00:43:12.719
Jade Mountain was still dry and clear and

00:43:12.719 --> 00:43:13.320
sunlit.

00:43:13.380 --> 00:43:17.280
Turtle tucked the broken stick, knobbly

00:43:17.280 --> 00:43:19.500
and half stripped of its bark, the most

00:43:19.500 --> 00:43:21.659
ordinary, insignificant looking thing in

00:43:21.659 --> 00:43:23.940
the world, carefully into the pouch

00:43:23.940 --> 00:43:24.539
around his neck.

00:43:24.599 --> 00:43:27.659
He tied the pouch shut twice as tightly

00:43:27.659 --> 00:43:30.000
as usual, and put his front claws over it

00:43:30.000 --> 00:43:31.380
as it rested on his chest.

00:43:31.440 --> 00:43:33.539
Anxiety twisted inside him.

00:43:33.599 --> 00:43:36.059
I'd better not lose this.

00:43:36.179 --> 00:43:39.599
He'd lost other animus touched objects

00:43:39.599 --> 00:43:39.900
before.

00:43:39.960 --> 00:43:42.360
It was a little embarrassing, actually.

00:43:42.420 --> 00:43:46.260
When he was three, his many, many older

00:43:46.260 --> 00:43:48.300
brothers used to make fun of him for

00:43:48.300 --> 00:43:50.340
being the slowest sea wing prints in the

00:43:50.340 --> 00:43:50.639
ocean.

00:43:50.699 --> 00:43:53.159
Guess somebody gave you the right name.

00:43:53.219 --> 00:43:54.000
Ha ha.

00:43:54.059 --> 00:43:56.400
Careful or clownfish will catch you.

00:43:56.460 --> 00:43:58.860
You swim like a sea cucumber.

00:43:58.920 --> 00:44:02.159
So Turtlehead enchanted a strand of

00:44:02.159 --> 00:44:04.619
purple kelp, wound 3 times around his

00:44:04.619 --> 00:44:06.960
upper arm to make him just a bit faster

00:44:06.960 --> 00:44:07.920
than some of his brothers.

00:44:08.039 --> 00:44:11.400
He couldn't make himself the fastest, that

00:44:11.400 --> 00:44:12.300
would attract attention.

00:44:12.420 --> 00:44:15.420
Attention was the last thing he wanted.

00:44:15.480 --> 00:44:18.119
But he could be faster than the other 2

00:44:18.119 --> 00:44:21.000
from his hatching, octopus and cerulean.

00:44:21.000 --> 00:44:23.639
He could be a tiny bit faster than a

00:44:23.639 --> 00:44:25.860
couple of the 4 year olds, and that's

00:44:25.860 --> 00:44:26.460
where he'd stop.

00:44:26.519 --> 00:44:29.639
Then he'd be nothing remarkable, and his

00:44:29.639 --> 00:44:31.139
brothers would move on to teasing someone

00:44:31.139 --> 00:44:31.440
else.

00:44:31.500 --> 00:44:33.300
It worked.

00:44:33.360 --> 00:44:35.940
They got bored and left him alone after a

00:44:35.940 --> 00:44:36.780
couple more races.

00:44:36.840 --> 00:44:39.000
But he still wished he hadn't lost the

00:44:39.000 --> 00:44:40.380
kelp a few weeks later.

00:44:40.440 --> 00:44:43.019
It drifted off in his sleep one night, and

00:44:43.019 --> 00:44:44.820
he often wondered if there was a startled

00:44:44.820 --> 00:44:46.800
seahorse tangled up in it somewhere out

00:44:46.800 --> 00:44:49.079
there, speeding along the ocean floor.

00:44:49.139 --> 00:44:51.659
He knew he should be smarter about what

00:44:51.659 --> 00:44:52.380
he enchanted.

00:44:52.440 --> 00:44:54.360
He should pick things he couldn't lose

00:44:54.360 --> 00:44:56.340
things that would last a while.

00:44:56.400 --> 00:44:58.980
But usually he didn't spend enough time

00:44:58.980 --> 00:45:01.380
thinking about his spells beforehand to

00:45:01.380 --> 00:45:02.400
plan them that carefully.

00:45:02.460 --> 00:45:06.239
His spells were all so little, just small

00:45:06.239 --> 00:45:08.880
magic to make his life easier, and he

00:45:08.880 --> 00:45:10.380
generally used whatever he could grab

00:45:10.380 --> 00:45:11.880
with his claws when he needed one.

00:45:11.940 --> 00:45:15.000
Like the very ordinary looking river

00:45:15.000 --> 00:45:17.639
stone in his pouch, bumping along with a

00:45:17.639 --> 00:45:17.820
stick.

00:45:17.940 --> 00:45:21.000
It could heal surface wounds and aches

00:45:21.000 --> 00:45:23.519
and pains, and he'd enchanted it to make

00:45:23.519 --> 00:45:25.440
himself feel better after a long day of

00:45:25.440 --> 00:45:25.800
lying.

00:45:25.920 --> 00:45:28.440
But it was a silly thing to enchant.

00:45:28.500 --> 00:45:30.300
Peril was right about that.

00:45:30.360 --> 00:45:33.059
If he ever lost it, he'd never find it

00:45:33.059 --> 00:45:33.300
again.

00:45:33.360 --> 00:45:36.780
Same with his stick, so he had to be

00:45:36.780 --> 00:45:37.079
careful.

00:45:37.139 --> 00:45:40.260
He flew toward the main entrance of Jade

00:45:40.260 --> 00:45:42.420
Mountain, where he had landed on his 1st

00:45:42.420 --> 00:45:43.440
day as a new student.

00:45:43.500 --> 00:45:46.980
He remembered how excited he had been, a

00:45:46.980 --> 00:45:49.260
new school, nobody knew him here.

00:45:49.500 --> 00:45:51.420
It was the perfect place to be a

00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:53.880
background character in other dragons

00:45:53.880 --> 00:45:54.420
stories.

00:45:54.539 --> 00:45:57.179
No one would expect anything of him.

00:45:57.239 --> 00:45:59.699
He'd be far away from octopus and

00:45:59.699 --> 00:46:01.860
cerulean, who knew about his biggest

00:46:01.860 --> 00:46:04.320
failure, and surely must think about it

00:46:04.320 --> 00:46:06.239
all the time, even if they never

00:46:06.239 --> 00:46:06.780
mentioned it.

00:46:06.840 --> 00:46:11.579
Here, he could blend in, be ordinary, and

00:46:11.579 --> 00:46:13.739
keep an eye on his little sister Anemone

00:46:13.739 --> 00:46:16.440
who had been acting strangely ever since

00:46:16.440 --> 00:46:17.880
the attack on the Summer Palace.

00:46:17.940 --> 00:46:20.880
None of that had quite worked out the way

00:46:20.880 --> 00:46:21.659
he'd planned.

00:46:21.719 --> 00:46:23.159
It was his own fault.

00:46:23.219 --> 00:46:25.380
If he hadn't chased after the other

00:46:25.380 --> 00:46:27.960
dragons in his winglet, he could be sound

00:46:27.960 --> 00:46:29.760
asleep with the rest of the sea wing

00:46:29.760 --> 00:46:30.480
students right now.

00:46:30.539 --> 00:46:33.840
A splash and a peal of laughter caught

00:46:33.840 --> 00:46:36.179
his attention, and he soared over Jade

00:46:36.179 --> 00:46:38.340
Mountain, following the sound to an

00:46:38.340 --> 00:46:39.659
opening in the roof of a cave.

00:46:39.719 --> 00:46:42.539
Down there was the underground lake.

00:46:42.599 --> 00:46:44.880
And there were dragons swimming in it

00:46:44.880 --> 00:46:47.099
even now, at the crack of dawn.

00:46:47.159 --> 00:46:49.079
Turtle never woke up early if he could

00:46:49.079 --> 00:46:49.380
help it.

00:46:49.440 --> 00:46:53.039
But anemone was often up at sunrise, which

00:46:53.039 --> 00:46:55.199
meant one of those swimming dragons might

00:46:55.199 --> 00:46:55.500
be her.

00:46:55.559 --> 00:46:57.599
I should warn her.

00:46:57.659 --> 00:46:59.460
Her more than anyone.

00:46:59.519 --> 00:47:02.820
He tucked his wings into a dive and

00:47:02.820 --> 00:47:05.460
arrowed through the hole, but he somewhat

00:47:05.460 --> 00:47:07.739
misjudged his speed, and ended up

00:47:07.739 --> 00:47:10.500
smacking into the cold lake, like a hippo

00:47:10.500 --> 00:47:11.639
dropped from a great height.

00:47:11.699 --> 00:47:16.320
Yow, he yelped, surfacing and rubbing his

00:47:16.320 --> 00:47:18.480
eyes, his scales stinging from the

00:47:18.480 --> 00:47:18.719
shock.

00:47:18.780 --> 00:47:20.519
Turtle?

00:47:20.519 --> 00:47:21.960
said a voice nearby.

00:47:22.019 --> 00:47:23.699
Turtle, you're back.

00:47:23.760 --> 00:47:26.519
Wet wings were flung around his shoulders

00:47:26.519 --> 00:47:29.400
dunking him underwater in a cascade of

00:47:29.400 --> 00:47:29.760
bubbles.

00:47:29.820 --> 00:47:32.639
Anemones glow in the dark scales flashed

00:47:32.639 --> 00:47:34.980
happily at him in aquatic as she dragged

00:47:34.980 --> 00:47:35.940
him up into the air again.

00:47:36.000 --> 00:47:39.239
Hi, he sputtered at his sister.

00:47:39.300 --> 00:47:42.840
Hey, you nearly landed on the princess.

00:47:42.900 --> 00:47:44.940
Pike shouted in his ear.

00:47:45.000 --> 00:47:47.639
The skinny gray blue sea wing had always

00:47:47.639 --> 00:47:49.199
been a little louder and more aggressive

00:47:49.199 --> 00:47:51.059
than turtle thought was strictly

00:47:51.059 --> 00:47:51.360
necessary.

00:47:51.480 --> 00:47:54.840
But he'd been much worse, since they'd

00:47:54.840 --> 00:47:57.059
arrived at Jade Mountain Academy, thanks

00:47:57.059 --> 00:47:59.039
to some secret instructions from Queen

00:47:59.039 --> 00:47:59.820
Coral.

00:47:59.820 --> 00:48:03.059
Turtle new from eavesdropping, that Pike

00:48:03.059 --> 00:48:04.920
was here specifically to be a covert

00:48:04.920 --> 00:48:06.719
bodyguard for Princess Anemone.

00:48:06.780 --> 00:48:08.820
Anemone, of course, had no idea.

00:48:08.880 --> 00:48:11.940
She never seemed surprised that Pike was

00:48:11.940 --> 00:48:13.019
so easy to boss around.

00:48:13.079 --> 00:48:16.139
In her mind, that was how all sea wings

00:48:16.139 --> 00:48:17.400
were supposed to behave around her.

00:48:17.460 --> 00:48:20.159
Oh, shush, I'm fine.

00:48:20.219 --> 00:48:23.460
Anemone splashed water up Pike's snout

00:48:23.460 --> 00:48:25.199
and he backed off, shaking his head

00:48:25.199 --> 00:48:25.920
irritably.

00:48:25.980 --> 00:48:27.900
Turtle, where have you been?

00:48:28.019 --> 00:48:30.239
I had the weirdest nightmare just before

00:48:30.239 --> 00:48:30.900
I woke up.

00:48:30.960 --> 00:48:33.300
I thought there was an earthquake, but

00:48:33.300 --> 00:48:34.139
nobody else felt it.

00:48:34.199 --> 00:48:36.000
Did you find your winglet?

00:48:36.059 --> 00:48:36.900
Are they here too?

00:48:36.960 --> 00:48:40.019
Turtle seized her front claws in his.

00:48:40.079 --> 00:48:41.639
Anemone.

00:48:41.699 --> 00:48:42.840
I need to talk to you.

00:48:42.900 --> 00:48:46.320
You are talking to me, fish face?

00:48:46.320 --> 00:48:46.920
she said.

00:48:46.980 --> 00:48:48.960
Did you find the rain wing you were

00:48:48.960 --> 00:48:49.980
moping about?

00:48:50.039 --> 00:48:51.659
You mean Kinkaju?

00:48:51.719 --> 00:48:54.059
A little rain wing was sitting in the

00:48:54.059 --> 00:48:56.219
shallows of the lake, tilting her ears

00:48:56.219 --> 00:48:56.699
toward them.

00:48:56.760 --> 00:49:00.179
Her scales were spiraling pale peach and

00:49:00.179 --> 00:49:02.400
citrus green, except where they were

00:49:02.400 --> 00:49:04.860
covered by swaths of bandages, and

00:49:04.860 --> 00:49:06.539
streaks of black scorch marks.

00:49:06.659 --> 00:49:09.300
A poultice of damb leaves was tied over

00:49:09.300 --> 00:49:09.659
her eyes.

00:49:09.719 --> 00:49:11.880
Is Kinkaju all right?

00:49:11.940 --> 00:49:15.360
I'm sure she's absolutely fine, Cameron.

00:49:15.420 --> 00:49:17.099
Pike said kindly.

00:49:17.159 --> 00:49:19.440
He jabbed Turtle in the shoulder with one

00:49:19.440 --> 00:49:22.320
claw, much less kindly, and jerked his

00:49:22.320 --> 00:49:24.539
head toward Tamarin, scowling.

00:49:24.599 --> 00:49:25.500
Turtle hesitated.

00:49:25.559 --> 00:49:28.019
The last time he'd seen Kinkaju.

00:49:28.079 --> 00:49:30.059
She was lying in a hospital bed in the

00:49:30.059 --> 00:49:32.280
town of possibility, unconscious.

00:49:32.340 --> 00:49:35.039
Her usually bright, shifting rainbow

00:49:35.039 --> 00:49:37.320
scales, had turned white and still.

00:49:37.380 --> 00:49:40.260
She had hardly looked like Hinkaju at

00:49:40.260 --> 00:49:40.440
all.

00:49:40.500 --> 00:49:42.599
But how could he say that to her best

00:49:42.599 --> 00:49:43.019
friend?

00:49:43.079 --> 00:49:46.079
To Tamarin, who was suffering from her

00:49:46.079 --> 00:49:48.059
own injuries after the explosion that

00:49:48.059 --> 00:49:49.619
rocked Jade Mountain Academy.

00:49:49.679 --> 00:49:52.679
She was alive when I saw her a few days

00:49:52.679 --> 00:49:54.300
ago, he hedged.

00:49:54.360 --> 00:49:56.400
I'm sure she'll come back to Jade

00:49:56.400 --> 00:49:58.380
Mountain, just as soon as she can.

00:49:58.440 --> 00:50:01.860
If it's still here when she wakes up.

00:50:01.920 --> 00:50:03.539
Oh.

00:50:03.599 --> 00:50:05.639
Tameron said softly.

00:50:05.699 --> 00:50:06.840
Good.

00:50:06.900 --> 00:50:09.900
Anemone, Turtle said.

00:50:09.960 --> 00:50:11.400
Come flying with me?

00:50:11.519 --> 00:50:14.639
You are being such a jellyfish right

00:50:14.639 --> 00:50:14.880
now.

00:50:14.940 --> 00:50:16.739
Anemone side.

00:50:16.800 --> 00:50:18.599
I don't want to fly.

00:50:18.659 --> 00:50:19.320
I want to swim.

00:50:19.380 --> 00:50:21.480
Can't you just say whatever it is right

00:50:21.480 --> 00:50:22.139
here.

00:50:22.199 --> 00:50:23.639
Pike and Tam won't care.

00:50:23.699 --> 00:50:27.659
Oh, they might, thought Turtle.

00:50:27.719 --> 00:50:30.000
But he could see that anemone wasn't

00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:30.179
moving.

00:50:30.239 --> 00:50:33.480
This was Anemone's new stubborn, petulant

00:50:33.480 --> 00:50:34.019
personality.

00:50:34.079 --> 00:50:36.539
The princess who'd risen to the surface

00:50:36.539 --> 00:50:38.579
after she was cut free from mother's

00:50:38.579 --> 00:50:39.000
harness.

00:50:39.059 --> 00:50:42.000
This anemone, made him feel nervous.

00:50:42.059 --> 00:50:45.300
This anemone made him feel guilty.

00:50:45.420 --> 00:50:48.179
All right, fine, he said.

00:50:48.300 --> 00:50:50.699
You're in danger, and you need to leave

00:50:50.699 --> 00:50:51.840
Jade Mountain right now.

00:50:51.900 --> 00:50:54.000
What danger?

00:50:54.059 --> 00:50:56.820
Pike barked, swiveling his head to glare

00:50:56.820 --> 00:50:57.659
around the dark cave.

00:50:57.719 --> 00:50:59.699
And go where?

00:50:59.760 --> 00:51:01.139
Anemone demanded.

00:51:01.199 --> 00:51:02.039
Home?

00:51:02.159 --> 00:51:04.800
Back to harnesses and boredom, and

00:51:04.800 --> 00:51:06.420
mothers staring at me all the time.

00:51:06.480 --> 00:51:08.099
No, thank you.

00:51:08.280 --> 00:51:09.059
I'm staying here.

00:51:09.119 --> 00:51:11.760
She scrambled up on one of the boulders

00:51:11.760 --> 00:51:14.159
that jutted out of the water and coiled

00:51:14.159 --> 00:51:15.900
her tail around her talons.

00:51:15.960 --> 00:51:19.860
But there's a big, scary dragon coming.

00:51:19.920 --> 00:51:21.119
Turtle protested.

00:51:21.179 --> 00:51:24.539
Anemone looked archly down her snout at

00:51:24.539 --> 00:51:24.960
Turtle.

00:51:25.019 --> 00:51:27.420
Who are you talking about?

00:51:27.480 --> 00:51:28.199
she asked.

00:51:28.260 --> 00:51:30.420
I thought our illustrious teachers

00:51:30.420 --> 00:51:32.039
defeated all the bad dragons.

00:51:32.099 --> 00:51:34.199
This is a new one.

00:51:34.260 --> 00:51:37.139
Turtle glanced anxiously up at the sky

00:51:37.139 --> 00:51:39.539
above them, which was shifting closer and

00:51:39.539 --> 00:51:40.679
closer to full daylight.

00:51:40.800 --> 00:51:44.099
His name is Dark Stalker, and he's been

00:51:44.099 --> 00:51:46.980
trapped underground for 2000 years and he

00:51:46.980 --> 00:51:47.579
just escaped.

00:51:47.639 --> 00:51:50.579
I don't really understand the whole story

00:51:50.579 --> 00:51:52.860
but I know he's a mind reader and an

00:51:52.860 --> 00:51:55.860
animus, and he seems nice on the surface

00:51:55.860 --> 00:51:56.460
but...

00:51:56.460 --> 00:51:58.320
An animus?

00:51:58.380 --> 00:52:00.599
Anemone cried, interrupting him.

00:52:00.659 --> 00:52:03.239
She stood up. flaring her wings.

00:52:03.300 --> 00:52:04.260
Really?

00:52:04.320 --> 00:52:06.119
A real animus?

00:52:06.179 --> 00:52:10.800
Yes, turtle said cautiously, but a bad

00:52:10.800 --> 00:52:13.380
one, like albatross.

00:52:13.500 --> 00:52:15.719
Oh, how would you know?

00:52:15.840 --> 00:52:17.340
Anemone scoffed.

00:52:17.400 --> 00:52:19.860
I've been dying to meet another animus.

00:52:19.920 --> 00:52:22.440
I visited the old fossil living in this

00:52:22.440 --> 00:52:25.019
mountain, and he was useless.

00:52:25.079 --> 00:52:26.880
His great helpful advice was that an

00:52:26.880 --> 00:52:28.920
animus dragon should never use her

00:52:28.920 --> 00:52:29.159
power.

00:52:29.219 --> 00:52:30.599
I mean, come on.

00:52:30.659 --> 00:52:33.780
He was all, but look what happened to

00:52:33.780 --> 00:52:34.679
me.

00:52:34.739 --> 00:52:37.139
Wheeze, moan, glug.

00:52:37.260 --> 00:52:39.480
And I wanted to be like, didn't you put

00:52:39.480 --> 00:52:41.579
this dopey stone scales spell on

00:52:41.579 --> 00:52:41.880
yourself?

00:52:41.940 --> 00:52:44.880
What use is your perfect soul if you

00:52:44.880 --> 00:52:45.900
can't move a muscle?

00:52:46.019 --> 00:52:47.579
So pathetic?

00:52:47.639 --> 00:52:50.579
If there's a real animus coming here, I

00:52:50.579 --> 00:52:51.179
want to meet him.

00:52:51.239 --> 00:52:54.360
No, Turtle protested.

00:52:54.420 --> 00:52:56.219
He'll probably kill you.

00:52:56.280 --> 00:52:57.480
He's really smart.

00:52:57.539 --> 00:53:00.000
He'll see another animus dragon as a

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:00.239
threat.

00:53:00.300 --> 00:53:03.960
If he's really smart, he'll see that I'm

00:53:03.960 --> 00:53:06.360
awesome, and want to get to know me.

00:53:06.480 --> 00:53:09.000
Anemone said, tossing her head.

00:53:09.059 --> 00:53:12.599
Princess, I think your brother is right

00:53:12.599 --> 00:53:14.159
Pike interjected.

00:53:14.219 --> 00:53:16.380
This sounds like a dangerous situation.

00:53:16.440 --> 00:53:19.619
You should hide while I assess this

00:53:19.619 --> 00:53:20.099
stranger.

00:53:20.159 --> 00:53:21.900
What?

00:53:21.960 --> 00:53:24.719
Anemone threw her wings up in disbelief.

00:53:24.780 --> 00:53:27.179
I'm not going to hide like some kind of

00:53:27.179 --> 00:53:29.519
nervous shrimp. 3 moons.

00:53:29.579 --> 00:53:31.619
Turtle, did you actually see him kill

00:53:31.619 --> 00:53:32.099
anyone?

00:53:32.159 --> 00:53:36.000
No, but according to history, he killed

00:53:36.000 --> 00:53:36.599
his dad.

00:53:36.659 --> 00:53:39.780
And according to history, she said

00:53:39.780 --> 00:53:42.480
dismissively, has he hurt anyone since he

00:53:42.480 --> 00:53:43.440
escaped?

00:53:43.500 --> 00:53:47.219
No, but he probably will.

00:53:47.280 --> 00:53:50.219
He doesn't like ice wings, and he doesn't

00:53:50.219 --> 00:53:50.519
like me.

00:53:50.579 --> 00:53:54.420
Well, I am not a nice wing, and I'm not

00:53:54.420 --> 00:53:56.880
the most boring prince on the planet, she

00:53:56.880 --> 00:53:57.239
said.

00:53:57.300 --> 00:53:59.340
So I think he'll like me just fine.

00:53:59.400 --> 00:54:01.199
Pike, shut up.

00:54:01.260 --> 00:54:03.900
Pike closed his mouth and ducked his

00:54:03.900 --> 00:54:04.139
head.

00:54:04.199 --> 00:54:06.360
Anemone clapped her front talons

00:54:06.360 --> 00:54:06.719
together.

00:54:06.780 --> 00:54:08.699
This is so exciting.

00:54:08.760 --> 00:54:10.440
Another animus to talk to.

00:54:10.500 --> 00:54:13.679
Guilt warmed through Turtle's heart

00:54:13.679 --> 00:54:13.980
again.

00:54:14.039 --> 00:54:15.960
He had thought about telling his sister

00:54:15.960 --> 00:54:19.199
his secret a 100 times, if he had ever

00:54:19.199 --> 00:54:21.119
admitted that he was a fellow animus

00:54:21.119 --> 00:54:23.159
would she be more willing to listen to

00:54:23.159 --> 00:54:23.460
him?

00:54:23.519 --> 00:54:25.199
Should he tell her now?

00:54:25.260 --> 00:54:27.539
Would that stop her from wanting to meet

00:54:27.539 --> 00:54:28.380
Dark Stalker?

00:54:28.440 --> 00:54:30.059
Probably not.

00:54:30.179 --> 00:54:33.000
And to tell her in front of Pike and

00:54:33.000 --> 00:54:35.639
Tamarin, just didn't seem like a good

00:54:35.639 --> 00:54:35.820
idea.

00:54:35.880 --> 00:54:39.059
Pike was one of Queen Coral's most loyal

00:54:39.059 --> 00:54:39.719
followers.

00:54:39.780 --> 00:54:42.239
He'd definitely report back to her the

00:54:42.239 --> 00:54:44.880
1st chance he got, even anemone.

00:54:44.940 --> 00:54:46.980
Would she keep his secret?

00:54:47.099 --> 00:54:48.599
He wasn't ready.

00:54:48.659 --> 00:54:51.480
Better to stay hidden and keep quiet

00:54:51.480 --> 00:54:52.920
safer that way.

00:54:52.980 --> 00:54:56.940
Anemone dove off her rock and paddled to

00:54:56.940 --> 00:54:58.619
the tunnel that led back to the school.

00:54:58.679 --> 00:55:01.139
Last one to the main hall is a rotten

00:55:01.139 --> 00:55:03.960
oyster. she called, galloping away into

00:55:03.960 --> 00:55:04.380
the dark.

00:55:04.500 --> 00:55:07.800
Pike hissed softly, twisting between the

00:55:07.800 --> 00:55:09.539
disappearing princess and the injured

00:55:09.539 --> 00:55:10.619
rain wing by the lake.

00:55:10.679 --> 00:55:12.960
It's all right, Pike.

00:55:13.019 --> 00:55:14.219
Tamarin said.

00:55:14.280 --> 00:55:17.340
She waited out of the water, limping, and

00:55:17.340 --> 00:55:19.079
rested one talon lightly on the wall.

00:55:19.139 --> 00:55:22.019
I can find my way back to the infirmary

00:55:22.019 --> 00:55:22.440
on my own.

00:55:22.500 --> 00:55:24.300
Can you go with her?

00:55:24.360 --> 00:55:26.400
Pike asked Turtle.

00:55:26.460 --> 00:55:28.260
He was halfway to the tunnel already.

00:55:28.320 --> 00:55:30.239
Make sure she gets safely to the

00:55:30.239 --> 00:55:30.780
infirmary.

00:55:30.900 --> 00:55:34.320
I can take care of myself.

00:55:34.380 --> 00:55:37.800
Tameron said, through gridded teeth

00:55:37.800 --> 00:55:39.360
limping another few steps.

00:55:39.420 --> 00:55:42.539
Turtle nodded, and Pike leaped out of the

00:55:42.539 --> 00:55:43.920
lake to run after anemone.

00:55:43.980 --> 00:55:47.460
I know you 2 were making secret faces at

00:55:47.460 --> 00:55:47.820
each other.

00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:51.179
Tamarin said, as Turtle climbed out of

00:55:51.179 --> 00:55:52.380
the lake beside her.

00:55:52.440 --> 00:55:54.300
I don't like it when dragons do that

00:55:54.300 --> 00:55:54.659
around me.

00:55:54.719 --> 00:55:57.900
Sorry, Turtle said.

00:55:57.960 --> 00:56:00.780
I was only responding to his secret

00:56:00.780 --> 00:56:01.380
faces.

00:56:01.440 --> 00:56:04.679
So is Kinkachu really all right?

00:56:04.739 --> 00:56:07.800
Or were his faces making you lie to me?

00:56:07.860 --> 00:56:08.880
She asked.

00:56:08.940 --> 00:56:11.460
She set off toward the tunnel.

00:56:11.519 --> 00:56:13.800
Stepping cautiously but confidently along

00:56:13.800 --> 00:56:16.380
the rocky lake shore, Turtle winced.

00:56:16.440 --> 00:56:18.300
She did get hurt.

00:56:18.360 --> 00:56:21.659
He admitted, following her, pretty

00:56:21.659 --> 00:56:22.079
badly.

00:56:22.139 --> 00:56:24.840
She's still unconscious, as far as I

00:56:24.840 --> 00:56:25.079
know.

00:56:25.139 --> 00:56:27.719
But the doctor's impossibility thought

00:56:27.719 --> 00:56:28.440
she'd be all right.

00:56:28.500 --> 00:56:30.480
If she wakes up soon.

00:56:30.480 --> 00:56:33.840
Oh, poor Kinkaju.

00:56:33.900 --> 00:56:35.340
Tameron cried.

00:56:35.400 --> 00:56:37.739
She stopped and pressed her talons to her

00:56:37.739 --> 00:56:38.460
face.

00:56:38.519 --> 00:56:40.860
I knew it was too dangerous for her out

00:56:40.860 --> 00:56:41.039
there.

00:56:41.099 --> 00:56:44.219
She's always running straight at the bad

00:56:44.219 --> 00:56:46.980
things, instead of hiding, or at least

00:56:46.980 --> 00:56:47.940
thinking first.

00:56:48.059 --> 00:56:51.840
That's true, Turtle realized.

00:56:51.900 --> 00:56:54.059
That was one of the things he liked about

00:56:54.059 --> 00:56:54.900
Kinkachu.

00:56:54.960 --> 00:56:56.820
That she was nothing like him.

00:56:56.880 --> 00:57:00.360
Queen Glory sent rain wing healers to

00:57:00.360 --> 00:57:01.800
watch over her. he said.

00:57:01.920 --> 00:57:03.179
She's not alone.

00:57:03.239 --> 00:57:07.500
I wish I could go to her, Cameron said

00:57:07.500 --> 00:57:08.039
with a sigh.

00:57:08.099 --> 00:57:10.559
She set off along the main passageway.

00:57:10.679 --> 00:57:14.099
After a moment, she said quietly, I

00:57:14.099 --> 00:57:15.840
didn't know anemone was an animus.

00:57:15.900 --> 00:57:18.420
Turtle felt like an idiot.

00:57:18.480 --> 00:57:20.880
He'd been so worried about hiding his own

00:57:20.880 --> 00:57:21.239
powers.

00:57:21.300 --> 00:57:23.460
He'd forgotten that anemones were

00:57:23.460 --> 00:57:24.900
supposed to be kept secret too.

00:57:25.019 --> 00:57:27.780
The other tribes aren't supposed to

00:57:27.780 --> 00:57:28.019
know.

00:57:28.079 --> 00:57:29.039
He said.

00:57:29.099 --> 00:57:32.219
Tsunami's friends do, but they swore not

00:57:32.219 --> 00:57:32.639
to tell anyone.

00:57:32.699 --> 00:57:34.800
I won't say anything.

00:57:34.860 --> 00:57:36.539
Tamron promised.

00:57:36.599 --> 00:57:40.019
That must be hard on anemone, keeping a

00:57:40.019 --> 00:57:40.559
secret like that.

00:57:40.679 --> 00:57:42.599
I guess.

00:57:42.659 --> 00:57:44.880
Turtles said uncomfortably.

00:57:44.940 --> 00:57:47.159
He'd been keeping the same secret his

00:57:47.159 --> 00:57:49.079
whole life, but from everyone.

00:57:49.139 --> 00:57:50.639
Was it hard?

00:57:50.699 --> 00:57:52.320
Maybe sometimes.

00:57:52.380 --> 00:57:54.900
Like whenever something happened, that he

00:57:54.900 --> 00:57:57.480
knew his magic could fix, but he had to

00:57:57.480 --> 00:57:58.920
go ahead and leave it broken.

00:57:59.159 --> 00:58:01.019
Like Tamarin's eyes.

00:58:01.079 --> 00:58:03.119
I could fix them.

00:58:03.179 --> 00:58:04.619
I could do it right now.

00:58:04.679 --> 00:58:07.980
I could enchant that bandage, so when she

00:58:07.980 --> 00:58:10.260
takes it off, she could see for the 1st

00:58:10.260 --> 00:58:11.039
time in her life.

00:58:11.099 --> 00:58:14.159
That was the kind of thing he wished he

00:58:14.159 --> 00:58:16.679
was free to do, and it felt awful to have

00:58:16.679 --> 00:58:19.559
to stop himself, but he still figured it

00:58:19.559 --> 00:58:21.599
was a lot easier to be a secret animus

00:58:21.599 --> 00:58:23.460
than an animus everyone knew about.

00:58:23.579 --> 00:58:27.719
I wouldn't want to be ananimous, Tamron

00:58:27.719 --> 00:58:28.019
said.

00:58:28.079 --> 00:58:30.599
She paused at a spot where the tunnel

00:58:30.599 --> 00:58:31.800
branched into three directions.

00:58:31.860 --> 00:58:34.619
I don't know how anyone could stay a good

00:58:34.619 --> 00:58:36.000
dragon with all that power.

00:58:36.059 --> 00:58:39.000
What if they only used it for good

00:58:39.000 --> 00:58:39.480
things?

00:58:39.599 --> 00:58:41.940
Turtle asked, a little stung.

00:58:42.000 --> 00:58:44.820
But who gets to decide what's a good

00:58:44.820 --> 00:58:45.239
thing?

00:58:45.300 --> 00:58:46.559
Tameron asked.

00:58:46.619 --> 00:58:49.679
Dragons would always be asking for spells

00:58:49.679 --> 00:58:52.019
or telling you your choices are wrong.

00:58:52.079 --> 00:58:54.780
And I think sometimes it's hard to tell

00:58:54.780 --> 00:58:57.480
what's good, and what's just easy.

00:58:57.539 --> 00:59:00.539
Turtle gave her a puzzled look.

00:59:00.599 --> 00:59:02.219
Aren't those the same?

00:59:02.340 --> 00:59:04.619
What's wrong with trying to make life

00:59:04.619 --> 00:59:05.039
easier?

00:59:05.099 --> 00:59:07.199
It depends.

00:59:07.260 --> 00:59:08.519
Tamron said.

00:59:08.579 --> 00:59:11.460
For instance, an animus dragon might

00:59:11.460 --> 00:59:11.880
think.

00:59:11.940 --> 00:59:14.880
I'll make all our medicinal herbs appear

00:59:14.880 --> 00:59:17.400
magically in the healer's treehouse, so

00:59:17.400 --> 00:59:18.840
we never have to go looking for them

00:59:18.840 --> 00:59:19.079
again.

00:59:19.139 --> 00:59:22.019
That seems obviously good, right?

00:59:22.079 --> 00:59:24.599
But then we'd stop learning how to look

00:59:24.599 --> 00:59:27.300
for them, and we'd stop experimenting

00:59:27.300 --> 00:59:29.219
with new ones to see how those might help

00:59:29.219 --> 00:59:30.599
dragons in different ways.

00:59:30.599 --> 00:59:33.360
We'd stop thinking about it at all

00:59:33.360 --> 00:59:35.579
because everything would be too easy.

00:59:35.639 --> 00:59:38.099
Don't we lose something when everything

00:59:38.099 --> 00:59:39.119
is done for us?

00:59:39.179 --> 00:59:42.420
Turtle blinked at her, confused.

00:59:42.480 --> 00:59:45.840
I thought rain wings were all lazy, he

00:59:45.840 --> 00:59:46.079
said.

00:59:46.139 --> 00:59:49.320
I thought your lives were easy, and you

00:59:49.320 --> 00:59:50.099
liked them that way.

00:59:50.159 --> 00:59:52.260
Not mine.

00:59:52.380 --> 00:59:53.940
Tamron said.

00:59:54.000 --> 00:59:57.239
Gesturing to her eyes, not Kinkaju.

00:59:57.300 --> 00:59:59.400
Maybe we're a little different from the

00:59:59.400 --> 00:59:59.639
others.

00:59:59.699 --> 01:00:01.260
She shrugged.

01:00:01.320 --> 01:00:04.440
Anyway, I can see why Anemone wants

01:00:04.440 --> 01:00:06.059
another animus to talk to about it.

01:00:06.119 --> 01:00:09.239
Right, said Turtle.

01:00:09.300 --> 01:00:12.599
His thoughts had snagged on Kinkaju, and

01:00:12.599 --> 01:00:14.219
how she wasn't anything like the rain

01:00:14.219 --> 01:00:15.840
wings he'd read about in mother's

01:00:15.840 --> 01:00:16.260
stories.

01:00:16.320 --> 01:00:18.239
He hadn't thought about that before

01:00:18.239 --> 01:00:20.940
because he didn't think Rainwing when he

01:00:20.940 --> 01:00:23.460
saw her, he only thought Kinkaju.

01:00:23.519 --> 01:00:27.059
I'm really fine from here, said Tamron

01:00:27.059 --> 01:00:28.860
flicking her tail at one of the side

01:00:28.860 --> 01:00:29.400
tunnels.

01:00:29.460 --> 01:00:32.039
You go find clay or tsunami with your

01:00:32.039 --> 01:00:32.519
news.

01:00:32.579 --> 01:00:35.940
She strode off to the left, limping as

01:00:35.940 --> 01:00:38.039
fast as she could, as if she wanted to

01:00:38.039 --> 01:00:39.179
prove she didn't need help.

01:00:39.300 --> 01:00:42.179
Turtle took the path all the way to the

01:00:42.179 --> 01:00:44.280
right, winding up through the mountain

01:00:44.280 --> 01:00:45.119
toward the great hall.

01:00:45.179 --> 01:00:47.940
Halfway there, he heard voices coming

01:00:47.940 --> 01:00:48.900
from one of the caves.

01:00:48.960 --> 01:00:50.519
Instinctively.

01:00:50.579 --> 01:00:53.219
He slowed down and snuck closer on quiet

01:00:53.219 --> 01:00:53.880
talons.

01:00:53.940 --> 01:00:56.579
He'd always been good at eavesdropping

01:00:56.579 --> 01:00:59.099
and made his life easier, knowing what

01:00:59.099 --> 01:01:00.659
other dragons whispered about behind

01:01:00.659 --> 01:01:01.739
closed doors.

01:01:01.800 --> 01:01:04.739
He'd avoided several palace scandals and

01:01:04.739 --> 01:01:05.579
feuds that way.

01:01:05.639 --> 01:01:09.239
This might be the kind of thing Tamron is

01:01:09.239 --> 01:01:09.659
talking about.

01:01:09.719 --> 01:01:11.940
He realized uncomfortably.

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:14.639
A way I make my life easier.

01:01:14.760 --> 01:01:16.260
That's not exactly good.

01:01:16.320 --> 01:01:20.699
Mother feels terrible, said one of the

01:01:20.699 --> 01:01:21.420
voices quietly.

01:01:21.539 --> 01:01:23.880
She can't figure out how they escaped.

01:01:23.940 --> 01:01:26.639
Can she trust her guards?

01:01:26.699 --> 01:01:29.340
asked another voice, which turtle

01:01:29.340 --> 01:01:31.139
recognized as his sister tsunami?

01:01:31.199 --> 01:01:33.420
Maybe she needs to replace them all

01:01:33.420 --> 01:01:34.320
without claws?

01:01:34.380 --> 01:01:36.780
Everyone knows their undying loyalty to

01:01:36.780 --> 01:01:37.139
Thorn.

01:01:37.199 --> 01:01:40.440
But she needs her best outlaws in other

01:01:40.440 --> 01:01:42.539
parts of the kingdom, said the 1st

01:01:42.539 --> 01:01:42.780
voice.

01:01:42.900 --> 01:01:45.000
That must be sunny.

01:01:45.059 --> 01:01:46.559
Turtle realized.

01:01:46.619 --> 01:01:48.840
There was an explosion at one of our

01:01:48.840 --> 01:01:50.579
Western oases a couple of days ago.

01:01:50.639 --> 01:01:53.340
Two dragons were killed, and we have no

01:01:53.340 --> 01:01:53.699
idea why.

01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:57.360
Was it one of those viper licking cactus

01:01:57.360 --> 01:01:58.260
bombs like the one here?

01:01:58.260 --> 01:02:00.780
asked tsunami, growling.

01:02:01.019 --> 01:02:02.639
Seems like it.

01:02:02.699 --> 01:02:03.780
Sunnyside.

01:02:03.840 --> 01:02:06.179
But it makes no sense that a sky wing

01:02:06.179 --> 01:02:08.519
would be out that far west, or targeting

01:02:08.519 --> 01:02:09.300
these dragons.

01:02:09.360 --> 01:02:12.840
Anyway, mother has enough problems, and

01:02:12.840 --> 01:02:14.460
now she's worried that Glory will be mad

01:02:14.460 --> 01:02:14.820
at her.

01:02:14.940 --> 01:02:16.440
She won't be, right?

01:02:16.500 --> 01:02:18.659
Glory knows how tough it is being a new

01:02:18.659 --> 01:02:19.019
queen.

01:02:19.079 --> 01:02:22.019
Of course, said tsunami.

01:02:22.079 --> 01:02:25.079
On the other talent, Thorn did promise to

01:02:25.079 --> 01:02:27.300
hang on to those prisoners for her, and

01:02:27.300 --> 01:02:28.920
who knows what they'll do now that

01:02:28.920 --> 01:02:29.519
they've escaped?

01:02:29.579 --> 01:02:32.219
I bet they'll go try to kill glory or

01:02:32.219 --> 01:02:32.519
you.

01:02:32.579 --> 01:02:34.320
They hate you too, don't they?

01:02:34.380 --> 01:02:37.739
See, this is why I come to you with my

01:02:37.739 --> 01:02:40.440
problems, Sonny said, because you're

01:02:40.440 --> 01:02:41.460
always so comforting.

01:02:41.519 --> 01:02:44.400
I can make a stab at comforting?

01:02:44.460 --> 01:02:45.659
Tsunami joked.

01:02:45.780 --> 01:02:47.099
Let me try.

01:02:47.159 --> 01:02:49.800
Um, hey, it's only 2 dragons, right?

01:02:49.920 --> 01:02:52.440
Uh, they won't be able to do anything.

01:02:52.500 --> 01:02:55.199
Deathbringer will totally stop them if

01:02:55.199 --> 01:02:56.460
they go anywhere near her.

01:02:56.519 --> 01:02:59.340
I mean, that is his entire purpose in

01:02:59.340 --> 01:03:00.480
life as far as I can tell.

01:03:00.539 --> 01:03:03.840
And if they kill him, glory will take

01:03:03.840 --> 01:03:05.579
them down with her magical death spit.

01:03:05.639 --> 01:03:08.280
So don't worry, pat, pat, pat.

01:03:08.400 --> 01:03:13.440
Hmm, said Sonny, that was very stabby

01:03:13.440 --> 01:03:14.099
comforting.

01:03:14.159 --> 01:03:16.920
There was the scrape of claws against

01:03:16.920 --> 01:03:19.440
rock. and Turtle realized they were

01:03:19.440 --> 01:03:20.639
coming toward the cave entrance.

01:03:20.699 --> 01:03:23.159
He backed up to act as though he was

01:03:23.159 --> 01:03:24.840
walking along the corridor when the 2

01:03:24.840 --> 01:03:25.800
dragons emerged.

01:03:25.860 --> 01:03:27.059
Turtle!

01:03:27.119 --> 01:03:29.699
Tsunami's face lit up with such delight

01:03:29.699 --> 01:03:31.860
that he felt ashamed of spying on her.

01:03:31.920 --> 01:03:34.739
By all the moons, Sonny, look!

01:03:34.800 --> 01:03:36.900
A student from the Jade Winglet is

01:03:36.900 --> 01:03:39.599
actually here at school, where they're

01:03:39.599 --> 01:03:40.860
supposed to be.

01:03:40.920 --> 01:03:41.940
What a glorious honor.

01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:43.380
Is it my hatching day?

01:03:43.380 --> 01:03:44.699
or am I hallucinating?

01:03:44.760 --> 01:03:47.639
All right, enough sarcasm.

01:03:47.699 --> 01:03:50.099
Sunny said, elbowing her in the chest.

01:03:50.219 --> 01:03:52.619
Turtle, we've been really worried.

01:03:52.679 --> 01:03:54.119
Is everyone else back too?

01:03:54.179 --> 01:03:58.380
Well, they're coming, he said.

01:03:58.440 --> 01:04:00.059
I'm here to warn you.

01:04:00.119 --> 01:04:01.980
They're coming with someone else.

01:04:02.039 --> 01:04:04.739
Maybe a bad someone else.

01:04:04.800 --> 01:04:07.440
Have either of you ever heard of Dark

01:04:07.440 --> 01:04:08.039
Stalker?

01:04:08.099 --> 01:04:10.980
Sonny jumped and gave him a startled

01:04:10.980 --> 01:04:11.579
look.

01:04:11.639 --> 01:04:14.940
I have, when I was chasing fierce teeth

01:04:14.940 --> 01:04:15.599
and the others.

01:04:15.659 --> 01:04:17.820
I heard them talking about this ancient

01:04:17.820 --> 01:04:20.579
night wing legend, a dragon called Dark

01:04:20.579 --> 01:04:21.119
Stalker.

01:04:21.179 --> 01:04:24.239
They were crazy scared of him, like he

01:04:24.239 --> 01:04:25.619
might actually be hunting them right that

01:04:25.619 --> 01:04:27.780
minute, even though he died, like

01:04:27.780 --> 01:04:29.039
centuries ago.

01:04:29.099 --> 01:04:35.039
Um, so that's the thing, said Turtle.

01:04:35.099 --> 01:04:36.420
He didn't so much.

01:04:36.420 --> 01:04:38.460
Exactly die.

01:04:38.519 --> 01:04:40.079
What?

01:04:40.139 --> 01:04:42.900
Tsunami demanded, lashing her tail.

01:04:42.960 --> 01:04:46.139
He's woken up, Turtle said.

01:04:46.199 --> 01:04:48.840
And he's on his way here, right now.

01:04:48.900 --> 01:04:51.900
There was a gasp from farther up the

01:04:51.900 --> 01:04:52.320
tunnel.

01:04:52.380 --> 01:04:54.659
They all turned and found a Nightwing

01:04:54.659 --> 01:04:56.760
Dragonette standing there, staring at

01:04:56.760 --> 01:04:58.800
Turtle, with his face contorted in

01:04:58.800 --> 01:04:59.159
terror.

01:04:59.219 --> 01:05:03.599
Chapter 3.

01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:08.820
Mighty Claus, Sonny said, holding out her

01:05:08.820 --> 01:05:09.420
talons.

01:05:09.480 --> 01:05:11.280
Wait, don't overreact.

01:05:11.340 --> 01:05:13.019
We don't even know.

01:05:13.079 --> 01:05:15.480
I have to warn the others, he cried.

01:05:15.539 --> 01:05:17.400
He bolted up the tunnel toward the main

01:05:17.400 --> 01:05:17.639
hall.

01:05:17.760 --> 01:05:20.639
Oh, good, said tsunami.

01:05:20.699 --> 01:05:22.380
School wide panic.

01:05:22.440 --> 01:05:24.539
We haven't had any of that in at least 2

01:05:24.539 --> 01:05:24.719
days.

01:05:24.780 --> 01:05:28.619
Mighty Claus, Sonny called, running after

01:05:28.619 --> 01:05:28.860
him.

01:05:28.920 --> 01:05:29.820
Wait.

01:05:29.880 --> 01:05:32.219
Tell me everything.

01:05:32.340 --> 01:05:34.199
Tsunami said to Turtle.

01:05:34.260 --> 01:05:36.300
He hurried to keep up with her as they

01:05:36.300 --> 01:05:38.099
strode along the winding stone tunnel.

01:05:38.159 --> 01:05:40.920
The violet and rose glass lights overhead

01:05:40.920 --> 01:05:43.739
reflected off her thoughtful expression.

01:05:43.800 --> 01:05:46.380
He didn't tell her everything.

01:05:46.440 --> 01:05:49.079
He didn't tell her about his own magic.

01:05:49.199 --> 01:05:51.780
He sort of skimmed over the part where he

01:05:51.780 --> 01:05:54.539
hid from Dark Stalker, implying that tall

01:05:54.539 --> 01:05:57.480
bushes and fallen trees were involved, but

01:05:57.480 --> 01:05:59.280
he had to tell her about Moon's powers

01:05:59.280 --> 01:06:01.260
although he felt as though that should

01:06:01.260 --> 01:06:03.000
have been Moon's secret to share.

01:06:03.059 --> 01:06:05.880
Still, there was no other way to explain

01:06:05.880 --> 01:06:08.219
the prophecy and how Moon had been

01:06:08.219 --> 01:06:09.780
communicating with Dark Stalker.

01:06:09.840 --> 01:06:14.880
Arr, no, tsunami said, sweeping her tail

01:06:14.880 --> 01:06:15.480
across the floor.

01:06:15.539 --> 01:06:18.300
More powers and prophecies?

01:06:18.360 --> 01:06:18.659
Seriously?

01:06:18.719 --> 01:06:20.280
I thought we were all done with that.

01:06:20.340 --> 01:06:23.280
Turtle had told Sunny about Moon's

01:06:23.280 --> 01:06:26.099
prophecy before, after his winglet left

01:06:26.099 --> 01:06:28.079
but he'd left it up to her to decide who

01:06:28.079 --> 01:06:28.679
else to tell.

01:06:28.739 --> 01:06:31.440
Apparently, tsunami hadn't been on that

01:06:31.440 --> 01:06:31.739
list.

01:06:31.800 --> 01:06:34.559
I hate prophecies.

01:06:34.679 --> 01:06:36.900
Tsunami muttered darkly.

01:06:37.019 --> 01:06:40.260
All cryptic and demanding, most useless

01:06:40.260 --> 01:06:41.880
way to communicate in the history of the

01:06:41.880 --> 01:06:42.059
world.

01:06:42.179 --> 01:06:45.300
Is Dark Stalker as terrifying as he

01:06:45.300 --> 01:06:45.539
sounds.

01:06:45.599 --> 01:06:48.420
That night wing student looked like he'd

01:06:48.420 --> 01:06:50.039
just been bitten by a ghost shark.

01:06:50.159 --> 01:06:52.019
He scared me.

01:06:52.079 --> 01:06:53.760
Turtle admitted.

01:06:53.820 --> 01:06:56.460
He felt a little better now, here in

01:06:56.460 --> 01:06:57.659
tsunami's shadow.

01:06:57.719 --> 01:06:59.880
The dragonettes of destiny could deal

01:06:59.880 --> 01:07:00.900
with Dark Stalker.

01:07:00.960 --> 01:07:02.099
He didn't have to do anything.

01:07:02.159 --> 01:07:04.679
He could leave saving the world in their

01:07:04.679 --> 01:07:05.099
talons.

01:07:05.219 --> 01:07:08.579
Let's swing by the library and ask for a

01:07:08.579 --> 01:07:10.980
lecture, tsunami said, grinning at

01:07:10.980 --> 01:07:11.340
turtle.

01:07:11.400 --> 01:07:13.199
It'll make Starflight's day.

01:07:13.260 --> 01:07:15.840
They took another branch of the tunnel

01:07:15.840 --> 01:07:18.659
and soon came to the wide open cave lined

01:07:18.659 --> 01:07:19.739
with scrolls.

01:07:19.800 --> 01:07:21.539
One of the leaf windows had been torn

01:07:21.539 --> 01:07:24.300
apart when icicle leaped out of it, and

01:07:24.300 --> 01:07:26.760
it still hadn't been fixed, allowing a

01:07:26.760 --> 01:07:28.800
burst of bright sunbeams to cut across

01:07:28.800 --> 01:07:31.019
the otherwise cool green light.

01:07:31.260 --> 01:07:33.659
Starflight was behind his desk with fate

01:07:33.659 --> 01:07:36.000
speaker, nudging scrolls into 3 different

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:36.420
piles.

01:07:36.480 --> 01:07:39.360
His forehead was creased with worry, as

01:07:39.360 --> 01:07:39.960
it often was.

01:07:40.019 --> 01:07:42.719
Turtle liked Starflight.

01:07:42.780 --> 01:07:46.019
He was quiet, and better yet, he led

01:07:46.019 --> 01:07:47.219
other dragons be quiet.

01:07:47.280 --> 01:07:50.460
After the rest of Jade Winglet left the

01:07:50.460 --> 01:07:50.639
school.

01:07:50.699 --> 01:07:53.280
Turtle would often sit in the library by

01:07:53.280 --> 01:07:53.639
himself.

01:07:53.699 --> 01:07:56.639
And Starflight never asked questions or

01:07:56.639 --> 01:07:57.239
made him talk.

01:07:57.300 --> 01:07:59.760
Hey, Starflight.

01:07:59.820 --> 01:08:02.820
Tsunami tapped the desk lightly, so the

01:08:02.820 --> 01:08:04.199
blind librarian would know where she

01:08:04.199 --> 01:08:04.440
was.

01:08:04.500 --> 01:08:08.099
Don't explode with joy or anything, but I

01:08:08.099 --> 01:08:09.659
have a historical question for you.

01:08:09.719 --> 01:08:11.099
Really?

01:08:11.159 --> 01:08:14.460
Starflight's phase lit up, turning toward

01:08:14.460 --> 01:08:16.739
the sound of her talons, which era?

01:08:16.800 --> 01:08:20.159
I have no idea, tsunami snorted.

01:08:20.220 --> 01:08:22.739
Is there an era of sinister bad guys?

01:08:22.800 --> 01:08:24.779
What do you know about a dragon called

01:08:24.779 --> 01:08:26.220
Dark Stalker?

01:08:26.279 --> 01:08:28.979
Something clattered to the floor across

01:08:28.979 --> 01:08:31.679
the room, and Turtle realized there was a

01:08:31.679 --> 01:08:33.719
trio of ice wings studying over by the

01:08:33.719 --> 01:08:34.079
windows.

01:08:34.140 --> 01:08:37.079
They'd dropped their scroll when they

01:08:37.079 --> 01:08:39.359
heard tsunami's question, and now they

01:08:39.359 --> 01:08:41.279
were leaning towards Starflight with

01:08:41.279 --> 01:08:42.720
sharp, curious expressions.

01:08:42.840 --> 01:08:46.739
He was a very powerful animus nightwing

01:08:46.739 --> 01:08:48.840
who disappeared over 2000 years ago.

01:08:48.899 --> 01:08:51.299
Starflight said cautiously.

01:08:51.420 --> 01:08:54.000
The stories say he was betrayed by his

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:57.180
friend, a sea wing animus named Fathom

01:08:57.180 --> 01:08:59.880
and perhaps also by his girlfriend

01:08:59.880 --> 01:09:00.779
Clearsight.

01:09:00.840 --> 01:09:02.939
But nobody knows exactly what happened to

01:09:02.939 --> 01:09:03.180
him.

01:09:03.239 --> 01:09:06.840
He didn't really disappear, said one of

01:09:06.840 --> 01:09:07.560
the ice wings.

01:09:07.619 --> 01:09:10.199
He spent years lurking in the shadows and

01:09:10.199 --> 01:09:11.279
killing ice wings.

01:09:11.399 --> 01:09:14.099
And you're leaving out the part about him

01:09:14.099 --> 01:09:16.499
killing his own father, said another ice

01:09:16.499 --> 01:09:19.679
wing, flicking her wings back, who was an

01:09:19.679 --> 01:09:20.759
ice wing prince?

01:09:20.819 --> 01:09:24.959
By the way, Whoa, really?

01:09:25.020 --> 01:09:27.899
Tsunami said, giving Turtle a worried

01:09:27.899 --> 01:09:28.140
look.

01:09:28.199 --> 01:09:33.659
That story has been highly oversimplified

01:09:33.720 --> 01:09:36.239
said Dark Stalker, poking his head in

01:09:36.239 --> 01:09:37.439
through the broken window.

01:09:37.500 --> 01:09:40.859
I mean, don't any of the scrolls mention

01:09:40.859 --> 01:09:42.359
that he totally deserved it.

01:09:42.420 --> 01:09:46.020
The ice wings shrieked in unison, loud

01:09:46.020 --> 01:09:46.979
enough to break glass.

01:09:47.039 --> 01:09:49.319
They scrambled over one another to get

01:09:49.319 --> 01:09:51.539
away from the oversized night wing

01:09:51.539 --> 01:09:54.000
knocking down an entire shelf of scrolls

01:09:54.000 --> 01:09:54.659
in the process.

01:09:54.720 --> 01:09:57.479
Paper unfurled across the cave in

01:09:57.479 --> 01:09:58.619
cascading fountains.

01:09:58.680 --> 01:10:01.800
Turtle froze, trying to sink into the

01:10:01.800 --> 01:10:01.979
floor.

01:10:02.039 --> 01:10:04.619
How had Dark Stalker gotten here so

01:10:04.619 --> 01:10:04.979
fast?

01:10:05.039 --> 01:10:06.779
Was he already done hunting?

01:10:06.840 --> 01:10:08.699
Where were turtles friends?

01:10:08.760 --> 01:10:10.380
What's happening?

01:10:10.439 --> 01:10:11.760
Starfly cried.

01:10:11.819 --> 01:10:12.779
Who was that?

01:10:12.840 --> 01:10:14.279
Oh, really?

01:10:14.340 --> 01:10:14.880
Really?

01:10:14.939 --> 01:10:16.619
Really big night wing?

01:10:16.739 --> 01:10:19.079
Fate speaker yelped, clutching his arm.

01:10:19.140 --> 01:10:21.119
I haven't had any visions about this.

01:10:21.180 --> 01:10:23.460
This seems seriously vision worthy.

01:10:23.520 --> 01:10:25.020
Powers, help me out.

01:10:25.140 --> 01:10:26.640
She closed her eyes.

01:10:26.699 --> 01:10:29.220
Oh no, I see.

01:10:29.520 --> 01:10:31.319
Darkness ahead.

01:10:31.380 --> 01:10:34.680
That's because you have your eyes closed

01:10:34.680 --> 01:10:35.640
you ninny.

01:10:35.699 --> 01:10:37.500
Dark Stalker said pleasantly.

01:10:37.560 --> 01:10:39.840
Who are you?

01:10:39.899 --> 01:10:41.340
Tsunami demanded.

01:10:41.399 --> 01:10:45.119
You already know, he said, startled.

01:10:45.180 --> 01:10:47.279
This is amazing.

01:10:47.340 --> 01:10:50.220
How empire did you know I was coming?

01:10:50.279 --> 01:10:51.600
He paused.

01:10:51.659 --> 01:10:54.180
I can't even find the answer to that in

01:10:54.180 --> 01:10:54.779
your mind.

01:10:54.840 --> 01:10:56.340
What in the world?

01:10:56.460 --> 01:10:58.800
A fascinating mystery.

01:10:58.859 --> 01:11:01.500
Don't think about it too hard.

01:11:01.560 --> 01:11:02.939
Turtle prayed.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:04.979
Don't figure out there's a secret to

01:11:04.979 --> 01:11:05.579
uncover here.

01:11:05.640 --> 01:11:08.699
So you are dark stalker.

01:11:08.760 --> 01:11:10.739
Tsunami lashed her tail.

01:11:10.800 --> 01:11:12.720
You'd better not hurt any of my

01:11:12.720 --> 01:11:13.979
students.

01:11:14.039 --> 01:11:15.060
What?

01:11:15.119 --> 01:11:17.039
Starflight sputtered.

01:11:17.100 --> 01:11:18.300
Dark stalker?

01:11:18.359 --> 01:11:18.659
How?

01:11:18.720 --> 01:11:21.779
Why would I hurt any of your students?

01:11:21.899 --> 01:11:23.640
Dark Stalker protested.

01:11:23.760 --> 01:11:26.640
There's literally 0 motivation for me to

01:11:26.640 --> 01:11:26.939
do that.

01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:30.899
Dragons today, so full of mistrust and

01:11:30.899 --> 01:11:31.439
hostility.

01:11:31.560 --> 01:11:34.800
Now, in my time, no wait.

01:11:34.859 --> 01:11:36.420
We were exactly the same.

01:11:36.420 --> 01:11:39.659
He poked at the ragged green edges of the

01:11:39.659 --> 01:11:40.680
leaf window pane.

01:11:40.680 --> 01:11:43.439
That's one of the many problems I was

01:11:43.439 --> 01:11:44.159
going to fix.

01:11:44.220 --> 01:11:48.300
It's the dark stalker, shouted one of the

01:11:48.300 --> 01:11:48.899
ice wings.

01:11:48.960 --> 01:11:50.640
Die, you monster.

01:11:50.699 --> 01:11:53.939
She leaped across the cave, blasting

01:11:53.939 --> 01:11:56.220
frost breath in Dark Stalker's face

01:11:56.220 --> 01:11:58.140
landed in a roll right in front of his

01:11:58.140 --> 01:12:00.720
snout, and slashed her serrated claws

01:12:00.720 --> 01:12:01.319
across his nose.

01:12:01.439 --> 01:12:05.039
All of which, of course, did nothing to

01:12:05.039 --> 01:12:05.220
him.

01:12:05.340 --> 01:12:08.699
The ice wings staggered back, shaking her

01:12:08.699 --> 01:12:10.920
arm as if she'd just smashed it into a

01:12:10.920 --> 01:12:11.579
rock.

01:12:11.640 --> 01:12:14.340
Dark Stalker gave her a bored look.

01:12:14.399 --> 01:12:16.739
Then reached one of his long talons

01:12:16.739 --> 01:12:19.140
through the window, and casually pinned

01:12:19.140 --> 01:12:19.619
her to the floor.

01:12:19.680 --> 01:12:23.100
All right, he said.

01:12:23.159 --> 01:12:26.100
Now, I'm a little motivated to hurt

01:12:26.100 --> 01:12:26.939
somebody.

01:12:27.000 --> 01:12:29.399
Tsunami started toward him, and he

01:12:29.399 --> 01:12:29.760
chuckled.

01:12:29.819 --> 01:12:31.920
Oh, I won't, he said.

01:12:31.979 --> 01:12:33.000
I promise.

01:12:33.060 --> 01:12:35.340
No need to get all ferocious with me

01:12:35.340 --> 01:12:35.880
tsunami.

01:12:35.939 --> 01:12:38.460
But you might want to add a manners class

01:12:38.460 --> 01:12:39.180
to your curriculum.

01:12:39.300 --> 01:12:41.220
Or is it fine with you if your students

01:12:41.220 --> 01:12:42.899
attack innocent visitors?

01:12:42.960 --> 01:12:44.819
Let her go.

01:12:44.880 --> 01:12:46.739
Tsunami growled.

01:12:46.800 --> 01:12:49.619
Dark Stalker lifted his claws, and the

01:12:49.619 --> 01:12:50.699
ice wing scrambled away.

01:12:50.760 --> 01:12:54.239
All 3 ice dragons bolted out of the cave

01:12:54.239 --> 01:12:55.319
as fast as they could run.

01:12:55.380 --> 01:12:58.140
I don't think I'll fit through the

01:12:58.140 --> 01:12:59.100
tunnels to get in here.

01:12:59.159 --> 01:13:02.399
Dark Stalker said regretfully, glancing

01:13:02.399 --> 01:13:05.039
around the library, but I love what

01:13:05.039 --> 01:13:06.539
you've done with the space, Starflight.

01:13:06.600 --> 01:13:09.119
Could you please bring any scrolls you

01:13:09.119 --> 01:13:12.060
have about Clearsight and meet me in the

01:13:12.060 --> 01:13:13.079
main entrance hall?

01:13:13.140 --> 01:13:16.979
Scrolls about clear site, Starflight

01:13:16.979 --> 01:13:17.399
echoed.

01:13:17.460 --> 01:13:20.699
You're, uh, the dragon, you...

01:13:20.819 --> 01:13:23.460
Yes, said Dark Stalker.

01:13:23.520 --> 01:13:25.560
The dragon I loved.

01:13:25.680 --> 01:13:28.739
Specifically, about what happened to her

01:13:28.739 --> 01:13:33.420
after, well, after our unfortunate

01:13:33.420 --> 01:13:34.859
misunderstanding.

01:13:34.979 --> 01:13:38.880
But nobody knows, Starfly blurted.

01:13:38.939 --> 01:13:40.920
She disappeared at the same time you

01:13:40.920 --> 01:13:41.100
did.

01:13:41.220 --> 01:13:45.180
Maybe there's a clue somewhere, Dark

01:13:45.180 --> 01:13:45.840
Stalker said.

01:13:45.899 --> 01:13:47.880
Or a terrific librarian.

01:13:47.939 --> 01:13:50.100
If anyone can find it, you can.

01:13:50.220 --> 01:13:52.260
His eyes narrowed.

01:13:52.380 --> 01:13:55.020
Perhaps it would also be useful.

01:13:55.140 --> 01:13:58.079
To bring any scrolls about what happened

01:13:58.079 --> 01:13:59.399
to fathom.

01:13:59.460 --> 01:14:04.079
I, I, Starflight stammered, moving his

01:14:04.079 --> 01:14:05.159
claws along the desk.

01:14:05.220 --> 01:14:07.560
Fate speaker grabbed one of his talons

01:14:07.560 --> 01:14:08.399
and leaned into him.

01:14:08.460 --> 01:14:12.359
Thanks ever so much, said Dark Stalker.

01:14:12.420 --> 01:14:15.300
Now, if you'll excuse me, someone is

01:14:15.300 --> 01:14:16.319
trying to attack my tail.

01:14:16.439 --> 01:14:19.079
He swung his head out the window, and

01:14:19.079 --> 01:14:22.140
Turtle heard him say, seriously, you

01:14:22.140 --> 01:14:22.380
too.

01:14:22.500 --> 01:14:24.359
Does everyone believe everything they

01:14:24.359 --> 01:14:25.020
read these days?

01:14:25.079 --> 01:14:27.840
Tsunami hurried over to the window.

01:14:27.899 --> 01:14:31.260
Turtle managed to breathe again, managed

01:14:31.260 --> 01:14:33.300
to move one foot slowly in front of the

01:14:33.300 --> 01:14:34.079
other to follow her.

01:14:34.140 --> 01:14:38.100
Outside, 2 small night wings were dive

01:14:38.100 --> 01:14:40.739
bombing dark stalker, shooting trails of

01:14:40.739 --> 01:14:41.939
flame across the scales.

01:14:42.000 --> 01:14:44.460
Turtle saw his friends hovering in the

01:14:44.460 --> 01:14:45.359
sky not far away.

01:14:45.420 --> 01:14:47.640
Moon was trying to call to the night

01:14:47.640 --> 01:14:49.260
wings, but they weren't listening to

01:14:49.260 --> 01:14:49.380
her.

01:14:49.500 --> 01:14:52.199
Dark Stalker lifted off from the

01:14:52.199 --> 01:14:54.539
mountainside and turned in a large, slow

01:14:54.539 --> 01:14:56.819
circle, watching the night wings without

01:14:56.819 --> 01:14:57.359
fighting back.

01:14:57.420 --> 01:14:59.640
He looked faintly amused.

01:14:59.699 --> 01:15:03.060
Tiny dragons, he boomed.

01:15:03.119 --> 01:15:06.420
Listen, I'm impressed, but this really

01:15:06.420 --> 01:15:07.439
isn't necessary.

01:15:07.500 --> 01:15:10.560
We're not going to let you hurt our tribe

01:15:10.560 --> 01:15:12.600
shouted one of the dragon ants.

01:15:12.659 --> 01:15:14.880
It was hard to tell from a distance, but

01:15:14.880 --> 01:15:16.439
Turtle thought that was Mighty Claus.

01:15:16.560 --> 01:15:18.840
By the shining moons.

01:15:18.899 --> 01:15:21.479
I'm not planning to herd the tribe, said

01:15:21.479 --> 01:15:22.319
Dark Stalker.

01:15:22.380 --> 01:15:24.060
It's my tribe too, isn't it?

01:15:24.119 --> 01:15:26.039
I'm a loyal night wing.

01:15:26.159 --> 01:15:28.319
All the stories ever mention that.

01:15:28.380 --> 01:15:29.640
Come on now.

01:15:29.699 --> 01:15:31.920
Nightwings are usually so clever.

01:15:31.979 --> 01:15:34.619
You must have noticed this isn't

01:15:34.619 --> 01:15:35.100
working.

01:15:35.159 --> 01:15:37.619
He caught mighty Claus gently in his

01:15:37.619 --> 01:15:39.659
talons and set him on a ledge.

01:15:39.720 --> 01:15:42.239
The other Nightwing darted in and wrapped

01:15:42.239 --> 01:15:44.579
herself around Dark Stalker's neck, trying

01:15:44.579 --> 01:15:46.739
to plunge her claws in between the scales

01:15:46.739 --> 01:15:47.579
of his underbelly.

01:15:47.640 --> 01:15:50.220
I don't mean the attack itself.

01:15:50.340 --> 01:15:53.399
Dark Stalker went on, as if he barely

01:15:53.399 --> 01:15:56.460
noticed his new violent scarf, although

01:15:56.460 --> 01:15:57.239
that's not working either.

01:15:57.300 --> 01:15:59.159
I mean the distraction.

01:15:59.220 --> 01:16:01.560
It's not actually possible to distract

01:16:01.560 --> 01:16:01.859
me.

01:16:01.920 --> 01:16:03.119
Because guess what?

01:16:03.180 --> 01:16:04.319
Mind reading.

01:16:04.380 --> 01:16:06.539
Plus also visions of the future.

01:16:06.600 --> 01:16:08.039
But good try.

01:16:08.159 --> 01:16:11.460
He whipped around, dove toward the forest

01:16:11.460 --> 01:16:13.800
and emerged a moment later with a 3rd

01:16:13.800 --> 01:16:15.479
night wing dragonette struggling between

01:16:15.479 --> 01:16:16.140
his talons.

01:16:16.199 --> 01:16:18.060
No, no.

01:16:18.119 --> 01:16:20.520
Dark Stalker shook his head at her.

01:16:20.579 --> 01:16:22.800
Listen, I understand.

01:16:22.859 --> 01:16:25.800
If I were you, I'd want to sneak off and

01:16:25.800 --> 01:16:27.000
warn the rest of the tribe too.

01:16:27.060 --> 01:16:29.340
But you know what they'll do then?

01:16:29.399 --> 01:16:30.539
I do.

01:16:30.659 --> 01:16:32.100
I saw it in a vision.

01:16:32.220 --> 01:16:34.680
They'll run away and try to hide from me

01:16:34.680 --> 01:16:37.199
again, without even giving me a chance to

01:16:37.199 --> 01:16:37.920
introduce myself.

01:16:37.979 --> 01:16:41.460
We know all about you, Mighty Claus

01:16:41.460 --> 01:16:41.939
yelled.

01:16:42.000 --> 01:16:43.680
We know you've been trying to break free

01:16:43.680 --> 01:16:46.380
for 2000 years so you can get revenge on

01:16:46.380 --> 01:16:46.800
our tribe.

01:16:46.859 --> 01:16:51.119
That makes no sense, Dark Stalker said

01:16:51.119 --> 01:16:51.539
reasonably.

01:16:51.600 --> 01:16:55.140
I did just escape a 2000 year trap.

01:16:55.199 --> 01:16:57.960
But the tribe didn't deceive me and stick

01:16:57.960 --> 01:16:58.619
me underground.

01:16:58.680 --> 01:17:03.600
That was 2 foolish dragons, using magic.

01:17:03.659 --> 01:17:05.880
It was nothing to do with the other night

01:17:05.880 --> 01:17:06.359
wings.

01:17:06.420 --> 01:17:08.579
I adore my tribe.

01:17:08.640 --> 01:17:11.520
I'm wildly excited to rejoin you and let

01:17:11.520 --> 01:17:13.739
everyone see the real me.

01:17:13.859 --> 01:17:17.220
He set down the night wing next to Matty

01:17:17.220 --> 01:17:19.140
Claus, and unwrapped the other one from

01:17:19.140 --> 01:17:21.119
his neck as though she were a harmless

01:17:21.119 --> 01:17:21.659
sloth.

01:17:21.720 --> 01:17:25.079
So, we're not going to ruin the surprise

01:17:25.079 --> 01:17:25.439
all right?

01:17:25.500 --> 01:17:28.079
We can all go together to tell the tribe

01:17:28.079 --> 01:17:28.619
I'm back.

01:17:28.680 --> 01:17:29.760
Trust me.

01:17:29.819 --> 01:17:31.020
It'll be great.

01:17:31.079 --> 01:17:34.199
Much less bloody and horrifying than what

01:17:34.199 --> 01:17:34.979
you all have in your minds.

01:17:35.039 --> 01:17:37.500
More feasting.

01:17:37.560 --> 01:17:38.880
And rainbows.

01:17:38.939 --> 01:17:40.079
Hang on.

01:17:40.140 --> 01:17:41.340
Where did that come from?

01:17:41.460 --> 01:17:43.380
Ah, I know.

01:17:43.439 --> 01:17:46.380
Dark soccer turned toward the landing

01:17:46.380 --> 01:17:47.640
area that led to the main school

01:17:47.640 --> 01:17:48.180
entrance.

01:17:48.239 --> 01:17:51.000
Clay and Sonny stood there, both of them

01:17:51.000 --> 01:17:52.800
breathing heavily, as though they'd been

01:17:52.800 --> 01:17:53.340
running.

01:17:53.399 --> 01:17:54.960
Feasting.

01:17:55.020 --> 01:17:57.659
Dark stalker said, pointing at clay.

01:17:57.779 --> 01:17:59.640
And rainbows.

01:17:59.699 --> 01:18:02.159
He pointed at Sonny and grinned.

01:18:02.220 --> 01:18:04.739
Step away.

01:18:04.800 --> 01:18:06.180
From my students.

01:18:06.239 --> 01:18:08.100
Sonny hissed.

01:18:08.159 --> 01:18:09.779
Sonny!

01:18:09.899 --> 01:18:12.359
Dark Stalker cried, with enormous

01:18:12.359 --> 01:18:12.779
delight.

01:18:12.840 --> 01:18:15.060
He swooped down to land facing her.

01:18:15.119 --> 01:18:18.119
It was so tiny for such a shaker of

01:18:18.119 --> 01:18:18.479
worlds.

01:18:18.539 --> 01:18:20.340
Don't you know who I am?

01:18:20.460 --> 01:18:21.960
I do.

01:18:22.020 --> 01:18:24.899
You're the dark stalker, she said.

01:18:24.960 --> 01:18:27.840
It's just dark stalker.

01:18:27.899 --> 01:18:29.039
He corrected her.

01:18:29.100 --> 01:18:31.979
Not sure where this the came from.

01:18:32.039 --> 01:18:33.779
That makes me sound like some kind of

01:18:33.779 --> 01:18:35.699
lurking Kraken type monster.

01:18:35.760 --> 01:18:37.560
Clay cleared his throat.

01:18:37.619 --> 01:18:42.119
Isn't that, um, kind of what you are?

01:18:42.180 --> 01:18:46.439
Not at all, Dark Stalker said with a

01:18:46.439 --> 01:18:46.680
laugh.

01:18:46.739 --> 01:18:48.359
Sonny, get this.

01:18:48.420 --> 01:18:51.600
I'm your great, great, great, great

01:18:51.600 --> 01:18:52.020
great.

01:18:52.079 --> 01:18:55.199
Okay, I'm losing count many greats.

01:18:55.260 --> 01:18:56.100
Great uncle.

01:18:56.220 --> 01:18:57.420
He bowed.

01:18:57.539 --> 01:18:59.279
Surprise.

01:18:59.340 --> 01:19:01.680
More funny looking family for you.

01:19:01.800 --> 01:19:04.859
He spread his wings, and Turtle realized

01:19:04.859 --> 01:19:07.380
he had a line of silvery scales against

01:19:07.380 --> 01:19:10.319
the black along the curve under his wings

01:19:10.319 --> 01:19:11.220
where they met his body.

01:19:11.279 --> 01:19:15.060
Those must be from his ice wing father.

01:19:15.119 --> 01:19:19.079
Sonny hesitated, glancing around at all

01:19:19.079 --> 01:19:21.300
the listening dragons, lit by the pink

01:19:21.300 --> 01:19:22.739
orange sunrise sky.

01:19:22.800 --> 01:19:25.979
The 3 night wings stood close together on

01:19:25.979 --> 01:19:27.899
the ledge where Dark Stalker had put them

01:19:27.899 --> 01:19:29.760
shivering, but unharmed.

01:19:29.819 --> 01:19:32.880
Overhead, the sunlight glinted off the

01:19:32.880 --> 01:19:35.579
scales of turtles' companions, winter's

01:19:35.579 --> 01:19:38.699
bright white, Kibley's pale yellow, and

01:19:38.699 --> 01:19:40.199
peril's fiery copper.

01:19:40.260 --> 01:19:43.380
Moon landed beside Sonny, and they

01:19:43.380 --> 01:19:45.300
brushed wings for a moment, each

01:19:45.300 --> 01:19:46.739
reassuring the other silently.

01:19:46.859 --> 01:19:49.560
Turtle wished he could read minds like

01:19:49.560 --> 01:19:50.039
Moon did.

01:19:50.100 --> 01:19:52.619
What did Sonny think of Dark Stalker?

01:19:52.680 --> 01:19:54.840
She'd obviously prepared to defend her

01:19:54.840 --> 01:19:57.779
students from a monster, only to find a

01:19:57.779 --> 01:19:59.399
charming relative instead.

01:19:59.399 --> 01:20:03.000
Beside him in the library window, tsunami

01:20:03.000 --> 01:20:04.979
was lashing her tail, as though she

01:20:04.979 --> 01:20:06.300
couldn't decide whether to go out and

01:20:06.300 --> 01:20:07.260
attack him or not.

01:20:07.260 --> 01:20:09.059
Uncle?

01:20:09.119 --> 01:20:11.039
Sonny asked dark stalker.

01:20:11.100 --> 01:20:12.180
Really?

01:20:12.239 --> 01:20:15.840
Great, Uncle Dog Stalker.

01:20:15.960 --> 01:20:18.359
The huge night wing shook his head

01:20:18.359 --> 01:20:19.079
chuckling.

01:20:19.140 --> 01:20:21.060
That sounds so weird.

01:20:21.119 --> 01:20:23.520
Like I'm a 1000 years old.

01:20:23.579 --> 01:20:26.460
I mean, I know I'm technically ancient.

01:20:26.520 --> 01:20:28.439
But I sure don't feel that way.

01:20:28.500 --> 01:20:31.739
Did Whiteout end up marrying that glass

01:20:31.739 --> 01:20:33.359
blowing dragon with the spectacles?

01:20:33.420 --> 01:20:35.460
I'll have to ask Starflight.

01:20:35.520 --> 01:20:36.359
I bet he knows.

01:20:36.420 --> 01:20:37.500
Sonny.

01:20:37.560 --> 01:20:39.479
You have my sister's eyes.

01:20:39.539 --> 01:20:43.020
Hers were bluer, of course, not so green

01:20:43.020 --> 01:20:44.100
but the same shape.

01:20:44.159 --> 01:20:46.140
You would have loved her.

01:20:46.199 --> 01:20:48.239
How can you say that?

01:20:48.239 --> 01:20:49.979
Sonny asked.

01:20:50.039 --> 01:20:50.640
You don't know me.

01:20:50.760 --> 01:20:54.539
Of course I do, said Dark Stalker.

01:20:54.600 --> 01:20:56.640
I can read your mind and see your

01:20:56.640 --> 01:20:57.659
futures.

01:20:57.720 --> 01:20:57.960
Remember?

01:20:58.020 --> 01:21:00.300
I woke up several months ago.

01:21:00.359 --> 01:21:04.260
To find myself under a mountain, and 20

01:21:04.260 --> 01:21:07.140
centuries older than I was, when my

01:21:07.140 --> 01:21:08.100
friends betrayed me.

01:21:08.159 --> 01:21:11.699
Since then, I've had nothing to do except

01:21:11.699 --> 01:21:14.340
read all your minds, and dream of

01:21:14.340 --> 01:21:14.760
freedom.

01:21:14.819 --> 01:21:17.460
All our minds?

01:21:17.520 --> 01:21:18.420
Clay asked.

01:21:18.479 --> 01:21:21.899
That's kind of nosy, isn't it?

01:21:21.960 --> 01:21:25.319
Literally, nothing else to do.

01:21:25.439 --> 01:21:28.199
Dark Stalker said apologetically.

01:21:28.260 --> 01:21:30.000
But don't worry, Clay.

01:21:30.060 --> 01:21:32.159
Your thoughts are all very sweet.

01:21:32.159 --> 01:21:35.399
Especially when it comes to certain

01:21:35.399 --> 01:21:36.300
dragons.

01:21:36.359 --> 01:21:39.359
He winked, and Clay managed to look

01:21:39.359 --> 01:21:42.180
embarrassed, alarmed and confused all at

01:21:42.180 --> 01:21:42.600
the same time.

01:21:42.659 --> 01:21:46.500
But wait, what makes you think we are

01:21:46.500 --> 01:21:48.000
related, Sonny asked.

01:21:48.119 --> 01:21:51.119
Your father's a night wing animus.

01:21:51.180 --> 01:21:52.859
Dark Stalker pointed out.

01:21:52.920 --> 01:21:56.220
So he must be descended from me or

01:21:56.220 --> 01:21:56.819
Whiteout.

01:21:56.880 --> 01:21:59.340
And I know I didn't have any

01:21:59.340 --> 01:22:00.000
dragonheads.

01:22:00.060 --> 01:22:02.340
Although I was supposed to.

01:22:02.460 --> 01:22:05.579
He caught a fragment of cloud between his

01:22:05.579 --> 01:22:07.979
talons and watched it fade into empty

01:22:07.979 --> 01:22:08.220
air.

01:22:08.279 --> 01:22:14.699
So, your sister, White Out, was my great

01:22:14.699 --> 01:22:16.500
great, great something great's

01:22:16.500 --> 01:22:18.539
grandmother, Sonny asked.

01:22:18.659 --> 01:22:21.960
She must have been, Dark Stalker said

01:22:22.020 --> 01:22:22.920
shaking himself.

01:22:22.979 --> 01:22:25.199
But there's so much I don't know.

01:22:25.260 --> 01:22:28.380
All my friends and family are gone

01:22:28.380 --> 01:22:28.619
sonny.

01:22:28.739 --> 01:22:31.619
I miss them, and I have no idea what

01:22:31.619 --> 01:22:32.159
happened to them.

01:22:32.220 --> 01:22:35.039
So I've asked Starflight to find some

01:22:35.039 --> 01:22:35.880
scrolls for me.

01:22:35.939 --> 01:22:38.939
Just to fill in the gaps and answer my

01:22:38.939 --> 01:22:39.239
questions.

01:22:39.300 --> 01:22:41.159
I hope that's all right.

01:22:41.220 --> 01:22:44.279
He smiled, but his eyes were sad.

01:22:44.340 --> 01:22:46.979
Turtle glanced over his shoulder.

01:22:47.039 --> 01:22:49.380
Starflight was hurrying around the

01:22:49.380 --> 01:22:51.600
library, pulling out scrolls and putting

01:22:51.600 --> 01:22:53.880
them back, checking their titles with his

01:22:53.880 --> 01:22:54.300
claws.

01:22:54.359 --> 01:22:57.000
He kept slipping on the loose scrolls and

01:22:57.000 --> 01:22:57.600
catching himself.

01:22:57.659 --> 01:23:00.539
Every once in a while, he paused, and

01:23:00.539 --> 01:23:02.579
gave a scroll to fate speaker, who wrote

01:23:02.579 --> 01:23:04.380
the title down on a slate.

01:23:04.439 --> 01:23:08.039
Maybe this really is all dark stalker

01:23:08.039 --> 01:23:08.460
once.

01:23:08.520 --> 01:23:09.539
Turtle thought.

01:23:09.600 --> 01:23:12.300
A few answers about what happened all

01:23:12.300 --> 01:23:13.380
those 100s of years ago.

01:23:13.439 --> 01:23:16.739
Maybe he's as friendly and harmless as he

01:23:16.739 --> 01:23:16.979
seems.

01:23:17.100 --> 01:23:22.619
And yet, and yet, the way he'd looked at

01:23:22.619 --> 01:23:25.260
turtle in winter, that flash of darkness

01:23:25.260 --> 01:23:27.479
deep inside him, peering out.

01:23:27.600 --> 01:23:30.479
Not to mention the ominous prophecy, of

01:23:30.479 --> 01:23:30.659
course.

01:23:30.659 --> 01:23:33.539
Turtle touched the pout that rested

01:23:33.539 --> 01:23:34.140
against his heart.

01:23:34.199 --> 01:23:36.060
Don't be noticed.

01:23:36.119 --> 01:23:38.939
He would stay hidden until he was

01:23:38.939 --> 01:23:40.979
absolutely positively sure it was safe.

01:23:41.100 --> 01:23:43.619
Dark stalker!

01:23:43.739 --> 01:23:46.859
A voice called from above, a peal of

01:23:46.859 --> 01:23:48.659
thunder boomed off the clouds like an

01:23:48.659 --> 01:23:49.079
echo.

01:23:49.140 --> 01:23:52.500
Turtle looked outside again and up, just

01:23:52.500 --> 01:23:54.600
like everyone else, including Dark

01:23:54.600 --> 01:23:55.079
Stalker.

01:23:55.140 --> 01:23:58.500
Lightning flashed, illuminating the

01:23:58.500 --> 01:24:00.779
outline of a dragon against a sky that

01:24:00.779 --> 01:24:02.760
was suddenly and rapidly getting darker.

01:24:02.819 --> 01:24:06.119
She spread her front talons, and wind

01:24:06.119 --> 01:24:08.340
rushed up behind her with a howling force

01:24:08.340 --> 01:24:11.039
that made even the giant night wing

01:24:11.039 --> 01:24:12.359
stagger back a few paces.

01:24:12.420 --> 01:24:15.000
Her wings twitched, and the thunder

01:24:15.000 --> 01:24:18.420
rolled again, louder and closer, and more

01:24:18.420 --> 01:24:19.380
menacing than before.

01:24:19.439 --> 01:24:22.739
Dark Stalker gathered his wings and

01:24:22.739 --> 01:24:24.840
planted his feet, watching the dragon

01:24:24.840 --> 01:24:25.500
overhead.

01:24:25.560 --> 01:24:28.560
A slow smile spread across his face.

01:24:28.920 --> 01:24:31.739
Anemone, he said.

01:24:31.800 --> 01:24:35.460
Just the dragon I was looking for.

01:24:35.520 --> 01:24:40.020
Chapter 4.

01:24:40.439 --> 01:24:43.020
Oh, no.

01:24:43.079 --> 01:24:44.819
Turtle breathed.

01:24:44.880 --> 01:24:46.260
Me?

01:24:46.319 --> 01:24:49.680
Anemone echoed. sounding as young as she

01:24:49.680 --> 01:24:51.899
was and heartbreakingly delighted.

01:24:51.960 --> 01:24:54.000
She flicked her claws to make the

01:24:54.000 --> 01:24:55.020
lightning flash again.

01:24:55.079 --> 01:24:56.699
Now illuminating her face.

01:24:56.760 --> 01:24:59.159
You were looking for me?

01:24:59.279 --> 01:25:02.760
And you made it more than easy for him to

01:25:02.760 --> 01:25:03.420
find you.

01:25:03.479 --> 01:25:04.560
Turtle thought.

01:25:04.619 --> 01:25:07.500
Not to mention announcing your power to

01:25:07.500 --> 01:25:09.899
everyone else who didn't know the sea

01:25:09.899 --> 01:25:11.279
wings have an animus.

01:25:11.340 --> 01:25:14.760
Now, every tribe in Pyria would know

01:25:14.760 --> 01:25:15.899
about anemones magic.

01:25:16.020 --> 01:25:18.779
Apart from all the dragons outside.

01:25:18.840 --> 01:25:20.760
He could see faces watching from nearly

01:25:20.760 --> 01:25:21.899
every window in the school.

01:25:21.960 --> 01:25:25.260
Students roused from their beds, either

01:25:25.260 --> 01:25:27.539
by the commotion outside, or by the

01:25:27.539 --> 01:25:28.560
panicked ice wings.

01:25:28.619 --> 01:25:30.899
Oh, anemone.

01:25:30.960 --> 01:25:33.659
Why would anyone ever draw so much

01:25:33.659 --> 01:25:34.680
attention to themselves?

01:25:34.739 --> 01:25:39.420
Tsunami snapped her tail, hissing, What

01:25:39.420 --> 01:25:40.319
is she doing?

01:25:40.380 --> 01:25:41.760
She cried.

01:25:41.819 --> 01:25:43.439
Before Turtle could answer.

01:25:43.500 --> 01:25:46.380
Not that he had any sort of answer, unless

01:25:46.380 --> 01:25:48.659
maybe losing her mind counted.

01:25:48.720 --> 01:25:51.420
Tsunami was out the window and flying up

01:25:51.420 --> 01:25:52.380
toward anemone.

01:25:52.439 --> 01:25:56.220
One moment, big sister, Anemone said

01:25:56.220 --> 01:25:57.659
holding out her talons.

01:25:57.720 --> 01:26:01.020
The wind spiraled up and around, spinning

01:26:01.020 --> 01:26:02.100
tsunami away from her.

01:26:02.100 --> 01:26:05.159
Below them, Clay and Sonny both started

01:26:05.159 --> 01:26:07.859
forward with a gasp, but tsunami caught

01:26:07.859 --> 01:26:10.140
herself on the 2nd spin and hovered where

01:26:10.140 --> 01:26:10.439
she was.

01:26:10.500 --> 01:26:13.199
Why were you looking for me?

01:26:13.260 --> 01:26:15.600
Anemone asked Dark Stalker.

01:26:15.659 --> 01:26:20.579
Because I sense to kindred spirit. he

01:26:20.579 --> 01:26:23.100
said, gesturing at the storm rising

01:26:23.100 --> 01:26:23.819
around her.

01:26:23.819 --> 01:26:26.100
I've been listening to your mind since

01:26:26.100 --> 01:26:27.420
you arrived at Jade Mountain.

01:26:27.479 --> 01:26:30.720
And I saw instantly how special you are.

01:26:30.779 --> 01:26:34.319
A dragon, as smart and practical as I am

01:26:34.319 --> 01:26:37.680
and of course, a fellow animus.

01:26:37.739 --> 01:26:40.920
Did he know about me before I hid

01:26:40.920 --> 01:26:41.279
myself?

01:26:41.340 --> 01:26:42.899
Turtle wondered.

01:26:42.960 --> 01:26:47.100
Only Winter, Kibli, Peril, and Moon knew

01:26:47.100 --> 01:26:49.380
about his anima's power, but neither

01:26:49.380 --> 01:26:52.260
peril nor moon wore skyfire to protect

01:26:52.260 --> 01:26:52.859
their thoughts.

01:26:52.920 --> 01:26:55.319
Dark Stalker could have lifted that

01:26:55.319 --> 01:26:57.000
information from either of their minds.

01:26:57.060 --> 01:26:59.579
Or he could have seen it in a vision of

01:26:59.579 --> 01:27:00.000
the future.

01:27:00.060 --> 01:27:02.880
If there was a crazy future where Turtle

01:27:02.880 --> 01:27:03.960
used magic in front of him.

01:27:04.020 --> 01:27:05.760
That's me.

01:27:05.819 --> 01:27:08.880
Anemone said, lifting her front claws

01:27:08.880 --> 01:27:09.420
into the air.

01:27:09.479 --> 01:27:12.119
Lightning sizzled down from the clouds

01:27:12.119 --> 01:27:14.579
and gathered in her webbed talons like

01:27:14.579 --> 01:27:15.840
deadly trapped moons.

01:27:15.899 --> 01:27:18.899
The light gave her face an eerie glow

01:27:18.899 --> 01:27:22.079
shining over her scales, like an aquatic

01:27:22.079 --> 01:27:24.539
birthmark, making sure everyone could see

01:27:24.539 --> 01:27:25.920
how different she was.

01:27:25.979 --> 01:27:29.640
Finally, someone who understands me.

01:27:29.699 --> 01:27:34.319
Anemone, tsunami said, her voice

01:27:34.319 --> 01:27:34.920
cracking.

01:27:34.979 --> 01:27:39.539
Oh, I know you love me, Anemone said to

01:27:39.539 --> 01:27:39.720
her.

01:27:39.779 --> 01:27:42.600
Plenty of dragons love me, but

01:27:42.600 --> 01:27:43.380
understanding me?

01:27:43.439 --> 01:27:46.920
See, that takes another animus.

01:27:46.979 --> 01:27:51.119
I'm not sure it does, Turtle thought.

01:27:51.180 --> 01:27:53.039
He'd never felt further from

01:27:53.039 --> 01:27:54.899
understanding her than he did right this

01:27:54.899 --> 01:27:55.319
moment.

01:27:55.380 --> 01:27:59.279
I did this all wrong, like I always do.

01:27:59.340 --> 01:28:01.680
I should have told her the truth about me

01:28:01.680 --> 01:28:03.659
or I should have lied about Dark

01:28:03.659 --> 01:28:04.260
Stalker.

01:28:04.319 --> 01:28:06.239
I should have come up with something that

01:28:06.239 --> 01:28:07.800
could have stopped this from happening.

01:28:07.859 --> 01:28:11.819
I'm very impressed, anemone.

01:28:11.880 --> 01:28:14.880
Dark Stalker said, spreading his wings at

01:28:14.880 --> 01:28:16.739
the churning stone colored sky.

01:28:16.800 --> 01:28:19.859
You know, I've never tried controlling

01:28:19.859 --> 01:28:20.159
the weather.

01:28:20.279 --> 01:28:21.899
What a clever idea.

01:28:21.960 --> 01:28:23.880
What did you enchant?

01:28:23.939 --> 01:28:27.359
Dark clouds now blotted out the sunrise

01:28:27.359 --> 01:28:29.279
bloated with rain that was forbidden to

01:28:29.279 --> 01:28:29.520
fall.

01:28:29.579 --> 01:28:32.579
Small flickers of lightning curled in the

01:28:32.579 --> 01:28:34.859
depths of the clouds, like the breath of

01:28:34.859 --> 01:28:37.979
newly hatched sky wings, the air smelled

01:28:37.979 --> 01:28:40.439
like the sea was hiding overhead, ready

01:28:40.439 --> 01:28:41.399
to drown everyone.

01:28:41.520 --> 01:28:46.380
These, anemones said, displaying 2 beaten

01:28:46.380 --> 01:28:48.840
copper armbands on her wrists, the metal

01:28:48.840 --> 01:28:50.460
rippling like waves of fire.

01:28:50.520 --> 01:28:52.739
I wanted you to see what I could do.

01:28:52.800 --> 01:28:54.420
She said proudly.

01:28:54.539 --> 01:28:57.779
But anemone, tsunami choked out.

01:28:57.840 --> 01:28:59.159
Your soul.

01:28:59.340 --> 01:29:03.479
I feel fine, tsunami, anemone said

01:29:03.479 --> 01:29:04.619
flicking her tail.

01:29:04.680 --> 01:29:07.979
I mean, we are supposed to use our powers

01:29:07.979 --> 01:29:09.359
sometimes, right?

01:29:09.420 --> 01:29:11.939
She asked Dark Stalker.

01:29:12.000 --> 01:29:14.460
Like, when it's really important, and

01:29:14.460 --> 01:29:16.260
couldn't these be totally useful?

01:29:16.260 --> 01:29:19.319
She reached up again and opened a small

01:29:19.319 --> 01:29:21.420
hole in the clouds for the sun to pour

01:29:21.420 --> 01:29:21.659
through.

01:29:21.720 --> 01:29:23.939
Absolutely.

01:29:24.000 --> 01:29:25.920
Dark Stalker agreed.

01:29:25.979 --> 01:29:27.479
They're brilliant.

01:29:27.539 --> 01:29:29.159
Don't worry, tsunami.

01:29:29.220 --> 01:29:31.380
Anemone is many spells away from

01:29:31.380 --> 01:29:32.399
massacring anyone.

01:29:32.460 --> 01:29:35.220
And now I'm here to help her without soul

01:29:35.220 --> 01:29:35.939
problem.

01:29:36.000 --> 01:29:38.880
Come on down, princess, and let's talk.

01:29:39.000 --> 01:29:42.119
Anemones soared down to him with no

01:29:42.119 --> 01:29:42.960
hesitation.

01:29:43.020 --> 01:29:46.619
Turtle watched her go with the same sick

01:29:46.619 --> 01:29:48.779
sinking feeling that had hit him the day

01:29:48.779 --> 01:29:50.699
he heard his father had been captured by

01:29:50.699 --> 01:29:52.140
Queen Scarlet's troops.

01:29:52.199 --> 01:29:54.300
There's nothing I can do.

01:29:54.359 --> 01:29:58.199
He could feel peril watching him, but he

01:29:58.199 --> 01:29:59.159
couldn't meet her eyes.

01:29:59.220 --> 01:30:01.500
Don't wait for me to fix this.

01:30:01.560 --> 01:30:02.939
I can't.

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:04.619
I don't know where to start.

01:30:04.680 --> 01:30:07.619
And I don't have any good ideas, and

01:30:07.619 --> 01:30:08.399
whatever I tried.

01:30:08.460 --> 01:30:10.079
I do it wrong anyway.

01:30:10.140 --> 01:30:13.859
As Anemone and Dark Stalker stepped into

01:30:13.859 --> 01:30:15.060
the main entrance cave.

01:30:15.119 --> 01:30:18.060
Anemone looked back up at her sister, and

01:30:18.060 --> 01:30:19.500
the other dragon still outside.

01:30:19.560 --> 01:30:21.180
She smiled.

01:30:21.300 --> 01:30:23.220
And the rain began to fall.

01:30:23.279 --> 01:30:28.199
Heavy droplets pelted turtles' wings as

01:30:28.199 --> 01:30:29.579
he flew up to where his friends were

01:30:29.579 --> 01:30:30.420
gathered in the sky.

01:30:30.479 --> 01:30:34.439
I'm sorry, he said, as soon as he was

01:30:34.439 --> 01:30:35.100
close enough to speak.

01:30:35.159 --> 01:30:38.880
I did try to warn the school, but I guess

01:30:38.880 --> 01:30:39.840
it didn't make any difference.

01:30:39.899 --> 01:30:42.359
Warn the school about what?

01:30:42.420 --> 01:30:43.560
Winter asked.

01:30:43.619 --> 01:30:49.020
The giant 2000-year-old super dragon that

01:30:49.020 --> 01:30:50.220
just climbed out of a mountain?

01:30:50.340 --> 01:30:51.600
Turtle answered.

01:30:51.659 --> 01:30:54.779
Oh, he's not here to hurt anyone, said

01:30:54.779 --> 01:30:55.260
Winter.

01:30:55.319 --> 01:30:56.220
I know.

01:30:56.279 --> 01:30:58.739
I was worried at 1st too, but dark

01:30:58.739 --> 01:30:59.880
stalker's not a monster.

01:30:59.939 --> 01:31:01.859
He just wants to make friends and start

01:31:01.859 --> 01:31:02.159
over.

01:31:02.220 --> 01:31:08.279
See, I feel like that's true, said Kibley

01:31:08.279 --> 01:31:10.680
but then winter, of all dragons, says

01:31:10.680 --> 01:31:12.960
something like that, and I get nervous.

01:31:13.020 --> 01:31:16.319
Cut off the exploding gets plan, turtle.

01:31:16.380 --> 01:31:19.140
Pearl called cheerfully, swooping around

01:31:19.140 --> 01:31:21.239
them with their wings, carving paths of

01:31:21.239 --> 01:31:22.800
steam through the pelting rain.

01:31:22.920 --> 01:31:24.539
He's not evil after all.

01:31:24.600 --> 01:31:27.600
Wait, really?

01:31:27.659 --> 01:31:30.300
Turtle tried to blink away the rain that

01:31:30.300 --> 01:31:31.619
kept pulling on his snout.

01:31:31.680 --> 01:31:33.239
Are we sure?

01:31:33.300 --> 01:31:35.460
What happened to change your mind so

01:31:35.460 --> 01:31:35.760
fast?

01:31:35.819 --> 01:31:39.539
Well, he's been super nice to me, said

01:31:39.539 --> 01:31:41.579
Pearl, which kind of never happens.

01:31:41.640 --> 01:31:44.100
So he's obviously more awesome than the

01:31:44.100 --> 01:31:45.000
average dragon.

01:31:45.060 --> 01:31:47.880
And he pointed out that animus powers and

01:31:47.880 --> 01:31:50.460
fire scales are the same, because other

01:31:50.460 --> 01:31:52.380
dragons are always scared of us, but they

01:31:52.380 --> 01:31:54.720
shouldn't be, totally true, right?

01:31:54.779 --> 01:31:57.840
I mean, I wouldn't want my insides

01:31:57.840 --> 01:31:59.819
exploded by magic just because someone

01:31:59.819 --> 01:32:01.979
thinks, I'm scary.

01:32:02.039 --> 01:32:03.840
You are scary.

01:32:03.899 --> 01:32:05.279
Kibli said to her.

01:32:05.340 --> 01:32:07.500
But I'm also in favor of you staying in

01:32:07.500 --> 01:32:07.859
one piece.

01:32:07.979 --> 01:32:11.640
Why, thank you, she said, pleased.

01:32:11.699 --> 01:32:13.140
So it makes sense, right?

01:32:13.260 --> 01:32:13.859
Turtle?

01:32:13.920 --> 01:32:16.020
If we deserve a chance to prove ourselves

01:32:16.020 --> 01:32:18.359
good, then why doesn't Darkstalker?

01:32:18.420 --> 01:32:21.180
That's right, said Kibli.

01:32:21.239 --> 01:32:22.199
That's a good point.

01:32:22.260 --> 01:32:25.439
But didn't he already have that chance?

01:32:25.500 --> 01:32:26.699
Turtle asked.

01:32:26.760 --> 01:32:29.220
And didn't it end with killing his own

01:32:29.220 --> 01:32:29.520
father?

01:32:29.579 --> 01:32:31.500
Oh.

01:32:31.560 --> 01:32:33.420
That's a good point too.

01:32:33.479 --> 01:32:36.420
Kibley scrunched his eyes shut, as though

01:32:36.420 --> 01:32:37.079
his head hurt.

01:32:37.140 --> 01:32:39.720
My brain feels like it's trying to swim

01:32:39.720 --> 01:32:40.500
through honey.

01:32:40.560 --> 01:32:43.920
That father business is ancient history

01:32:44.039 --> 01:32:45.060
said Winter.

01:32:45.119 --> 01:32:46.739
We don't know exactly what happened.

01:32:46.800 --> 01:32:49.140
I'm sure he has a good explanation.

01:32:49.260 --> 01:32:52.199
Me too, said Pearl.

01:32:52.260 --> 01:32:54.180
So we're all.

01:32:54.180 --> 01:32:57.420
We're not worried anymore, said Turtle.

01:32:57.479 --> 01:33:00.960
Welcome back, Dark Stalker, carry on.

01:33:01.020 --> 01:33:02.699
Do all the magic you'd like.

01:33:02.760 --> 01:33:05.520
You just need to spend a little time with

01:33:05.520 --> 01:33:06.420
him and you'll see.

01:33:06.479 --> 01:33:07.560
Winter said.

01:33:07.680 --> 01:33:09.119
Are we done with this boring

01:33:09.119 --> 01:33:09.659
conversation?

01:33:09.720 --> 01:33:12.000
I'd like to go get dry, if you please.

01:33:12.060 --> 01:33:14.760
He shook off his wings and dove toward

01:33:14.760 --> 01:33:16.560
the caves without waiting for an answer.

01:33:16.680 --> 01:33:20.399
Never tell him I said this, said Pearl

01:33:20.399 --> 01:33:22.619
but I agree with a chili prince.

01:33:22.680 --> 01:33:24.779
Off with your hiding spell, turtle, and

01:33:24.779 --> 01:33:25.979
onward with your face.

01:33:26.039 --> 01:33:29.039
She gestured toward Turtle's pouch, and

01:33:29.039 --> 01:33:31.020
he shied away from her. covering it with

01:33:31.020 --> 01:33:31.500
his talons.

01:33:31.619 --> 01:33:35.220
Or you can keep skulking around, she said

01:33:35.220 --> 01:33:36.960
with a shrug, whatever you want.

01:33:37.020 --> 01:33:39.119
I'm going to go say hi to Clay.

01:33:39.180 --> 01:33:41.819
I mean, to uh, him and his friends.

01:33:41.880 --> 01:33:43.800
So I can tell him what I did to Scarlet.

01:33:43.859 --> 01:33:45.659
I mean, tell all of them.

01:33:45.720 --> 01:33:48.659
What Ruby did, technically, but with my

01:33:48.659 --> 01:33:48.899
help.

01:33:49.020 --> 01:33:51.180
He's going to be so excited, don't you

01:33:51.180 --> 01:33:51.420
think?

01:33:51.479 --> 01:33:52.560
So excited.

01:33:52.619 --> 01:33:55.020
I mean, not that it's any big deal.

01:33:55.079 --> 01:33:57.960
Well, I guess it's kind of a big deal

01:33:57.960 --> 01:34:00.600
that I stopped his like super worst enemy

01:34:00.600 --> 01:34:01.619
from coming after him.

01:34:01.680 --> 01:34:04.020
He'll be happy about that, right?

01:34:04.140 --> 01:34:05.640
Not that it matters.

01:34:05.699 --> 01:34:06.899
Why am I nervous?

01:34:06.960 --> 01:34:08.640
I'm not.

01:34:08.699 --> 01:34:10.500
Stop being nervous, Parel.

01:34:10.560 --> 01:34:11.579
Ha ha.

01:34:11.640 --> 01:34:12.539
That'll work.

01:34:12.600 --> 01:34:14.340
Three moons.

01:34:14.399 --> 01:34:16.739
Just go talk to him, you unexpected

01:34:16.739 --> 01:34:17.399
flutterhead.

01:34:17.520 --> 01:34:19.140
Kibley said with a laugh.

01:34:19.199 --> 01:34:20.340
I will.

01:34:20.399 --> 01:34:22.140
I'm going, peril said.

01:34:22.199 --> 01:34:24.899
Don't wish me luck because I don't even

01:34:24.899 --> 01:34:26.460
need it, because why would I?

01:34:26.520 --> 01:34:27.539
Because who cares?

01:34:27.659 --> 01:34:30.239
She shook herself from horns to tail.

01:34:30.300 --> 01:34:32.819
Wipe to raindrops off her snout and

01:34:32.819 --> 01:34:33.960
spiral down to the school.

01:34:34.020 --> 01:34:37.380
Wow, said Kibley.

01:34:37.439 --> 01:34:39.720
Am I like that around Moon?

01:34:39.779 --> 01:34:41.399
Are you?

01:34:41.460 --> 01:34:43.920
Turtle asked. only half listening.

01:34:43.979 --> 01:34:46.439
Peril did seem like the kind of dragon

01:34:46.439 --> 01:34:47.939
who could change her mind about someone

01:34:47.939 --> 01:34:49.199
at a moment's notice.

01:34:49.260 --> 01:34:51.180
So maybe this was normal.

01:34:51.239 --> 01:34:54.000
And maybe Dark Stalker was as great as

01:34:54.000 --> 01:34:56.340
they all thought, and Turtle was wrong to

01:34:56.340 --> 01:34:57.060
be so anxious.

01:34:57.119 --> 01:34:59.100
But something didn't feel right.

01:34:59.159 --> 01:35:01.079
Just kidding.

01:35:01.140 --> 01:35:03.899
Kibley said quickly, forget I said that.

01:35:03.960 --> 01:35:05.460
Um, turtle.

01:35:05.520 --> 01:35:08.640
I think actually, don't unhide yourself

01:35:08.640 --> 01:35:09.000
yet.

01:35:09.060 --> 01:35:10.680
Really?

01:35:10.739 --> 01:35:13.199
Turtle twisted toward him in the air.

01:35:13.260 --> 01:35:16.260
Raindrops kept splashing in his eyes and

01:35:16.260 --> 01:35:17.819
making it hard to see.

01:35:17.880 --> 01:35:20.220
It felt as if the clouds were gathering

01:35:20.220 --> 01:35:23.159
lower and lower, as though they might all

01:35:23.159 --> 01:35:25.500
pile on top of his wings at any moment.

01:35:25.560 --> 01:35:29.460
My instincts tell me I can trust Dark

01:35:29.460 --> 01:35:31.319
Stalker, Kibley said.

01:35:31.380 --> 01:35:34.140
Tilting his claws to watch the raindrops

01:35:34.140 --> 01:35:35.279
side in different directions.

01:35:35.340 --> 01:35:38.460
But my head says to be more careful.

01:35:38.520 --> 01:35:41.819
So maybe it's smart to have one dragon

01:35:41.819 --> 01:35:44.039
who can watch him without being seen for

01:35:44.039 --> 01:35:44.699
a little while.

01:35:44.760 --> 01:35:45.840
Can you do that?

01:35:45.899 --> 01:35:48.479
Watch him, and then tell me what you

01:35:48.479 --> 01:35:48.659
see.

01:35:48.779 --> 01:35:50.880
I guess.

01:35:50.939 --> 01:35:53.819
Turtle tugged the webs between his talons

01:35:53.819 --> 01:35:54.420
nervously.

01:35:54.479 --> 01:35:56.279
But like what?

01:35:56.340 --> 01:35:57.840
What if I missed something?

01:35:57.899 --> 01:35:59.699
What am I looking for?

01:35:59.760 --> 01:36:03.000
I don't know, Kibley admitted.

01:36:03.060 --> 01:36:05.340
But whatever you see, come talk to me

01:36:05.340 --> 01:36:06.060
about it, all right?

01:36:06.119 --> 01:36:07.859
We'll figure it out together.

01:36:07.920 --> 01:36:09.779
All right.

01:36:09.899 --> 01:36:11.880
Turtle said uncomfortably.

01:36:11.939 --> 01:36:14.520
He stayed in the air for a moment as

01:36:14.520 --> 01:36:15.600
Kibley flew away.

01:36:15.659 --> 01:36:18.359
At least I'm not the only one who's

01:36:18.359 --> 01:36:18.659
worried.

01:36:18.779 --> 01:36:21.180
But he couldn't shake the dread that

01:36:21.180 --> 01:36:22.260
crept along his wings.

01:36:22.319 --> 01:36:25.140
It was a lot of pressure, being the one

01:36:25.140 --> 01:36:27.300
who had to keep an eye on Dark Stalker

01:36:27.300 --> 01:36:29.340
being the only one who could, really.

01:36:29.460 --> 01:36:32.340
He didn't like the feeling that Kibley

01:36:32.340 --> 01:36:33.239
was relying on him.

01:36:33.300 --> 01:36:36.060
I don't want to be the spy.

01:36:36.119 --> 01:36:38.279
In all the stories.

01:36:38.460 --> 01:36:40.739
Spies are competent, and quick thinking

01:36:40.739 --> 01:36:43.079
and clever, and I'm none of those things

01:36:43.079 --> 01:36:46.199
or else they're incompetent, and then

01:36:46.199 --> 01:36:48.119
they get caught, and their part of the

01:36:48.119 --> 01:36:50.579
story ends in a dungeon, or a quick

01:36:50.579 --> 01:36:50.939
death.

01:36:51.000 --> 01:36:53.880
Not exactly the character arc I was

01:36:53.880 --> 01:36:54.180
hoping for.

01:36:54.239 --> 01:36:56.640
I'm not the right dragon for this.

01:36:56.760 --> 01:37:00.479
He followed his friends slowly, listening

01:37:00.479 --> 01:37:02.939
to the thunder roll overhead, and

01:37:02.939 --> 01:37:04.800
wondering where the lightning would

01:37:04.800 --> 01:37:05.340
strike.

01:37:05.399 --> 01:37:09.479
Chapter 5.

01:37:09.840 --> 01:37:14.220
Inside the main entrance cave, Turtle

01:37:14.220 --> 01:37:16.079
crept around the small groups of gathered

01:37:16.079 --> 01:37:18.239
dragons until he was huddled behind the

01:37:18.239 --> 01:37:19.199
bronze gong.

01:37:19.260 --> 01:37:20.760
Nobody noticed him.

01:37:20.819 --> 01:37:23.399
He'd perfected the art of moving slowly

01:37:23.399 --> 01:37:25.979
of being boring and forgettable and

01:37:25.979 --> 01:37:28.619
ordinary, and it certainly helped that

01:37:28.619 --> 01:37:31.199
everyone had a much bigger, flashier

01:37:31.199 --> 01:37:32.640
dragon on their minds at the moment.

01:37:32.699 --> 01:37:35.699
It's such a vague threat.

01:37:35.760 --> 01:37:39.060
Dog stalker was saying to anemone, as

01:37:39.060 --> 01:37:40.739
turtle curled into his hiding spot.

01:37:40.800 --> 01:37:44.159
I mean, what is a soul?

01:37:44.220 --> 01:37:46.680
How do you really know if someone's

01:37:46.680 --> 01:37:49.199
losing theirs, or it's going bad, or

01:37:49.199 --> 01:37:50.640
whatever the big danger is supposed to

01:37:50.640 --> 01:37:50.880
be?

01:37:50.939 --> 01:37:54.779
Right, Anemone said, as though she were

01:37:54.779 --> 01:37:56.220
pouncing on a scuttling crab.

01:37:56.279 --> 01:37:58.619
I mean, there haven't been that many

01:37:58.619 --> 01:38:00.659
animus dragons in history, have there?

01:38:00.720 --> 01:38:04.079
What if Albatross was already bad, and it

01:38:04.079 --> 01:38:05.699
had nothing to do with his magic at all?

01:38:05.760 --> 01:38:07.800
Turtles shivered.

01:38:07.859 --> 01:38:09.840
He'd had these thoughts himself.

01:38:09.899 --> 01:38:12.720
Many times, but it was unsettling to hear

01:38:12.720 --> 01:38:13.739
them spoken aloud.

01:38:13.800 --> 01:38:16.739
He wanted to believe that his soul would

01:38:16.739 --> 01:38:18.300
be fine no matter what he did.

01:38:18.359 --> 01:38:20.460
He would still be the one making all the

01:38:20.460 --> 01:38:22.739
choices, good or bad, wouldn't he?

01:38:22.800 --> 01:38:24.479
And he was a good dragon.

01:38:24.539 --> 01:38:27.899
But perfectly nice, harmless dragon, with

01:38:27.899 --> 01:38:29.100
no reason to hurt anyone.

01:38:29.159 --> 01:38:32.279
A plume of blood flickered through his

01:38:32.279 --> 01:38:32.520
memory.

01:38:32.579 --> 01:38:34.680
Was it only 2 days ago?

01:38:34.739 --> 01:38:35.880
Or three?

01:38:35.939 --> 01:38:38.699
He remembered the clammy feeling of mud

01:38:38.699 --> 01:38:40.979
between his talons as they confronted

01:38:40.979 --> 01:38:44.340
that dragon, Perel's father, sore, or

01:38:44.340 --> 01:38:46.979
chameleon, or shapeshifter, the one with

01:38:46.979 --> 01:38:47.579
many names.

01:38:47.640 --> 01:38:50.760
He'd been holding Dark Stalker's scroll

01:38:50.760 --> 01:38:53.220
and Turtle had used animus magic to take

01:38:53.220 --> 01:38:53.640
it from him.

01:38:53.699 --> 01:38:57.479
The truth was, he hadn't just taken the

01:38:57.479 --> 01:38:57.899
scroll.

01:38:57.960 --> 01:39:00.060
He'd attacked Chameleon with it.

01:39:00.119 --> 01:39:02.279
Bashing him in the face and probably

01:39:02.279 --> 01:39:03.239
breaking his nose.

01:39:03.359 --> 01:39:06.420
It was the only violent spell he'd ever

01:39:06.420 --> 01:39:06.840
cast.

01:39:06.899 --> 01:39:10.439
Once more, he noticed his talons were

01:39:10.439 --> 01:39:11.520
clenched against his will.

01:39:11.579 --> 01:39:13.439
And he had to force them straight.

01:39:13.500 --> 01:39:16.020
Deep breaths.

01:39:16.079 --> 01:39:19.020
I am in control of my own self.

01:39:19.079 --> 01:39:21.539
I am not a bad dragon.

01:39:21.600 --> 01:39:24.359
He'd never done anything like that before

01:39:24.359 --> 01:39:25.020
in his life.

01:39:25.079 --> 01:39:27.300
He certainly wouldn't be able to do it

01:39:27.300 --> 01:39:28.199
with his own claws.

01:39:28.260 --> 01:39:29.760
But with magic.

01:39:29.819 --> 01:39:31.260
It was different.

01:39:31.319 --> 01:39:33.479
It didn't feel like he was really hurting

01:39:33.479 --> 01:39:33.960
someone else.

01:39:34.079 --> 01:39:38.579
Except for now, in his memories, where

01:39:38.579 --> 01:39:40.800
the screaming dragon kept appearing over

01:39:40.800 --> 01:39:41.880
and over again.

01:39:42.000 --> 01:39:44.579
But he hurt Kinkachu.

01:39:44.640 --> 01:39:46.439
Turtle reminded himself.

01:39:46.500 --> 01:39:48.180
He put her in a coma.

01:39:48.300 --> 01:39:51.300
He also tricked peril and put a spell on

01:39:51.300 --> 01:39:52.920
her to make her work for Scarlet again.

01:39:52.979 --> 01:39:54.840
He deserved it.

01:39:54.899 --> 01:39:58.619
He brushed his front talons together, as

01:39:58.619 --> 01:40:00.300
though he were wiping off wet sand.

01:40:00.359 --> 01:40:03.420
Was this what it felt like to lose part

01:40:03.420 --> 01:40:04.020
of his soul?

01:40:04.079 --> 01:40:07.140
Was this the 1st step toward darkness?

01:40:07.199 --> 01:40:09.779
He still felt like himself.

01:40:09.840 --> 01:40:13.020
But maybe a slightly more powerful

01:40:13.020 --> 01:40:13.920
version of himself.

01:40:13.979 --> 01:40:15.479
Was that bad?

01:40:15.539 --> 01:40:18.539
I know what you did.

01:40:18.600 --> 01:40:22.260
Dark Stalker rumbled softly, and for a

01:40:22.260 --> 01:40:24.960
moment, Turtle's heart stopped.

01:40:25.020 --> 01:40:26.699
I know what you worry about.

01:40:26.760 --> 01:40:28.619
You do?

01:40:28.680 --> 01:40:30.239
Anemone whispered.

01:40:30.300 --> 01:40:32.880
Turtle peeked out and saw that the cay

01:40:32.880 --> 01:40:33.779
was almost empty now.

01:40:33.840 --> 01:40:37.619
Only dark soccer, anemone, tsunami, and

01:40:37.619 --> 01:40:38.399
moon remained.

01:40:38.460 --> 01:40:42.119
She was protecting us, tsunami said

01:40:42.119 --> 01:40:42.539
quickly.

01:40:42.600 --> 01:40:44.220
She was saving us.

01:40:44.279 --> 01:40:46.560
Turtle felt a flash of panic.

01:40:46.619 --> 01:40:48.539
What did anemone do?

01:40:48.600 --> 01:40:50.159
Something terrible?

01:40:50.220 --> 01:40:51.180
When?

01:40:51.300 --> 01:40:52.680
How did he miss it?

01:40:52.739 --> 01:40:56.159
I agree, said Dark Stalker.

01:40:56.220 --> 01:40:58.319
You shouldn't feel guilty, princess.

01:40:58.439 --> 01:41:02.100
I don't, Anemone said, lifting her chin.

01:41:02.159 --> 01:41:03.600
He deserved it.

01:41:03.659 --> 01:41:06.539
Turtle heard the echo of his own thought

01:41:06.539 --> 01:41:07.680
and winced.

01:41:07.739 --> 01:41:09.420
Who was she talking about?

01:41:09.479 --> 01:41:12.060
But did it change you?

01:41:12.119 --> 01:41:13.560
Tsunami asked.

01:41:13.619 --> 01:41:14.939
Do you feel?

01:41:14.939 --> 01:41:16.380
Soulless?

01:41:16.439 --> 01:41:17.939
Anemone laughed.

01:41:18.000 --> 01:41:19.199
A little too brightly.

01:41:19.260 --> 01:41:20.579
No way.

01:41:20.640 --> 01:41:23.159
I think I have a pretty normal soul for a

01:41:23.159 --> 01:41:23.460
dragon.

01:41:23.579 --> 01:41:26.760
But you won't ever have to worry again.

01:41:26.819 --> 01:41:30.420
If we protect that soul, like I protected

01:41:30.420 --> 01:41:30.600
mine.

01:41:30.659 --> 01:41:33.060
Dark Stalker flicked his tail.

01:41:33.119 --> 01:41:35.640
With a different spell this time though.

01:41:35.699 --> 01:41:38.460
We're going to need something to

01:41:38.460 --> 01:41:39.000
enchant.

01:41:39.060 --> 01:41:42.840
None of my talismans survived the 2000

01:41:42.840 --> 01:41:43.920
years underground with me.

01:41:43.979 --> 01:41:47.520
I can find us something, Anemone said

01:41:47.520 --> 01:41:48.840
jumping to her feet.

01:41:48.899 --> 01:41:50.640
I have some great treasure.

01:41:50.699 --> 01:41:52.800
Mother always gives me the best jewels.

01:41:52.859 --> 01:41:56.579
It doesn't have to be fancy, Dark Stalker

01:41:56.579 --> 01:41:56.760
said.

01:41:56.880 --> 01:41:58.500
It just has to be sturdy.

01:41:58.560 --> 01:42:01.739
So our souls will be safe forever.

01:42:01.859 --> 01:42:03.899
He smiled at Moon.

01:42:03.960 --> 01:42:06.300
I know that would make certain dragons

01:42:06.300 --> 01:42:07.260
here a lot happier.

01:42:07.319 --> 01:42:11.819
I don't know, said Moon, studying him

01:42:11.819 --> 01:42:12.899
with a wary expression.

01:42:12.960 --> 01:42:17.279
Your soul was protected before, and you

01:42:17.279 --> 01:42:18.180
still killed your father.

01:42:18.239 --> 01:42:22.319
Oh, by all the moons, Dark Stalker said

01:42:22.319 --> 01:42:22.920
crossly.

01:42:22.979 --> 01:42:25.800
He reared up, filling the cavern with his

01:42:25.800 --> 01:42:26.460
giant wings.

01:42:26.579 --> 01:42:27.960
Listen.

01:42:28.020 --> 01:42:30.300
Arctic was about to betray the whole

01:42:30.300 --> 01:42:30.779
tribe.

01:42:30.840 --> 01:42:33.840
He was trying to sell my sister to the

01:42:33.840 --> 01:42:36.000
ice wings in exchange for his own

01:42:36.000 --> 01:42:36.300
safety.

01:42:36.420 --> 01:42:39.300
He would have made her marry an ice wing

01:42:39.300 --> 01:42:41.279
and live in their kingdom forever.

01:42:41.340 --> 01:42:44.399
And he was mind controlling her.

01:42:44.460 --> 01:42:47.699
If I hadn't stopped him, Sonny wouldn't

01:42:47.699 --> 01:42:48.060
even exist.

01:42:48.119 --> 01:42:50.399
And maybe the night wings wouldn't

01:42:50.399 --> 01:42:50.640
either.

01:42:50.699 --> 01:42:53.520
Because Arctic was going to help the ice

01:42:53.520 --> 01:42:54.779
wings wipe us out.

01:42:54.840 --> 01:42:57.600
He was a traitor, who had to die.

01:42:57.659 --> 01:43:00.659
Dark Stalker pointed at Moon.

01:43:00.720 --> 01:43:04.260
I was protecting you, and all the tribes

01:43:04.260 --> 01:43:05.279
of future descendants.

01:43:05.340 --> 01:43:08.220
I'm shocked that everyone has completely

01:43:08.220 --> 01:43:09.180
forgotten about that.

01:43:09.239 --> 01:43:12.600
Well, said Moon.

01:43:12.659 --> 01:43:15.420
Watching a dragon disembowel himself

01:43:15.420 --> 01:43:18.239
probably has kind of a traumatizing

01:43:18.239 --> 01:43:19.319
effect on one's memory.

01:43:19.380 --> 01:43:22.020
Wait, what?

01:43:22.020 --> 01:43:23.220
said tsunami.

01:43:23.279 --> 01:43:25.079
Dissum, what now?

01:43:25.140 --> 01:43:27.000
Did you really do that?

01:43:27.119 --> 01:43:28.800
Anemone said.

01:43:28.859 --> 01:43:30.539
Looking up at Dark Stalker.

01:43:30.600 --> 01:43:33.180
But Turtle didn't like her expression.

01:43:33.239 --> 01:43:35.699
There wasn't nearly enough disgust or

01:43:35.699 --> 01:43:36.359
horror there.

01:43:36.420 --> 01:43:38.039
He didn't like it at all.

01:43:38.100 --> 01:43:41.579
Did I say disembowel?

01:43:41.640 --> 01:43:43.859
Dark soccer waved one talon?

01:43:43.920 --> 01:43:45.539
I was exaggerating.

01:43:45.600 --> 01:43:47.819
It was a simple honor suicide.

01:43:47.880 --> 01:43:49.920
Even he knew he deserved it.

01:43:49.979 --> 01:43:53.520
Moon crossed her front talons, arching

01:43:53.520 --> 01:43:54.720
her brows at him skeptically.

01:43:54.840 --> 01:43:58.079
Wow, said Dark Stalker.

01:43:58.140 --> 01:44:00.359
Oh, we sure clear sight didn't have

01:44:00.359 --> 01:44:02.699
dragonets after I was gone, because you

01:44:02.699 --> 01:44:04.560
do an uncanny impression of my true

01:44:04.560 --> 01:44:06.060
love's disapproving phase.

01:44:06.119 --> 01:44:09.779
I'm only trying to make sure you don't

01:44:09.779 --> 01:44:11.579
overuse your power.

01:44:11.640 --> 01:44:14.100
Go crazy and hurt someone, Moon said.

01:44:14.159 --> 01:44:18.060
Moon, Dark Stalker said reproachfully.

01:44:18.119 --> 01:44:20.640
I can see the future, remember?

01:44:20.699 --> 01:44:22.920
I know how to stop myself from doing

01:44:22.920 --> 01:44:23.220
that.

01:44:23.279 --> 01:44:25.619
Do you want me to show you where our

01:44:25.619 --> 01:44:26.460
paths are going?

01:44:26.579 --> 01:44:29.279
He held out one of his talons to her.

01:44:29.340 --> 01:44:32.279
I can take you along the whole timeline

01:44:32.279 --> 01:44:34.079
for the next 100 years.

01:44:34.140 --> 01:44:35.279
If you like.

01:44:35.340 --> 01:44:38.100
His tale nudged her mischievously.

01:44:38.159 --> 01:44:40.680
One to see which one of them you should

01:44:40.680 --> 01:44:40.920
choose.

01:44:40.979 --> 01:44:43.920
I can show you what the future looks like

01:44:43.920 --> 01:44:44.699
with both options.

01:44:44.760 --> 01:44:47.819
Although frankly, I think neither of them

01:44:47.819 --> 01:44:48.539
are good enough for you.

01:44:48.600 --> 01:44:51.479
No, no, no, thank you.

01:44:51.539 --> 01:44:54.239
Moon said quickly, covering her ears.

01:44:54.300 --> 01:44:55.619
I don't want to hear it.

01:44:55.680 --> 01:44:57.779
I have no idea who you're talking about.

01:44:57.840 --> 01:44:59.640
I mean, what you're talking about.

01:44:59.699 --> 01:45:01.500
Stop thinking about them.

01:45:01.560 --> 01:45:03.300
La la la, ignoring you.

01:45:03.359 --> 01:45:06.180
Hey, what about me?

01:45:06.239 --> 01:45:07.920
Anemone interjected.

01:45:07.979 --> 01:45:09.479
I want to see the future.

01:45:09.539 --> 01:45:11.220
Will you show me what's going to happen

01:45:11.220 --> 01:45:11.520
to me?

01:45:11.579 --> 01:45:14.939
Tsunami looked from her sister to Dark

01:45:14.939 --> 01:45:15.600
Stalker.

01:45:15.659 --> 01:45:17.699
Her expression wavering between concern

01:45:17.699 --> 01:45:19.260
and curiosity.

01:45:19.319 --> 01:45:23.279
A vision could show us that anemone turns

01:45:23.279 --> 01:45:23.760
out all right.

01:45:23.819 --> 01:45:25.140
Turtle thought.

01:45:25.199 --> 01:45:27.479
We wouldn't have to worry about her soul

01:45:27.479 --> 01:45:30.000
anymore if we saw a peaceful future ahead

01:45:30.000 --> 01:45:30.359
for her.

01:45:30.479 --> 01:45:34.920
Anything you want, Dark Stalker said

01:45:34.920 --> 01:45:37.319
expanding his wings to their full width.

01:45:37.439 --> 01:45:40.979
You both have so many possible amazing

01:45:40.979 --> 01:45:41.880
futures.

01:45:42.000 --> 01:45:45.600
And now that I'm here, if you trust me, we

01:45:45.600 --> 01:45:47.880
can make sure you get exactly the right

01:45:47.880 --> 01:45:48.779
future for you.

01:45:48.840 --> 01:45:52.079
Anemone's eyes were shining like the

01:45:52.079 --> 01:45:53.159
Skyfire comet.

01:45:53.220 --> 01:45:56.460
Even Turtle couldn't help thinking, It

01:45:56.460 --> 01:45:57.659
would be nice to know my future.

01:45:57.720 --> 01:46:00.359
To have someone who could tell me the

01:46:00.359 --> 01:46:02.640
right steps to follow, to make sure my

01:46:02.640 --> 01:46:05.340
life turns out all right, which spells

01:46:05.340 --> 01:46:07.920
are safe to cast, how to protect myself

01:46:07.920 --> 01:46:08.880
and my soul.

01:46:08.939 --> 01:46:10.920
What I'm here for.

01:46:10.979 --> 01:46:15.119
Dark Stalker raised one of his talons, and

01:46:15.119 --> 01:46:16.800
Turtle nearly ducked behind the gong

01:46:16.800 --> 01:46:19.560
again, out of sight, but he managed to

01:46:19.560 --> 01:46:22.680
stay put, sinking into a crouch, and so

01:46:22.680 --> 01:46:25.319
he was watching, as Dark Stalker lifted a

01:46:25.319 --> 01:46:27.300
claw to gently touch the earring in his

01:46:27.300 --> 01:46:30.180
ear, pale against the black scales.

01:46:30.239 --> 01:46:31.800
An earring.

01:46:31.920 --> 01:46:33.840
Had that been there before?

01:46:33.899 --> 01:46:37.079
Turtle tried to think back, to remember

01:46:37.079 --> 01:46:39.119
what dark stalker had looked like when he

01:46:39.119 --> 01:46:41.399
rose from the earth, he thought he

01:46:41.399 --> 01:46:42.779
remembered no jewelry.

01:46:42.840 --> 01:46:45.659
And didn't Dark Stalker just say that

01:46:45.659 --> 01:46:48.060
nothing had survived the 2000 years

01:46:48.060 --> 01:46:49.079
underground with him?

01:46:49.140 --> 01:46:51.720
But now he was wearing an earring.

01:46:51.840 --> 01:46:55.140
A plain white half loop stabbed through

01:46:55.140 --> 01:46:55.800
his earlobe.

01:46:55.859 --> 01:46:57.720
Turtle squinted at it.

01:46:57.779 --> 01:47:00.539
It looked as though it was made of bone.

01:47:00.600 --> 01:47:04.439
Like a bone one might get from one's prey

01:47:04.439 --> 01:47:04.979
after hunting.

01:47:05.039 --> 01:47:08.220
Could Dark Stalker have made the bone

01:47:08.220 --> 01:47:09.659
earring and enchanted it today?

01:47:09.720 --> 01:47:12.180
While Turtle was flying to Jade Mountain

01:47:12.180 --> 01:47:12.899
to warn the school?

01:47:12.960 --> 01:47:14.520
And more important.

01:47:14.579 --> 01:47:18.359
If it was animus touched, what was the

01:47:18.359 --> 01:47:18.720
spell?

01:47:18.779 --> 01:47:23.039
A short while later, tsunami and moon

01:47:23.039 --> 01:47:24.300
went off to separate parts of the

01:47:24.300 --> 01:47:24.479
school.

01:47:24.539 --> 01:47:27.539
Turtle crouched in the shadows, watching

01:47:27.539 --> 01:47:27.960
them leave.

01:47:28.079 --> 01:47:30.840
He felt like stalagmites were growing

01:47:30.840 --> 01:47:32.760
through his talons, pinning him to the

01:47:32.760 --> 01:47:32.939
floor.

01:47:33.000 --> 01:47:35.460
He didn't want to be left alone here.

01:47:35.520 --> 01:47:37.859
The only one keeping an eye on Dark

01:47:37.859 --> 01:47:38.340
Stalker.

01:47:38.399 --> 01:47:40.319
Who would ever think that was a good

01:47:40.319 --> 01:47:40.619
idea?

01:47:40.680 --> 01:47:42.899
He couldn't be trusted to do anything

01:47:42.899 --> 01:47:43.199
right.

01:47:43.260 --> 01:47:46.920
Maybe I need to enchant someone else to

01:47:46.920 --> 01:47:49.319
be hidden with me. someone who could be a

01:47:49.319 --> 01:47:49.979
better observer.

01:47:50.039 --> 01:47:51.180
A better spy.

01:47:51.300 --> 01:47:53.039
A real hero.

01:47:53.159 --> 01:47:56.220
He thought about that while Anemone

01:47:56.220 --> 01:47:58.199
brought Dark Stalker several pieces of

01:47:58.199 --> 01:47:59.520
treasure from her travel chest.

01:47:59.640 --> 01:48:02.699
Turtle remembered that chest, because

01:48:02.699 --> 01:48:04.260
he'd had to help carry it here from the

01:48:04.260 --> 01:48:06.180
kingdom of the sea, and it was

01:48:06.180 --> 01:48:07.199
ridiculously heavy.

01:48:07.260 --> 01:48:11.460
Now, seeing the ropes of pearls, bulky

01:48:11.460 --> 01:48:14.220
silver neck bands, and sapphire laden

01:48:14.220 --> 01:48:16.319
tiaras she laid out on the cave floor

01:48:16.319 --> 01:48:17.819
turtle could understand why.

01:48:17.880 --> 01:48:20.640
Although he still wasn't entirely clear

01:48:20.640 --> 01:48:23.159
on why she needed any of this for history

01:48:23.159 --> 01:48:25.020
lessons and math classes.

01:48:25.079 --> 01:48:28.500
Together, dark stalker and anemone, picked

01:48:28.500 --> 01:48:30.600
through the jewels, discussing the merits

01:48:30.600 --> 01:48:30.899
of each.

01:48:30.960 --> 01:48:33.359
It was difficult to find anything that

01:48:33.359 --> 01:48:36.659
fit dark stalker's enormous size, but

01:48:36.659 --> 01:48:38.460
they eventually settled on a piece that

01:48:38.460 --> 01:48:40.920
was supposed to be a metal breastplate

01:48:40.920 --> 01:48:43.020
for anemone, fitting around her entire

01:48:43.020 --> 01:48:45.239
chest to protect her from attacks.

01:48:45.300 --> 01:48:48.180
It clicked neatly around one of Dark

01:48:48.180 --> 01:48:48.899
Stalker's wrists.

01:48:49.020 --> 01:48:52.020
Mother is always giving me ridiculous

01:48:52.020 --> 01:48:53.939
things like that, Anemone said.

01:48:54.000 --> 01:48:56.760
As if I need armor to protect me when I

01:48:56.760 --> 01:48:57.899
have magic like ours.

01:48:57.960 --> 01:49:01.560
She has no idea what it's like to be

01:49:01.560 --> 01:49:02.039
ananimous.

01:49:02.100 --> 01:49:04.439
Dark soccer said sympathetically.

01:49:04.500 --> 01:49:07.260
He passed anemone a necklace.

01:49:07.319 --> 01:49:08.220
Maybe this one for you.

01:49:08.279 --> 01:49:11.100
If you think you'd be happy wearing it

01:49:11.100 --> 01:49:11.399
all the time.

01:49:11.460 --> 01:49:12.899
Oh.

01:49:13.020 --> 01:49:16.560
Sure, said Anemone, taking the heavy

01:49:16.560 --> 01:49:18.119
silver band in her talons.

01:49:18.180 --> 01:49:21.359
I mean, I never liked it before, but if

01:49:21.359 --> 01:49:22.920
you think it would work, then I like it

01:49:22.920 --> 01:49:23.100
too.

01:49:23.220 --> 01:49:26.880
It's up to you, said Dark Stalker.

01:49:26.939 --> 01:49:28.560
It should be something you love.

01:49:28.619 --> 01:49:32.819
I love this, Anemone said emphatically.

01:49:32.880 --> 01:49:35.460
She snapped it around her neck with a

01:49:35.460 --> 01:49:38.520
sound like eggs cracking, turtle's

01:49:38.520 --> 01:49:40.439
stomach twisted, as though it were full

01:49:40.439 --> 01:49:41.819
of rotten shrimp.

01:49:41.880 --> 01:49:44.640
Now, the enchantment.

01:49:44.699 --> 01:49:46.680
Dark Stalker said.

01:49:46.739 --> 01:49:49.800
He touched his wristband with one claw

01:49:49.800 --> 01:49:51.899
gazing thoughtfully up at the vines

01:49:51.899 --> 01:49:53.699
draped between the stalactites.

01:49:53.760 --> 01:49:56.159
In a slightly deeper voice, he intoned.

01:49:56.220 --> 01:49:59.939
I enchant this bracelet, to protect my

01:49:59.939 --> 01:50:02.039
soul from the effects of animus magic

01:50:02.039 --> 01:50:02.399
forever.

01:50:02.520 --> 01:50:04.319
There was a pause.

01:50:04.380 --> 01:50:06.300
Is that it?

01:50:06.359 --> 01:50:07.800
Anemone asked.

01:50:07.859 --> 01:50:09.119
Seriously?

01:50:09.180 --> 01:50:10.079
It's that simple?

01:50:10.140 --> 01:50:13.439
Surely not. thought Turtle.

01:50:13.500 --> 01:50:14.279
It can't be.

01:50:14.399 --> 01:50:16.380
I don't know.

01:50:16.439 --> 01:50:19.319
Dog stalker twitched his wings back and

01:50:19.319 --> 01:50:21.119
held out his arm to study the bracelet.

01:50:21.180 --> 01:50:23.220
I guess we'll have to see if it works.

01:50:23.279 --> 01:50:24.659
He squinted.

01:50:24.720 --> 01:50:27.779
My visions of the future seem to indicate

01:50:27.779 --> 01:50:28.319
that it does.

01:50:28.380 --> 01:50:29.640
Yep, yep.

01:50:29.699 --> 01:50:32.100
I'm still a pretty awesome dragon 50

01:50:32.100 --> 01:50:32.640
years from now.

01:50:32.699 --> 01:50:34.560
All right.

01:50:34.619 --> 01:50:36.479
Said anemone with a giggle.

01:50:36.600 --> 01:50:38.399
Well, 3 moons?

01:50:38.460 --> 01:50:39.300
I can do that.

01:50:39.420 --> 01:50:40.859
I could have done that months ago.

01:50:40.920 --> 01:50:43.439
Why hasn't every animus done something

01:50:43.439 --> 01:50:43.739
like this?

01:50:43.800 --> 01:50:47.159
They haven't always known to worry about

01:50:47.159 --> 01:50:47.520
these things.

01:50:47.579 --> 01:50:49.619
Dark stalker observed.

01:50:49.680 --> 01:50:52.380
Or perhaps they did have objects like

01:50:52.380 --> 01:50:54.840
this, and we just don't know about them.

01:50:54.899 --> 01:50:56.699
Hmm.

01:50:56.760 --> 01:50:59.760
Anemone touched her necklace with one

01:50:59.760 --> 01:51:02.640
claw, mirroring dark soccer's movement.

01:51:02.699 --> 01:51:05.399
Wait, said Dark Stalker.

01:51:05.460 --> 01:51:07.920
My soul is safe now.

01:51:07.979 --> 01:51:11.460
Let me use my magic to enchant yours, so

01:51:11.460 --> 01:51:13.079
you don't have to waste any more of your

01:51:13.079 --> 01:51:13.979
soul.

01:51:14.039 --> 01:51:16.319
No, turtle thought.

01:51:16.380 --> 01:51:17.460
Don't let him.

01:51:17.520 --> 01:51:19.140
Anemone, don't trust him.

01:51:19.199 --> 01:51:20.880
Great idea.

01:51:20.939 --> 01:51:22.920
Anemone said happily.

01:51:22.979 --> 01:51:24.659
Should he stop this?

01:51:24.779 --> 01:51:26.340
Could he stop this?

01:51:26.399 --> 01:51:28.020
What can I do?

01:51:28.079 --> 01:51:30.000
I have to do something, don't I?

01:51:30.060 --> 01:51:30.899
Like what?

01:51:30.960 --> 01:51:32.819
I need more time to think.

01:51:32.880 --> 01:51:35.579
The turtle couldn't think of anything he

01:51:35.579 --> 01:51:37.920
could do without dark stalk or noticing

01:51:37.920 --> 01:51:39.600
and it was already too late.

01:51:39.659 --> 01:51:42.479
I enchant this necklace.

01:51:42.479 --> 01:51:44.880
To protect anemone's soul from the

01:51:44.880 --> 01:51:47.159
effects of animus magic forever.

01:51:47.220 --> 01:51:50.640
Said Dark Stalker, tapping the silver

01:51:50.640 --> 01:51:52.439
collar lightly with his claws.

01:51:52.500 --> 01:51:54.239
It sounded safe.

01:51:54.300 --> 01:51:57.600
It sounded exactly like the spell on Dark

01:51:57.600 --> 01:52:00.720
Stalker's own talisman, but Turtle knew

01:52:00.720 --> 01:52:02.939
all too well that spells could be cast

01:52:02.939 --> 01:52:03.899
without speaking.

01:52:03.960 --> 01:52:06.659
Had Dark Stalker added anything to the

01:52:06.659 --> 01:52:07.800
spell with his mind.

01:52:07.859 --> 01:52:09.720
Oh anemone.

01:52:09.779 --> 01:52:12.359
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

01:52:12.479 --> 01:52:16.560
This is so cool, said Anemone.

01:52:16.619 --> 01:52:18.359
Now we can do anything we want.

01:52:18.420 --> 01:52:22.140
That, said Dark Stalker with a grin.

01:52:22.260 --> 01:52:24.180
Is the whole idea.

01:52:24.239 --> 01:52:29.039
Chapter 6.

01:52:29.100 --> 01:52:33.060
Dark Stalker spent the rest of the day in

01:52:33.060 --> 01:52:35.100
the main entrance cave. reading through

01:52:35.100 --> 01:52:37.380
scrolls, and talking to any students who

01:52:37.380 --> 01:52:38.699
are brave enough to approach him.

01:52:38.760 --> 01:52:41.579
By the middle of the day, it began to

01:52:41.579 --> 01:52:43.199
feel quietly normal to have him there.

01:52:43.260 --> 01:52:45.359
He didn't do anything sinister.

01:52:45.420 --> 01:52:47.159
He didn't use any magic.

01:52:47.220 --> 01:52:50.100
He acted like a friendly visitor who just

01:52:50.100 --> 01:52:51.779
needed to use the library on his way

01:52:51.779 --> 01:52:52.380
through the mountains.

01:52:52.439 --> 01:52:55.500
Anemone sat beside him with her chin

01:52:55.500 --> 01:52:58.199
lifted, looking as royal as she did when

01:52:58.199 --> 01:52:59.819
she sat beside mother at council

01:52:59.819 --> 01:53:00.300
meetings.

01:53:00.300 --> 01:53:03.000
Every once in a while, Dark Stalker would

01:53:03.000 --> 01:53:05.340
pass her a scroll and ask her to read it

01:53:05.340 --> 01:53:07.380
out loud to him, or to check it for

01:53:07.380 --> 01:53:09.779
references to Fathom, and she would do so

01:53:09.779 --> 01:53:10.680
beaming.

01:53:10.800 --> 01:53:13.739
The school gradually returned to its

01:53:13.739 --> 01:53:14.579
usual activities.

01:53:14.640 --> 01:53:17.579
From his spot, hidden behind the bronze

01:53:17.579 --> 01:53:20.279
gong, Turtle saw mudwings passed through

01:53:20.279 --> 01:53:21.359
on the way to the art room.

01:53:21.420 --> 01:53:24.000
He saw sand wings carrying musical

01:53:24.000 --> 01:53:26.399
instruments, he saw rain wings with

01:53:26.399 --> 01:53:28.260
baskets heading out to pick berries.

01:53:28.380 --> 01:53:30.720
There was no sign of the ice wings.

01:53:30.779 --> 01:53:32.819
Turtle wondered if they were hiding

01:53:32.819 --> 01:53:33.119
somewhere.

01:53:33.180 --> 01:53:36.779
He also wondered why nobody came to make

01:53:36.779 --> 01:53:39.180
anemone go to whichever class she was

01:53:39.180 --> 01:53:40.020
supposed to be in.

01:53:40.079 --> 01:53:43.859
Pike stalked through a few times, eyeing

01:53:43.859 --> 01:53:46.079
Dark Stalker suspiciously, but didn't try

01:53:46.079 --> 01:53:46.680
talking to him.

01:53:46.739 --> 01:53:50.579
At one point, around midday, Turtle

01:53:50.579 --> 01:53:52.739
watched Clay gather the sky wings to hear

01:53:52.739 --> 01:53:54.960
Peril's story of the duel between Queen

01:53:54.960 --> 01:53:56.579
Scarlet and Queen Ruby.

01:53:56.640 --> 01:53:59.640
Soon they came back through the cave, all

01:53:59.640 --> 01:54:01.979
of them with relieved expressions, knowing

01:54:01.979 --> 01:54:04.140
that Scarlet was dead, and Ruby was

01:54:04.140 --> 01:54:05.579
safely their queen for certain now.

01:54:05.699 --> 01:54:08.760
One of them paused not far from Dark

01:54:08.760 --> 01:54:11.100
Stalker, and gazed enviously at the

01:54:11.100 --> 01:54:12.960
treasure anemone had swept into a messy

01:54:12.960 --> 01:54:13.319
pile.

01:54:13.439 --> 01:54:16.140
He was the one with a badly scarred face

01:54:16.140 --> 01:54:18.119
from the gold winglet.

01:54:18.119 --> 01:54:20.159
He had a black leather pouch around his

01:54:20.159 --> 01:54:22.680
neck, like most of the students, but no

01:54:22.680 --> 01:54:25.380
other accessories, nothing like anemones

01:54:25.380 --> 01:54:26.939
confections of sparkles from the sea.

01:54:27.060 --> 01:54:29.399
Turtle couldn't remember speaking to

01:54:29.399 --> 01:54:29.819
him.

01:54:29.880 --> 01:54:32.579
The Skywing always looked as if he was in

01:54:32.579 --> 01:54:33.479
a murderous mood.

01:54:33.539 --> 01:54:35.699
Hello Flame.

01:54:35.760 --> 01:54:37.979
Dark Stalker said politely.

01:54:38.039 --> 01:54:40.439
He put a rock down on the scroll he'd

01:54:40.439 --> 01:54:41.640
been reading to hold his place.

01:54:41.699 --> 01:54:43.800
Stay out of my head.

01:54:43.920 --> 01:54:45.899
Flame snarled at him.

01:54:45.960 --> 01:54:48.779
With pleasure, said dark stalker.

01:54:48.840 --> 01:54:51.060
I know you were poking around in my mind

01:54:51.060 --> 01:54:51.359
before.

01:54:51.420 --> 01:54:54.779
Flame lashed his tail and glared up at

01:54:54.779 --> 01:54:55.439
the night wing.

01:54:55.500 --> 01:54:56.699
I felt it.

01:54:56.760 --> 01:54:57.659
I hated it.

01:54:57.720 --> 01:54:59.399
Yes.

01:54:59.460 --> 01:55:01.739
Dark Stalker said thoughtfully.

01:55:01.800 --> 01:55:03.000
Indeed.

01:55:03.060 --> 01:55:05.159
It's quite dark in there.

01:55:05.220 --> 01:55:07.739
What's that supposed to mean?

01:55:07.800 --> 01:55:09.300
Flame demanded.

01:55:09.359 --> 01:55:11.880
Like, evil dark?

01:55:11.939 --> 01:55:13.979
Anemone asked curiously.

01:55:14.039 --> 01:55:16.680
Or there's nothing going on inside dark.

01:55:16.800 --> 01:55:18.960
Flame hissed at her.

01:55:19.020 --> 01:55:21.119
And Dark Stalker gently stepped between

01:55:21.119 --> 01:55:21.359
them.

01:55:21.420 --> 01:55:26.279
You know, I have an idea, Flame, he

01:55:26.279 --> 01:55:26.520
said.

01:55:26.579 --> 01:55:29.399
I could fix your face.

01:55:29.460 --> 01:55:33.060
This guy Wing Dragonette started back and

01:55:33.060 --> 01:55:35.579
touched his venom slash snout, scowling

01:55:35.579 --> 01:55:37.979
don't lie to me, he said.

01:55:38.039 --> 01:55:40.560
I already asked an animist to do that, and

01:55:40.560 --> 01:55:42.779
he said he wouldn't, or couldn't

01:55:42.779 --> 01:55:44.520
slithering toadstool worm.

01:55:44.579 --> 01:55:47.100
You mean stone mover.

01:55:47.220 --> 01:55:50.039
Dog stalker said, with a surprised

01:55:50.039 --> 01:55:50.579
expression.

01:55:50.640 --> 01:55:52.560
I wonder why he said no.

01:55:52.619 --> 01:55:54.420
It wouldn't be that hard.

01:55:54.479 --> 01:55:56.340
Or take very much out of him.

01:55:56.399 --> 01:55:57.960
Really?

01:55:58.020 --> 01:56:00.119
Flame looked even more furious.

01:56:00.180 --> 01:56:03.420
He moaned and griped, and acted like it

01:56:03.420 --> 01:56:03.960
would kill him.

01:56:04.020 --> 01:56:06.479
He said he couldn't cure all the wounded

01:56:06.479 --> 01:56:09.659
dragons in Pyria, so why even start

01:56:09.659 --> 01:56:11.220
festering rotted lungfish?

01:56:11.279 --> 01:56:15.600
Oh, dear. said Dark Stalker, shaking his

01:56:15.600 --> 01:56:15.779
head.

01:56:15.840 --> 01:56:19.979
Well, I'm sure he has his reasons, but I

01:56:19.979 --> 01:56:20.819
could certainly do it.

01:56:20.880 --> 01:56:22.560
If you want.

01:56:22.680 --> 01:56:24.960
Flame hesitated.

01:56:25.020 --> 01:56:27.479
Turtle could see his talons trembling

01:56:27.479 --> 01:56:30.060
slightly, although his face was fixed in

01:56:30.060 --> 01:56:31.319
a state of permanent rage.

01:56:31.439 --> 01:56:34.560
Finally, he said, Why would you do that

01:56:34.560 --> 01:56:34.920
for me?

01:56:34.979 --> 01:56:36.840
What do you want in return?

01:56:36.899 --> 01:56:39.180
Nothing at all.

01:56:39.239 --> 01:56:42.479
Dark Stalker caught a deep indigo flower

01:56:42.479 --> 01:56:44.399
that was drifting down from one of the

01:56:44.399 --> 01:56:46.500
banners overhead and cupped it in his

01:56:46.500 --> 01:56:46.859
claws.

01:56:46.920 --> 01:56:49.920
He took a step toward Flame, who held his

01:56:49.920 --> 01:56:50.159
ground.

01:56:50.220 --> 01:56:53.340
I am currently trying to prove to certain

01:56:53.340 --> 01:56:55.859
dragons that I'm not the villain they

01:56:55.859 --> 01:56:56.220
think I am.

01:56:56.279 --> 01:56:57.960
I can be trusted.

01:56:58.020 --> 01:57:00.060
I'm here to help others.

01:57:00.119 --> 01:57:03.539
So why shouldn't you be one of the ones I

01:57:03.539 --> 01:57:03.779
help?

01:57:03.840 --> 01:57:07.619
No strings attached, Flame said.

01:57:07.680 --> 01:57:08.520
Ha!

01:57:08.579 --> 01:57:09.300
I don't buy it.

01:57:09.359 --> 01:57:13.560
I have a lot to make up for, Dark Stalker

01:57:13.560 --> 01:57:13.800
said.

01:57:13.859 --> 01:57:15.359
What's that word?

01:57:15.420 --> 01:57:18.779
Oh, I'm atoning.

01:57:18.840 --> 01:57:22.739
I need Everyone to see that.

01:57:22.800 --> 01:57:25.800
I don't need your pity, and I don't want

01:57:25.800 --> 01:57:28.439
to be your experiment, Flame growled.

01:57:28.500 --> 01:57:31.560
It's a simple good deed, Flame.

01:57:31.680 --> 01:57:33.779
There's no need to be suspicious.

01:57:33.840 --> 01:57:36.420
Dark Stalker stopped in front of him.

01:57:36.539 --> 01:57:39.239
His head nearly brushing the fire globes

01:57:39.239 --> 01:57:39.779
on the ceiling.

01:57:39.840 --> 01:57:43.079
Flame stared up at him, as though he was

01:57:43.079 --> 01:57:46.020
frozen in place, paralyzed by wanting

01:57:46.020 --> 01:57:48.239
something, and not believing he could

01:57:48.239 --> 01:57:49.500
truly have it.

01:57:49.560 --> 01:57:52.680
I've seen in your mind how badly you need

01:57:52.680 --> 01:57:53.039
this.

01:57:53.159 --> 01:57:55.079
Just accept it.

01:57:55.140 --> 01:57:58.859
Dark Stalker reached out and brushed the

01:57:58.859 --> 01:58:01.800
flower across Flame's face, tracing the

01:58:01.800 --> 01:58:03.300
scar from one end to the other.

01:58:03.359 --> 01:58:07.560
I enchant this flower to heal flame, the

01:58:07.560 --> 01:58:11.520
sky wing. without pain, erasing his scars

01:58:11.520 --> 01:58:13.560
and returning his face to the way it was

01:58:13.560 --> 01:58:16.140
before the accident with a sand wing.

01:58:16.140 --> 01:58:19.800
He lifted the flower away, and flame

01:58:19.800 --> 01:58:20.520
jerked back.

01:58:20.579 --> 01:58:24.600
Turtle watched, awestruck, as flames

01:58:24.600 --> 01:58:27.300
scales writhed and rippled over his snout

01:58:27.300 --> 01:58:30.000
like snakes, suddenly rising up and

01:58:30.000 --> 01:58:33.060
shaking off their skins, Flame let out a

01:58:33.060 --> 01:58:35.819
yell, clapped his talons over his eyes

01:58:35.819 --> 01:58:37.560
and wrapped his wings around his head.

01:58:37.619 --> 01:58:41.760
In the ensuing silence, Dark Stalker

01:58:41.760 --> 01:58:43.920
quietly plucked the pedals off the flower

01:58:43.920 --> 01:58:46.020
and let them drift down to the stone

01:58:46.020 --> 01:58:46.800
floor.

01:58:47.100 --> 01:58:50.579
Finally, Flame folded back his wings and

01:58:50.579 --> 01:58:52.020
lifted his face toward the light.

01:58:52.079 --> 01:58:54.779
Turtles stifled a gasp.

01:58:54.840 --> 01:58:57.600
He'd expected it to work, but it was

01:58:57.600 --> 01:59:00.180
shocking to see the smooth, unblemished

01:59:00.180 --> 01:59:02.699
ruby scales, and the perfect shape of

01:59:02.699 --> 01:59:03.479
Flame's face.

01:59:03.539 --> 01:59:06.000
The Skywing Dragonette looked years

01:59:06.000 --> 01:59:08.340
younger, and infinitely more innocent.

01:59:08.399 --> 01:59:11.399
Turtle wondered with a stab of shame

01:59:11.399 --> 01:59:13.500
whether he had judged Flame by his

01:59:13.500 --> 01:59:16.500
damaged looks, assuming he was a scarier

01:59:16.500 --> 01:59:17.880
dragonette than he truly was.

01:59:17.939 --> 01:59:21.000
Flames, claws touched his snout.

01:59:21.060 --> 01:59:23.159
Brushing over the new scales with

01:59:23.159 --> 01:59:25.739
disbelieving care, as though they were

01:59:25.739 --> 01:59:27.600
made of the thinnest ice and might

01:59:27.600 --> 01:59:28.619
shatter at any moment.

01:59:28.680 --> 01:59:31.859
Wow, anemone blurted.

01:59:31.920 --> 01:59:33.300
You look totally different.

01:59:33.359 --> 01:59:35.279
Dark Stalker, that's amazing.

01:59:35.340 --> 01:59:39.119
Flame glanced up at Dark Stalker, then

01:59:39.119 --> 01:59:41.100
turned, and bolted from the cave.

01:59:41.220 --> 01:59:43.020
Oh, right.

01:59:43.079 --> 01:59:45.960
Don't bother saying thank you, Anemone

01:59:45.960 --> 01:59:46.560
called after him.

01:59:46.619 --> 01:59:50.579
Some dragons, she said to dark stalker

01:59:50.579 --> 01:59:51.359
shaking her head.

01:59:51.420 --> 01:59:54.720
You know, I offered to cure Starflight's

01:59:54.720 --> 01:59:57.539
blindness once, but tsunami said no, my

01:59:57.539 --> 01:59:58.800
soul was too valuable.

01:59:58.859 --> 02:00:00.239
Whatever, whatever.

02:00:00.359 --> 02:00:02.460
She touched her neck band.

02:00:02.520 --> 02:00:04.920
But now I can, or you can.

02:00:04.979 --> 02:00:05.819
One of us can.

02:00:05.880 --> 02:00:07.800
Won't Starflight be excited?

02:00:07.859 --> 02:00:09.359
I'm not sure.

02:00:09.420 --> 02:00:11.819
Dark Stalker said kindly.

02:00:11.939 --> 02:00:15.359
It's a generous idea, but in my visions

02:00:15.359 --> 02:00:18.000
he's reluctant to accept a magic cure

02:00:18.000 --> 02:00:18.420
from us.

02:00:18.479 --> 02:00:21.060
Maybe if we give him a little time to get

02:00:21.060 --> 02:00:21.600
used to the idea.

02:00:21.720 --> 02:00:23.760
Reluctant?

02:00:23.819 --> 02:00:24.600
Why?

02:00:24.659 --> 02:00:26.159
Anemone demanded.

02:00:26.220 --> 02:00:28.260
We can fix everybody now.

02:00:28.319 --> 02:00:31.020
Dog Stalker didn't respond.

02:00:31.079 --> 02:00:34.079
His eyes were on a tunnel across the cave

02:00:34.079 --> 02:00:37.020
where, a moment later, moon emerged

02:00:37.020 --> 02:00:39.180
leading the other 3 night wing students.

02:00:39.239 --> 02:00:44.220
Well, this is exciting, said Dark Stalker

02:00:44.220 --> 02:00:44.640
with a smile.

02:00:44.760 --> 02:00:47.579
I thought a better introduction might be

02:00:47.579 --> 02:00:49.260
in order, Moon said.

02:00:49.319 --> 02:00:51.300
She glanced at the other night wings

02:00:51.300 --> 02:00:51.840
anxiously.

02:00:51.899 --> 02:00:56.340
All right, everyone, this is Dark

02:00:56.340 --> 02:00:56.939
Stalker.

02:00:57.000 --> 02:00:59.699
He promises he's not as bad as all the

02:00:59.699 --> 02:01:00.779
stories say he is.

02:01:00.840 --> 02:01:04.859
Dark Stalker, this is Mighty Claus, Mind

02:01:04.859 --> 02:01:06.239
Reader, and Fearless.

02:01:06.359 --> 02:01:09.659
I know Dark Stalker said.

02:01:09.720 --> 02:01:12.000
I've been looking forward to meeting you

02:01:12.000 --> 02:01:13.020
all face to face.

02:01:13.079 --> 02:01:15.479
It seems like the Nightwing tribe has

02:01:15.479 --> 02:01:17.399
changed a lot since I was around.

02:01:17.460 --> 02:01:19.979
Fearless was the 1st to speak.

02:01:20.100 --> 02:01:22.619
Turtle peeked out and saw her claws

02:01:22.619 --> 02:01:24.600
nervously picking at the rock below her.

02:01:24.659 --> 02:01:26.819
What was it like in your day?

02:01:26.819 --> 02:01:28.020
she asked.

02:01:28.079 --> 02:01:31.380
Amazing, said Dark Stalker.

02:01:31.439 --> 02:01:34.020
We were, without question, the most

02:01:34.020 --> 02:01:36.239
powerful and sophisticated tribe.

02:01:36.300 --> 02:01:39.420
Our kingdom had a remarkable library, a

02:01:39.420 --> 02:01:41.460
huge training arena where we hosted all

02:01:41.460 --> 02:01:44.340
the tribes for tournaments, a museum, with

02:01:44.340 --> 02:01:46.920
a most beautiful art empirea, and a new

02:01:46.920 --> 02:01:48.539
music festival every full moon.

02:01:48.600 --> 02:01:50.640
It was glorious.

02:01:50.760 --> 02:01:52.680
It was?

02:01:52.680 --> 02:01:54.720
said Mindreader wistfully.

02:01:54.779 --> 02:01:57.180
I can't believe it's all gone.

02:01:57.300 --> 02:02:00.119
Dark Stalker said, shaking his head.

02:02:00.180 --> 02:02:03.180
He touched the scroll beside him, as

02:02:03.180 --> 02:02:04.859
though all his memories had vanished into

02:02:04.859 --> 02:02:05.100
it.

02:02:05.159 --> 02:02:08.520
Do you know where we've been living all

02:02:08.520 --> 02:02:09.060
these years?

02:02:09.180 --> 02:02:11.220
Mighty Claus asked.

02:02:11.279 --> 02:02:13.739
Turtle noticed that he was the only one

02:02:13.739 --> 02:02:15.420
with a note of hostility in his voice.

02:02:15.479 --> 02:02:20.220
I can see it, in your memories, said Dark

02:02:20.220 --> 02:02:20.699
Stalker.

02:02:20.819 --> 02:02:22.439
The island.

02:02:22.500 --> 02:02:23.640
The volcano.

02:02:23.760 --> 02:02:25.560
It looks terrible.

02:02:25.619 --> 02:02:27.479
It was terrible.

02:02:27.600 --> 02:02:29.939
Mighty Klaus said accusingly.

02:02:30.000 --> 02:02:33.659
In a place of such darkness, and danger

02:02:33.659 --> 02:02:35.159
Dark Stalker mused.

02:02:35.279 --> 02:02:38.279
The night wings who are left must have

02:02:38.279 --> 02:02:39.420
been very strong to survive.

02:02:39.479 --> 02:02:43.140
The dragonettes hesitated, glancing at

02:02:43.140 --> 02:02:43.560
one another.

02:02:43.619 --> 02:02:46.079
The sound of the rain pouring down

02:02:46.079 --> 02:02:47.640
outside filled in the silence.

02:02:47.699 --> 02:02:50.819
It sounded like claws running overhead

02:02:50.819 --> 02:02:53.460
like the waterfalls in the summer palace

02:02:53.460 --> 02:02:56.520
like hurricanes closing in as the waters

02:02:56.520 --> 02:02:56.939
rise.

02:02:57.000 --> 02:02:58.800
I guess.

02:02:58.859 --> 02:03:00.960
Mighty Claus said thoughtfully.

02:03:01.020 --> 02:03:03.000
But we live in the rainforest now.

02:03:03.060 --> 02:03:06.779
That's much better, mind reader

02:03:06.779 --> 02:03:07.319
interjected.

02:03:07.380 --> 02:03:09.659
Now we're not starving or sick anymore

02:03:09.659 --> 02:03:10.439
and we can breathe.

02:03:10.500 --> 02:03:14.340
I'm sure, said Dark Stalker.

02:03:14.399 --> 02:03:17.279
Although, now you don't have a queen.

02:03:17.399 --> 02:03:21.840
We do, said Moon, we have Queen Glory.

02:03:21.899 --> 02:03:23.939
The other 3 nodded.

02:03:24.000 --> 02:03:26.819
Mind reader first, Turtle noticed, and

02:03:26.819 --> 02:03:27.960
the other 2 more slowly.

02:03:28.020 --> 02:03:31.680
Dark Stalker's eyebrows twitched, but he

02:03:31.680 --> 02:03:32.520
didn't say anything for a moment.

02:03:32.640 --> 02:03:36.239
And I understand no one in the tribe has

02:03:36.239 --> 02:03:39.119
powers anymore, he observed.

02:03:39.180 --> 02:03:41.159
Were those really real?

02:03:41.159 --> 02:03:42.659
Fearless asked.

02:03:42.720 --> 02:03:44.460
Could Nightwings really do all those

02:03:44.460 --> 02:03:45.600
things, once?

02:03:45.659 --> 02:03:48.779
Some of them could, he said.

02:03:48.840 --> 02:03:50.760
If they hurts to the right time.

02:03:50.819 --> 02:03:53.640
We had mind reading and prophesy classes

02:03:53.640 --> 02:03:54.779
for the gifted in my school.

02:03:54.840 --> 02:03:56.699
Oh, wow.

02:03:56.760 --> 02:03:58.680
Mind reader breathed.

02:03:58.739 --> 02:04:01.500
Not just classes on pretending to read

02:04:01.500 --> 02:04:03.479
minds and how to make up believable

02:04:03.479 --> 02:04:04.079
prophecies.

02:04:04.140 --> 02:04:06.180
Dark Stalker chuckled.

02:04:06.239 --> 02:04:08.279
No, it was all real.

02:04:08.340 --> 02:04:12.420
I wish I could really read minds, she

02:04:12.420 --> 02:04:13.020
said sadly.

02:04:13.140 --> 02:04:15.899
Do you have any jewelry on you?

02:04:15.960 --> 02:04:18.060
Dark Stalker asked.

02:04:18.119 --> 02:04:20.760
Um, this?

02:04:20.939 --> 02:04:23.220
Mind reader held out her arm to display a

02:04:23.220 --> 02:04:25.500
bracelet of green and silver glass beads

02:04:25.500 --> 02:04:27.600
strung along a twisted black wire.

02:04:27.659 --> 02:04:30.239
Turtle guessed she had made it here in

02:04:30.239 --> 02:04:30.899
art class.

02:04:30.960 --> 02:04:35.340
Heads up, Moon, Dark Stalker said, sliding

02:04:35.340 --> 02:04:37.020
the bracelet off mind reader's arm.

02:04:37.079 --> 02:04:38.699
Exciting things about to happen.

02:04:38.760 --> 02:04:41.039
Is this a good idea?

02:04:41.100 --> 02:04:42.539
Moon said anxiously.

02:04:42.600 --> 02:04:45.539
We can't leave this poor dragonette with

02:04:45.539 --> 02:04:46.979
a name that's a lie, can we?

02:04:47.039 --> 02:04:48.180
He asked.

02:04:48.239 --> 02:04:50.640
Dark Stalker held the bracelet between

02:04:50.640 --> 02:04:52.680
his claws for a moment, with something

02:04:52.680 --> 02:04:54.119
glimmering in his dark eyes.

02:04:54.180 --> 02:04:56.399
Finally, he passed it back to

02:04:56.399 --> 02:04:57.000
Mindreader.

02:04:57.060 --> 02:05:01.439
Wish grunted, he said, smiling again.

02:05:01.500 --> 02:05:03.420
What?

02:05:03.479 --> 02:05:06.300
Oh, she gasped as the bracelet touched

02:05:06.300 --> 02:05:06.899
her scales.

02:05:06.960 --> 02:05:09.359
She looked up at him, eyes wide with

02:05:09.359 --> 02:05:09.659
wonder.

02:05:09.720 --> 02:05:12.960
I can, I can hear what everyone's

02:05:12.960 --> 02:05:13.319
thinking.

02:05:13.380 --> 02:05:14.819
I really can.

02:05:14.880 --> 02:05:15.720
Is this real?

02:05:15.779 --> 02:05:16.800
3 moons.

02:05:16.859 --> 02:05:17.760
Let's see.

02:05:17.819 --> 02:05:19.979
The sea wing princess is thinking I don't

02:05:19.979 --> 02:05:20.819
deserve a gift like this.

02:05:20.880 --> 02:05:23.579
Moon is worried about whether it'll be

02:05:23.579 --> 02:05:25.619
too much for me, hearing everything all

02:05:25.619 --> 02:05:26.279
at once.

02:05:26.520 --> 02:05:28.800
Mighty Claus and Fearless are both super

02:05:28.800 --> 02:05:29.460
jealous.

02:05:29.520 --> 02:05:30.479
Ha!

02:05:30.539 --> 02:05:31.140
This is amazing.

02:05:31.199 --> 02:05:34.140
She did a little jump into the air

02:05:34.140 --> 02:05:34.920
fluttering her wings.

02:05:34.979 --> 02:05:38.340
Moon's right said Dark Stalker.

02:05:38.399 --> 02:05:41.039
It's a lot to handle at first, but moon

02:05:41.039 --> 02:05:42.600
can help you if you feel overwhelmed.

02:05:42.659 --> 02:05:44.640
Moon can?

02:05:44.640 --> 02:05:45.840
said Mighty Claus.

02:05:45.899 --> 02:05:46.500
Why?

02:05:46.560 --> 02:05:48.600
Dark Stalker.

02:05:48.659 --> 02:05:49.680
Moon started.

02:05:49.739 --> 02:05:52.140
Have a little faith in your fellow night

02:05:52.140 --> 02:05:52.739
wings moon.

02:05:52.859 --> 02:05:54.479
Dark Stalker said.

02:05:54.539 --> 02:05:56.460
Don't you think it's fair for them to

02:05:56.460 --> 02:05:57.899
know that you have mind reading and

02:05:57.899 --> 02:05:58.920
prophecy powers?

02:05:58.979 --> 02:06:00.300
What?

02:06:00.359 --> 02:06:01.859
Fearless cried.

02:06:01.920 --> 02:06:03.960
They all looked at Moon as though she had

02:06:03.960 --> 02:06:05.939
suddenly sprouted 6 extra heads.

02:06:06.000 --> 02:06:09.479
But I was going to tell them, Moon

02:06:09.479 --> 02:06:10.079
protested.

02:06:10.140 --> 02:06:14.699
I mean, eventually, soon, when I figured

02:06:14.699 --> 02:06:15.060
out how.

02:06:15.119 --> 02:06:18.899
Well, now we're even for you telling your

02:06:18.899 --> 02:06:19.979
friends about Skyfire.

02:06:20.039 --> 02:06:22.079
Dark Stalker said cheerfully.

02:06:22.140 --> 02:06:25.140
Besides, I promise nobody's going to hate

02:06:25.140 --> 02:06:25.319
you.

02:06:25.380 --> 02:06:27.359
The way you were so worried everyone

02:06:27.359 --> 02:06:27.899
would.

02:06:27.960 --> 02:06:29.579
Right, my friends.

02:06:29.640 --> 02:06:33.779
I don't hate her, mind reader said, with

02:06:33.779 --> 02:06:35.880
a touch of smugness, admiring her

02:06:35.880 --> 02:06:36.359
bracelet.

02:06:36.420 --> 02:06:38.760
How could you keep something like that

02:06:38.760 --> 02:06:39.479
secret?

02:06:39.479 --> 02:06:40.680
Fearless demanded.

02:06:40.739 --> 02:06:44.100
That's not fair. mighty Klaus cried.

02:06:44.159 --> 02:06:47.279
She got to grow up in the rainforest, safe

02:06:47.279 --> 02:06:49.859
and fed and happy, and she gets all our

02:06:49.859 --> 02:06:50.640
lost powers.

02:06:50.640 --> 02:06:52.739
Ooh.

02:06:52.800 --> 02:06:55.560
He's thinking, why couldn't it be me?

02:06:55.619 --> 02:06:57.840
Mind reader announced gleefully.

02:06:57.899 --> 02:07:01.439
All right, genius, anyone can guess that

02:07:01.439 --> 02:07:03.239
Fearless snapped at her.

02:07:03.300 --> 02:07:04.500
Does your mother know?

02:07:04.619 --> 02:07:05.880
She asked Moon.

02:07:05.939 --> 02:07:08.520
I'm assuming yes, since lying apparently

02:07:08.520 --> 02:07:09.239
runs in your family.

02:07:09.300 --> 02:07:11.760
How could I tell anyone?

02:07:11.760 --> 02:07:14.100
When I knew you'd react this way?

02:07:14.159 --> 02:07:15.659
Moon confronted her.

02:07:15.720 --> 02:07:17.939
Exactly the way I expected.

02:07:18.000 --> 02:07:20.220
Hey now.

02:07:20.279 --> 02:07:20.819
Hey now.

02:07:20.880 --> 02:07:22.619
Dark Stalker said.

02:07:22.680 --> 02:07:25.500
He reached out with one massive talent

02:07:25.500 --> 02:07:28.319
and nudged Fearless back a few paces, away

02:07:28.319 --> 02:07:29.340
from Moon.

02:07:29.399 --> 02:07:30.420
That's right.

02:07:30.479 --> 02:07:32.100
I forgot one little step.

02:07:32.159 --> 02:07:33.600
Sorry, Moon.

02:07:33.659 --> 02:07:36.180
He turned to Monte Claus and tapped the

02:07:36.180 --> 02:07:38.579
miniature diamond stud embedded in the

02:07:38.579 --> 02:07:39.659
dragonette's earlobe.

02:07:39.720 --> 02:07:42.840
It was so small that for a long time

02:07:42.840 --> 02:07:44.699
Turtle had thought it was a tiny silver

02:07:44.699 --> 02:07:46.800
scale, but now he could see that it was

02:07:46.800 --> 02:07:47.279
an earring.

02:07:47.399 --> 02:07:51.180
Tell me, mighty Claus, if you could have

02:07:51.180 --> 02:07:52.380
any power.

02:07:52.439 --> 02:07:52.979
What would you choose?

02:07:53.039 --> 02:07:54.720
Dark Stalker asked.

02:07:54.779 --> 02:07:58.560
Dark stalker, Moon said warily.

02:07:58.619 --> 02:08:00.119
Shouldn't you be thinking about your

02:08:00.119 --> 02:08:00.420
soul?

02:08:00.479 --> 02:08:02.760
All taken care of?

02:08:02.819 --> 02:08:05.399
Dark Stalker said, waving one of his

02:08:05.399 --> 02:08:05.939
wings at her.

02:08:06.000 --> 02:08:07.319
Right.

02:08:07.380 --> 02:08:08.220
Little princess.

02:08:08.279 --> 02:08:09.720
That's right.

02:08:09.779 --> 02:08:12.359
Anemone flared her wings and looked

02:08:12.359 --> 02:08:12.960
imperious.

02:08:13.020 --> 02:08:15.420
So you can quit acting like you know

02:08:15.420 --> 02:08:16.500
everything, Moon.

02:08:16.560 --> 02:08:18.659
Dark soccer and I are just fine.

02:08:18.720 --> 02:08:21.960
Moon gave her a puzzled sideways look.

02:08:22.079 --> 02:08:24.779
So, mighty Claus.

02:08:24.840 --> 02:08:27.239
Darkstalker's eyes glittered at the young

02:08:27.239 --> 02:08:27.840
night wing.

02:08:27.899 --> 02:08:29.399
What do you think?

02:08:29.460 --> 02:08:32.039
Any power at all.

02:08:32.100 --> 02:08:36.960
I guess, prophecy, he said.

02:08:37.020 --> 02:08:39.659
I mean, to be different from a mind

02:08:39.659 --> 02:08:40.079
reader.

02:08:40.199 --> 02:08:42.960
You're thinking too small.

02:08:43.020 --> 02:08:46.260
Dark soccer grin with all his teeth.

02:08:46.319 --> 02:08:49.020
Don't limit yourself to traditional night

02:08:49.020 --> 02:08:49.739
wing powers.

02:08:49.800 --> 02:08:51.420
What if you could do anything?

02:08:51.479 --> 02:08:54.300
Any power you can imagine?

02:08:54.359 --> 02:08:56.939
Oh, Dark Stalker.

02:08:57.000 --> 02:08:59.760
Moon said, starting to pace up and down

02:08:59.760 --> 02:09:00.180
the cave.

02:09:00.239 --> 02:09:02.520
I'm really not sure about this.

02:09:02.579 --> 02:09:06.420
Ooh, she's imagining all sorts of

02:09:06.420 --> 02:09:07.020
terrible things.

02:09:07.079 --> 02:09:09.720
Mind reader reported enthusiastically.

02:09:09.779 --> 02:09:13.319
Shouldn't we check with Sonny or Tsunami

02:09:13.319 --> 02:09:14.699
or Queen Glory at least?

02:09:14.760 --> 02:09:15.720
Moon asked.

02:09:15.779 --> 02:09:18.600
Do you think they'd really stop me from

02:09:18.600 --> 02:09:20.699
improving these dragons' lives?

02:09:20.760 --> 02:09:22.079
Dark Stalker asked.

02:09:22.140 --> 02:09:24.720
Look how happy Mind Reader is now.

02:09:24.779 --> 02:09:26.159
Yes.

02:09:26.220 --> 02:09:29.039
But, Moon trailed off.

02:09:29.100 --> 02:09:31.979
But you want all the power for yourself

02:09:31.979 --> 02:09:32.399
is that it?

02:09:32.460 --> 02:09:34.859
Mari Claus asked, lashing his tail.

02:09:34.920 --> 02:09:37.439
You don't like the idea of other dragons

02:09:37.439 --> 02:09:38.220
being special too.

02:09:38.279 --> 02:09:40.979
Powers like these can be hard to live

02:09:40.979 --> 02:09:43.739
with, Moon said fiercely.

02:09:43.800 --> 02:09:44.880
I'm just worried for you all.

02:09:44.939 --> 02:09:47.939
I'll take you always if you want to give

02:09:47.939 --> 02:09:49.920
them up, Mighty Claus suggested.

02:09:49.979 --> 02:09:51.180
Me too.

02:09:51.239 --> 02:09:52.380
Anemone said.

02:09:52.439 --> 02:09:55.380
Ooh, then I'd be just like Dark Stalker.

02:09:55.439 --> 02:09:58.199
Moon is sensible to worry.

02:09:58.319 --> 02:10:00.960
Dark Stalker said soothingly.

02:10:01.020 --> 02:10:03.779
But luckily, I am here to make sure

02:10:03.779 --> 02:10:04.920
everything turns out fine.

02:10:04.979 --> 02:10:07.979
Mighty Claus, what have you decided?

02:10:08.039 --> 02:10:11.279
And me, Fearless interjected.

02:10:11.340 --> 02:10:12.899
Am I getting a power too?

02:10:13.020 --> 02:10:15.479
Do you have anything to enchant?

02:10:15.600 --> 02:10:18.119
Dark soccer asked, looking her up and

02:10:18.119 --> 02:10:18.359
down.

02:10:18.479 --> 02:10:19.859
I will.

02:10:19.979 --> 02:10:22.680
Fearless world and ran out of the cave.

02:10:22.739 --> 02:10:26.039
I have one idea.

02:10:26.159 --> 02:10:28.079
Mighty Claus said hesitantly.

02:10:28.140 --> 02:10:30.359
But it might be stupid.

02:10:30.420 --> 02:10:34.079
It's not, said Dark Stalker.

02:10:34.140 --> 02:10:35.699
I can see what you're thinking.

02:10:35.760 --> 02:10:36.960
It's very creative.

02:10:37.020 --> 02:10:38.640
What?

02:10:38.760 --> 02:10:40.079
Anemone demanded.

02:10:40.140 --> 02:10:40.979
What is it?

02:10:41.039 --> 02:10:44.100
I don't get it, said mind reader.

02:10:44.159 --> 02:10:46.319
He wants to draw things and then make

02:10:46.319 --> 02:10:46.739
them real.

02:10:46.800 --> 02:10:51.239
Like, if I draw a sword, then I could

02:10:51.239 --> 02:10:52.979
touch it, and it would become a real

02:10:52.979 --> 02:10:56.460
sword, Monte Claus said, glowing a little

02:10:56.460 --> 02:10:57.180
with excitement.

02:10:57.239 --> 02:11:00.060
And if I drew a pond, I could touch it

02:11:00.060 --> 02:11:01.739
and it would become a real pond.

02:11:01.800 --> 02:11:05.039
Or if I drew a banana, then I could touch

02:11:05.039 --> 02:11:06.119
it, and...

02:11:06.119 --> 02:11:09.840
And, um, have a real banana to eat.

02:11:09.899 --> 02:11:12.899
Oh, that's what he really wants.

02:11:12.960 --> 02:11:15.420
Mind reader giggled, and endless supply

02:11:15.420 --> 02:11:15.960
of food.

02:11:16.020 --> 02:11:18.659
Would have been pretty useful back on the

02:11:18.659 --> 02:11:19.199
volcano.

02:11:19.260 --> 02:11:21.060
Mighty Claus bristled.

02:11:21.119 --> 02:11:22.739
You wouldn't be making fun of me then.

02:11:22.800 --> 02:11:24.960
You'd be kissing my claws for a banana.

02:11:25.079 --> 02:11:29.399
We don't live on the volcano anymore, mind

02:11:29.399 --> 02:11:30.239
reader pointed out.

02:11:30.359 --> 02:11:33.000
We live in basically the banana capital

02:11:33.000 --> 02:11:33.899
of the universe.

02:11:33.960 --> 02:11:36.600
We don't need a magic banana maker.

02:11:36.659 --> 02:11:39.300
It's not just for bananas.

02:11:39.420 --> 02:11:40.739
Money Klaus cried.

02:11:40.800 --> 02:11:44.819
Well, I think it's extremely clever, Dark

02:11:44.819 --> 02:11:47.579
Stalker said, and mind reader subsided at

02:11:47.579 --> 02:11:47.819
once.

02:11:47.880 --> 02:11:50.220
Let me think for a moment.

02:11:50.279 --> 02:11:52.199
About how exactly to word the spell.

02:11:52.260 --> 02:11:55.079
He tapped his chin pensively for a few

02:11:55.079 --> 02:11:58.199
long, silent seconds, and then he touched

02:11:58.199 --> 02:12:00.600
mighty Claw's earring again, whispering

02:12:00.600 --> 02:12:01.079
under his breath.

02:12:01.140 --> 02:12:04.380
There we go, he said.

02:12:04.439 --> 02:12:05.939
Did it work?

02:12:06.000 --> 02:12:07.439
Mighty Claus asked.

02:12:07.500 --> 02:12:09.720
Run to the odd cave and see.

02:12:09.779 --> 02:12:11.279
Dark Stalker suggested.

02:12:11.340 --> 02:12:14.880
Bring me back a banana.

02:12:14.939 --> 02:12:17.880
Mind reader called after him as Mighty

02:12:17.880 --> 02:12:18.600
Claus darted away.

02:12:18.659 --> 02:12:20.939
Dark stalker.

02:12:21.000 --> 02:12:22.439
Why are you doing this?

02:12:22.500 --> 02:12:23.699
Moon asked.

02:12:23.760 --> 02:12:27.119
She stopped pacing and sat down, with her

02:12:27.119 --> 02:12:28.500
tail around her talons.

02:12:28.560 --> 02:12:30.659
Turtle wished he were brave enough to

02:12:30.659 --> 02:12:33.180
stand next to her, taking strength from

02:12:33.180 --> 02:12:33.779
her strength.

02:12:33.840 --> 02:12:35.939
He wished she could tell him what to

02:12:35.939 --> 02:12:36.840
think about any of this.

02:12:36.899 --> 02:12:39.960
The more he watched Dark Stalker, the

02:12:39.960 --> 02:12:40.979
more confused he felt.

02:12:41.039 --> 02:12:44.279
Because this was a good thing Dark

02:12:44.279 --> 02:12:45.300
Stalker was doing, wasn't it?

02:12:45.420 --> 02:12:47.399
Giving other dragon's powers.

02:12:47.460 --> 02:12:50.039
That's what you want to think.

02:12:50.100 --> 02:12:52.199
His conscience whispered.

02:12:52.319 --> 02:12:55.979
Our tribe needs help, Moon.

02:12:56.100 --> 02:12:58.260
Dark soccer said earnestly.

02:12:58.319 --> 02:13:00.479
They've fallen so far.

02:13:00.539 --> 02:13:03.119
I want to restore them to the powerful

02:13:03.119 --> 02:13:04.079
tribe I remember.

02:13:04.140 --> 02:13:06.720
And if I can do that by sharing my gift

02:13:06.720 --> 02:13:07.859
why shouldn't I?

02:13:07.920 --> 02:13:12.000
Because Are you sure you won't turn

02:13:12.000 --> 02:13:12.539
evil?

02:13:12.659 --> 02:13:13.739
Moon asked.

02:13:13.800 --> 02:13:16.020
And these are huge decisions.

02:13:16.079 --> 02:13:17.880
Shouldn't you think about them a little

02:13:17.880 --> 02:13:18.180
more?

02:13:18.239 --> 02:13:20.819
I have been thinking about them.

02:13:20.880 --> 02:13:23.100
Dark Stalker assured her.

02:13:23.159 --> 02:13:25.680
I've been thinking nonstop since I woke

02:13:25.680 --> 02:13:25.859
up.

02:13:25.920 --> 02:13:27.779
And I've checked all the possible

02:13:27.779 --> 02:13:28.380
futures.

02:13:28.439 --> 02:13:31.020
This is the best path, believe me.

02:13:31.140 --> 02:13:33.659
A happy nightwing tribe.

02:13:33.720 --> 02:13:36.000
Tullins of power for everyone.

02:13:36.060 --> 02:13:38.760
Talons of power?

02:13:38.880 --> 02:13:41.279
Moon echoed, her eyes wide.

02:13:41.340 --> 02:13:44.279
Like the prophecy, the whole beware

02:13:44.279 --> 02:13:44.760
part?

02:13:44.819 --> 02:13:48.539
I'm just joking, said Dark Stalker.

02:13:48.600 --> 02:13:50.460
Try not to worry so much.

02:13:50.520 --> 02:13:52.500
I'm back.

02:13:52.619 --> 02:13:54.899
Fearless ran into the room, panting.

02:13:54.960 --> 02:13:56.100
I'm here.

02:13:56.159 --> 02:13:57.300
I have something.

02:13:57.420 --> 02:13:58.739
She thrust out her arm.

02:13:58.800 --> 02:14:01.319
A pair of silver and black wires had been

02:14:01.319 --> 02:14:03.479
hastily twisted into a rough bracelet

02:14:03.479 --> 02:14:05.100
barely visible on her wrist.

02:14:05.159 --> 02:14:08.100
She smiled up at Dark Stalker, in a

02:14:08.100 --> 02:14:09.600
frighteningly worshipful way.

02:14:09.720 --> 02:14:13.859
Super strength, please, she said

02:14:13.859 --> 02:14:14.460
breathlessly.

02:14:14.579 --> 02:14:16.979
Dark Stalker smiled back at her.

02:14:17.039 --> 02:14:18.720
Anything you wish.

02:14:18.779 --> 02:14:21.359
He touched her wrist and muttered

02:14:21.359 --> 02:14:21.720
something.

02:14:21.779 --> 02:14:24.300
When he finished, she turned her talon

02:14:24.300 --> 02:14:26.699
over, then spun around and slammed her

02:14:26.699 --> 02:14:28.260
tail into a stalagmite.

02:14:28.319 --> 02:14:30.899
It instantly crumbled into a cascade of

02:14:30.899 --> 02:14:31.739
tiny rocks.

02:14:31.800 --> 02:14:34.319
Fearless let out a shriek of delight.

02:14:34.380 --> 02:14:36.239
Did you see that?

02:14:36.300 --> 02:14:37.380
she cried.

02:14:37.439 --> 02:14:40.140
Mind reader toyed with her own bracelet

02:14:40.140 --> 02:14:40.739
frowning.

02:14:40.800 --> 02:14:45.180
Well, she said, it's cool, I suppose, if

02:14:45.180 --> 02:14:47.939
you like that kind of thing, I mean, a

02:14:47.939 --> 02:14:49.739
bit obvious, but all right.

02:14:49.859 --> 02:14:53.340
Dark Stalker suddenly sat up, lifting his

02:14:53.340 --> 02:14:55.439
head, as though he could see monsters

02:14:55.439 --> 02:14:57.960
crawling out of the stalactites, he

02:14:57.960 --> 02:14:59.579
stared into space for a moment with

02:14:59.579 --> 02:15:00.479
faraway eyes.

02:15:00.539 --> 02:15:02.760
The other dragons all held their breath

02:15:02.760 --> 02:15:04.260
and watched in silence.

02:15:04.319 --> 02:15:06.960
Did you sense something?

02:15:07.020 --> 02:15:10.079
He said finally, looking down at Moon?

02:15:10.140 --> 02:15:11.100
She shook her head.

02:15:11.159 --> 02:15:12.779
What was it?

02:15:12.840 --> 02:15:13.920
A vision?

02:15:13.979 --> 02:15:17.340
More of a premonition.

02:15:17.399 --> 02:15:18.359
He said.

02:15:18.420 --> 02:15:20.399
His expression was troubled.

02:15:20.460 --> 02:15:23.100
And if this was an act, Turtle thought

02:15:23.100 --> 02:15:25.500
then Dark Stalker was really good at it

02:15:25.500 --> 02:15:28.260
even Turtle felt his anxiety jump a few

02:15:28.260 --> 02:15:29.039
notches higher.

02:15:29.039 --> 02:15:31.319
Someone's in danger.

02:15:31.380 --> 02:15:32.640
Can you feel it?

02:15:32.699 --> 02:15:34.500
Moon closed her eyes.

02:15:34.560 --> 02:15:37.140
Mind reader saw her do it, and

02:15:37.140 --> 02:15:39.239
immediately closed her eyes too, putting

02:15:39.239 --> 02:15:40.859
on a deeply pensive look.

02:15:40.920 --> 02:15:42.720
Hmm.

02:15:42.840 --> 02:15:45.899
Yes, said Mind Reader, nodding.

02:15:46.020 --> 02:15:49.020
The princess, who smells like fish, is

02:15:49.020 --> 02:15:50.460
thinking maybe she should give herself

02:15:50.460 --> 02:15:52.380
some cool powers like ours.

02:15:52.439 --> 02:15:54.060
Ha ha, copycat.

02:15:54.119 --> 02:15:57.659
Oh, and they're Sonny's mind, coming this

02:15:57.659 --> 02:16:00.060
way with a squirrel for dog stalker

02:16:00.060 --> 02:16:02.100
wondering what he's found out about clear

02:16:02.100 --> 02:16:02.640
sight.

02:16:02.699 --> 02:16:05.760
Turtle felt a flash of worry that she'd

02:16:05.760 --> 02:16:08.340
hear his mind hiding nearby and give him

02:16:08.340 --> 02:16:08.640
away.

02:16:08.699 --> 02:16:11.880
But then he remembered the skyfire, which

02:16:11.880 --> 02:16:13.619
shielded him from all mind readers.

02:16:13.680 --> 02:16:16.199
He felt for his armband with a sigh of

02:16:16.199 --> 02:16:16.619
relief.

02:16:16.680 --> 02:16:19.260
Only 3 stones left.

02:16:19.319 --> 02:16:21.300
The other 3 holes marked the stones he'd

02:16:21.300 --> 02:16:23.760
given to winter, Kibley, and Kinkachu.

02:16:23.819 --> 02:16:26.100
Would Moon want a stone for herself?

02:16:26.159 --> 02:16:28.199
Now that there were 2 other mind readers

02:16:28.199 --> 02:16:28.500
around.

02:16:28.560 --> 02:16:29.760
Maybe not.

02:16:29.819 --> 02:16:32.100
He wasn't sure she'd still be able to

02:16:32.100 --> 02:16:33.899
read other minds if she was holding a

02:16:33.899 --> 02:16:34.739
Skyfire rock.

02:16:34.799 --> 02:16:36.719
It's Stone Mover.

02:16:36.780 --> 02:16:39.719
Moon cried suddenly, her eyes flying

02:16:39.719 --> 02:16:40.020
open.

02:16:40.079 --> 02:16:43.139
She leaped to her feet, wings spread wide

02:16:43.139 --> 02:16:44.940
and turned towards Sonny as she entered

02:16:44.940 --> 02:16:45.360
the cave.

02:16:45.420 --> 02:16:48.780
Sonny, your father, someone's trying to

02:16:48.780 --> 02:16:49.079
kill him.

02:16:49.200 --> 02:16:53.819
Chapter 7.

02:16:53.879 --> 02:16:58.259
There was a sudden rush of wings, like a

02:16:58.259 --> 02:17:00.299
1000000 seagulls taking flight at once.

02:17:00.360 --> 02:17:03.420
Sonny, dark stalker, and moon dove out

02:17:03.420 --> 02:17:04.079
into the storm.

02:17:04.139 --> 02:17:07.079
Anemone pivoted in a circle, as though

02:17:07.079 --> 02:17:09.179
startled that they'd left without her

02:17:09.179 --> 02:17:10.079
then flew after them.

02:17:10.139 --> 02:17:12.719
Mind reader and fearless exchanged a

02:17:12.719 --> 02:17:14.519
glance, and finally followed as well.

02:17:14.579 --> 02:17:17.399
Turtle hurried out from behind the gong

02:17:17.399 --> 02:17:19.440
and stood in the cave entrance for a

02:17:19.440 --> 02:17:20.819
moment, dithering.

02:17:20.879 --> 02:17:22.739
It would be hard to sneak along behind

02:17:22.739 --> 02:17:25.199
them, but then he wanted to know what was

02:17:25.199 --> 02:17:25.559
happening.

02:17:25.620 --> 02:17:28.500
On the other talon, it was raining quite

02:17:28.500 --> 02:17:28.860
a lot.

02:17:28.920 --> 02:17:31.920
But then again, Kibli had asked him to

02:17:31.920 --> 02:17:34.079
keep an eye on Dart Stalker, so that was

02:17:34.079 --> 02:17:35.700
really what he had to do, wasn't it?

02:17:35.760 --> 02:17:38.940
He growled softly.

02:17:39.000 --> 02:17:41.700
And then he was out in the rain, instantly

02:17:41.700 --> 02:17:43.860
drenched, flying through flashes of

02:17:43.860 --> 02:17:44.159
lightning.

02:17:44.219 --> 02:17:46.799
He chased the dragons around the mountain

02:17:46.799 --> 02:17:49.019
to the cave, Stone Mover had chosen to

02:17:49.019 --> 02:17:51.359
live in for the rest of his life, like a

02:17:51.359 --> 02:17:52.679
petrified hermit crab.

02:17:52.739 --> 02:17:55.440
Turtle had never visited the old night

02:17:55.440 --> 02:17:57.420
wing animus during his time at Jade

02:17:57.420 --> 02:17:57.840
Mountain.

02:17:57.899 --> 02:18:00.959
He had a weird, irrational fear that the

02:18:00.959 --> 02:18:03.120
dragon would somehow recognize him as a

02:18:03.120 --> 02:18:05.040
fellow animus and reveal his secret.

02:18:05.100 --> 02:18:08.639
Although if he searched deeper, he'd also

02:18:08.639 --> 02:18:10.680
have to admit that he was afraid of

02:18:10.680 --> 02:18:13.020
seeing what an animus could become when

02:18:13.020 --> 02:18:14.520
he used his magic too much.

02:18:14.520 --> 02:18:18.360
He heard Dark Stalker roar, angry and

02:18:18.360 --> 02:18:20.819
earth shaking, sending a slide of rocks

02:18:20.819 --> 02:18:22.379
clattering down the mountainside.

02:18:22.440 --> 02:18:24.840
Turtle wobbled down to the ledge outside

02:18:24.840 --> 02:18:27.180
the cave and slid himself into the very

02:18:27.180 --> 02:18:28.739
edge of the shadows inside.

02:18:28.860 --> 02:18:32.280
He sucked in a sharp breath as he

02:18:32.280 --> 02:18:34.379
suddenly realized how close he was to

02:18:34.379 --> 02:18:37.260
Dark Stalker's scales, the enormous

02:18:37.260 --> 02:18:39.360
dragon filled the mouth of the cave

02:18:39.360 --> 02:18:41.340
leaning in toward the others.

02:18:41.399 --> 02:18:44.940
His smooth ebony side rose and fell, only

02:18:44.940 --> 02:18:47.520
a thin slice of air away from turtle's

02:18:47.520 --> 02:18:47.760
nose.

02:18:47.819 --> 02:18:51.059
If I touch him, will he notice me then?

02:18:51.180 --> 02:18:53.280
Or will he wonder why he can touch

02:18:53.280 --> 02:18:54.420
something that he cannot see?

02:18:54.479 --> 02:18:58.620
Turtle held himself tensely frozen, wings

02:18:58.620 --> 02:19:00.719
pinned to the wall behind him, like

02:19:00.719 --> 02:19:03.059
stingrays caught on a sea wing's sharp

02:19:03.059 --> 02:19:06.059
claws, from his position, he could just

02:19:06.059 --> 02:19:09.000
see a sliver of the cave beyond, stone

02:19:09.000 --> 02:19:12.420
movers, gray, fossilized arm, a tangle of

02:19:12.420 --> 02:19:15.299
night wing tails, a pool of blood slowly

02:19:15.299 --> 02:19:16.799
creeping across the stone floor.

02:19:16.860 --> 02:19:21.780
Father, Sonny cried, was crying, had

02:19:21.780 --> 02:19:22.860
cried several times over.

02:19:22.920 --> 02:19:24.780
The word echoing around the cave.

02:19:24.840 --> 02:19:26.639
Who did this?

02:19:26.700 --> 02:19:29.399
Moon's voice, then a glimpse of her

02:19:29.399 --> 02:19:31.379
teardrop scales as she turned to Dark

02:19:31.379 --> 02:19:31.920
Stalker.

02:19:31.979 --> 02:19:33.120
You must know.

02:19:33.180 --> 02:19:36.959
He went into the tunnels, Dark Stalker

02:19:36.959 --> 02:19:40.319
said, pointing, his wings shifting, warm

02:19:40.319 --> 02:19:42.780
fire smelling breath past Turtle's face.

02:19:42.840 --> 02:19:45.120
Otherwise, I'd chase him down myself.

02:19:45.180 --> 02:19:47.219
I'll do it.

02:19:47.280 --> 02:19:49.440
Anemone yelped from her spot at

02:19:49.440 --> 02:19:51.959
Darkstalker's talons, she seized a loose

02:19:51.959 --> 02:19:52.920
prey bone on the floor.

02:19:53.040 --> 02:19:55.319
Lead me to Stone Waver's killer.

02:19:55.379 --> 02:19:57.180
Anemone, no.

02:19:57.239 --> 02:19:58.920
But Sonny was too late.

02:19:58.979 --> 02:20:02.100
Anemone's pale blue tail flashed a trail

02:20:02.100 --> 02:20:03.540
through the blood, and she was gone.

02:20:03.600 --> 02:20:06.299
Why didn't you see this coming?

02:20:06.360 --> 02:20:08.399
Moon asked Dark Stalker.

02:20:08.520 --> 02:20:10.620
I thought you could see everything, all

02:20:10.620 --> 02:20:11.219
the futures.

02:20:11.280 --> 02:20:14.819
There are 1000000000s upon 1000000000s of

02:20:14.819 --> 02:20:15.299
futures.

02:20:15.420 --> 02:20:17.340
Dark Stalker answered.

02:20:17.399 --> 02:20:18.420
I'm sorry.

02:20:18.479 --> 02:20:21.540
Even I can't study all of them. especially

02:20:21.540 --> 02:20:23.280
when something small can set off a sharp

02:20:23.280 --> 02:20:23.520
turn.

02:20:23.639 --> 02:20:25.680
Sonny, is he still alive?

02:20:25.739 --> 02:20:28.079
It seems like I can still hear a glimmer

02:20:28.079 --> 02:20:28.920
of life in his mind.

02:20:28.979 --> 02:20:32.879
Oh, so can I, Moon gasped.

02:20:32.940 --> 02:20:35.100
Um, yeah.

02:20:35.159 --> 02:20:36.120
Me too.

02:20:36.180 --> 02:20:38.040
Mind reader declared quickly.

02:20:38.100 --> 02:20:40.920
Dark Stalker squeezed forward another few

02:20:40.920 --> 02:20:43.979
steps, and as he ducked his head, Turtle

02:20:43.979 --> 02:20:46.200
could see a slash of dark red beads

02:20:46.200 --> 02:20:48.600
dripping across stone mover's neck.

02:20:48.659 --> 02:20:50.760
If Stone Mover was still alive.

02:20:50.819 --> 02:20:53.399
Turtles healing rock could save him.

02:20:53.459 --> 02:20:56.579
This was a wound like Winters, on the

02:20:56.579 --> 02:20:58.920
surface, where the enchantment turtle had

02:20:58.920 --> 02:21:00.840
crafted so thoughtlessly could actually

02:21:00.840 --> 02:21:01.079
help.

02:21:01.200 --> 02:21:03.420
But to bring it out now would be

02:21:03.420 --> 02:21:03.959
suicidal.

02:21:04.020 --> 02:21:06.360
Not only would everyone discover that

02:21:06.360 --> 02:21:09.120
Turtle was an animus, but Dark Stalker

02:21:09.120 --> 02:21:10.799
would want to know where the rock came

02:21:10.799 --> 02:21:13.319
from, who'd enchanted it and how he

02:21:13.319 --> 02:21:14.040
didn't know about it.

02:21:14.100 --> 02:21:17.399
No, there was no way to help.

02:21:17.459 --> 02:21:20.700
Once again, Turtle had to sit on his

02:21:20.700 --> 02:21:21.659
claws and do nothing.

02:21:21.719 --> 02:21:24.840
He had to stay useless if he wanted to

02:21:24.840 --> 02:21:25.260
stay safe.

02:21:25.319 --> 02:21:29.280
He's alive, Dark Stalker said firmly.

02:21:29.340 --> 02:21:30.719
I can't save him.

02:21:30.840 --> 02:21:33.719
He reached up and snapped a stalactite

02:21:33.719 --> 02:21:36.120
off the roof with casual, terrifying

02:21:36.120 --> 02:21:36.600
strength.

02:21:36.659 --> 02:21:40.260
But you shouldn't, should you?

02:21:40.319 --> 02:21:41.399
Sonny asked.

02:21:41.459 --> 02:21:43.200
He's my family too.

02:21:43.260 --> 02:21:46.020
Dog stalker wrapped his front talons

02:21:46.020 --> 02:21:46.920
around the spear of rock.

02:21:46.979 --> 02:21:51.000
Enchant, this stalactite, to heal the

02:21:51.000 --> 02:21:52.920
wounds of any dragon it touches.

02:21:53.040 --> 02:21:55.079
He said, in a deep voice.

02:21:55.200 --> 02:21:58.260
A little deeper than necessary, Turtle

02:21:58.260 --> 02:21:58.559
thought.

02:21:58.680 --> 02:22:01.559
A little theatrical, let's be honest.

02:22:01.620 --> 02:22:04.079
But it seemed to have the intended effect

02:22:04.079 --> 02:22:05.280
on the dragon's watching.

02:22:05.340 --> 02:22:08.280
All their eyes followed Dark Stalker's

02:22:08.280 --> 02:22:10.680
movements as he reached down and tapped

02:22:10.680 --> 02:22:12.540
stone mover lightly on the chest.

02:22:12.600 --> 02:22:15.360
A hushed moment passed, and then stone

02:22:15.360 --> 02:22:16.620
mover let out a sigh.

02:22:16.739 --> 02:22:19.379
The slash of red on his neck, knitted

02:22:19.379 --> 02:22:20.639
together, and vanished.

02:22:20.700 --> 02:22:23.219
He rolled his head back with a groan of

02:22:23.219 --> 02:22:26.340
pain, opened his eyes, and saw Dark

02:22:26.340 --> 02:22:26.819
Stalker.

02:22:26.879 --> 02:22:29.879
Hello, Dark Soccer said.

02:22:29.940 --> 02:22:31.260
You're all right now.

02:22:31.319 --> 02:22:34.200
Ooh, are you?

02:22:34.260 --> 02:22:37.319
Stone mover croaked in his dust covered

02:22:37.319 --> 02:22:37.620
voice.

02:22:37.680 --> 02:22:41.520
An ancestor of yours, said Dark Stalker

02:22:41.520 --> 02:22:43.139
returned from the dead.

02:22:43.260 --> 02:22:44.760
So we have that in common.

02:22:44.819 --> 02:22:47.459
My name is Dog Stalker.

02:22:47.520 --> 02:22:51.479
No, whispered Stone Mover. his eyes

02:22:51.479 --> 02:22:52.079
widening.

02:22:52.139 --> 02:22:53.819
Don't be scared.

02:22:53.879 --> 02:22:55.319
Moon said quickly.

02:22:55.379 --> 02:22:56.700
He's not here to hurt us.

02:22:56.760 --> 02:23:00.420
He saved your life, Sonny added.

02:23:00.479 --> 02:23:03.120
She rested one of her small talons on

02:23:03.120 --> 02:23:06.059
stone mover's petrified shoulder, a tiny

02:23:06.059 --> 02:23:08.340
island of gold among all the black scales

02:23:08.340 --> 02:23:08.940
in the cave.

02:23:09.000 --> 02:23:13.979
With magic, Stone Mover said, sounding

02:23:13.979 --> 02:23:14.579
half panicked.

02:23:14.639 --> 02:23:16.379
No, you can't.

02:23:16.500 --> 02:23:18.000
It's wrong.

02:23:18.059 --> 02:23:18.959
It's wrong.

02:23:19.020 --> 02:23:21.000
My clothes.

02:23:21.059 --> 02:23:23.100
They're not mine.

02:23:23.159 --> 02:23:26.340
His eyes rolled wildly toward his talons

02:23:26.340 --> 02:23:28.739
and Turtle saw the stone cracking all

02:23:28.739 --> 02:23:31.260
along his arms, crumbling back to release

02:23:31.260 --> 02:23:32.340
the scales underneath.

02:23:32.399 --> 02:23:34.139
What do you mean?

02:23:34.200 --> 02:23:35.280
Sonny asked.

02:23:35.340 --> 02:23:36.180
What's wrong?

02:23:36.239 --> 02:23:39.959
These aren't my claws.

02:23:40.020 --> 02:23:41.520
Stone mover shrieked.

02:23:41.579 --> 02:23:42.840
What are they doing?

02:23:42.899 --> 02:23:44.040
Stop them.

02:23:44.100 --> 02:23:45.479
Somebody stop them.

02:23:45.600 --> 02:23:47.520
Bewildered.

02:23:47.579 --> 02:23:49.500
Sonny pounce on one of his front talons.

02:23:49.559 --> 02:23:52.500
Dark stalker dropped the stalactite and

02:23:52.500 --> 02:23:53.459
gently pinned the other.

02:23:53.520 --> 02:23:55.500
Don't panic.

02:23:55.559 --> 02:23:56.459
He said.

02:23:56.520 --> 02:23:58.079
You've had a shock.

02:23:58.139 --> 02:23:59.760
Someone tried to kill you.

02:23:59.819 --> 02:24:01.319
But you're safe now.

02:24:01.379 --> 02:24:04.559
Your petrified scales are healing, that's

02:24:04.559 --> 02:24:04.739
all.

02:24:04.799 --> 02:24:07.319
You're not used to being able to feel

02:24:07.319 --> 02:24:08.520
your limbs anymore.

02:24:08.579 --> 02:24:09.959
In a moment.

02:24:10.020 --> 02:24:12.600
All the rock will be gone, and you'll be

02:24:12.600 --> 02:24:13.020
back to normal.

02:24:13.079 --> 02:24:15.959
Then not mine.

02:24:16.020 --> 02:24:19.260
Stone Mover said again, in a low

02:24:19.260 --> 02:24:21.899
desperate voice, tension radiated through

02:24:21.899 --> 02:24:24.659
his muscles, down his arms to the claws

02:24:24.659 --> 02:24:26.819
that twitched and twitched, breaking

02:24:26.819 --> 02:24:27.120
free.

02:24:27.180 --> 02:24:28.680
No.

02:24:28.739 --> 02:24:31.799
No, I gave mine up.

02:24:31.860 --> 02:24:33.780
My talons are gone.

02:24:33.840 --> 02:24:37.260
These are monsters, crawling out of the

02:24:37.260 --> 02:24:40.379
earth, and they will rend the sky and

02:24:40.379 --> 02:24:43.379
crush the wings of small dragons, and I

02:24:43.379 --> 02:24:44.280
can't let them.

02:24:44.340 --> 02:24:46.860
I won't, I won't, I won't let them be

02:24:46.860 --> 02:24:47.280
used again.

02:24:47.399 --> 02:24:51.360
His voice arose and rose to an agonized

02:24:51.360 --> 02:24:51.780
roar.

02:24:51.840 --> 02:24:54.719
The head splitting sound, pounded images

02:24:54.719 --> 02:24:57.780
of blood, and death, and slashing claws

02:24:57.780 --> 02:24:58.680
through Turtle's brain.

02:24:58.739 --> 02:25:01.319
Do you trust your talons?

02:25:01.500 --> 02:25:02.760
Do you trust them, do you?

02:25:02.819 --> 02:25:04.620
Stop him.

02:25:04.680 --> 02:25:06.719
Moon shouted to Dark Stalker.

02:25:06.780 --> 02:25:08.700
He's trying to use his magic to hurt

02:25:08.700 --> 02:25:09.180
himself.

02:25:09.239 --> 02:25:12.120
Mind reader had her talons over her ears

02:25:12.120 --> 02:25:14.219
and was huddled in a ball on the cave

02:25:14.219 --> 02:25:14.579
floor.

02:25:14.639 --> 02:25:17.520
Dark stalker took stone mover's head in

02:25:17.520 --> 02:25:19.860
his claws and forced the roaring dragon

02:25:19.860 --> 02:25:20.819
to meet his gaze.

02:25:20.879 --> 02:25:25.379
Calm down, he said. in a voice that shook

02:25:25.379 --> 02:25:25.860
the mountain.

02:25:25.920 --> 02:25:28.440
Stone mover's voice dropped away.

02:25:28.500 --> 02:25:30.479
He stared back at Dark Stalker.

02:25:30.540 --> 02:25:34.079
I'm healing you, Dark Stalker said.

02:25:34.139 --> 02:25:34.860
That's all.

02:25:34.920 --> 02:25:38.340
Don't, Stone Mover whispered.

02:25:38.399 --> 02:25:39.959
It's not safe.

02:25:40.020 --> 02:25:42.479
You don't have to punish yourself for

02:25:42.479 --> 02:25:43.260
being ananimous.

02:25:43.319 --> 02:25:46.139
Dark Stalker flicked his tail, frowning.

02:25:46.200 --> 02:25:48.780
You're allowed to be whole, to be happy.

02:25:48.840 --> 02:25:52.260
I agree with Darkstocker, Turtle

02:25:52.260 --> 02:25:52.620
thought.

02:25:52.680 --> 02:25:53.940
Is that a bad sign?

02:25:54.000 --> 02:25:57.000
I don't want to spend my life in terror

02:25:57.000 --> 02:25:57.659
of my powers.

02:25:57.719 --> 02:25:59.579
I want to be happy too.

02:25:59.639 --> 02:26:02.520
Does that mean I'm in danger of turning

02:26:02.520 --> 02:26:03.780
out like Dark Stalker?

02:26:03.840 --> 02:26:06.360
Would I rather end up like him?

02:26:06.360 --> 02:26:08.040
Or stone mover.

02:26:08.100 --> 02:26:11.760
He couldn't imagine willingly fossilizing

02:26:11.760 --> 02:26:14.100
himself, but he looked down at his

02:26:14.100 --> 02:26:16.379
clenched talons and wondered what he

02:26:16.379 --> 02:26:17.760
would do to stop them from hurting

02:26:17.760 --> 02:26:18.299
anyone.

02:26:18.360 --> 02:26:21.600
Did Stone Mover have flashes of blood and

02:26:21.600 --> 02:26:24.120
screaming in his head too, before he cast

02:26:24.120 --> 02:26:24.600
his spell?

02:26:24.719 --> 02:26:27.899
Stone Mover rolled his eyes toward his

02:26:27.899 --> 02:26:30.059
tail, where more rock was crumbling

02:26:30.059 --> 02:26:30.360
away.

02:26:30.420 --> 02:26:33.180
I can't be free.

02:26:33.239 --> 02:26:34.200
He said.

02:26:34.260 --> 02:26:36.360
I don't know what I might do.

02:26:36.420 --> 02:26:38.159
Cage me again.

02:26:38.219 --> 02:26:40.440
Leave me in stone.

02:26:40.500 --> 02:26:42.959
It's the only way to be safe.

02:26:43.020 --> 02:26:47.159
He means it, Moon said to Dark Stalker.

02:26:47.280 --> 02:26:50.040
She edged around the pool of blood to

02:26:50.040 --> 02:26:51.899
catch some of the falling pebbles from

02:26:51.899 --> 02:26:53.159
the old dragon's wings.

02:26:53.219 --> 02:26:56.399
He's terrified of his power, of his own

02:26:56.399 --> 02:26:58.379
claws, of any dark magic.

02:26:58.440 --> 02:27:00.780
His mind is shredding itself to pieces.

02:27:00.840 --> 02:27:03.659
Yeah, and it's giving me the worst

02:27:03.659 --> 02:27:04.319
headache.

02:27:04.379 --> 02:27:05.879
Mind reader complained.

02:27:05.940 --> 02:27:07.979
All this fear.

02:27:08.040 --> 02:27:10.260
Dark soccer said with a sigh.

02:27:10.379 --> 02:27:13.559
I've seen it before, he brightened.

02:27:13.680 --> 02:27:15.180
Maybe I can fix it.

02:27:15.239 --> 02:27:17.399
The right spell could take away all his

02:27:17.399 --> 02:27:17.639
worry.

02:27:17.700 --> 02:27:18.899
No.

02:27:18.959 --> 02:27:21.479
Sonny and Stone Mover said at the same

02:27:21.479 --> 02:27:23.700
time, looking equally alarmed.

02:27:23.760 --> 02:27:26.879
No spells on my brain.

02:27:26.940 --> 02:27:30.239
Stone Mover said, his voice rising toward

02:27:30.239 --> 02:27:31.260
panic again.

02:27:31.319 --> 02:27:32.639
Why not?

02:27:32.760 --> 02:27:35.520
Dark soccer asked, with genuine

02:27:35.520 --> 02:27:36.120
bewilderment.

02:27:36.180 --> 02:27:38.219
If it would make you happier.

02:27:38.280 --> 02:27:40.020
He turned to Moon.

02:27:40.079 --> 02:27:42.540
Isn't it all right to make other dragons

02:27:42.540 --> 02:27:43.739
happier, if you can?

02:27:43.860 --> 02:27:47.819
Not if they don't want you to, she said

02:27:47.819 --> 02:27:48.239
gently.

02:27:48.299 --> 02:27:52.200
But they should want me to, he said.

02:27:52.319 --> 02:27:53.520
It makes no sense.

02:27:53.639 --> 02:27:56.219
He lifted his wings in a shrug.

02:27:56.280 --> 02:27:58.379
They nearly whacked Turtle in the nose.

02:27:58.440 --> 02:28:00.059
Fine.

02:28:00.120 --> 02:28:00.840
All right.

02:28:00.899 --> 02:28:02.700
I'll leave him in his misery.

02:28:02.760 --> 02:28:05.819
And put me back.

02:28:05.819 --> 02:28:10.200
The way I was, Stone Mover asked. leaning

02:28:10.200 --> 02:28:11.879
against the wall and closing his eyes.

02:28:11.940 --> 02:28:15.719
Dragons who wallow in their own tragedy.

02:28:15.840 --> 02:28:18.540
Dog stalker muttered, so pointless.

02:28:18.600 --> 02:28:21.719
He scooped up a talon full of rocks and

02:28:21.719 --> 02:28:24.120
crushed it in his claws, then blew the

02:28:24.120 --> 02:28:26.579
stone dust all over stone movers' wings

02:28:26.579 --> 02:28:27.659
tail, and arms.

02:28:27.719 --> 02:28:31.379
A moment later, the cold gray of the cave

02:28:31.379 --> 02:28:33.600
began creeping over Stone Movers' scales

02:28:33.600 --> 02:28:36.000
again, embedding him into the walls and

02:28:36.000 --> 02:28:36.899
floor once more.

02:28:36.959 --> 02:28:39.180
There you go.

02:28:39.239 --> 02:28:40.920
Dark Stalker said.

02:28:40.979 --> 02:28:43.379
May you always be as thoroughly unhappy

02:28:43.379 --> 02:28:44.280
as you want to be.

02:28:44.340 --> 02:28:46.319
Thank you.

02:28:46.379 --> 02:28:49.979
Stone Mover whispered, relief printed all

02:28:49.979 --> 02:28:50.579
over his face.

02:28:50.639 --> 02:28:53.760
Dark stalker wrinkled its snout at moon

02:28:53.760 --> 02:28:55.020
and she shook her head at him.

02:28:55.079 --> 02:28:56.819
Turtle wondered if they were

02:28:56.819 --> 02:28:58.079
communicating telepathically.

02:28:58.139 --> 02:29:01.079
Did Moon really like Dark Stalker?

02:29:01.139 --> 02:29:03.959
If she did, did that mean Turtle was

02:29:03.959 --> 02:29:04.440
wrong about him?

02:29:04.500 --> 02:29:06.540
Healing flame?

02:29:06.600 --> 02:29:09.959
Saving stone mover, protecting anemone's

02:29:09.959 --> 02:29:12.420
soul, giving powers to the night wings.

02:29:12.479 --> 02:29:15.059
Dog Stalker hadn't exactly spent his day

02:29:15.059 --> 02:29:16.440
spreading evil and doom.

02:29:16.500 --> 02:29:19.200
Am I worrying about nothing?

02:29:19.260 --> 02:29:21.840
Sonny wrapped her arms around her

02:29:21.840 --> 02:29:23.399
father's neck and hugged him.

02:29:23.459 --> 02:29:26.280
Blood from the healed wound smeared her

02:29:26.280 --> 02:29:28.079
scales, but she didn't seem to notice.

02:29:28.200 --> 02:29:31.620
A few minutes passed in silence, and then

02:29:31.620 --> 02:29:33.299
they all heard footsteps coming up

02:29:33.299 --> 02:29:34.200
through the tunnels.

02:29:34.319 --> 02:29:37.559
Sonny sat up and arranged her wings, as

02:29:37.559 --> 02:29:39.000
though she was trying to match an image

02:29:39.000 --> 02:29:40.020
of a queen in her head.

02:29:40.079 --> 02:29:44.219
I found him, Anemone announced, coming

02:29:44.219 --> 02:29:45.059
into the cave.

02:29:45.120 --> 02:29:47.579
A dragon edged into the space behind

02:29:47.579 --> 02:29:47.879
her.

02:29:47.940 --> 02:29:50.879
The sharp edge of the broken prey bone

02:29:50.879 --> 02:29:53.340
pressed into the crevice below his jaw

02:29:53.340 --> 02:29:54.959
enchanted to threaten him forward.

02:29:55.020 --> 02:29:59.340
It was flame, guilt and shame written all

02:29:59.340 --> 02:30:01.079
over his new, perfect face.

02:30:01.139 --> 02:30:03.719
Sunny stared down at him without

02:30:03.719 --> 02:30:06.059
comprehension for a long moment, not

02:30:06.059 --> 02:30:07.139
understanding who he was.

02:30:07.200 --> 02:30:11.459
Lame, Dark Stalker said at last.

02:30:11.520 --> 02:30:13.500
Why would you do this?

02:30:13.559 --> 02:30:17.100
Especially when Dark Stalker just healed

02:30:17.100 --> 02:30:19.920
your face, said Anemone, I thought you'd

02:30:19.920 --> 02:30:21.239
be dancing and flying around.

02:30:21.299 --> 02:30:23.819
It's not exactly normal to celebrate by

02:30:23.819 --> 02:30:25.379
killing some random old dragon.

02:30:25.440 --> 02:30:28.680
She noticed stone mover's eyes opened and

02:30:28.680 --> 02:30:29.219
jumped back.

02:30:29.280 --> 02:30:31.979
Yikes, and you didn't even do it right.

02:30:32.040 --> 02:30:34.440
You guys, the fossil is still alive.

02:30:34.500 --> 02:30:37.739
We know, Fearless said.

02:30:37.799 --> 02:30:39.959
Dark stalker saved him.

02:30:40.020 --> 02:30:42.000
Flame.

02:30:42.059 --> 02:30:44.040
Why would you do something like this?

02:30:44.100 --> 02:30:45.360
Sonny asked.

02:30:45.420 --> 02:30:49.139
He lied to me, Flames said, through

02:30:49.139 --> 02:30:50.040
clenched teeth.

02:30:50.100 --> 02:30:52.979
He could have healed me, but he chose not

02:30:52.979 --> 02:30:53.219
to.

02:30:53.280 --> 02:30:58.319
Oh, wow, said mind reader, squinting at

02:30:58.319 --> 02:30:58.799
flame.

02:30:58.860 --> 02:31:01.139
Moon, are you hearing this too?

02:31:01.200 --> 02:31:04.379
This dragon seriously hates everyone.

02:31:04.440 --> 02:31:06.899
Stay out of my mind.

02:31:06.959 --> 02:31:08.520
Flame shouted at her.

02:31:08.639 --> 02:31:10.739
Mind reader jerked back with a yelp.

02:31:10.799 --> 02:31:15.360
But you are healed, Sonny said to him

02:31:15.360 --> 02:31:15.899
wonderingly.

02:31:15.959 --> 02:31:18.420
So why would it matter who did it?

02:31:18.479 --> 02:31:20.340
Enough to kill someone for it?

02:31:20.459 --> 02:31:25.799
He lied to me, Flame growled. sinking

02:31:25.799 --> 02:31:26.399
closer to the floor.

02:31:26.459 --> 02:31:30.000
That's an interesting complaint coming

02:31:30.000 --> 02:31:32.879
from a dragon with his own secrets, said

02:31:32.879 --> 02:31:33.659
Dark Stalker.

02:31:33.719 --> 02:31:36.659
He beckoned with one claw, and Flames

02:31:36.659 --> 02:31:39.239
leather pouch ripped free and floated

02:31:39.239 --> 02:31:40.860
into Dark Stalker's talons.

02:31:40.920 --> 02:31:42.299
Give that back.

02:31:42.360 --> 02:31:44.100
Flame reward.

02:31:44.159 --> 02:31:46.979
But when he tried to leap forward, Anemone

02:31:46.979 --> 02:31:49.020
stood in his way, glittering with self

02:31:49.020 --> 02:31:49.680
righteousness.

02:31:49.739 --> 02:31:52.379
The bone pressed itself harder into his

02:31:52.379 --> 02:31:55.020
neck, conjuring a jeweled drop of blood

02:31:55.020 --> 02:31:57.959
and flame stopped with a gasp of pain.

02:31:58.020 --> 02:32:02.579
Wow, he is so angry, mind reader

02:32:02.579 --> 02:32:02.940
reported.

02:32:03.059 --> 02:32:04.319
Ooh.

02:32:04.379 --> 02:32:06.719
He wants to horribly kill all of us.

02:32:06.840 --> 02:32:09.959
Dark Stalker shook the pouch and caught 2

02:32:09.959 --> 02:32:11.520
objects as they tumbled out.

02:32:11.579 --> 02:32:16.079
Flame's library card and a blue sapphire

02:32:16.079 --> 02:32:19.379
shaped like a long, elegant star.

02:32:19.440 --> 02:32:23.399
The 3rd dream visitor, sunny gasped.

02:32:23.459 --> 02:32:27.479
That's right, said Dark Stalker. holding

02:32:27.479 --> 02:32:28.440
it up to catch the light.

02:32:28.500 --> 02:32:32.100
This is what I've suspected, since I 1st

02:32:32.100 --> 02:32:33.239
heard Moon's prophecy.

02:32:33.360 --> 02:32:36.780
Flame is the darkness of dragons.

02:32:36.840 --> 02:32:40.200
And he's the stalker of dreams.

02:32:40.260 --> 02:32:44.700
Chapter 8.

02:32:44.760 --> 02:32:48.899
Beware the darkness of dragons.

02:32:48.959 --> 02:32:51.479
Beware the stalker of dreams.

02:32:51.540 --> 02:32:54.899
A breath of cold air shivered along

02:32:54.899 --> 02:32:55.799
turtles' wings.

02:32:55.860 --> 02:32:58.200
Was dark stalker right?

02:32:58.260 --> 02:33:01.500
Was one of the dangers of the prophecy

02:33:01.500 --> 02:33:03.299
seething under their noses this whole

02:33:03.299 --> 02:33:03.540
time?

02:33:03.600 --> 02:33:07.500
I'm not any of that, Flame snarled.

02:33:07.559 --> 02:33:09.479
What does that tripe even mean?

02:33:09.540 --> 02:33:12.719
You must have stolen this from Starflight

02:33:12.719 --> 02:33:13.799
on the Nightwing Island?

02:33:13.860 --> 02:33:16.020
Sonny said, pointing to the dream

02:33:16.020 --> 02:33:16.680
visitor?

02:33:16.739 --> 02:33:18.719
But how did you hide it all this time?

02:33:18.840 --> 02:33:20.760
While you were injured in everything?

02:33:20.879 --> 02:33:24.059
I had help, spat flame.

02:33:24.120 --> 02:33:26.520
Idiot help, but that's all I had to work

02:33:26.520 --> 02:33:26.760
with.

02:33:26.819 --> 02:33:29.940
He's thinking about to dragon with a

02:33:29.940 --> 02:33:30.540
weird name.

02:33:30.600 --> 02:33:36.479
Ogre, Okra, mused mind reader, who he

02:33:36.479 --> 02:33:37.440
also hates, by the way.

02:33:37.500 --> 02:33:41.280
Stop sticking your snout in my brain

02:33:41.280 --> 02:33:44.159
flame hissed, or I'll slice it off.

02:33:44.219 --> 02:33:48.059
I wish I could, flared mind reader.

02:33:48.120 --> 02:33:49.979
You're a miserable dragon, and your

02:33:49.979 --> 02:33:51.899
thoughts are like nasty boiling tar.

02:33:51.959 --> 02:33:54.420
What are we going to do with you?

02:33:54.479 --> 02:33:56.280
Sonny asked Flame.

02:33:56.340 --> 02:33:58.739
I'll have to tell Queen Ruby what you

02:33:58.739 --> 02:33:59.040
did.

02:33:59.100 --> 02:34:01.799
But until she sends someone for you, it's

02:34:01.799 --> 02:34:03.059
not like we have somewhere to lock you

02:34:03.059 --> 02:34:03.239
up.

02:34:03.299 --> 02:34:04.860
Really?

02:34:04.920 --> 02:34:07.559
What kind of respectable school doesn't

02:34:07.559 --> 02:34:08.219
have a dungeon?

02:34:08.280 --> 02:34:09.899
Dark Stalker asked.

02:34:09.959 --> 02:34:12.600
Fearless and mind reader turned toward

02:34:12.600 --> 02:34:15.600
him with wide eyes, and he chuckled, I'm

02:34:15.600 --> 02:34:15.959
just kidding.

02:34:16.020 --> 02:34:18.840
Sonny, I can take care of this for you.

02:34:18.899 --> 02:34:21.239
How, exactly?

02:34:21.299 --> 02:34:23.040
She asked warily.

02:34:23.100 --> 02:34:26.219
Dark Stalker took Flame's library card

02:34:26.219 --> 02:34:28.500
and touched it to one of Flame's front

02:34:28.500 --> 02:34:31.139
talons, instantly it flipped over and

02:34:31.139 --> 02:34:33.719
outward, transforming into an iron band

02:34:33.719 --> 02:34:36.659
that clamped around Flame's forearm, a

02:34:36.659 --> 02:34:38.459
thick metal chain sprouted from the band

02:34:38.459 --> 02:34:39.899
like a coiling snake.

02:34:39.959 --> 02:34:42.840
It plunged into the rock, trapping flame

02:34:42.840 --> 02:34:43.260
in place.

02:34:43.319 --> 02:34:47.159
Flame roared his fury, but he couldn't

02:34:47.159 --> 02:34:49.440
move, couldn't reach any of the throats

02:34:49.440 --> 02:34:50.340
he was clawing for.

02:34:50.399 --> 02:34:52.200
There.

02:34:52.260 --> 02:34:53.700
Dark Stalker said.

02:34:53.760 --> 02:34:55.500
He's not going anywhere now.

02:34:55.559 --> 02:34:57.899
He backed out of the cave.

02:34:57.959 --> 02:35:00.299
Turtle pressed himself tightly against

02:35:00.299 --> 02:35:03.000
the wall, closing his eyes, as the

02:35:03.000 --> 02:35:05.100
massive ebony scales rippled by.

02:35:05.159 --> 02:35:08.819
Giant claws scraped the stone perilously

02:35:08.819 --> 02:35:11.159
close to his own pitifully small webbed

02:35:11.159 --> 02:35:12.059
talons.

02:35:12.120 --> 02:35:13.920
Sunny circled flame.

02:35:13.979 --> 02:35:16.559
Her expression uncertain, until she

02:35:16.559 --> 02:35:18.719
noticed that she was leaving tracks of

02:35:18.719 --> 02:35:20.399
stone mover's blood across the floor.

02:35:20.459 --> 02:35:23.760
With a sigh, she bowed her head and

02:35:23.760 --> 02:35:25.020
slipped away into the tunnels.

02:35:25.079 --> 02:35:27.600
That was awesome.

02:35:27.659 --> 02:35:30.299
Anemone danced out of the cave and spread

02:35:30.299 --> 02:35:31.020
her wings.

02:35:31.079 --> 02:35:33.000
Looking up at Dark Stalker, where he

02:35:33.000 --> 02:35:33.600
stood in the rain.

02:35:33.659 --> 02:35:36.540
If she noticed turtle as she went by him

02:35:36.540 --> 02:35:38.459
she didn't acknowledge his presence.

02:35:38.459 --> 02:35:40.620
Let's solve some more mysteries.

02:35:40.680 --> 02:35:43.260
Catch some more bad guys, be even more

02:35:43.260 --> 02:35:43.680
awesome.

02:35:43.739 --> 02:35:47.159
You should have an early night.

02:35:47.219 --> 02:35:48.959
Dark Stalker said to her.

02:35:49.079 --> 02:35:51.600
He swept his wings toward mind reader and

02:35:51.600 --> 02:35:53.760
fearless, who were huddled under the cave

02:35:53.760 --> 02:35:56.459
overhang, looking severely displeased

02:35:56.459 --> 02:35:57.059
about the weather.

02:35:57.120 --> 02:36:00.959
You all should, because tomorrow, we're

02:36:00.959 --> 02:36:01.799
going to the rainforest.

02:36:01.920 --> 02:36:03.420
And it's a long flight.

02:36:03.479 --> 02:36:04.860
Moon.

02:36:04.979 --> 02:36:06.899
He called as she slipped out of the

02:36:06.899 --> 02:36:07.200
cave.

02:36:07.260 --> 02:36:08.940
Come flying with me.

02:36:09.000 --> 02:36:10.680
She hesitated.

02:36:10.739 --> 02:36:13.860
Kibley and I told Starflight we'd help

02:36:13.860 --> 02:36:15.899
him clean up the library and look for

02:36:15.899 --> 02:36:17.340
more scrolls for you.

02:36:17.399 --> 02:36:18.000
Maybe later.

02:36:18.059 --> 02:36:21.659
Of course, Dark Stalker said.

02:36:21.719 --> 02:36:22.739
No problem.

02:36:22.799 --> 02:36:24.959
He watched her fly away.

02:36:25.079 --> 02:36:27.479
Raindrops slithering down his sides.

02:36:27.540 --> 02:36:30.719
His expression reminded Turtle of someone

02:36:30.719 --> 02:36:32.040
but he couldn't think who.

02:36:32.100 --> 02:36:34.920
I'll go flying with you, Anemone

02:36:34.920 --> 02:36:35.399
chirped.

02:36:35.459 --> 02:36:37.559
I'm way more interesting than Moon, and

02:36:37.559 --> 02:36:38.219
I'm not tired.

02:36:38.280 --> 02:36:42.299
You will be tomorrow, Dark Stalker said

02:36:42.299 --> 02:36:44.340
and we're not stopping on the way to the

02:36:44.340 --> 02:36:44.819
rainforest.

02:36:44.879 --> 02:36:48.479
Thank you, princess, but I'll be fine by

02:36:48.479 --> 02:36:49.260
myself tonight.

02:36:49.319 --> 02:36:52.739
He spread his wings, and Turtle realized

02:36:52.739 --> 02:36:54.540
who Dark Stalker had reminded him of.

02:36:54.659 --> 02:36:57.479
The soldiers in the garden of the wounded

02:36:57.479 --> 02:37:00.899
the ones who couldn't swim anymore, who'd

02:37:00.899 --> 02:37:04.260
lost a tail or a limb, or a wing, and

02:37:04.260 --> 02:37:06.000
didn't quite know yet how to go on living

02:37:06.000 --> 02:37:06.659
without them.

02:37:06.659 --> 02:37:09.780
That was the expression he'd glimpsed

02:37:09.780 --> 02:37:12.659
very briefly, on Dark Stalker's face.

02:37:12.719 --> 02:37:15.600
The enormous night wing turned and flew

02:37:15.600 --> 02:37:18.479
away, higher and higher into the gray

02:37:18.479 --> 02:37:20.940
glowering clouds, until the storm seemed

02:37:20.940 --> 02:37:23.340
to melt into his scales, and swallow him

02:37:23.340 --> 02:37:23.520
whole.

02:37:23.639 --> 02:37:27.000
Turtle thought about following him, but

02:37:27.000 --> 02:37:28.920
his wings felt coated in thick sand.

02:37:28.979 --> 02:37:31.920
He hadn't slept all night, and he'd spent

02:37:31.920 --> 02:37:34.260
the entire day before, flying across the

02:37:34.260 --> 02:37:35.520
continent as fast as he could.

02:37:35.579 --> 02:37:38.280
His fear of dark stalker had kept him

02:37:38.280 --> 02:37:40.680
awake for most of the day, but now his

02:37:40.680 --> 02:37:42.059
eyes were desperate for sleep.

02:37:42.120 --> 02:37:45.360
He hasn't done anything terrible yet.

02:37:45.540 --> 02:37:48.059
He told himself, as he flew back to the

02:37:48.059 --> 02:37:48.659
entrance hall.

02:37:48.719 --> 02:37:50.879
And I have to sleep sometime.

02:37:51.000 --> 02:37:53.700
He dragged his tail through the tunnels.

02:37:53.760 --> 02:37:56.399
I can't watch him every 2nd of his life

02:37:56.399 --> 02:37:57.180
forever.

02:37:57.239 --> 02:37:59.639
He paused in the doorway to his own

02:37:59.639 --> 02:38:00.420
sleeping cave.

02:38:00.479 --> 02:38:03.959
It was so empty, like a giant hollowed

02:38:03.959 --> 02:38:05.100
out oyster shell.

02:38:05.159 --> 02:38:08.340
The walls rose around him, there, and

02:38:08.340 --> 02:38:09.360
scraped of all life.

02:38:09.420 --> 02:38:12.959
In the kingdom of the sea, the sons of

02:38:12.959 --> 02:38:14.819
Queen Coral were almost always together.

02:38:14.879 --> 02:38:18.000
They shared rooms, classes, prey.

02:38:18.059 --> 02:38:19.920
They filled the palaces with their

02:38:19.920 --> 02:38:21.659
wrestling matches and shouting games.

02:38:21.719 --> 02:38:24.120
So when one of them did something wrong.

02:38:24.180 --> 02:38:26.459
And if someone was paying attention to

02:38:26.459 --> 02:38:28.379
them long enough to notice, their

02:38:28.379 --> 02:38:31.020
punishment was almost always isolation.

02:38:31.079 --> 02:38:34.920
Sometimes it was imposed from above, by

02:38:34.920 --> 02:38:37.139
someone like their Uncle Shark, or Cousin

02:38:37.139 --> 02:38:37.680
Moray.

02:38:37.739 --> 02:38:39.780
Sometimes it came from within.

02:38:39.899 --> 02:38:42.059
When the brothers banded together to

02:38:42.059 --> 02:38:43.319
exile one of their own.

02:38:43.379 --> 02:38:46.139
Turtle's punishment for failing his

02:38:46.139 --> 02:38:48.719
father was chosen and carried out by his

02:38:48.719 --> 02:38:49.260
own brothers.

02:38:49.319 --> 02:38:51.899
The older ones caught wind of the news

02:38:51.899 --> 02:38:54.600
that Gil was furious about something, and

02:38:54.600 --> 02:38:56.520
they finally pried the whole story out of

02:38:56.520 --> 02:38:57.840
octopus and cerulean.

02:38:57.899 --> 02:39:00.719
Turtle was shut out completely for a

02:39:00.719 --> 02:39:01.020
month.

02:39:01.139 --> 02:39:02.940
Nobody spoke to him.

02:39:03.000 --> 02:39:06.420
He was left to sleep in an empty room, and

02:39:06.420 --> 02:39:08.040
his brothers all behaved as though he

02:39:08.040 --> 02:39:08.520
didn't exist.

02:39:08.579 --> 02:39:12.180
Turtle had felt his sense of dragonhood

02:39:12.180 --> 02:39:14.940
drifting away, dissolving into the ocean

02:39:14.940 --> 02:39:16.020
like a mist of ink.

02:39:16.079 --> 02:39:18.000
If no one could see you.

02:39:18.059 --> 02:39:19.260
Were you real?

02:39:19.379 --> 02:39:22.500
If no one spoke to you, how long could

02:39:22.500 --> 02:39:24.299
you go on existing before disappearing

02:39:24.299 --> 02:39:24.780
completely?

02:39:24.840 --> 02:39:27.959
Which was why he'd finally used his magic

02:39:27.959 --> 02:39:28.319
on them.

02:39:28.379 --> 02:39:31.860
An enchanted seagull egg cracked into

02:39:31.860 --> 02:39:33.780
their fish stew one night, and

02:39:33.780 --> 02:39:35.219
forgiveness was suddenly his.

02:39:35.280 --> 02:39:38.399
But it left him with an unshakable sense

02:39:38.399 --> 02:39:39.000
of doubt.

02:39:39.059 --> 02:39:41.459
Would they ever have forgiven him on

02:39:41.459 --> 02:39:41.760
their own?

02:39:41.819 --> 02:39:43.920
Or would he have been alone forever?

02:39:43.979 --> 02:39:46.680
He knew he hadn't earned it.

02:39:46.739 --> 02:39:50.159
This beguiled friendliness, this false

02:39:50.159 --> 02:39:52.020
tide of mercy that had washed away his

02:39:52.020 --> 02:39:52.500
sins.

02:39:52.559 --> 02:39:55.920
Empty caves always reminded him of that

02:39:55.920 --> 02:39:59.459
feeling. 1st a loneliness, and then the

02:39:59.459 --> 02:40:00.059
guilt.

02:40:00.120 --> 02:40:02.280
He'd had trouble sleeping in his school

02:40:02.280 --> 02:40:05.159
cave, ever since his clawmade umber had

02:40:05.159 --> 02:40:06.059
run away with Sora.

02:40:06.120 --> 02:40:09.180
Umber had all the warmth and energy that

02:40:09.180 --> 02:40:12.120
Turtle didn't have, and as a mudwing, he

02:40:12.120 --> 02:40:13.680
needed brothers and sisters around him

02:40:13.680 --> 02:40:13.979
too.

02:40:14.040 --> 02:40:17.159
From the 1st night, they had dragged

02:40:17.159 --> 02:40:19.440
their reed mats together and slept back

02:40:19.440 --> 02:40:21.600
to back, feeling as if the world was

02:40:21.600 --> 02:40:24.000
really still there, as long as there were

02:40:24.000 --> 02:40:25.139
other scales close by.

02:40:25.200 --> 02:40:28.319
Umber had felt like a new brother right

02:40:28.319 --> 02:40:28.620
away.

02:40:28.680 --> 02:40:30.840
Turtle missed him.

02:40:30.899 --> 02:40:34.020
He glanced along the hall, then slipped

02:40:34.020 --> 02:40:35.639
quietly down to Kibley and Winter's

02:40:35.639 --> 02:40:35.819
room.

02:40:35.879 --> 02:40:38.879
It looked a lot bigger without Winter's

02:40:38.879 --> 02:40:40.979
scavenger cage taking up half the space.

02:40:41.040 --> 02:40:43.620
Winter was tinkering with a new wire

02:40:43.620 --> 02:40:46.379
construction, muttering, while Kibley sat

02:40:46.379 --> 02:40:48.899
curled on a ledge, surrounded by scrolls

02:40:48.899 --> 02:40:50.879
a pensive look in his black eyes.

02:40:50.940 --> 02:40:55.079
Hey, turtle said, poking his head

02:40:55.079 --> 02:40:55.440
inside.

02:40:55.500 --> 02:40:57.780
Can I sleep in here tonight?

02:40:57.840 --> 02:41:00.059
Kibley snapped back to the world

02:41:00.059 --> 02:41:00.600
immediately?

02:41:00.659 --> 02:41:02.159
Of course.

02:41:02.219 --> 02:41:04.559
He jumped off the ledge and hurried over

02:41:04.559 --> 02:41:05.159
to Turtle.

02:41:05.219 --> 02:41:09.600
Oh, hello, yes, there is another dragon

02:41:09.600 --> 02:41:11.639
in here, Winter observed.

02:41:11.700 --> 02:41:14.459
I wonder if he has an opinion about extra

02:41:14.459 --> 02:41:16.139
snoring in his sleeping cave.

02:41:16.200 --> 02:41:18.420
What's happened?

02:41:18.540 --> 02:41:21.420
Kibli asked Turtle, ignoring his claw

02:41:21.420 --> 02:41:21.780
mate.

02:41:21.840 --> 02:41:23.040
What have you seen?

02:41:23.100 --> 02:41:26.520
Not much, Turtle said.

02:41:26.579 --> 02:41:29.280
Dark Stalker's been really quiet all

02:41:29.280 --> 02:41:29.579
day.

02:41:29.639 --> 02:41:33.239
He read a bunch of scrolls, fixed flames

02:41:33.239 --> 02:41:36.420
face, made talismans to protect his soul

02:41:36.420 --> 02:41:39.360
and anemones, and then gave powers to the

02:41:39.360 --> 02:41:40.200
night wing students.

02:41:40.260 --> 02:41:43.139
And then Flame tried to kill Stone Mover

02:41:43.139 --> 02:41:46.620
and, Wait, whoa, said Kibley.

02:41:46.680 --> 02:41:48.180
That doesn't sound like not much.

02:41:48.239 --> 02:41:49.559
Start from the beginning.

02:41:49.620 --> 02:41:53.219
So Turtle told him and Winter as much as

02:41:53.219 --> 02:41:55.319
he could about Dark Stalker's activities

02:41:55.319 --> 02:41:55.680
that day.

02:41:55.739 --> 02:41:58.799
Both dragons looked horrified when they

02:41:58.799 --> 02:42:01.200
heard what happened to Stone Mover, but

02:42:01.200 --> 02:42:03.600
winter seemed even more horrified by the

02:42:03.600 --> 02:42:05.280
news that Dark Stalker was handing out

02:42:05.280 --> 02:42:07.139
superpowers to the night wings.

02:42:07.200 --> 02:42:09.840
Winter threw his silver blue wings up in

02:42:09.840 --> 02:42:10.200
the air.

02:42:10.260 --> 02:42:13.079
We only just found out that those powers

02:42:13.079 --> 02:42:15.120
were fake, and now they're real again?

02:42:15.180 --> 02:42:17.579
You don't have to worry, though.

02:42:17.700 --> 02:42:20.459
Turtle reminded him, you still have the

02:42:20.459 --> 02:42:22.559
sky fire, so no one can read your mind.

02:42:22.620 --> 02:42:25.440
I can be a little worried about super

02:42:25.440 --> 02:42:27.540
strength, Winter growled.

02:42:27.600 --> 02:42:29.940
And whatever that other one can do.

02:42:30.059 --> 02:42:33.659
Make bananas, Kibley filled in.

02:42:33.719 --> 02:42:35.579
Absolutely terrifying.

02:42:35.639 --> 02:42:36.899
Run for your life.

02:42:36.959 --> 02:42:39.360
Winter narrowed his eyes at his

02:42:39.360 --> 02:42:39.899
clawmate.

02:42:39.959 --> 02:42:42.959
So what is Dark Stalker up to?

02:42:43.020 --> 02:42:44.639
Kibley said thoughtfully.

02:42:44.700 --> 02:42:46.020
What does he want?

02:42:46.079 --> 02:42:49.319
Seems obvious to those of us whose brains

02:42:49.319 --> 02:42:49.739
work.

02:42:49.799 --> 02:42:51.479
Winter snapped at him.

02:42:51.540 --> 02:42:53.280
He wants to make friends and help

02:42:53.280 --> 02:42:53.879
dragons.

02:42:54.000 --> 02:42:57.719
That is what it looks like said Turtle.

02:42:57.780 --> 02:42:59.459
It's really confusing.

02:42:59.520 --> 02:43:01.860
He's only done good things all day.

02:43:01.920 --> 02:43:05.819
As far as we can see, Kibley pointed

02:43:05.819 --> 02:43:06.000
out.

02:43:06.059 --> 02:43:08.219
We don't know what he might be doing in

02:43:08.219 --> 02:43:10.739
secret, that being the entire point of

02:43:10.739 --> 02:43:11.399
secrecy.

02:43:11.459 --> 02:43:14.280
Why do you have to be so suspicious?

02:43:14.340 --> 02:43:15.899
Winter flared.

02:43:15.959 --> 02:43:18.299
Dark Stalker is the one who saved Stone

02:43:18.299 --> 02:43:18.840
Mover.

02:43:18.899 --> 02:43:21.120
He's a good dragon with a good heart.

02:43:21.180 --> 02:43:25.200
Also that, said Kibley.

02:43:25.260 --> 02:43:27.840
Does that sound like our winter at all?

02:43:27.899 --> 02:43:30.959
Remember yesterday, when he was yelling

02:43:30.959 --> 02:43:32.760
at Moon about how you could never trust

02:43:32.760 --> 02:43:33.840
Dark Stalker?

02:43:33.899 --> 02:43:36.120
Wouldn't he normally be more suspicious

02:43:36.120 --> 02:43:36.840
than anyone else?

02:43:36.899 --> 02:43:40.799
I've changed and grown, Winter

02:43:40.799 --> 02:43:41.280
protested.

02:43:41.340 --> 02:43:44.340
I'm a much more open-minded dragon since

02:43:44.340 --> 02:43:46.680
my parents decided to sacrifice my life

02:43:46.680 --> 02:43:48.899
in exchange for my brother's place on a

02:43:48.899 --> 02:43:49.139
wall.

02:43:49.200 --> 02:43:53.040
I'm sure you are a winter, but still

02:43:53.040 --> 02:43:55.559
Kimberly spread his front talons.

02:43:55.620 --> 02:43:59.159
Listen, I'm just picturing myself as a

02:43:59.159 --> 02:44:00.120
dark stalker, right?

02:44:00.180 --> 02:44:03.420
So I pop out of a mountain, and yikes

02:44:03.420 --> 02:44:06.780
here's a fierce, smart, excessively shiny

02:44:06.780 --> 02:44:09.540
ice wing print, with an ego the size of

02:44:09.540 --> 02:44:12.000
an iceberg, and a 1000000 potential great

02:44:12.000 --> 02:44:12.540
futures.

02:44:12.600 --> 02:44:16.020
I'm pretty sure I'd think, hmm, that

02:44:16.020 --> 02:44:17.700
dragon could be a serious threat.

02:44:17.760 --> 02:44:20.760
And then I'd think, 1st thing I'd better

02:44:20.760 --> 02:44:22.260
do is neutralize you.

02:44:22.319 --> 02:44:24.540
I'm just wondering if that's what he

02:44:24.540 --> 02:44:25.020
did.

02:44:25.079 --> 02:44:28.079
Winter fluffed his wings, as though he

02:44:28.079 --> 02:44:29.639
wasn't sure whether to be flattered or

02:44:29.639 --> 02:44:30.000
offended.

02:44:30.059 --> 02:44:32.700
Well, stop wondering.

02:44:32.760 --> 02:44:34.799
I would know if I was under a spell.

02:44:34.860 --> 02:44:36.959
Right.

02:44:37.020 --> 02:44:39.600
Of course, said Kibley.

02:44:39.659 --> 02:44:43.139
With your magic ice wing brain.

02:44:43.200 --> 02:44:46.500
How exactly would you know, Lord Genius?

02:44:46.559 --> 02:44:49.079
I don't have to stay and listen to this

02:44:49.079 --> 02:44:52.020
Winter said, flouncing out of the cave.

02:44:52.079 --> 02:44:54.180
Kibley poked his head out the door to

02:44:54.180 --> 02:44:56.399
watch until winter was gone, then came

02:44:56.399 --> 02:44:58.319
back inside and sat down in front of

02:44:58.319 --> 02:45:00.180
Turtle with a rueful expression.

02:45:00.239 --> 02:45:03.360
I have a really bad feeling that he's

02:45:03.360 --> 02:45:04.920
gone to tell Dark Stalker about this

02:45:04.920 --> 02:45:05.340
conversation.

02:45:05.399 --> 02:45:08.940
He can't tell him about me, though, said

02:45:08.940 --> 02:45:12.180
Turtle, or if he does, Dark Stalker won't

02:45:12.180 --> 02:45:12.420
hear it.

02:45:12.479 --> 02:45:15.000
My enchantment hides me completely from

02:45:15.000 --> 02:45:15.180
him.

02:45:15.239 --> 02:45:18.299
I hope, I hope, I hope, I hope.

02:45:18.420 --> 02:45:21.719
If I did it right, which seems unlikely

02:45:21.719 --> 02:45:23.459
knowing me.

02:45:23.520 --> 02:45:26.879
That's clever, said Kibley.

02:45:26.940 --> 02:45:27.959
How did you think of that?

02:45:28.079 --> 02:45:31.319
I used this brainstorming method called

02:45:31.319 --> 02:45:34.200
pure terror, turtle admitted.

02:45:34.260 --> 02:45:37.139
It wasn't so much clever as deeply

02:45:37.139 --> 02:45:37.979
cowardly.

02:45:38.040 --> 02:45:40.079
How does your soul feel?

02:45:40.139 --> 02:45:42.840
Like it's still there?

02:45:42.899 --> 02:45:44.879
Turtle said with a shrug.

02:45:44.940 --> 02:45:47.399
He wasn't going to talk about the flashes

02:45:47.399 --> 02:45:50.159
of screaming chameleon in his head, or

02:45:50.159 --> 02:45:51.840
the way his heart sped up when he thought

02:45:51.840 --> 02:45:53.879
about how he'd do the same thing again to

02:45:53.879 --> 02:45:55.680
anyone else who hurt Kinkachu.

02:45:55.739 --> 02:45:58.440
Would you be willing to do a couple more

02:45:58.440 --> 02:45:59.100
spells?

02:45:59.219 --> 02:46:00.420
Kibley asked.

02:46:00.479 --> 02:46:03.540
If I had any powers of my own, I wouldn't

02:46:03.540 --> 02:46:03.780
ask.

02:46:03.840 --> 02:46:06.180
Oh, said Turtle.

02:46:06.239 --> 02:46:09.239
I mean, yes, I suppose so.

02:46:09.299 --> 02:46:11.940
The problem is, I don't know what.

02:46:12.000 --> 02:46:14.219
I've been thinking about it all day.

02:46:14.280 --> 02:46:16.860
I should be able to do something useful

02:46:16.860 --> 02:46:17.280
shouldn't I?

02:46:17.340 --> 02:46:19.860
If I can just figure out the exact right

02:46:19.860 --> 02:46:20.340
thing.

02:46:20.399 --> 02:46:23.459
Peril wanted me to kill Dark Stalker.

02:46:23.520 --> 02:46:25.260
But I don't think that's possible.

02:46:25.319 --> 02:46:29.280
And I'm just, not the kind of dragon who

02:46:29.280 --> 02:46:30.659
kills other dragons.

02:46:30.780 --> 02:46:32.340
I don't want to be.

02:46:32.459 --> 02:46:34.440
The flashes again.

02:46:34.559 --> 02:46:37.260
The enchanted scroll case smashing into

02:46:37.260 --> 02:46:40.260
chameleon's face, the blood flying, the

02:46:40.260 --> 02:46:43.079
power tingling in turtle's claws, the

02:46:43.079 --> 02:46:44.700
power to punish those who deserved

02:46:44.700 --> 02:46:47.760
punishing, the power to cause violence

02:46:47.760 --> 02:46:49.559
with a twitch of one talon.

02:46:49.559 --> 02:46:51.239
No.

02:46:51.239 --> 02:46:53.760
No, no, no, that's not me.

02:46:53.819 --> 02:46:57.540
Plus, what if he actually is good?

02:46:57.659 --> 02:47:00.540
He hurried on, pushing the images away.

02:47:00.600 --> 02:47:03.299
Winter is not the only one who thinks

02:47:03.299 --> 02:47:03.479
so.

02:47:03.540 --> 02:47:06.899
Peril does, and I think Moon does too.

02:47:07.020 --> 02:47:09.420
Then it would be really wrong to kill

02:47:09.420 --> 02:47:09.780
him.

02:47:09.840 --> 02:47:12.600
So then I wondered if I should do

02:47:12.600 --> 02:47:14.700
something to protect anemone from him

02:47:14.700 --> 02:47:14.879
right?

02:47:14.940 --> 02:47:16.319
Just in case.

02:47:16.440 --> 02:47:18.659
But I don't want to do anything he might

02:47:18.659 --> 02:47:20.159
notice, you know?

02:47:20.219 --> 02:47:22.260
That's the most important thing.

02:47:22.319 --> 02:47:25.139
I don't want him to suspect, there's

02:47:25.139 --> 02:47:27.780
another animus out here, just in case

02:47:27.780 --> 02:47:28.680
he's evil.

02:47:28.799 --> 02:47:31.079
I don't want him to have any clues that I

02:47:31.079 --> 02:47:31.379
exist.

02:47:31.440 --> 02:47:35.040
He shifted his tail, thinking of all the

02:47:35.040 --> 02:47:37.079
heroes his mother had ever written about

02:47:37.079 --> 02:47:39.000
and how none of them would have ever said

02:47:39.000 --> 02:47:40.860
anything like that.

02:47:40.920 --> 02:47:43.559
I understand, said Kibley.

02:47:43.620 --> 02:47:44.879
He took a deep breath.

02:47:44.940 --> 02:47:46.920
This is something small.

02:47:46.979 --> 02:47:50.340
I was hoping you could tell me if there's

02:47:50.340 --> 02:47:51.000
a spell on me.

02:47:51.120 --> 02:47:53.040
On you?

02:47:53.159 --> 02:47:55.200
Turtle said, startled.

02:47:55.260 --> 02:47:58.620
Remember that little fight I just had

02:47:58.620 --> 02:47:59.340
with the winter.

02:47:59.399 --> 02:48:01.200
Kibley said wryly.

02:48:01.319 --> 02:48:02.819
Applies to me too.

02:48:02.879 --> 02:48:06.239
The thing that bothers me is, I like Dark

02:48:06.239 --> 02:48:06.780
Stalker.

02:48:06.840 --> 02:48:10.260
He's funny and charming, and he does seem

02:48:10.260 --> 02:48:10.739
helpful.

02:48:10.739 --> 02:48:13.799
Andy acts like I'm an important, valuable

02:48:13.799 --> 02:48:14.280
dragon.

02:48:14.340 --> 02:48:17.280
Why aren't I more suspicious?

02:48:17.340 --> 02:48:20.219
I can think logically of all these doubts

02:48:20.219 --> 02:48:22.260
and worries, but none of them seem to

02:48:22.260 --> 02:48:25.319
change the way I feel, and that makes me

02:48:25.319 --> 02:48:28.139
crazy, because I've always trusted my

02:48:28.139 --> 02:48:30.899
mind to figure things out for me when my

02:48:30.899 --> 02:48:31.379
gut is wrong.

02:48:31.440 --> 02:48:34.559
All right, said Turtle.

02:48:34.620 --> 02:48:36.780
But the spell might not be on you.

02:48:36.840 --> 02:48:39.659
It might be on something else, like the

02:48:39.659 --> 02:48:41.819
earring Dark Stalker is wearing, and it

02:48:41.819 --> 02:48:43.260
might apply to everyone around him.

02:48:43.319 --> 02:48:45.540
Kibli frowned.

02:48:45.659 --> 02:48:47.100
I hadn't thought of that.

02:48:47.219 --> 02:48:49.379
He tapped his claws.

02:48:49.440 --> 02:48:51.239
Then what else can we do?

02:48:51.299 --> 02:48:52.979
Could you?

02:48:53.100 --> 02:48:54.479
He hesitated.

02:48:54.540 --> 02:48:56.819
You probably wouldn't want to do this.

02:48:56.879 --> 02:48:58.379
What?

02:48:58.440 --> 02:49:01.799
Kibli traced to crack in the cave wall

02:49:01.799 --> 02:49:02.819
with one of his claws.

02:49:02.879 --> 02:49:04.620
Could.

02:49:05.340 --> 02:49:07.799
Could you turn me into an animus dragon

02:49:07.799 --> 02:49:08.159
too?

02:49:08.219 --> 02:49:11.459
Turtle's stomach gave a guilty lurch.

02:49:11.520 --> 02:49:14.219
I shouldn't, he said.

02:49:14.280 --> 02:49:15.899
You wouldn't want that.

02:49:15.959 --> 02:49:18.899
You think you do, but you really don't.

02:49:18.959 --> 02:49:22.200
I'd be careful, Kibley insisted.

02:49:22.260 --> 02:49:24.719
I'd protect my soul 1st thing, I

02:49:24.719 --> 02:49:25.020
promise.

02:49:25.079 --> 02:49:27.239
For my very 1st spell.

02:49:27.299 --> 02:49:29.940
I'd enchant something to make sure my

02:49:29.940 --> 02:49:31.139
soul was always good.

02:49:31.200 --> 02:49:34.079
Or that I always made the kind and right

02:49:34.079 --> 02:49:36.479
choice that helped the most dragons.

02:49:36.540 --> 02:49:38.219
Doesn't that make sense?

02:49:38.280 --> 02:49:40.860
He looked down at his claws.

02:49:40.920 --> 02:49:43.920
That's what I would have done, with Dark

02:49:43.920 --> 02:49:46.079
Stalker scroll too, in case you were

02:49:46.079 --> 02:49:46.379
wondering.

02:49:46.440 --> 02:49:49.440
Toto remembered the fight Winter and

02:49:49.440 --> 02:49:51.899
Kibley had had over who could keep dark

02:49:51.899 --> 02:49:53.579
stalkers scroll and use it for

02:49:53.579 --> 02:49:54.000
themselves.

02:49:54.059 --> 02:49:57.299
It had scared him, but not as much as

02:49:57.299 --> 02:49:58.260
Dark Stalker did.

02:49:58.319 --> 02:50:01.559
What would the world look like if either

02:50:01.559 --> 02:50:03.780
Winter or Kibling now had all this power

02:50:03.780 --> 02:50:04.260
instead?

02:50:04.379 --> 02:50:09.120
I believe you, he said, but I still don't

02:50:09.120 --> 02:50:09.959
think it's a good idea.

02:50:10.020 --> 02:50:13.739
Making him an animus would put Kibli in

02:50:13.739 --> 02:50:14.819
danger in too many ways.

02:50:14.879 --> 02:50:17.459
Turtle would always feel responsible for

02:50:17.459 --> 02:50:18.479
whatever happened to him.

02:50:18.540 --> 02:50:21.000
Sure, that's all right.

02:50:21.059 --> 02:50:22.860
Kibley said quickly.

02:50:22.920 --> 02:50:24.299
Sorry I asked.

02:50:24.360 --> 02:50:26.879
I'd probably feel weird about making more

02:50:26.879 --> 02:50:28.739
animous dragons if I were one too.

02:50:28.799 --> 02:50:31.979
It's not turtle started.

02:50:32.040 --> 02:50:34.559
I mean, it's not you.

02:50:34.620 --> 02:50:36.059
I'm not trying to.

02:50:36.180 --> 02:50:38.879
Don't worry about it, Kibley said

02:50:38.879 --> 02:50:40.200
fiddling with his earring.

02:50:40.260 --> 02:50:42.360
Maybe something else would make more

02:50:42.360 --> 02:50:42.959
sense anyway.

02:50:43.020 --> 02:50:46.319
Can you make me immune to anima spells?

02:50:46.379 --> 02:50:49.440
It was strange to be discussing his power

02:50:49.440 --> 02:50:50.760
openly with another dragon.

02:50:50.819 --> 02:50:54.360
Strange to be taking someone's advice, and

02:50:54.360 --> 02:50:55.920
to know that the other dragon would never

02:50:55.920 --> 02:50:57.899
be able to stop wanting things from him

02:50:57.899 --> 02:51:01.020
even if it was a friend, like Kibley.

02:51:01.079 --> 02:51:03.659
All anima spells.

02:51:03.780 --> 02:51:04.920
Ask Turtle.

02:51:04.979 --> 02:51:05.760
Are you sure?

02:51:05.819 --> 02:51:08.639
I mean, some spells are good, aren't

02:51:08.639 --> 02:51:08.760
they?

02:51:08.879 --> 02:51:11.459
Like my healing rock, or the dream

02:51:11.459 --> 02:51:12.120
visitors?

02:51:12.180 --> 02:51:14.459
Being immune means those wouldn't work on

02:51:14.459 --> 02:51:14.879
you anymore.

02:51:14.940 --> 02:51:18.479
And if you're completely immune, then an

02:51:18.479 --> 02:51:20.579
animus couldn't even change you back if

02:51:20.579 --> 02:51:21.420
you changed your mind.

02:51:21.479 --> 02:51:25.020
That's true, said Kibley.

02:51:25.079 --> 02:51:27.420
What if you just made me immune to dark

02:51:27.420 --> 02:51:28.260
stalker spells then?

02:51:28.379 --> 02:51:31.079
Don't you think he'd notice?

02:51:31.200 --> 02:51:32.520
Turtle fretted.

02:51:32.579 --> 02:51:34.680
If he suddenly couldn't control you?

02:51:34.739 --> 02:51:37.079
Or he tried to cast a spell and you

02:51:37.079 --> 02:51:37.500
didn't react.

02:51:37.620 --> 02:51:41.219
He'd get really suspicious, wouldn't he?

02:51:41.280 --> 02:51:44.760
I'll take that risk, Kibble said.

02:51:44.819 --> 02:51:47.040
He tapped his claws against the floor in

02:51:47.040 --> 02:51:48.479
a nervous drumbeat rhythm.

02:51:48.540 --> 02:51:50.940
As long as he can't use magic against

02:51:50.940 --> 02:51:51.239
me.

02:51:51.299 --> 02:51:53.219
I can handle anything else he does.

02:51:53.280 --> 02:51:57.719
Oh, Turtle said, feeling like even more

02:51:57.719 --> 02:51:58.620
of an inch worm.

02:51:58.680 --> 02:52:02.879
I meant, yes, of course, suspicious of

02:52:02.879 --> 02:52:05.579
you too, but then he'd know it's a spell

02:52:05.579 --> 02:52:07.319
and that could lead him to me.

02:52:07.379 --> 02:52:12.360
Which, I guess I'm not sure I can handle

02:52:12.360 --> 02:52:13.559
anything else he does.

02:52:13.620 --> 02:52:16.739
Kibli picked up a scroll that had rolled

02:52:16.739 --> 02:52:18.780
across the cavern and tucked it back into

02:52:18.780 --> 02:52:19.860
one of the racks by the door.

02:52:19.979 --> 02:52:23.219
You are some kind of worrying expert

02:52:23.219 --> 02:52:23.940
aren't you?

02:52:24.000 --> 02:52:28.860
Yes, Turtle said, his wings drooping.

02:52:28.920 --> 02:52:29.760
I'm sorry.

02:52:29.879 --> 02:52:32.459
I like to think through everything as

02:52:32.459 --> 02:52:34.680
much as possible before making any big

02:52:34.680 --> 02:52:35.219
decisions.

02:52:35.340 --> 02:52:39.120
That's all right, Kibli reassured him.

02:52:39.180 --> 02:52:40.379
It's smart.

02:52:40.440 --> 02:52:42.479
As long as you can also make decisions

02:52:42.479 --> 02:52:44.639
even when there's not enough time to

02:52:44.639 --> 02:52:45.180
think about them.

02:52:45.239 --> 02:52:47.760
Turtle didn't like that idea.

02:52:47.819 --> 02:52:50.100
It gave him a scrunching feeling in his

02:52:50.100 --> 02:52:50.399
chest.

02:52:50.459 --> 02:52:54.239
Listen, turtle, it's your magic.

02:52:54.299 --> 02:52:56.340
You're the boss of whether you want to

02:52:56.340 --> 02:52:56.700
use it.

02:52:56.760 --> 02:53:00.180
But I look at winter and I think, that is

02:53:00.180 --> 02:53:03.180
not the normal behavior of her majesty

02:53:03.180 --> 02:53:04.500
Queen Glacier's nephew.

02:53:04.620 --> 02:53:07.440
And then I think, what about me?

02:53:07.500 --> 02:53:10.079
What if I'm acting like a hallucinating

02:53:10.079 --> 02:53:11.399
sun baked lizard?

02:53:11.459 --> 02:53:12.299
And I have no idea.

02:53:12.360 --> 02:53:16.500
You seem normal to me, Turtle said.

02:53:16.559 --> 02:53:17.760
Does that help?

02:53:17.819 --> 02:53:21.479
Kibli shrugged and turned away, rolling

02:53:21.479 --> 02:53:22.559
up another scroll.

02:53:22.680 --> 02:53:25.079
I need to know my mind is my own.

02:53:25.139 --> 02:53:25.979
That's all.

02:53:26.100 --> 02:53:27.540
It's all I have.

02:53:27.600 --> 02:53:29.399
No superpowers.

02:53:29.459 --> 02:53:32.280
No fire scales, no royal family.

02:53:32.340 --> 02:53:35.700
Just me and my brain, if it's working.

02:53:35.760 --> 02:53:39.120
I am the lowest of cowards.

02:53:39.180 --> 02:53:42.899
How can I say no to the one dragon who's

02:53:42.899 --> 02:53:44.459
still willing to think twice about Dark

02:53:44.459 --> 02:53:45.000
Stalker?

02:53:45.059 --> 02:53:47.879
To my friend who needs protection.

02:53:47.940 --> 02:53:51.059
I'll do it, Turtle said.

02:53:51.120 --> 02:53:52.200
Of course I will.

02:53:52.260 --> 02:53:54.479
Immune to dark stalker spells.

02:53:54.540 --> 02:53:55.500
That's what you want?

02:53:55.559 --> 02:53:57.299
Really?

02:53:57.360 --> 02:53:59.760
Kibley said, his face alight.

02:53:59.819 --> 02:54:00.780
Yes.

02:54:00.840 --> 02:54:01.860
That would be amazing.

02:54:01.920 --> 02:54:03.780
Here, enchant my earring.

02:54:03.840 --> 02:54:07.020
He took it off and dropped the small gold

02:54:07.020 --> 02:54:09.299
and amber earring into Turtle's palm.

02:54:09.360 --> 02:54:11.340
Do you know what you're going to say?

02:54:11.399 --> 02:54:13.319
Want me to write down some ideas?

02:54:13.440 --> 02:54:16.500
He seized a scroll in a pot of ink before

02:54:16.500 --> 02:54:18.180
Turtle could answer, and started

02:54:18.180 --> 02:54:20.219
scribbling on a blank corner.

02:54:20.280 --> 02:54:23.159
If this works, he went on, we could do a

02:54:23.159 --> 02:54:24.719
spell like this for winter too, couldn't

02:54:24.719 --> 02:54:24.899
we?

02:54:24.959 --> 02:54:26.700
Sure.

02:54:26.760 --> 02:54:28.860
Turtle said uncomfortably.

02:54:28.920 --> 02:54:32.879
Here I go again, helping my friends, which

02:54:32.879 --> 02:54:35.159
could mean getting noticed, which will

02:54:35.159 --> 02:54:37.559
surely lead to getting caught and slowly

02:54:37.559 --> 02:54:40.139
dismembered by a giant nightmare dragon

02:54:40.139 --> 02:54:40.620
from the past.

02:54:40.680 --> 02:54:44.100
There weren't any stories in the scrolls

02:54:44.100 --> 02:54:44.459
like this.

02:54:44.520 --> 02:54:47.459
He didn't know quite what role Kibley saw

02:54:47.459 --> 02:54:48.239
Turtle playing.

02:54:48.299 --> 02:54:49.860
Helpful Wizard.

02:54:49.920 --> 02:54:53.340
Those often died by the end too, or maybe

02:54:53.340 --> 02:54:55.559
in Kibley's story, Turtle was the

02:54:55.559 --> 02:54:58.020
enchanted fish, who granted 3 wishes if

02:54:58.020 --> 02:54:58.620
you caught him.

02:54:58.680 --> 02:55:01.440
You've got 2 left, Kibley.

02:55:01.500 --> 02:55:03.059
Turtle thought wryly.

02:55:03.120 --> 02:55:05.399
Then I think I can turn your nose into a

02:55:05.399 --> 02:55:07.440
sausage and escape back into the sea.

02:55:07.500 --> 02:55:09.360
Wait.

02:55:09.420 --> 02:55:12.540
Kibley said, lifting his ink stained claw

02:55:12.540 --> 02:55:13.200
from the scroll.

02:55:13.260 --> 02:55:15.659
Have you made something to protect your

02:55:15.659 --> 02:55:16.139
soul yet?

02:55:16.200 --> 02:55:18.479
Um...

02:55:18.479 --> 02:55:20.940
No, Turtle said.

02:55:21.000 --> 02:55:23.280
I mean, I think it's fine.

02:55:23.340 --> 02:55:26.940
You should do that first, Kibley said.

02:55:27.000 --> 02:55:29.340
He started absent-mindedly drawing a

02:55:29.340 --> 02:55:31.260
series of concentric circles around the

02:55:31.260 --> 02:55:32.579
words he'd written on the scroll.

02:55:32.579 --> 02:55:35.340
Something like what dark stalker and

02:55:35.340 --> 02:55:36.120
anemone have.

02:55:36.180 --> 02:55:37.799
That's more important than this.

02:55:37.920 --> 02:55:42.659
Let's do this first, Turtle said, reaching

02:55:42.659 --> 02:55:45.120
for the scroll. since it's all ready to

02:55:45.120 --> 02:55:45.299
go.

02:55:45.360 --> 02:55:48.239
It could take me all night to decide how

02:55:48.239 --> 02:55:49.260
to do the soul spell.

02:55:49.319 --> 02:55:52.379
He tried to return Kibley's grin.

02:55:52.440 --> 02:55:55.979
If you're sure, Kibley said, and you're

02:55:55.979 --> 02:55:57.479
feeling totally nonviolent.

02:55:57.540 --> 02:56:00.360
Turtle read the words carefully a few

02:56:00.360 --> 02:56:02.819
times, then focused on the small amber

02:56:02.819 --> 02:56:05.159
teardrop in his palm, glowing like

02:56:05.159 --> 02:56:06.780
sunlight against the dark green.

02:56:06.840 --> 02:56:11.159
Enchant this earring to make the wearer

02:56:11.159 --> 02:56:14.280
immune to any spell, dark stalker has

02:56:14.280 --> 02:56:18.479
cast, or will cast, whether past, present

02:56:18.479 --> 02:56:19.440
or future.

02:56:19.500 --> 02:56:22.739
Kibli inspected the earring like a poorly

02:56:22.739 --> 02:56:25.020
drawn map, then picked it up between 2

02:56:25.020 --> 02:56:26.219
claws to squint at it.

02:56:26.280 --> 02:56:28.799
I thought it would get all sparkly or

02:56:28.799 --> 02:56:29.879
something, he said.

02:56:29.940 --> 02:56:32.819
See if it makes you feel any different.

02:56:32.879 --> 02:56:34.620
Turtle suggested.

02:56:34.680 --> 02:56:37.139
The sand wing slipped it back through the

02:56:37.139 --> 02:56:39.000
hole in his ear and blinked a few times.

02:56:39.059 --> 02:56:41.040
Huh, he said.

02:56:41.100 --> 02:56:42.659
I think so.

02:56:42.719 --> 02:56:44.760
You think so?

02:56:44.819 --> 02:56:47.459
Turtle echoed, somewhat disappointed.

02:56:47.520 --> 02:56:50.579
If he was going to use his magic, he

02:56:50.579 --> 02:56:53.100
wanted it to make a big, obvious, cool

02:56:53.100 --> 02:56:54.059
helpful difference.

02:56:54.120 --> 02:56:57.719
Kibley started pacing, tipping his head

02:56:57.719 --> 02:56:59.940
from side to side, as though he was

02:56:59.940 --> 02:57:01.799
resettling everything inside his skull.

02:57:01.860 --> 02:57:03.540
Let's see.

02:57:03.600 --> 02:57:06.239
I still think dark soccer is funny and

02:57:06.239 --> 02:57:08.639
charming, but I definitely feel more

02:57:08.639 --> 02:57:09.540
anxious about that.

02:57:09.600 --> 02:57:13.500
There was this calm trusting feeling I

02:57:13.500 --> 02:57:15.899
had before, and that's vanished.

02:57:15.959 --> 02:57:19.920
Could be a coincidence, Turtle observed.

02:57:19.979 --> 02:57:22.739
Like, all psychological?

02:57:22.860 --> 02:57:24.540
No.

02:57:24.600 --> 02:57:26.940
Kibley stopped in front of him and met

02:57:26.940 --> 02:57:27.780
Turtle's eyes.

02:57:27.840 --> 02:57:30.659
I feel like my mind and my instincts are

02:57:30.659 --> 02:57:32.579
linked up again, which is really

02:57:32.579 --> 02:57:33.239
important to me.

02:57:33.299 --> 02:57:34.620
Thank you.

02:57:34.680 --> 02:57:37.379
Hmm, Turtle said.

02:57:37.500 --> 02:57:39.540
This didn't seem like a particularly

02:57:39.540 --> 02:57:41.459
useful use of his magic, honestly.

02:57:41.520 --> 02:57:44.040
He guessed Kibley hadn't been under a

02:57:44.040 --> 02:57:44.579
spell at all.

02:57:44.639 --> 02:57:47.700
Dark soccer was charming and convincing

02:57:47.700 --> 02:57:49.139
enough to win everyone over without

02:57:49.139 --> 02:57:49.559
magic.

02:57:49.620 --> 02:57:52.920
I can help you figure out your soul spell

02:57:52.920 --> 02:57:54.180
Kibley offered.

02:57:54.239 --> 02:57:56.700
I know how I'd phrase mine, if I could

02:57:56.700 --> 02:57:57.959
protect my soul with magic.

02:57:58.020 --> 02:58:00.780
You've thought about it that much?

02:58:00.959 --> 02:58:02.219
asked Turtle.

02:58:02.280 --> 02:58:04.500
When have you ever had to worry about

02:58:04.500 --> 02:58:05.159
your soul?

02:58:05.219 --> 02:58:07.920
Aren't you one of those naturally heroic

02:58:07.920 --> 02:58:08.399
dragons?

02:58:08.459 --> 02:58:11.100
Kibli let out a startled laugh.

02:58:11.159 --> 02:58:13.379
No way, he said.

02:58:13.440 --> 02:58:15.840
I grew up in the scorpion den, remember?

02:58:15.899 --> 02:58:17.639
I was stealing before I could fly.

02:58:17.700 --> 02:58:21.059
My mother was an assassin, who tried to

02:58:21.059 --> 02:58:22.979
teach me garroting and poisons instead of

02:58:22.979 --> 02:58:23.639
reading and writing.

02:58:23.700 --> 02:58:25.979
I've done lots of bad things.

02:58:26.040 --> 02:58:28.680
And the problem is, I know I do more if

02:58:28.680 --> 02:58:31.979
it was for, for, um, Queen Thorn.

02:58:32.040 --> 02:58:35.340
I guess I could make you a soul spell

02:58:35.340 --> 02:58:35.819
too.

02:58:35.879 --> 02:58:37.200
Turtle offered.

02:58:37.260 --> 02:58:39.000
Trying to hide is reluctance.

02:58:39.059 --> 02:58:40.440
What was wrong with him?

02:58:40.500 --> 02:58:43.139
Dark Stalker was giving out powers all

02:58:43.139 --> 02:58:45.600
over the place, helping other dragons he

02:58:45.600 --> 02:58:46.079
barely knew.

02:58:46.200 --> 02:58:49.139
Why couldn't Turtle be equally willing to

02:58:49.139 --> 02:58:50.579
share with his closest friends?

02:58:50.639 --> 02:58:53.219
Was it just that he was afraid of being

02:58:53.219 --> 02:58:53.819
exposed?

02:58:53.879 --> 02:58:56.459
Or was he worried about how the magic

02:58:56.459 --> 02:58:57.420
might affect his friends?

02:58:57.479 --> 02:58:59.459
Thanks.

02:58:59.520 --> 02:59:02.579
Kibley said, pinning down the scroll he'd

02:59:02.579 --> 02:59:03.059
been riding on.

02:59:03.120 --> 02:59:05.639
But let's make sure yours is safe first.

02:59:05.700 --> 02:59:08.340
Maybe that's it.

02:59:08.399 --> 02:59:10.139
Turtle thought anxiously.

02:59:10.200 --> 02:59:13.379
Maybe my soul isn't as fine as I think it

02:59:13.379 --> 02:59:13.620
is.

02:59:13.739 --> 02:59:16.739
Maybe using my magic has made me selfish

02:59:16.739 --> 02:59:18.239
and a terrible friend.

02:59:18.299 --> 02:59:21.659
Kibley blew a small flame on the corner

02:59:21.659 --> 02:59:23.639
where he'd written the 1st spell.

02:59:23.700 --> 02:59:26.159
As it burned away, he checked the other

02:59:26.159 --> 02:59:27.780
side of the scroll and made a face.

02:59:27.899 --> 02:59:31.260
I probably shouldn't have used my history

02:59:31.260 --> 02:59:33.000
reading for this, he said.

02:59:33.059 --> 02:59:34.440
Well, too late now.

02:59:34.500 --> 02:59:36.180
It was really boring anyway.

02:59:36.239 --> 02:59:37.139
All right.

02:59:37.200 --> 02:59:39.540
One soul spell coming right.

02:59:39.600 --> 02:59:42.540
A sudden thud from above shook the

02:59:42.540 --> 02:59:43.020
caves.

02:59:43.079 --> 02:59:44.879
Kibli and Turtle looked up.

02:59:44.940 --> 02:59:47.700
Then at each other as more thuds followed

02:59:47.700 --> 02:59:50.219
and then the scraping of scales and claws

02:59:50.219 --> 02:59:52.079
against rock echoed down the tunnels.

02:59:52.139 --> 02:59:54.360
What is?

02:59:54.780 --> 02:59:56.639
Kibley started toward the door, but

02:59:56.639 --> 02:59:58.920
before he could get there, Black scales

02:59:58.920 --> 03:00:01.379
blotted out the fire globes, and dark

03:00:01.379 --> 03:00:03.420
stalker was squeezing his head and

03:00:03.420 --> 03:00:05.520
shoulders through the narrow space to

03:00:05.520 --> 03:00:06.840
peer into Kibley's room.

03:00:06.899 --> 03:00:10.559
Turtles scramble to the back wall as far

03:00:10.559 --> 03:00:11.399
away as he could get.

03:00:11.459 --> 03:00:13.500
Why is he here?

03:00:13.559 --> 03:00:14.219
Why is he here?

03:00:14.340 --> 03:00:16.979
It took all his willpower not to close

03:00:16.979 --> 03:00:18.719
his eyes and curl up completely.

03:00:18.780 --> 03:00:21.659
He stood perfectly still, as dark

03:00:21.659 --> 03:00:24.299
stalker's sharp gaze scoured the cave.

03:00:24.360 --> 03:00:26.940
That looks uncomfortable.

03:00:27.059 --> 03:00:29.520
Kibley said to Dark Stalker, in a

03:00:29.520 --> 03:00:31.799
friendly voice, I can't believe you

03:00:31.799 --> 03:00:33.299
squashed yourself into our tunnels.

03:00:33.420 --> 03:00:35.340
Not a problem.

03:00:35.459 --> 03:00:38.459
Dark Stalker said, a bit breathlessly.

03:00:38.520 --> 03:00:41.159
I'm surprisingly squishy.

03:00:41.219 --> 03:00:43.680
He grinned at Kibley, but there was

03:00:43.680 --> 03:00:44.879
something a little forced about his

03:00:44.879 --> 03:00:45.180
smile.

03:00:45.299 --> 03:00:47.760
This is your cave.

03:00:47.819 --> 03:00:50.399
I thought it might be anemones.

03:00:50.459 --> 03:00:52.920
What were you just doing in here?

03:00:52.979 --> 03:00:55.979
Looking at scrolls?

03:00:56.100 --> 03:00:58.799
Kibley said, waving at the ripples of

03:00:58.799 --> 03:01:00.420
paper that covered his sleeping ledge

03:01:00.420 --> 03:01:02.819
trying to figure out if I should bother

03:01:02.819 --> 03:01:05.459
studying, accidentally setting history on

03:01:05.459 --> 03:01:05.819
fire.

03:01:05.879 --> 03:01:07.260
The usual?

03:01:07.319 --> 03:01:09.899
He waved at the thin trail of smoke that

03:01:09.899 --> 03:01:11.459
was still rising from the scroll on the

03:01:11.459 --> 03:01:11.700
floor.

03:01:11.760 --> 03:01:15.479
Dark stalkers studied each outcropping

03:01:15.479 --> 03:01:18.420
each shadow with such slicing intensity

03:01:18.420 --> 03:01:21.360
that Turtle was sure he'd be seen, and

03:01:21.360 --> 03:01:24.479
not just seen, but peeled and flayed from

03:01:24.479 --> 03:01:26.639
horns to tail by those searching eyes.

03:01:26.700 --> 03:01:28.799
Is something wrong?

03:01:28.860 --> 03:01:30.360
Kibli asked.

03:01:30.420 --> 03:01:33.360
Was anemone in here a moment ago.

03:01:33.420 --> 03:01:35.100
Dark Stalker asked.

03:01:35.159 --> 03:01:39.840
No, Kibley said cautiously, I haven't

03:01:39.840 --> 03:01:40.200
seen her.

03:01:40.260 --> 03:01:42.479
Oh, you sure?

03:01:42.540 --> 03:01:44.340
Dark Stalker demanded.

03:01:44.399 --> 03:01:46.200
Or maybe passing by.

03:01:46.260 --> 03:01:49.260
She might have been talking to herself, or

03:01:49.260 --> 03:01:50.280
doing something unusual.

03:01:50.340 --> 03:01:53.819
A lightning bolt of fear scorched through

03:01:53.819 --> 03:01:54.600
turtle's body.

03:01:54.659 --> 03:01:57.360
The spell on Kibley's earring.

03:01:57.479 --> 03:01:59.940
Dark stalker showing up only moments

03:01:59.940 --> 03:02:01.559
later asking about anemone.

03:02:01.620 --> 03:02:03.959
He was looking for the source of a

03:02:03.959 --> 03:02:04.860
spell.

03:02:04.920 --> 03:02:07.860
Somehow, he knew magic had happened here

03:02:07.860 --> 03:02:10.379
and he came immediately to find out what

03:02:10.379 --> 03:02:11.399
anemone was up to.

03:02:11.459 --> 03:02:15.360
Dark stalkers given himself the power to

03:02:15.360 --> 03:02:16.920
sense animus magic.

03:02:16.979 --> 03:02:21.600
Chapter 9.

03:02:21.659 --> 03:02:26.100
If Dark Stalker can tell when an animus

03:02:26.100 --> 03:02:29.579
casts a spell, Turtle realized, his heart

03:02:29.579 --> 03:02:31.920
floundering wildly around in his chest

03:02:31.920 --> 03:02:34.319
then I can never use my magic again.

03:02:34.379 --> 03:02:37.680
Turtle couldn't tell from Kibley's

03:02:37.680 --> 03:02:39.540
expression, whether he'd figured it out

03:02:39.540 --> 03:02:39.840
as well.

03:02:39.899 --> 03:02:43.979
But then Kibley said, oh, anemone.

03:02:44.040 --> 03:02:44.579
Yeah.

03:02:44.639 --> 03:02:46.500
She might have gone by a little while

03:02:46.500 --> 03:02:46.799
ago.

03:02:46.860 --> 03:02:48.239
I'm not totally sure.

03:02:48.299 --> 03:02:50.819
And Turtle knew that he must have made

03:02:50.819 --> 03:02:51.659
the same connections.

03:02:51.719 --> 03:02:53.819
Interesting.

03:02:53.879 --> 03:02:55.799
Dark Stalker mused.

03:02:55.860 --> 03:02:57.659
If you see her.

03:02:57.719 --> 03:02:59.819
Please tell her I wish to speak with her

03:02:59.819 --> 03:03:00.420
as soon as possible.

03:03:00.540 --> 03:03:03.420
Sure. said Kibley.

03:03:03.479 --> 03:03:04.319
You bet.

03:03:04.379 --> 03:03:04.979
I'll do that.

03:03:05.040 --> 03:03:08.159
Dog Stalker gave him another appraising

03:03:08.159 --> 03:03:08.459
look.

03:03:08.520 --> 03:03:10.860
Kibli, he said.

03:03:10.979 --> 03:03:14.159
Please order that scroll to roll itself

03:03:14.159 --> 03:03:14.399
up.

03:03:14.459 --> 03:03:16.440
Kibley laughed.

03:03:16.500 --> 03:03:18.840
Don't you think I've spent my whole life

03:03:18.840 --> 03:03:21.360
hoping magic would suddenly pop out of my

03:03:21.360 --> 03:03:22.620
claws, he said.

03:03:22.680 --> 03:03:24.540
Hey, scroll.

03:03:24.600 --> 03:03:26.280
Roll yourself up.

03:03:26.340 --> 03:03:29.579
The scroll lay there, inert, and

03:03:29.579 --> 03:03:30.299
uninteresting.

03:03:30.420 --> 03:03:33.180
Khibli shrugged at Dark Stalker.

03:03:33.239 --> 03:03:34.500
Disappointed again.

03:03:34.559 --> 03:03:39.719
I think that's for the best, Dark Stalker

03:03:39.719 --> 03:03:41.700
said, smiling at him a bit more

03:03:41.700 --> 03:03:42.420
genuinely.

03:03:42.479 --> 03:03:45.299
With your mind, you'd be a very

03:03:45.299 --> 03:03:46.260
formidable animus.

03:03:46.379 --> 03:03:48.540
He backed out of the cave.

03:03:48.600 --> 03:03:50.100
See you in the morning.

03:03:50.159 --> 03:03:51.659
You too.

03:03:51.719 --> 03:03:53.159
Kibley answered.

03:03:53.219 --> 03:03:56.219
Dark Stalker disappeared down the hall

03:03:56.219 --> 03:03:58.559
with a sound of scraping scales jittering

03:03:58.559 --> 03:04:00.059
through the walls behind him.

03:04:00.120 --> 03:04:01.319
He knew.

03:04:01.440 --> 03:04:02.879
Turtle whispered.

03:04:03.000 --> 03:04:05.459
Not because Dark Stalker might hear him

03:04:05.459 --> 03:04:07.559
but because his voice didn't quite seem

03:04:07.559 --> 03:04:08.639
to be working the way it should.

03:04:08.700 --> 03:04:12.299
He knows when someone is using animus

03:04:12.299 --> 03:04:12.600
magic.

03:04:12.719 --> 03:04:15.479
He must have enchanted something to warn

03:04:15.479 --> 03:04:15.600
him.

03:04:15.659 --> 03:04:18.959
Kibli waited until the vibrations of Dark

03:04:18.959 --> 03:04:20.579
Stalker's passage had faded away.

03:04:20.639 --> 03:04:23.520
Lucky you cast your hiding spell before

03:04:23.520 --> 03:04:24.000
he did that.

03:04:24.059 --> 03:04:25.799
Yes.

03:04:25.860 --> 03:04:27.780
Turtle said fervently.

03:04:27.840 --> 03:04:30.360
You're also lucky he didn't cast the

03:04:30.360 --> 03:04:32.040
enchantment to tell him exactly what the

03:04:32.040 --> 03:04:32.639
spell was.

03:04:32.700 --> 03:04:34.260
Kibley mused.

03:04:34.319 --> 03:04:35.579
That's what I would have done.

03:04:35.700 --> 03:04:37.860
But he didn't act like he knew what we

03:04:37.860 --> 03:04:38.159
did.

03:04:38.219 --> 03:04:40.920
Turtle couldn't speak for a moment.

03:04:40.979 --> 03:04:42.479
He was so appalled.

03:04:42.540 --> 03:04:44.399
He'd come so close to getting caught.

03:04:44.459 --> 03:04:47.639
In a way he hadn't even imagined worrying

03:04:47.639 --> 03:04:50.879
about what other spells did Dark Stalker

03:04:50.879 --> 03:04:52.440
have in place that might tangle him up?

03:04:52.559 --> 03:04:55.860
Now I can't use my magic anymore.

03:04:55.920 --> 03:05:00.780
He finally managed to say, or else he'll

03:05:00.780 --> 03:05:03.000
figure out I'm out here, hiding from

03:05:03.000 --> 03:05:03.239
him.

03:05:03.299 --> 03:05:06.719
His spell seems to be location based

03:05:06.719 --> 03:05:08.159
Kibley pointed out.

03:05:08.219 --> 03:05:10.920
Maybe if you were standing near anemone

03:05:10.920 --> 03:05:12.899
or stone mover when you cast it.

03:05:13.020 --> 03:05:14.639
He'd think it came from one of them.

03:05:14.760 --> 03:05:16.979
Maybe.

03:05:17.040 --> 03:05:19.379
But then wouldn't he ask them what spell

03:05:19.379 --> 03:05:20.579
they just cast?

03:05:20.639 --> 03:05:22.319
And if they say they didn't use their

03:05:22.319 --> 03:05:23.819
magic, what then?

03:05:23.879 --> 03:05:25.620
Would he think they're lying?

03:05:25.680 --> 03:05:28.440
I don't want him to think anemone is

03:05:28.440 --> 03:05:30.540
secretly using her magic, maybe against

03:05:30.540 --> 03:05:30.899
him.

03:05:30.959 --> 03:05:34.139
He worried the edge of a wing between his

03:05:34.139 --> 03:05:34.620
claws.

03:05:34.680 --> 03:05:36.840
I don't want to get her in trouble.

03:05:36.899 --> 03:05:39.120
I don't want him to blame her for what

03:05:39.120 --> 03:05:39.899
I'm doing.

03:05:39.959 --> 03:05:42.959
That's true, said Kibley.

03:05:43.020 --> 03:05:44.940
Yeah, that could be bad.

03:05:45.000 --> 03:05:50.040
Turtle groaned, lying down and covering

03:05:50.040 --> 03:05:51.420
his head with his wings.

03:05:51.479 --> 03:05:54.659
Look, I know it's terrible, but it's

03:05:54.659 --> 03:05:56.340
smart too, said Kibley.

03:05:56.399 --> 03:05:59.280
If you got trapped underground by an

03:05:59.280 --> 03:05:59.940
animus spell.

03:06:00.000 --> 03:06:01.739
Wouldn't you want to keep a pretty close

03:06:01.739 --> 03:06:03.959
eye on any new spells after you got out?

03:06:04.020 --> 03:06:06.540
He's not going to let himself be fooled

03:06:06.540 --> 03:06:06.840
again.

03:06:06.899 --> 03:06:09.420
I'm sorry you didn't get to cast a spell

03:06:09.420 --> 03:06:10.860
to protect your soul, though.

03:06:10.920 --> 03:06:13.139
I'm going home.

03:06:13.200 --> 03:06:16.079
Turtle said, leaping up and whirling

03:06:16.079 --> 03:06:16.620
toward the door.

03:06:16.680 --> 03:06:19.200
I'm going back to the kingdom of the sea

03:06:19.200 --> 03:06:21.120
to hide in the deep palace.

03:06:21.180 --> 03:06:22.440
He can't follow me there.

03:06:22.500 --> 03:06:24.120
Unless he can.

03:06:24.180 --> 03:06:26.340
He could enchant something to let him

03:06:26.340 --> 03:06:28.680
breathe underwater, or something to make

03:06:28.680 --> 03:06:30.479
the entire ocean evaporate.

03:06:30.540 --> 03:06:31.620
He could do anything.

03:06:31.680 --> 03:06:35.040
Moons above stop panicking.

03:06:35.159 --> 03:06:37.440
Kibli jumped in Turtle's way.

03:06:37.500 --> 03:06:38.760
It's not the end of the world.

03:06:38.819 --> 03:06:41.399
This doesn't prove he's evil.

03:06:41.459 --> 03:06:44.280
All we know for sure is he's protecting

03:06:44.280 --> 03:06:44.579
himself.

03:06:44.639 --> 03:06:47.399
So we keep watching him, like you have

03:06:47.399 --> 03:06:47.639
been.

03:06:47.700 --> 03:06:50.760
I can't, Turtle said.

03:06:50.819 --> 03:06:52.920
He's going to the rainforest tomorrow

03:06:52.920 --> 03:06:53.940
with the other night wings.

03:06:54.000 --> 03:06:56.700
All the night wings?

03:06:56.760 --> 03:06:58.680
Kibley asked, including Moon?

03:06:58.739 --> 03:07:00.299
I don't know.

03:07:00.360 --> 03:07:01.559
Turtle answered.

03:07:01.620 --> 03:07:02.639
I think so.

03:07:02.700 --> 03:07:05.700
Kibli thought for a moment, drumming his

03:07:05.700 --> 03:07:06.299
claws again.

03:07:06.360 --> 03:07:08.760
I don't have a good excuse to go along

03:07:08.760 --> 03:07:10.139
with them, he said.

03:07:10.200 --> 03:07:11.639
It'll have to be you.

03:07:11.700 --> 03:07:13.319
Me?

03:07:13.379 --> 03:07:15.360
Turtles said, startled.

03:07:15.420 --> 03:07:18.000
You mean follow him to the rainforest?

03:07:18.059 --> 03:07:21.659
So we can see what he does next, Kibley

03:07:21.659 --> 03:07:21.899
said.

03:07:21.959 --> 03:07:23.399
I can watch things here.

03:07:23.459 --> 03:07:25.860
You know, keep an eye out for any thunder

03:07:25.860 --> 03:07:27.719
and ice coming to destroy the school.

03:07:27.780 --> 03:07:30.120
Then we'll report back to each other and

03:07:30.120 --> 03:07:30.840
see what we think.

03:07:30.899 --> 03:07:33.479
If only we had a dream visitor too.

03:07:33.540 --> 03:07:35.760
So we can send each other messages.

03:07:35.819 --> 03:07:39.059
Maybe Sonny would let me use hers.

03:07:39.120 --> 03:07:42.120
Oh, Turtle realized.

03:07:42.180 --> 03:07:44.579
I'm not his enchanted fish.

03:07:44.700 --> 03:07:47.100
He thinks we're on some kind of detective

03:07:47.100 --> 03:07:49.739
team story, solving crimes together

03:07:49.799 --> 03:07:52.200
investigating strange behavior.

03:07:52.260 --> 03:07:55.500
Or maybe I'm his sidekick.

03:07:55.559 --> 03:07:58.620
But the sidekick doesn't get sent on the

03:07:58.620 --> 03:08:00.479
crazy, dangerous mission alone.

03:08:00.600 --> 03:08:02.159
Does he?

03:08:02.219 --> 03:08:04.799
He was dangerously tempted by this

03:08:04.799 --> 03:08:05.159
vision.

03:08:05.219 --> 03:08:08.040
In detective stories, it was all right

03:08:08.040 --> 03:08:10.079
for one of the partners to be incompetent

03:08:10.079 --> 03:08:12.239
and unreliable, because the other one

03:08:12.239 --> 03:08:13.260
would make up for it.

03:08:13.500 --> 03:08:16.020
In that kind of story, Turtle's character

03:08:16.020 --> 03:08:17.639
wouldn't have to make all the decisions.

03:08:17.700 --> 03:08:20.159
No one would be waiting for him to save

03:08:20.159 --> 03:08:20.760
the day.

03:08:20.879 --> 03:08:23.399
That was the kind of story he might

03:08:23.399 --> 03:08:24.479
actually survive.

03:08:24.540 --> 03:08:28.079
I might have something we could use.

03:08:28.139 --> 03:08:29.940
He said hesitantly.

03:08:30.000 --> 03:08:33.239
He checked and triple checked, that Dark

03:08:33.239 --> 03:08:35.100
Stalker was long gone from the hallways

03:08:35.100 --> 03:08:37.440
then led Kibley back to his own lonely

03:08:37.440 --> 03:08:37.799
cave.

03:08:37.860 --> 03:08:40.860
Tucked under his woven reed sleeping mat

03:08:40.860 --> 03:08:43.739
was the small satchel of belongings he'd

03:08:43.739 --> 03:08:44.340
brought to the school.

03:08:44.399 --> 03:08:46.799
A significantly lighter burden than

03:08:46.799 --> 03:08:49.020
anemones sparkle extravaganza.

03:08:49.079 --> 03:08:51.479
Turtle tugged it out and shook the

03:08:51.479 --> 03:08:52.379
contents onto the floor.

03:08:52.440 --> 03:08:54.600
A broken piece of coral.

03:08:54.659 --> 03:08:57.479
A pair of small cracked writing slates

03:08:57.479 --> 03:08:58.799
with a slate pencil.

03:08:58.860 --> 03:09:01.739
Three pieces of curved wood that slotted

03:09:01.739 --> 03:09:03.899
together to form a weathered food stained

03:09:03.899 --> 03:09:04.260
bowl.

03:09:04.319 --> 03:09:07.739
Kibli regarded the tiny pile with an

03:09:07.739 --> 03:09:09.000
extremely polite expression.

03:09:09.120 --> 03:09:13.739
Well, he said, honestly, I've seen

03:09:13.739 --> 03:09:15.540
weirder treasure in the Scorpion den.

03:09:15.659 --> 03:09:18.059
Turtle checked the corridor again.

03:09:18.120 --> 03:09:21.360
These are the things I've animus

03:09:21.360 --> 03:09:21.780
touched.

03:09:21.840 --> 03:09:23.040
He whispered.

03:09:23.100 --> 03:09:26.700
Oh, Kibley said, his eyes alight.

03:09:26.819 --> 03:09:27.959
What do they do?

03:09:28.020 --> 03:09:30.479
Protect your loved ones from harm?

03:09:30.540 --> 03:09:33.299
Smite your enemies, make everybody love

03:09:33.299 --> 03:09:33.840
you?

03:09:33.899 --> 03:09:35.639
Er.

03:09:35.819 --> 03:09:36.840
No.

03:09:36.899 --> 03:09:38.940
Turtle said awkwardly.

03:09:39.000 --> 03:09:40.500
He touched the coral.

03:09:40.559 --> 03:09:43.260
This one helps me find things I've lost.

03:09:43.319 --> 03:09:45.780
He assembled the bowl and tipped it

03:09:45.780 --> 03:09:46.379
toward Kibley.

03:09:46.440 --> 03:09:49.020
This doubles the amount of food you put

03:09:49.020 --> 03:09:49.500
in it.

03:09:49.559 --> 03:09:52.500
I just drop it in and say, twice as much

03:09:52.500 --> 03:09:53.340
please.

03:09:53.399 --> 03:09:55.500
Then instead of 2 muscles, I'd have

03:09:55.500 --> 03:09:55.799
four.

03:09:55.860 --> 03:09:59.159
Or instead of a ladleful of clam soup, I

03:09:59.159 --> 03:10:00.180
have twice that amount.

03:10:00.239 --> 03:10:01.440
That kind of thing.

03:10:01.500 --> 03:10:03.840
Kibley tipped his head to the side.

03:10:03.899 --> 03:10:05.639
Aren't you a prince?

03:10:05.700 --> 03:10:07.680
I thought that meant you'd have plenty of

03:10:07.680 --> 03:10:07.920
food.

03:10:08.040 --> 03:10:12.360
Well, yes, turtle admitted.

03:10:12.420 --> 03:10:14.280
But I was still competing with all my

03:10:14.280 --> 03:10:16.680
brothers for it, and I get hungry between

03:10:16.680 --> 03:10:19.020
meals and wouldn't feel like hunting, you

03:10:19.020 --> 03:10:19.260
know?

03:10:19.319 --> 03:10:22.079
All right, said Kibli.

03:10:22.139 --> 03:10:22.860
What about those?

03:10:22.920 --> 03:10:25.620
The slates clattered like falling

03:10:25.620 --> 03:10:27.959
seashells as Turtle picked them up and

03:10:27.959 --> 03:10:28.979
passed one to Kibley.

03:10:29.040 --> 03:10:32.340
With these, if you write a note on one

03:10:32.340 --> 03:10:33.780
it'll appear on the other.

03:10:33.840 --> 03:10:37.680
He took the pencil and wrote, hi, Kibley

03:10:37.680 --> 03:10:39.420
on the smaller slate.

03:10:39.479 --> 03:10:41.399
The message appeared simultaneously in

03:10:41.399 --> 03:10:43.620
his looping, scraggly handwriting on the

03:10:43.620 --> 03:10:44.159
other slate.

03:10:44.280 --> 03:10:47.219
When Turtle erased his slate, the message

03:10:47.219 --> 03:10:48.600
stayed in place on Kibley's.

03:10:48.719 --> 03:10:50.940
Kibley turned his slate over in his

03:10:50.940 --> 03:10:52.799
talons, as though he were hoping to

03:10:52.799 --> 03:10:54.360
discover a better spell on the other

03:10:54.360 --> 03:10:54.780
side.

03:10:54.840 --> 03:10:56.879
Huh, he said.

03:10:56.940 --> 03:11:00.659
So we can use these to communicate, I

03:11:00.659 --> 03:11:03.659
think, Turtle said, I've never used it

03:11:03.659 --> 03:11:05.340
across a really big distance before.

03:11:05.399 --> 03:11:07.860
Oh, and it only works one way.

03:11:07.920 --> 03:11:11.040
But at least I can send you panicked.

03:11:11.100 --> 03:11:11.639
Help.

03:11:11.700 --> 03:11:14.280
He's got messages.

03:11:14.340 --> 03:11:16.440
It only works one way.

03:11:16.500 --> 03:11:18.239
Kibli echoed.

03:11:18.299 --> 03:11:20.520
His face seemed to be struggling with a

03:11:20.520 --> 03:11:22.860
concept of a world in which amazing magic

03:11:22.860 --> 03:11:25.260
could be given to a dragon like turtle

03:11:25.260 --> 03:11:26.100
instead of him.

03:11:26.159 --> 03:11:29.040
Well, said Turtle.

03:11:29.100 --> 03:11:29.819
Yeah.

03:11:29.879 --> 03:11:32.639
I mean, I never thought I'd use it with

03:11:32.639 --> 03:11:33.360
anyone else.

03:11:33.420 --> 03:11:36.120
Kibli, to his credit.

03:11:36.180 --> 03:11:38.579
Managed to restrain his reaction to a

03:11:38.579 --> 03:11:39.180
slow blink.

03:11:39.299 --> 03:11:43.379
Then what in the world did you use this

03:11:43.379 --> 03:11:43.739
for?

03:11:43.799 --> 03:11:46.739
It's a little embarrassing.

03:11:46.799 --> 03:11:48.420
Turtle admitted.

03:11:48.479 --> 03:11:51.059
More embarrassing than a bowl that

03:11:51.059 --> 03:11:53.520
doubles your royal meals, said Kibley's

03:11:53.520 --> 03:11:53.819
expression.

03:11:53.940 --> 03:11:56.819
I used to think I wanted to be a writer

03:11:56.819 --> 03:11:57.899
Turtle said.

03:11:57.959 --> 03:12:01.139
So sometimes, when I was out hunting or

03:12:01.139 --> 03:12:03.479
training or whatever, I'd have a great

03:12:03.479 --> 03:12:05.760
idea, or think of how I wanted to phrase

03:12:05.760 --> 03:12:08.159
something, but I'd always forget it by

03:12:08.159 --> 03:12:08.940
the time I got home.

03:12:09.000 --> 03:12:11.879
With these, I could take notes on the

03:12:11.879 --> 03:12:14.159
slate I carried with me, then erase it

03:12:14.159 --> 03:12:17.040
quick before my brothers saw it, but the

03:12:17.040 --> 03:12:18.479
notes would be there waiting on the other

03:12:18.479 --> 03:12:19.920
slate once I got home.

03:12:19.979 --> 03:12:21.959
I see.

03:12:22.020 --> 03:12:24.600
Kibley said, finally looking

03:12:24.600 --> 03:12:25.379
sympathetic.

03:12:25.440 --> 03:12:27.780
I had siblings who picked on me too.

03:12:27.840 --> 03:12:29.639
Oh, Ryder.

03:12:29.700 --> 03:12:31.680
So fancy scales.

03:12:31.739 --> 03:12:34.920
Oh, I gave that up a long time ago.

03:12:34.979 --> 03:12:36.719
Turtle shook his head.

03:12:36.780 --> 03:12:38.639
I wasn't any good anyway.

03:12:38.700 --> 03:12:40.920
He nudged the other items.

03:12:41.040 --> 03:12:43.920
I keep these kind of for sentimental

03:12:43.920 --> 03:12:44.280
value.

03:12:44.340 --> 03:12:47.219
I don't use them very much, since I don't

03:12:47.219 --> 03:12:48.719
want anyone to notice me using them.

03:12:48.780 --> 03:12:51.719
Sure, Kibley said.

03:12:51.780 --> 03:12:53.760
He tipped his slate up to the light.

03:12:53.819 --> 03:12:55.620
But this is a great idea.

03:12:55.680 --> 03:12:58.260
I'll hang on to this one, and you can

03:12:58.260 --> 03:13:00.059
send me notes on what Dark Stalker is

03:13:00.059 --> 03:13:02.100
doing, or anytime you need me.

03:13:02.159 --> 03:13:05.219
Or if moon needs me, or anyone.

03:13:05.340 --> 03:13:08.100
I mean, hypothetically moon, but anyone.

03:13:08.159 --> 03:13:09.780
I'll come flying.

03:13:09.840 --> 03:13:10.379
All right.

03:13:10.440 --> 03:13:13.020
Turtle nodded.

03:13:13.079 --> 03:13:14.700
It made him a little nervous to let half

03:13:14.700 --> 03:13:17.100
of one of his animus touched objects out

03:13:17.100 --> 03:13:17.639
of his sight.

03:13:17.700 --> 03:13:20.700
What if it fell into the wrong claws?

03:13:20.760 --> 03:13:23.100
On the other talent, it was reassuring to

03:13:23.100 --> 03:13:24.540
have someone he could call for help.

03:13:24.600 --> 03:13:28.139
I guess I just agreed to follow Dark

03:13:28.139 --> 03:13:29.399
Stalker to the rainforest.

03:13:29.459 --> 03:13:30.780
He realized.

03:13:30.840 --> 03:13:34.020
A clatter of talons came from the hallway

03:13:34.020 --> 03:13:37.020
followed by a whooshing sound, a yelp of

03:13:37.020 --> 03:13:39.239
fury, and the distinct smell of something

03:13:39.239 --> 03:13:39.899
burning.

03:13:39.959 --> 03:13:42.299
Think I can guess who that is.

03:13:42.360 --> 03:13:44.219
Kibley said with a grin.

03:13:44.280 --> 03:13:46.440
Turtle peeked out the door and found

03:13:46.440 --> 03:13:49.079
peril, jumping around trying to stomp out

03:13:49.079 --> 03:13:51.479
a small fire, except every time she

03:13:51.479 --> 03:13:53.219
touched it, the flames got higher.

03:13:53.280 --> 03:13:56.159
A few sleepy faces peered out from their

03:13:56.159 --> 03:13:58.500
caves, and immediately withdrew when they

03:13:58.500 --> 03:13:59.100
saw her.

03:13:59.159 --> 03:14:01.200
Eck, she yelped.

03:14:01.260 --> 03:14:02.040
Stop.

03:14:02.100 --> 03:14:03.479
Bucket of gizzards.

03:14:03.540 --> 03:14:04.440
Go out already.

03:14:04.500 --> 03:14:06.719
Back, back, back.

03:14:06.840 --> 03:14:09.479
Kibley said, hurrying over and flapping

03:14:09.479 --> 03:14:10.620
her away with his wings.

03:14:10.680 --> 03:14:11.280
I got it.

03:14:11.340 --> 03:14:14.100
He pulled one of the message chalkboards

03:14:14.100 --> 03:14:16.440
off the wall and smothered the fire, then

03:14:16.440 --> 03:14:18.540
trampled out the last few glowing sparks

03:14:18.540 --> 03:14:19.799
as they tried to scuttle away.

03:14:19.860 --> 03:14:24.239
What kind of jerk leaves scrolls lying

03:14:24.239 --> 03:14:26.760
around in the hallway where anyone could

03:14:26.760 --> 03:14:27.540
set them on fire?

03:14:27.600 --> 03:14:29.819
Peril demanded?

03:14:29.879 --> 03:14:31.500
Someone is trying to pick a fight with

03:14:31.500 --> 03:14:31.680
me.

03:14:31.739 --> 03:14:32.459
Is that it?

03:14:32.579 --> 03:14:34.260
Um.

03:14:34.440 --> 03:14:36.420
That was my homework.

03:14:36.479 --> 03:14:39.420
Mumbled a rain wing nervously from the

03:14:39.420 --> 03:14:40.319
nearest doorway.

03:14:40.379 --> 03:14:43.319
Oh, Peril said.

03:14:43.379 --> 03:14:46.319
She drew her wings back in, eyeing the

03:14:46.319 --> 03:14:48.719
hapless dragonette, who was hat for her

03:14:48.719 --> 03:14:51.120
size, and a nervous fizzy green color.

03:14:51.180 --> 03:14:55.680
Um, she shot a glance at Turtle of the

03:14:55.680 --> 03:14:57.659
there's a right thing to say here, isn't

03:14:57.659 --> 03:14:57.840
there?

03:14:57.899 --> 03:14:58.620
Variety.

03:14:58.680 --> 03:15:02.639
Well, next time, keep your mess in your

03:15:02.639 --> 03:15:04.739
own cave, all right, she said.

03:15:04.799 --> 03:15:06.899
With what Turtle knew was about as much

03:15:06.899 --> 03:15:08.579
gentleness as she could muster.

03:15:08.639 --> 03:15:12.360
So sorry, stammered the rain wing.

03:15:12.420 --> 03:15:13.979
Turtle cleared his throat.

03:15:14.040 --> 03:15:17.280
I'm sure peril is sorry too, he offered.

03:15:17.340 --> 03:15:19.680
She tilted her head at him.

03:15:19.799 --> 03:15:22.319
For burning up this dragon's homework

03:15:22.319 --> 03:15:24.899
which he probably worked very hard on.

03:15:24.959 --> 03:15:27.659
Turtle tipped his head at the

03:15:27.659 --> 03:15:28.200
dragonette.

03:15:28.319 --> 03:15:30.000
Uh, okay.

03:15:30.059 --> 03:15:31.079
Sure.

03:15:31.139 --> 03:15:33.659
Perl said, nodding vigorously.

03:15:33.719 --> 03:15:35.940
I'm sorry your scroll got under my claws

03:15:35.940 --> 03:15:37.139
and met a fiery end.

03:15:37.139 --> 03:15:39.120
She said to the rain wing.

03:15:39.180 --> 03:15:40.860
On the plus side.

03:15:40.920 --> 03:15:43.920
At least it was a scroll and not say, your

03:15:43.920 --> 03:15:44.280
tail.

03:15:44.399 --> 03:15:47.520
He turned an even paler shade of green

03:15:47.520 --> 03:15:49.200
and vanished into his cave.

03:15:49.319 --> 03:15:52.500
Good idea, she called after him.

03:15:52.559 --> 03:15:54.659
You shouldn't leave tail lying around the

03:15:54.659 --> 03:15:55.139
hallways either.

03:15:55.200 --> 03:15:57.659
That's our peril.

03:15:57.719 --> 03:16:00.540
Turtles said to Kibley, spreading a

03:16:00.540 --> 03:16:01.739
little terror before bedtime.

03:16:01.799 --> 03:16:03.479
Was I?

03:16:03.540 --> 03:16:04.260
She said.

03:16:04.319 --> 03:16:05.520
Humph.

03:16:05.579 --> 03:16:07.500
I thought that was a very nice apology

03:16:07.500 --> 03:16:07.979
myself.

03:16:08.040 --> 03:16:11.340
Turtle liked the dragon he was when he

03:16:11.340 --> 03:16:13.500
was with Parel, although he hadn't quite

03:16:13.500 --> 03:16:15.059
figured out how their stories fit

03:16:15.059 --> 03:16:15.479
together.

03:16:15.540 --> 03:16:19.020
He might be her sidekick, although she

03:16:19.020 --> 03:16:22.020
wasn't exactly a normal hero, or he might

03:16:22.020 --> 03:16:24.360
be her voice of reason, like the dragon

03:16:24.360 --> 03:16:26.100
assigned to take care of a mad prophet or

03:16:26.100 --> 03:16:26.340
something.

03:16:26.399 --> 03:16:29.700
The closest parallel he could think of

03:16:29.700 --> 03:16:31.799
though, was this scroll he'd once read

03:16:31.799 --> 03:16:34.200
about a dragonette who'd been lost and

03:16:34.200 --> 03:16:35.819
raised by a pack of orcas.

03:16:36.540 --> 03:16:38.819
So when she returned to her tribe, she

03:16:38.819 --> 03:16:40.139
had to be taught everything about

03:16:40.139 --> 03:16:42.899
language and relationships and how to

03:16:42.899 --> 03:16:45.059
interact with other dragons, and

03:16:45.059 --> 03:16:47.280
occasionally she would have furious fits

03:16:47.280 --> 03:16:48.299
and bite someone.

03:16:48.360 --> 03:16:51.360
With peril, he sometimes felt like that

03:16:51.360 --> 03:16:54.479
wild dragon's foster brother, a minor

03:16:54.479 --> 03:16:54.959
character.

03:16:55.020 --> 03:16:56.940
But one of the few willing to risk

03:16:56.940 --> 03:16:57.659
hanging out with her.

03:16:57.719 --> 03:17:00.059
He was pretty sure they were friends

03:17:00.059 --> 03:17:01.920
though, which was crazy.

03:17:01.979 --> 03:17:04.860
Never in a 1000000 years would he have

03:17:04.860 --> 03:17:06.959
guessed that he might end up friends with

03:17:06.959 --> 03:17:09.180
the sky wing queen's deadliest weapon.

03:17:09.239 --> 03:17:12.239
She followed him and Kibley back into a

03:17:12.239 --> 03:17:14.639
sleeping cave, where he hurriedly scooted

03:17:14.639 --> 03:17:16.020
his sleeping mat to the far end of the

03:17:16.020 --> 03:17:17.639
room, away from peril.

03:17:17.700 --> 03:17:20.159
He could move it to Kibley and Winter's

03:17:20.159 --> 03:17:20.579
cave later.

03:17:20.639 --> 03:17:23.579
He packed the smaller slate, the slate

03:17:23.579 --> 03:17:25.979
pencil, and the coral into his pouch to

03:17:25.979 --> 03:17:27.239
take with him to the rainforest.

03:17:27.299 --> 03:17:29.639
The pieces of the bowl were too big to

03:17:29.639 --> 03:17:32.280
fit, so he repacked them in his satchel

03:17:32.280 --> 03:17:34.379
and hid it under umbers sleeping mat.

03:17:34.500 --> 03:17:37.020
How was your meeting with Clay?

03:17:37.079 --> 03:17:38.819
Kibley asked Parel.

03:17:38.879 --> 03:17:40.979
Fine, she blurted.

03:17:41.040 --> 03:17:43.620
Fine, normal, great.

03:17:43.680 --> 03:17:44.579
Weird.

03:17:44.639 --> 03:17:46.020
Totally fine.

03:17:46.079 --> 03:17:46.559
Why?

03:17:46.620 --> 03:17:47.040
What did you hear?

03:17:47.159 --> 03:17:50.219
Nothing at all. he is shorter.

03:17:50.280 --> 03:17:51.059
Just wondering.

03:17:51.120 --> 03:17:53.340
Right, she said.

03:17:53.399 --> 03:17:55.979
He was very pleased to hear about Queen.

03:17:55.979 --> 03:17:57.420
About Scarlet.

03:17:57.540 --> 03:18:00.659
She paused, looking like she'd swallowed

03:18:00.659 --> 03:18:02.100
an exploding cactus for a moment.

03:18:02.159 --> 03:18:04.860
There was hugging.

03:18:04.920 --> 03:18:05.879
She finally burst out.

03:18:05.940 --> 03:18:08.100
I mean, he gave me a hug.

03:18:08.159 --> 03:18:09.540
No big deal.

03:18:09.600 --> 03:18:11.159
Normal stuff, I'm sure.

03:18:11.219 --> 03:18:13.680
Dragons probably hug you guys all the

03:18:13.680 --> 03:18:13.860
time.

03:18:13.920 --> 03:18:16.440
Oh, peril.

03:18:16.500 --> 03:18:19.319
Turtle kind of wished he could hug her, to

03:18:19.319 --> 03:18:20.520
let her know he understood.

03:18:20.639 --> 03:18:22.860
Clay likes you too.

03:18:22.920 --> 03:18:24.659
Kibley said to Parel.

03:18:24.719 --> 03:18:25.860
Really?

03:18:25.920 --> 03:18:29.040
Peril glowed like molten glass.

03:18:29.100 --> 03:18:30.120
He does?

03:18:30.180 --> 03:18:31.620
How do you know?

03:18:31.680 --> 03:18:33.120
I can tell.

03:18:33.180 --> 03:18:35.219
He just doesn't quite know what to do

03:18:35.219 --> 03:18:35.760
about it yet.

03:18:35.819 --> 03:18:37.020
Kibley said.

03:18:37.079 --> 03:18:39.000
Give him some time to figure it out.

03:18:39.059 --> 03:18:40.500
Like...

03:18:40.500 --> 03:18:43.440
Lots and lots and lots of time.

03:18:43.559 --> 03:18:46.379
I have lots and lots of time.

03:18:46.440 --> 03:18:48.959
Peril said, exhaling.

03:18:49.020 --> 03:18:51.120
That's totally all right with me.

03:18:51.180 --> 03:18:53.040
She beamed at Turtle.

03:18:53.100 --> 03:18:58.020
Kibli thinks Clay likes me, she said, in

03:18:58.020 --> 03:18:58.920
a loud whisper.

03:18:58.979 --> 03:19:00.540
I heard.

03:19:00.600 --> 03:19:02.639
Turtle smiled back at her.

03:19:02.700 --> 03:19:06.299
I was a little worried he'd hate me after

03:19:06.299 --> 03:19:08.579
I burned the magic scroll and released a

03:19:08.579 --> 03:19:09.540
giant bad guy.

03:19:09.600 --> 03:19:11.100
Peril admitted.

03:19:11.159 --> 03:19:13.500
But I guess Dark Stalkers, not bad.

03:19:13.559 --> 03:19:14.700
So everything's all right?

03:19:14.760 --> 03:19:17.700
She squinted at the items turtle was

03:19:17.700 --> 03:19:18.059
packing.

03:19:18.120 --> 03:19:19.319
What are you doing?

03:19:19.379 --> 03:19:22.680
I'm going to follow Dark Stalker to the

03:19:22.680 --> 03:19:24.899
rainforest tomorrow, Turtle said.

03:19:25.020 --> 03:19:27.420
Just to see what happens.

03:19:27.479 --> 03:19:32.219
Oh, peril said, her wings drooping.

03:19:32.280 --> 03:19:34.319
One of them nearly caught on one of the

03:19:34.319 --> 03:19:36.540
scroll racks by the door, and Kibli

03:19:36.540 --> 03:19:37.920
quietly dragged it out of her reach.

03:19:37.979 --> 03:19:39.719
You're leaving?

03:19:39.780 --> 03:19:43.860
Only for a little while, I hope, Turtles

03:19:43.860 --> 03:19:44.159
said.

03:19:44.219 --> 03:19:45.659
I wish you could come with me.

03:19:45.719 --> 03:19:48.719
Peril held out her front talons.

03:19:48.780 --> 03:19:50.340
I wish I could too.

03:19:50.399 --> 03:19:53.219
But no fire scales in the rainforest.

03:19:53.219 --> 03:19:55.379
By order of the queen.

03:19:55.440 --> 03:19:56.940
She said haughtily.

03:19:57.000 --> 03:19:59.159
I'll miss your boring face though.

03:19:59.219 --> 03:20:00.659
She said to Turtle.

03:20:00.719 --> 03:20:03.059
Not like a lot.

03:20:03.180 --> 03:20:04.860
But I'll miss it a little bit.

03:20:04.920 --> 03:20:07.920
You won't miss me at all, he said.

03:20:07.979 --> 03:20:09.420
You'll have Clay to hang out with.

03:20:09.479 --> 03:20:13.440
True. she said. true, true.

03:20:13.500 --> 03:20:16.500
She tried to squash back her smile, but

03:20:16.500 --> 03:20:17.579
it kept sneaking out.

03:20:17.639 --> 03:20:21.180
I really do wish she could come with me.

03:20:21.239 --> 03:20:22.920
Turtle thought.

03:20:22.979 --> 03:20:26.340
Her unpredictable, hilarious company was

03:20:26.340 --> 03:20:28.020
the only thing that had made him able to

03:20:28.020 --> 03:20:29.760
leave Jade Mountain in the 1st place.

03:20:29.819 --> 03:20:31.739
He'd been able to think of their

03:20:31.739 --> 03:20:35.219
adventure as her quest to find Scarlet, no

03:20:35.219 --> 03:20:35.879
pressure on him.

03:20:35.940 --> 03:20:38.700
Nothing enormously major he could mess

03:20:38.700 --> 03:20:38.940
up.

03:20:39.000 --> 03:20:41.399
Nobody expecting anything of him.

03:20:41.459 --> 03:20:45.059
Not like tomorrow, when he'd be following

03:20:45.059 --> 03:20:47.219
Dark Stalker to the rainforest alone.

03:20:47.280 --> 03:20:50.159
Without the option of using his magic

03:20:50.159 --> 03:20:51.420
alone.

03:20:51.479 --> 03:20:52.860
Powerless.

03:20:52.920 --> 03:20:54.360
Useless.

03:20:54.420 --> 03:20:57.719
This story couldn't possibly end well.

03:20:57.780 --> 03:21:02.159
Part two.

03:21:02.219 --> 03:21:04.200
Rise to power.

03:21:04.260 --> 03:21:07.979
Chapter 10.

03:21:08.280 --> 03:21:12.180
The rainforest was an ocean of leaves

03:21:12.180 --> 03:21:14.760
below turtle, tossing and rippling in the

03:21:14.760 --> 03:21:16.739
wind, like a dark green sea.

03:21:16.860 --> 03:21:19.200
A spray of bright yellow birds flew out

03:21:19.200 --> 03:21:22.139
of it, squawking and diving, and looping

03:21:22.139 --> 03:21:23.700
back down again to sink beneath the

03:21:23.700 --> 03:21:24.540
surface.

03:21:24.600 --> 03:21:26.579
But the smell here was nothing like the

03:21:26.579 --> 03:21:26.940
ocean.

03:21:27.000 --> 03:21:31.799
Wild fruit and monkey droppings, heat and

03:21:31.799 --> 03:21:34.680
rich dirt, and roots growing in thick

03:21:34.680 --> 03:21:37.860
tangles in place of fish, salt, wide open

03:21:37.860 --> 03:21:38.159
air.

03:21:38.280 --> 03:21:41.520
I have no idea why you decided to come

03:21:41.520 --> 03:21:44.579
Anemone said. sweeping up on turtles

03:21:44.579 --> 03:21:44.940
left.

03:21:45.000 --> 03:21:47.819
He started, then glanced around at Dark

03:21:47.819 --> 03:21:50.280
Stalker, but the large dragon was far in

03:21:50.280 --> 03:21:52.379
the lead, scanning the forest below.

03:21:52.440 --> 03:21:55.319
Anemone had been so close to him all

03:21:55.319 --> 03:21:57.180
morning, the turtle hadn't had a chance

03:21:57.180 --> 03:21:59.700
to speak to her or try to convince her

03:21:59.700 --> 03:22:00.180
not to come.

03:22:00.239 --> 03:22:03.659
I could say the same about you, he

03:22:03.659 --> 03:22:04.200
pointed out.

03:22:04.260 --> 03:22:05.819
Shouldn't you be in school?

03:22:05.940 --> 03:22:08.280
Mother wouldn't want you wandering around

03:22:08.280 --> 03:22:09.360
Pyria like this.

03:22:09.420 --> 03:22:12.719
I can learn far more from Dark Stalker

03:22:12.719 --> 03:22:15.180
than from a crusty old shipwreck like

03:22:15.180 --> 03:22:18.540
Webbs, anemone snorted, and mother

03:22:18.540 --> 03:22:20.819
doesn't have me on a leash anymore.

03:22:20.879 --> 03:22:22.860
I can go wherever I like.

03:22:22.920 --> 03:22:26.219
Wasn't Pike worried about you leaving?

03:22:26.280 --> 03:22:27.420
Turtle tried.

03:22:27.479 --> 03:22:29.879
His pouch thumbed lightly against his

03:22:29.879 --> 03:22:31.979
chest as he twisted in the air to keep

03:22:31.979 --> 03:22:33.000
anemone in sight.

03:22:33.000 --> 03:22:35.639
I'm surprised he didn't insist on coming

03:22:35.639 --> 03:22:36.479
with you at least.

03:22:36.540 --> 03:22:40.920
Oh, I didn't tell him, she said, tossing

03:22:40.920 --> 03:22:41.340
her head.

03:22:41.399 --> 03:22:44.399
He was sleeping outside my cave, which he

03:22:44.399 --> 03:22:48.000
often does because he's such a weirdo, and

03:22:48.000 --> 03:22:49.139
I snack right past him.

03:22:49.200 --> 03:22:51.719
Not much of a guard, if that's what he

03:22:51.719 --> 03:22:52.860
was trying to do.

03:22:52.920 --> 03:22:53.399
Ha ha.

03:22:53.459 --> 03:22:55.260
Poor Pike.

03:22:55.319 --> 03:22:57.420
Waking up to find the princess had

03:22:57.420 --> 03:23:00.120
disappeared on his watch, he'd feel like

03:23:00.120 --> 03:23:00.840
such a failure.

03:23:00.899 --> 03:23:02.819
Turtle knew what that was like.

03:23:02.940 --> 03:23:05.399
But what's your excuse?

03:23:05.459 --> 03:23:06.719
Anemone demanded.

03:23:06.780 --> 03:23:08.700
I thought you were terrified of Dark

03:23:08.700 --> 03:23:09.239
Stalker.

03:23:09.299 --> 03:23:11.639
You said he doesn't like you, but he

03:23:11.639 --> 03:23:12.479
never even looks at you.

03:23:12.540 --> 03:23:17.219
I just... want to see what he does, said

03:23:17.219 --> 03:23:17.760
Turtle.

03:23:17.819 --> 03:23:20.520
His claws itched to reach for his pouch

03:23:20.520 --> 03:23:22.680
to make sure the stick was still there

03:23:22.680 --> 03:23:24.420
but he fought back the urge.

03:23:24.479 --> 03:23:28.379
In case he does something super evil

03:23:28.379 --> 03:23:31.260
anemone teased, pouncing at him.

03:23:31.319 --> 03:23:32.579
Turtle flinched away.

03:23:32.639 --> 03:23:34.319
You jellyfish.

03:23:34.379 --> 03:23:36.420
He's going to rescue his tribe, that's

03:23:36.420 --> 03:23:36.540
all.

03:23:36.659 --> 03:23:40.200
Queen Glory already rescued his tribe.

03:23:40.260 --> 03:23:41.819
Turtle pointed out.

03:23:41.879 --> 03:23:43.979
They're not on the volcano anymore.

03:23:44.040 --> 03:23:45.299
They're perfectly safe.

03:23:45.360 --> 03:23:47.040
Right.

03:23:47.100 --> 03:23:49.739
Safe to be the crushed seashells under

03:23:49.739 --> 03:23:51.180
the talons of the rain wings.

03:23:51.299 --> 03:23:53.520
Anemone rolled her eyes.

03:23:53.520 --> 03:23:55.139
Think about it, big brother.

03:23:55.260 --> 03:23:58.139
Imagine if mother died, and I was too

03:23:58.139 --> 03:23:59.459
spineless to take the throne.

03:23:59.520 --> 03:24:01.979
So all the sea wings decided to go live

03:24:01.979 --> 03:24:04.739
in the mud kingdom and let Queen Moorhen

03:24:04.739 --> 03:24:05.819
bosses around.

03:24:05.879 --> 03:24:07.920
Is that any way for a self-respecting

03:24:07.920 --> 03:24:08.520
tribe to live?

03:24:08.579 --> 03:24:12.000
Turtle noticed Fearless, listening to

03:24:12.000 --> 03:24:14.399
them with a scowl on her face, he decided

03:24:14.399 --> 03:24:16.079
it might be a good idea to change the

03:24:16.079 --> 03:24:17.340
subject.

03:24:17.399 --> 03:24:19.680
Did you get in trouble with Dark Stalker

03:24:19.680 --> 03:24:20.040
last night?

03:24:20.159 --> 03:24:21.180
He asked.

03:24:21.239 --> 03:24:23.579
I mean, I heard he was looking for you.

03:24:23.639 --> 03:24:26.340
He needed to know what was going on in

03:24:26.340 --> 03:24:27.479
Darkstalker's head.

03:24:27.540 --> 03:24:30.000
Did he suspect there was another animus

03:24:30.000 --> 03:24:30.239
around?

03:24:30.299 --> 03:24:33.959
Oh, that was the most ridiculous thing

03:24:33.959 --> 03:24:35.819
Anemone said with a laugh.

03:24:35.940 --> 03:24:38.760
He asked me if I cast a spell without his

03:24:38.760 --> 03:24:39.299
permission.

03:24:39.360 --> 03:24:42.540
I said, oh, permission?

03:24:42.600 --> 03:24:44.219
Is that how this is?

03:24:44.280 --> 03:24:47.040
And he said, without my brilliant advice

03:24:47.040 --> 03:24:47.399
then?

03:24:47.459 --> 03:24:50.819
I said, I didn't think so, but sometimes

03:24:50.819 --> 03:24:52.620
I've used my power accidentally without

03:24:52.620 --> 03:24:53.159
noticing.

03:24:53.219 --> 03:24:55.979
Like, you'd think an animus would learn

03:24:55.979 --> 03:24:58.379
not to yell at our stuff, but sometimes I

03:24:58.379 --> 03:24:59.700
forget and do it anyway.

03:24:59.760 --> 03:25:02.280
I made a pearl necklace explode that way

03:25:02.280 --> 03:25:03.420
once.

03:25:03.479 --> 03:25:05.760
Anyway, no, of course I'm not in

03:25:05.760 --> 03:25:06.059
trouble.

03:25:06.120 --> 03:25:08.819
He knows I'm a princess and can do

03:25:08.819 --> 03:25:09.479
whatever I want.

03:25:09.540 --> 03:25:11.760
Oh, does he?

03:25:11.819 --> 03:25:13.260
Turtle thought.

03:25:13.319 --> 03:25:15.299
But he didn't have a chance to respond.

03:25:15.360 --> 03:25:16.920
Up ahead.

03:25:16.979 --> 03:25:19.440
Dark Stalker shot a burst of flame into

03:25:19.440 --> 03:25:22.079
the sky, and beckoned to anemone and the

03:25:22.079 --> 03:25:22.739
night wings.

03:25:22.799 --> 03:25:25.020
They darted over to him as though he was

03:25:25.020 --> 03:25:27.420
the sun, and they all wanted to fall into

03:25:27.420 --> 03:25:27.659
it.

03:25:27.780 --> 03:25:31.079
Time for our grand entrance.

03:25:31.139 --> 03:25:33.180
Dark Stalker announced.

03:25:33.239 --> 03:25:35.760
He dove into the canopy, and the others

03:25:35.760 --> 03:25:39.360
followed, one by one, turtles sighed and

03:25:39.360 --> 03:25:40.319
flapped along behind them.

03:25:40.379 --> 03:25:42.840
He wondered what would happen if Anemone

03:25:42.840 --> 03:25:45.180
figured out that Dark Stalker couldn't

03:25:45.180 --> 03:25:46.200
see or hear Turtle.

03:25:46.319 --> 03:25:49.079
She tended to accept that the world

03:25:49.079 --> 03:25:51.420
revolved around her, so it would probably

03:25:51.420 --> 03:25:53.340
be a while before she noticed.

03:25:53.399 --> 03:25:56.399
And then, will I tell her the truth?

03:25:56.459 --> 03:26:00.600
He dropped from the hot sun sky down and

03:26:00.600 --> 03:26:03.479
down into dappled green light that

03:26:03.479 --> 03:26:05.760
reminded him of the summer palace before

03:26:05.760 --> 03:26:06.479
it was destroyed.

03:26:06.540 --> 03:26:10.139
Long limbed creatures of fur flurried out

03:26:10.139 --> 03:26:12.180
along the branches as he maneuvered

03:26:12.180 --> 03:26:14.280
carefully between the thick vines and

03:26:14.280 --> 03:26:15.540
grasping spider webs.

03:26:15.659 --> 03:26:18.239
The trees were interwoven like living

03:26:18.239 --> 03:26:20.520
nets, lying in wait for their prey.

03:26:20.639 --> 03:26:24.180
Far below them on the rainforest floor

03:26:24.180 --> 03:26:26.459
the entire night wing tribe was gathered

03:26:26.459 --> 03:26:27.959
in a clearing, looking up.

03:26:28.020 --> 03:26:30.899
All around them were grass huts and

03:26:30.899 --> 03:26:33.180
ramshackle wooden structures, many of

03:26:33.180 --> 03:26:34.079
them only half built.

03:26:34.139 --> 03:26:37.559
The scent of crispy boar meat rose from a

03:26:37.559 --> 03:26:39.840
fire pit that glowed in the center of the

03:26:39.840 --> 03:26:41.819
village, carefully lined with rocks.

03:26:41.940 --> 03:26:45.239
Queen Glory stood on a mahogany platform

03:26:45.239 --> 03:26:46.500
facing the tribe.

03:26:46.500 --> 03:26:49.559
She was the only rain wing present, or at

03:26:49.559 --> 03:26:52.379
least visible, and her scales were set in

03:26:52.379 --> 03:26:54.959
an intricate, overlapping leaf pattern of

03:26:54.959 --> 03:26:57.120
bright green, gold, and black.

03:26:57.120 --> 03:27:01.079
Beside her, as close as her shadow, was a

03:27:01.079 --> 03:27:02.700
night wing with a worried expression

03:27:02.700 --> 03:27:05.819
turtle guest that was death bringer, from

03:27:05.819 --> 03:27:07.319
the stories he'd heard about the young

03:27:07.319 --> 03:27:10.379
rain wing queen, and her loyal, self

03:27:09.719 --> 03:27:10.799
appointed bodyguard.

03:27:10.860 --> 03:27:14.159
Glory watched dark stalker descend

03:27:14.159 --> 03:27:17.399
without a hint of emotion on her face, nor

03:27:17.399 --> 03:27:19.079
even the slightest color change in her

03:27:19.079 --> 03:27:19.440
scales.

03:27:19.500 --> 03:27:22.200
Turtle wondered if she'd ever been afraid

03:27:22.200 --> 03:27:23.100
of anything in her life.

03:27:23.159 --> 03:27:27.000
He perched on a branch overhead, where

03:27:27.000 --> 03:27:29.340
the tooth shaped leaves matched the dark

03:27:29.340 --> 03:27:31.319
green of his gales below.

03:27:31.379 --> 03:27:34.500
Dark stalker soared down to land next to

03:27:34.500 --> 03:27:37.020
glory, instantly dwarfing her and

03:27:37.020 --> 03:27:37.620
Deathbringer.

03:27:37.680 --> 03:27:40.680
A muffled gasp rustled through the crowd

03:27:40.680 --> 03:27:41.399
of night wings.

03:27:41.459 --> 03:27:43.979
Death Bringer sidled a step closer to

03:27:43.979 --> 03:27:46.200
glory, but the queen herself neither

03:27:46.200 --> 03:27:47.100
flinched nor moved.

03:27:47.219 --> 03:27:50.639
Anemone hovered for a moment at Dark

03:27:50.639 --> 03:27:52.860
Stalker's shoulder, but there was no room

03:27:52.860 --> 03:27:54.420
on the platform for anyone else.

03:27:54.420 --> 03:27:57.360
Huffing grumbly, she landed on the ground

03:27:57.360 --> 03:27:59.819
close by, then spent several minutes

03:27:59.819 --> 03:28:02.100
pointedly scraping all the muddy leaves

03:28:02.100 --> 03:28:03.899
out of her little patch of dirt.

03:28:03.959 --> 03:28:06.479
Dog stalker, I presume?

03:28:06.479 --> 03:28:07.860
said Glory.

03:28:07.920 --> 03:28:10.500
She nodded to Moon and the other 3 night

03:28:10.500 --> 03:28:12.540
wing dragonettes as they slipped into the

03:28:12.540 --> 03:28:12.899
tribe.

03:28:12.959 --> 03:28:15.420
Turtle saw each of them find their

03:28:15.420 --> 03:28:15.719
parents.

03:28:15.780 --> 03:28:18.239
He saw Moon's mother wrap her wings

03:28:18.239 --> 03:28:19.260
around her daughter.

03:28:19.319 --> 03:28:21.899
He saw a mind reader whispering excitedly

03:28:21.899 --> 03:28:24.120
to a tall male night wing, holding out

03:28:24.120 --> 03:28:24.719
her bracelet.

03:28:24.780 --> 03:28:28.799
I see Sonny used the dream visitor to

03:28:28.799 --> 03:28:29.700
tell you we were coming.

03:28:29.760 --> 03:28:32.700
Dark Stalker said, even though I asked

03:28:32.700 --> 03:28:34.979
her very nicely not to. interesting.

03:28:35.100 --> 03:28:38.579
The tribe prefers not to be surprised

03:28:38.579 --> 03:28:41.700
Glory said, indicating the sea of black

03:28:41.700 --> 03:28:42.780
dragons below them.

03:28:42.840 --> 03:28:46.139
But as you can see, despite your

03:28:46.139 --> 03:28:47.760
prediction, no one has run away.

03:28:47.819 --> 03:28:50.940
They chose to be brave, to stand together

03:28:50.940 --> 03:28:51.780
and face you.

03:28:51.840 --> 03:28:55.379
That wasn't entirely accurate.

03:28:55.440 --> 03:28:58.379
Turtle had seen a few dragons bolt into

03:28:58.379 --> 03:29:01.559
the forest as Dark Stalker flew down, but

03:29:01.559 --> 03:29:03.659
he didn't blame them, considering Dark

03:29:03.659 --> 03:29:05.340
Stalker had been the tribe's worst

03:29:05.340 --> 03:29:07.200
nightmare for the last 2000 years.

03:29:07.260 --> 03:29:09.959
He was amazed so many of them were able

03:29:09.959 --> 03:29:10.739
to hold their ground.

03:29:10.799 --> 03:29:13.979
He wondered what Queen Glory had said to

03:29:13.979 --> 03:29:15.239
them to give them that strength.

03:29:15.299 --> 03:29:18.840
Dark Stalker smiled his dazzling smile.

03:29:18.899 --> 03:29:22.139
There's no need to be brave, he said.

03:29:22.200 --> 03:29:23.639
I'm no monster.

03:29:23.760 --> 03:29:26.520
The history you've been fed is all a pack

03:29:26.520 --> 03:29:27.059
of lies.

03:29:27.180 --> 03:29:30.420
He opened his talons palm up toward the

03:29:30.420 --> 03:29:33.239
tribe, as if revealing all his secrets to

03:29:33.239 --> 03:29:33.479
them.

03:29:33.600 --> 03:29:37.739
They told you I was evil, that I was

03:29:37.739 --> 03:29:38.879
about to do terrible things.

03:29:38.940 --> 03:29:41.399
And that I was locked away to protect

03:29:41.399 --> 03:29:41.579
you.

03:29:41.639 --> 03:29:43.799
None of that is true.

03:29:43.920 --> 03:29:45.899
My fellow night wings.

03:29:45.959 --> 03:29:49.379
I had a majestic future plan for our

03:29:49.379 --> 03:29:49.920
tribe.

03:29:49.979 --> 03:29:54.360
Power, and security, and wealth, and

03:29:54.360 --> 03:29:56.520
peace for every dragon.

03:29:56.579 --> 03:30:00.420
No running, no hiding, no lying or

03:30:00.420 --> 03:30:02.100
starving, or living in fear.

03:30:02.219 --> 03:30:04.920
But there were dragons who didn't trust

03:30:04.920 --> 03:30:05.819
my vision for us.

03:30:05.879 --> 03:30:08.940
They feared what our tribe could become.

03:30:09.059 --> 03:30:13.200
He swept one wing open in an arc, as

03:30:13.200 --> 03:30:15.239
though he were flinging diamond dust over

03:30:15.239 --> 03:30:16.139
the entire crowd.

03:30:16.200 --> 03:30:19.379
Turtle wondered how much dark stalker had

03:30:19.379 --> 03:30:22.139
rehearsed this speech, alone in the dark

03:30:22.139 --> 03:30:23.700
deep under layers of rock.

03:30:23.819 --> 03:30:28.200
I was betrayed, on the brink of changing

03:30:28.200 --> 03:30:28.620
everything.

03:30:28.739 --> 03:30:32.579
Dark Stalker took a breath, as if he

03:30:32.579 --> 03:30:34.319
could feel daggers stabbing into his

03:30:34.319 --> 03:30:34.500
back.

03:30:34.620 --> 03:30:36.840
Dragons.

03:30:36.899 --> 03:30:39.120
I thought I could trust, trapped me

03:30:39.120 --> 03:30:41.340
underground, where I'd been asleep

03:30:41.340 --> 03:30:43.620
against my will for the last 2000 years.

03:30:43.680 --> 03:30:48.420
Meanwhile, our tribe fell apart.

03:30:48.479 --> 03:30:50.159
Lost its power.

03:30:50.280 --> 03:30:51.600
Its home.

03:30:51.659 --> 03:30:53.879
Its position in Pyria.

03:30:53.940 --> 03:30:57.420
And history scrolls were written about me

03:30:57.420 --> 03:31:00.959
by deceitful dragons, who feared my

03:31:00.959 --> 03:31:01.379
powers.

03:31:01.440 --> 03:31:03.840
Am I evil?

03:31:03.959 --> 03:31:05.159
No.

03:31:05.280 --> 03:31:08.879
Murderous, not even remotely.

03:31:08.940 --> 03:31:14.159
Dangerous, not my own tribe, or to my

03:31:14.159 --> 03:31:14.399
friends.

03:31:14.520 --> 03:31:17.940
His eyes went to moon, and a few other

03:31:17.940 --> 03:31:19.379
night wings turned to look at her as

03:31:19.379 --> 03:31:19.739
well.

03:31:19.799 --> 03:31:21.780
Here's the real truth.

03:31:21.840 --> 03:31:24.840
I love our tribe.

03:31:24.899 --> 03:31:28.379
Dark Stalker looked alive in a way Turtle

03:31:28.379 --> 03:31:28.979
hadn't seen yet.

03:31:29.040 --> 03:31:31.379
He looked happy.

03:31:31.440 --> 03:31:34.319
The night wings were once the most

03:31:34.319 --> 03:31:38.219
powerful, most respected, and creative

03:31:38.219 --> 03:31:39.420
tribe in Pyria.

03:31:39.479 --> 03:31:42.479
And I can show you the way to become that

03:31:42.479 --> 03:31:43.200
tribe again.

03:31:43.260 --> 03:31:47.700
He paused, perhaps expecting applause, but

03:31:47.700 --> 03:31:50.459
the only sound was the wind in the trees

03:31:50.459 --> 03:31:52.079
and a jaguar roar in the distance.

03:31:52.200 --> 03:31:56.219
These dragons have been working hard to

03:31:56.219 --> 03:31:59.399
build their new home, Glory said, her

03:31:59.399 --> 03:32:01.979
calm voice carrying across the clearing

03:32:01.979 --> 03:32:04.440
they have security and peace here.

03:32:04.500 --> 03:32:08.700
They are smart, fierce, determined, and

03:32:08.700 --> 03:32:10.079
full of surprising ideas.

03:32:10.139 --> 03:32:12.600
They don't need any help to become a

03:32:12.600 --> 03:32:13.620
great tribe.

03:32:13.680 --> 03:32:15.059
They already are one.

03:32:15.120 --> 03:32:17.819
Now there was a reaction.

03:32:17.940 --> 03:32:20.760
A wrestling as several night wings stood

03:32:20.760 --> 03:32:22.979
up straighter, tipped their wings back

03:32:22.979 --> 03:32:25.020
lifted their chins.

03:32:25.079 --> 03:32:28.319
I'm sure they are, said Dark Stalker.

03:32:28.379 --> 03:32:30.479
But I know what they could be.

03:32:30.600 --> 03:32:35.100
I can see the shining future ahead, if

03:32:35.100 --> 03:32:36.899
everyone follows me.

03:32:36.959 --> 03:32:38.639
Follows you.

03:32:38.700 --> 03:32:40.680
Death bringer jumped in.

03:32:40.739 --> 03:32:43.500
Glory gave him a quelling look, but he

03:32:43.500 --> 03:32:44.219
barreled on.

03:32:44.280 --> 03:32:45.600
Follows you where?

03:32:45.659 --> 03:32:49.739
Back to our old kingdom, of course, said

03:32:49.739 --> 03:32:50.579
Dark Stalker.

03:32:50.639 --> 03:32:53.879
He gazed down at glory, a slow smile

03:32:53.879 --> 03:32:55.739
spreading across his face.

03:32:55.799 --> 03:33:00.000
Queen glory, he said, and there was a

03:33:00.000 --> 03:33:02.159
lilt to his voice that hinted at how

03:33:02.159 --> 03:33:03.719
amusing he found that phrase.

03:33:03.840 --> 03:33:07.559
I'm here to challenge you, for the throne

03:33:07.559 --> 03:33:08.879
of the night wing tribe.

03:33:08.940 --> 03:33:13.319
Chapter 11.

03:33:13.620 --> 03:33:17.219
Turtle wasn't sure why he was so

03:33:17.219 --> 03:33:17.700
shocked.

03:33:17.760 --> 03:33:20.819
After all, wanting to become king of the

03:33:20.819 --> 03:33:22.739
night wings, certainly fit in with

03:33:22.739 --> 03:33:24.600
everything else Dark Stalker had done so

03:33:24.600 --> 03:33:26.940
far, but it still hadn't occurred to

03:33:26.940 --> 03:33:27.059
him.

03:33:27.120 --> 03:33:30.299
No tribe had ever had a king in the

03:33:30.299 --> 03:33:32.700
history of Pyria, as far as turtle knew.

03:33:32.760 --> 03:33:35.399
He never could have imagined this scene

03:33:35.399 --> 03:33:38.280
or how Queen Glory could suddenly look as

03:33:38.280 --> 03:33:39.719
though she were made of spun glass.

03:33:39.780 --> 03:33:44.459
If he could be king, then I could be a

03:33:44.459 --> 03:33:44.940
king too.

03:33:45.000 --> 03:33:47.819
Where did that thought come from?

03:33:47.879 --> 03:33:50.819
Turtle would never want to be king in a

03:33:50.819 --> 03:33:53.159
1000000 years, and he would never be able

03:33:53.159 --> 03:33:54.659
to do what it took to become one.

03:33:54.719 --> 03:33:58.260
Even after what I did to Chameleon.

03:33:58.319 --> 03:34:02.040
He frowned down at his twitching talons.

03:34:02.100 --> 03:34:04.860
That was not the real him.

03:34:04.920 --> 03:34:06.719
These thoughts were not the real him

03:34:06.719 --> 03:34:07.079
either.

03:34:07.139 --> 03:34:10.260
Moon broke away from her mother and

03:34:10.260 --> 03:34:11.639
started pushing forward through the

03:34:11.639 --> 03:34:12.299
crowd.

03:34:12.600 --> 03:34:14.159
You can't do that.

03:34:14.219 --> 03:34:16.979
Death Bringer spat at Dark Stalker.

03:34:17.040 --> 03:34:18.600
Glory didn't stop him.

03:34:18.659 --> 03:34:21.239
She was staring at Dark Stalker as though

03:34:21.239 --> 03:34:24.360
he'd upended 800000 words on her head, and

03:34:24.360 --> 03:34:25.680
she was trying to put them in the right

03:34:25.680 --> 03:34:26.760
order to make a scroll.

03:34:26.819 --> 03:34:28.920
Why not?

03:34:28.979 --> 03:34:30.719
Dark Stalker asked.

03:34:30.780 --> 03:34:33.360
For one thing, you're male said

03:34:33.360 --> 03:34:34.139
Deathbringer.

03:34:34.200 --> 03:34:36.540
And for another, you're not royalty, so

03:34:36.540 --> 03:34:37.680
you have no right to the throne.

03:34:37.799 --> 03:34:42.000
In case you hadn't noticed, she's not

03:34:42.000 --> 03:34:44.399
exactly of royal night wing blood either

03:34:44.399 --> 03:34:47.579
Dark Socker said, flicking his tail at

03:34:47.579 --> 03:34:47.879
glory.

03:34:47.940 --> 03:34:50.579
And just because we've never had a king

03:34:50.579 --> 03:34:52.680
before, doesn't mean we shouldn't have

03:34:52.680 --> 03:34:53.040
one now.

03:34:53.100 --> 03:34:57.000
Pyria has only had queens for the

03:34:57.000 --> 03:34:58.860
entirety of dragon history. said

03:34:58.860 --> 03:34:59.520
Deathbringer.

03:34:59.579 --> 03:35:02.459
Male dragons cannot rule their tribes.

03:35:02.520 --> 03:35:03.239
That just the way it is.

03:35:03.299 --> 03:35:06.299
Things can change.

03:35:06.360 --> 03:35:08.219
Dark Stalker said airily.

03:35:08.280 --> 03:35:10.559
Where dragons, not ants.

03:35:10.620 --> 03:35:12.540
We can do things differently if we choose

03:35:12.540 --> 03:35:12.840
to.

03:35:12.899 --> 03:35:16.739
Turtle had a flash of déjà vu and touched

03:35:16.739 --> 03:35:17.879
his claws to his head.

03:35:17.940 --> 03:35:19.559
Where had he heard that before?

03:35:19.620 --> 03:35:22.020
From one of the teachers at Jade

03:35:22.020 --> 03:35:22.440
Mountain?

03:35:22.500 --> 03:35:26.700
Dark Stalker, Moon hissed from the front

03:35:26.700 --> 03:35:29.159
of the crowd, and he looked down at her.

03:35:29.399 --> 03:35:30.239
What are you doing?

03:35:30.299 --> 03:35:33.180
You promised not to hurt my friends.

03:35:33.239 --> 03:35:36.659
Feel free to check on your friends, said

03:35:36.659 --> 03:35:39.540
Dark Stalker, in an unsettlingly gentle

03:35:39.540 --> 03:35:39.959
voice.

03:35:40.020 --> 03:35:43.139
I'm sure you'll find that they're all

03:35:43.139 --> 03:35:45.239
safe, and perfectly unharmed.

03:35:45.299 --> 03:35:50.159
But glory is my friend too, Moon said, her

03:35:50.159 --> 03:35:51.000
voice wobbling.

03:35:51.059 --> 03:35:52.680
I don't want you to kill her.

03:35:52.739 --> 03:35:56.700
Was that real sympathy and dark stalker's

03:35:56.700 --> 03:35:56.819
eyes?

03:35:56.940 --> 03:36:00.059
Oh, moon, he said.

03:36:00.120 --> 03:36:02.100
The truth is, you don't want me to kill

03:36:02.100 --> 03:36:02.459
anybody.

03:36:02.520 --> 03:36:06.299
And neither do I. But we are dragons.

03:36:06.360 --> 03:36:08.520
There's a way these things have to be

03:36:08.520 --> 03:36:08.760
done.

03:36:08.819 --> 03:36:13.139
I cannot accept your challenge, Glory

03:36:13.139 --> 03:36:13.379
said.

03:36:13.440 --> 03:36:15.959
And Dark Stalker turned back to her

03:36:15.959 --> 03:36:18.659
leaving Moon with her talons helplessly

03:36:18.659 --> 03:36:19.440
outstretched.

03:36:19.500 --> 03:36:21.780
The rain wings need me too.

03:36:21.840 --> 03:36:25.079
If I fault you, I'd be putting their

03:36:25.079 --> 03:36:27.000
tribe and throne at risk.

03:36:27.059 --> 03:36:31.020
Maybe I could be king of both tribes, Dark

03:36:31.020 --> 03:36:31.620
Stalker said.

03:36:31.680 --> 03:36:33.299
Ha ha, just a joke.

03:36:33.420 --> 03:36:35.520
I have no interest in ruling a bunch of

03:36:35.520 --> 03:36:37.379
snoozy, colorful vegetarians.

03:36:37.440 --> 03:36:40.379
Turtle wasn't sure if he was imagining it

03:36:40.379 --> 03:36:42.540
but he thought a few of the night wings

03:36:42.540 --> 03:36:43.920
actually looked a bit offended by that

03:36:43.920 --> 03:36:44.340
comment.

03:36:44.399 --> 03:36:48.420
There's another alternative.

03:36:48.479 --> 03:36:50.219
Dark Stalker went on.

03:36:50.280 --> 03:36:53.579
You could just give me the night wing

03:36:53.579 --> 03:36:54.059
throne.

03:36:54.120 --> 03:36:56.639
He shot a glance at Moon as if to say

03:36:56.639 --> 03:36:58.979
look, I'm making an effort.

03:36:59.100 --> 03:37:00.180
Now do you approve?

03:37:00.239 --> 03:37:03.719
That would not be fair to the dragons

03:37:03.719 --> 03:37:06.059
here who swore loyalty to me, said

03:37:06.059 --> 03:37:06.479
Glory.

03:37:06.540 --> 03:37:09.840
Well, said Dark Stalker.

03:37:09.899 --> 03:37:12.299
Let's all remember that they had a

03:37:12.299 --> 03:37:13.799
volcano pointed to their heads at the

03:37:13.799 --> 03:37:13.979
time.

03:37:14.040 --> 03:37:16.799
You're certainly more appealing than

03:37:16.799 --> 03:37:17.700
death by lava.

03:37:17.760 --> 03:37:21.299
But if there were a charming, handsome

03:37:21.299 --> 03:37:23.280
superpowered night wing as an option

03:37:23.280 --> 03:37:23.700
instead.

03:37:23.760 --> 03:37:26.700
Queen Glory looked out if they gathered

03:37:26.700 --> 03:37:27.299
night wings.

03:37:27.360 --> 03:37:29.159
What are they thinking?

03:37:29.219 --> 03:37:30.659
Turtle wondered.

03:37:30.719 --> 03:37:33.479
Would they rather be ruled by a rain wing

03:37:33.479 --> 03:37:35.280
or by a legendary monster?

03:37:35.340 --> 03:37:38.879
He remembered the stories he'd read about

03:37:38.879 --> 03:37:39.780
albatross.

03:37:39.899 --> 03:37:42.479
The sea wing animus who massacred most of

03:37:42.479 --> 03:37:43.739
his family.

03:37:43.799 --> 03:37:46.020
If albatross somehow came back to life.

03:37:46.079 --> 03:37:49.200
And he acted like a sane, friendly dragon

03:37:49.200 --> 03:37:51.899
and turtle had to choose between him or

03:37:51.899 --> 03:37:55.440
say, Queen Glacier to rule the kingdom of

03:37:55.440 --> 03:37:55.739
the sea.

03:37:55.799 --> 03:37:57.479
Who would he pick?

03:37:57.540 --> 03:38:02.579
Oh, said Dark Stalker, nodding at glory.

03:38:02.639 --> 03:38:05.760
Very interesting idea, Your Majesty.

03:38:05.819 --> 03:38:08.219
Glory looked at him sharply.

03:38:08.280 --> 03:38:11.280
Let the night wings choose for themselves

03:38:11.280 --> 03:38:12.180
he said.

03:38:12.239 --> 03:38:13.379
Indeed.

03:38:13.500 --> 03:38:15.120
I could agree to that.

03:38:15.180 --> 03:38:18.899
I haven't offered it to you yet, said

03:38:18.899 --> 03:38:19.319
Glory.

03:38:19.379 --> 03:38:21.180
In this time period.

03:38:21.239 --> 03:38:23.399
It's considered bad manners to read

03:38:23.399 --> 03:38:24.719
another dragon's thoughts.

03:38:24.780 --> 03:38:26.940
My apologies.

03:38:27.000 --> 03:38:28.799
But you had such a good idea.

03:38:28.860 --> 03:38:32.219
A peaceful transition of power.

03:38:32.280 --> 03:38:35.340
Maybe dragons have evolved in the last

03:38:35.340 --> 03:38:36.719
2000 years after all.

03:38:36.780 --> 03:38:37.979
What do you think?

03:38:38.040 --> 03:38:40.620
Dark Stalker said to the assembled

03:38:40.620 --> 03:38:41.340
Nightwings.

03:38:41.399 --> 03:38:43.079
Shall we put it to a vote?

03:38:43.139 --> 03:38:45.959
Like some enormous sprawling mess of a

03:38:45.959 --> 03:38:46.260
council.

03:38:46.379 --> 03:38:50.520
King dog stalker, or Queen Rain Wing.

03:38:50.639 --> 03:38:55.020
No, Queen Glory said, stepping forward

03:38:55.020 --> 03:38:57.420
into a bar of sunlight that lit up every

03:38:57.420 --> 03:38:58.319
brilliant scale.

03:38:58.379 --> 03:39:00.540
Not a vote.

03:39:00.600 --> 03:39:02.100
I don't want my...

03:39:02.219 --> 03:39:05.040
Any night wing, to be forced to live

03:39:05.040 --> 03:39:06.780
somewhere or under someone they are

03:39:06.780 --> 03:39:07.379
unhappy with.

03:39:07.440 --> 03:39:10.620
She studied the ebony dragons below her.

03:39:10.680 --> 03:39:13.620
Those who wish to stay in the rainforest

03:39:13.620 --> 03:39:14.040
with me.

03:39:14.100 --> 03:39:16.379
In the village, you've built with your

03:39:16.379 --> 03:39:19.379
own talons are welcome here forever.

03:39:19.379 --> 03:39:21.719
Those who would rather follow dark

03:39:21.719 --> 03:39:24.479
stalker to the old kingdom, are free to

03:39:24.479 --> 03:39:24.659
go.

03:39:24.719 --> 03:39:28.020
Dark Stalker looked down at the crowd

03:39:28.020 --> 03:39:28.319
too.

03:39:28.379 --> 03:39:31.739
From a considerably greater distance, and

03:39:31.739 --> 03:39:33.299
he did not look pleased with what he

03:39:33.299 --> 03:39:33.600
saw.

03:39:33.659 --> 03:39:36.360
Or what he was hearing in their minds

03:39:36.360 --> 03:39:37.500
Turtle realized.

03:39:37.559 --> 03:39:40.440
But you don't have to decide right now

03:39:40.440 --> 03:39:44.280
Dark Stalker said, quickly, slippery

03:39:44.280 --> 03:39:44.700
smooth.

03:39:44.760 --> 03:39:46.799
You should get to know me first.

03:39:46.860 --> 03:39:49.920
I presume Queen Glory won't mind if I

03:39:49.920 --> 03:39:51.479
spend a day or 2 in the rainforest

03:39:51.479 --> 03:39:54.000
reacquainting myself with my tribe.

03:39:54.000 --> 03:39:55.979
Be our guest.

03:39:56.040 --> 03:39:58.979
Glory rested her quiet gaze on him for a

03:39:58.979 --> 03:39:59.219
moment.

03:39:59.340 --> 03:40:00.600
Just a moment.

03:40:00.659 --> 03:40:03.420
While something puzzled flickered behind

03:40:03.420 --> 03:40:03.899
her eyes.

03:40:03.959 --> 03:40:07.200
Then she turned to Deathbringer, and the

03:40:07.200 --> 03:40:09.360
2 of them hopped down from the stage to

03:40:09.360 --> 03:40:10.500
walk among the night wings.

03:40:10.559 --> 03:40:14.399
A hubbub of voices rose, hushed and

03:40:14.399 --> 03:40:17.219
panicked at the same time, who would stay

03:40:17.219 --> 03:40:18.120
who would go?

03:40:18.180 --> 03:40:19.920
What would become of them?

03:40:19.979 --> 03:40:22.979
Dark stalker's eyes went to moon.

03:40:23.040 --> 03:40:25.799
See, he said softly.

03:40:25.860 --> 03:40:28.139
I knew I wouldn't really have to kill

03:40:28.139 --> 03:40:31.079
glory, but I had to present myself as a

03:40:31.079 --> 03:40:32.040
strong leader moon.

03:40:32.100 --> 03:40:35.219
That's what dragons understand.

03:40:35.280 --> 03:40:38.819
Moon gave him a wounded look, and turned

03:40:38.819 --> 03:40:41.219
away, back toward her mother's wings.

03:40:41.280 --> 03:40:44.340
Turtle watched Dark Stalker watching her

03:40:44.340 --> 03:40:44.520
go.

03:40:44.639 --> 03:40:48.479
I think I found one true thing about Dark

03:40:48.479 --> 03:40:49.920
Stalker, he thought.

03:40:49.979 --> 03:40:52.319
He actually cares about Moon.

03:40:52.379 --> 03:40:54.120
But how does she feel?

03:40:54.180 --> 03:40:56.520
She's the one who's been helping him so

03:40:56.520 --> 03:40:56.760
far.

03:40:56.819 --> 03:40:59.579
Will she follow him to the night

03:40:59.579 --> 03:40:59.879
kingdom?

03:40:59.940 --> 03:41:02.399
Or will she choose Queen Glory?

03:41:02.459 --> 03:41:06.059
And if she does, how is he going to

03:41:06.059 --> 03:41:06.360
react?

03:41:06.479 --> 03:41:10.620
Queen Glory stayed in the Nightwing

03:41:10.620 --> 03:41:13.319
Village until midafternoon, answering

03:41:13.319 --> 03:41:15.360
questions, and talking with any dragon

03:41:15.360 --> 03:41:16.079
who approached her.

03:41:16.139 --> 03:41:19.319
Dark Stalker installed himself on a flat

03:41:19.319 --> 03:41:21.239
boulder by the river and did the same

03:41:21.239 --> 03:41:24.180
while Anemone splashed and swam in the

03:41:24.180 --> 03:41:25.139
fish flickering water.

03:41:25.200 --> 03:41:28.739
It all seemed very peaceful, entirely

03:41:28.739 --> 03:41:31.379
open, nothing suspicious or underhanded.

03:41:31.440 --> 03:41:34.260
Turtle wrote a quick note on his slate to

03:41:34.260 --> 03:41:34.680
Kibley.

03:41:34.739 --> 03:41:38.280
Dark stalker wants to be Nightwing King.

03:41:38.340 --> 03:41:40.500
Nightwings deciding what they want.

03:41:40.559 --> 03:41:44.399
Then he wiped it clean, and tried not to

03:41:44.399 --> 03:41:46.680
fall asleep while Dark Stalker droned on

03:41:46.680 --> 03:41:48.719
about parliamentary procedures in the

03:41:48.719 --> 03:41:49.920
ancient night kingdom.

03:41:50.040 --> 03:41:53.399
But then glory left, flying back to check

03:41:53.399 --> 03:41:56.219
on her rain wings, Dark Stalker saw her

03:41:56.219 --> 03:41:56.459
go.

03:41:56.520 --> 03:41:59.459
He waited a few minutes, swirling his

03:41:59.459 --> 03:42:01.620
tail in the river, as he listened to a

03:42:01.620 --> 03:42:03.659
sly looking dragon named Obsidian

03:42:03.659 --> 03:42:05.879
complain about rainforest insects.

03:42:05.940 --> 03:42:09.840
Finally, Dark Stalker said, that does

03:42:09.840 --> 03:42:10.739
sound dreadful.

03:42:10.799 --> 03:42:13.680
You know, the night kingdom doesn't have

03:42:13.680 --> 03:42:15.120
any mosquitoes.

03:42:15.180 --> 03:42:18.540
He sat up and called, mind reader.

03:42:18.600 --> 03:42:20.760
Touching his head as though summoning her

03:42:20.760 --> 03:42:21.780
by telepathy as well.

03:42:21.840 --> 03:42:25.680
A few moments later, the dragonette came

03:42:25.680 --> 03:42:27.659
scampering through the village with an

03:42:27.659 --> 03:42:29.760
older, significantly more reluctant

03:42:29.760 --> 03:42:31.860
looking night wing, limping behind her.

03:42:31.920 --> 03:42:35.879
Here, she said breathlessly, skidding to

03:42:35.879 --> 03:42:37.200
a stop below Dark Stalker.

03:42:37.260 --> 03:42:40.139
Come on, father, you have to meet him.

03:42:40.200 --> 03:42:42.000
He's got amazing powers.

03:42:42.059 --> 03:42:44.159
So I hear.

03:42:44.159 --> 03:42:46.620
Mind reader's father said gruffly.

03:42:46.680 --> 03:42:49.020
But don't you understand that he's

03:42:49.020 --> 03:42:50.459
sharing them, she said.

03:42:50.520 --> 03:42:52.620
If you could have any power in the world

03:42:52.620 --> 03:42:53.940
what would you want, Father?

03:42:54.000 --> 03:42:55.500
He snorted.

03:42:55.559 --> 03:42:57.840
To be anonymous, of course.

03:42:57.899 --> 03:43:00.059
Is there anything more powerful?

03:43:00.120 --> 03:43:03.360
Mind reader turned to Dark Stalker with

03:43:03.360 --> 03:43:06.000
shining eyes, but Dark Stalker was

03:43:06.000 --> 03:43:07.680
shaking his head with a regretful

03:43:07.680 --> 03:43:08.100
expression.

03:43:08.219 --> 03:43:10.920
I'm sorry, he said.

03:43:10.979 --> 03:43:14.399
That is the one gift, which is beyond my

03:43:14.399 --> 03:43:15.360
abilities to grant.

03:43:15.420 --> 03:43:19.379
An animus dragon cannot make other animus

03:43:19.379 --> 03:43:19.860
dragons.

03:43:19.979 --> 03:43:22.920
Huh, thought Turtle.

03:43:22.979 --> 03:43:24.479
He knew that was a lie.

03:43:24.540 --> 03:43:27.780
Does Dark Stalker know he's lying, or

03:43:27.780 --> 03:43:28.680
does he believe that?

03:43:28.739 --> 03:43:31.860
That's not the only thing father wants.

03:43:31.920 --> 03:43:33.719
Mind reader said quickly.

03:43:33.780 --> 03:43:35.459
I can hear it in his head.

03:43:35.520 --> 03:43:37.860
He wants the ability to heal instantly

03:43:37.860 --> 03:43:40.860
from any wound, not just new wounds, but

03:43:40.860 --> 03:43:43.559
all the old aches and weak bones and

03:43:43.559 --> 03:43:45.899
clouded lungs he got from living on the

03:43:45.899 --> 03:43:46.440
volcano.

03:43:46.500 --> 03:43:49.319
Oh, father, I'm sorry.

03:43:49.440 --> 03:43:51.899
I didn't know you were always in pain

03:43:51.899 --> 03:43:52.500
like that.

03:43:52.559 --> 03:43:55.739
She twined her tail around his, and

03:43:55.739 --> 03:43:57.600
Turtle found himself liking her for the

03:43:57.600 --> 03:43:58.079
1st time.

03:43:58.200 --> 03:44:01.620
You're not supposed to know these things

03:44:01.620 --> 03:44:04.139
her father said with a wince.

03:44:04.200 --> 03:44:06.360
I'm not sure it's going to be good for

03:44:06.360 --> 03:44:08.940
you, little one, hearing everyone's

03:44:08.940 --> 03:44:09.659
thoughts this way.

03:44:09.719 --> 03:44:12.959
Dragons like to keep their secrets.

03:44:13.020 --> 03:44:15.420
I know.

03:44:15.479 --> 03:44:16.979
It's incredible how many secrets there

03:44:16.979 --> 03:44:19.559
are, mind reader said, her eyes

03:44:19.559 --> 03:44:20.159
widening.

03:44:20.219 --> 03:44:23.459
If I were blackmailing sort of dragon, I

03:44:23.459 --> 03:44:26.040
could get so much treasure, but I'm not

03:44:26.040 --> 03:44:26.340
of course.

03:44:26.399 --> 03:44:27.840
Of course I'm not.

03:44:27.899 --> 03:44:29.040
And I wouldn't.

03:44:29.100 --> 03:44:30.959
She let out a little laugh.

03:44:31.020 --> 03:44:34.079
Enough about me, dark soccer.

03:44:34.139 --> 03:44:38.280
I'm not sure about this, said her father

03:44:38.340 --> 03:44:40.920
edging away as Dark Stalker reached

03:44:40.920 --> 03:44:41.459
toward him.

03:44:41.520 --> 03:44:44.879
I don't trust anyone to put a spell on

03:44:44.879 --> 03:44:45.180
me.

03:44:45.239 --> 03:44:48.299
So we'll use something temporary.

03:44:48.360 --> 03:44:50.700
Dark Stalker said winningly.

03:44:50.760 --> 03:44:53.219
He sliced a vine off the tree branch

03:44:53.219 --> 03:44:55.500
overhead, and wove it into a simple loop

03:44:55.500 --> 03:44:57.840
which he dropped over the other dragon's

03:44:57.840 --> 03:44:58.079
neck.

03:44:58.139 --> 03:45:00.360
I'll enchant this to heal you.

03:45:00.420 --> 03:45:03.780
And when it rots away, come back, and let

03:45:03.780 --> 03:45:05.399
me know if you liked it, and want

03:45:05.399 --> 03:45:06.120
something more permanent.

03:45:06.239 --> 03:45:09.299
He hooked one claw in the vine necklace

03:45:09.299 --> 03:45:11.040
and muttered something under his breath.

03:45:11.100 --> 03:45:14.219
Mind reader's father let out a startled

03:45:14.219 --> 03:45:14.700
gasp.

03:45:14.760 --> 03:45:17.159
He stretched his wings and tail.

03:45:17.219 --> 03:45:19.379
He turned his head from side to side.

03:45:19.440 --> 03:45:22.079
He looked 40 years younger just from the

03:45:22.079 --> 03:45:24.239
way he was suddenly standing, and the way

03:45:24.239 --> 03:45:25.200
his eyes were shining.

03:45:25.260 --> 03:45:30.059
Oh, he said. 3 moons.

03:45:30.120 --> 03:45:32.520
I couldn't even remember what it was like

03:45:32.520 --> 03:45:33.420
to feel this way.

03:45:33.479 --> 03:45:37.739
I'm here to help. said Dark Stalker, with

03:45:37.739 --> 03:45:38.879
his charming grin.

03:45:38.940 --> 03:45:42.780
Now, go tell all your friends.

03:45:42.840 --> 03:45:46.620
Uh oh, thought Turtle.

03:45:46.680 --> 03:45:48.600
Uh-oh was right.

03:45:48.659 --> 03:45:51.479
The 1st trickle of curious night wings

03:45:51.479 --> 03:45:52.500
became a waterfall.

03:45:52.559 --> 03:45:55.260
Once words spread that Dark Stalker was

03:45:55.260 --> 03:45:56.219
handing out superpowers.

03:45:56.280 --> 03:46:00.120
The ability to catch any prey, done.

03:46:00.180 --> 03:46:03.840
Flight speed faster than any sky wing, or

03:46:03.840 --> 03:46:06.059
indeed any other dragon on Pyria.

03:46:06.180 --> 03:46:07.200
Done.

03:46:07.260 --> 03:46:10.620
Camouflage scales like the rain wings.

03:46:10.680 --> 03:46:13.260
Dark stalker chuckled, and talked to that

03:46:13.260 --> 03:46:14.579
dragon out of his choice.

03:46:14.639 --> 03:46:17.040
Why would you want to blow the lines of

03:46:17.040 --> 03:46:17.579
what you really are?

03:46:17.639 --> 03:46:20.579
Be a nightwing, and proud of it.

03:46:20.639 --> 03:46:24.600
If I give you advanced warrior skills

03:46:24.600 --> 03:46:26.399
you'll never need to hide again anyway.

03:46:26.459 --> 03:46:28.979
Advanced Warrior Skills.

03:46:29.040 --> 03:46:30.000
Done.

03:46:30.059 --> 03:46:32.340
The ability to go for days without sleep

03:46:32.340 --> 03:46:33.659
done.

03:46:33.719 --> 03:46:37.260
And then, Dark Stalker announced that

03:46:37.260 --> 03:46:39.840
powering up 5 dragons per day was his

03:46:39.840 --> 03:46:40.079
limit.

03:46:40.200 --> 03:46:42.719
But this way you can think about it

03:46:42.719 --> 03:46:44.159
overnight, he said.

03:46:44.280 --> 03:46:46.739
What do you each really want?

03:46:46.799 --> 03:46:49.620
What would be the best possible power for

03:46:49.620 --> 03:46:49.799
you?

03:46:49.920 --> 03:46:51.299
I promise you.

03:46:51.360 --> 03:46:54.059
I'll share my gift with 5 more dragons

03:46:54.059 --> 03:46:54.479
tomorrow.

03:46:54.540 --> 03:46:57.719
On the way to the old knight kingdom.

03:46:57.780 --> 03:46:59.940
Wow.

03:47:00.000 --> 03:47:01.379
Turtle thought.

03:47:01.440 --> 03:47:03.120
He's not messing around.

03:47:03.180 --> 03:47:07.020
Follow me, and I'll make you special, or

03:47:07.020 --> 03:47:07.559
stay here.

03:47:07.620 --> 03:47:10.319
And remain your own ordinary self.

03:47:10.379 --> 03:47:13.260
What dragon could resist an offer like

03:47:13.260 --> 03:47:13.440
that?

03:47:13.500 --> 03:47:16.979
What chance does glory have when that's

03:47:16.979 --> 03:47:17.520
the alternative?

03:47:17.579 --> 03:47:20.639
He pulled out his slate and thought for a

03:47:20.639 --> 03:47:22.559
moment, then wrote to Kibley.

03:47:23.579 --> 03:47:25.440
The night wings are getting a king.

03:47:25.559 --> 03:47:29.879
Chapter 12.

03:47:30.239 --> 03:47:34.379
Turtle could feel the tides shifting in

03:47:34.379 --> 03:47:34.799
the village.

03:47:34.860 --> 03:47:37.979
Dragons whispering about another side to

03:47:37.979 --> 03:47:40.260
dark stalker, about how the history

03:47:40.260 --> 03:47:42.899
scrolls could have been wrong, about how

03:47:42.899 --> 03:47:44.700
night wings should stick with their own

03:47:44.700 --> 03:47:47.520
and stop mingling with lazy vegetarians.

03:47:47.579 --> 03:47:50.760
I should tell glory, shouldn't I?

03:47:50.819 --> 03:47:52.559
She has no idea who I am.

03:47:52.620 --> 03:47:55.319
But she'd want to know what Dark Stalker

03:47:55.319 --> 03:47:56.520
is doing, wouldn't she?

03:47:56.579 --> 03:48:00.120
He worried for a while, watching Dark

03:48:00.120 --> 03:48:02.879
Stalker tell stories of the old days to a

03:48:02.879 --> 03:48:04.319
rapt audience of dragons.

03:48:04.379 --> 03:48:07.020
Finally, he scooted back along his branch

03:48:07.020 --> 03:48:09.299
and set off in the direction Glory had

03:48:09.299 --> 03:48:09.659
gone.

03:48:09.719 --> 03:48:12.120
A short distance beyond the Nightwing

03:48:12.120 --> 03:48:14.219
village, all the trees began to look the

03:48:14.219 --> 03:48:14.459
same.

03:48:14.520 --> 03:48:17.940
Not long after that, Turtle realized he

03:48:17.940 --> 03:48:19.319
didn't exactly know where he was going.

03:48:19.379 --> 03:48:22.739
He stopped, hovering in midair, and

03:48:22.739 --> 03:48:25.079
glanced around at the dense, never ending

03:48:25.079 --> 03:48:27.659
greenery, lost in the rainforest.

03:48:27.719 --> 03:48:30.360
That sounded exactly like what would

03:48:30.360 --> 03:48:32.040
happen to the turtle character in a

03:48:32.040 --> 03:48:32.700
story.

03:48:32.760 --> 03:48:35.879
While the heroic heroes battled onward

03:48:35.879 --> 03:48:37.739
wondering vaguely where he'd gone.

03:48:37.799 --> 03:48:41.340
Except in this case, there were no heroic

03:48:41.340 --> 03:48:43.500
heroes battling, because they were all

03:48:43.500 --> 03:48:45.360
too busy making friends with a potential

03:48:45.360 --> 03:48:46.139
supervillain.

03:48:46.260 --> 03:48:48.059
Turtle side.

03:48:48.120 --> 03:48:52.319
So, I can't be lost in the rainforest, he

03:48:52.319 --> 03:48:52.620
thought.

03:48:52.680 --> 03:48:55.379
I can't be the inept best friend right

03:48:55.379 --> 03:48:55.739
now.

03:48:55.799 --> 03:48:57.360
I have to be someone else.

03:48:57.420 --> 03:49:00.840
The messenger, perhaps, who warns the

03:49:00.840 --> 03:49:03.420
heroes of the danger, and then fades back

03:49:03.420 --> 03:49:03.899
into the background.

03:49:03.959 --> 03:49:07.260
What would a successful, determined

03:49:07.260 --> 03:49:09.000
messenger do about being lost in the

03:49:09.000 --> 03:49:09.659
rainforest?

03:49:09.719 --> 03:49:13.979
He found a very fat tree with comfortable

03:49:13.979 --> 03:49:15.360
wide branches to sit on.

03:49:15.420 --> 03:49:17.760
All around him, the bright red flowers

03:49:17.760 --> 03:49:21.180
danced, the leaves twitched, the shadows

03:49:21.180 --> 03:49:23.819
and sunlight darted and glimmered as wind

03:49:23.819 --> 03:49:25.200
pushed the treetops around.

03:49:25.260 --> 03:49:27.840
Hello, he said.

03:49:27.899 --> 03:49:30.420
Any chance I'm being followed?

03:49:30.479 --> 03:49:31.920
If he was?

03:49:31.979 --> 03:49:33.120
No one answered.

03:49:33.180 --> 03:49:34.559
He tried again.

03:49:34.620 --> 03:49:37.200
I have an urgent message for Queen

03:49:37.200 --> 03:49:37.979
Glory.

03:49:38.040 --> 03:49:39.659
She'll want to hear it, I promise.

03:49:39.719 --> 03:49:42.239
But I don't know how to find her.

03:49:42.299 --> 03:49:44.219
More silence.

03:49:44.280 --> 03:49:46.979
More trees flapping their leaves at him

03:49:46.979 --> 03:49:47.579
dismissively.

03:49:47.700 --> 03:49:50.340
So, that didn't work.

03:49:50.399 --> 03:49:52.739
He wasn't quite lucky enough to have any

03:49:52.739 --> 03:49:55.020
camouflaged rain wings spying on him

03:49:55.020 --> 03:49:55.319
right now.

03:49:55.379 --> 03:49:58.979
His immediate instinct was to use his

03:49:58.979 --> 03:49:59.459
magic.

03:49:59.520 --> 03:50:02.100
That would be the easiest solution.

03:50:02.159 --> 03:50:05.100
That was always the easiest solution.

03:50:05.219 --> 03:50:08.700
Whenever he felt a little sick, or too

03:50:08.700 --> 03:50:11.100
tired for anatomy class, or needed help

03:50:11.100 --> 03:50:13.319
finding something, he'd reach for a

03:50:13.319 --> 03:50:13.920
magical solution.

03:50:14.040 --> 03:50:16.620
As long as it was small enough for no one

03:50:16.620 --> 03:50:16.979
to notice.

03:50:17.040 --> 03:50:20.459
But he couldn't do that now, because Dark

03:50:20.459 --> 03:50:22.979
Stalker would notice any spell, no matter

03:50:22.979 --> 03:50:23.579
how small.

03:50:23.639 --> 03:50:25.920
His talons went to his pouch.

03:50:25.979 --> 03:50:29.159
Wait, maybe he already had what he

03:50:29.159 --> 03:50:29.399
needed.

03:50:29.520 --> 03:50:32.399
He slipped the pouch open with careful

03:50:32.399 --> 03:50:35.700
claws, tipping it, so his animus touched

03:50:35.700 --> 03:50:37.440
treasures clicked and tumbled together.

03:50:37.500 --> 03:50:40.620
Near the bottom, wrapped in leaves to

03:50:40.620 --> 03:50:42.659
protect it, was the piece of coral.

03:50:42.719 --> 03:50:46.139
It was shaped like a small lacy red tree

03:50:46.139 --> 03:50:48.120
with little bubbles all along its

03:50:48.120 --> 03:50:48.600
branches.

03:50:48.659 --> 03:50:51.360
Turtle remembered the night he'd

03:50:51.360 --> 03:50:51.840
enchanted it.

03:50:51.899 --> 03:50:53.819
The night he'd realized he was an

03:50:53.819 --> 03:50:54.780
animus.

03:50:54.840 --> 03:50:57.840
Queen Coral's sons were rarely invited to

03:50:57.840 --> 03:51:00.059
royal functions, as there were simply too

03:51:00.059 --> 03:51:00.540
many of them.

03:51:00.659 --> 03:51:03.840
But when turtle, octopus, and cerulean

03:51:03.840 --> 03:51:06.059
were all one year old, their father

03:51:06.059 --> 03:51:08.159
managed to get them invited to their 1st

03:51:08.159 --> 03:51:09.059
graham ball.

03:51:09.120 --> 03:51:10.920
Turtles brothers were excited.

03:51:11.040 --> 03:51:13.079
Turtle was mostly nervous.

03:51:13.139 --> 03:51:14.760
Would he say the right things?

03:51:14.819 --> 03:51:16.739
Would he remember all the rules about

03:51:16.739 --> 03:51:20.100
when to eat, and more important, when not

03:51:20.100 --> 03:51:20.760
to eat?

03:51:20.819 --> 03:51:23.879
Gil had sent matching earrings for all

03:51:23.879 --> 03:51:24.780
the princes to wear.

03:51:24.840 --> 03:51:27.959
Each one a heavy gold ring with a pearl

03:51:27.959 --> 03:51:28.559
hanging from it.

03:51:28.620 --> 03:51:31.559
Octopus and cerulean clipped theirs on

03:51:31.559 --> 03:51:33.899
easily, but turtle could not figure his

03:51:33.899 --> 03:51:34.139
out.

03:51:34.200 --> 03:51:36.360
He'd never worn an earring before.

03:51:36.420 --> 03:51:39.299
His claws felt too big and awkward to

03:51:39.299 --> 03:51:41.459
work the catch open far enough, and the

03:51:41.459 --> 03:51:43.139
earrings kept slipping out of his grasp

03:51:43.139 --> 03:51:45.899
and floating slowly down to the seaweed

03:51:45.899 --> 03:51:46.920
carpeted floor of his room.

03:51:46.979 --> 03:51:50.459
Octopus and cerulean laughed at him as he

03:51:50.459 --> 03:51:52.620
scrabbled in the seaweed, which had

03:51:52.620 --> 03:51:54.059
swallowed one of the earrings

03:51:54.059 --> 03:51:54.540
completely.

03:51:54.600 --> 03:51:58.319
It's not that hard, Octopus teased.

03:51:58.379 --> 03:52:00.600
His phosphorescent scales flashing.

03:52:00.659 --> 03:52:02.879
By all the whales' turtle, do you have

03:52:02.879 --> 03:52:04.139
tentacles for talons?

03:52:04.200 --> 03:52:06.180
They turn to swim out of the room.

03:52:06.239 --> 03:52:09.659
See there, Cerolean called mockingly.

03:52:09.719 --> 03:52:13.139
If you ever make it, octopus agreed, and

03:52:13.139 --> 03:52:14.879
they cackled their way down the hall.

03:52:14.879 --> 03:52:17.819
Grimly, Turtle glared at the remaining

03:52:17.819 --> 03:52:19.920
earring, pinched between his claws.

03:52:20.040 --> 03:52:24.420
Arr, earring, he snarled, shaking it.

03:52:24.479 --> 03:52:27.239
Get on my ear right now, and stay there.

03:52:27.299 --> 03:52:31.200
The earring moved, shimmying in turtle's

03:52:31.200 --> 03:52:31.440
grasp.

03:52:31.559 --> 03:52:34.860
Startled, he let go, and the earring

03:52:34.860 --> 03:52:37.020
confidently made a beeline straight for

03:52:37.020 --> 03:52:37.799
turtle's ear.

03:52:37.799 --> 03:52:40.799
A moment later, he felt a nudging pinch

03:52:40.799 --> 03:52:43.020
and when he looked in the mirror, there

03:52:43.020 --> 03:52:45.420
it was, hanging from his ear exactly

03:52:45.420 --> 03:52:46.500
where it was supposed to be.

03:52:46.559 --> 03:52:48.659
Did I do that?

03:52:48.719 --> 03:52:52.139
He felt terrified and elated at the same

03:52:52.139 --> 03:52:52.379
time.

03:52:52.440 --> 03:52:55.200
If he did that, there was only one

03:52:55.200 --> 03:52:56.100
explanation.

03:52:56.159 --> 03:52:59.579
He'd heard the stories about Albatross

03:52:59.579 --> 03:53:02.760
the ancient animus sea wing, although

03:53:02.760 --> 03:53:04.440
that particular story didn't end very

03:53:04.440 --> 03:53:04.739
well.

03:53:04.739 --> 03:53:07.139
There were fewer stories about other

03:53:07.139 --> 03:53:10.260
animus sea wings, like Fathom, who were

03:53:10.260 --> 03:53:11.760
much more cautious with their powers.

03:53:11.819 --> 03:53:14.879
Despite the horror stories, a part of

03:53:14.879 --> 03:53:16.500
Turtle had always wondered what it would

03:53:16.500 --> 03:53:19.020
be like to be an animus, with all that

03:53:19.020 --> 03:53:20.700
power in his claws.

03:53:20.760 --> 03:53:23.340
He had to test it out, to find out if it

03:53:23.340 --> 03:53:23.639
was real.

03:53:23.760 --> 03:53:26.340
One of the walls of their room was made

03:53:26.340 --> 03:53:28.920
of coral, and he'd noticed a small piece

03:53:28.920 --> 03:53:30.120
that was nearly broken off.

03:53:30.239 --> 03:53:32.940
He swam over and carefully snapped it

03:53:32.940 --> 03:53:35.040
free, then clasped it between his

03:53:35.040 --> 03:53:36.059
talons.

03:53:36.120 --> 03:53:39.659
I enchant this piece of coral to help me

03:53:39.659 --> 03:53:41.100
find whatever I'm looking for.

03:53:41.159 --> 03:53:44.399
He peeked to the coral, but it looked

03:53:44.399 --> 03:53:45.180
exactly the same.

03:53:45.239 --> 03:53:46.680
Hmm.

03:53:46.739 --> 03:53:50.819
My other earring, he flashed at it in

03:53:50.819 --> 03:53:51.420
aquatic.

03:53:51.479 --> 03:53:53.819
He caught himself wondering whether coral

03:53:53.819 --> 03:53:56.219
could speak aquatic, just as the little

03:53:56.219 --> 03:53:58.319
red tree twitched and twisted in his

03:53:58.319 --> 03:53:59.100
claws.

03:53:59.159 --> 03:54:01.739
It tugged him down to the seaweed carpet

03:54:01.739 --> 03:54:03.899
where it poked through the flapping

03:54:03.899 --> 03:54:06.180
overlapping strands until it bumped

03:54:06.180 --> 03:54:07.260
against his missing earring.

03:54:07.319 --> 03:54:10.139
That might have been the most glorious

03:54:10.139 --> 03:54:11.399
moment of turtle's life.

03:54:11.459 --> 03:54:14.040
It was certainly all downhill from there

03:54:14.040 --> 03:54:14.760
if you asked him.

03:54:14.819 --> 03:54:17.159
He was an animus.

03:54:17.219 --> 03:54:19.680
His brothers couldn't laugh at him now.

03:54:19.739 --> 03:54:22.139
His mother and father would have to pay

03:54:22.139 --> 03:54:22.739
attention to him.

03:54:22.799 --> 03:54:25.139
He'd be the star of the whole palace.

03:54:25.200 --> 03:54:28.500
That was kind of a frightening thought

03:54:28.500 --> 03:54:28.739
actually.

03:54:28.860 --> 03:54:31.440
Everyone looking at him.

03:54:31.500 --> 03:54:36.000
Everyone wanting him to perform, everyone

03:54:36.000 --> 03:54:37.680
waiting for him to mess up.

03:54:37.799 --> 03:54:41.700
But the truth was, only one thing stopped

03:54:41.700 --> 03:54:43.860
him from swimming straight into the ball

03:54:43.860 --> 03:54:45.899
and announcing his discovery to everyone

03:54:45.959 --> 03:54:47.819
stories.

03:54:47.940 --> 03:54:50.520
Turtle knew how stories worked.

03:54:50.579 --> 03:54:53.760
He knew that a dragon with strange powers

03:54:53.760 --> 03:54:56.700
could be a hero, or a villain.

03:54:56.760 --> 03:54:59.280
And a lot depended on how everyone found

03:54:59.280 --> 03:55:01.319
out what he or she could do.

03:55:01.379 --> 03:55:04.559
The best heroes were the ones who took

03:55:04.559 --> 03:55:06.420
everyone by surprise in their hour of

03:55:06.420 --> 03:55:09.659
need, just when all hope was lost, the

03:55:09.659 --> 03:55:12.059
unexpected hero would swoop in and save

03:55:12.059 --> 03:55:12.360
the day.

03:55:12.420 --> 03:55:15.959
And if Turtle revealed his power that way

03:55:15.959 --> 03:55:19.020
when it was really needed, then no one

03:55:19.020 --> 03:55:19.920
would be scared of him.

03:55:19.979 --> 03:55:21.719
He'd clearly be a hero.

03:55:21.780 --> 03:55:25.979
Drama, excitement, and the chance to do

03:55:25.979 --> 03:55:27.780
something wonderful when no one saw it

03:55:27.780 --> 03:55:28.079
coming.

03:55:28.139 --> 03:55:31.260
That's what Turtle wanted in his story.

03:55:31.319 --> 03:55:34.739
So he hit his power, waiting for the

03:55:34.739 --> 03:55:36.000
perfect moment of revelation.

03:55:36.059 --> 03:55:38.940
The tribes were all at war.

03:55:39.000 --> 03:55:40.079
Surely it would come soon.

03:55:40.139 --> 03:55:43.920
But then it came, when his father needed

03:55:43.920 --> 03:55:46.200
him, and he didn't recognize it.

03:55:46.260 --> 03:55:47.700
And then it was gone.

03:55:47.760 --> 03:55:51.299
In the rainforest, far from home.

03:55:51.360 --> 03:55:54.780
Turtles sighed and turned the coral over

03:55:54.780 --> 03:55:55.440
in his claws.

03:55:55.559 --> 03:55:58.799
The last time he'd used it was the day

03:55:58.799 --> 03:56:00.659
Gil sent him searching for Snapper.

03:56:00.780 --> 03:56:03.959
Turtle had had to be very surreptitious

03:56:03.959 --> 03:56:06.540
since octopus and cerulean insisted on

03:56:06.540 --> 03:56:08.760
following him around, and giggling over

03:56:08.760 --> 03:56:09.959
how incompetent he was.

03:56:10.020 --> 03:56:12.360
At 1st he thought he'd been very clever

03:56:12.360 --> 03:56:14.700
to think of using the coral, but it

03:56:14.700 --> 03:56:15.239
hadn't worked.

03:56:15.299 --> 03:56:16.799
Something was wrong with it.

03:56:16.860 --> 03:56:19.559
It kept trying to lead him out of the

03:56:19.559 --> 03:56:21.719
deep palace, which was why he was

03:56:21.719 --> 03:56:23.700
uselessly prowling the gardens when Gil

03:56:23.700 --> 03:56:24.120
found him.

03:56:24.180 --> 03:56:26.579
He should have enchanted something else

03:56:26.579 --> 03:56:29.520
even with octopus and Zerulean watching.

03:56:29.579 --> 03:56:32.219
He should have realized that finding

03:56:32.219 --> 03:56:34.319
Snapper was the great thing he was meant

03:56:34.319 --> 03:56:34.620
to do.

03:56:34.739 --> 03:56:37.440
He should have revealed his secret right

03:56:37.440 --> 03:56:39.000
then and saved the day.

03:56:39.059 --> 03:56:42.959
In fact, he should have used his magic to

03:56:42.959 --> 03:56:44.700
find the assassin who was killing off the

03:56:44.700 --> 03:56:45.239
princesses.

03:56:45.299 --> 03:56:49.139
It was embarrassing and awful, that he'd

03:56:49.139 --> 03:56:50.459
never even thought of that until years

03:56:50.459 --> 03:56:53.159
later, when tsunami showed up and figured

03:56:53.159 --> 03:56:53.760
out who it was.

03:56:53.819 --> 03:56:57.299
But after Turtle's failure, he didn't

03:56:57.299 --> 03:56:59.579
know how to tell anyone he was an animus

03:56:59.579 --> 03:57:01.799
he'd lost the plot of his story.

03:57:01.920 --> 03:57:05.459
He kept imagining his father saying, But

03:57:05.459 --> 03:57:07.260
if you had magic the whole time.

03:57:07.319 --> 03:57:09.059
Why didn't you find Snapper?

03:57:09.120 --> 03:57:11.159
Why didn't you save your sisters?

03:57:11.219 --> 03:57:14.159
What kind of dragon has this power and

03:57:14.159 --> 03:57:15.479
doesn't use it to help his family?

03:57:15.540 --> 03:57:18.780
I'm more disappointed in you than ever.

03:57:18.840 --> 03:57:21.840
And the longer he hit it, the worse it

03:57:21.840 --> 03:57:22.079
got.

03:57:22.139 --> 03:57:25.200
Why didn't he use his magic to rescue his

03:57:25.200 --> 03:57:26.700
father from the sky wings?

03:57:26.760 --> 03:57:29.340
Why didn't he use his magic to stop the

03:57:29.340 --> 03:57:30.719
attack on the summer palace?

03:57:30.780 --> 03:57:34.139
Why was he such a useless, wretched

03:57:34.139 --> 03:57:35.340
excuse for a dragon?

03:57:35.399 --> 03:57:39.120
Turtle realized he was gripping the

03:57:39.120 --> 03:57:41.280
corals so tightly that it was leaving an

03:57:41.280 --> 03:57:42.420
imprint in his palm.

03:57:42.479 --> 03:57:45.479
He unclenched his fist and looked at it

03:57:45.479 --> 03:57:48.000
He wasn't even sure why he'd kept the

03:57:48.000 --> 03:57:49.500
thing after it failed him.

03:57:49.559 --> 03:57:51.600
Maybe because it was the 1st real

03:57:51.600 --> 03:57:53.399
enchantment he'd ever cast.

03:57:53.459 --> 03:57:56.399
It reminded him of that brief moment when

03:57:56.399 --> 03:57:58.559
he'd been so happy and excited about his

03:57:58.559 --> 03:57:58.920
future.

03:57:58.979 --> 03:58:02.219
Most likely, it wouldn't work now

03:58:02.219 --> 03:58:02.520
either.

03:58:02.579 --> 03:58:05.280
But he couldn't enchant anything new.

03:58:05.340 --> 03:58:08.280
He didn't have many other options, and it

03:58:08.280 --> 03:58:08.879
was worth a try.

03:58:09.000 --> 03:58:12.239
Queen Glory, he whispered.

03:58:12.299 --> 03:58:16.079
The coral twitched and hummed softly, then

03:58:16.079 --> 03:58:17.040
tugged him northward.

03:58:17.100 --> 03:58:20.040
He spread his wings and flew, paying

03:58:20.040 --> 03:58:22.500
attention to the signals it gave, turning

03:58:22.500 --> 03:58:24.840
him this way and that, and upward through

03:58:24.840 --> 03:58:26.280
the forest toward the canopy.

03:58:26.340 --> 03:58:29.760
I could have used this to help peril find

03:58:29.760 --> 03:58:32.940
Scarlet, he realized, or to find my

03:58:32.940 --> 03:58:33.959
friends in possibility.

03:58:34.020 --> 03:58:37.620
Instead, he had left it behind at school

03:58:37.620 --> 03:58:40.440
with his other animus touched objects, it

03:58:40.440 --> 03:58:41.819
hadn't even occurred to him to try using

03:58:41.819 --> 03:58:42.120
it.

03:58:42.180 --> 03:58:45.120
He wouldn't have expected it to work, and

03:58:45.120 --> 03:58:46.860
he wouldn't have wanted peril to notice

03:58:46.860 --> 03:58:47.159
it.

03:58:47.219 --> 03:58:49.739
But it certainly would have been useful.

03:58:49.799 --> 03:58:51.360
He thought ruefully.

03:58:51.420 --> 03:58:54.420
Add that to the list of ways I could have

03:58:54.420 --> 03:58:56.459
helpfully used my magic and didn't.

03:58:56.579 --> 03:58:59.940
Soon enough, there was glory.

03:59:00.000 --> 03:59:03.299
There, in fact, was the entire rain wing

03:59:03.299 --> 03:59:05.579
village tucked into the treetops.

03:59:05.579 --> 03:59:08.520
As Turtle flew closer, he saw more and

03:59:08.520 --> 03:59:10.620
more shapes emerge from the leaves

03:59:10.620 --> 03:59:13.979
hammocks, and walkways, pavilions and

03:59:13.979 --> 03:59:16.979
dwellings, silver furred sloths, and

03:59:16.979 --> 03:59:18.420
beautiful dragons of all colors

03:59:18.420 --> 03:59:19.139
everywhere.

03:59:19.200 --> 03:59:22.379
Queen Glory was on one of the highest

03:59:22.379 --> 03:59:25.440
pavilions, bathed in sunlight with her

03:59:25.440 --> 03:59:26.520
wings spread wide.

03:59:26.579 --> 03:59:29.940
She was asleep, but Deathbringer sat

03:59:29.940 --> 03:59:32.219
watchfully beside her, scanning the

03:59:32.219 --> 03:59:33.479
undergrowth for any threats.

03:59:33.540 --> 03:59:36.899
Threats seemed hard to imagine here, in

03:59:36.899 --> 03:59:39.299
this peaceful place, but turtle thought

03:59:39.299 --> 03:59:41.040
of dark stalker and his 5 new

03:59:41.040 --> 03:59:43.620
superpowered night wings, only a short

03:59:43.620 --> 03:59:45.479
flight away, and he shivered.

03:59:45.540 --> 03:59:48.360
The coral tugged him stubbornly toward

03:59:48.360 --> 03:59:48.840
the platform.

03:59:48.899 --> 03:59:52.440
Deathbringer saw him coming and sat up

03:59:52.440 --> 03:59:54.360
with a sharply curious, but not

03:59:54.360 --> 03:59:55.319
unfriendly expression.

03:59:55.379 --> 03:59:57.840
Holt, he called.

03:59:57.899 --> 03:59:59.520
When turtle was only a short distance

03:59:59.520 --> 04:00:00.059
away.

04:00:00.120 --> 04:00:02.100
What business do you have with the

04:00:02.100 --> 04:00:02.340
queen?

04:00:02.459 --> 04:00:05.639
The animus touched Coral did not like it

04:00:05.639 --> 04:00:08.040
at all when Turtles stopped and hovered

04:00:08.040 --> 04:00:08.579
in midair.

04:00:08.639 --> 04:00:11.639
It jabbed painfully at his palm, trying

04:00:11.639 --> 04:00:12.299
to move him forward.

04:00:12.360 --> 04:00:13.860
A bit late.

04:00:13.920 --> 04:00:16.200
Turtle remembered the coral's weird

04:00:16.200 --> 04:00:16.620
habit.

04:00:16.680 --> 04:00:19.379
It would not stop searching for the thing

04:00:19.379 --> 04:00:21.479
he wanted to find until he actually

04:00:21.479 --> 04:00:23.459
touched the object with the coral.

04:00:23.520 --> 04:00:25.559
It wouldn't fly away on its own.

04:00:25.620 --> 04:00:28.079
But every time he picked it up, it would

04:00:28.079 --> 04:00:30.000
squirm and poke him until it reached its

04:00:30.000 --> 04:00:30.420
goal.

04:00:30.420 --> 04:00:33.659
This had been confirmed rather gruesomely

04:00:33.659 --> 04:00:35.520
when it dragged him through the palace

04:00:35.520 --> 04:00:38.219
the night after his failure, just so it

04:00:38.219 --> 04:00:40.260
could bump itself against the side of

04:00:40.260 --> 04:00:43.139
Snapper's corpse, in a way that turtle

04:00:43.139 --> 04:00:45.540
thought was entirely too smug for a

04:00:45.540 --> 04:00:47.100
malfunctioning scrap of coral.

04:00:47.159 --> 04:00:51.420
Um, turtle said, clapping his other

04:00:51.420 --> 04:00:52.799
talent around the one that held the

04:00:52.799 --> 04:00:53.280
coral.

04:00:53.340 --> 04:00:56.399
I've been watching Dark Stalker since you

04:00:56.399 --> 04:00:58.739
left the Nightwing Village, and I thought

04:00:58.739 --> 04:01:00.299
the Queen should know what he's been up

04:01:00.299 --> 04:01:00.540
to.

04:01:00.600 --> 04:01:04.200
What's a sea wing doing in the rainforest

04:01:04.200 --> 04:01:05.040
in the 1st place?

04:01:05.100 --> 04:01:07.139
Death Bringer asked doubtfully.

04:01:07.200 --> 04:01:10.020
Are you here with dog stalker, like the

04:01:10.020 --> 04:01:10.319
princess?

04:01:10.379 --> 04:01:12.059
No, no.

04:01:12.120 --> 04:01:13.379
Turtle said.

04:01:13.440 --> 04:01:15.420
I mean, I'm just watching him.

04:01:15.479 --> 04:01:19.620
Anemone is my sister, he fumbled, but

04:01:19.620 --> 04:01:20.879
apparently that was enough of an

04:01:20.879 --> 04:01:22.200
explanation for Deathbringer.

04:01:22.260 --> 04:01:24.600
I see, he said.

04:01:24.659 --> 04:01:27.540
Well, I'm reluctant to wake the queen

04:01:27.540 --> 04:01:28.620
during her suntime.

04:01:28.680 --> 04:01:29.700
Is it urgent?

04:01:29.760 --> 04:01:32.579
Um said turtle.

04:01:32.639 --> 04:01:33.780
Probably not.

04:01:33.899 --> 04:01:36.780
If Dark Stalker wasn't going to enchant

04:01:36.780 --> 04:01:39.120
any more dragons today, did it make any

04:01:39.120 --> 04:01:39.659
difference?

04:01:39.659 --> 04:01:41.879
Death bringer.

04:01:42.000 --> 04:01:45.360
Queen Glory said with a sigh, opening her

04:01:45.360 --> 04:01:45.659
eyes.

04:01:45.719 --> 04:01:48.479
I'm not sure if you're familiar with a

04:01:48.479 --> 04:01:51.600
concept of ears and how they work, but

04:01:51.600 --> 04:01:53.579
most normal dragons would find it very

04:01:53.579 --> 04:01:55.379
difficult to sleep through your allowed

04:01:55.379 --> 04:01:56.340
interrogations.

04:01:56.399 --> 04:01:59.579
I was giving you the opportunity to

04:01:59.579 --> 04:02:01.319
pretend to sleep through them.

04:02:01.440 --> 04:02:03.180
Death bringer objected.

04:02:03.239 --> 04:02:05.100
You're usually much better at it.

04:02:05.159 --> 04:02:08.459
I nearly gave myself away by laughing

04:02:08.459 --> 04:02:12.479
when you said, halt, though, Glory said

04:02:12.479 --> 04:02:14.459
stretching and sitting up.

04:02:14.520 --> 04:02:17.639
I mean, who says halt, seriously.

04:02:17.700 --> 04:02:20.819
I thought it sounded dignified and

04:02:20.819 --> 04:02:22.799
commanding, said Deathbringer.

04:02:22.860 --> 04:02:26.459
Indeed, or like a pretentious night wing

04:02:26.459 --> 04:02:27.420
glory observed.

04:02:27.479 --> 04:02:30.840
I am a pretentious night wing.

04:02:30.899 --> 04:02:32.219
It's part of my appeal.

04:02:32.280 --> 04:02:36.420
All right, hush, you, said Glory.

04:02:36.479 --> 04:02:38.520
Patting Deathbringer's talons with her

04:02:38.520 --> 04:02:38.760
tail.

04:02:38.819 --> 04:02:41.940
Come here, Seawing, what's your name?

04:02:42.000 --> 04:02:46.139
Turtle, your majesty, he said.

04:02:46.200 --> 04:02:49.260
The coral was kind of going berserk as he

04:02:49.260 --> 04:02:51.420
landed beside her, and she shot a curious

04:02:51.420 --> 04:02:53.159
look at his squirming talons.

04:02:53.219 --> 04:02:55.319
I'm tsunami's brother.

04:02:55.379 --> 04:02:56.459
One of them.

04:02:56.520 --> 04:02:58.139
I'm nobody really.

04:02:58.200 --> 04:03:00.059
The messenger.

04:03:00.180 --> 04:03:02.100
Here to tell someone who can actually

04:03:02.100 --> 04:03:02.879
save the world.

04:03:03.000 --> 04:03:06.299
I just thought you should know that Dark

04:03:06.299 --> 04:03:08.340
Stalker has given a few night wings

04:03:08.340 --> 04:03:09.540
special powers.

04:03:09.600 --> 04:03:13.500
Special powers, Deathbringer echoed.

04:03:13.559 --> 04:03:14.340
Like what?

04:03:14.399 --> 04:03:19.020
Mind reading, turtle listed off, super

04:03:19.020 --> 04:03:22.079
strength, fighting skills, the power to

04:03:22.079 --> 04:03:25.379
catch any prey, instant healing, that

04:03:25.379 --> 04:03:25.739
kind of thing.

04:03:25.799 --> 04:03:28.979
Wow, said Glory.

04:03:29.040 --> 04:03:30.959
It's going to be hard to compete with

04:03:30.959 --> 04:03:31.319
that.

04:03:31.379 --> 04:03:34.680
I wouldn't leave you, even for a

04:03:34.680 --> 04:03:37.020
superpower, Deathbringer said loyally.

04:03:37.079 --> 04:03:40.739
I think that is your superpower, Glory

04:03:40.739 --> 04:03:41.280
said to him.

04:03:41.340 --> 04:03:43.559
Extreme heroic idiocy.

04:03:43.620 --> 04:03:46.139
She arranged her face to look serious

04:03:46.139 --> 04:03:47.700
again and turned to turtle.

04:03:47.760 --> 04:03:51.540
Well, if that means all the night wings

04:03:51.540 --> 04:03:54.120
decide to go with dark stalker, I suppose

04:03:54.120 --> 04:03:55.500
my job around here will get a lot

04:03:55.500 --> 04:03:55.860
easier.

04:03:55.920 --> 04:03:58.799
She looked wistfully out at the rest of

04:03:58.799 --> 04:04:01.139
the village, where many of the rain wings

04:04:01.139 --> 04:04:03.000
were asleep in their leaf hammocks and

04:04:03.000 --> 04:04:03.959
sunlit nests.

04:04:04.020 --> 04:04:08.459
That's true, said Deathbringer, much less

04:04:08.459 --> 04:04:10.139
grumbling and complaining to deal with.

04:04:10.200 --> 04:04:13.559
They were kind of growing on me, though

04:04:13.559 --> 04:04:14.700
Glory admitted.

04:04:14.760 --> 04:04:18.299
They're impressively resilient.

04:04:18.360 --> 04:04:22.079
Not to mention, observed with scrolls and

04:04:22.079 --> 04:04:25.079
learning and stuff, said Deathbringer, all

04:04:25.079 --> 04:04:25.799
your favorite things.

04:04:25.860 --> 04:04:29.159
I did think the night wings and the rain

04:04:29.159 --> 04:04:30.360
wings could be good for each other.

04:04:30.420 --> 04:04:32.879
Once they had some mutual respect and

04:04:32.879 --> 04:04:33.600
trust in place.

04:04:33.659 --> 04:04:36.959
Glory lifted her wings up and down in a

04:04:36.959 --> 04:04:37.620
soft sigh.

04:04:37.680 --> 04:04:39.420
Oh, well.

04:04:39.540 --> 04:04:43.799
Wait, said Turtle, you're not going to do

04:04:43.799 --> 04:04:45.420
anything to stop him?

04:04:45.479 --> 04:04:47.520
We have an agreement.

04:04:47.579 --> 04:04:49.799
Glory said, surprised.

04:04:49.860 --> 04:04:51.420
Why would I stop him?

04:04:51.479 --> 04:04:55.860
Um, maybe because he's turning his tribe

04:04:55.860 --> 04:04:57.180
into kind of a super army.

04:04:57.239 --> 04:04:59.399
Doesn't that worry either of you?

04:04:59.459 --> 04:05:02.639
Huh, said Deathbringer.

04:05:02.700 --> 04:05:04.739
I guess you could look at it that way.

04:05:04.799 --> 04:05:07.799
Isn't it your job to look at it that

04:05:07.799 --> 04:05:08.040
way?

04:05:08.100 --> 04:05:09.659
Turtle thought?

04:05:09.719 --> 04:05:10.440
Frustrated?

04:05:10.500 --> 04:05:13.500
Maybe, if it was anyone else.

04:05:13.559 --> 04:05:17.520
Quinn Gloria agreed, but I mean, Dark

04:05:17.520 --> 04:05:19.139
Stalker is such a great dragon.

04:05:19.200 --> 04:05:21.239
I just trust him.

04:05:21.299 --> 04:05:22.620
Don't you?

04:05:22.680 --> 04:05:26.459
I do, Deathbringer said, nodding.

04:05:26.520 --> 04:05:27.059
I like him.

04:05:27.120 --> 04:05:29.040
Turtle couldn't speak.

04:05:29.100 --> 04:05:31.260
His head felt as if it was full of

04:05:31.260 --> 04:05:33.840
squirming, flashing electric eels.

04:05:33.899 --> 04:05:36.959
All his suspicions coalesced into one

04:05:36.959 --> 04:05:38.399
diamond bright conviction.

04:05:38.459 --> 04:05:43.200
This was not a normal reaction, not to

04:05:43.200 --> 04:05:45.899
dark stalker, nor any dragon who came in

04:05:45.899 --> 04:05:47.579
to steal the tribe you were ruling.

04:05:47.700 --> 04:05:50.700
None of the dragons who'd spoken to Dark

04:05:50.700 --> 04:05:52.739
Stalker were reacting to him in a normal

04:05:52.739 --> 04:05:53.340
way.

04:05:53.399 --> 04:05:55.260
Kibley was right after all.

04:05:55.319 --> 04:05:57.600
He had been under a spell.

04:05:57.659 --> 04:06:01.020
That calm, trusting feeling he'd had

04:06:01.020 --> 04:06:03.299
about dark stalker, that was the work of

04:06:03.299 --> 04:06:03.659
magic.

04:06:03.719 --> 04:06:06.600
This was why everyone was behaving so

04:06:06.600 --> 04:06:08.639
weird and unworried.

04:06:08.700 --> 04:06:11.459
Dark Stalker had crafted some kind of

04:06:11.459 --> 04:06:13.920
spell. something that affected every

04:06:13.920 --> 04:06:15.000
dragon who met him.

04:06:15.059 --> 04:06:18.360
It made dragons like him and trust him

04:06:18.360 --> 04:06:20.219
and perhaps worse.

04:06:20.280 --> 04:06:22.739
What if it made everyone obey him?

04:06:22.799 --> 04:06:25.739
Or willing to sacrifice their lives for

04:06:25.739 --> 04:06:25.979
him.

04:06:26.040 --> 04:06:30.000
If Dark Stalker wanted to, he could turn

04:06:30.000 --> 04:06:33.120
all the dragons of Pyria, one by one, into

04:06:33.120 --> 04:06:35.879
his own personal puppets, and nobody

04:06:35.879 --> 04:06:38.340
would be able to stop him, because nobody

04:06:38.340 --> 04:06:39.899
would even know anything was wrong.

04:06:39.959 --> 04:06:44.700
Chapter 13.

04:06:44.879 --> 04:06:51.120
So, maybe now it's time to run and hide.

04:06:51.180 --> 04:06:52.319
Turtle thought.

04:06:52.379 --> 04:06:54.540
Back to the kingdom of the sea.

04:06:54.600 --> 04:06:56.819
Back to the anonymity of his pack of

04:06:56.819 --> 04:06:57.239
brothers.

04:06:57.299 --> 04:07:00.840
Back to a world so distant that Dark

04:07:00.840 --> 04:07:02.459
Stalker might never come there.

04:07:02.520 --> 04:07:05.040
Back to the only place that might be safe

04:07:05.040 --> 04:07:06.840
at least for a little while.

04:07:06.899 --> 04:07:09.719
This was too big for him to handle.

04:07:09.780 --> 04:07:12.659
He sort of had Kibley, but what if

04:07:12.659 --> 04:07:15.120
something happened to Kibley, or Dark

04:07:15.120 --> 04:07:16.860
Stalker figured out how to ensnare him

04:07:16.860 --> 04:07:17.100
again?

04:07:17.159 --> 04:07:19.979
Turtle could end up as the only dragon

04:07:19.979 --> 04:07:22.739
Empyrea, who saw dark stalker the way he

04:07:22.739 --> 04:07:23.159
really was.

04:07:23.219 --> 04:07:24.600
And then what?

04:07:24.719 --> 04:07:27.000
Spend the rest of his life as the

04:07:27.000 --> 04:07:29.100
unbalanced, invisible dragon?

04:07:29.159 --> 04:07:31.319
trying to convince his friends, they were

04:07:31.319 --> 04:07:33.239
bewitched by a sinister magician.

04:07:33.299 --> 04:07:35.879
The mad prophet of doom.

04:07:35.940 --> 04:07:38.879
Not exactly the role I ever saw myself

04:07:38.879 --> 04:07:39.299
in.

04:07:39.360 --> 04:07:43.319
But the alternative was coward who sits

04:07:43.319 --> 04:07:45.420
and waits for the inevitable apocalypse.

04:07:45.479 --> 04:07:48.540
If he scurried off back to the ocean.

04:07:48.600 --> 04:07:50.280
Would anyone ever notice what Dark

04:07:50.280 --> 04:07:51.180
Stalker was doing?

04:07:51.239 --> 04:07:53.579
Would anyone ever be able to stop him?

04:07:53.639 --> 04:07:57.299
So if he couldn't run away, and he

04:07:57.299 --> 04:07:59.459
couldn't change anyone's mind, and he

04:07:59.459 --> 04:08:01.920
couldn't fight Dark Stalker himself, what

04:08:01.920 --> 04:08:02.579
could he do?

04:08:02.639 --> 04:08:04.860
I need help.

04:08:04.920 --> 04:08:08.159
He touched the cord of his pouch, tied

04:08:08.159 --> 04:08:08.700
around his neck.

04:08:08.760 --> 04:08:10.680
Should he write to Kibley?

04:08:10.680 --> 04:08:11.819
ask him to come here.

04:08:11.879 --> 04:08:15.600
He could feel his worrying reflex kicking

04:08:15.600 --> 04:08:15.959
into action.

04:08:16.020 --> 04:08:19.319
His scales felt hot and clammy at the

04:08:19.319 --> 04:08:19.559
same time.

04:08:19.620 --> 04:08:23.159
Was he sure that Kibley was free of any

04:08:23.159 --> 04:08:24.299
dark stalker spells?

04:08:24.360 --> 04:08:26.819
What if dark stalker had enchanted his

04:08:26.819 --> 04:08:29.219
spell to be irreversible, even by other

04:08:29.219 --> 04:08:29.579
magic?

04:08:29.639 --> 04:08:32.639
Or what if he'd enchanted Kibley to stay

04:08:32.639 --> 04:08:34.920
at Jade Mountain, so seeing him in the

04:08:34.920 --> 04:08:36.299
rainforest would make him suspicious.

04:08:36.420 --> 04:08:39.719
Everything Kibley did might give Dark

04:08:39.719 --> 04:08:42.299
Stalker a clue that his spell wasn't

04:08:42.299 --> 04:08:43.079
working on him anymore.

04:08:43.139 --> 04:08:46.739
Turtle's safety would be in danger, if

04:08:46.739 --> 04:08:48.719
Kibley and Dark Stalker spent too much

04:08:48.719 --> 04:08:49.559
time near each other.

04:08:49.620 --> 04:08:52.620
I wish I could get his advice, though.

04:08:52.739 --> 04:08:56.159
Turtle dropped his talons, frustrated.

04:08:56.219 --> 04:08:58.860
Too bad the slates don't work both ways.

04:08:58.920 --> 04:09:01.739
Thanks to me being a short-sighted idiot

04:09:01.739 --> 04:09:02.219
again.

04:09:02.340 --> 04:09:04.620
Who else could help him?

04:09:04.739 --> 04:09:07.379
I need someone who hasn't met Dark

04:09:07.379 --> 04:09:08.040
Stalker yet.

04:09:08.100 --> 04:09:10.979
Someone who will believe me, someone who

04:09:10.979 --> 04:09:12.120
can actually be the hero.

04:09:12.180 --> 04:09:13.979
His mother?

04:09:14.040 --> 04:09:16.620
Would Queen Coral believe him if he went

04:09:16.620 --> 04:09:17.459
to her with this story?

04:09:17.520 --> 04:09:21.299
Would she be able, or willing, to fight

04:09:21.299 --> 04:09:22.200
dark stalker?

04:09:22.260 --> 04:09:24.899
He couldn't really imagine her trusting

04:09:24.899 --> 04:09:25.500
him that much.

04:09:25.559 --> 04:09:28.559
And if she did, and brought the sea wings

04:09:28.559 --> 04:09:30.719
out to fight dark stalker, wouldn't that

04:09:30.719 --> 04:09:32.579
put turtle's entire tribe in danger?

04:09:32.639 --> 04:09:35.280
So perhaps one of the other queens.

04:09:35.340 --> 04:09:39.299
Glacier, Ruby, Morhen, or Thorn.

04:09:39.899 --> 04:09:41.459
Would any of them listen to a sea wing?

04:09:41.520 --> 04:09:43.440
And wouldn't they fall under Dark

04:09:43.440 --> 04:09:45.180
Stalker's spell the moment they met him?

04:09:45.239 --> 04:09:48.299
Not to mention, in order to convince them

04:09:48.299 --> 04:09:50.579
his story was true, he'd have to tell

04:09:50.579 --> 04:09:51.420
them everything.

04:09:51.479 --> 04:09:53.940
As in, oh, yes.

04:09:54.000 --> 04:09:55.860
And I'm an animist.

04:09:55.920 --> 04:09:56.760
Everything.

04:09:56.819 --> 04:10:00.120
He shuddered, and his hold on the coral

04:10:00.120 --> 04:10:02.219
loosened, and it darted forward in a

04:10:02.219 --> 04:10:04.559
flash and bopped Queen Glory on the side

04:10:04.559 --> 04:10:05.040
of her tail.

04:10:05.100 --> 04:10:07.020
She turned to stare at him.

04:10:07.079 --> 04:10:08.159
What was that?

04:10:08.219 --> 04:10:09.780
Nothing?

04:10:09.840 --> 04:10:11.280
Nothing, he said.

04:10:11.340 --> 04:10:12.959
My talon slipped.

04:10:13.020 --> 04:10:13.260
Sorry.

04:10:13.319 --> 04:10:15.360
She raised one eyebrow.

04:10:15.420 --> 04:10:17.879
You're an odd dragon turtle.

04:10:17.940 --> 04:10:21.540
That's what my friends tell me, he said

04:10:21.540 --> 04:10:24.479
and his friends rose up in his mind, and

04:10:24.479 --> 04:10:26.760
a possibility shot through him, shining

04:10:26.760 --> 04:10:27.120
with hope.

04:10:27.180 --> 04:10:30.059
Your majesty. he said.

04:10:30.120 --> 04:10:33.180
May I ask, how is Kinkaju?

04:10:33.239 --> 04:10:36.239
I don't know, Glory said.

04:10:36.299 --> 04:10:37.799
Her wings drooping.

04:10:37.860 --> 04:10:40.559
The healers can't understand why she

04:10:40.559 --> 04:10:41.579
hasn't woken up yet.

04:10:41.639 --> 04:10:43.379
They don't know what to do for her.

04:10:43.440 --> 04:10:46.020
We all thought that once she was back in

04:10:46.020 --> 04:10:48.360
the rainforest, around the smells and

04:10:48.360 --> 04:10:50.520
sounds and some that she grew up with

04:10:50.520 --> 04:10:54.420
she'd, Back in the rainforest, Turtle

04:10:54.420 --> 04:10:55.920
interrupted, she's here.

04:10:55.979 --> 04:10:57.479
Of course.

04:10:57.540 --> 04:11:00.600
Queen Glory flicked her tail, knocking

04:11:00.600 --> 04:11:02.100
loose a shower of yellow blossoms.

04:11:02.219 --> 04:11:04.739
I wasn't going to leave her alone on the

04:11:04.739 --> 04:11:05.819
other side of the continent.

04:11:05.879 --> 04:11:08.219
The healers got back with her yesterday.

04:11:08.280 --> 04:11:09.959
Can I see her?

04:11:10.020 --> 04:11:11.159
Turtle asked.

04:11:11.280 --> 04:11:13.079
His claws were tingling.

04:11:13.139 --> 04:11:15.899
Kinkaju hadn't met Dark Stalker.

04:11:15.959 --> 04:11:17.340
Kinkaju would believe him.

04:11:17.399 --> 04:11:19.500
He could trust her with his secret.

04:11:19.559 --> 04:11:22.620
And Kinkajou was much more cut out for

04:11:22.620 --> 04:11:23.760
heroism than he was.

04:11:23.819 --> 04:11:26.879
Glory gave him directions to the healer's

04:11:26.879 --> 04:11:29.639
pavilion, not far away, tucked into a

04:11:29.639 --> 04:11:31.860
little alcove of the rainforest that

04:11:31.860 --> 04:11:33.600
seemed even more peaceful than the rest

04:11:33.600 --> 04:11:34.139
of the village.

04:11:34.200 --> 04:11:37.379
Turtle could smell healing herbs and

04:11:37.379 --> 04:11:39.059
oranges as he flew to the opening.

04:11:39.120 --> 04:11:42.840
Inside, sunlight poured through the rooms

04:11:42.840 --> 04:11:44.879
from skylights that had been opened in

04:11:44.879 --> 04:11:45.239
the roofs.

04:11:45.299 --> 04:11:48.479
A pair of pale blue heelers were asleep

04:11:48.479 --> 04:11:49.200
in one corner.

04:11:49.260 --> 04:11:51.840
Another was neatly folding cobwebs and

04:11:51.840 --> 04:11:54.299
moss into bundles on one of the shelves.

04:11:54.360 --> 04:11:56.940
She looked up as Turtle came in, but

04:11:56.940 --> 04:11:59.340
seemed only mildly surprised to see a sea

04:11:59.340 --> 04:12:00.299
wing in her pavilion.

04:12:00.360 --> 04:12:02.760
She swept one wing toward the bed where

04:12:02.760 --> 04:12:04.979
Kinkachu slept, and Turtle nodded

04:12:04.979 --> 04:12:07.020
unconsciously flashing his scales in

04:12:07.020 --> 04:12:07.620
aquatic.

04:12:07.680 --> 04:12:10.079
Yes, that's what I'm looking for.

04:12:10.139 --> 04:12:13.860
Kinkachu lay in a sunbeam that outlined

04:12:13.860 --> 04:12:14.940
every scale with gold.

04:12:15.059 --> 04:12:18.120
She was still as white as an ice wing.

04:12:18.239 --> 04:12:21.360
White being the color of pain or shock to

04:12:21.360 --> 04:12:22.079
the rain wings.

04:12:22.139 --> 04:12:25.139
But in this sun, it was the white of

04:12:25.139 --> 04:12:28.020
opals, jeweled and glinting with hints of

04:12:28.020 --> 04:12:30.959
hidden colors, pearl pinks, and sparks of

04:12:30.959 --> 04:12:31.200
green.

04:12:31.260 --> 04:12:34.200
It wasn't the color of her scales that

04:12:34.200 --> 04:12:36.540
made her look so unlike Kinkachu.

04:12:36.600 --> 04:12:38.159
It was her complete stillness.

04:12:38.219 --> 04:12:41.399
Turtle had never seen Kinkaju sit still

04:12:41.399 --> 04:12:41.819
for a moment.

04:12:41.879 --> 04:12:43.620
Even in class.

04:12:43.680 --> 04:12:46.379
Her wings always twitched, or her claws

04:12:46.379 --> 04:12:48.959
fidgeted, or her face would make sideways

04:12:48.959 --> 04:12:50.579
expressions at him or moon.

04:12:50.639 --> 04:12:52.379
What did he say?

04:12:52.440 --> 04:12:53.639
I knew that answer.

04:12:53.700 --> 04:12:55.739
Is it time to eat yet?

04:12:55.799 --> 04:12:56.399
Are you starving?

04:12:56.459 --> 04:12:57.180
I'm starving.

04:12:57.239 --> 04:12:58.920
Isn't school amazing?

04:12:59.040 --> 04:13:02.340
Turtle sat down beside her bed and curled

04:13:02.340 --> 04:13:03.000
his tail in.

04:13:03.059 --> 04:13:05.399
Missing her in a way that filled him with

04:13:05.399 --> 04:13:07.440
heavy seaweed from nose to tail.

04:13:07.500 --> 04:13:09.360
He knew this was ridiculous.

04:13:09.420 --> 04:13:11.399
He didn't even know her that well.

04:13:11.459 --> 04:13:14.399
They'd had barely 4 days at Jade Mountain

04:13:14.399 --> 04:13:15.420
before everything went wrong.

04:13:15.540 --> 04:13:18.540
Before Kinkaju left to find Winter's

04:13:18.540 --> 04:13:21.059
brother, defeat Scarlet, and save the

04:13:21.059 --> 04:13:22.739
world from Moon's prophecy.

04:13:22.799 --> 04:13:25.440
While Turtle chose to slink back to the

04:13:25.440 --> 04:13:26.760
safety of the school instead.

04:13:26.819 --> 04:13:29.639
That was exactly why he needed her.

04:13:29.700 --> 04:13:32.340
Kinkaju, he whispered.

04:13:32.399 --> 04:13:33.360
Can you hear me?

04:13:33.420 --> 04:13:34.979
I need you to wake up.

04:13:35.040 --> 04:13:37.200
Knowing Kinkaju.

04:13:37.319 --> 04:13:39.059
He have expected her to open her eyes and

04:13:39.059 --> 04:13:39.360
joke.

04:13:39.420 --> 04:13:43.020
Oh, well, if you need me to, then sure.

04:13:43.079 --> 04:13:45.659
I was just taking a really long nap, but

04:13:45.659 --> 04:13:46.739
let's go fight some bad guys.

04:13:46.799 --> 04:13:48.780
She didn't though.

04:13:48.840 --> 04:13:51.540
He'd already tried this, back in

04:13:51.540 --> 04:13:53.940
possibility, but now he fumbled his

04:13:53.940 --> 04:13:55.559
healing river stone out of his pouch

04:13:55.559 --> 04:13:55.979
again.

04:13:56.040 --> 04:13:59.100
His stupid, short-sighted enchantment

04:13:59.100 --> 04:14:01.260
that only healed surface wounds.

04:14:01.319 --> 04:14:04.079
Still, he brushed it lightly along

04:14:04.079 --> 04:14:06.899
Kinkajoo's bruised spine over the

04:14:06.899 --> 04:14:09.299
bandages on her broken ribs and gently

04:14:09.299 --> 04:14:10.799
around her fractured skull.

04:14:10.860 --> 04:14:13.020
Impossibility.

04:14:13.139 --> 04:14:15.780
They'd watched the bruises fade, and all

04:14:15.780 --> 04:14:18.479
the scrapes and cuts disappear, but it

04:14:18.479 --> 04:14:20.940
didn't work any deeper, and Kinkaju did

04:14:20.940 --> 04:14:21.299
not wake up.

04:14:21.360 --> 04:14:24.059
This time wasn't any different.

04:14:24.120 --> 04:14:27.420
Kinkaju still lay quietly, quietly

04:14:27.420 --> 04:14:29.340
breathing, eyes closed.

04:14:29.399 --> 04:14:32.219
Turtle had wanted to enchant something

04:14:32.219 --> 04:14:34.559
right then that could wake her, but he

04:14:34.559 --> 04:14:35.940
was afraid that one of the possibility

04:14:35.940 --> 04:14:38.879
doctors would notice, and Moon had been

04:14:38.879 --> 04:14:39.659
worried for his soul.

04:14:39.780 --> 04:14:43.260
She'd suggested waiting 2 more days, at

04:14:43.260 --> 04:14:45.239
least, to see if Kinkaju woke up on her

04:14:45.239 --> 04:14:45.479
own.

04:14:45.540 --> 04:14:48.360
But then they'd flown off to find peril

04:14:48.360 --> 04:14:51.000
which had led them to the scroll, and

04:14:51.000 --> 04:14:53.280
then the release of Dark Stalker, and now

04:14:53.280 --> 04:14:53.760
here they were.

04:14:53.819 --> 04:14:56.520
And now he couldn't use magic to help

04:14:56.520 --> 04:14:56.700
her.

04:14:56.760 --> 04:14:59.940
He crushed a bright orange flower between

04:14:59.940 --> 04:15:02.219
his claws, frustrated.

04:15:02.280 --> 04:15:04.680
If only he'd been brave and stubborn

04:15:04.680 --> 04:15:06.299
enough to heal her earlier.

04:15:06.360 --> 04:15:09.180
But then, she would have meant dark

04:15:09.180 --> 04:15:11.100
stalker, along with everyone else.

04:15:11.159 --> 04:15:13.319
She'd be under his spell too.

04:15:13.379 --> 04:15:16.920
Kinkaju, he said sternly.

04:15:16.979 --> 04:15:18.360
Enough sleeping.

04:15:18.420 --> 04:15:20.040
Time to get up and save the world.

04:15:20.159 --> 04:15:22.319
No reaction.

04:15:22.379 --> 04:15:25.799
You know you've always wanted to. he

04:15:25.799 --> 04:15:26.280
wheedled.

04:15:26.399 --> 04:15:29.399
Think how impressed Queen Glory will be.

04:15:29.520 --> 04:15:32.399
All you have to do is wake up and figure

04:15:32.399 --> 04:15:34.500
out how to stop the most powerful dragon

04:15:34.500 --> 04:15:35.819
in the history of Pyria.

04:15:35.879 --> 04:15:37.379
No problem, right?

04:15:37.440 --> 04:15:40.260
No reaction from Kinkaju.

04:15:40.319 --> 04:15:42.420
But he got a very odd look from the

04:15:42.420 --> 04:15:44.219
healer at the other end of the pavilion.

04:15:44.219 --> 04:15:48.180
All right, he couldn't talk her awake, and

04:15:48.180 --> 04:15:49.260
he couldn't use his magic.

04:15:49.319 --> 04:15:50.879
Wait.

04:15:50.940 --> 04:15:54.299
He couldn't use his magic.

04:15:54.360 --> 04:15:57.959
Turtle thought for a long time, his brow

04:15:57.959 --> 04:16:00.059
froed into serious wrinkles.

04:16:00.120 --> 04:16:02.280
Five iridescent purple butterflies

04:16:02.280 --> 04:16:05.159
settled on his tail, and fluttered serene

04:16:05.159 --> 04:16:07.319
butterfly thoughts at one another without

04:16:07.319 --> 04:16:08.760
him even noticing they were there.

04:16:08.819 --> 04:16:12.360
Finally, turtle blinked and sat up

04:16:12.360 --> 04:16:14.520
scattering indigo wings in all

04:16:14.520 --> 04:16:15.420
directions.

04:16:15.479 --> 04:16:16.319
He had a plan.

04:16:16.379 --> 04:16:19.680
Possibly a terrible plan, but the only

04:16:19.680 --> 04:16:20.399
one he could think of.

04:16:20.459 --> 04:16:23.459
He flew out of the pavilion and used his

04:16:23.459 --> 04:16:25.979
coral again to navigate the rainforest

04:16:25.979 --> 04:16:28.020
and find his way back to anemone.

04:16:28.079 --> 04:16:30.899
The sea wing princess was swimming in a

04:16:30.899 --> 04:16:33.059
pool several lengths upstream from dark

04:16:33.059 --> 04:16:34.079
stalkers gathering.

04:16:34.079 --> 04:16:36.959
Her pale shape flickered like a dolphin

04:16:36.959 --> 04:16:39.059
below the water, in and out of the

04:16:39.059 --> 04:16:39.479
shadows.

04:16:39.540 --> 04:16:42.420
Turtle landed with a squelch in the mud

04:16:42.420 --> 04:16:45.420
let the coolness sink into his claws, and

04:16:45.420 --> 04:16:46.440
waited for her to surface.

04:16:46.500 --> 04:16:50.219
Oh, hi, she said cheerfully. when she

04:16:50.219 --> 04:16:50.879
finally saw him.

04:16:50.940 --> 04:16:52.739
I was wondering where you went.

04:16:52.799 --> 04:16:55.979
Dog soccer's stories are great, but I'm

04:16:55.979 --> 04:16:57.959
kind of not so interested in ancient

04:16:57.959 --> 04:16:59.040
nightwing history.

04:16:59.159 --> 04:17:02.459
Blah, blah, 8000000 years ago, they had a

04:17:02.459 --> 04:17:04.500
cool library, yawn.

04:17:04.559 --> 04:17:07.680
I was like, so what were the sea wings up

04:17:07.680 --> 04:17:08.280
to back then?

04:17:08.340 --> 04:17:11.040
And he was all getting massacred.

04:17:11.100 --> 04:17:13.379
So that was cheerful.

04:17:13.440 --> 04:17:16.020
I would say come on in, but I should warn

04:17:16.020 --> 04:17:18.000
you, there are all kinds of weird sticky

04:17:18.000 --> 04:17:19.139
plants under the surface here.

04:17:19.200 --> 04:17:22.500
Thanks anyway, Turtle said.

04:17:22.620 --> 04:17:26.280
Hey, anemone, is it true you can do as

04:17:26.280 --> 04:17:27.479
many spells as you want now?

04:17:27.540 --> 04:17:29.219
Yep.

04:17:29.280 --> 04:17:32.219
His sister ducked under the water and

04:17:32.219 --> 04:17:34.379
surfaced again, shooting a spray of water

04:17:34.379 --> 04:17:36.120
at a grumpy looking frog on the

04:17:36.120 --> 04:17:36.479
riverbank.

04:17:36.540 --> 04:17:39.479
Thanks to my cool enchanted silver

04:17:39.479 --> 04:17:40.139
necklace.

04:17:40.200 --> 04:17:42.540
She tapped the collar with one claw.

04:17:42.659 --> 04:17:45.360
I'm going to cast so many spells.

04:17:45.420 --> 04:17:47.879
It'll be like the sea is full of magic.

04:17:47.940 --> 04:17:51.120
I could rebuild the Summer Palace, or

04:17:51.120 --> 04:17:52.440
make us a new palace, maybe.

04:17:52.559 --> 04:17:55.440
I can stop hurricanes.

04:17:55.500 --> 04:17:58.739
I could make Uncle Sharks scales, turn

04:17:58.739 --> 04:18:00.780
bright pink, and all his teeth fall out.

04:18:00.840 --> 04:18:01.920
Ah.

04:18:01.979 --> 04:18:04.500
I can enchant every pearl in the ocean to

04:18:04.500 --> 04:18:06.360
come rolling up to our door.

04:18:06.479 --> 04:18:11.520
Oh, Turtle said, bewildered by this rush

04:18:11.520 --> 04:18:12.059
of ideas.

04:18:12.120 --> 04:18:15.659
But the pearl divers like their jobs.

04:18:15.719 --> 04:18:20.040
It's just an example, turtle, Anemone

04:18:20.040 --> 04:18:21.000
said scornfully.

04:18:21.059 --> 04:18:23.819
And just saying, when we get home, things

04:18:23.819 --> 04:18:25.620
are going to be pretty different in the

04:18:25.620 --> 04:18:26.399
kingdom of the sea.

04:18:26.520 --> 04:18:28.559
You're not.

04:18:28.620 --> 04:18:30.600
You're not going to try to take the

04:18:30.600 --> 04:18:31.440
throne, are you?

04:18:31.500 --> 04:18:33.239
Turtle asked.

04:18:33.299 --> 04:18:35.219
He hadn't quite thought ahead to what

04:18:35.219 --> 04:18:35.819
might happen.

04:18:35.879 --> 04:18:38.100
If Anemone decided to use her magic

04:18:38.100 --> 04:18:39.840
against their mother in a challenge

04:18:39.840 --> 04:18:40.319
duel.

04:18:40.440 --> 04:18:43.620
It didn't seem fair, although Queen Coral

04:18:43.620 --> 04:18:45.959
had somehow defeated Orca, who had turned

04:18:45.959 --> 04:18:48.120
out to be an animus too, but a secret

04:18:48.120 --> 04:18:49.020
one.

04:18:49.079 --> 04:18:49.860
Like me.

04:18:49.920 --> 04:18:52.319
Not yet.

04:18:52.379 --> 04:18:54.120
Anemone said with a laugh.

04:18:54.180 --> 04:18:56.459
I want to have a lot more fun before I

04:18:56.459 --> 04:18:58.799
get stuck in a boring old palace, making

04:18:58.799 --> 04:18:59.819
decisions all day.

04:18:59.879 --> 04:19:02.100
And I want to learn everything dark

04:19:02.100 --> 04:19:03.840
stalker can teach me about being an

04:19:03.840 --> 04:19:04.500
animist.

04:19:04.559 --> 04:19:05.639
Isn't he cool?

04:19:05.700 --> 04:19:08.100
Don't you feel like an idiot for being so

04:19:08.100 --> 04:19:08.520
worried?

04:19:08.579 --> 04:19:10.500
Right.

04:19:10.620 --> 04:19:14.219
Turtle glance downstream, realizing that

04:19:14.219 --> 04:19:15.899
Dark Stalker might come looking for

04:19:15.899 --> 04:19:16.920
anemone any moment now.

04:19:16.979 --> 04:19:20.760
So, since you're so super powerful now

04:19:20.760 --> 04:19:22.799
could you do something for me?

04:19:22.799 --> 04:19:26.459
An irritated look briefly flitted across

04:19:26.459 --> 04:19:29.700
anemones face, and Turtle winced, knowing

04:19:29.700 --> 04:19:31.020
exactly how she felt.

04:19:31.020 --> 04:19:33.719
Other dragons wanting to use your magic

04:19:33.719 --> 04:19:35.940
it was like they were asking to wear your

04:19:35.940 --> 04:19:36.420
scales.

04:19:36.479 --> 04:19:38.280
Like what?

04:19:38.340 --> 04:19:39.659
Anemone asked.

04:19:39.719 --> 04:19:42.840
It's Kinkaju, Turtle said.

04:19:42.899 --> 04:19:45.840
I wouldn't ask for me, but she's really

04:19:45.840 --> 04:19:48.600
hurt. and she won't wake up, and I'm

04:19:48.600 --> 04:19:50.280
afraid only magic can save her.

04:19:50.459 --> 04:19:52.979
Oh, Anemone said.

04:19:53.040 --> 04:19:55.680
Her frown clearing like the tide pulling

04:19:55.680 --> 04:19:56.459
away from the beach.

04:19:56.520 --> 04:19:58.079
Aww.

04:19:58.139 --> 04:20:00.059
You want me to save the cute little rain

04:20:00.059 --> 04:20:01.200
wing you're in love with?

04:20:01.319 --> 04:20:04.500
I'm not in love with her, Turtle

04:20:04.500 --> 04:20:07.680
protested, but she's, you know, she's

04:20:07.680 --> 04:20:07.979
awesome.

04:20:08.040 --> 04:20:09.899
And I just wanted to get better.

04:20:09.959 --> 04:20:12.479
I can totally do that.

04:20:12.540 --> 04:20:15.659
Anemone said gleefully, splashing it out

04:20:15.659 --> 04:20:16.559
of the pool toward him.

04:20:16.620 --> 04:20:18.780
He bopped her lightly with a wriggling

04:20:18.780 --> 04:20:20.700
coral as she went by, but she didn't

04:20:20.700 --> 04:20:21.180
notice.

04:20:21.239 --> 04:20:23.879
But I am going to tease you about it

04:20:23.879 --> 04:20:24.540
forever.

04:20:24.600 --> 04:20:26.760
You think she's cute.

04:20:26.819 --> 04:20:29.459
You totally love her.

04:20:29.520 --> 04:20:31.379
Anemone.

04:20:31.440 --> 04:20:34.139
Turtle swatted at her with his tail, and

04:20:34.139 --> 04:20:35.760
she danced away, giggling.

04:20:35.819 --> 04:20:39.120
In the palace, Anemone had been a distant

04:20:39.120 --> 04:20:42.000
figure. always attached to the queen by a

04:20:42.000 --> 04:20:42.420
harness.

04:20:42.479 --> 04:20:45.420
She was never allowed to wander freely, or

04:20:45.420 --> 04:20:47.040
associate with her rough and tumble

04:20:47.040 --> 04:20:48.059
brothers.

04:20:48.120 --> 04:20:50.040
Turtle had only known her as the beloved

04:20:50.040 --> 04:20:52.139
princess, who got all their mother's

04:20:52.139 --> 04:20:52.379
love.

04:20:52.440 --> 04:20:55.500
He'd seen her at royal gatherings, or at

04:20:55.500 --> 04:20:57.959
Queen Coral's scroll readings, sitting

04:20:57.959 --> 04:21:00.420
quietly beside her, soaking up all that

04:21:00.420 --> 04:21:00.899
attention.

04:21:00.959 --> 04:21:03.840
But then tsunami came and caught the

04:21:03.840 --> 04:21:06.059
assassin, and a new princess finally

04:21:06.059 --> 04:21:08.700
hatched, an anemone was released from the

04:21:08.700 --> 04:21:09.479
harness at last.

04:21:09.540 --> 04:21:12.120
She began visiting her brothers out of

04:21:12.120 --> 04:21:15.000
curiosity, and Turtle watched her closely

04:21:15.000 --> 04:21:17.040
wondering what her life was like as a

04:21:17.040 --> 04:21:17.940
known animus.

04:21:18.000 --> 04:21:20.700
She seemed funny and happy much of the

04:21:20.700 --> 04:21:23.280
time, but there was a dark streak to some

04:21:23.280 --> 04:21:25.799
of her jokes, along with an imperious

04:21:25.799 --> 04:21:28.079
certainty that she deserved all of her

04:21:28.079 --> 04:21:29.340
princess privileges.

04:21:29.399 --> 04:21:32.340
It worried him, and it worried him more

04:21:32.340 --> 04:21:33.719
the more he found he liked her.

04:21:33.719 --> 04:21:37.020
All right, take me into your sleeping

04:21:37.020 --> 04:21:37.559
beauty.

04:21:37.620 --> 04:21:39.540
Anemone said dramatically.

04:21:39.600 --> 04:21:43.500
Oh, brother, Turtle said, rolling his

04:21:43.500 --> 04:21:43.739
eyes.

04:21:43.799 --> 04:21:46.319
He tucked the coral back into its pouch

04:21:46.319 --> 04:21:49.260
and lifted off into the trees, anemone

04:21:49.260 --> 04:21:51.899
followed him, singing, Turlin Kinkaju

04:21:51.899 --> 04:21:55.799
flying in the sky, getting all K-I-S-S

04:21:54.059 --> 04:21:55.799
Y.

04:21:55.860 --> 04:21:59.040
He clapped his talons over his ears and

04:21:59.040 --> 04:22:00.840
kept them there the rest of the way to

04:22:00.840 --> 04:22:01.739
the rain wing village.

04:22:01.799 --> 04:22:05.579
Anemone fell silent as they crossed the

04:22:05.579 --> 04:22:07.620
threshold into the healer's pavilion.

04:22:07.680 --> 04:22:10.920
She gazed around at the other patients, a

04:22:10.920 --> 04:22:13.139
rain wing with a head wound, and a night

04:22:13.139 --> 04:22:14.879
wing with a jagged tear in one of his

04:22:14.879 --> 04:22:15.120
wings.

04:22:15.239 --> 04:22:18.120
Both of them were unconscious, probably

04:22:18.120 --> 04:22:19.079
tranquilized.

04:22:19.139 --> 04:22:21.540
Turtle wondered if their injuries made

04:22:21.540 --> 04:22:23.520
anemone think of all the wounded sea

04:22:23.520 --> 04:22:26.280
wings, who'd survived the war and the

04:22:26.280 --> 04:22:27.899
bombing of the summer palace.

04:22:27.959 --> 04:22:30.780
Maybe instead of collecting pearls, and

04:22:30.780 --> 04:22:32.639
turning their unfriendly uncle's shades

04:22:32.639 --> 04:22:34.680
of fuchsia, Anemone might think about

04:22:34.680 --> 04:22:36.420
healing some of her fellow dragons

04:22:36.420 --> 04:22:36.959
instead.

04:22:37.020 --> 04:22:39.659
Not that I'm one to judge.

04:22:39.719 --> 04:22:42.059
How many dragons have I ever helped with

04:22:42.059 --> 04:22:42.600
my magic?

04:22:42.659 --> 04:22:46.079
Turtles stopped next to Kinkaju.

04:22:46.139 --> 04:22:48.120
An anemone went around her other side

04:22:48.120 --> 04:22:50.700
studying the pale little rain wing.

04:22:51.000 --> 04:22:53.700
Kinkachoo was older than anemone, but

04:22:53.700 --> 04:22:55.079
they were not very different in size.

04:22:55.139 --> 04:22:58.020
Anemone lifted one of Kinkaju's drooping

04:22:58.020 --> 04:22:58.620
talons.

04:22:58.680 --> 04:23:01.260
Wow, she said softly.

04:23:01.319 --> 04:23:03.059
She does look terrible.

04:23:03.120 --> 04:23:05.340
I'm sorry for teasing you, turtle.

04:23:05.399 --> 04:23:08.520
Oh, good, he said.

04:23:08.579 --> 04:23:10.979
I mean, I'm going to keep doing it, she

04:23:10.979 --> 04:23:12.780
added, but not until she's well again.

04:23:12.840 --> 04:23:15.360
Okay, let me think for a minute.

04:23:15.420 --> 04:23:18.120
Anemone scrunged up her snout.

04:23:18.180 --> 04:23:19.139
Oops.

04:23:19.260 --> 04:23:21.780
I'm supposed to tell dark stalker if I

04:23:21.780 --> 04:23:22.920
decided to do any more spells.

04:23:22.979 --> 04:23:24.959
He doesn't really want me trying new

04:23:24.959 --> 04:23:25.799
things on my own yet.

04:23:25.860 --> 04:23:27.840
Seriously?

04:23:27.840 --> 04:23:28.860
said Turtle.

04:23:28.920 --> 04:23:31.440
Haven't you been doing spells on your own

04:23:31.440 --> 04:23:33.000
pretty much your whole life?

04:23:33.059 --> 04:23:36.540
That's true, said anemone.

04:23:36.600 --> 04:23:39.360
And I mean, what does he care if I heal

04:23:39.360 --> 04:23:40.979
some random rain wing, right?

04:23:41.100 --> 04:23:44.040
Exactly, said Turtle.

04:23:44.100 --> 04:23:45.360
He held his breath.

04:23:45.420 --> 04:23:47.940
I'll tell him about it when we get back

04:23:47.940 --> 04:23:50.639
Anemone said, flicking one of her wings

04:23:50.639 --> 04:23:53.280
and startling a cluster of dragonflies in

04:23:53.280 --> 04:23:54.000
the leaf roof.

04:23:54.059 --> 04:23:56.520
What are you going to enchant?

04:23:56.639 --> 04:23:59.340
Turtle asked, exhaling with relief.

04:23:59.399 --> 04:24:02.579
Anemone glanced around dubiously at the

04:24:02.579 --> 04:24:03.659
flowery vines.

04:24:03.719 --> 04:24:06.719
The leaves, the wooden bowls of herbs, all

04:24:06.719 --> 04:24:08.940
the biodegradable rainforest things that

04:24:08.940 --> 04:24:09.840
wouldn't last very long.

04:24:09.899 --> 04:24:12.840
Her eyes fell on the black leather pouch

04:24:12.840 --> 04:24:14.520
that was tied to Kinkaju's ankle.

04:24:14.579 --> 04:24:16.559
Maybe something in here?

04:24:16.559 --> 04:24:18.780
she said, poking it open.

04:24:18.840 --> 04:24:20.040
Wait.

04:24:20.100 --> 04:24:22.620
Turtle started to say, but already

04:24:22.620 --> 04:24:25.559
Kinkachu's library card was tumbling into

04:24:25.559 --> 04:24:28.139
Anemone's palm, along with one of the

04:24:28.139 --> 04:24:31.260
Skyfire rocks from Turtle's armband, a

04:24:31.260 --> 04:24:34.260
gift to protect her thoughts from Moon, or

04:24:34.260 --> 04:24:36.659
any mind reader, although Anemone had no

04:24:36.659 --> 04:24:37.200
way of knowing that.

04:24:37.260 --> 04:24:39.780
His sister peered at the rock for a

04:24:39.780 --> 04:24:41.819
moment, then looked up at him with wide

04:24:41.819 --> 04:24:44.340
eyes, apparently noticing the holes in

04:24:44.340 --> 04:24:45.959
his armband for the 1st time.

04:24:47.219 --> 04:24:48.959
You gave her one of your rocks from the

04:24:48.959 --> 04:24:49.260
sky.

04:24:49.319 --> 04:24:50.760
She crowed.

04:24:50.819 --> 04:24:52.739
You love her so much.

04:24:52.799 --> 04:24:56.579
Can we please get on with this, he

04:24:56.579 --> 04:24:57.000
demanded.

04:24:57.059 --> 04:24:59.280
It was going to be a hilarious day

04:24:59.280 --> 04:25:01.799
whenever she discovered that he'd also

04:25:01.799 --> 04:25:03.479
given matching rocks to Winter and

04:25:03.479 --> 04:25:04.139
Kibley.

04:25:04.200 --> 04:25:07.680
Well, this should work, she said.

04:25:07.739 --> 04:25:09.719
Curling her claws around the star

04:25:09.719 --> 04:25:11.879
speckled rock, she closed her eyes.

04:25:11.940 --> 04:25:14.040
This is it, turtle.

04:25:14.100 --> 04:25:15.239
One chance.

04:25:15.299 --> 04:25:17.459
Perfect timing, right?

04:25:17.520 --> 04:25:18.659
Now.

04:25:18.719 --> 04:25:22.379
I enchant this rock to heal Kinkaju of

04:25:22.379 --> 04:25:24.959
all her injuries, so she can wake up, as

04:25:24.959 --> 04:25:27.659
happy and healthy as she's ever been, said

04:25:27.659 --> 04:25:28.379
Anemone.

04:25:28.440 --> 04:25:31.680
And at the same moment, Turtle thought

04:25:31.680 --> 04:25:34.739
with all his might, Enchant this Skyfire

04:25:34.739 --> 04:25:38.280
to make Kinkaju immune to any spell, Dark

04:25:38.280 --> 04:25:41.579
Stalker has ever or will ever cast, and

04:25:41.579 --> 04:25:43.260
enchant it, to make her completely

04:25:43.260 --> 04:25:46.139
insignificant in his eyes, not worth

04:25:46.139 --> 04:25:46.920
thinking about.

04:25:47.040 --> 04:25:50.100
Not visible in his futures, not in any

04:25:50.100 --> 04:25:51.600
way a threat to him.

04:25:51.659 --> 04:25:54.899
He wasn't sure how many times over you

04:25:54.899 --> 04:25:57.719
could enchant an object, or if one animus

04:25:57.719 --> 04:25:59.219
touch might cancel out another.

04:25:59.280 --> 04:26:02.399
So he added hurriedly, and enchanted to

04:26:02.399 --> 04:26:03.600
heal all her injuries as well.

04:26:03.659 --> 04:26:05.760
This was the key.

04:26:05.819 --> 04:26:08.459
Casting his spell in the same moment as

04:26:08.459 --> 04:26:09.180
anemones.

04:26:09.239 --> 04:26:11.399
He didn't know the details of Dark

04:26:11.399 --> 04:26:13.920
Stalker's warning system, but he hoped

04:26:13.920 --> 04:26:15.840
one spell would obscure the other, like

04:26:15.840 --> 04:26:16.620
Kibley thought.

04:26:16.680 --> 04:26:19.260
He'd considered the phrasing of his spell

04:26:19.260 --> 04:26:21.540
as carefully as he could, borrowing

04:26:21.540 --> 04:26:23.340
Kibley's words and adding more of his

04:26:23.340 --> 04:26:23.579
own.

04:26:23.639 --> 04:26:26.159
He hoped Dark Stalker would forgive

04:26:26.159 --> 04:26:27.899
Anemone for using her spell to help

04:26:27.899 --> 04:26:28.739
Kinkaju.

04:26:28.799 --> 04:26:31.260
That was why he couldn't hide Kinkachu

04:26:31.260 --> 04:26:32.459
the way he'd hidden himself.

04:26:32.520 --> 04:26:35.520
And he hoped Dark Stalker wouldn't think

04:26:35.520 --> 04:26:37.500
too hard about what else might have

04:26:37.500 --> 04:26:37.860
happened here.

04:26:37.920 --> 04:26:41.760
Anemone opened her eyes and gave Turtle a

04:26:41.760 --> 04:26:42.360
sly smile.

04:26:42.420 --> 04:26:46.319
And while we're at it, she said, her

04:26:46.319 --> 04:26:47.040
voice playful.

04:26:47.100 --> 04:26:50.040
I also enchant this rock to make kinkajoo

04:26:50.040 --> 04:26:52.260
love turtle just as much as he loves

04:26:52.260 --> 04:26:52.500
her.

04:26:52.559 --> 04:26:57.120
Chapter 14.

04:26:57.360 --> 04:26:59.940
What?

04:27:00.000 --> 04:27:02.700
Turtle cried, horror struck.

04:27:02.760 --> 04:27:03.840
Anemone?

04:27:03.899 --> 04:27:04.739
You can't do that.

04:27:04.799 --> 04:27:08.639
I so absolutely can. she said

04:27:08.639 --> 04:27:11.340
triumphantly, already sliding the Skyfire

04:27:11.340 --> 04:27:12.780
back into Kinkaju's pouch.

04:27:12.840 --> 04:27:14.579
My magic can do anything.

04:27:14.639 --> 04:27:16.680
But that's awful.

04:27:16.739 --> 04:27:19.799
You can't enchant someone's feelings

04:27:19.799 --> 04:27:22.079
Anemone, please take that spell off.

04:27:22.200 --> 04:27:25.920
I don't think I can, Anemone said with a

04:27:25.920 --> 04:27:26.340
shrug.

04:27:26.399 --> 04:27:29.219
Squids and sea monsters, you should be

04:27:29.219 --> 04:27:29.879
thanking me.

04:27:29.940 --> 04:27:32.459
I just did such an awesome, nice thing

04:27:32.459 --> 04:27:32.819
for you.

04:27:32.940 --> 04:27:36.120
She reached over Kinkaju and patted one

04:27:36.120 --> 04:27:37.680
of his talons, grinning.

04:27:37.739 --> 04:27:40.020
I'm the best sister ever.

04:27:40.079 --> 04:27:43.020
But I don't want her to like me because

04:27:43.020 --> 04:27:43.620
of a spell.

04:27:43.680 --> 04:27:46.799
Turtle felt as if he was caught in one of

04:27:46.799 --> 04:27:49.559
the rainforest's enormous spider laden

04:27:49.559 --> 04:27:50.459
cobwebs.

04:27:50.520 --> 04:27:52.620
He couldn't undo the enchantment himself

04:27:52.620 --> 04:27:55.739
if that was even possible, or else Dark

04:27:55.739 --> 04:27:56.639
Stalker would notice.

04:27:56.700 --> 04:27:58.860
But he couldn't take the Skyfire away

04:27:58.860 --> 04:28:00.000
from Kinkaju either.

04:28:00.059 --> 04:28:02.399
She needed it to be safe from Dark

04:28:02.399 --> 04:28:02.879
Stalker.

04:28:02.940 --> 04:28:05.100
You'll thank me later.

04:28:05.159 --> 04:28:07.260
Anemone said confidently.

04:28:07.319 --> 04:28:11.100
When you're married and have lots of

04:28:11.100 --> 04:28:13.020
little pink dragonettes with webbed

04:28:13.020 --> 04:28:13.739
talons.

04:28:13.860 --> 04:28:17.399
Turtle buried his face and his claws, poor

04:28:17.399 --> 04:28:18.239
kinkaju.

04:28:18.299 --> 04:28:21.600
This was so wrong, so wrong.

04:28:21.659 --> 04:28:24.059
Who's getting married?

04:28:24.180 --> 04:28:26.520
said a soft, hoarse voice.

04:28:26.579 --> 04:28:30.659
He looked up and saw colors rising slowly

04:28:30.659 --> 04:28:33.299
into the scales, all across Kinkaju's

04:28:33.299 --> 04:28:35.340
back, like the time he'd spilled 5

04:28:35.340 --> 04:28:37.079
different ink bottles over his blank

04:28:37.079 --> 04:28:39.479
scroll, back when he still dreamed of

04:28:39.479 --> 04:28:42.719
being a rider, sunrises drifted into her

04:28:42.719 --> 04:28:45.659
wings, pale peaches, and yellows

04:28:45.659 --> 04:28:47.760
strengthening into glorious bands of

04:28:47.760 --> 04:28:48.659
orange and gold.

04:28:48.780 --> 04:28:52.260
Her green eyes were open, and her head

04:28:52.260 --> 04:28:54.120
was turned, pillowed on her arms.

04:28:54.180 --> 04:28:55.860
She was looking at him.

04:28:55.920 --> 04:28:59.340
Hey, turtle, she said sleepily.

04:28:59.399 --> 04:29:02.340
We missed you on our heroic quest.

04:29:02.399 --> 04:29:07.260
I missed you too, he said, a lump rising

04:29:07.260 --> 04:29:07.680
in his throat.

04:29:07.739 --> 04:29:12.180
At least, I think it was a heroic quest

04:29:12.180 --> 04:29:12.959
she said.

04:29:13.020 --> 04:29:15.719
I'm a little bit fuzzy on whether we

04:29:15.719 --> 04:29:17.040
actually succeeded.

04:29:17.159 --> 04:29:20.040
You did, he said.

04:29:20.100 --> 04:29:22.620
You saved Winter's brother, and stopped

04:29:22.620 --> 04:29:23.459
Queen Scarlet.

04:29:23.579 --> 04:29:25.079
I did?

04:29:25.139 --> 04:29:26.219
she said.

04:29:26.219 --> 04:29:27.239
Really?

04:29:27.299 --> 04:29:28.680
Like how?

04:29:28.739 --> 04:29:30.000
In my sleep?

04:29:30.059 --> 04:29:33.719
Am I so amazing that I can save the world

04:29:33.719 --> 04:29:35.159
and nap at the same time?

04:29:35.280 --> 04:29:38.700
She laughed, and her gaze drifted up to

04:29:38.700 --> 04:29:39.120
the ceiling.

04:29:39.180 --> 04:29:41.280
She sat up, startled.

04:29:41.340 --> 04:29:42.659
Whoa.

04:29:42.719 --> 04:29:44.940
This place looks exactly like the

04:29:44.940 --> 04:29:45.780
rainforest.

04:29:45.899 --> 04:29:48.959
It is the rainforest, Turtle said.

04:29:49.020 --> 04:29:49.920
You're home.

04:29:49.979 --> 04:29:52.799
There's a lot to explain.

04:29:52.920 --> 04:29:56.579
Hi, Anemone said.

04:29:56.639 --> 04:29:58.260
Elbowing turtle out of the way.

04:29:58.319 --> 04:30:00.120
I'm Princess Anemone.

04:30:00.180 --> 04:30:01.739
I don't think we officially met at

04:30:01.739 --> 04:30:02.100
school.

04:30:02.159 --> 04:30:04.440
I'm the one who totally just saved your

04:30:04.440 --> 04:30:04.860
life.

04:30:04.920 --> 04:30:07.440
She fluffed her wings and stretched her

04:30:07.440 --> 04:30:08.159
neck a little longer.

04:30:08.219 --> 04:30:10.079
Oh, wow.

04:30:10.139 --> 04:30:11.219
Thank you.

04:30:11.280 --> 04:30:13.200
Kinkaju said earnestly.

04:30:13.260 --> 04:30:15.719
Um, saved my life from what?

04:30:15.840 --> 04:30:19.559
You got clobbered by a bad guy, Anemone

04:30:19.559 --> 04:30:20.219
said.

04:30:20.280 --> 04:30:23.040
You've been unconscious for like days.

04:30:23.159 --> 04:30:25.379
You might never have woken up except that

04:30:25.379 --> 04:30:26.940
Turtle begged me to heal you.

04:30:27.000 --> 04:30:30.120
She poked Turtles backside meaningfully

04:30:30.120 --> 04:30:30.659
with her tail.

04:30:30.780 --> 04:30:32.940
What bad guy?

04:30:33.000 --> 04:30:34.379
Kinkachu cried.

04:30:34.440 --> 04:30:35.879
Did we clobber her back?

04:30:35.940 --> 04:30:37.139
Three moons?

04:30:37.200 --> 04:30:39.420
Did I miss all the excitement again?

04:30:39.479 --> 04:30:42.360
She flared her wings, then did a double

04:30:42.360 --> 04:30:43.799
take at one of them and jumped.

04:30:43.860 --> 04:30:47.459
Hey, my venom splash scars are gone.

04:30:47.520 --> 04:30:50.520
Total, remember, the triangle of black

04:30:50.520 --> 04:30:53.100
spots that had dotted Kinkaju's wing.

04:30:53.159 --> 04:30:55.500
He shifted uncomfortably on its talons.

04:30:55.559 --> 04:30:59.219
I guess Anemone's spell healed those

04:30:59.219 --> 04:31:01.559
along with your other injuries, he said.

04:31:01.620 --> 04:31:03.239
Spell?

04:31:03.299 --> 04:31:04.680
Kinkaju yelped.

04:31:04.739 --> 04:31:06.479
You healed me with magic?

04:31:06.540 --> 04:31:07.979
That is amazing.

04:31:08.040 --> 04:31:12.059
I know, it really is, said anemone

04:31:12.059 --> 04:31:12.899
preening.

04:31:12.959 --> 04:31:16.739
I did like those scars, though, Kinkachu

04:31:16.739 --> 04:31:18.120
said, a little wistfully.

04:31:18.180 --> 04:31:20.819
They made me seem all battle hardened and

04:31:20.819 --> 04:31:21.180
tough.

04:31:21.239 --> 04:31:23.520
Turtle bit back a laugh.

04:31:23.579 --> 04:31:26.100
As much as he adored her, it would never

04:31:26.100 --> 04:31:28.200
in a 1000000 years, have occurred to him

04:31:28.200 --> 04:31:29.940
to use those adjectives to describe

04:31:29.940 --> 04:31:30.719
Kinkaju.

04:31:30.780 --> 04:31:33.899
Oh, well, she said with a shrug.

04:31:34.020 --> 04:31:35.639
Thanks again, Anemone.

04:31:35.700 --> 04:31:38.280
Ooh, I'd love to be an animus.

04:31:38.340 --> 04:31:38.940
Is it fun?

04:31:39.000 --> 04:31:42.000
It is now, Anemone said.

04:31:42.059 --> 04:31:44.040
Now that I'm the one in charge of my

04:31:44.040 --> 04:31:46.079
spells, and nobody's telling me what to

04:31:46.079 --> 04:31:47.219
do all the time.

04:31:47.280 --> 04:31:50.940
There was a crash outside, like a tree

04:31:50.940 --> 04:31:52.440
falling not too far away.

04:31:52.500 --> 04:31:55.739
Anemone's face brightened, and she darted

04:31:55.739 --> 04:31:56.399
to the doorway.

04:31:56.459 --> 04:31:58.079
Don't be scared.

04:31:58.139 --> 04:32:01.319
Turtle said to Kingachu, quickly, in a

04:32:01.319 --> 04:32:04.319
low voice, a very big, scary looking

04:32:04.319 --> 04:32:06.719
dragon is about to show up, but he can't

04:32:06.719 --> 04:32:09.000
hurt you, and he can't see me or hear

04:32:09.000 --> 04:32:09.299
me.

04:32:09.360 --> 04:32:10.860
So don't be confused by that.

04:32:10.920 --> 04:32:13.020
I'll explain everything when he's gone.

04:32:13.079 --> 04:32:15.959
Kinkachu's eyes were shining with

04:32:15.959 --> 04:32:16.379
excitement.

04:32:16.440 --> 04:32:18.840
I feel like I fell asleep in one

04:32:18.840 --> 04:32:20.639
adventure and woke up in a totally

04:32:20.639 --> 04:32:21.239
different one.

04:32:21.299 --> 04:32:22.500
What is happening?

04:32:22.559 --> 04:32:23.520
This is amazing.

04:32:23.579 --> 04:32:25.680
Anemone?

04:32:25.739 --> 04:32:28.379
Rumbled Dark Stalker's voice outside the

04:32:28.379 --> 04:32:28.920
pavilion.

04:32:28.979 --> 04:32:31.440
Have you been doing more magic?

04:32:31.500 --> 04:32:34.260
Just a little healing spell?

04:32:34.319 --> 04:32:36.000
Anemone said cheerfully.

04:32:36.059 --> 04:32:37.559
Kingatu, come here.

04:32:37.620 --> 04:32:40.559
I don't know if you should be walking yet

04:32:40.559 --> 04:32:43.260
Turtle said, but Kinkaju was already

04:32:43.260 --> 04:32:44.159
bouncing off the bed.

04:32:44.219 --> 04:32:45.840
Woo!

04:32:45.899 --> 04:32:48.540
she said, wobbling on her talons for a

04:32:48.540 --> 04:32:48.780
moment.

04:32:48.840 --> 04:32:51.600
Guess I haven't stood up in a few days.

04:32:51.659 --> 04:32:52.860
Here we go.

04:32:52.920 --> 04:32:55.739
She flared her wings for balance and

04:32:55.739 --> 04:32:56.879
hopped over to the opening.

04:32:56.940 --> 04:32:58.860
Where anemone was holding the flower

04:32:58.860 --> 04:32:59.639
curtain aside.

04:32:59.700 --> 04:33:02.399
Kingachu stuck her head outside.

04:33:02.459 --> 04:33:04.799
Yikes, she yelped.

04:33:04.919 --> 04:33:05.879
Who are you?

04:33:05.939 --> 04:33:07.379
You are so big.

04:33:07.439 --> 04:33:11.219
Oh, said Dark Stalker.

04:33:11.279 --> 04:33:13.319
His voice immediately softening.

04:33:13.380 --> 04:33:14.819
Moon's friend.

04:33:14.880 --> 04:33:15.840
That's all right.

04:33:15.900 --> 04:33:18.360
I was planning to heal her myself, in

04:33:18.360 --> 04:33:20.099
fact, but anemone.

04:33:20.159 --> 04:33:22.380
Please remember to run your spells by me

04:33:22.380 --> 04:33:22.680
first.

04:33:22.799 --> 04:33:25.799
The 3 healers had all disappeared

04:33:25.799 --> 04:33:28.439
somewhere, perhaps scattering at the side

04:33:28.439 --> 04:33:30.959
of Dark Stalker, Turtle crept to the

04:33:30.959 --> 04:33:32.220
window and peeked out.

04:33:32.279 --> 04:33:34.739
The great night wing had landed on a

04:33:34.739 --> 04:33:37.319
pavilion outside, and all around him were

04:33:37.319 --> 04:33:39.959
flurries of leaves that weren't leaves

04:33:39.959 --> 04:33:42.419
and branches that weren't branches, as

04:33:42.419 --> 04:33:44.699
alarmed rain wings tried to hide and spy

04:33:44.699 --> 04:33:46.679
and sidle away at the same time.

04:33:46.740 --> 04:33:50.759
I don't like being bossed around, Anemone

04:33:50.759 --> 04:33:52.139
said, lifting her chin.

04:33:52.200 --> 04:33:53.459
I know what I'm doing.

04:33:53.520 --> 04:33:56.939
Of course you do, he said.

04:33:57.000 --> 04:33:59.580
But a 2nd eye on your spells can be

04:33:59.580 --> 04:33:59.880
helpful.

04:33:59.939 --> 04:34:03.299
I wish I'd had someone to give me advice

04:34:03.299 --> 04:34:04.739
about my scroll for instance.

04:34:04.799 --> 04:34:07.680
So I could enchant it to be used only by

04:34:07.680 --> 04:34:10.619
me, or to return to me if it was stolen.

04:34:10.740 --> 04:34:12.360
Wouldn't that have been smart?

04:34:12.419 --> 04:34:15.839
I can give you advice like that, because

04:34:15.839 --> 04:34:17.399
I've already made my mistakes.

04:34:17.459 --> 04:34:23.819
Oh, Anemone said, considering, sure, that

04:34:23.819 --> 04:34:24.240
makes sense.

04:34:24.299 --> 04:34:27.000
Turtle breathed a sigh of relief.

04:34:27.060 --> 04:34:30.360
Dark Stalker wasn't angry, and he didn't

04:34:30.360 --> 04:34:31.919
seem to have noticed Turtle's spell

04:34:31.919 --> 04:34:33.659
underneath anemones.

04:34:33.720 --> 04:34:36.240
Apart from the horrible fact that Kinkaju

04:34:36.240 --> 04:34:38.400
was now bewitched into loving him, the

04:34:38.400 --> 04:34:39.060
plan had worked.

04:34:39.119 --> 04:34:43.379
Your Majesty, Dark Stalker called.

04:34:43.439 --> 04:34:45.899
Turtles saw Glory and Deathbringer

04:34:45.899 --> 04:34:47.279
gliding through the treetops toward

04:34:47.279 --> 04:34:47.459
them.

04:34:47.520 --> 04:34:50.220
They landed on a branch nearby, and

04:34:50.220 --> 04:34:51.840
Gloria studied Dark Stalker

04:34:51.840 --> 04:34:52.860
thoughtfully.

04:34:52.919 --> 04:34:54.959
How did you find our village?

04:34:54.959 --> 04:34:55.739
she asked.

04:34:55.799 --> 04:34:58.799
I followed the sounds of rain wings

04:34:58.799 --> 04:35:01.259
thinking, he said. tapping his head.

04:35:01.319 --> 04:35:04.979
Or at least what passes for thinking in a

04:35:04.979 --> 04:35:05.759
rain wing these days.

04:35:05.819 --> 04:35:08.819
This tribe has really gone soft.

04:35:08.880 --> 04:35:12.000
Hey, Hinkachu objected.

04:35:12.060 --> 04:35:14.340
We defeated your stupid tribe, didn't

04:35:14.340 --> 04:35:14.459
we?

04:35:14.580 --> 04:35:17.279
Dog Stalker didn't bother to respond.

04:35:17.340 --> 04:35:19.740
He didn't even bother to look at her.

04:35:19.799 --> 04:35:22.080
I came to deliver a warning.

04:35:22.139 --> 04:35:23.340
Your majesty.

04:35:23.400 --> 04:35:25.799
He glanced around at the whispering

04:35:25.799 --> 04:35:26.220
trees.

04:35:26.279 --> 04:35:30.179
There are 5 dragons on their way here to

04:35:30.179 --> 04:35:30.539
kill you.

04:35:30.599 --> 04:35:33.899
They will most likely attack tonight, and

04:35:33.899 --> 04:35:36.299
unless I stop them, they will succeed.

04:35:36.360 --> 04:35:38.700
The trees gasped.

04:35:38.759 --> 04:35:42.959
I'll stop them, Deathbringer said, lashing

04:35:42.959 --> 04:35:43.259
his tail.

04:35:43.380 --> 04:35:45.360
I've stopped assassins before.

04:35:45.419 --> 04:35:49.679
I have bad news for you, said Dark

04:35:49.679 --> 04:35:50.219
Stalker.

04:35:50.279 --> 04:35:52.259
I'm the one who can see the future.

04:35:52.319 --> 04:35:54.959
I've seen the part where you get stabbed

04:35:54.959 --> 04:35:56.819
by a sandwing tail.

04:35:56.880 --> 04:36:00.299
Sandwings, Glory asked.

04:36:00.360 --> 04:36:02.819
Why would Sandwings want to attack me?

04:36:02.880 --> 04:36:05.819
They're working with a pair of night

04:36:05.819 --> 04:36:07.919
wings, you misplaced?

04:36:08.040 --> 04:36:09.720
Dark Stalker said.

04:36:09.779 --> 04:36:11.699
Does that ring a bell?

04:36:11.759 --> 04:36:14.279
Glory exchanged a glance with

04:36:14.279 --> 04:36:16.739
Deathbringer, and Turtle remembered the

04:36:16.739 --> 04:36:18.359
missing prisoners he'd heard about while

04:36:18.359 --> 04:36:20.759
eavesdropping, the ones who'd escaped

04:36:20.759 --> 04:36:22.199
from the Sandwing stronghold.

04:36:22.319 --> 04:36:24.240
You know what you need?

04:36:24.299 --> 04:36:26.279
Dark Stalker went on.

04:36:26.340 --> 04:36:28.500
A nice strong prison of your own.

04:36:28.560 --> 04:36:30.840
Wouldn't that solve a lot of problems?

04:36:30.900 --> 04:36:34.500
Rain wings are not really a prison kind

04:36:34.500 --> 04:36:35.220
of tribe.

04:36:35.279 --> 04:36:38.519
Glory started to say, the dark stalker

04:36:38.519 --> 04:36:40.259
was already snapping a branch off one of

04:36:40.259 --> 04:36:40.979
the trees overhead.

04:36:41.040 --> 04:36:43.799
Brunch, he commanded.

04:36:43.860 --> 04:36:47.400
Grow into a fine, strong, indestructible

04:36:47.400 --> 04:36:49.560
prison, with room for at least 10

04:36:49.560 --> 04:36:52.139
prisoners that no dragon could ever break

04:36:52.139 --> 04:36:52.439
out of.

04:36:52.500 --> 04:36:55.259
He flung the branch down toward the

04:36:55.259 --> 04:36:57.720
ground, and as it fell, it began to grow

04:36:57.720 --> 04:37:01.200
snapping outward and up, smashing through

04:37:01.200 --> 04:37:02.880
everything it hit as it plummeted.

04:37:02.880 --> 04:37:05.700
When it finally crashed to Earth, far

04:37:05.700 --> 04:37:08.759
below them, it was a massive, dense cube

04:37:08.759 --> 04:37:11.520
of some unfamiliar material with no

04:37:11.520 --> 04:37:11.880
windows.

04:37:11.939 --> 04:37:15.299
The last few blocks slammed into place

04:37:15.299 --> 04:37:17.519
and then it fell silent, apparently

04:37:17.519 --> 04:37:17.999
finished.

04:37:18.060 --> 04:37:21.060
The rain wings all stared down at it.

04:37:21.119 --> 04:37:23.819
Turtle could see Kinkajoo leaning over

04:37:23.819 --> 04:37:25.559
the edge of the walkway outside the

04:37:25.559 --> 04:37:28.079
healer's hut, her face a picture of

04:37:28.079 --> 04:37:28.679
outrage.

04:37:28.740 --> 04:37:32.580
The prison was gray and solid, large and

04:37:32.580 --> 04:37:33.240
forbidding.

04:37:33.299 --> 04:37:36.240
It hulked on the rainforest floor, like a

04:37:36.240 --> 04:37:38.700
sinister cloud that had been dragged to

04:37:38.700 --> 04:37:40.020
earth and chained down.

04:37:40.080 --> 04:37:42.840
Everything about it exuded wrongness.

04:37:42.959 --> 04:37:46.619
Perfect. said Dark Stalker.

04:37:46.680 --> 04:37:48.959
A ring of metal keys had appeared in his

04:37:48.959 --> 04:37:50.759
talons, and he tossed them to Queen

04:37:50.759 --> 04:37:51.240
Glory.

04:37:51.299 --> 04:37:52.919
You're welcome.

04:37:52.979 --> 04:37:55.799
Glory caught the keys and held them at

04:37:55.799 --> 04:37:57.840
arm's length, like a talon full of

04:37:57.840 --> 04:37:58.319
slugs.

04:37:58.380 --> 04:38:03.060
I don't see any windows on that thing, she

04:38:03.060 --> 04:38:03.299
said.

04:38:03.360 --> 04:38:05.880
It would be cruel to put any rain wings

04:38:05.880 --> 04:38:08.939
in there, shut off from the sun, and 10

04:38:08.939 --> 04:38:10.860
seems like far more prisoners than we'll

04:38:10.860 --> 04:38:11.099
ever have.

04:38:11.220 --> 04:38:13.680
Dark Stalker shrugged.

04:38:13.740 --> 04:38:17.400
You never know, he said, but use it

04:38:17.400 --> 04:38:18.119
however you like.

04:38:18.180 --> 04:38:20.639
At least you can get mastermind out of

04:38:20.639 --> 04:38:21.419
the quicksand now.

04:38:21.479 --> 04:38:23.639
Or give him to me.

04:38:23.700 --> 04:38:25.560
And I'll take him far away.

04:38:25.619 --> 04:38:27.119
It's up to you.

04:38:27.180 --> 04:38:29.459
Gloria lifted her chin.

04:38:29.520 --> 04:38:32.099
He still has to answer for his crimes

04:38:32.099 --> 04:38:33.299
against rain wings.

04:38:33.360 --> 04:38:37.020
Oh, yes. said Dark Stalker.

04:38:37.080 --> 04:38:40.200
Does this tribe have a terribly complex

04:38:40.200 --> 04:38:41.220
justice system?

04:38:41.220 --> 04:38:43.439
Or what's taking so long?

04:38:43.500 --> 04:38:48.419
It's A work in progress, Glory said.

04:38:48.479 --> 04:38:52.439
Let's visit your new prison, which should

04:38:52.439 --> 04:38:53.700
be a safe place to wait for the

04:38:53.700 --> 04:38:54.599
assassins.

04:38:54.840 --> 04:38:57.299
Dark Stalker suggested, spreading his

04:38:57.299 --> 04:39:00.240
wings, and meanwhile, I can tell you all

04:39:00.240 --> 04:39:02.939
about the courts and trials, and laws we

04:39:02.939 --> 04:39:04.259
had in the old night kingdom.

04:39:04.319 --> 04:39:07.500
It was a fascinating process, really

04:39:07.500 --> 04:39:10.319
beginning and ending with a Queen's

04:39:10.319 --> 04:39:10.919
judgment, of course.

04:39:10.979 --> 04:39:14.099
He spiraled down to the rainforest floor

04:39:14.099 --> 04:39:16.080
his voice fading as he dropped.

04:39:16.139 --> 04:39:19.619
Queen Glory, death bringer and anemone

04:39:19.619 --> 04:39:20.580
all flew after him.

04:39:20.639 --> 04:39:23.220
Turtle took a step back into the

04:39:23.220 --> 04:39:23.819
pavilion.

04:39:23.880 --> 04:39:25.860
His heart was beating anxiously.

04:39:25.919 --> 04:39:28.799
What if his spell didn't work, and

04:39:28.799 --> 04:39:31.499
Kinkaju was as bewitched by dark stalker

04:39:31.499 --> 04:39:32.039
as anyone else.

04:39:32.099 --> 04:39:34.859
Or what if Dark Stalker wasn't using a

04:39:34.859 --> 04:39:37.019
spell after all, and everyone else

04:39:37.019 --> 04:39:39.719
genuinely liked him, and Turtle was just

04:39:39.719 --> 04:39:40.079
wrong.

04:39:40.139 --> 04:39:44.099
Kinkaju ducked back inside, catching a

04:39:44.099 --> 04:39:45.779
delicate lavender orchid on one of her

04:39:45.779 --> 04:39:47.880
frills, and sauntered over to him.

04:39:47.880 --> 04:39:52.740
So that dragon's totally evil, she said.

04:39:52.799 --> 04:39:54.360
You think so?

04:39:54.419 --> 04:39:55.560
You really do?

04:39:55.680 --> 04:39:56.759
said Turtle.

04:39:56.880 --> 04:39:59.340
He felt as though he could collapse right

04:39:59.340 --> 04:40:01.259
here and nap for 3 days.

04:40:01.319 --> 04:40:04.740
He wasn't imagining things, and he wasn't

04:40:04.740 --> 04:40:05.459
alone anymore.

04:40:05.520 --> 04:40:08.939
He's acting like the boss of anemone.

04:40:09.000 --> 04:40:12.419
He's making creepy, unnecessary, un rain

04:40:12.419 --> 04:40:14.819
wingy things with his magic, and he's

04:40:14.819 --> 04:40:16.319
clearly trying to manipulate everyone

04:40:16.319 --> 04:40:18.840
with stuff like, oh, save you from

04:40:18.840 --> 04:40:19.799
assassins.

04:40:19.860 --> 04:40:23.400
And, oh, I was going to heal her myself

04:40:23.400 --> 04:40:24.180
actually.

04:40:24.240 --> 04:40:27.299
The good news is Queen Glory and

04:40:27.299 --> 04:40:28.740
Deathbringer will see right through him.

04:40:28.799 --> 04:40:31.080
They're probably planning some clever way

04:40:31.080 --> 04:40:33.119
to drive him out of the rainforest right

04:40:33.119 --> 04:40:33.360
now.

04:40:33.419 --> 04:40:36.540
Um, said Turtle.

04:40:36.599 --> 04:40:38.819
Unfortunately, they're not.

04:40:38.880 --> 04:40:41.880
They like him, or they think they do.

04:40:41.939 --> 04:40:45.479
See, I think he's using his magic on

04:40:45.479 --> 04:40:46.139
everyone.

04:40:46.200 --> 04:40:49.259
I don't know the details of the spell, but

04:40:49.259 --> 04:40:51.540
it seems like everyone who meets him or

04:40:51.540 --> 04:40:53.819
talks to him, ends up thinking he's

04:40:53.819 --> 04:40:55.680
perfectly nice, harmless, and

04:40:55.680 --> 04:40:56.580
trustworthy.

04:40:56.639 --> 04:40:58.680
Everyone?

04:40:58.680 --> 04:40:59.939
said Kinkaju.

04:41:00.000 --> 04:41:02.400
Even winter, said Turtle.

04:41:02.459 --> 04:41:04.200
Winter worst of all.

04:41:04.259 --> 04:41:07.200
Holy coconuts.

04:41:07.259 --> 04:41:10.259
Kingaju scratched her nose, turning a

04:41:10.259 --> 04:41:11.639
thoughtful shade of deep blue.

04:41:11.700 --> 04:41:13.680
I'm really surprised.

04:41:13.740 --> 04:41:15.959
That night wing seems like the kind of

04:41:15.959 --> 04:41:18.540
dragon who believes he's super charming

04:41:18.540 --> 04:41:20.759
like he wouldn't need magic to win

04:41:20.759 --> 04:41:21.360
dragons over.

04:41:21.419 --> 04:41:24.360
Maybe, said Turtle.

04:41:24.419 --> 04:41:27.540
But it's failed him once before, so I

04:41:27.540 --> 04:41:29.279
think he wants the extra security of the

04:41:29.279 --> 04:41:29.580
magic.

04:41:29.639 --> 04:41:32.700
He explained Dark Stalker's history to

04:41:32.700 --> 04:41:34.919
Kinkachu, at least as much as he knew of

04:41:34.919 --> 04:41:35.159
it.

04:41:35.220 --> 04:41:37.979
That led him to Dark Stalker's animus

04:41:37.979 --> 04:41:38.459
scroll.

04:41:38.520 --> 04:41:40.439
So then he had to explain what had

04:41:40.439 --> 04:41:42.779
happened with Apparel and Scarlet, and

04:41:42.779 --> 04:41:44.459
then as much as he knew of the story with

04:41:44.459 --> 04:41:46.919
Hailstorm, it was getting dark by the

04:41:46.919 --> 04:41:47.639
time he finished.

04:41:47.700 --> 04:41:49.319
Bah!

04:41:49.380 --> 04:41:52.500
Kinkachu grumbled, flicking her wings as

04:41:52.500 --> 04:41:54.540
orange starbursts went off across her

04:41:54.540 --> 04:41:55.259
scales.

04:41:55.319 --> 04:41:57.180
I really did miss everything.

04:41:57.240 --> 04:41:58.619
That's so unfair.

04:41:58.680 --> 04:42:02.279
Well, you're not missing this crisis.

04:42:02.340 --> 04:42:03.720
Turtle pointed out.

04:42:03.779 --> 04:42:06.779
You and I are the only dragons here who

04:42:06.779 --> 04:42:08.220
are safe from Dark Stalker.

04:42:08.279 --> 04:42:11.520
Which means he took a deep breath.

04:42:11.580 --> 04:42:13.919
You're the only one who can stop him.

04:42:13.979 --> 04:42:17.700
You mean, we're the only ones who can

04:42:17.700 --> 04:42:18.900
stop him, right?

04:42:18.959 --> 04:42:20.340
Kinkaju said.

04:42:20.400 --> 04:42:23.340
I was sort of hoping you would do it

04:42:23.340 --> 04:42:24.840
Turtle admitted.

04:42:24.900 --> 04:42:26.520
Turtle?

04:42:26.580 --> 04:42:29.520
She nudged him, so he teetered sideways.

04:42:29.580 --> 04:42:32.099
I totally would, but I'd rather do it

04:42:32.099 --> 04:42:32.340
with you.

04:42:32.459 --> 04:42:36.180
Saving the world is more fun, plus also

04:42:36.180 --> 04:42:37.979
less terrifying with friends.

04:42:38.099 --> 04:42:41.880
She gave him a sweet smile that made him

04:42:41.880 --> 04:42:44.040
extremely nervous about what Anemone's

04:42:44.040 --> 04:42:45.540
love spell might be doing to her brain.

04:42:45.599 --> 04:42:49.080
I am not a heroic dragon.

04:42:49.139 --> 04:42:50.520
Turtle protested.

04:42:50.580 --> 04:42:52.080
I don't have good ideas.

04:42:52.139 --> 04:42:54.959
I'm lazy, and I hide when bad things

04:42:54.959 --> 04:42:55.319
happen.

04:42:55.380 --> 04:42:59.340
Waking me up was a good idea, Kinkaju

04:42:59.340 --> 04:43:01.380
said brightly, and look, you're not

04:43:01.380 --> 04:43:01.799
hiding.

04:43:01.860 --> 04:43:03.779
You're right here, where the bad things

04:43:03.779 --> 04:43:06.299
are, and you left Jade Mountain to find

04:43:06.299 --> 04:43:08.220
me and Moon and the others.

04:43:08.279 --> 04:43:10.380
That's not lazy or hiding either.

04:43:10.439 --> 04:43:15.000
I was following peril, Turtle pointed

04:43:15.000 --> 04:43:15.240
out.

04:43:15.299 --> 04:43:18.479
If I'm anything in the story, I may be

04:43:18.479 --> 04:43:19.740
the hapless sidekick.

04:43:19.799 --> 04:43:21.060
Awesome.

04:43:21.180 --> 04:43:24.720
Kingachu leaped to her feet, beaming, I've

04:43:24.720 --> 04:43:26.279
always wanted a hapless sidekick.

04:43:26.340 --> 04:43:29.040
Okay, I don't know what hapless means, but

04:43:29.040 --> 04:43:30.840
it sounds like happy, so I bet it's

04:43:30.840 --> 04:43:31.259
awesome.

04:43:31.319 --> 04:43:32.459
Let's go take him down.

04:43:32.520 --> 04:43:34.740
She made a beeline for the door.

04:43:34.799 --> 04:43:36.840
Wait, now?

04:43:36.900 --> 04:43:37.860
Turtles said.

04:43:37.919 --> 04:43:39.240
What's the plan?

04:43:39.299 --> 04:43:40.380
Is there a plan?

04:43:40.439 --> 04:43:42.419
You know the hapless sidekick is the one

04:43:42.419 --> 04:43:43.080
who dies, right?

04:43:43.139 --> 04:43:45.119
Not in our story?

04:43:45.240 --> 04:43:46.619
Kinkaju called.

04:43:46.680 --> 04:43:48.900
Kinkaju, where are you going?

04:43:48.959 --> 04:43:52.080
Turtle shouted, as she barged through the

04:43:52.080 --> 04:43:53.580
hanging orchids into the desk.

04:43:53.639 --> 04:43:57.180
I'm going to go study him, Kinkaju

04:43:57.180 --> 04:43:59.700
explained, as he emerged behind her, as

04:43:59.700 --> 04:44:02.340
though this were all perfectly obvious, so

04:44:02.340 --> 04:44:04.259
we can figure out what he's enchanted to

04:44:04.259 --> 04:44:06.419
hypnotize everybody, and then we're going

04:44:06.419 --> 04:44:08.279
to steal it or break it, and then

04:44:08.279 --> 04:44:10.619
everyone will be all, ah, there's a

04:44:10.619 --> 04:44:12.840
monster dragon trying to manipulate us.

04:44:12.900 --> 04:44:14.880
And they'll rise up and stop him.

04:44:14.939 --> 04:44:16.080
Done.

04:44:16.139 --> 04:44:17.040
The day is saved.

04:44:17.099 --> 04:44:19.439
Turtle was beginning to wonder.

04:44:19.500 --> 04:44:22.259
Whether his problem-solving approach and

04:44:22.259 --> 04:44:24.180
kinkajoos might be completely

04:44:24.180 --> 04:44:27.479
incompatible. don't think it'll be that

04:44:27.479 --> 04:44:27.779
easy.

04:44:27.900 --> 04:44:30.240
He said, rubbing his forehead.

04:44:30.299 --> 04:44:31.380
Why not?

04:44:31.439 --> 04:44:33.000
You said he can't hurt me.

04:44:33.060 --> 04:44:34.439
Kinkatu pointed out.

04:44:34.500 --> 04:44:36.479
Wait, why can't he hurt me?

04:44:36.540 --> 04:44:40.380
Because of the spell I put on you, said

04:44:40.380 --> 04:44:40.740
Turtle.

04:44:40.799 --> 04:44:42.540
Kinkaju stared at him.

04:44:42.599 --> 04:44:44.939
Oh right, he said.

04:44:45.000 --> 04:44:47.279
There's one more thing I should probably

04:44:47.279 --> 04:44:48.299
have mentioned.

04:44:48.419 --> 04:44:51.180
She bundled him back inside the healer's

04:44:51.180 --> 04:44:51.779
pavilion.

04:44:51.840 --> 04:44:54.060
You're an animus?

04:44:54.119 --> 04:44:55.799
She hissed softly.

04:44:55.860 --> 04:44:58.319
Kind of a secret one.

04:44:58.380 --> 04:45:01.979
He said with a shrug, like, please don't

04:45:01.979 --> 04:45:02.459
tell anybody.

04:45:02.520 --> 04:45:04.979
I went through this already with peril

04:45:04.979 --> 04:45:07.319
and moon and winter and Kibli.

04:45:07.380 --> 04:45:09.180
Three moons!

04:45:09.240 --> 04:45:10.439
Kingachu cried.

04:45:10.500 --> 04:45:12.360
Why am I always the last to know

04:45:12.360 --> 04:45:12.779
everything?

04:45:12.840 --> 04:45:16.439
Well, no, he said.

04:45:16.500 --> 04:45:18.900
That would make you 5th.

04:45:18.959 --> 04:45:20.520
The 5th to know.

04:45:20.580 --> 04:45:24.240
Out of all the dragons Empirea, or sixth

04:45:24.240 --> 04:45:25.319
I suppose, if you count me.

04:45:25.380 --> 04:45:28.319
Kinkachu considered that for a moment

04:45:28.319 --> 04:45:30.299
with her snout scrunged up.

04:45:30.360 --> 04:45:32.700
Cool, she said finally.

04:45:32.759 --> 04:45:34.680
All right, that's not too bad.

04:45:34.799 --> 04:45:38.220
But next time you have a major enormous

04:45:38.220 --> 04:45:40.380
secret, tell me first, okay?

04:45:40.439 --> 04:45:43.200
Okay, he said.

04:45:43.259 --> 04:45:46.860
Maybe I should mention that I've cast a

04:45:46.860 --> 04:45:49.380
spell to hide myself from Dark Stalker?

04:45:49.560 --> 04:45:51.599
He pulled out his stick and explained

04:45:51.599 --> 04:45:53.939
what it did, and how he couldn't cast any

04:45:53.939 --> 04:45:56.220
more spells because Dark Stalker would

04:45:56.220 --> 04:45:58.259
sense them, except for the one he'd

04:45:58.259 --> 04:46:00.119
managed to hide under anemones.

04:46:00.240 --> 04:46:04.919
So you see, he finished, I'm not actually

04:46:04.919 --> 04:46:07.500
here in the middle of all the bad things

04:46:07.500 --> 04:46:10.020
because I'm really actually hiding.

04:46:10.080 --> 04:46:12.900
I'm hiding all the time.

04:46:12.959 --> 04:46:18.240
Ooh, Kinkachu said, her eyes shining

04:46:18.240 --> 04:46:20.819
totally invisible to dark stalker.

04:46:20.880 --> 04:46:23.159
That is an excellent spell.

04:46:23.220 --> 04:46:25.319
Another great idea, see?

04:46:25.380 --> 04:46:26.759
We'll be an awesome team.

04:46:26.819 --> 04:46:30.000
You can be the idea dragon, and I can be

04:46:30.000 --> 04:46:32.580
the wham bam, shove a pineapple up as

04:46:32.580 --> 04:46:33.299
snout dragon.

04:46:33.360 --> 04:46:35.759
No, no, that won't work.

04:46:35.819 --> 04:46:37.979
I think his snout is enchanted.

04:46:38.099 --> 04:46:39.540
Turtle pointed out.

04:46:39.659 --> 04:46:43.259
To be invulnerable to pineapples?

04:46:43.319 --> 04:46:45.479
Kinkaju asked, and burst into giggles.

04:46:45.540 --> 04:46:47.099
Oh dear.

04:46:47.159 --> 04:46:50.279
An image of tiny rainbow colored kinkaju

04:46:50.279 --> 04:46:52.500
lobbing fruit and dark stalker popped

04:46:52.500 --> 04:46:53.340
into turtle's head.

04:46:53.400 --> 04:46:56.040
Maybe he hadn't entirely thought through

04:46:56.040 --> 04:46:57.060
his choice of hero.

04:46:57.119 --> 04:47:00.900
Don't worry so much, Kinkachu said

04:47:00.900 --> 04:47:02.639
brushing his wing with hers.

04:47:02.700 --> 04:47:04.680
Your forehead will get stuck that way.

04:47:04.740 --> 04:47:07.500
My plan will totally work, I swear.

04:47:07.560 --> 04:47:10.319
Or if it doesn't, we'll come up with a

04:47:10.319 --> 04:47:11.220
new amazing plan.

04:47:11.279 --> 04:47:16.020
Ooh, I bet this is exactly how glory felt

04:47:16.020 --> 04:47:18.060
when she was about to save the world.

04:47:18.119 --> 04:47:21.000
She bounded off to the doorway again.

04:47:21.060 --> 04:47:23.939
And Turtle found himself thinking that he

04:47:23.939 --> 04:47:26.700
couldn't imagine Queen Glory bounding, or

04:47:26.700 --> 04:47:28.319
in fact, getting this excited about

04:47:28.319 --> 04:47:28.680
anything.

04:47:28.740 --> 04:47:32.520
Outside, the sky was fading into purple

04:47:32.520 --> 04:47:35.279
dark, shadows hurrying into all the gaps

04:47:35.279 --> 04:47:36.240
between the trees.

04:47:36.299 --> 04:47:40.080
Turtle felt the brush of soft fur as a

04:47:40.080 --> 04:47:41.819
sloth clambered by right over his head.

04:47:41.939 --> 04:47:44.459
He could hear snoring coming from a few

04:47:44.459 --> 04:47:47.400
hammocks already, and the air hummed with

04:47:47.400 --> 04:47:49.500
a hungry buzz of dusk happy insects.

04:47:49.619 --> 04:47:53.580
Far below them, a ring of fire smoldered

04:47:53.580 --> 04:47:56.040
on the forest floor, encircling the

04:47:56.040 --> 04:47:58.500
shadowy figures of dark stalker, Queen

04:47:58.500 --> 04:48:00.060
Glory, and the others.

04:48:00.119 --> 04:48:02.459
Kingajou let out a small growl when she

04:48:02.459 --> 04:48:02.819
saw it.

04:48:02.880 --> 04:48:06.479
Queen Glory doesn't usually allow that

04:48:06.479 --> 04:48:09.119
much fire in our forest, she whispered.

04:48:09.180 --> 04:48:11.279
There are strict rules for the night

04:48:11.279 --> 04:48:13.860
wings about how and when, and how

04:48:13.860 --> 04:48:14.759
carefully to use it.

04:48:14.759 --> 04:48:17.639
She's definitely fallen for that baboon

04:48:17.639 --> 04:48:18.360
butts act.

04:48:18.419 --> 04:48:20.279
Spell.

04:48:20.340 --> 04:48:22.860
Turtle reminded her, it's a spell.

04:48:22.919 --> 04:48:24.779
Let's get closer.

04:48:24.840 --> 04:48:27.599
Can get you wafted down toward the

04:48:27.599 --> 04:48:30.000
gathered dragons as softly as a falling

04:48:30.000 --> 04:48:32.459
leaf, navigating the interlocking

04:48:32.459 --> 04:48:33.360
branches with ease.

04:48:33.479 --> 04:48:37.020
Turtle realized that rain wings must have

04:48:37.020 --> 04:48:39.419
some ability to see in the dark, just as

04:48:39.419 --> 04:48:40.200
sea wings did.

04:48:40.319 --> 04:48:41.700
He followed her.

04:48:41.759 --> 04:48:44.279
Less gracefully and with a bit more noise

04:48:44.279 --> 04:48:46.619
but he knew dark stalker couldn't hear

04:48:46.619 --> 04:48:46.799
him.

04:48:46.860 --> 04:48:50.279
They settled near the prison, outside the

04:48:50.279 --> 04:48:52.319
fiery circle, but close enough to hear

04:48:52.319 --> 04:48:53.819
the dragons inside it.

04:48:53.880 --> 04:48:57.659
Damp leaves flapped in their faces, and

04:48:57.659 --> 04:48:59.159
things scuttled away beneath their

04:48:59.159 --> 04:48:59.639
claws.

04:48:59.700 --> 04:49:02.400
Kinkajoo shuffled in closer to Turtle.

04:49:02.459 --> 04:49:05.880
He could feel her wings brushing his, her

04:49:05.880 --> 04:49:08.639
scales cool and camouflaged to a dark

04:49:08.639 --> 04:49:09.419
black blue.

04:49:09.479 --> 04:49:12.000
Was she really in love with him now?

04:49:12.060 --> 04:49:14.939
She was acting exactly the same as she

04:49:14.939 --> 04:49:15.419
always had.

04:49:15.479 --> 04:49:17.700
But maybe that's the way she was with

04:49:17.700 --> 04:49:19.680
everyone, no matter how she felt about

04:49:19.680 --> 04:49:19.919
them.

04:49:20.040 --> 04:49:23.400
Or maybe she already felt this way about

04:49:23.400 --> 04:49:23.639
you.

04:49:23.700 --> 04:49:25.139
Way back at school.

04:49:25.200 --> 04:49:28.860
Turtles shook off that highly unlikely

04:49:28.860 --> 04:49:29.159
thought.

04:49:29.220 --> 04:49:31.680
He was not a dragon anyone would notice

04:49:31.680 --> 04:49:34.319
or fall for, especially when he was

04:49:34.319 --> 04:49:36.299
standing next to funny Kibley, or

04:49:36.299 --> 04:49:38.939
handsome Winter, or kindhearted umber.

04:49:39.000 --> 04:49:41.400
He felt a pang at the thought of his

04:49:41.400 --> 04:49:42.000
clawmate.

04:49:42.060 --> 04:49:45.540
If this is ever over, maybe I could use

04:49:45.540 --> 04:49:48.240
my magic to find umber and make sure he's

04:49:48.240 --> 04:49:48.540
all right.

04:49:48.599 --> 04:49:50.939
Did you hear something?

04:49:51.060 --> 04:49:53.880
Glory asked, turning to look out at the

04:49:53.880 --> 04:49:55.860
dark in the direction of turtle and

04:49:55.860 --> 04:49:56.520
kinkaju.

04:49:56.580 --> 04:50:01.200
Just an orangutan, said Dark Stalker with

04:50:01.200 --> 04:50:02.040
a flick of his tail.

04:50:02.099 --> 04:50:04.979
I'll be able to hear the killer's minds

04:50:04.979 --> 04:50:05.459
approaching.

04:50:05.520 --> 04:50:09.000
I heard a noise, said Deathbringer

04:50:09.000 --> 04:50:10.200
sounding disgruntled.

04:50:10.259 --> 04:50:12.659
But of course, I can't see anything

04:50:12.659 --> 04:50:14.819
because there's a fire in the way.

04:50:14.880 --> 04:50:16.979
Trust me.

04:50:17.040 --> 04:50:20.639
This will keep your queen safe, said Dark

04:50:20.639 --> 04:50:21.180
Stalker.

04:50:21.240 --> 04:50:23.520
They'll have to run through the fire to

04:50:23.520 --> 04:50:25.500
get to her, which they are not brave

04:50:25.500 --> 04:50:28.380
enough to do, or fly over it, which will

04:50:28.380 --> 04:50:29.580
let us hear them coming.

04:50:29.819 --> 04:50:32.580
Although I'll hear them coming my way

04:50:32.580 --> 04:50:33.119
first.

04:50:33.180 --> 04:50:34.380
Of course.

04:50:34.500 --> 04:50:37.919
He lifted his head and stared piercingly

04:50:37.919 --> 04:50:38.400
into the dark.

04:50:38.520 --> 04:50:41.400
He looks like he's posing for a

04:50:41.400 --> 04:50:41.819
portrait.

04:50:41.880 --> 04:50:43.919
Kinkagu whispered to Turtle.

04:50:43.979 --> 04:50:47.700
Pompous Snerdegaard, the magnificent

04:50:47.700 --> 04:50:49.979
awaits his allegiance of doomed enemies.

04:50:50.040 --> 04:50:52.860
Turtles smothered a laugh.

04:50:52.919 --> 04:50:55.439
He realized that his wings were less

04:50:55.439 --> 04:50:57.959
tense than they'd been in days and at

04:50:57.959 --> 04:51:00.540
this, perhaps, was the best part of

04:51:00.540 --> 04:51:01.979
sharing his burden with someone else.

04:51:02.040 --> 04:51:05.040
He hadn't thought of chameleon, or seen

04:51:05.040 --> 04:51:07.439
any flashes of blood in his mind, since

04:51:07.439 --> 04:51:08.520
Kinkaju woke up.

04:51:08.580 --> 04:51:12.180
His constant pulsing anxiety had ebbed

04:51:12.180 --> 04:51:14.520
just a little, and cracks of hope were

04:51:14.520 --> 04:51:15.180
sliding in.

04:51:15.240 --> 04:51:17.520
Shh, he said anyway.

04:51:17.580 --> 04:51:19.740
He could still hear you.

04:51:19.799 --> 04:51:22.439
But he won't care, she answered.

04:51:22.560 --> 04:51:24.599
I'm less than nobody to him.

04:51:24.659 --> 04:51:26.340
She paused.

04:51:26.400 --> 04:51:27.419
Yeek.

04:51:27.479 --> 04:51:29.040
I don't know if I like the sound of

04:51:29.040 --> 04:51:29.279
that.

04:51:29.400 --> 04:51:31.319
Being less than nobody?

04:51:31.380 --> 04:51:33.540
Being unimportant to the future?

04:51:33.599 --> 04:51:35.580
I want to be somebody.

04:51:35.639 --> 04:51:38.099
Somebody drag its notice and remember.

04:51:38.159 --> 04:51:41.400
Nope, turtle thought.

04:51:41.459 --> 04:51:43.139
Nope, nope, nope.

04:51:43.200 --> 04:51:45.599
I gave up on that idea a long time ago.

04:51:45.659 --> 04:51:48.779
If no one notices you, you can't let

04:51:48.779 --> 04:51:49.439
anyone down.

04:51:49.500 --> 04:51:52.500
Kinkachu was watching him expectantly.

04:51:52.619 --> 04:51:56.639
Oh, he said, um, you're somebody to me.

04:51:56.700 --> 04:51:59.759
She clasped her front talons over her

04:51:59.759 --> 04:52:01.200
snout to hide her giggles.

04:52:01.259 --> 04:52:04.500
Right line, she said, but you need to

04:52:04.500 --> 04:52:06.659
work on your timing and believability.

04:52:06.720 --> 04:52:09.540
You are, he protested.

04:52:09.599 --> 04:52:11.459
I was thinking about something else.

04:52:11.520 --> 04:52:15.419
Oh, now I feel very fascinating, she

04:52:15.419 --> 04:52:15.900
joked.

04:52:15.959 --> 04:52:18.299
I'm not sure you're taking this seriously

04:52:18.299 --> 04:52:20.220
enough, he said sternly.

04:52:20.279 --> 04:52:22.200
Here they come.

04:52:22.259 --> 04:52:25.680
Dark Stalker rumbled suddenly, in a voice

04:52:25.680 --> 04:52:27.540
like the 1st breath of a snowstorm.

04:52:27.599 --> 04:52:30.180
I will take care of them, Your Majesty.

04:52:30.299 --> 04:52:32.759
He stepped over the fire with his

04:52:32.759 --> 04:52:33.659
towering legs.

04:52:33.720 --> 04:52:36.779
The flames lapped at his scales, but left

04:52:36.779 --> 04:52:37.380
no marks.

04:52:37.439 --> 04:52:38.759
Turtles shivered.

04:52:38.819 --> 04:52:41.459
The powerful night wing stalked away into

04:52:41.459 --> 04:52:43.740
the night, the ground trembling with

04:52:43.740 --> 04:52:44.520
every footstep.

04:52:44.580 --> 04:52:46.139
Ha!

04:52:46.200 --> 04:52:48.659
Anemone said merrily, from her spot in

04:52:48.659 --> 04:52:50.700
the center of the circle, as far away

04:52:50.700 --> 04:52:52.139
from the flames as she could get.

04:52:52.200 --> 04:52:54.659
I feel sorry for those assassins.

04:52:54.720 --> 04:52:56.939
I went on to run into him in a dark

04:52:56.939 --> 04:52:57.419
forest.

04:52:57.479 --> 04:53:00.720
In a startlingly brief amount of time

04:53:00.720 --> 04:53:03.900
Dark Stalker came back, accompanied by

04:53:03.900 --> 04:53:05.340
the noise of clanking chains.

04:53:05.400 --> 04:53:08.279
As he approached the fire, Turtle

04:53:08.279 --> 04:53:10.619
realized that he was dragging 4 dragons

04:53:10.619 --> 04:53:12.959
behind him, all of them linked by chains

04:53:12.959 --> 04:53:14.340
around their necks and angles.

04:53:14.340 --> 04:53:17.099
One of them was a young female nightwing

04:53:17.099 --> 04:53:18.840
and she was spitting mad.

04:53:18.900 --> 04:53:20.819
Let us go.

04:53:20.880 --> 04:53:22.979
She hissed Dark Stalker.

04:53:23.040 --> 04:53:24.240
Who do you think you are?

04:53:24.299 --> 04:53:25.799
Are you a nightwing or not?

04:53:25.860 --> 04:53:27.119
Whose side are you on?

04:53:27.180 --> 04:53:29.099
Chains.

04:53:29.159 --> 04:53:30.360
Glory murmured.

04:53:30.419 --> 04:53:32.759
We don't usually do chains in the

04:53:32.759 --> 04:53:33.419
rainforest.

04:53:33.479 --> 04:53:35.400
They're very effective though.

04:53:35.520 --> 04:53:37.139
Deathbringer pointed out.

04:53:37.200 --> 04:53:39.419
I much prefer seeing your enemies this

04:53:39.419 --> 04:53:39.599
way.

04:53:39.659 --> 04:53:43.860
Queen Glory, Dark Stalker said.

04:53:43.919 --> 04:53:46.560
Here are the dragons who are planning to

04:53:46.560 --> 04:53:46.919
kill you.

04:53:47.040 --> 04:53:50.159
He stopped, and blew out most of the fire

04:53:50.159 --> 04:53:53.040
in one long breath, leaving only a small

04:53:53.040 --> 04:53:54.000
section of flames.

04:53:54.119 --> 04:53:56.819
Turtle blinked away the dancing orange

04:53:56.819 --> 04:53:59.700
spots in his vision as his eyes adjusted

04:53:59.700 --> 04:54:00.299
back to the dark.

04:54:00.360 --> 04:54:04.380
Would you like me to dispose of them?

04:54:04.439 --> 04:54:08.400
Dark Stalker's voice asked, deep and

04:54:08.400 --> 04:54:09.900
eerie in the shadows overhead.

04:54:09.959 --> 04:54:13.619
Oh, wonderful. said the female prisoner

04:54:13.619 --> 04:54:14.099
bitterly.

04:54:14.159 --> 04:54:15.840
Fat lot of use you were.

04:54:15.900 --> 04:54:18.599
She hissed to the 2 sand wing captives.

04:54:18.659 --> 04:54:21.119
The last was another night wing, a

04:54:21.119 --> 04:54:23.700
solidly built male, who shuffled toward

04:54:23.700 --> 04:54:25.560
her and reached his tail to rest gently

04:54:25.560 --> 04:54:26.040
on hers.

04:54:26.099 --> 04:54:30.360
Wait, said Glory, I want to talk to

04:54:30.360 --> 04:54:30.540
them.

04:54:30.599 --> 04:54:33.060
Your fierce teeth, aren't you?

04:54:33.119 --> 04:54:35.639
And this must be strong wings.

04:54:35.700 --> 04:54:39.479
The female only glared back, but the male

04:54:39.479 --> 04:54:39.720
nodded.

04:54:39.840 --> 04:54:42.299
Listen, said Glory.

04:54:42.360 --> 04:54:45.360
What you did cannot easily be forgiven.

04:54:45.419 --> 04:54:48.599
You kidnapped Sonny, and you planned to

04:54:48.599 --> 04:54:51.000
betray us to burn in the hope that my

04:54:51.000 --> 04:54:53.459
friends and I would die, including your

04:54:53.459 --> 04:54:54.000
own brother.

04:54:54.000 --> 04:54:57.720
Turtle blinked at Kinkaju, then back at

04:54:57.720 --> 04:54:58.680
the other dragons.

04:54:58.740 --> 04:54:59.580
Brother?

04:54:59.639 --> 04:55:02.639
Was this hissing ball of fury related to

04:55:02.639 --> 04:55:03.299
Starflight?

04:55:03.360 --> 04:55:06.659
No, fierce teeth snapped.

04:55:06.720 --> 04:55:08.040
I would have kept him out of it.

04:55:08.159 --> 04:55:11.279
Glory regarded her for a moment, as

04:55:11.279 --> 04:55:12.900
though she wasn't sure what to believe.

04:55:12.959 --> 04:55:17.880
Well, that's something, at least, she

04:55:17.880 --> 04:55:18.119
said.

04:55:18.180 --> 04:55:20.099
What was your plan here tonight?

04:55:20.159 --> 04:55:23.580
To take the throne for a true night wing

04:55:23.580 --> 04:55:26.040
so our tribe can have its pride back.

04:55:26.099 --> 04:55:28.860
Fierce teeth tried to lift her shoulders

04:55:28.860 --> 04:55:30.180
under the weight of the chains.

04:55:30.240 --> 04:55:34.500
Oh, already taken care of, said dark

04:55:34.500 --> 04:55:35.099
stalker.

04:55:35.159 --> 04:55:37.619
He gave a little tug on the chain he held

04:55:37.619 --> 04:55:40.139
and strong wings stumbled forward into an

04:55:40.139 --> 04:55:40.979
accidental bow.

04:55:41.040 --> 04:55:44.279
I'm going to rule the night wings now.

04:55:44.400 --> 04:55:47.580
The ones who choose to go with him.

04:55:47.639 --> 04:55:49.200
Glory interjected.

04:55:49.259 --> 04:55:52.439
You can't, fierce teeth said.

04:55:52.500 --> 04:55:53.580
You're male.

04:55:53.639 --> 04:55:55.139
And where did you come from?

04:55:55.200 --> 04:55:57.479
You weren't with us on the volcano, that's

04:55:57.479 --> 04:55:57.720
for sure.

04:55:57.779 --> 04:55:59.819
What gives you the right to rule us?

04:55:59.880 --> 04:56:01.619
Size.

04:56:01.740 --> 04:56:02.819
Power.

04:56:02.880 --> 04:56:05.700
Timing, charm.

04:56:05.819 --> 04:56:09.000
And a whole bunch of dragons who think

04:56:09.000 --> 04:56:12.299
it's a great idea, said Dark Stalker, with

04:56:12.299 --> 04:56:12.659
a grin.

04:56:12.779 --> 04:56:15.900
My name is Dog Stalker.

04:56:15.959 --> 04:56:19.259
Strong wings let out a whimper and

04:56:19.259 --> 04:56:20.220
covered his head with his wings.

04:56:20.279 --> 04:56:23.639
We're going to die, he said in a muffled

04:56:23.639 --> 04:56:23.819
voice.

04:56:23.880 --> 04:56:25.259
It was all true.

04:56:25.319 --> 04:56:26.099
It was.

04:56:26.159 --> 04:56:26.880
I knew it.

04:56:26.939 --> 04:56:28.500
He's come back to kill us all.

04:56:28.560 --> 04:56:31.979
But fierce teeth held her ground, staring

04:56:31.979 --> 04:56:33.000
up at Dark Stalker.

04:56:33.060 --> 04:56:34.380
Really?

04:56:34.439 --> 04:56:35.340
She said.

04:56:35.400 --> 04:56:37.200
From the ghost stories.

04:56:37.259 --> 04:56:38.520
You.

04:56:38.580 --> 04:56:42.060
In the scales, he said.

04:56:42.180 --> 04:56:44.819
Right, she scoffed.

04:56:44.880 --> 04:56:46.439
That's a pretty clever trick.

04:56:46.500 --> 04:56:47.639
Show up.

04:56:47.700 --> 04:56:49.919
Pretend to be everyone's worst nightmare

04:56:49.919 --> 04:56:51.180
and scare them into giving you the

04:56:51.180 --> 04:56:51.479
crown.

04:56:51.540 --> 04:56:54.060
Well, it's not going to work on me, you

04:56:54.060 --> 04:56:54.959
scaly worm.

04:56:55.020 --> 04:56:56.939
I'm not even a little bit of right of

04:56:56.939 --> 04:56:57.119
you.

04:56:57.240 --> 04:57:00.479
Dark Stalker chuckled, rustling the

04:57:00.479 --> 04:57:01.500
leaves in the trees.

04:57:01.560 --> 04:57:04.680
Beast teeth, strong wings whispered.

04:57:04.740 --> 04:57:06.240
Stop, it's him.

04:57:06.299 --> 04:57:07.319
Don't make him mad.

04:57:07.380 --> 04:57:12.479
It is Dark Stalker, Anemone said loudly

04:57:12.479 --> 04:57:14.880
from behind Glory and Deathbringer, and

04:57:14.880 --> 04:57:16.680
he could crush you with one flick of his

04:57:16.680 --> 04:57:17.099
claw.

04:57:17.159 --> 04:57:18.959
Maybe he should.

04:57:19.020 --> 04:57:21.060
Given what you were planning to do to the

04:57:21.060 --> 04:57:21.360
queen.

04:57:21.479 --> 04:57:23.040
Deathbringer added.

04:57:23.099 --> 04:57:26.220
If you're so powerful, then you can

04:57:26.220 --> 04:57:27.000
handle a challenge.

04:57:27.060 --> 04:57:29.639
Fierce teeth said to Dark Stalker

04:57:29.639 --> 04:57:30.599
ignoring the others.

04:57:30.720 --> 04:57:33.060
I want the night wing throne.

04:57:33.180 --> 04:57:35.220
I think I should get to be queen.

04:57:35.279 --> 04:57:37.740
I'm female, and I know my tribe.

04:57:37.799 --> 04:57:39.900
I'd be better at it than some lying

04:57:39.900 --> 04:57:40.200
stranger.

04:57:40.319 --> 04:57:44.459
Hey, Turtle whispered to Kinkaju.

04:57:44.520 --> 04:57:46.799
Maybe I'm wrong about dark stalker

04:57:46.799 --> 04:57:47.159
spell.

04:57:47.220 --> 04:57:49.560
She doesn't seem affected by it at all.

04:57:49.619 --> 04:57:53.220
Actually, I think this is how she talks

04:57:53.220 --> 04:57:54.540
to dragons she likes.

04:57:54.599 --> 04:57:56.459
Kinkachu said ruefully.

04:57:56.520 --> 04:58:00.540
Brave little fierce teeth, said Dark

04:58:00.540 --> 04:58:01.080
Stalker.

04:58:01.200 --> 04:58:03.779
Don't call me little, she interrupted

04:58:03.779 --> 04:58:04.020
him.

04:58:04.080 --> 04:58:06.360
Just because you're overgrown, doesn't

04:58:06.360 --> 04:58:07.439
mean you can patronize me.

04:58:07.500 --> 04:58:09.900
I was going to say.

04:58:10.080 --> 04:58:11.520
I like your spirit.

04:58:11.580 --> 04:58:13.500
Dark Stalker started.

04:58:13.560 --> 04:58:15.779
Can you make that a bit more

04:58:15.779 --> 04:58:16.680
condescending?

04:58:16.740 --> 04:58:18.840
Fierce teeth snapped back.

04:58:18.900 --> 04:58:21.779
He paused, and Turtle got the distinct

04:58:21.779 --> 04:58:23.040
impression that he was trying not to

04:58:23.040 --> 04:58:23.220
laugh.

04:58:23.279 --> 04:58:25.200
All right.

04:58:25.259 --> 04:58:26.520
He said at length.

04:58:26.580 --> 04:58:28.740
You're not a dragon who likes

04:58:28.740 --> 04:58:29.400
compliments.

04:58:29.459 --> 04:58:30.000
I see.

04:58:30.060 --> 04:58:31.319
So I'll be blunt.

04:58:31.380 --> 04:58:34.200
I don't want to begin my reign as king of

04:58:34.200 --> 04:58:36.299
the night wings by killing one of my

04:58:36.299 --> 04:58:36.720
subjects.

04:58:36.779 --> 04:58:40.259
Especially one who could be such valuable

04:58:40.259 --> 04:58:42.419
asset in rebuilding our tribe.

04:58:42.540 --> 04:58:44.220
He turned to glory.

04:58:44.279 --> 04:58:46.979
Given the utter failure of all her

04:58:46.979 --> 04:58:49.560
schemes so far, and her relationship to

04:58:49.560 --> 04:58:51.659
Starflight, my proposal is this.

04:58:51.779 --> 04:58:55.080
Grant her your mercy and give her to me.

04:58:55.139 --> 04:58:57.659
Tomorrow, I'll take her to the Night

04:58:57.659 --> 04:58:59.700
Kingdom with me, where she'll have no

04:58:59.700 --> 04:59:00.840
reason to bother you anymore.

04:59:00.900 --> 04:59:04.439
She can be my problem instead.

04:59:04.500 --> 04:59:07.080
I will be your problem.

04:59:07.139 --> 04:59:08.880
Fierce teeth growled.

04:59:08.939 --> 04:59:10.380
No one gives me to anybody.

04:59:10.439 --> 04:59:12.720
I'll go to the Night Kingdom only if I

04:59:12.720 --> 04:59:13.259
want to.

04:59:13.380 --> 04:59:15.240
She paused.

04:59:15.299 --> 04:59:17.639
Narrowed her eyes suspiciously and added

04:59:17.639 --> 04:59:19.740
What night kingdom?

04:59:19.799 --> 04:59:20.220
Where?

04:59:20.279 --> 04:59:25.139
The old one, said Dark Stalker, where the

04:59:25.139 --> 04:59:27.119
tribe should have been for the last 2000

04:59:27.119 --> 04:59:27.479
years.

04:59:27.599 --> 04:59:28.680
You'll love it.

04:59:28.740 --> 04:59:31.680
We'll find you something important to

04:59:31.680 --> 04:59:31.860
do.

04:59:31.919 --> 04:59:35.279
Hang on said Deathbringer.

04:59:35.400 --> 04:59:37.860
She tries to assassinate glory, and her

04:59:37.860 --> 04:59:39.720
punishment. if she gets to be a part of

04:59:39.720 --> 04:59:41.400
your court ruling the night wings.

04:59:41.520 --> 04:59:45.360
Makes sense to me, said Glory

04:59:45.360 --> 04:59:45.959
thoughtfully.

04:59:46.020 --> 04:59:48.299
She wouldn't be a threat to me anymore.

04:59:48.360 --> 04:59:51.840
Once she has what she wants, right, fierce

04:59:51.840 --> 04:59:53.759
teeth, and then I don't have to have

04:59:53.759 --> 04:59:56.580
Starflight's entire family behind bars.

04:59:56.639 --> 04:59:59.819
She took a step closer to fierce teeth.

04:59:59.880 --> 05:00:03.180
Would you leave my rainforest, my friends

05:00:03.180 --> 05:00:06.540
and my tribe alone if we give you this

05:00:06.540 --> 05:00:07.080
2nd chance?

05:00:07.139 --> 05:00:10.439
Fierce teeth glared sideways at Dark

05:00:10.439 --> 05:00:10.919
Stalker.

05:00:10.979 --> 05:00:13.439
Are you lying?

05:00:13.560 --> 05:00:13.979
she demanded.

05:00:14.040 --> 05:00:16.200
Would I really be in charge of

05:00:16.200 --> 05:00:16.439
something?

05:00:16.560 --> 05:00:21.360
All you want is a little power, and a lot

05:00:21.360 --> 05:00:23.819
of respect, Dog Stalker observed.

05:00:23.880 --> 05:00:25.619
I can give you those.

05:00:25.740 --> 05:00:29.099
And strong wings, she interjected.

05:00:29.159 --> 05:00:30.360
He stays with me.

05:00:30.479 --> 05:00:33.720
Dark stalker gave strong wings an

05:00:33.720 --> 05:00:35.400
unimpressed look and shrugged.

05:00:35.459 --> 05:00:37.380
If you insist.

05:00:37.439 --> 05:00:40.020
Fierce teeth tapped her claws on the

05:00:40.020 --> 05:00:40.740
ground thoughtfully.

05:00:40.799 --> 05:00:43.259
Strong wings still had his head covered

05:00:43.259 --> 05:00:45.240
looking very much like a dragon who

05:00:45.240 --> 05:00:47.340
regretted all his live choices so far.

05:00:47.340 --> 05:00:50.159
Think about it overnight.

05:00:50.220 --> 05:00:54.360
Dark Stalker suggested, in our lovely new

05:00:54.360 --> 05:00:56.759
accommodations, for troublemakers.

05:00:56.880 --> 05:01:00.419
He swept one wing toward the prison, where

05:01:00.419 --> 05:01:02.939
turtle was sure, even a few minutes would

05:01:02.939 --> 05:01:05.220
convince any dragon to accept alternate

05:01:05.220 --> 05:01:05.520
offers.

05:01:05.580 --> 05:01:08.639
Hey, what about us?

05:01:08.759 --> 05:01:10.740
grunted one of the sand wings.

05:01:10.799 --> 05:01:14.099
Queen Thorn gets to decide your fate.

05:01:14.159 --> 05:01:17.400
Glory said, drawing herself up regally.

05:01:17.459 --> 05:01:20.099
In the meanwhile, you're going in there

05:01:20.099 --> 05:01:20.340
too.

05:01:20.459 --> 05:01:23.459
She tossed the keys to Dark Stalker.

05:01:23.520 --> 05:01:26.580
Dark Stalker twitched the chain, and

05:01:26.580 --> 05:01:28.319
Strong Wings stumbled back to his feet

05:01:28.319 --> 05:01:31.020
wings drooping as they marched inside.

05:01:31.080 --> 05:01:34.139
All 4 prisoners disappeared, into the

05:01:34.139 --> 05:01:36.000
forbidding gray block behind Dark

05:01:36.000 --> 05:01:36.540
Stalker.

05:01:36.599 --> 05:01:38.580
Glory shuddered.

05:01:38.639 --> 05:01:41.040
That was awful, she said.

05:01:41.099 --> 05:01:44.040
I always thought I'd like dispensing

05:01:44.040 --> 05:01:45.119
justice more than that.

05:01:45.180 --> 05:01:47.939
I wouldn't call that justice.

05:01:48.000 --> 05:01:49.799
Death bringer grumbled.

05:01:49.860 --> 05:01:52.319
We're looking for what brings peace to

05:01:52.319 --> 05:01:54.599
our rainforest, Glory pointed out.

05:01:54.720 --> 05:01:57.299
And for whatever gives dragons a chance

05:01:57.299 --> 05:01:58.380
to be their best selves.

05:01:58.500 --> 05:02:02.400
She hesitated. glancing around at anemone

05:02:02.400 --> 05:02:04.380
who had curled up drowsily under a

05:02:04.380 --> 05:02:05.159
mammoth fern.

05:02:05.220 --> 05:02:07.740
Something does feel weird, though.

05:02:07.799 --> 05:02:12.240
She added, in a lower voice, like, I'm

05:02:12.240 --> 05:02:14.220
not entirely sure I trust my decisions

05:02:14.220 --> 05:02:14.639
right now.

05:02:14.700 --> 05:02:18.180
She's feeling what Kibli felt.

05:02:18.240 --> 05:02:19.500
Turtle gassed.

05:02:19.560 --> 05:02:23.279
Torn between dark stalker's spell and

05:02:23.279 --> 05:02:24.659
what her own intelligence is telling

05:02:24.659 --> 05:02:24.900
her.

05:02:24.959 --> 05:02:28.380
Dark Stalker emerged from the prison

05:02:28.380 --> 05:02:30.720
closing the heavy metal door with a grim

05:02:30.720 --> 05:02:32.040
clunk behind him.

05:02:32.099 --> 05:02:35.099
Turtle noticed that he didn't return the

05:02:35.099 --> 05:02:37.200
keys to glory, but neither did she ask

05:02:37.200 --> 05:02:37.560
for them.

05:02:37.619 --> 05:02:41.639
Now that's taken care of, he said.

05:02:41.700 --> 05:02:43.860
And your life has been saved and

05:02:43.860 --> 05:02:44.159
everything.

05:02:44.220 --> 05:02:46.560
I'll return to my tribe and get some

05:02:46.560 --> 05:02:46.860
sleep.

05:02:46.979 --> 05:02:49.020
We have a long flight ahead in the

05:02:49.020 --> 05:02:49.200
morning.

05:02:49.319 --> 05:02:52.560
Thank you, Glory said.

05:02:52.619 --> 05:02:55.740
A little reluctantly, Turtle thought, or

05:02:55.740 --> 05:02:56.880
maybe he just hoped so.

05:02:56.939 --> 05:03:01.619
Cheer up, Your Majesty, Dark Stalker said

05:03:01.619 --> 05:03:02.220
cheerfully.

05:03:02.279 --> 05:03:04.319
We stopped some bad guys tonight.

05:03:04.380 --> 05:03:05.939
Isn't that fantastic?

05:03:06.000 --> 05:03:08.520
Just think, what kind of teamwork?

05:03:08.639 --> 05:03:10.560
Our tribes might have ahead of us.

05:03:10.619 --> 05:03:14.759
Wait, said Death Bringer, tilting his

05:03:14.759 --> 05:03:14.880
head.

05:03:15.000 --> 05:03:17.400
Didn't you say there were 5 dragons

05:03:17.400 --> 05:03:18.599
coming to attack glory tonight?

05:03:18.659 --> 05:03:20.819
Why were there only 4 prisoners?

05:03:20.880 --> 05:03:24.240
Was that a moment of hesitation from Dark

05:03:24.240 --> 05:03:24.779
Stalker?

05:03:24.840 --> 05:03:28.139
I didn't want to alarm you.

05:03:28.259 --> 05:03:29.819
He said slowly.

05:03:29.880 --> 05:03:33.180
There was a 3rd sandwing.

05:03:33.240 --> 05:03:37.020
But he fought back, and I was forced to

05:03:37.020 --> 05:03:37.259
kill him.

05:03:37.319 --> 05:03:41.099
If that's true, he did it very quickly.

05:03:41.159 --> 05:03:43.560
Turtle thought, and silently.

05:03:43.619 --> 05:03:46.799
Oh said Deathbringer.

05:03:46.860 --> 05:03:47.939
Well, good.

05:03:48.000 --> 05:03:51.779
That's unfortunate, said Glory at the

05:03:51.779 --> 05:03:52.380
same time.

05:03:52.439 --> 05:03:54.419
We should find out his name from the

05:03:54.419 --> 05:03:54.779
other two.

05:03:54.840 --> 05:03:57.180
I'm sure Queen Thorn will want that

05:03:57.180 --> 05:03:57.540
information.

05:03:57.659 --> 05:03:59.759
Indeed.

05:03:59.819 --> 05:04:04.080
Very wise, said Dark Stalker, nodding, and

05:04:04.080 --> 05:04:05.340
I'll take care of the body for you.

05:04:05.400 --> 05:04:05.939
Don't worry.

05:04:06.000 --> 05:04:09.060
Can't get you jabbed turtle in the side

05:04:09.060 --> 05:04:11.580
and he nearly jumped out of his scales.

05:04:11.639 --> 05:04:14.819
Lying, she whispered, pointing one clawed

05:04:14.819 --> 05:04:17.400
dark stalker, lying, lying, super liar.

05:04:17.459 --> 05:04:20.639
He agreed with her, but he couldn't see

05:04:20.639 --> 05:04:21.479
the point of this lie.

05:04:21.540 --> 05:04:24.060
What was Dark Stalker hiding now?

05:04:24.119 --> 05:04:26.159
Very well.

05:04:26.220 --> 05:04:29.340
We'll see you in the morning, said Glory

05:04:29.340 --> 05:04:30.659
spreading her wings.

05:04:30.779 --> 05:04:32.700
She and Deathbringer flew off to the

05:04:32.700 --> 05:04:35.099
treetops, leaving Dark Stalker and

05:04:35.099 --> 05:04:37.080
Anemone alone in the dying glow of the

05:04:37.080 --> 05:04:37.500
embers.

05:04:37.560 --> 05:04:40.500
Dark Stalker looked down at the sleeping

05:04:40.500 --> 05:04:41.939
sea wing princess.

05:04:42.000 --> 05:04:44.819
Something glinted in his eyes, something

05:04:44.819 --> 05:04:46.680
that made turtle want to throw hiding

05:04:46.680 --> 05:04:49.259
spells all over his sister, no matter the

05:04:49.259 --> 05:04:49.799
risk.

05:04:50.040 --> 05:04:52.439
He crouched closer to the damp earth

05:04:52.439 --> 05:04:56.159
wishing he were smarter, braver, bolder.

05:04:56.279 --> 05:04:58.919
Really any other kind of dragon than the

05:04:58.919 --> 05:04:59.459
kind he was.

05:04:59.520 --> 05:05:02.520
Not much longer, princess.

05:05:02.580 --> 05:05:04.619
Dark Stalker whispered.

05:05:04.680 --> 05:05:05.819
Soon.

05:05:05.880 --> 05:05:08.159
It'll be your turn to change the world.

05:05:08.220 --> 05:05:13.020
Chapter 15.

05:05:13.319 --> 05:05:17.340
Turtle and Kinkaju spent the night in the

05:05:17.340 --> 05:05:19.319
healing pavilion, where the healers were

05:05:19.319 --> 05:05:21.419
pinkly at Twitter with Delight when they

05:05:21.419 --> 05:05:22.860
discovered Kinkaju was awake.

05:05:22.979 --> 05:05:25.259
While they checked her for any remaining

05:05:25.259 --> 05:05:27.779
injuries, and freaked out when they found

05:05:27.779 --> 05:05:30.119
none, Turtle wrote another note to

05:05:30.119 --> 05:05:30.779
Kibley.

05:05:30.840 --> 05:05:34.080
Kinkaju is awake and fine.

05:05:34.139 --> 05:05:35.939
Please tell Tamarin.

05:05:36.060 --> 05:05:39.000
Dark stalker taking the tribe to the old

05:05:39.000 --> 05:05:40.319
knife kingdom in the morning.

05:05:40.380 --> 05:05:42.959
He thought for a moment, then added

05:05:42.959 --> 05:05:45.900
Everyone definitely under his spell

05:05:45.900 --> 05:05:47.580
except Kinkachoo.

05:05:47.639 --> 05:05:50.759
He hoped that was enough information as

05:05:50.759 --> 05:05:52.799
he erased it, although he wasn't sure

05:05:52.799 --> 05:05:54.540
what good it did for Kibli to know all

05:05:54.540 --> 05:05:54.720
that.

05:05:54.720 --> 05:05:57.900
Before he fell asleep, Turtle made

05:05:57.900 --> 05:06:00.599
Kinkaju promised not to go deal with dark

05:06:00.599 --> 05:06:01.979
stalker without him.

05:06:02.040 --> 05:06:03.900
However, she might interpret that

05:06:03.900 --> 05:06:04.380
phrase.

05:06:04.439 --> 05:06:07.860
No sneaking, stealing, attacking

05:06:07.860 --> 05:06:09.900
thwacking, or pineapples.

05:06:09.959 --> 05:06:13.020
He begged He also asked her not to tell

05:06:13.020 --> 05:06:14.279
Queen Glory anything.

05:06:14.340 --> 05:06:16.740
I have to let her know I'm all right.

05:06:16.799 --> 05:06:18.360
Kinkaju insisted.

05:06:18.419 --> 05:06:21.840
That's fine, he said, but don't say

05:06:21.840 --> 05:06:24.240
anything about me, or our suspicions

05:06:24.240 --> 05:06:26.580
about Dark Stalker, or how much you know

05:06:26.580 --> 05:06:28.319
about it, or what we might do next.

05:06:28.439 --> 05:06:32.400
Jumping poison frogs, Kingaju said

05:06:32.400 --> 05:06:33.840
looking exasperated.

05:06:33.900 --> 05:06:34.619
Why not?

05:06:34.740 --> 05:06:37.919
Because he can read Glory's mind.

05:06:38.040 --> 05:06:40.619
Turtle pointed out, and we don't want him

05:06:40.619 --> 05:06:42.180
to hear anything that might make him

05:06:42.180 --> 05:06:43.500
nervous or suspicious.

05:06:43.560 --> 05:06:47.340
After much arguing, she agreed, and

05:06:47.340 --> 05:06:49.860
Turtle fell asleep, feeling maybe a tiny

05:06:49.860 --> 05:06:52.200
iota less nervous than before.

05:06:52.200 --> 05:06:55.740
At daybreak, Kingachu woke him, and they

05:06:55.740 --> 05:06:57.119
flew to the night wing village.

05:06:57.180 --> 05:07:00.540
As they soared through the trees, Kinkachu

05:07:00.540 --> 05:07:02.639
tossed mangoes and bananas to turtle

05:07:02.639 --> 05:07:03.840
chattering busily.

05:07:03.900 --> 05:07:07.200
I visited my close personal friend, Queen

05:07:07.200 --> 05:07:09.900
Glory last night, she said, just to let

05:07:09.900 --> 05:07:11.400
her know I'm totally fine now.

05:07:11.459 --> 05:07:16.380
She was so mad and so happy and so mad at

05:07:16.380 --> 05:07:16.860
the same time.

05:07:16.919 --> 05:07:19.979
I got a seriously serious lecture about

05:07:19.979 --> 05:07:22.200
staying away from dangerous dragons from

05:07:22.200 --> 05:07:25.799
now on, la, la, la, irony, but she'll

05:07:25.799 --> 05:07:27.299
forgive me when we save the world, right?

05:07:27.360 --> 05:07:28.680
Right?

05:07:28.740 --> 05:07:30.419
Turtle?

05:07:30.479 --> 05:07:34.979
Oh yes, sure, he said, through a mouthful

05:07:34.979 --> 05:07:35.639
of banana.

05:07:35.700 --> 05:07:37.500
He hadn't realized this was a

05:07:37.500 --> 05:07:39.240
conversation he'd have to take an active

05:07:39.240 --> 05:07:39.659
pardon.

05:07:39.720 --> 05:07:42.840
I told her I want to go back to Jade

05:07:42.840 --> 05:07:45.119
Mountain, said Kinkaju, which is true.

05:07:45.180 --> 05:07:47.279
I do want to go back there.

05:07:47.340 --> 05:07:49.919
I'm just going to take a quick detour to

05:07:49.919 --> 05:07:52.380
the new Knight Kingdom on the way and not

05:07:52.380 --> 05:07:54.479
mention that part to her until later, like

05:07:54.479 --> 05:07:56.159
way much later.

05:07:56.279 --> 05:07:58.560
Like, maybe when we were 100.

05:07:58.799 --> 05:08:01.979
Do we have to go to the Night Kingdom?

05:08:01.979 --> 05:08:02.939
Turtle asked.

05:08:03.000 --> 05:08:05.400
Maybe there is another way to stop Dark

05:08:05.400 --> 05:08:06.060
Stalker.

05:08:06.119 --> 05:08:07.080
From here?

05:08:07.139 --> 05:08:10.919
No, I figured it out, Kinkachu said.

05:08:10.979 --> 05:08:13.500
I was thinking about it last night.

05:08:13.560 --> 05:08:15.720
This is all about Moon's prophecy.

05:08:15.779 --> 05:08:17.459
It's right there in the words.

05:08:17.520 --> 05:08:19.919
He's the thing that shakes the earth and

05:08:19.919 --> 05:08:21.000
scorches the ground.

05:08:21.060 --> 05:08:21.419
Right?

05:08:21.479 --> 05:08:24.360
So we have to save Jade Mountain by

05:08:24.360 --> 05:08:26.040
finding the lost city of night.

05:08:26.099 --> 05:08:28.860
And that's where Dark Stalker is going.

05:08:28.919 --> 05:08:31.319
So we just follow him there and boom

05:08:31.319 --> 05:08:33.000
catastrophe averted.

05:08:33.060 --> 05:08:33.900
Everybody safe.

05:08:34.020 --> 05:08:36.540
Why are you rubbing your forehead again?

05:08:36.659 --> 05:08:39.720
No reason, said Turtle.

05:08:39.779 --> 05:08:42.479
He'd read enough scrolls to know that no

05:08:42.479 --> 05:08:45.840
heroic quest was ever that easy, but he'd

05:08:45.840 --> 05:08:47.700
also spent enough time with Kinkaju to

05:08:47.700 --> 05:08:49.439
realize that it wouldn't do any good to

05:08:49.439 --> 05:08:49.919
tell her that.

05:08:49.979 --> 05:08:53.220
Dark Stalker had been busy in the night.

05:08:53.279 --> 05:08:55.560
When they arrived at the village, they

05:08:55.560 --> 05:08:57.900
discovered that he'd already packed, or

05:08:57.900 --> 05:09:00.840
made someone pack, several nets full of

05:09:00.840 --> 05:09:02.099
food from the rainforest.

05:09:02.159 --> 05:09:05.159
He stood on glory's platform, counting

05:09:05.159 --> 05:09:07.680
the supplies gathered below him as night

05:09:07.680 --> 05:09:09.779
wings gradually filled the clearing and

05:09:09.779 --> 05:09:11.700
whispering clumps of twos and threes.

05:09:11.759 --> 05:09:14.639
I wonder how many of them are going with

05:09:14.639 --> 05:09:17.700
him, Kinkaju said, swooping down to land

05:09:17.700 --> 05:09:18.840
at the back of the crowd.

05:09:18.900 --> 05:09:22.020
Turtle touched down beside her, folding

05:09:22.020 --> 05:09:24.000
in his wings and ducking his head, to

05:09:24.000 --> 05:09:25.740
avoid the funny looks he was getting from

05:09:25.740 --> 05:09:26.880
the rest of the night wings.

05:09:26.939 --> 05:09:30.060
I bet most of them, he said.

05:09:30.119 --> 05:09:32.400
Wouldn't you follow a king who could give

05:09:32.400 --> 05:09:33.299
you superpowers?

05:09:33.360 --> 05:09:37.439
No way, Kinkachu said, with fierce

05:09:37.439 --> 05:09:38.099
loyalty.

05:09:38.159 --> 05:09:39.840
Queen Glory is perfect.

05:09:39.900 --> 05:09:42.419
I want her to be my queen forever and

05:09:42.419 --> 05:09:42.959
always.

05:09:43.020 --> 05:09:46.860
Moon, she shrieked suddenly, spotting her

05:09:46.860 --> 05:09:48.540
claw mate as Moon passed by with her

05:09:48.540 --> 05:09:48.840
mother.

05:09:48.900 --> 05:09:51.840
Moon jumped nearly the height of a small

05:09:51.840 --> 05:09:53.400
tree and turned around.

05:09:53.459 --> 05:09:56.400
Her face lit up like a 1000 dragons

05:09:56.400 --> 05:09:57.959
shouting an aquatic at once.

05:09:58.020 --> 05:09:59.639
Kinkajou?

05:09:59.700 --> 05:10:00.419
She cried.

05:10:00.479 --> 05:10:03.299
They barreled into each other, wings

05:10:03.299 --> 05:10:06.240
overlapping in a ferocious hug, voices

05:10:06.240 --> 05:10:08.099
overlapping as they both tried to talk at

05:10:08.099 --> 05:10:08.700
once.

05:10:08.759 --> 05:10:10.139
You're awake.

05:10:10.200 --> 05:10:11.939
Moon yelped through tears.

05:10:12.000 --> 05:10:13.200
You're all right.

05:10:13.259 --> 05:10:14.459
I've been so worried.

05:10:14.520 --> 05:10:17.220
You did everything cool without me

05:10:17.220 --> 05:10:19.200
Kinkaju said at the same time.

05:10:19.259 --> 05:10:21.419
I can't believe all the amazing things

05:10:21.419 --> 05:10:23.220
you've been doing without me.

05:10:23.279 --> 05:10:26.159
I was going to come check on you today

05:10:26.159 --> 05:10:27.360
Moon said.

05:10:27.419 --> 05:10:28.380
Wiping her eyes.

05:10:28.439 --> 05:10:31.619
After dog stalker leaves, I would have

05:10:31.619 --> 05:10:33.900
come yesterday, but I've been busy trying

05:10:33.900 --> 05:10:36.119
to convince as many night wings as I can

05:10:36.119 --> 05:10:38.279
to stay here in the rainforest.

05:10:38.340 --> 05:10:39.779
She sighed.

05:10:39.840 --> 05:10:42.419
I'm not exactly the best spokes dragon

05:10:42.419 --> 05:10:42.720
now.

05:10:42.840 --> 05:10:46.380
Nobody particularly liked me before, and

05:10:46.380 --> 05:10:48.360
they don't like me much better, now that

05:10:48.360 --> 05:10:50.939
I've returned with mind reading powers

05:10:50.939 --> 05:10:52.439
and the dark stalker.

05:10:52.500 --> 05:10:55.860
I like you enough to make up for 10,000

05:10:55.860 --> 05:10:57.000
grumpy dragons.

05:10:57.060 --> 05:10:58.619
Kinkachu promised.

05:10:58.680 --> 05:11:01.740
Moon smiled at her shyly, like that was

05:11:01.740 --> 05:11:02.819
still hard for her to believe.

05:11:02.880 --> 05:11:05.159
What did you tell them?

05:11:05.279 --> 05:11:06.419
Turtle asked.

05:11:06.479 --> 05:11:08.520
I thought you liked Dark Stalker.

05:11:08.639 --> 05:11:10.979
I do, Moon said.

05:11:11.040 --> 05:11:12.540
He's been great so far.

05:11:12.599 --> 05:11:15.119
But Queen Glory is the best thing to

05:11:15.119 --> 05:11:17.819
happen to this tribe in 2000 years.

05:11:17.880 --> 05:11:20.880
She's fair and generous, and she's given

05:11:20.880 --> 05:11:22.139
them a safe place to live.

05:11:22.200 --> 05:11:24.779
Nightwings have always been afraid of

05:11:24.779 --> 05:11:26.819
living somewhere the ice wings could find

05:11:26.819 --> 05:11:29.700
them, in case the old war flares up.

05:11:29.759 --> 05:11:32.040
The Queen Glory made sure there was a

05:11:32.040 --> 05:11:34.860
truce with Queen Glacier 1st thing, to

05:11:34.860 --> 05:11:35.819
keep the tribe safe.

05:11:35.939 --> 05:11:37.500
She shook her head.

05:11:37.560 --> 05:11:40.380
I think Queen Glory has proven herself to

05:11:40.380 --> 05:11:41.939
be a just and kind queen.

05:11:42.000 --> 05:11:44.939
We don't know anything about dark stalker

05:11:44.939 --> 05:11:46.560
or what kind of king he would be.

05:11:46.619 --> 05:11:49.259
I feel like this is all happening too

05:11:49.259 --> 05:11:49.680
fast.

05:11:49.740 --> 05:11:53.400
Turtle noticed that several night wings

05:11:53.400 --> 05:11:55.680
had edged closer, pretending not to

05:11:55.680 --> 05:11:57.900
listen, but clearly listening to Moon.

05:11:57.959 --> 05:12:02.759
And plus, also, Kingaju chimed in, don't

05:12:02.759 --> 05:12:04.680
forget the part where he's totally evil.

05:12:04.799 --> 05:12:06.959
Moon raised her eyebrows.

05:12:07.020 --> 05:12:10.979
He's not evil, she said, not like Scarlet

05:12:10.979 --> 05:12:11.580
was.

05:12:11.639 --> 05:12:14.099
If he were evil, wouldn't I have seen it

05:12:14.099 --> 05:12:14.759
in his thoughts?

05:12:14.819 --> 05:12:17.639
You've seen the thoughts he wanted you to

05:12:17.639 --> 05:12:19.380
see, said Kinkaju.

05:12:19.439 --> 05:12:20.040
Right?

05:12:20.099 --> 05:12:22.319
He can totally shield the rest of them

05:12:22.319 --> 05:12:22.979
can't he?

05:12:23.040 --> 05:12:24.599
The evil thoughts?

05:12:24.659 --> 05:12:27.299
Moon lifted her head to look over the

05:12:27.299 --> 05:12:28.619
crowd at Dark Stalker.

05:12:28.680 --> 05:12:31.799
He had his head bowed, and was absent

05:12:31.799 --> 05:12:34.020
mindedly shredding a mauve flower that

05:12:34.020 --> 05:12:35.400
had grown up at the edge of the stage.

05:12:35.459 --> 05:12:38.459
Maybe, she said.

05:12:38.520 --> 05:12:40.619
But I think he's really trying to help

05:12:40.619 --> 05:12:42.900
even if I wouldn't do it the way he's

05:12:42.900 --> 05:12:45.479
doing it, I think he just wants his try

05:12:45.479 --> 05:12:47.459
back, the way it was before.

05:12:47.520 --> 05:12:51.060
Kinkaju opened her mouth, and Turtles

05:12:51.060 --> 05:12:52.380
stood on her foot to hush her up.

05:12:52.439 --> 05:12:55.799
If moon were under a spell, telling her

05:12:55.799 --> 05:12:58.080
about it wouldn't do any good, it was

05:12:58.080 --> 05:12:59.700
encouraging, though, that she could

05:12:59.700 --> 05:13:02.459
choose glory over dark stalker, despite

05:13:02.459 --> 05:13:03.900
whatever spells he was using on her.

05:13:04.020 --> 05:13:07.020
Was Dark Stalker upset when you told

05:13:07.020 --> 05:13:07.380
him?

05:13:07.439 --> 05:13:08.159
He asked.

05:13:08.220 --> 05:13:12.060
He said he understands, she said, and

05:13:12.060 --> 05:13:13.680
that he expects me to change my mind.

05:13:13.740 --> 05:13:15.299
Ha!

05:13:15.360 --> 05:13:16.860
Not likely.

05:13:16.919 --> 05:13:18.540
Kinkatoo gave Moon another hug.

05:13:18.599 --> 05:13:20.819
So, what are you going to do now?

05:13:20.880 --> 05:13:23.220
Go back to school?

05:13:23.279 --> 05:13:25.080
Moon said with a sigh.

05:13:25.139 --> 05:13:27.959
It feels a little weird with everything

05:13:27.959 --> 05:13:28.560
happening.

05:13:28.619 --> 05:13:30.900
But that's what Queen Glory wants me to

05:13:30.900 --> 05:13:31.080
do.

05:13:31.139 --> 05:13:34.259
And that's where Kibli and Winter are, and

05:13:34.259 --> 05:13:35.459
you guys will be there too, right?

05:13:35.580 --> 05:13:37.020
Sure.

05:13:37.080 --> 05:13:38.279
Eventually.

05:13:38.340 --> 05:13:40.439
But don't you want to see the old knight

05:13:40.439 --> 05:13:41.099
kingdom first?

05:13:41.159 --> 05:13:42.419
Kinkachu asked.

05:13:42.479 --> 05:13:44.880
Maybe just a quick visit before we go

05:13:44.880 --> 05:13:46.020
back to Jade Mountain?

05:13:46.080 --> 05:13:48.119
Why would we do that?

05:13:48.240 --> 05:13:49.259
Moon asked.

05:13:49.319 --> 05:13:50.520
No reason.

05:13:50.580 --> 05:13:52.860
Kinkatu glanced around and whispered

05:13:52.860 --> 05:13:56.220
loudly, except maybe a prophecy reason?

05:13:56.340 --> 05:13:59.819
Moon flicked a fat green beetle off her

05:13:59.819 --> 05:14:01.799
tail and tipped her head at Kinkaju.

05:14:01.919 --> 05:14:05.459
I kind of do want to see it, she said.

05:14:05.580 --> 05:14:08.700
I mean, I have been thinking about the

05:14:08.700 --> 05:14:11.340
prophecy, but I don't understand how

05:14:11.340 --> 05:14:13.080
going there will stop anything from

05:14:13.080 --> 05:14:13.500
happening.

05:14:13.560 --> 05:14:17.159
You never know until you try, Kinkaju

05:14:17.159 --> 05:14:17.759
said brightly.

05:14:17.819 --> 05:14:19.319
That's settled then.

05:14:19.380 --> 05:14:22.200
We'll all go to the Night Kingdom, not

05:14:22.200 --> 05:14:24.180
with Dark Stalker, though.

05:14:24.240 --> 05:14:25.919
Definitely not with him.

05:14:25.979 --> 05:14:28.439
More like, right behind him.

05:14:28.500 --> 05:14:29.040
Yes?

05:14:29.099 --> 05:14:30.060
Yes.

05:14:30.180 --> 05:14:30.840
Settled.

05:14:30.900 --> 05:14:31.619
Woo!

05:14:31.740 --> 05:14:33.900
I thought it was going to be much weirder

05:14:33.900 --> 05:14:36.479
to try explaining why I was in the Night

05:14:36.479 --> 05:14:38.880
Kingdom, but if I'm there with you, my

05:14:38.880 --> 05:14:41.400
gifted and awesome clawmate, then it

05:14:41.400 --> 05:14:42.000
makes total sense.

05:14:42.060 --> 05:14:44.279
I'm not sure.

05:14:44.340 --> 05:14:47.580
Moon began, but the crowd suddenly parted

05:14:47.580 --> 05:14:50.159
and Dark Stalker came striding through

05:14:50.159 --> 05:14:52.080
straight toward their little group.

05:14:52.139 --> 05:14:55.080
Turtle felt himself shrinking as the

05:14:55.080 --> 05:14:56.700
Nightwing loomed over them.

05:14:56.759 --> 05:14:59.400
Kinkaju, on the other talon, seemed to be

05:14:59.400 --> 05:15:00.840
trying to make herself look bigger.

05:15:00.900 --> 05:15:03.240
She spread her wings and puffed up her

05:15:03.240 --> 05:15:05.759
chest, and fixed dark stalker with her

05:15:05.759 --> 05:15:06.599
fiercest stare.

05:15:06.659 --> 05:15:10.979
Moon, Dark Stalker said quietly.

05:15:11.040 --> 05:15:13.200
Lost chance.

05:15:13.259 --> 05:15:14.400
Come with us.

05:15:14.520 --> 05:15:17.639
He hesitated, dipped his head toward her

05:15:17.639 --> 05:15:18.779
met her eyes.

05:15:18.840 --> 05:15:19.979
Please.

05:15:20.099 --> 05:15:23.040
Dark stalker, Moon said.

05:15:23.099 --> 05:15:24.360
You are my friend.

05:15:24.419 --> 05:15:27.540
You are, but glory is my queen.

05:15:27.599 --> 05:15:30.419
Then come as my friend.

05:15:30.540 --> 05:15:31.740
He said.

05:15:31.799 --> 05:15:33.540
I could use a friend there.

05:15:33.599 --> 05:15:36.900
And I know you will, soon, anyway.

05:15:36.959 --> 05:15:39.419
I've had visions of us flying around the

05:15:39.419 --> 05:15:40.259
night kingdom together.

05:15:40.319 --> 05:15:44.939
Maybe soon, Moon said, but not this way.

05:15:45.000 --> 05:15:47.639
She gestured at the dragons around them.

05:15:47.700 --> 05:15:50.099
I have to make my loyalty clear.

05:15:50.159 --> 05:15:53.220
All right, he said.

05:15:53.279 --> 05:15:56.279
All right, it's up to you.

05:15:56.340 --> 05:15:57.720
But come soon.

05:15:57.779 --> 05:16:00.119
I'll be there, waiting for you.

05:16:00.180 --> 05:16:03.119
He leaned down and bummed noses with her

05:16:03.119 --> 05:16:05.400
then turned and strode briskly back to

05:16:05.400 --> 05:16:06.000
the platform.

05:16:06.060 --> 05:16:09.840
Standing behind him, revealed by his exit

05:16:09.840 --> 05:16:10.979
was anemone.

05:16:11.040 --> 05:16:13.919
She lifted her snout haughtily at Moon.

05:16:13.979 --> 05:16:15.959
You don't deserve his friendship.

05:16:16.020 --> 05:16:17.639
You're not loyal at all.

05:16:17.759 --> 05:16:20.580
I say never come to the knight kingdom.

05:16:20.639 --> 05:16:22.380
He'll be better off without you.

05:16:22.500 --> 05:16:25.380
She stuck out her tongue and stomped

05:16:25.380 --> 05:16:25.560
away.

05:16:25.619 --> 05:16:27.599
Sorry about my sister.

05:16:27.659 --> 05:16:30.000
Turtles said sheepishly.

05:16:30.060 --> 05:16:31.740
She doesn't like competing for

05:16:31.740 --> 05:16:32.700
attention.

05:16:32.759 --> 05:16:33.540
She's not used to it.

05:16:33.599 --> 05:16:37.560
She can have all his attention if you ask

05:16:37.560 --> 05:16:39.240
me, Kinkachu said.

05:16:39.360 --> 05:16:41.700
Turtle looked sideways at Moon.

05:16:41.819 --> 05:16:44.520
Her face was somber, but resolved.

05:16:44.580 --> 05:16:48.060
If Moon were under Dark Stalker's control

05:16:48.060 --> 05:16:49.439
then Dark Stalker wouldn't have had to

05:16:49.439 --> 05:16:50.400
plead with her to come with him.

05:16:50.459 --> 05:16:52.439
She wouldn't have been able to say no.

05:16:52.500 --> 05:16:55.740
Had she escaped his spell somehow?

05:16:55.799 --> 05:16:57.479
Or did it work differently on her?

05:16:57.540 --> 05:17:00.180
Or was this all a part of a larger plan

05:17:00.180 --> 05:17:01.319
of dark stalkers?

05:17:01.380 --> 05:17:03.299
Hello?

05:17:03.360 --> 05:17:05.459
My fellow night wings.

05:17:05.520 --> 05:17:08.279
Dark stalker boomed out over the crowd.

05:17:08.400 --> 05:17:10.139
Is everyone here?

05:17:10.200 --> 05:17:12.720
Are you ready to follow me to the

05:17:12.720 --> 05:17:13.919
greatest place in the world?

05:17:14.040 --> 05:17:16.860
He beckoned to a black dragon in the

05:17:16.860 --> 05:17:17.340
front row.

05:17:17.459 --> 05:17:20.279
She leaped up onto the platform, and

05:17:20.279 --> 05:17:22.259
Turtle realized that it was fierce

05:17:22.259 --> 05:17:22.740
teeth.

05:17:22.799 --> 05:17:26.459
Whoa, he whispered to Kinkaju.

05:17:26.520 --> 05:17:27.779
She's out of the jail already.

05:17:27.840 --> 05:17:29.880
Do you think glory knows?

05:17:29.939 --> 05:17:32.040
Kingaju hissed softly.

05:17:32.099 --> 05:17:34.979
Fierce teeth positioned herself at Dark

05:17:34.979 --> 05:17:37.979
Stalker's side, nudging anemone off to a

05:17:37.979 --> 05:17:39.959
corner of the platform, which earned her

05:17:39.959 --> 05:17:41.939
a glare from the sea wing princess.

05:17:42.000 --> 05:17:44.340
My new lieutenant.

05:17:44.400 --> 05:17:47.099
Fierce teeth will be organizing

05:17:47.099 --> 05:17:49.680
volunteers to carry our supplies.

05:17:49.740 --> 05:17:52.020
We'll have a feast when we get there.

05:17:52.139 --> 05:17:54.779
Wait until you see our kingdom.

05:17:54.840 --> 05:17:57.840
A murmur of excitement eddied around the

05:17:57.840 --> 05:17:58.139
tribe.

05:17:58.200 --> 05:18:01.200
Dark Stalker swept his wings wide to

05:18:01.200 --> 05:18:02.340
encompass the entire crowd.

05:18:02.400 --> 05:18:05.639
Our wonderful kingdom is not too far

05:18:05.639 --> 05:18:05.939
away.

05:18:06.000 --> 05:18:09.540
Our glorious future is on the horizon.

05:18:09.599 --> 05:18:11.880
Come with me, night wings.

05:18:12.000 --> 05:18:15.419
He rose into the air, just as Glory and

05:18:15.419 --> 05:18:16.919
Death Bringer appeared from the trees.

05:18:16.979 --> 05:18:20.340
They swooped down to the platform, and

05:18:20.340 --> 05:18:21.659
looked up at him as he hovered above

05:18:21.659 --> 05:18:21.900
them.

05:18:21.959 --> 05:18:25.380
Time for all true night wings to go, Your

05:18:25.380 --> 05:18:25.860
Majesty.

05:18:25.979 --> 05:18:28.200
Dog Stalker said to Glory.

05:18:28.259 --> 05:18:30.959
Thank you for watching over them for me

05:18:30.959 --> 05:18:31.799
until I could get here.

05:18:31.860 --> 05:18:35.159
I wish you luck with your own tribe.

05:18:35.220 --> 05:18:39.000
He ascended into the sky, with powerful

05:18:39.000 --> 05:18:41.520
wing beats that shook the treetops, and

05:18:41.520 --> 05:18:43.080
dragons began to follow him.

05:18:43.259 --> 05:18:46.680
One by one, night wings lifted off, until

05:18:46.680 --> 05:18:49.080
the sky was full of beating black wings

05:18:49.080 --> 05:18:51.720
lashing tails, and flashing silver

05:18:51.720 --> 05:18:52.139
scales.

05:18:52.200 --> 05:18:55.439
The sound of the tribe in flight rolled

05:18:55.439 --> 05:18:56.939
like a thunderstorm across the

05:18:56.939 --> 05:18:57.540
rainforest.

05:18:57.599 --> 05:19:00.119
Turtle watched them in despair.

05:19:00.180 --> 05:19:02.880
He couldn't believe so many dragons had

05:19:02.880 --> 05:19:04.439
fallen for dark stalker already.

05:19:04.500 --> 05:19:06.599
Barely 3 days free.

05:19:06.659 --> 05:19:09.360
Dark Stalker now had an army at his claw

05:19:09.360 --> 05:19:11.459
tips, and an entire kingdom to serve

05:19:11.459 --> 05:19:11.700
him.

05:19:11.759 --> 05:19:14.880
He became more unstoppable with every

05:19:14.880 --> 05:19:15.479
passing moment.

05:19:15.540 --> 05:19:19.380
There's nothing we can do, he whispered.

05:19:19.439 --> 05:19:20.819
He's too powerful.

05:19:20.939 --> 05:19:25.439
But not all powerful, Kinkaju whispered

05:19:25.439 --> 05:19:26.580
back, nudging him.

05:19:26.639 --> 05:19:27.599
Look.

05:19:27.659 --> 05:19:30.060
She pointed to the night wings who were

05:19:30.060 --> 05:19:30.720
still on the ground.

05:19:30.779 --> 05:19:33.840
Moon and Deathbringer, of course, but

05:19:33.840 --> 05:19:36.840
also at least 50 others, including, to

05:19:36.840 --> 05:19:39.360
Turtle's surprise, Mighty Claus and his

05:19:39.360 --> 05:19:39.540
mother.

05:19:39.599 --> 05:19:42.900
I guess some of them actually like us

05:19:42.900 --> 05:19:44.700
Kinkaju said proudly.

05:19:44.759 --> 05:19:46.860
The smart ones can see how awesome it is

05:19:46.860 --> 05:19:47.099
here.

05:19:47.159 --> 05:19:50.880
Or they're just terrified of Dark Stalker

05:19:50.880 --> 05:19:52.380
Turtle suggested.

05:19:52.439 --> 05:19:54.180
Kingaju whacked him with her tail.

05:19:54.240 --> 05:19:57.299
Still, compared to the mass exodus

05:19:57.299 --> 05:19:59.520
overhead, what remained was nothing that

05:19:59.520 --> 05:20:00.599
could be called a tribe.

05:20:00.659 --> 05:20:04.080
The few night wings left, shuffled closer

05:20:04.080 --> 05:20:06.779
together, glancing around, as though the

05:20:06.779 --> 05:20:08.459
forest had suddenly grown bigger and

05:20:08.459 --> 05:20:08.880
darker.

05:20:08.939 --> 05:20:11.639
They looked like refugees from a

05:20:11.639 --> 05:20:12.000
disaster.

05:20:12.060 --> 05:20:13.919
Which they are.

05:20:13.979 --> 05:20:17.400
Turtle realized, from the disaster of the

05:20:17.400 --> 05:20:20.459
volcano first, and now, from the disaster

05:20:20.459 --> 05:20:22.200
of a king stealing their tribe.

05:20:22.319 --> 05:20:25.680
Maybe we should go back to Jade Mountain

05:20:25.680 --> 05:20:26.159
after all.

05:20:26.220 --> 05:20:29.159
Turtle said, a sense of hopelessness

05:20:29.159 --> 05:20:30.000
creeping over him.

05:20:30.119 --> 05:20:32.939
It's probably one of the safer places to

05:20:32.939 --> 05:20:35.159
be with tsunami and clay there.

05:20:35.279 --> 05:20:38.880
Until it falls beneath thunder and ice

05:20:38.880 --> 05:20:40.319
Kinkaju protested.

05:20:40.380 --> 05:20:42.779
Because we were too boring to save the

05:20:42.779 --> 05:20:43.080
world?

05:20:43.139 --> 05:20:44.880
No way, not me.

05:20:44.939 --> 05:20:46.619
You go if you want to.

05:20:46.680 --> 05:20:47.939
Moon and I can do everything.

05:20:48.000 --> 05:20:51.419
Um, I think a bit more definition of

05:20:51.419 --> 05:20:53.159
everything might be in order.

05:20:53.279 --> 05:20:56.220
Moon said, sounding a little alarmed.

05:20:56.279 --> 05:20:59.580
No, Turtle said glumly.

05:20:59.639 --> 05:21:00.959
I'm staying with you.

05:21:01.020 --> 05:21:02.159
I promised.

05:21:02.220 --> 05:21:04.860
Nice to see that you're completely

05:21:04.860 --> 05:21:07.560
thrilled about that, Kinkaju said with a

05:21:07.560 --> 05:21:07.799
laugh.

05:21:07.860 --> 05:21:09.180
Don't worry.

05:21:09.240 --> 05:21:10.259
I'm sure it won't take long.

05:21:10.319 --> 05:21:12.599
We'll be back at school learning math in

05:21:12.599 --> 05:21:13.080
no time.

05:21:13.139 --> 05:21:15.119
How does she do that?

05:21:15.240 --> 05:21:16.680
Turtle wondered.

05:21:16.740 --> 05:21:19.020
How can she look at the same exact thing

05:21:19.020 --> 05:21:22.680
I'm looking at, but think, oh, here's a

05:21:22.680 --> 05:21:23.580
problem I can solve.

05:21:23.639 --> 05:21:26.400
Instead of everything is hopeless.

05:21:26.459 --> 05:21:29.580
They waited until later in the morning to

05:21:29.580 --> 05:21:29.880
leave.

05:21:29.939 --> 05:21:32.759
Moon and Kinkaju said their goodbyes to

05:21:32.759 --> 05:21:35.220
glory, and mighty Claus told them he'd

05:21:35.220 --> 05:21:36.599
meet them back at school in a few days.

05:21:36.659 --> 05:21:39.240
Fearless and mind reader and their

05:21:39.240 --> 05:21:42.060
families had gone with Dark Stalker, and

05:21:42.060 --> 05:21:43.560
Glory wasn't sure whether they'd be

05:21:43.560 --> 05:21:44.759
returning to Jade Mountain.

05:21:44.880 --> 05:21:47.459
Turtle wrote another note to Kibley.

05:21:47.520 --> 05:21:51.119
Kingaju Moon and I are following Dark

05:21:51.119 --> 05:21:53.520
Stalker to Night Kingdom, hopefully back

05:21:53.520 --> 05:21:54.180
at school soon.

05:21:54.240 --> 05:21:57.900
That was some advanced wishful thinking

05:21:57.900 --> 05:21:58.200
there.

05:21:58.259 --> 05:22:01.200
But maybe, if he wrote it down, it would

05:22:01.200 --> 05:22:01.979
end up coming true.

05:22:02.040 --> 05:22:04.979
He brushed his talons over the slate

05:22:04.979 --> 05:22:07.020
remembering how he used to write down

05:22:07.020 --> 05:22:09.479
everything, every passing idea or

05:22:09.479 --> 05:22:12.180
observation, as though they were pools of

05:22:12.180 --> 05:22:13.979
genius he had to capture before they

05:22:13.979 --> 05:22:14.700
evaporated.

05:22:14.759 --> 05:22:17.459
He liked the feeling of the slate pencil

05:22:17.459 --> 05:22:18.360
in his claws again.

05:22:18.419 --> 05:22:22.139
Maybe if I survive all of this, I could

05:22:22.139 --> 05:22:22.799
try writing again.

05:22:22.860 --> 05:22:26.459
It wasn't hard to follow Dark Stalker and

05:22:26.459 --> 05:22:27.000
the Night Wings.

05:22:27.060 --> 05:22:28.919
Even with half a morning's lead.

05:22:28.979 --> 05:22:31.380
The tribe in flight was like a dark cloud

05:22:31.380 --> 05:22:32.520
in the sky ahead of them.

05:22:32.580 --> 05:22:35.279
At one point, as they flew through the

05:22:35.279 --> 05:22:37.680
mountains, Turtle looked down and spotted

05:22:37.680 --> 05:22:39.599
what appeared to be a small abandoned

05:22:39.599 --> 05:22:40.979
scavenger encampment.

05:22:40.979 --> 05:22:43.020
He imagined being one of those little

05:22:43.020 --> 05:22:45.720
creatures, looking up to see literally

05:22:45.720 --> 05:22:48.419
100s of dragons suddenly thundering by

05:22:48.419 --> 05:22:49.139
overhead.

05:22:49.200 --> 05:22:51.900
If he were one of them, he'd find a rock

05:22:51.900 --> 05:22:53.819
to hide under and stay there for the next

05:22:53.819 --> 05:22:54.060
month.

05:22:54.119 --> 05:22:57.360
Dark Stalker led them south of Jade

05:22:57.360 --> 05:22:59.520
Mountain, over the delta where the

05:22:59.520 --> 05:23:01.439
winding Tail River spilled into the

05:23:01.439 --> 05:23:03.659
Southern Sea and westward along the

05:23:03.659 --> 05:23:04.380
coast.

05:23:04.439 --> 05:23:07.439
Below them, waves pounded against a rocky

05:23:07.439 --> 05:23:09.959
shoreline, and the ocean was dark gray

05:23:09.959 --> 05:23:12.119
with hints of brilliant green where the

05:23:12.119 --> 05:23:12.779
sun slipped through.

05:23:12.900 --> 05:23:15.900
Turtle couldn't help thinking how easy it

05:23:15.900 --> 05:23:18.000
would be to dive into those waves.

05:23:18.060 --> 05:23:20.700
He could disappear into the watery depths

05:23:20.700 --> 05:23:22.919
and leave all these dangers behind.

05:23:22.979 --> 05:23:26.279
But he looked over at Kinkaju's gray blue

05:23:26.279 --> 05:23:29.520
sky scales, and determined expression, and

05:23:29.520 --> 05:23:31.319
he knew he couldn't leave her.

05:23:31.380 --> 05:23:34.080
Dark stalker flew without stopping.

05:23:34.139 --> 05:23:35.880
And so the tribe did too.

05:23:35.939 --> 05:23:38.819
Although as the day wore on, they became

05:23:38.819 --> 05:23:41.340
more spread out across the sky, with the

05:23:41.340 --> 05:23:43.259
weakest flyers dropping farther and

05:23:43.259 --> 05:23:43.919
farther behind.

05:23:44.040 --> 05:23:47.279
The landscape along the coast shifted

05:23:47.279 --> 05:23:50.159
from mountains to scrub covered hills, and

05:23:50.159 --> 05:23:52.200
then desert as they reached the southern

05:23:52.200 --> 05:23:53.459
edge of the kingdom of sand.

05:23:53.520 --> 05:23:56.939
The wind up this high was chilly, but the

05:23:56.939 --> 05:23:58.500
sun beat down mercilessly on their

05:23:58.500 --> 05:23:58.799
scales.

05:23:58.860 --> 05:24:02.220
Turtle tried to remember the map of Pyre

05:24:02.220 --> 05:24:03.900
in his head, so he could figure out where

05:24:03.900 --> 05:24:04.319
they were going.

05:24:04.380 --> 05:24:06.720
There wasn't anything in this direction

05:24:06.720 --> 05:24:10.200
except more sand, as far as he knew, and

05:24:10.200 --> 05:24:11.220
then the Western Ocean.

05:24:11.279 --> 05:24:12.720
Another island?

05:24:12.720 --> 05:24:15.419
The sun was slipping down the sky ahead

05:24:15.419 --> 05:24:18.060
of them, shining right into turtles' eyes

05:24:18.060 --> 05:24:20.520
when Dark Stalker suddenly dove toward

05:24:20.520 --> 05:24:23.220
the land, like a flock of hungry crows

05:24:23.220 --> 05:24:25.259
the night wings swept after him.

05:24:25.319 --> 05:24:28.500
Turtle sensed moon hesitating beside

05:24:28.500 --> 05:24:28.860
him.

05:24:28.919 --> 05:24:30.779
I don't want to join them.

05:24:30.840 --> 05:24:33.180
She explained, when she caught him

05:24:33.180 --> 05:24:33.720
looking at her.

05:24:33.779 --> 05:24:36.240
I don't want them to think I've chosen

05:24:36.240 --> 05:24:37.080
Dark Stalker.

05:24:37.139 --> 05:24:38.700
This is just a visit.

05:24:38.759 --> 05:24:41.159
I don't want to hang out with those

05:24:41.159 --> 05:24:44.459
dragons either, Kinkaju said firmly, or

05:24:44.459 --> 05:24:46.319
listen to another endless windbag

05:24:46.319 --> 05:24:46.799
speech.

05:24:46.860 --> 05:24:48.900
Let's find a spot to sleep where they

05:24:48.900 --> 05:24:49.500
can't see us.

05:24:49.560 --> 05:24:51.900
But where are they going?

05:24:51.959 --> 05:24:54.659
Turtle asked, screening his eyes and

05:24:54.659 --> 05:24:55.740
squinting west.

05:24:55.799 --> 05:24:56.939
Why stop now?

05:24:57.000 --> 05:24:58.740
How much farther can it be?

05:24:58.799 --> 05:25:02.220
I have no idea, Moon answered.

05:25:02.279 --> 05:25:04.439
They both hovered in the air for a moment

05:25:04.439 --> 05:25:07.319
watching the faraway cloud of night wings

05:25:07.319 --> 05:25:09.840
settle across the dunes and pebbled beach

05:25:09.840 --> 05:25:11.939
like a black carpet flung over the

05:25:11.939 --> 05:25:12.119
ground.

05:25:12.180 --> 05:25:15.659
Kinkachu found a small cave facing the

05:25:15.659 --> 05:25:17.639
ocean, that the 3 of them could just

05:25:17.639 --> 05:25:20.340
barely squeeze into, and Moon caught them

05:25:20.340 --> 05:25:21.180
a few crabs to eat.

05:25:21.240 --> 05:25:24.000
It was a relief to stop and rest his

05:25:24.000 --> 05:25:24.419
wings.

05:25:24.479 --> 05:25:26.819
Turtle immediately brought out his

05:25:26.819 --> 05:25:28.979
healing stone to erase the ache in his

05:25:28.979 --> 05:25:31.380
shoulders, but it also made Turtle

05:25:31.380 --> 05:25:34.139
anxious that he couldn't see Dark Stalker

05:25:34.139 --> 05:25:36.060
and he had no idea what the ancient

05:25:36.060 --> 05:25:37.080
animus would do next.

05:25:37.200 --> 05:25:39.479
What if he wasn't really leading the

05:25:39.479 --> 05:25:40.860
night wings to their old kingdom?

05:25:40.919 --> 05:25:43.439
What if he was planning to smash the

05:25:43.439 --> 05:25:45.060
entire tribe into a cliff?

05:25:45.119 --> 05:25:48.720
That delightfully morbid image wouldn't

05:25:48.720 --> 05:25:50.400
leave Turtle's brain as he tried to lie

05:25:50.400 --> 05:25:51.000
down and sleep.

05:25:51.060 --> 05:25:54.000
Moonlight poured into their cave from the

05:25:54.000 --> 05:25:56.099
night sky, and from the silver

05:25:56.099 --> 05:25:57.540
reflections in the sea below.

05:25:57.599 --> 05:26:00.060
Kinkaju and Moon already had their eyes

05:26:00.060 --> 05:26:02.459
closed, their tails intertwined.

05:26:02.520 --> 05:26:05.400
He wondered if he'd imagined it, that

05:26:05.400 --> 05:26:07.319
Kinkachu had maneuvered to be the one

05:26:07.319 --> 05:26:08.700
sleeping next to him.

05:26:08.759 --> 05:26:11.580
Her scales were warm, as though she'd

05:26:11.580 --> 05:26:13.020
been collecting sunshine in them all

05:26:13.020 --> 05:26:13.319
day.

05:26:13.380 --> 05:26:16.619
And in her sleep, they'd turned indigo

05:26:16.619 --> 05:26:18.959
and gold, with flecks of citrus green.

05:26:19.020 --> 05:26:23.099
Carefully, reluctantly, he eased himself

05:26:23.099 --> 05:26:25.919
away from Kinkajou's side and slid out of

05:26:25.919 --> 05:26:26.819
the cave onto the beach.

05:26:26.880 --> 05:26:30.360
Sand crumbled around his webbed talons

05:26:30.360 --> 05:26:33.060
and sharp edges of broken seashells poked

05:26:33.060 --> 05:26:33.360
his tail.

05:26:33.419 --> 05:26:36.000
The waves looked as though they were

05:26:36.000 --> 05:26:38.099
trying to reach out and drag him in.

05:26:38.159 --> 05:26:47.400
His, his, Safe, shh, Hi.

05:26:47.520 --> 05:26:51.060
He turned his head north, toward the

05:26:51.060 --> 05:26:52.740
night wing encampment, and watched.

05:26:52.799 --> 05:26:56.099
He did know how long he sat there, staring

05:26:56.099 --> 05:26:58.680
at that small patch of stars, but

05:26:58.680 --> 05:27:01.560
sometime later, he saw a vast shadow blot

05:27:01.560 --> 05:27:04.080
them out, then soar away west.

05:27:04.139 --> 05:27:08.700
Dark stalkers going somewhere, by himself

05:27:08.700 --> 05:27:12.479
in the middle of the night, which means I

05:27:12.479 --> 05:27:13.439
have to follow him.

05:27:13.500 --> 05:27:18.060
Part three.

05:27:18.180 --> 05:27:20.459
The Lost City of Night.

05:27:20.520 --> 05:27:24.419
Chapter 16.

05:27:24.659 --> 05:27:28.560
Turtle glanced up the beach at the cave

05:27:28.560 --> 05:27:30.959
where his friends slept, but this was

05:27:30.959 --> 05:27:32.099
just a spying mission.

05:27:32.159 --> 05:27:35.040
He was the only one dark stalker couldn't

05:27:35.040 --> 05:27:38.580
see, whereas, if dark stalker caught moon

05:27:38.580 --> 05:27:40.619
and kinkaju trailing after him in the

05:27:40.619 --> 05:27:42.540
middle of the night, there would be some

05:27:42.540 --> 05:27:45.659
explaining to do, insignificance spell or

05:27:45.659 --> 05:27:47.400
no insignificance spell.

05:27:47.459 --> 05:27:50.220
He rose into the air and followed Dark

05:27:50.220 --> 05:27:52.560
Stalker, feeling as if his heart and

05:27:52.560 --> 05:27:53.880
stomach had traded places.

05:27:53.939 --> 05:27:57.240
Don't be a coward, he scolded himself.

05:27:57.299 --> 05:28:00.299
This is nothing. eavesdropping with a

05:28:00.299 --> 05:28:02.700
cloak of invisibility, sneaking around

05:28:02.700 --> 05:28:04.500
which is the one thing you're good at.

05:28:04.560 --> 05:28:07.919
He thought of peril's fierce lack of

05:28:07.919 --> 05:28:10.139
stealth, the way she always made the most

05:28:10.139 --> 05:28:13.080
noise, or picked a fight, or accidentally

05:28:13.080 --> 05:28:13.799
blew something up.

05:28:13.860 --> 05:28:15.540
He missed her.

05:28:15.599 --> 05:28:17.400
He wondered what she was doing now.

05:28:17.459 --> 05:28:20.580
Their adventure together, setting out to

05:28:20.580 --> 05:28:23.099
stop Scarlet, and find the rest of Jade

05:28:23.099 --> 05:28:25.439
Winglet, had felt a lot safer and more

05:28:25.439 --> 05:28:26.220
fun than this.

05:28:26.279 --> 05:28:29.279
Maybe because he'd known her fire scales

05:28:29.279 --> 05:28:31.740
could protect him, or because his magic

05:28:31.740 --> 05:28:33.119
had still been a secret from everyone

05:28:33.119 --> 05:28:33.659
back then.

05:28:33.720 --> 05:28:37.500
The 3 moons lit up a ridge of jagged

05:28:37.500 --> 05:28:39.299
mountains stabbing into the clouds ahead

05:28:39.299 --> 05:28:39.599
of them.

05:28:39.720 --> 05:28:43.500
For a moment, Turtle was disoriented, and

05:28:43.500 --> 05:28:44.580
he turned to look back over his

05:28:44.580 --> 05:28:44.939
shoulder.

05:28:45.000 --> 05:28:48.060
But no, there were the claws of the

05:28:48.060 --> 05:28:49.380
clouds mountains behind him.

05:28:49.439 --> 05:28:52.560
The ones up ahead, rose out of the desert

05:28:52.560 --> 05:28:55.200
like a wall made of shark's teeth, ending

05:28:55.200 --> 05:28:56.700
at sheer cliffs along the ocean.

05:28:56.759 --> 05:29:00.720
Oh, turtle thought, remembering the map

05:29:00.720 --> 05:29:01.560
of Pyria.

05:29:01.619 --> 05:29:04.020
There was a small peninsula that jutted

05:29:04.020 --> 05:29:05.520
out at the southwest corner of the

05:29:05.520 --> 05:29:06.180
kingdom of sand.

05:29:06.240 --> 05:29:09.299
If the continent was a dragon, and that

05:29:09.299 --> 05:29:11.880
peninsula was a talon reaching out, these

05:29:11.880 --> 05:29:13.919
mountains were sort of like turtle's

05:29:13.919 --> 05:29:14.340
armband.

05:29:14.459 --> 05:29:17.580
And nobody has crossed them in 100s of

05:29:17.580 --> 05:29:17.759
years.

05:29:17.880 --> 05:29:19.259
Turtle wondered.

05:29:19.380 --> 05:29:21.360
They were quite forbidding.

05:29:21.419 --> 05:29:23.880
He wasn't sure he particularly wanted to

05:29:23.880 --> 05:29:24.720
cross them himself.

05:29:24.779 --> 05:29:28.259
But that was clearly where dark stalker

05:29:28.259 --> 05:29:28.560
was going.

05:29:28.619 --> 05:29:32.279
At one point, as they flew over land that

05:29:32.279 --> 05:29:33.419
began sloping up into hills.

05:29:33.479 --> 05:29:37.139
Turtle felt a sudden, buzzing shock, like

05:29:37.139 --> 05:29:38.939
he'd been accidentally grabbed by a baby

05:29:38.939 --> 05:29:40.080
electric eel.

05:29:40.139 --> 05:29:41.279
What was that?

05:29:41.400 --> 05:29:43.439
There was no way to know.

05:29:43.500 --> 05:29:44.880
And it was over in a moment.

05:29:44.939 --> 05:29:47.819
Turtle glanced uneasily down at the

05:29:47.819 --> 05:29:49.979
ground below him, and hoped he was

05:29:49.979 --> 05:29:52.500
imagining the pale flash of what looked

05:29:52.500 --> 05:29:54.299
like bones sticking out of the earth.

05:29:54.360 --> 05:29:58.080
Up ahead, dark stalker tipped his wings

05:29:58.080 --> 05:30:00.540
to soar high over the peaks, and turtle

05:30:00.540 --> 05:30:03.060
followed, gasping in the thin air.

05:30:03.119 --> 05:30:06.659
And there was the night kingdom.

05:30:06.779 --> 05:30:10.139
Spread out below them, outlined by

05:30:10.139 --> 05:30:12.540
moonlight, were the ruins of an ancient

05:30:12.540 --> 05:30:15.060
city that sprawled across the peninsula.

05:30:15.119 --> 05:30:18.299
Much of it was hidden within canyons and

05:30:18.299 --> 05:30:20.159
cliff faces, but at the foot of the

05:30:20.159 --> 05:30:22.979
mountain, partially built into it, stood

05:30:22.979 --> 05:30:26.099
a palace, or what was left of a palace.

05:30:26.159 --> 05:30:28.500
In front of it was an overgrown square

05:30:28.500 --> 05:30:31.319
paved in marble, and studded with bits of

05:30:31.319 --> 05:30:34.259
toppled columns, a kind of platform had

05:30:34.259 --> 05:30:36.299
collapsed in the center of it, and was

05:30:36.299 --> 05:30:38.700
nearly submerged in a wild tangle of

05:30:38.700 --> 05:30:39.119
vines.

05:30:39.240 --> 05:30:41.880
All around the square were more ruins.

05:30:41.939 --> 05:30:44.700
Once elegant buildings whose roofs had

05:30:44.700 --> 05:30:48.060
caved in, statues missing heads, talons

05:30:48.060 --> 05:30:49.619
tails, or all three.

05:30:49.680 --> 05:30:52.860
Sculptural details worn away by weather.

05:30:52.919 --> 05:30:56.400
Dark stalker's wing beats faltered, as he

05:30:56.400 --> 05:30:57.840
took in the devastation below him.

05:30:57.900 --> 05:31:01.439
He slowed to a stop, hovering outside the

05:31:01.439 --> 05:31:03.479
palace, staring down at the square.

05:31:03.599 --> 05:31:06.479
Bats flitted in and out of the windows

05:31:06.479 --> 05:31:09.360
behind him, like dark thoughts scattering

05:31:09.360 --> 05:31:09.720
into the air.

05:31:09.779 --> 05:31:14.159
He feels like he was just here, turtle

05:31:14.159 --> 05:31:14.520
guessed.

05:31:14.580 --> 05:31:18.000
It's like, if I returned to the kingdom

05:31:18.000 --> 05:31:20.220
of the sea tomorrow, and found that

05:31:20.220 --> 05:31:22.619
everything I knew my whole life has been

05:31:22.619 --> 05:31:25.979
destroyed, apparently overnight, and my

05:31:25.979 --> 05:31:28.619
tribe was scattered, weakened with no

05:31:28.619 --> 05:31:29.040
queen.

05:31:29.099 --> 05:31:32.759
And everyone I ever loved was dead.

05:31:32.819 --> 05:31:36.540
The giant knight wing put out one talon

05:31:36.540 --> 05:31:38.759
and touched the overgrown wall of the

05:31:38.759 --> 05:31:39.180
palace.

05:31:39.240 --> 05:31:42.540
Abruptly he turned, and flew toward one

05:31:42.540 --> 05:31:44.040
of the other stately buildings that

05:31:44.040 --> 05:31:44.880
flanked the square.

05:31:44.939 --> 05:31:48.060
Turtle spread his wings to follow, and

05:31:48.060 --> 05:31:50.700
felt a sudden strange chill along his

05:31:50.700 --> 05:31:53.099
spine, as though someone was watching

05:31:53.099 --> 05:31:53.459
him.

05:31:53.520 --> 05:31:56.939
He twisted in the air, searching the

05:31:56.939 --> 05:31:57.900
palace windows.

05:31:57.959 --> 05:32:00.360
Every shadow was full of eyes.

05:32:00.419 --> 05:32:03.119
Every stirring of air, the quiet breath

05:32:03.119 --> 05:32:04.319
of a hidden dragon.

05:32:04.380 --> 05:32:06.419
Was someone still living here?

05:32:06.479 --> 05:32:09.659
Had some night wings never left?

05:32:09.720 --> 05:32:11.040
All those 100s of years ago?

05:32:11.099 --> 05:32:14.819
But no one emerged, and no sound came

05:32:14.819 --> 05:32:16.139
from within the palace walls.

05:32:16.200 --> 05:32:18.659
Maybe he was imagining things.

05:32:18.720 --> 05:32:21.060
This place was creepy enough to make

05:32:21.060 --> 05:32:22.680
anyone's scales crawl.

05:32:22.799 --> 05:32:25.979
Turtle flue after dark stalker as fast as

05:32:25.979 --> 05:32:26.279
he could.

05:32:26.340 --> 05:32:28.860
At 1st he couldn't figure out what this

05:32:28.860 --> 05:32:29.459
new building was.

05:32:29.520 --> 05:32:32.700
It had at least 3 entrances, on different

05:32:32.700 --> 05:32:34.979
levels, although one was blocked by fall

05:32:34.979 --> 05:32:35.580
and rubble.

05:32:35.639 --> 05:32:39.299
Turtle also counted 5 towers, 3 of them

05:32:39.299 --> 05:32:41.580
half tumbled away, and a trickle that

05:32:41.580 --> 05:32:42.779
looked as though it might once have been

05:32:42.779 --> 05:32:43.319
a waterfall.

05:32:43.380 --> 05:32:46.259
Dark Stalker flew to the uppermost

05:32:46.259 --> 05:32:49.259
entrance and paced inside, ducking his

05:32:49.259 --> 05:32:51.060
head slightly to avoid cracking it on the

05:32:51.060 --> 05:32:51.900
high ceiling.

05:32:51.959 --> 05:32:55.319
And here, in the spiral hallways, there

05:32:55.319 --> 05:32:58.560
were clues, large rooms lined with tables

05:32:58.560 --> 05:33:01.740
broken slates on the floor, displays of

05:33:01.740 --> 05:33:04.200
awkward, crumbling clay statues that

05:33:04.200 --> 05:33:05.639
looked as though they'd been molded by

05:33:05.639 --> 05:33:06.479
dragonettes.

05:33:06.540 --> 05:33:08.279
Because they were.

05:33:08.340 --> 05:33:09.900
Turtle realized.

05:33:09.959 --> 05:33:11.580
This is a school.

05:33:11.639 --> 05:33:15.060
Why would Dark Stalker come to a ruined

05:33:15.060 --> 05:33:16.979
night wing school in the middle of the

05:33:16.979 --> 05:33:17.159
night?

05:33:17.220 --> 05:33:19.500
If he was searching for something of

05:33:19.500 --> 05:33:21.599
power, wouldn't it be at the palace?

05:33:21.659 --> 05:33:23.700
Or if he was looking for something of his

05:33:23.700 --> 05:33:26.459
own, something he missed, wouldn't it be

05:33:26.459 --> 05:33:28.560
wherever he used to live?

05:33:28.619 --> 05:33:32.580
Turtle realized that he had no idea how

05:33:32.580 --> 05:33:35.459
old Dark Stalker had been when Clearsight

05:33:35.459 --> 05:33:36.599
put the sleeping spell on him.

05:33:36.659 --> 05:33:39.840
He'd always imagined an older dragon

05:33:39.840 --> 05:33:41.939
close to the age of the queen he was

05:33:41.939 --> 05:33:42.599
trying to replace.

05:33:42.659 --> 05:33:45.720
Dark stalker stopped at a turn in the

05:33:45.720 --> 05:33:48.599
corridor, brushed aside cobwebs and dust

05:33:48.599 --> 05:33:50.340
and uncovered a painting.

05:33:50.400 --> 05:33:53.159
It was hard to make out the subject under

05:33:53.159 --> 05:33:55.740
the accumulated dirt of centuries, but

05:33:55.740 --> 05:33:57.180
Turtle thought it might have been a

05:33:57.180 --> 05:33:57.659
portrait of someone.

05:33:57.720 --> 05:34:00.779
Dark stalker traced to the outer edge of

05:34:00.779 --> 05:34:02.939
it with his claws for a moment, and then

05:34:02.939 --> 05:34:04.619
he put one talon on the center of the

05:34:04.619 --> 05:34:05.099
canvas.

05:34:05.159 --> 05:34:08.159
Senturies of dust swirled away in a

05:34:08.159 --> 05:34:10.500
sudden blast, making turtles' eyes

05:34:10.500 --> 05:34:10.799
water.

05:34:10.860 --> 05:34:14.040
He clapped his talons over a snout to

05:34:14.040 --> 05:34:15.360
stop himself from sneezing.

05:34:15.419 --> 05:34:18.119
When he looked up again, blinking away

05:34:18.119 --> 05:34:20.700
tears, he saw that dark stalker had used

05:34:20.700 --> 05:34:22.139
his magic to restore the painting.

05:34:22.200 --> 05:34:25.139
Now it looked the way it must have looked

05:34:25.139 --> 05:34:27.180
in his time, brand new.

05:34:27.240 --> 05:34:29.340
The colors and lines still sharp.

05:34:29.400 --> 05:34:32.580
It was a portrait of a female night wing

05:34:32.580 --> 05:34:35.819
seated with her wings folded back, gazing

05:34:35.819 --> 05:34:36.360
out at the viewer.

05:34:36.479 --> 05:34:39.540
Behind her, a web of fiery lines

05:34:39.540 --> 05:34:42.060
crisscrossed the sky, like a pattern in

05:34:42.060 --> 05:34:44.880
the stars, with smaller falling stars in

05:34:44.880 --> 05:34:45.659
between the lines.

05:34:45.720 --> 05:34:48.299
For the most part, it was not a great

05:34:48.299 --> 05:34:48.900
portrait.

05:34:49.020 --> 05:34:51.060
The proportions were all wrong

05:34:51.060 --> 05:34:54.240
particularly in the undersized talons and

05:34:54.240 --> 05:34:55.259
oversized head.

05:34:55.319 --> 05:34:57.840
But there was something in her eyes that

05:34:57.840 --> 05:34:58.799
made you look twice.

05:34:58.860 --> 05:35:01.979
Something that made you think this dragon

05:35:01.979 --> 05:35:03.299
truly loved the painter.

05:35:03.360 --> 05:35:05.880
Could that be Clearsight?

05:35:05.939 --> 05:35:07.259
Turtle wondered.

05:35:07.380 --> 05:35:10.200
Dark Stalker stared at her for a long

05:35:10.200 --> 05:35:12.900
moment before pulling himself away and

05:35:12.900 --> 05:35:13.979
continuing on.

05:35:14.040 --> 05:35:16.560
Turtle followed him through the spiraling

05:35:16.560 --> 05:35:18.659
labyrinth of the school, until finally

05:35:18.659 --> 05:35:20.400
they emerged in a central courtyard.

05:35:20.459 --> 05:35:23.400
Classrooms looked out on the courtyard on

05:35:23.400 --> 05:35:25.619
all sides, and it wasn't hard to imagine

05:35:25.619 --> 05:35:27.959
being a student here, eating lunch under

05:35:27.959 --> 05:35:30.240
the trees, or practicing your flying.

05:35:30.299 --> 05:35:33.180
Turtle had to navigate the tangles of

05:35:33.180 --> 05:35:35.340
vines, shrubs, and tall grass carefully

05:35:35.340 --> 05:35:37.020
to avoid getting stuck.

05:35:37.080 --> 05:35:40.560
The dark stalker's huge talons, crushed

05:35:40.560 --> 05:35:42.720
all the undergrowth in his path, as he

05:35:42.720 --> 05:35:45.180
strode to a spot under a towering pine

05:35:45.180 --> 05:35:45.540
tree.

05:35:45.599 --> 05:35:47.159
Here he stopped.

05:35:47.279 --> 05:35:48.779
He bowed his head.

05:35:48.840 --> 05:35:51.840
His wings slowly drifted down to droop

05:35:51.840 --> 05:35:52.500
beside him.

05:35:52.560 --> 05:35:54.720
Long heartbeats passed.

05:35:54.779 --> 05:35:57.000
What is he thinking about?

05:35:57.060 --> 05:35:58.439
Turtle wondered.

05:35:58.500 --> 05:36:00.959
And why here?

05:36:01.020 --> 05:36:04.560
He inched closer, although it made his

05:36:04.560 --> 05:36:06.959
scales run cold, to step through dark

05:36:06.959 --> 05:36:08.040
stalker's shadow.

05:36:08.099 --> 05:36:10.799
It was an eerie, unsettling kind of

05:36:10.799 --> 05:36:13.139
spying, to stand right in front of a

05:36:13.139 --> 05:36:15.419
dragon, and know he couldn't see you?

05:36:15.479 --> 05:36:18.419
Also that if he did, you'd be dead.

05:36:18.479 --> 05:36:21.840
A silver scale shone on Dark Stalker's

05:36:21.840 --> 05:36:24.360
face, then slipped down his snout to

05:36:24.360 --> 05:36:25.139
splash on the ground.

05:36:25.200 --> 05:36:30.180
Oh, Turtle realized, with an awful twist

05:36:30.180 --> 05:36:30.840
in his heart.

05:36:30.900 --> 05:36:32.580
He's crying.

05:36:32.639 --> 05:36:36.119
He did not know how to feel about that.

05:36:36.180 --> 05:36:38.639
Sympathy for dark stalker?

05:36:38.700 --> 05:36:40.200
He couldn't afford that.

05:36:40.259 --> 05:36:41.340
Could he?

05:36:41.400 --> 05:36:43.799
Not if he wanted to stay strong enough to

05:36:43.799 --> 05:36:44.220
stop him.

05:36:44.279 --> 05:36:48.479
But this is the real dark stalker.

05:36:48.540 --> 05:36:51.180
He's not performing for anyone right

05:36:51.180 --> 05:36:51.419
now.

05:36:51.479 --> 05:36:55.200
He's just really sad.

05:36:55.259 --> 05:36:58.919
Turtle glanced around, wishing he knew

05:36:58.919 --> 05:36:59.400
what to do.

05:36:59.459 --> 05:37:02.700
Here, perhaps, was a dragon who could be

05:37:02.700 --> 05:37:03.180
reasoned with.

05:37:03.240 --> 05:37:05.639
Here was a dragon who might tell the

05:37:05.639 --> 05:37:07.799
truth, if he had the right audience to

05:37:07.799 --> 05:37:08.340
say it to.

05:37:08.400 --> 05:37:11.880
That idea, combined with the eerie

05:37:11.880 --> 05:37:14.639
experience outside the palace, led Turtle

05:37:14.639 --> 05:37:15.419
to a crazy thought.

05:37:15.479 --> 05:37:18.840
There was another kind of story Turtle

05:37:18.840 --> 05:37:21.180
used to read when he was younger, ghost

05:37:21.180 --> 05:37:21.779
stories.

05:37:21.840 --> 05:37:24.779
Spirits of the Dead, coming back to haunt

05:37:24.779 --> 05:37:27.659
those who wronged them, lost loves

05:37:27.659 --> 05:37:29.340
lingering around the ones who held their

05:37:29.340 --> 05:37:30.000
heart and life.

05:37:30.119 --> 05:37:33.119
Did dark stalker believe in ghosts?

05:37:33.180 --> 05:37:36.900
Turtle backed cautiously away, scanning

05:37:36.900 --> 05:37:38.220
the ground for something he might be able

05:37:38.220 --> 05:37:38.639
to use.

05:37:38.759 --> 05:37:42.000
Dark Stalker couldn't see him or hear him

05:37:42.000 --> 05:37:44.220
as he moved around, but he'd be able to

05:37:44.220 --> 05:37:45.779
see something turtle left behind.

05:37:45.840 --> 05:37:48.720
The moonlight glinted off something small

05:37:48.720 --> 05:37:51.119
and shiny, tucked in the hollow of a

05:37:51.119 --> 05:37:51.779
nearby tree.

05:37:51.840 --> 05:37:54.540
Turtle reached in, digging through the

05:37:54.540 --> 05:37:56.639
moss, and found a stash of beautiful

05:37:56.639 --> 05:37:59.459
marbles and different colors, blues and

05:37:59.459 --> 05:38:01.380
greens, and silvery blacks.

05:38:01.439 --> 05:38:04.799
He glanced back at Dark Stalker and chose

05:38:04.799 --> 05:38:06.900
a white marble with a sea blue heart.

05:38:06.959 --> 05:38:09.840
It looked like a tiny moon, and he

05:38:09.840 --> 05:38:11.220
thought it would be the most visible in

05:38:11.220 --> 05:38:11.880
the dark grass.

05:38:11.939 --> 05:38:13.740
Is this stupid?

05:38:13.799 --> 05:38:16.259
Is this the stupidest thing I've ever

05:38:16.259 --> 05:38:16.500
done?

05:38:16.560 --> 05:38:18.599
He hesitated.

05:38:18.659 --> 05:38:21.360
But all he wanted to do was see how Dark

05:38:21.360 --> 05:38:23.279
Stalker reacted, if at all.

05:38:23.340 --> 05:38:25.560
He'd still be as hidden as ever.

05:38:25.619 --> 05:38:26.759
He'd be careful.

05:38:26.819 --> 05:38:30.000
Dark Stalker might just think he hadn't

05:38:30.000 --> 05:38:30.479
noticed it before.

05:38:30.540 --> 05:38:34.020
He crept forward on trembling talons

05:38:34.020 --> 05:38:36.840
until he was almost under dark stalker's

05:38:36.840 --> 05:38:37.139
nose.

05:38:37.139 --> 05:38:40.680
He waited until the huge night wing wiped

05:38:40.680 --> 05:38:43.560
his eyes and glanced up at the sky in a

05:38:43.560 --> 05:38:43.860
flash.

05:38:43.919 --> 05:38:46.740
Turtle set the marble down an inch from

05:38:46.740 --> 05:38:49.139
those massive claws and back away.

05:38:49.200 --> 05:38:51.240
Nothing happened for a moment.

05:38:51.360 --> 05:38:53.639
Dark Stalker was still looking at the

05:38:53.639 --> 05:38:56.040
moons, but then he lowered his head again

05:38:56.040 --> 05:38:58.259
with a sigh, which caught in his throat

05:38:58.259 --> 05:38:59.700
when he saw the marble.

05:38:59.759 --> 05:39:03.060
He snatched it up in his claws and stared

05:39:03.060 --> 05:39:04.319
around the garden.

05:39:04.439 --> 05:39:06.479
His gaze passed right through turtle

05:39:06.479 --> 05:39:08.819
making turtle feel like a skewered moth.

05:39:08.880 --> 05:39:10.740
Clear sight.

05:39:10.860 --> 05:39:12.599
Dark stalker whispered.

05:39:12.659 --> 05:39:15.180
He cleared his throat and tried again, a

05:39:15.180 --> 05:39:15.900
little stronger.

05:39:15.959 --> 05:39:17.220
Clear sight.

05:39:17.279 --> 05:39:20.099
The wind murmured through the shadows

05:39:20.099 --> 05:39:22.560
scattering pine needles across dark

05:39:22.560 --> 05:39:25.139
stalkers' wings, and breathing evergreen

05:39:25.139 --> 05:39:26.520
air in turtle's direction.

05:39:26.580 --> 05:39:31.439
Clear sight, Dark Stalker said, stepping

05:39:31.439 --> 05:39:32.099
out into the moonlight.

05:39:32.159 --> 05:39:35.580
If you're here, speak to me.

05:39:35.639 --> 05:39:36.599
Please.

05:39:36.720 --> 05:39:38.400
Please speak to me.

05:39:38.459 --> 05:39:41.639
He waited, with an expression of such

05:39:41.639 --> 05:39:44.220
hope that Turtle was filled with guilt.

05:39:44.279 --> 05:39:48.779
Then listen, Dark Stalker said after a

05:39:48.779 --> 05:39:49.020
while.

05:39:49.080 --> 05:39:51.060
I won't hurt you.

05:39:51.119 --> 05:39:52.979
I would never hurt you.

05:39:53.040 --> 05:39:55.020
I forgive you.

05:39:55.080 --> 05:39:57.900
I know you were scared.

05:39:57.959 --> 05:40:01.560
I saw everything you were afraid of, in

05:40:01.560 --> 05:40:04.439
that last moment when you, when you put

05:40:04.439 --> 05:40:05.279
the bracelet on me.

05:40:05.340 --> 05:40:09.000
He hesitated, and his voice cracked as he

05:40:09.000 --> 05:40:12.119
added, I'm sorry, I put that spell on

05:40:12.119 --> 05:40:12.360
you.

05:40:12.419 --> 05:40:15.419
He closed his eyes and rubbed his

05:40:15.419 --> 05:40:16.439
forehead with his talons.

05:40:16.560 --> 05:40:18.540
What spell?

05:40:18.659 --> 05:40:20.040
Turtle wondered.

05:40:20.159 --> 05:40:22.680
What kind of dragon puts a spell on

05:40:22.680 --> 05:40:23.520
someone he loves?

05:40:23.639 --> 05:40:26.819
Then he remembered the love spell on

05:40:26.819 --> 05:40:28.979
Kinkaju, and wanted to claw his own face

05:40:28.979 --> 05:40:29.279
off.

05:40:29.340 --> 05:40:32.040
If you come back to me.

05:40:32.099 --> 05:40:36.779
Dark Stalker said, sadly, softly to the

05:40:36.779 --> 05:40:37.139
shadows.

05:40:37.200 --> 05:40:39.360
I promise.

05:40:39.419 --> 05:40:41.340
I'll never enchant your mind again.

05:40:41.400 --> 05:40:44.220
I promise I'll listen to you this time.

05:40:44.279 --> 05:40:47.159
We can choose the best future together.

05:40:47.220 --> 05:40:49.619
He let out a small laugh.

05:40:49.680 --> 05:40:52.200
I could use your help with what you've

05:40:52.200 --> 05:40:53.939
left me, a ruined city.

05:40:54.060 --> 05:40:56.400
A week and broken tribe.

05:40:56.459 --> 05:40:59.700
You'd be their queen clear sight.

05:40:59.759 --> 05:41:01.799
Doesn't that sound all right now?

05:41:01.860 --> 05:41:04.259
When you can have the crown without

05:41:04.259 --> 05:41:05.279
anyone having to die.

05:41:05.340 --> 05:41:08.580
It was just waiting for us clear sight.

05:41:08.639 --> 05:41:11.220
He started to pace.

05:41:11.279 --> 05:41:13.619
You should have to help fix this.

05:41:13.680 --> 05:41:16.200
Do you see what you did when you betrayed

05:41:16.200 --> 05:41:16.380
me?

05:41:16.439 --> 05:41:17.700
It's all gone.

05:41:17.819 --> 05:41:20.279
Our tribe's power, our kingdom.

05:41:20.340 --> 05:41:22.740
Our beautiful future.

05:41:22.799 --> 05:41:26.459
You did this to our whole tribe, not just

05:41:26.459 --> 05:41:26.700
to me.

05:41:26.759 --> 05:41:29.580
Dark Stalker's breath was ragged.

05:41:29.639 --> 05:41:32.400
His jaw clenched, and his claws ripped at

05:41:32.400 --> 05:41:34.380
the plants and grass, killing everything

05:41:34.380 --> 05:41:34.860
in his wake.

05:41:34.979 --> 05:41:37.560
Clear sight, he said.

05:41:37.680 --> 05:41:40.860
I I keep looking at all my new possible

05:41:40.860 --> 05:41:41.819
futures.

05:41:41.880 --> 05:41:43.500
Millions of possibilities.

05:41:43.560 --> 05:41:45.240
But they're all empty.

05:41:45.299 --> 05:41:47.639
They're empty without you.

05:41:47.700 --> 05:41:50.459
I have no one clear sight.

05:41:50.520 --> 05:41:52.619
All I can see around me.

05:41:52.680 --> 05:41:56.700
As far as the future unrolls, are slaves

05:41:56.700 --> 05:41:58.259
and soldiers.

05:41:58.319 --> 05:42:01.500
Turtles shivered involuntarily.

05:42:01.560 --> 05:42:03.599
Slaves and soldiers.

05:42:03.659 --> 05:42:05.819
Is that how he sees his own tribe?

05:42:05.880 --> 05:42:09.119
Dark Stalker paused again for a long

05:42:09.119 --> 05:42:12.599
moment, and then said, so quietly that

05:42:12.599 --> 05:42:13.919
Turtle almost couldn't hear him.

05:42:13.979 --> 05:42:16.860
I know you can't be out there.

05:42:16.919 --> 05:42:19.799
You're not in any of my futures.

05:42:19.919 --> 05:42:23.639
But please, clear sight.

05:42:23.700 --> 05:42:25.439
Please come back.

05:42:25.500 --> 05:42:28.080
And tell me there's still hope for us.

05:42:28.139 --> 05:42:32.700
The next pause lasted forever, and

05:42:32.700 --> 05:42:33.900
another 10 forever.

05:42:33.959 --> 05:42:36.659
Turtle's talons were starting to fall

05:42:36.659 --> 05:42:39.540
asleep, but he didn't dare move while

05:42:39.540 --> 05:42:40.979
Dark Stalker was still listening so

05:42:40.979 --> 05:42:41.459
intently.

05:42:41.520 --> 05:42:45.479
Finally, Dark Stalker lifted the marble

05:42:45.479 --> 05:42:47.939
up to glare at it, then clenched his fist

05:42:47.939 --> 05:42:48.599
shut around it.

05:42:48.659 --> 05:42:51.180
I'm a sentimental idiot.

05:42:51.240 --> 05:42:53.700
You're not here, he muttered.

05:42:53.759 --> 05:42:54.959
You could have been.

05:42:55.020 --> 05:42:56.939
If you'd waited another day or two.

05:42:57.000 --> 05:42:59.279
I would have made you immortal

05:42:59.279 --> 05:42:59.819
Clearsight.

05:42:59.939 --> 05:43:01.919
We could have been together forever.

05:43:01.979 --> 05:43:05.400
He turned a pace back and forth under the

05:43:05.400 --> 05:43:06.659
spreading pine branches.

05:43:06.720 --> 05:43:09.299
He is immortal then.

05:43:09.419 --> 05:43:12.720
Turtle had suspected it, but now he knew

05:43:12.720 --> 05:43:13.080
for sure.

05:43:13.200 --> 05:43:16.619
Invulnerable scales, immortal life.

05:43:16.680 --> 05:43:19.619
The 1st spells that any young animus

05:43:19.619 --> 05:43:20.159
would think of.

05:43:20.220 --> 05:43:22.200
But no one would actually do them.

05:43:22.319 --> 05:43:25.500
Between the cost to your soul and the

05:43:25.500 --> 05:43:28.860
unforeseen risks, at least, that's what I

05:43:28.860 --> 05:43:29.400
always thought.

05:43:29.459 --> 05:43:32.220
So what did you do instead?

05:43:32.340 --> 05:43:34.919
Dark Stalker hissed softly.

05:43:34.979 --> 05:43:37.020
Did you go back to Fathom?

05:43:37.080 --> 05:43:39.180
Did you 2 laugh at the wonderful trick

05:43:39.180 --> 05:43:39.840
you played on me?

05:43:39.900 --> 05:43:43.500
Did you let him cast spells for you?

05:43:43.560 --> 05:43:46.979
He clawed at his neck as though something

05:43:46.979 --> 05:43:48.540
sticky was clinging to it.

05:43:48.599 --> 05:43:53.279
That sneaking serpent of a sea wing, all

05:43:53.279 --> 05:43:55.319
high and mighty about protecting his soul

05:43:55.319 --> 05:43:58.200
and keeping his oath, until it comes to

05:43:58.200 --> 05:43:59.099
betraying his best friend.

05:43:59.159 --> 05:44:01.020
Then it's sure, why not?

05:44:01.080 --> 05:44:03.659
It's full speed ahead to sleeping spells

05:44:03.659 --> 05:44:05.880
and conniving and lies.

05:44:05.939 --> 05:44:09.299
He stopped, his sides heaving.

05:44:09.360 --> 05:44:10.799
No.

05:44:10.860 --> 05:44:11.939
He said.

05:44:12.000 --> 05:44:13.860
You loved me.

05:44:13.919 --> 05:44:15.720
I know that was true.

05:44:15.779 --> 05:44:18.599
Fathom talked you into doing this to me.

05:44:18.659 --> 05:44:20.400
He's the traitor.

05:44:20.459 --> 05:44:23.099
He's the one I'll never forgive.

05:44:23.159 --> 05:44:26.159
Dark Stalker hurled the marble at the

05:44:26.159 --> 05:44:28.380
nearest tree with such force that the

05:44:28.380 --> 05:44:29.459
trunk split down the middle.

05:44:29.520 --> 05:44:32.099
Turtle had to scramble out of the way of

05:44:32.099 --> 05:44:34.319
falling branches, and when he was able to

05:44:34.319 --> 05:44:36.900
look up again, Dark Stalker had vanished

05:44:36.900 --> 05:44:38.159
into the night sky.

05:44:38.159 --> 05:44:42.599
Chapter 17.

05:44:42.779 --> 05:44:46.439
Moon was awake when Turtle got back.

05:44:46.500 --> 05:44:49.380
She was sitting on the beach, staring out

05:44:49.380 --> 05:44:51.540
to sea. tracing shapes in the sand

05:44:51.540 --> 05:44:53.040
without looking at what her claws were

05:44:53.040 --> 05:44:55.439
doing, a thin thread of light on the

05:44:55.439 --> 05:44:57.779
horizon, hinted at the sunrise about to

05:44:57.779 --> 05:45:00.060
come, but the cold air smelled like

05:45:00.060 --> 05:45:00.299
rain.

05:45:00.360 --> 05:45:02.700
Why aren't you sleeping?

05:45:02.759 --> 05:45:05.340
Turtle asked, landing beside her.

05:45:05.400 --> 05:45:07.439
She gave him a rueful look.

05:45:07.500 --> 05:45:09.900
I never sleep well at night.

05:45:09.959 --> 05:45:13.020
In the rainforest, I mostly slept during

05:45:13.020 --> 05:45:15.360
the day, and I haven't quite adjusted to

05:45:15.360 --> 05:45:16.860
a normal dragon schedule.

05:45:16.919 --> 05:45:17.939
She hesitated.

05:45:18.060 --> 05:45:21.599
Although, Dark Stalker says, I'm the one

05:45:21.599 --> 05:45:23.459
who's normal, and it's the other night

05:45:23.459 --> 05:45:24.959
wings who need to fix themselves to

05:45:24.959 --> 05:45:25.259
match.

05:45:25.319 --> 05:45:28.560
Her tail flicked sand across the patterns

05:45:28.560 --> 05:45:29.159
she'd drawn.

05:45:29.279 --> 05:45:31.259
And I had a nightmare.

05:45:31.319 --> 05:45:34.860
The nightmare, the one I always have.

05:45:34.919 --> 05:45:37.979
About Jade Mountain falling.

05:45:38.099 --> 05:45:39.720
Moon nodded.

05:45:39.779 --> 05:45:43.319
Fire and death, and screaming, and death

05:45:43.319 --> 05:45:44.580
it's not awesome.

05:45:44.639 --> 05:45:47.819
You can't see anything about how to stop

05:45:47.819 --> 05:45:48.119
it?

05:45:48.180 --> 05:45:49.560
Turtle asked.

05:45:49.619 --> 05:45:50.700
Any clues?

05:45:50.759 --> 05:45:54.119
Like something we might find in the Lost

05:45:54.119 --> 05:45:55.139
City of Night?

05:45:55.200 --> 05:45:57.180
Moon suggested with a sigh.

05:45:57.299 --> 05:45:58.560
Not so far.

05:45:58.619 --> 05:45:59.880
Where have you been?

05:46:00.000 --> 05:46:02.819
Turtle discovered that he didn't want to

05:46:02.819 --> 05:46:05.220
tell her about what he'd seen, especially

05:46:05.220 --> 05:46:07.380
about dark stalkers crushing sadness.

05:46:07.439 --> 05:46:09.720
She already sympathized with him too

05:46:09.720 --> 05:46:10.259
much.

05:46:10.259 --> 05:46:12.360
She didn't need more reasons to want to

05:46:12.360 --> 05:46:13.619
give Dark Stalker a hug.

05:46:13.680 --> 05:46:16.200
She needed to see him as bad and

05:46:16.200 --> 05:46:18.720
dangerous, so that she'd help Kinkaju

05:46:18.720 --> 05:46:20.459
when the time came for whatever heroics

05:46:20.459 --> 05:46:21.000
were necessary.

05:46:21.060 --> 05:46:25.200
Just scouting out the night wings, he

05:46:25.200 --> 05:46:27.779
said evasively, checking on anemone.

05:46:27.840 --> 05:46:30.060
This was partly true.

05:46:30.119 --> 05:46:32.759
As he flew over them, he had peered down

05:46:32.759 --> 05:46:34.919
at the night wings, their black scales

05:46:34.919 --> 05:46:37.080
blanketing the dunes, and the beach where

05:46:37.080 --> 05:46:37.680
they slept.

05:46:37.740 --> 05:46:40.259
He'd spotted anemone down by the ocean

05:46:40.259 --> 05:46:42.720
sleeping as close to the sound and scent

05:46:42.720 --> 05:46:43.919
of the waves as you could get.

05:46:43.979 --> 05:46:47.159
You're a good brother, Moon said.

05:46:47.220 --> 05:46:51.299
No, I'm not, he protested, and she looked

05:46:51.299 --> 05:46:52.740
startled at his vehemence.

05:46:52.860 --> 05:46:54.299
Don't say that.

05:46:54.360 --> 05:46:55.860
I'm a terrible brother.

05:46:55.979 --> 05:46:59.279
Great heavens, turtle, Moon said

05:46:59.279 --> 05:46:59.759
blinking.

05:46:59.819 --> 05:47:01.319
That's not true at all.

05:47:01.380 --> 05:47:03.419
You're following her to the end of the

05:47:03.419 --> 05:47:04.319
continent, aren't you?

05:47:04.439 --> 05:47:05.759
To make sure she's all right?

05:47:05.880 --> 05:47:08.939
I'm following Dark Stalker.

05:47:09.000 --> 05:47:11.520
I know anemone's not all right.

05:47:11.580 --> 05:47:14.099
And that's my fault, and there's nothing

05:47:14.099 --> 05:47:14.880
I can do about it.

05:47:14.939 --> 05:47:18.000
Trust me, he said.

05:47:18.060 --> 05:47:20.580
I'm the worst brother a dragon could

05:47:20.580 --> 05:47:21.119
possibly have.

05:47:21.240 --> 05:47:24.840
Moon studied him for a long moment, with

05:47:24.840 --> 05:47:26.159
a faint frown on her face.

05:47:26.220 --> 05:47:29.700
I had a vision about you once, she said.

05:47:29.759 --> 05:47:31.500
About me?

05:47:31.560 --> 05:47:32.819
Turtle snorted.

05:47:32.880 --> 05:47:35.040
Was I hiding at the bottom of the ocean?

05:47:35.099 --> 05:47:37.560
Because that's what I see in most of my

05:47:37.560 --> 05:47:38.700
possible futures.

05:47:38.700 --> 05:47:40.380
Now.

05:47:40.500 --> 05:47:43.139
I'm not sure whether to tell you about it

05:47:43.139 --> 05:47:43.979
she said.

05:47:44.040 --> 05:47:46.619
It was a little scary.

05:47:46.680 --> 05:47:49.439
Turtle dug one of his talons into the

05:47:49.439 --> 05:47:51.900
beach, and let the sand fill in over it

05:47:51.900 --> 05:47:52.680
until it disappeared.

05:47:52.740 --> 05:47:55.500
With dark stalker around, probably

05:47:55.500 --> 05:47:57.360
everyone had a scary future ahead.

05:47:57.479 --> 05:48:00.299
I think you should tell me, he said.

05:48:00.360 --> 05:48:04.860
You were on a beach, she said, her voice

05:48:04.860 --> 05:48:07.319
getting softer, nearly swallowed by the

05:48:07.319 --> 05:48:10.319
rush of the waves, and you were attacking

05:48:10.319 --> 05:48:11.040
anemone.

05:48:11.099 --> 05:48:13.200
Turtles stared at her.

05:48:13.259 --> 05:48:15.060
Why would I do that?

05:48:15.119 --> 05:48:17.040
I don't know.

05:48:17.099 --> 05:48:17.939
She said.

05:48:18.000 --> 05:48:19.680
You had her pinned down.

05:48:19.740 --> 05:48:21.240
That's all I saw.

05:48:21.299 --> 05:48:24.240
Why are you just telling me now?

05:48:24.299 --> 05:48:25.319
he asked.

05:48:25.439 --> 05:48:28.380
One of the crescent moons was reflected

05:48:28.380 --> 05:48:28.860
in her eyes.

05:48:28.919 --> 05:48:30.779
I didn't want to scare you.

05:48:30.900 --> 05:48:34.560
I was worried it might happen because you

05:48:34.560 --> 05:48:36.840
use your magic too much, and lose your

05:48:36.840 --> 05:48:37.020
soul.

05:48:37.139 --> 05:48:41.279
Turtle's claws twitched, as though they

05:48:41.279 --> 05:48:42.479
were reaching for someone's throat.

05:48:42.599 --> 05:48:45.360
He tried to imagine them sinking into

05:48:45.360 --> 05:48:48.240
anemones scales, drawing his sister's

05:48:48.240 --> 05:48:48.419
blood.

05:48:48.479 --> 05:48:51.779
The screaming battered night wing flashed

05:48:51.779 --> 05:48:53.459
through his mind again, along with a

05:48:53.459 --> 05:48:55.860
whisper, you have violence in you.

05:48:55.919 --> 05:48:57.840
But that was different.

05:48:57.900 --> 05:49:00.060
I would never hurt my own sister.

05:49:00.119 --> 05:49:03.659
His claws curled inward, as though they

05:49:03.659 --> 05:49:04.380
disagreed with him.

05:49:04.439 --> 05:49:07.979
It might not come true, Moon said.

05:49:08.040 --> 05:49:11.279
Dark Stalker says, our visions are only

05:49:11.279 --> 05:49:14.159
the most probable futures, but things can

05:49:14.159 --> 05:49:15.599
always go in a different direction.

05:49:15.659 --> 05:49:18.060
Turtle jumped to his feet.

05:49:18.119 --> 05:49:20.580
Clenching and unclenching his talons.

05:49:20.639 --> 05:49:22.799
I'm sure it won't happen.

05:49:22.860 --> 05:49:25.619
I'm a bad brother, but not that

05:49:25.619 --> 05:49:26.099
terrible.

05:49:26.159 --> 05:49:28.500
He didn't want to think about this

05:49:28.500 --> 05:49:28.799
anymore.

05:49:28.860 --> 05:49:31.200
He didn't need one more thing to worry

05:49:31.200 --> 05:49:31.439
about.

05:49:31.500 --> 05:49:34.380
Movement on the horizon caught his

05:49:34.380 --> 05:49:36.659
attention, and he looked up to see black

05:49:36.659 --> 05:49:38.279
wings ascending into the sky.

05:49:38.340 --> 05:49:39.840
They're moving.

05:49:39.900 --> 05:49:41.400
I'll get Kinkachu.

05:49:41.520 --> 05:49:43.979
Turtle ran up the beach and poked his

05:49:43.979 --> 05:49:46.439
nose into the cave, nudging Kinkaju in

05:49:46.439 --> 05:49:46.680
the side.

05:49:46.799 --> 05:49:49.200
No.

05:49:49.439 --> 05:49:51.599
Kinkaju mumbled from under her wings.

05:49:51.659 --> 05:49:54.599
Time to go, Kinkaju, he said.

05:49:54.659 --> 05:49:56.459
Go away.

05:49:56.520 --> 05:49:58.259
Bromiliad.

05:49:58.319 --> 05:50:00.119
Kinkaju grumped in her sleep.

05:50:00.180 --> 05:50:03.060
You smell like fish and I don't want to

05:50:03.060 --> 05:50:03.720
train today.

05:50:03.779 --> 05:50:07.200
Turtle felt a stab of affection for her

05:50:07.200 --> 05:50:09.479
for this grouchy, sleepy side of her he

05:50:09.479 --> 05:50:10.139
hadn't seen before.

05:50:10.200 --> 05:50:13.740
She was so real, and so kind, and so

05:50:13.740 --> 05:50:14.159
present.

05:50:14.279 --> 05:50:16.680
She was the opposite of a terrifying

05:50:16.680 --> 05:50:17.459
vision of his future.

05:50:17.520 --> 05:50:19.979
It's me, turtle.

05:50:20.040 --> 05:50:22.619
He said, brushing one of his wings over

05:50:22.619 --> 05:50:22.979
hers.

05:50:23.099 --> 05:50:25.500
Come on, Kinkachu, wake up.

05:50:25.560 --> 05:50:27.900
Turtle.

05:50:27.959 --> 05:50:31.259
Kinkachu sighed dreamily, and clouds of

05:50:31.259 --> 05:50:33.000
light pink started drifting through her

05:50:33.000 --> 05:50:33.360
scales.

05:50:33.419 --> 05:50:36.000
Turtle pulled his wing back, feeling

05:50:36.000 --> 05:50:36.419
sick.

05:50:36.479 --> 05:50:39.540
So Anemone's spell really was working.

05:50:39.599 --> 05:50:42.360
He knew this wasn't how Kinkaju actually

05:50:42.360 --> 05:50:42.959
felt about him.

05:50:43.020 --> 05:50:45.900
She'd be so furious and embarrassed when

05:50:45.900 --> 05:50:47.520
she found out it was all magic.

05:50:47.580 --> 05:50:49.680
But I can't tell her.

05:50:49.799 --> 05:50:51.900
What if it makes her so angry?

05:50:51.959 --> 05:50:53.819
She takes off the Skyfire.

05:50:53.880 --> 05:50:56.880
And then Dark Stalker notices her, and

05:50:56.880 --> 05:50:58.020
terrible things happen.

05:50:58.080 --> 05:51:01.380
Is this why I attack anemone on some

05:51:01.380 --> 05:51:02.459
future beach?

05:51:02.520 --> 05:51:04.139
Because I'm angry with her about the

05:51:04.139 --> 05:51:05.279
spell on Kinkaju?

05:51:05.400 --> 05:51:09.419
We have to go, he said gruffly, and

05:51:09.419 --> 05:51:10.500
whacked her with his tail.

05:51:10.560 --> 05:51:11.880
Who's that?

05:51:12.000 --> 05:51:14.400
she yelped, leaping to her feet and

05:51:14.400 --> 05:51:16.259
turning red with stripes of pale green.

05:51:16.380 --> 05:51:18.180
You want my venom?

05:51:18.240 --> 05:51:19.439
I'll show you vent.

05:51:19.560 --> 05:51:21.180
Oh, hi turtle.

05:51:21.240 --> 05:51:23.340
She shook herself from head to tail.

05:51:23.400 --> 05:51:24.779
Whoa.

05:51:24.840 --> 05:51:26.040
That was a weird dream.

05:51:26.099 --> 05:51:28.740
My old teacher turned into the night wing

05:51:28.740 --> 05:51:29.700
who used to study us.

05:51:29.759 --> 05:51:32.400
She shook herself again, harder.

05:51:32.459 --> 05:51:35.279
Two of my least favorite dragons.

05:51:35.340 --> 05:51:36.360
Yeesh.

05:51:36.419 --> 05:51:38.220
Anyone would think I'm worried about

05:51:38.220 --> 05:51:38.459
something.

05:51:38.520 --> 05:51:41.759
The night wings are moving, Turtles

05:51:41.759 --> 05:51:42.060
said.

05:51:42.119 --> 05:51:43.259
We should get going too.

05:51:43.319 --> 05:51:45.299
Oh, sure.

05:51:45.360 --> 05:51:47.459
Kinkachu rubbed her face and then

05:51:47.459 --> 05:51:49.919
stretched, shifting her scales through a

05:51:49.919 --> 05:51:52.680
dazzling cascade of colors from purple to

05:51:52.680 --> 05:51:54.959
aquamarine to saffron where they

05:51:54.959 --> 05:51:55.319
settled.

05:51:55.380 --> 05:51:58.619
Turtle, you're looking at me as though

05:51:58.619 --> 05:52:00.540
I've been stabbed by a stalactite, but

05:52:00.540 --> 05:52:01.139
haven't noticed yet.

05:52:01.200 --> 05:52:05.040
Sorry, he said, backing out of the cave

05:52:05.040 --> 05:52:05.400
quickly.

05:52:05.459 --> 05:52:08.340
They watched the night wings gather in

05:52:08.340 --> 05:52:10.860
the sky like storm clouds until the tribe

05:52:10.860 --> 05:52:13.020
finally wheeled away west, and then

05:52:13.020 --> 05:52:15.840
Turtle, Moon, and Kinkaju lifted off and

05:52:15.840 --> 05:52:16.259
followed them.

05:52:16.319 --> 05:52:19.500
The landscape looked much the same in the

05:52:19.500 --> 05:52:21.479
light as it had the night before, and

05:52:21.479 --> 05:52:23.819
Turtle felt the same strange zap of

05:52:23.819 --> 05:52:26.040
energy as they flew over that spot in the

05:52:26.040 --> 05:52:26.939
hills.

05:52:27.000 --> 05:52:27.720
Did you?

05:52:27.779 --> 05:52:30.779
he asked his friends, just as Kinkaju

05:52:30.779 --> 05:52:32.700
yelped, ow, what was that?

05:52:32.759 --> 05:52:36.959
I don't know, Moon said, glancing down.

05:52:37.020 --> 05:52:39.779
She fell silent, and Turtle wondered if

05:52:39.779 --> 05:52:41.459
she had seen the shapes of bones below

05:52:41.459 --> 05:52:41.939
them too.

05:52:42.000 --> 05:52:45.060
They waited until all the night wings had

05:52:45.060 --> 05:52:46.979
vanished over the peaks before flying

05:52:46.979 --> 05:52:47.400
after them.

05:52:47.459 --> 05:52:49.979
But as they came up and over the last

05:52:49.979 --> 05:52:52.380
mountain, they found a dragon waiting for

05:52:52.380 --> 05:52:53.099
them in the sky.

05:52:53.159 --> 05:52:55.020
Dark stalker.

05:52:55.139 --> 05:52:56.819
Moon.

05:52:56.880 --> 05:52:59.220
He cried, with genuine delight.

05:52:59.279 --> 05:53:01.860
I thought my visions were messing with me

05:53:01.860 --> 05:53:03.240
but you did come after all.

05:53:03.299 --> 05:53:06.540
He did a joyful flip in the air, spreading

05:53:06.540 --> 05:53:07.500
his wings toward the city.

05:53:07.560 --> 05:53:09.720
Isn't this amazing?

05:53:09.779 --> 05:53:12.240
Look at our beautiful kingdom.

05:53:12.299 --> 05:53:16.500
Oh, wow, Moon said faintly.

05:53:16.560 --> 05:53:19.439
In the gray sunlight, Turtle could see

05:53:19.439 --> 05:53:21.119
that the city was even larger and more

05:53:21.119 --> 05:53:22.860
ornate than he'd realized the night

05:53:22.860 --> 05:53:25.139
before, but he could also see more

05:53:25.139 --> 05:53:27.540
clearly how broken it was, and how time

05:53:27.540 --> 05:53:28.619
had eaten away at it.

05:53:28.680 --> 05:53:31.080
The rest of the tribe had swooped down

05:53:31.080 --> 05:53:33.180
into the ruins, diving through the

05:53:33.180 --> 05:53:35.159
canyons, exploring their new home.

05:53:35.220 --> 05:53:38.880
That's the great diamond down there.

05:53:38.939 --> 05:53:41.639
Dark Stalker said eagerly to Moon

05:53:41.639 --> 05:53:43.740
pointing at the overgrown square.

05:53:43.799 --> 05:53:45.840
On one side is the museum.

05:53:45.900 --> 05:53:48.479
Over there is the school, and that

05:53:48.479 --> 05:53:49.680
building is the library.

05:53:49.799 --> 05:53:51.599
The library moon.

05:53:51.659 --> 05:53:53.279
I can't wait to show it to you.

05:53:53.340 --> 05:53:55.979
It makes starflights, it'll cave at Jade

05:53:55.979 --> 05:53:58.560
Mountain, look like a toad's den, although

05:53:58.560 --> 05:53:59.880
it's not in the greatest shape now.

05:53:59.939 --> 05:54:02.939
But surely some of our scrolls must have

05:54:02.939 --> 05:54:03.240
survived.

05:54:03.360 --> 05:54:06.180
He poked Moon with his tail, grinning.

05:54:06.240 --> 05:54:08.639
I was hoping my visions were right, and

05:54:08.639 --> 05:54:09.060
you'd come.

05:54:09.119 --> 05:54:10.439
This is great.

05:54:10.560 --> 05:54:13.680
I'm not staying, Moon said quickly.

05:54:13.740 --> 05:54:15.659
I'm going back to Jade Mountain.

05:54:15.720 --> 05:54:18.180
I just wanted to see it.

05:54:18.240 --> 05:54:19.680
Me too.

05:54:19.740 --> 05:54:21.299
Kinkaju volunteered.

05:54:21.360 --> 05:54:23.639
Popping up behind Moon and waving at Dark

05:54:23.639 --> 05:54:24.180
Stalker.

05:54:24.240 --> 05:54:25.979
I'm here to see it too.

05:54:26.040 --> 05:54:27.479
Moon's best friend, remember?

05:54:27.540 --> 05:54:29.159
Yes, right.

05:54:29.220 --> 05:54:31.439
Dark Stalker said dismissively.

05:54:31.500 --> 05:54:33.060
Well, sure, Moon.

05:54:33.180 --> 05:54:35.099
If you want to go back to Jade Mountain

05:54:35.099 --> 05:54:35.520
that's fine.

05:54:35.580 --> 05:54:38.099
But you might find that our school is

05:54:38.099 --> 05:54:39.840
much better and more perfect for you.

05:54:39.900 --> 05:54:42.840
After all, it's where I went to school.

05:54:42.900 --> 05:54:45.659
We had classes in all kinds of things.

05:54:45.720 --> 05:54:47.520
They'll never get to a jade mountain.

05:54:47.580 --> 05:54:49.680
I just have to rebuild it a little.

05:54:49.740 --> 05:54:50.700
Clean it up.

05:54:50.759 --> 05:54:52.860
Find some decent teachers.

05:54:52.919 --> 05:54:55.139
He frowned down at the scattered night

05:54:55.139 --> 05:54:55.919
wings below him.

05:54:55.979 --> 05:54:58.619
I suppose I could enchant some of them

05:54:58.619 --> 05:54:59.880
into becoming good teachers.

05:55:00.000 --> 05:55:01.380
He said thoughtfully.

05:55:01.500 --> 05:55:05.279
But would your school be only for night

05:55:05.279 --> 05:55:05.759
wings?

05:55:05.819 --> 05:55:06.779
Moon asked.

05:55:06.840 --> 05:55:09.180
Or would you invite students from other

05:55:09.180 --> 05:55:12.060
tribes, like Sonny did at Jade Mountain?

05:55:12.119 --> 05:55:15.060
Sunny is very sweet.

05:55:15.119 --> 05:55:16.740
Dark Stalker said.

05:55:16.799 --> 05:55:18.720
But you saw how that turned out.

05:55:18.779 --> 05:55:21.000
It doesn't work to throw tribes together

05:55:21.000 --> 05:55:22.860
and just hope they'll get along, because

05:55:22.860 --> 05:55:23.580
they won't.

05:55:23.639 --> 05:55:24.599
They can't.

05:55:24.720 --> 05:55:26.520
Dragons don't work that way.

05:55:26.580 --> 05:55:28.439
No matter what tribe they're from.

05:55:28.560 --> 05:55:31.380
I get along with dragons from other

05:55:31.380 --> 05:55:33.240
tribes, Kinkatu objected.

05:55:33.299 --> 05:55:35.099
Moon is my best friend.

05:55:35.159 --> 05:55:36.240
Our winglet is awesome.

05:55:36.299 --> 05:55:39.779
I kind of like meeting the other tribes

05:55:39.779 --> 05:55:41.580
Moon said to Dark Stalker.

05:55:41.639 --> 05:55:45.299
They're not all like Icicle or Flame, or

05:55:45.299 --> 05:55:46.139
poor Sora.

05:55:46.200 --> 05:55:50.340
Well, Dark Stalker said, flicking his

05:55:50.340 --> 05:55:50.639
tail.

05:55:50.700 --> 05:55:52.979
Maybe one day you can organize an

05:55:52.979 --> 05:55:53.880
exchange program.

05:55:53.939 --> 05:55:56.340
But for now, we need to focus on

05:55:56.340 --> 05:55:58.139
educating our own dragonettes.

05:55:58.200 --> 05:55:59.819
We have a tribe to rebuild.

05:55:59.880 --> 05:56:02.040
There's so much they need to learn.

05:56:02.099 --> 05:56:04.680
Perhaps once we've solved all the

05:56:04.680 --> 05:56:06.119
problems within our tribe.

05:56:06.180 --> 05:56:07.979
We can start thinking about reaching out

05:56:07.979 --> 05:56:10.259
to other tribes.

05:56:10.319 --> 05:56:13.259
Anyway, let me give you a tour of the

05:56:13.259 --> 05:56:13.740
palace.

05:56:13.799 --> 05:56:16.259
He tugged on one of Moon's wings and

05:56:16.259 --> 05:56:17.099
flashed away.

05:56:17.159 --> 05:56:19.500
Moon gave Turtle and Kinkachu an

05:56:19.500 --> 05:56:21.360
apologetic look, and went after him.

05:56:21.419 --> 05:56:23.520
They followed a few wing beats behind.

05:56:23.580 --> 05:56:27.419
He pays me no attention at all, Kinkaju

05:56:27.419 --> 05:56:27.840
grumbled.

05:56:27.900 --> 05:56:29.400
It's like I'm not even there.

05:56:29.459 --> 05:56:32.159
That's good, Kikachu.

05:56:32.220 --> 05:56:34.740
Turtle reminded her, you don't want him

05:56:34.740 --> 05:56:35.639
to pay attention to you.

05:56:35.759 --> 05:56:40.139
I know, she said with a sigh, but I don't

05:56:40.139 --> 05:56:41.580
like feeling as though I've disappeared.

05:56:41.639 --> 05:56:43.560
Like I'm not important enough to even

05:56:43.560 --> 05:56:44.159
look at.

05:56:44.340 --> 05:56:47.700
You're very important, Turtle said

05:56:47.700 --> 05:56:48.540
reassuringly.

05:56:48.599 --> 05:56:50.520
You're the hero of the story, remember?

05:56:50.580 --> 05:56:53.159
You have to fulfill Moon's prophecy.

05:56:53.220 --> 05:56:54.779
That's right.

05:56:54.840 --> 05:56:56.759
She said, brightening.

05:56:56.819 --> 05:56:59.700
We're here, in the lost city of night.

05:56:59.819 --> 05:57:02.400
She glanced around as though she expected

05:57:02.400 --> 05:57:04.500
a parade of cheering dragons to pop out

05:57:04.500 --> 05:57:04.919
of the mountain.

05:57:05.040 --> 05:57:06.419
We did it.

05:57:06.479 --> 05:57:09.060
So, did it work?

05:57:09.119 --> 05:57:10.500
Is the world saved?

05:57:10.619 --> 05:57:12.900
She poked his shoulder experimentally.

05:57:12.959 --> 05:57:15.479
Does the world feel saved to you?

05:57:15.540 --> 05:57:17.880
Not even remotely?

05:57:17.939 --> 05:57:21.360
Turtle admitted, watching dark soccer and

05:57:21.360 --> 05:57:23.159
moon land on one of the balconies of the

05:57:23.159 --> 05:57:23.520
palace.

05:57:23.580 --> 05:57:27.659
That's the right attitude, Kinkaju said.

05:57:27.720 --> 05:57:30.060
They swept down to land on the same

05:57:30.060 --> 05:57:32.520
balcony, carefully avoiding the parts of

05:57:32.520 --> 05:57:34.139
the balustrade that had caved in.

05:57:34.200 --> 05:57:37.139
Inside, Dark Stalker was walking around

05:57:37.139 --> 05:57:39.959
what appeared to be a giant bedroom, 8

05:57:39.959 --> 05:57:41.939
times the size of any sleeping cave

05:57:41.939 --> 05:57:42.900
turtle had ever been in.

05:57:42.959 --> 05:57:45.479
These were the queen's room.

05:57:45.540 --> 05:57:47.580
Dark Stalker said to Moon.

05:57:47.639 --> 05:57:49.560
They're mine now, of course.

05:57:49.619 --> 05:57:51.180
It looks like she took most of her

05:57:51.180 --> 05:57:52.319
treasure with her when she left.

05:57:52.380 --> 05:57:55.680
He blew some dust off an enormous mirror

05:57:55.680 --> 05:57:56.520
and frowned at it.

05:57:56.580 --> 05:58:00.240
It all used to be so clean and perfect.

05:58:00.299 --> 05:58:02.819
There were grand parties every other

05:58:02.819 --> 05:58:05.279
night, and things you would actually like

05:58:05.279 --> 05:58:06.180
too, Moon.

05:58:06.240 --> 05:58:09.659
Salons and scientific lectures, and

05:58:09.659 --> 05:58:10.200
readings.

05:58:10.259 --> 05:58:13.319
His voice trailed off as he wandered into

05:58:13.319 --> 05:58:15.479
one of the side rooms of the suite, where

05:58:15.479 --> 05:58:17.819
he started overturning empty chests and

05:58:17.819 --> 05:58:19.619
opening all the cabinets, moon

05:58:19.619 --> 05:58:20.520
disappeared after him.

05:58:20.639 --> 05:58:22.680
Dark Stalker.

05:58:22.740 --> 05:58:24.959
Anemone appeared in the doorway to the

05:58:24.959 --> 05:58:27.419
hall, her talons covered in white stone

05:58:27.419 --> 05:58:28.020
dust.

05:58:28.080 --> 05:58:29.639
I couldn't find the rooms you were

05:58:29.639 --> 05:58:30.060
talking about.

05:58:30.180 --> 05:58:31.799
Oh, the doors look the same.

05:58:31.860 --> 05:58:34.799
She spotted turtle, and her mouth dropped

05:58:34.799 --> 05:58:35.459
open.

05:58:35.520 --> 05:58:36.900
What are you doing here?

05:58:36.959 --> 05:58:38.220
She hissed.

05:58:38.279 --> 05:58:39.720
I thought you were going back to school.

05:58:39.779 --> 05:58:41.099
Stop following me.

05:58:41.159 --> 05:58:44.639
He's not following you, Kinkaju said

05:58:44.639 --> 05:58:45.119
haughtily.

05:58:45.180 --> 05:58:46.020
He's with me.

05:58:46.080 --> 05:58:48.299
Oh.

05:58:48.360 --> 05:58:51.419
Anemone's snout crinkled into a wickedly

05:58:51.419 --> 05:58:52.080
sly grin.

05:58:52.200 --> 05:58:54.779
Ah, that's wonderful.

05:58:54.840 --> 05:58:56.819
That's so, so cute.

05:58:56.880 --> 05:58:59.220
You guys are so cute together.

05:58:59.279 --> 05:59:02.099
She lowered her voice, although not far

05:59:02.099 --> 05:59:04.860
enough, and whispered to Turtle, you're

05:59:04.860 --> 05:59:05.220
welcome.

05:59:05.340 --> 05:59:08.159
Moon heard this as she came back into the

05:59:08.159 --> 05:59:08.340
room.

05:59:08.400 --> 05:59:11.099
She gave him and anemone a surprised

05:59:11.099 --> 05:59:11.400
look.

05:59:11.459 --> 05:59:13.680
Turtle hoped the floor was about to

05:59:13.680 --> 05:59:15.000
collapse and take him with it.

05:59:15.060 --> 05:59:18.119
Wait, you're here too?

05:59:18.240 --> 05:59:21.659
Anemone said to Moon, lashing her tail.

05:59:21.720 --> 05:59:23.340
Do you just keep changing your mind about

05:59:23.340 --> 05:59:24.360
who you're loyal to?

05:59:24.419 --> 05:59:26.040
He doesn't need you, you know.

05:59:26.099 --> 05:59:26.939
He has me.

05:59:27.000 --> 05:59:30.720
We are not staying long, Moon said

05:59:30.720 --> 05:59:31.380
uncomfortably.

05:59:31.439 --> 05:59:34.080
What is it, anemone?

05:59:34.139 --> 05:59:36.840
Dark Stalker asked, slithering back into

05:59:36.840 --> 05:59:37.380
the main room.

05:59:37.439 --> 05:59:39.900
Turtle wondered if he was imagining the

05:59:39.900 --> 05:59:41.639
hint of weary impatience in dark

05:59:41.639 --> 05:59:42.419
stalker's voice.

05:59:42.479 --> 05:59:45.659
You said there was a perfect suite for me

05:59:45.659 --> 05:59:46.200
remember?

05:59:46.259 --> 05:59:49.619
Anemone said, in her wheedling whining

05:59:49.619 --> 05:59:52.139
princess voice, but I couldn't figure out

05:59:52.139 --> 05:59:53.939
your directions, and I can't find it.

05:59:54.000 --> 05:59:56.040
Oh, dear.

05:59:56.099 --> 05:59:59.099
I'm so sorry for straining your tiny sea

05:59:59.099 --> 05:59:59.880
wing brain.

05:59:59.939 --> 06:00:00.900
He said.

06:00:00.959 --> 06:00:03.180
Anemone didn't even look offended.

06:00:03.240 --> 06:00:05.279
The insult seemed to sail right past

06:00:05.279 --> 06:00:05.520
her.

06:00:05.580 --> 06:00:08.040
Come on, I'll just show you.

06:00:08.099 --> 06:00:10.500
She jumped out of his way as he thumped

06:00:10.500 --> 06:00:13.080
past, and Turtle noticed that the doors

06:00:13.080 --> 06:00:14.400
in this palace were so big.

06:00:14.459 --> 06:00:16.799
Dark Stalker didn't even have to duck as

06:00:16.799 --> 06:00:17.220
he went through.

06:00:17.279 --> 06:00:20.459
They all trailed after Dark Stalker

06:00:20.459 --> 06:00:22.139
through the long black marble halls of

06:00:22.139 --> 06:00:24.240
the palace, many of which opened onto

06:00:24.240 --> 06:00:27.180
courtyards, or balconies, or grand halls

06:00:27.180 --> 06:00:27.840
far below them.

06:00:27.900 --> 06:00:30.360
Turtle had always thought the deep palace

06:00:30.360 --> 06:00:32.819
of the sea wings was the most luxurious

06:00:32.819 --> 06:00:35.759
imposing castle in all of Pyria, but he

06:00:35.759 --> 06:00:37.139
guessed that at least 5 of them would fit

06:00:37.139 --> 06:00:38.220
inside this place.

06:00:38.279 --> 06:00:40.740
Anemone might have been thinking the same

06:00:40.740 --> 06:00:43.740
thing, because she said jealously, you

06:00:43.740 --> 06:00:46.139
know, our palace has a lot more artwork

06:00:46.139 --> 06:00:49.080
and treasure, lots of jewels everywhere.

06:00:49.139 --> 06:00:52.979
Dark soccer paused and ran one claw

06:00:52.979 --> 06:00:54.360
through the dust on one of the walls.

06:00:54.419 --> 06:00:57.060
There used to be artwork and treasure

06:00:57.060 --> 06:00:59.040
here too, he said thoughtfully.

06:00:59.099 --> 06:01:01.919
I'm surprised the queen was able to take

06:01:01.919 --> 06:01:02.819
so much of it with her.

06:01:02.939 --> 06:01:04.200
He paused.

06:01:04.259 --> 06:01:07.200
Unless she didn't.

06:01:07.259 --> 06:01:10.020
His eyebrows drew down menacingly.

06:01:10.080 --> 06:01:13.560
Unless another tribe came in here later

06:01:13.560 --> 06:01:15.180
and looted the palace.

06:01:15.240 --> 06:01:17.520
He whirled toward Moon.

06:01:17.580 --> 06:01:19.799
Which try would you say is the

06:01:19.799 --> 06:01:20.220
wealthiest?

06:01:20.279 --> 06:01:22.259
The wealthiest?

06:01:22.319 --> 06:01:23.159
Moon said.

06:01:23.220 --> 06:01:24.419
I don't know.

06:01:24.479 --> 06:01:26.459
I mean, how would anyone know that?

06:01:26.520 --> 06:01:29.700
Which tribe has the most treasure?

06:01:29.700 --> 06:01:31.439
he asked edgily.

06:01:31.500 --> 06:01:32.759
What would you guess?

06:01:32.819 --> 06:01:34.380
I don't need exact numbers.

06:01:34.439 --> 06:01:36.900
In all those scrolls of yours, which

06:01:36.900 --> 06:01:39.900
queens buy the most extravagant things

06:01:39.900 --> 06:01:41.520
which castles are the most full of

06:01:41.520 --> 06:01:42.060
jewels.

06:01:42.119 --> 06:01:45.240
He shot anemone, a suspicious look.

06:01:45.299 --> 06:01:48.240
Um, all of them?

06:01:48.299 --> 06:01:50.220
Except the rain wings.

06:01:50.279 --> 06:01:53.099
Moon said awkwardly, but maybe the sky

06:01:53.099 --> 06:01:56.159
wings have a lot because of scarlet, and

06:01:56.159 --> 06:01:57.900
the sand wing treasury was supposed to be

06:01:57.900 --> 06:01:59.939
one of the greatest in the world before

06:01:59.939 --> 06:02:01.860
the war, and the whole lie about the

06:02:01.860 --> 06:02:03.419
scavengers stealing all of it.

06:02:03.540 --> 06:02:05.700
Sandwings.

06:02:05.759 --> 06:02:07.919
Dark Stalker hissed.

06:02:07.979 --> 06:02:10.080
They barely hide any treasure in my

06:02:10.080 --> 06:02:10.380
time.

06:02:10.439 --> 06:02:11.759
It must have been them.

06:02:11.880 --> 06:02:15.119
He wrapped the wall with one claw and

06:02:15.119 --> 06:02:15.720
turned away again.

06:02:15.779 --> 06:02:17.159
All right.

06:02:17.220 --> 06:02:18.840
Anemone, come along.

06:02:18.900 --> 06:02:23.459
Princess anemone. she said, tossing her

06:02:23.459 --> 06:02:23.639
head.

06:02:23.700 --> 06:02:27.000
Dark Stalker sped up, whisked around a

06:02:27.000 --> 06:02:29.099
corner, and threw open a huge set of

06:02:29.099 --> 06:02:29.880
black doors.

06:02:29.939 --> 06:02:33.840
Here you go, he said, with a strange

06:02:33.840 --> 06:02:34.740
gleam in his eyes.

06:02:34.799 --> 06:02:37.020
The perfect suite for you.

06:02:37.020 --> 06:02:40.860
Decorated with a sea wing in mind, 2000

06:02:40.860 --> 06:02:41.459
years ago.

06:02:41.520 --> 06:02:44.520
In fact, your own ancestors stayed in

06:02:44.520 --> 06:02:45.299
these very rooms.

06:02:45.419 --> 06:02:47.159
Fathom?

06:02:47.220 --> 06:02:48.419
Turtle blurted.

06:02:48.479 --> 06:02:51.540
Anemone looked curiously from him to Dark

06:02:51.540 --> 06:02:53.220
Stalker, expecting an answer.

06:02:53.279 --> 06:02:55.080
Kinkaju jumped in quickly.

06:02:55.139 --> 06:02:57.180
Was that Fathom?

06:02:57.180 --> 06:02:57.779
she asked.

06:02:57.840 --> 06:02:59.459
Yes.

06:02:59.520 --> 06:03:01.139
Dog stalker said.

06:03:01.200 --> 06:03:04.380
He glanced at Moon and steeled his face

06:03:04.380 --> 06:03:05.759
as though hiding his true feelings from

06:03:05.759 --> 06:03:05.939
her.

06:03:06.000 --> 06:03:08.459
He stepped through into the main bedroom

06:03:08.459 --> 06:03:11.220
his black eyes studying every inch of the

06:03:11.220 --> 06:03:11.759
space.

06:03:11.759 --> 06:03:14.400
This is where our queen put him.

06:03:14.520 --> 06:03:16.319
When she brought him over from the

06:03:16.319 --> 06:03:19.919
kingdom of the sea, to educate me about

06:03:19.919 --> 06:03:21.419
the perils of animus magic.

06:03:21.479 --> 06:03:25.259
Oh, Anemone stepped around him and

06:03:25.259 --> 06:03:25.860
sneezed.

06:03:25.919 --> 06:03:26.880
Huh.

06:03:26.939 --> 06:03:28.080
This is it?

06:03:28.139 --> 06:03:30.299
It's not what I pictured.

06:03:30.360 --> 06:03:33.299
She peered into a dry, cracked pool in

06:03:33.299 --> 06:03:33.659
the floor.

06:03:33.720 --> 06:03:36.540
Her tail bombed one of the tattered, moth

06:03:36.540 --> 06:03:39.180
eaten cushions, sending up a halo of dust

06:03:39.180 --> 06:03:40.259
and she sneezed again.

06:03:40.319 --> 06:03:44.580
So, use your magic to clean it up, Dark

06:03:44.580 --> 06:03:45.779
Stalker said impatiently.

06:03:45.840 --> 06:03:48.479
Or better yet, learn how to use a mop and

06:03:48.479 --> 06:03:49.020
your own claws.

06:03:49.080 --> 06:03:51.840
Where does Moon get to stay?

06:03:51.900 --> 06:03:53.340
Anemone demanded.

06:03:53.400 --> 06:03:56.459
Wherever she likes, Dog Stalker

06:03:56.459 --> 06:03:56.819
answered.

06:03:56.880 --> 06:03:59.099
If she decides to stay, that is.

06:03:59.159 --> 06:04:02.400
He turned to Moon with a smile, let's go

06:04:02.400 --> 06:04:03.659
see how the gardens have turned out.

06:04:03.720 --> 06:04:06.779
He bounded out the door again, but Moon

06:04:06.779 --> 06:04:08.279
lingered for a moment after he left.

06:04:08.340 --> 06:04:11.459
I think the room is really nice, Anemone

06:04:11.459 --> 06:04:11.939
she said.

06:04:12.000 --> 06:04:13.979
It has a balcony and everything.

06:04:14.040 --> 06:04:18.119
You would think it's nice, said Anemone.

06:04:18.180 --> 06:04:20.759
You grew up in a gross muddy fern gully

06:04:20.759 --> 06:04:21.599
in a rainforest.

06:04:21.659 --> 06:04:23.459
I am a princess.

06:04:23.520 --> 06:04:26.040
I have always lived in a palace, and I've

06:04:26.040 --> 06:04:27.599
never had to clean my own room.

06:04:27.659 --> 06:04:28.979
The idea.

06:04:29.099 --> 06:04:31.799
I've never had to clean my room either.

06:04:31.860 --> 06:04:33.360
Kinkaju volunteered.

06:04:33.419 --> 06:04:36.180
I mean, I don't have a room, but I have a

06:04:36.180 --> 06:04:36.659
hammock.

06:04:36.720 --> 06:04:38.759
Sometimes I shake it really hard to get

06:04:38.759 --> 06:04:40.380
all the leaves and bugs out.

06:04:40.439 --> 06:04:40.799
Does that count?

06:04:40.860 --> 06:04:42.659
Moon.

06:04:42.720 --> 06:04:44.340
Dark Stalker called.

06:04:44.400 --> 06:04:45.840
Anemone stamped her foot.

06:04:45.900 --> 06:04:48.299
Why doesn't he want to show me the

06:04:48.299 --> 06:04:48.659
gardens?

06:04:48.779 --> 06:04:50.459
She scowled at Moon?

06:04:50.580 --> 06:04:53.340
The minute you show up, suddenly you're

06:04:53.340 --> 06:04:54.959
the only dragon he wants to talk to.

06:04:55.020 --> 06:04:57.060
I don't see what's so special about you.

06:04:57.119 --> 06:04:59.279
Nothing at all.

06:04:59.400 --> 06:05:00.360
Moon said.

06:05:00.419 --> 06:05:02.880
I'm just the 1st dragon he met when he

06:05:02.880 --> 06:05:03.419
woke up.

06:05:03.479 --> 06:05:04.380
I'd better go.

06:05:04.439 --> 06:05:06.240
She took a step backward.

06:05:06.299 --> 06:05:09.060
No, Anemone barked.

06:05:09.119 --> 06:05:11.159
If you're so wonderful and amazing.

06:05:11.220 --> 06:05:13.319
Why don't you clean my room?

06:05:13.439 --> 06:05:16.560
She grabbed a talon full of loose pebbles

06:05:16.560 --> 06:05:16.979
from the floor.

06:05:17.040 --> 06:05:20.279
Turn into a bucket of water and a mop, she

06:05:20.279 --> 06:05:22.919
ordered, and instantly a long mop and a

06:05:22.919 --> 06:05:24.419
pail of water appeared in her claws.

06:05:24.479 --> 06:05:27.180
She held up the mop and pointed at Moon.

06:05:27.240 --> 06:05:30.479
Now go hit that dragon really hard until

06:05:30.479 --> 06:05:32.340
she starts using you to clean this place

06:05:32.340 --> 06:05:34.919
and don't let her stop until I say it's

06:05:34.919 --> 06:05:35.099
done.

06:05:35.159 --> 06:05:39.720
Chapter 18.

06:05:39.959 --> 06:05:42.479
What?

06:05:42.599 --> 06:05:44.040
Kinkachu yelped.

06:05:44.099 --> 06:05:45.659
Anemone!

06:05:45.720 --> 06:05:46.500
Turtle cried.

06:05:46.560 --> 06:05:48.599
The mop sailed across the room and

06:05:48.599 --> 06:05:50.939
wrapped moon sharply on the snout as she

06:05:50.939 --> 06:05:51.659
tried to back away.

06:05:51.720 --> 06:05:55.080
Ow, moon cried, fending it off.

06:05:55.139 --> 06:05:55.979
Stop.

06:05:56.099 --> 06:05:58.919
The mob evaded her talons and whapped her

06:05:58.919 --> 06:05:59.279
again.

06:05:59.340 --> 06:06:02.520
Tears of pain sprang into Moon's eyes, and

06:06:02.520 --> 06:06:04.439
she grabbed the handle, wrestling it down

06:06:04.439 --> 06:06:04.979
to the floor.

06:06:05.040 --> 06:06:06.779
What are you doing?

06:06:06.840 --> 06:06:08.639
She shouted at anemone.

06:06:08.700 --> 06:06:10.139
I'm not going to let you hurt me.

06:06:10.200 --> 06:06:13.439
Neither am I. Kinkachu yelled.

06:06:13.500 --> 06:06:15.479
She dashed over and threw herself on the

06:06:15.479 --> 06:06:17.520
mop, helping moon pin it to the ground.

06:06:17.580 --> 06:06:21.180
Anemone, Turtle said helplessly.

06:06:21.240 --> 06:06:22.200
Stop this.

06:06:22.319 --> 06:06:25.259
But his sister was busy scooping up

06:06:25.259 --> 06:06:26.880
another talon full of pebbles.

06:06:26.939 --> 06:06:29.939
Turn into opals and sapphires, she

06:06:29.939 --> 06:06:32.159
ordered them, and go distract Dark

06:06:32.159 --> 06:06:33.779
Stalker, so he doesn't come looking for

06:06:33.779 --> 06:06:34.020
her.

06:06:34.080 --> 06:06:37.319
She opened her claws, and a glittering

06:06:37.319 --> 06:06:39.720
constellation of blue and iridescent gems

06:06:39.720 --> 06:06:42.000
shot out the door, tumbling over one

06:06:42.000 --> 06:06:43.259
another in the air.

06:06:43.319 --> 06:06:46.319
There anemone said, satisfied.

06:06:46.380 --> 06:06:48.119
Now he won't come rescue you.

06:06:48.180 --> 06:06:50.939
And hey, he did say I should use my magic

06:06:50.939 --> 06:06:53.159
to clean up, just stop fighting and do

06:06:53.159 --> 06:06:53.400
it.

06:06:53.459 --> 06:06:55.979
She made a sweeping gesture with one

06:06:55.979 --> 06:06:58.380
talon, and the mob's long handle shot

06:06:58.380 --> 06:07:00.959
upright, cracking kinkaju in the jaw.

06:07:01.020 --> 06:07:02.639
Yowch!

06:07:02.759 --> 06:07:03.900
Kinkaju roared.

06:07:04.020 --> 06:07:06.959
Turtle jumped forward, but he didn't know

06:07:06.959 --> 06:07:07.319
what to do.

06:07:07.380 --> 06:07:09.060
Should he cast a spell?

06:07:09.119 --> 06:07:11.279
Would it be hidden by Anemone's other

06:07:11.279 --> 06:07:11.939
magic in here?

06:07:12.000 --> 06:07:13.200
What could he do?

06:07:13.259 --> 06:07:14.759
Enchant the mop?

06:07:14.819 --> 06:07:16.319
Or enchant anemone?

06:07:16.380 --> 06:07:18.720
But then she'd know he was an animus.

06:07:18.779 --> 06:07:20.939
This seemed like perhaps not the best

06:07:20.939 --> 06:07:21.959
time to reveal that.

06:07:22.020 --> 06:07:24.540
Still, he had to do something to help

06:07:24.540 --> 06:07:25.740
Kinkaju and Moon.

06:07:25.799 --> 06:07:27.900
What would the hapless sidekick do in

06:07:27.900 --> 06:07:28.380
this situation?

06:07:28.439 --> 06:07:30.360
A heartfelt speech.

06:07:30.419 --> 06:07:32.639
There was always a right thing to say

06:07:32.639 --> 06:07:33.240
wasn't there?

06:07:33.299 --> 06:07:35.939
Even the sidekick sometimes got a decent

06:07:35.939 --> 06:07:38.040
useful speech, he could talk her down.

06:07:38.099 --> 06:07:39.900
She was his sister after all.

06:07:39.959 --> 06:07:42.119
Anemone.

06:07:42.180 --> 06:07:44.880
Think about what you're doing, he started

06:07:44.880 --> 06:07:45.959
his voice cracking.

06:07:46.020 --> 06:07:48.119
Blah, blah, blah.

06:07:48.180 --> 06:07:50.700
Anemone said, flapping her claws at him.

06:07:50.759 --> 06:07:52.560
Quit your jellyfishing turtle.

06:07:52.619 --> 06:07:54.479
I'll let your girlfriend and her annoying

06:07:54.479 --> 06:07:55.979
friend go in a minute.

06:07:56.040 --> 06:07:58.560
I just don't get what Dark Stalker sees

06:07:58.560 --> 06:07:59.700
in Moon, do you?

06:07:59.759 --> 06:08:01.139
She's nobody special.

06:08:01.200 --> 06:08:02.340
Not like me.

06:08:02.400 --> 06:08:05.220
A slow smile spread across her face.

06:08:05.340 --> 06:08:08.099
Maybe I just need to make him realize

06:08:08.099 --> 06:08:08.400
that.

06:08:08.459 --> 06:08:11.819
Anemone swept over to the dry fountain

06:08:11.819 --> 06:08:14.459
and fished something out of it, some kind

06:08:14.459 --> 06:08:16.080
of small device that looked like a

06:08:16.080 --> 06:08:17.939
telescope and an hourglass stuck

06:08:17.939 --> 06:08:18.419
together.

06:08:18.479 --> 06:08:21.180
What in the moons is this?

06:08:21.240 --> 06:08:24.060
Anemone turned it over in her claws for a

06:08:24.060 --> 06:08:26.400
moment, shrugged, and tossed it aside.

06:08:26.459 --> 06:08:28.919
She plucked a piece of broken tile out of

06:08:28.919 --> 06:08:29.279
the pool.

06:08:29.340 --> 06:08:33.000
Turn into an earring, she commanded the

06:08:33.000 --> 06:08:33.479
tile.

06:08:33.540 --> 06:08:36.180
Something really sparkly and cool that

06:08:36.180 --> 06:08:37.319
dark stalker would like.

06:08:37.439 --> 06:08:40.380
A twisty silver snake with ruby eyes

06:08:40.380 --> 06:08:42.299
appeared in her talon.

06:08:42.360 --> 06:08:42.779
Perfect.

06:08:42.840 --> 06:08:45.900
Now, earring, as soon as Dark Stalker

06:08:45.900 --> 06:08:47.819
puts you on, I want you to make him stop

06:08:47.819 --> 06:08:49.139
caring about Moon at all.

06:08:49.200 --> 06:08:51.659
She'll be just another random dragon

06:08:51.659 --> 06:08:54.240
bothering him, and I'll be the only

06:08:54.240 --> 06:08:55.680
dragon he finds interesting.

06:08:55.740 --> 06:08:59.759
You can't do that to him, Turtle said.

06:08:59.819 --> 06:09:00.779
Can you?

06:09:00.840 --> 06:09:03.840
Would a spell like that even work on Dark

06:09:03.840 --> 06:09:04.380
Stalker?

06:09:04.439 --> 06:09:07.020
If it did, maybe it would be a good

06:09:07.020 --> 06:09:07.319
thing.

06:09:07.380 --> 06:09:10.080
Maybe it would help Turtle get Moon away

06:09:10.080 --> 06:09:11.700
from Dark Stalker's influence.

06:09:11.759 --> 06:09:14.279
Maybe it would keep her safer from him

06:09:14.279 --> 06:09:15.479
than she would otherwise be.

06:09:15.540 --> 06:09:19.020
I should enchant that earring too, he

06:09:19.020 --> 06:09:20.099
realized suddenly.

06:09:20.159 --> 06:09:21.779
But with what spell?

06:09:21.840 --> 06:09:24.119
What's the right spell to put on Dark

06:09:24.119 --> 06:09:25.560
Stalker if I had the chance?

06:09:25.619 --> 06:09:28.080
Another sleeping spell?

06:09:28.139 --> 06:09:30.419
Or something to make other dragons see

06:09:30.419 --> 06:09:33.060
him the way he really was, a spell to

06:09:33.060 --> 06:09:36.180
make him reveal all his secret plans, or

06:09:36.180 --> 06:09:38.340
a spell that could kill him.

06:09:38.400 --> 06:09:40.560
Could I really do that?

06:09:40.619 --> 06:09:42.720
Is that what he deserves?

06:09:42.779 --> 06:09:46.080
His brain offered up a flash of a lonely

06:09:46.080 --> 06:09:48.180
dark stalker in the school gardens last

06:09:48.180 --> 06:09:51.419
night, missing his lost love, and then

06:09:51.419 --> 06:09:53.580
another flash of blood staining his own

06:09:53.580 --> 06:09:54.060
claws.

06:09:54.180 --> 06:09:57.360
Am I a dragon who could kill someone?

06:09:57.419 --> 06:09:58.799
Anyone?

06:09:58.860 --> 06:10:00.000
Even him?

06:10:00.060 --> 06:10:03.479
If I did, would that tip my soul into

06:10:03.479 --> 06:10:03.900
darkness?

06:10:03.959 --> 06:10:07.439
Is that the choice I make that leads to

06:10:07.439 --> 06:10:09.119
me attacking my sister on a beach?

06:10:09.180 --> 06:10:12.720
You, you jackdaw!

06:10:12.779 --> 06:10:15.779
Kinkatu yelled at anemone, coiling her

06:10:15.779 --> 06:10:17.400
tail around the mop and leaning on it

06:10:17.400 --> 06:10:20.459
with all her weight, you overripe melon.

06:10:20.520 --> 06:10:22.619
Next to her, moon was struggling

06:10:22.619 --> 06:10:23.099
silently.

06:10:23.159 --> 06:10:25.919
You're being absolutely horrible.

06:10:26.040 --> 06:10:26.880
Kingaju yelled.

06:10:26.939 --> 06:10:30.000
Oh, turtle, is this her losing her soul?

06:10:30.060 --> 06:10:31.319
Is she turning evil?

06:10:31.380 --> 06:10:33.119
Is it?

06:10:33.240 --> 06:10:35.099
Turtle thought with horror.

06:10:35.159 --> 06:10:37.139
He'd stopped worrying about that after

06:10:37.139 --> 06:10:39.599
she put on the silver necklace, but if it

06:10:39.599 --> 06:10:40.020
didn't work.

06:10:40.080 --> 06:10:42.900
Or if the spell on it wasn't quite what

06:10:42.900 --> 06:10:43.740
she thought it was.

06:10:43.860 --> 06:10:45.419
Ha!

06:10:45.479 --> 06:10:46.560
Anemone cried.

06:10:46.619 --> 06:10:47.759
I'm not evil.

06:10:47.819 --> 06:10:49.740
My soul is protected, remember?

06:10:49.799 --> 06:10:51.000
I've seen evil.

06:10:51.060 --> 06:10:52.680
This isn't evil at all.

06:10:52.740 --> 06:10:55.560
This is just a princess dealing with one

06:10:55.560 --> 06:10:56.819
of her pesky problems.

06:10:56.880 --> 06:10:59.880
She held up the earring and dangled it in

06:10:59.880 --> 06:11:00.659
Moon's direction.

06:11:00.720 --> 06:11:03.299
What else should I do with my magic, do

06:11:03.299 --> 06:11:03.540
you think?

06:11:03.599 --> 06:11:06.959
Ooh, I can make him give me the queen's

06:11:06.959 --> 06:11:07.319
rooms.

06:11:07.439 --> 06:11:10.259
Or I could make him build me my own

06:11:10.259 --> 06:11:12.419
palace right next to this one.

06:11:12.479 --> 06:11:15.599
She breathed out a contented sigh and

06:11:15.599 --> 06:11:16.439
touched her necklace.

06:11:16.500 --> 06:11:19.200
Life is so much easier now that I can do

06:11:19.200 --> 06:11:19.919
anything I want.

06:11:19.979 --> 06:11:22.619
I wouldn't be so sure of that.

06:11:22.680 --> 06:11:25.860
Moon said, looking over Anemone's

06:11:25.860 --> 06:11:26.159
shoulder.

06:11:26.220 --> 06:11:28.619
Anemone.

06:11:28.680 --> 06:11:32.220
Dark Stalker's menacing voice rumbled

06:11:32.220 --> 06:11:33.720
like an earthquake rising through

06:11:33.720 --> 06:11:35.099
turtle's claws.

06:11:35.159 --> 06:11:36.900
Explain yourself.

06:11:36.959 --> 06:11:39.959
The enormous Nightwing stepped through

06:11:39.959 --> 06:11:41.759
the door and made a gesture toward Moon.

06:11:41.819 --> 06:11:44.459
The mob clattered to the ground, harmless

06:11:44.459 --> 06:11:44.939
once more.

06:11:45.000 --> 06:11:47.459
Kinkachu put one wing around Moon.

06:11:47.520 --> 06:11:50.639
Anemone swung around to Dark Stalker with

06:11:50.639 --> 06:11:52.740
a sweet, practiced smile on her face.

06:11:52.860 --> 06:11:54.299
There you are.

06:11:54.360 --> 06:11:55.619
Oh, this is nothing.

06:11:55.680 --> 06:11:56.159
Don't worry.

06:11:56.220 --> 06:11:58.319
I was trying to clean up, and the mop

06:11:58.319 --> 06:12:00.360
went a bit haywire, and these 2 decided

06:12:00.360 --> 06:12:02.220
to tackle it, so weird.

06:12:02.279 --> 06:12:04.380
But look, I found this really cool

06:12:04.380 --> 06:12:06.180
earring in one of the side tables.

06:12:06.240 --> 06:12:07.560
Isn't it perfect for you?

06:12:07.619 --> 06:12:09.900
Liar!

06:12:09.959 --> 06:12:11.279
Kinkaju yelled.

06:12:11.340 --> 06:12:12.959
The Dark Stalker ignored her.

06:12:13.020 --> 06:12:16.139
He stepped forward to loom over anemone

06:12:16.139 --> 06:12:18.540
and she backed into a wall, babbling.

06:12:18.659 --> 06:12:21.479
I mean, the king of the night wing should

06:12:21.479 --> 06:12:23.040
really wear the best jewelry, don't you

06:12:23.040 --> 06:12:23.220
think?

06:12:23.279 --> 06:12:28.860
I don't accept gifts, from animus dragons

06:12:28.860 --> 06:12:31.799
he growled, especially from deceitful

06:12:31.799 --> 06:12:33.540
conniving sea wings.

06:12:33.599 --> 06:12:36.659
What kind of idiot do you think I am, that

06:12:36.659 --> 06:12:37.860
I would fall for a trick like that?

06:12:37.919 --> 06:12:39.779
It's not a trick.

06:12:39.840 --> 06:12:41.459
Anemone protested.

06:12:41.520 --> 06:12:43.380
It's just a pretty earring.

06:12:43.439 --> 06:12:45.060
Squid guts.

06:12:45.119 --> 06:12:46.560
You don't have to be so paranoid.

06:12:46.619 --> 06:12:48.479
She laughed nervously.

06:12:48.599 --> 06:12:50.759
Spare me your lies.

06:12:50.819 --> 06:12:52.619
Dark Stalker spat.

06:12:52.680 --> 06:12:53.819
I heard everything.

06:12:53.880 --> 06:12:57.119
He uncurled his talon, scattering the

06:12:57.119 --> 06:12:58.560
dust of gemstones at her feet.

06:12:58.619 --> 06:13:02.520
You thought these baubles would distract

06:13:02.520 --> 06:13:03.779
me so you could hurt Moon.

06:13:03.900 --> 06:13:06.119
He snatched the earring out of her

06:13:06.119 --> 06:13:06.540
claws.

06:13:06.599 --> 06:13:10.259
You plan to manipulate my emotions, to

06:13:10.259 --> 06:13:12.720
cast a spell on me.

06:13:12.779 --> 06:13:17.520
Just a little one, Anemone stammered.

06:13:17.580 --> 06:13:20.400
I just want you to be my mentor and only

06:13:20.400 --> 06:13:21.779
pay attention to me, that's all.

06:13:21.840 --> 06:13:25.439
Don't be angry at her dark stalker, Moon

06:13:25.439 --> 06:13:25.799
said.

06:13:25.919 --> 06:13:27.900
Her sides heaving as she caught her

06:13:27.900 --> 06:13:28.200
breath.

06:13:28.259 --> 06:13:29.520
She's young.

06:13:29.580 --> 06:13:31.979
It was just a mistake, and I'm fine.

06:13:32.040 --> 06:13:35.580
I will not have dragons stolen from me.

06:13:35.700 --> 06:13:37.860
Dark Stalker snarled.

06:13:37.919 --> 06:13:39.299
Not ever again.

06:13:39.419 --> 06:13:42.360
He reached one talent toward moon and

06:13:42.360 --> 06:13:45.060
Kinkachu, and made an odd circling motion

06:13:45.060 --> 06:13:45.900
with his claws.

06:13:45.959 --> 06:13:48.599
Instantly moon stopped moving, as though

06:13:48.599 --> 06:13:50.520
she'd been frozen, staring forward

06:13:50.520 --> 06:13:52.200
blankly with unblinking eyes.

06:13:52.259 --> 06:13:55.500
Kingachu let out a small gasp and reached

06:13:55.500 --> 06:13:56.340
toward her friend.

06:13:56.400 --> 06:14:00.540
Oh, no, Turtle thought frantically, that

06:14:00.540 --> 06:14:02.639
spell is supposed to be on Kinkachu too.

06:14:02.700 --> 06:14:05.040
Dark Stalker is going to notice that his

06:14:05.040 --> 06:14:06.240
magic doesn't work on her.

06:14:06.299 --> 06:14:10.259
Dark stalker frowned at Kinkaju, then

06:14:10.259 --> 06:14:11.159
down at his talon.

06:14:11.220 --> 06:14:14.279
Turtle hissed, catching Kinkaju's

06:14:14.279 --> 06:14:16.080
attention, and pretended to freeze in

06:14:16.080 --> 06:14:16.560
place.

06:14:16.619 --> 06:14:18.419
Light dawned in her eyes.

06:14:18.479 --> 06:14:20.759
When Dark Stalker reached toward her

06:14:20.759 --> 06:14:22.979
again, she immediately froze where she

06:14:22.979 --> 06:14:25.500
was, mimicking Moon's blank stare.

06:14:25.619 --> 06:14:26.939
Good.

06:14:27.000 --> 06:14:29.279
Turtle thought, although his heart was

06:14:29.279 --> 06:14:29.880
still pounding.

06:14:29.939 --> 06:14:31.200
Now hold that.

06:14:31.259 --> 06:14:32.639
Don't give yourself away.

06:14:32.700 --> 06:14:35.880
Luckily, Dark Stalker turned his back on

06:14:35.880 --> 06:14:38.459
Kinkaju almost immediately, focusing his

06:14:38.459 --> 06:14:39.599
attention on anemone.

06:14:39.659 --> 06:14:42.119
It's time for you to go, princess.

06:14:42.180 --> 06:14:43.680
He growled.

06:14:43.740 --> 06:14:45.540
What do you mean, go?

06:14:45.599 --> 06:14:47.099
Anemone cried.

06:14:47.159 --> 06:14:47.580
Go where?

06:14:47.639 --> 06:14:50.340
She glanced anxiously at Moon and

06:14:50.340 --> 06:14:51.060
Kinkaju.

06:14:51.119 --> 06:14:52.319
What did you do to them?

06:14:52.380 --> 06:14:55.979
They don't need to hear this part.

06:14:56.040 --> 06:14:58.500
Dark Stalker said softly.

06:14:58.560 --> 06:15:01.080
It's time for you to go back to the

06:15:01.080 --> 06:15:01.919
kingdom of the sea.

06:15:01.979 --> 06:15:04.080
What is he doing?

06:15:04.200 --> 06:15:06.299
Turtle thought in a panic.

06:15:06.360 --> 06:15:07.919
Is he putting a spell on my sister?

06:15:08.040 --> 06:15:10.259
But I don't want to.

06:15:10.380 --> 06:15:12.119
Anemone stamped her foot.

06:15:12.180 --> 06:15:13.979
I hate it there.

06:15:14.040 --> 06:15:15.840
I want to stay with you and learn about

06:15:15.840 --> 06:15:16.619
being an animus.

06:15:16.680 --> 06:15:19.500
You know all you need to know.

06:15:19.560 --> 06:15:21.900
Dark Stalker said.

06:15:21.959 --> 06:15:24.540
His voice seemed to be getting colder and

06:15:24.540 --> 06:15:25.200
darker.

06:15:25.259 --> 06:15:27.959
Like water from the deepest ocean depths

06:15:27.959 --> 06:15:30.119
curling slowly into turtles' ears.

06:15:30.180 --> 06:15:33.299
You know what albatross did.

06:15:33.360 --> 06:15:36.540
You know how easily you could be queen.

06:15:36.599 --> 06:15:39.180
You know that nobody can stand in your

06:15:39.180 --> 06:15:39.479
way.

06:15:39.540 --> 06:15:42.419
If you decide to go take the sea wing

06:15:42.419 --> 06:15:46.200
throne, right now, is...

06:15:47.040 --> 06:15:48.060
Is that what you want me to do?

06:15:48.119 --> 06:15:49.560
Anemone asked.

06:15:49.619 --> 06:15:53.220
I don't care what you do, said Dark

06:15:53.220 --> 06:15:53.700
Stalker.

06:15:53.759 --> 06:15:56.220
I was beginning to think you could be a

06:15:56.220 --> 06:15:56.639
worthy student.

06:15:56.759 --> 06:15:59.220
And perhaps I should keep you around

06:15:59.220 --> 06:15:59.700
after all.

06:15:59.759 --> 06:16:03.060
I thought you might, be someone who could

06:16:03.060 --> 06:16:04.080
work alongside me.

06:16:04.139 --> 06:16:07.740
He glanced at Moon, then fixed his cold

06:16:07.740 --> 06:16:08.939
black eyes on anemone.

06:16:09.000 --> 06:16:10.919
But I was an idiot.

06:16:10.979 --> 06:16:13.560
To let any affection for you creep in.

06:16:13.619 --> 06:16:16.680
You are truly Fathom's descendant.

06:16:16.740 --> 06:16:19.799
You're just as bad as he is, and I don't

06:16:19.799 --> 06:16:22.439
want you anywhere near me.

06:16:22.500 --> 06:16:25.860
I can't help ping Fathom's descendant

06:16:25.860 --> 06:16:27.240
anemone cried.

06:16:27.299 --> 06:16:28.439
I'm sorry, all right?

06:16:28.500 --> 06:16:30.479
I won't try to cast any more spells on

06:16:30.479 --> 06:16:31.200
you, I promise.

06:16:31.259 --> 06:16:33.959
It wouldn't have worked anyway.

06:16:34.020 --> 06:16:37.319
Dark Stalker said, flicking the earring

06:16:37.319 --> 06:16:37.619
at her.

06:16:37.680 --> 06:16:40.259
It bounced off her forehead and skidded

06:16:40.259 --> 06:16:40.799
across the floor.

06:16:40.860 --> 06:16:43.740
None of your spells will ever work on

06:16:43.740 --> 06:16:43.979
me.

06:16:44.040 --> 06:16:46.380
I protected myself from your magic.

06:16:46.439 --> 06:16:47.520
Now get out.

06:16:47.580 --> 06:16:50.159
Go kill your mother if you want.

06:16:50.220 --> 06:16:52.619
Feel free to kill any other dragons who

06:16:52.619 --> 06:16:53.220
stand in your way.

06:16:53.340 --> 06:16:56.040
He made the circling motion with his

06:16:56.040 --> 06:16:56.580
claws again.

06:16:56.639 --> 06:17:00.000
Moon took a breath in, glancing around as

06:17:00.000 --> 06:17:02.099
though mildly puzzled, and Kingachu

06:17:02.099 --> 06:17:03.000
imitated her a moment later.

06:17:03.060 --> 06:17:06.599
You won't be able to hurt Moon anymore

06:17:06.599 --> 06:17:09.720
Dark Stalker said, sweeping one wing

06:17:09.720 --> 06:17:12.060
toward the doorway, so don't even try.

06:17:12.180 --> 06:17:15.779
This isn't fair, Anemone yelled.

06:17:15.840 --> 06:17:16.979
It's not fair.

06:17:17.040 --> 06:17:19.680
She bolted toward the balcony instead.

06:17:19.740 --> 06:17:22.259
Then turned back, framed by the gray

06:17:22.259 --> 06:17:22.919
light outside.

06:17:22.979 --> 06:17:25.560
I'll show you how special and important I

06:17:25.560 --> 06:17:25.860
am.

06:17:25.919 --> 06:17:26.819
You'll see.

06:17:26.880 --> 06:17:29.159
She flung herself into the air.

06:17:29.220 --> 06:17:31.259
Anemone.

06:17:31.319 --> 06:17:34.860
Turtle's chest ached, as though all his

06:17:34.860 --> 06:17:36.840
guilt had become bolders piled on his

06:17:36.840 --> 06:17:37.080
heart.

06:17:37.139 --> 06:17:38.880
This is my fault.

06:17:38.939 --> 06:17:40.799
This is my fault.

06:17:40.860 --> 06:17:43.560
I can't believe she did that.

06:17:43.619 --> 06:17:44.819
Kinkachu said.

06:17:44.880 --> 06:17:46.259
Moon, are you all right?

06:17:46.319 --> 06:17:49.380
Did she cast any spells on you?

06:17:49.439 --> 06:17:51.840
Dark Stalker asked gently.

06:17:51.959 --> 06:17:53.459
Not on me.

06:17:53.520 --> 06:17:54.240
No.

06:17:54.299 --> 06:17:56.700
Moon said, in a shaky voice.

06:17:56.759 --> 06:17:58.319
I don't think so.

06:17:58.380 --> 06:18:00.599
Just on the mop and the earring.

06:18:00.659 --> 06:18:02.159
Three moons.

06:18:02.220 --> 06:18:04.500
I didn't realize how upset she was with

06:18:04.500 --> 06:18:04.680
me.

06:18:04.740 --> 06:18:06.779
Did you see that in her mind?

06:18:06.840 --> 06:18:08.580
She asked Dark Stalker.

06:18:08.639 --> 06:18:09.959
A little.

06:18:10.020 --> 06:18:12.419
But I didn't think it would escalate so

06:18:12.419 --> 06:18:14.459
quickly either, he said.

06:18:14.520 --> 06:18:16.139
Are you having a vision?

06:18:16.259 --> 06:18:18.479
Moon touched her temples.

06:18:18.540 --> 06:18:21.419
I have a vision headache, but nothing

06:18:21.419 --> 06:18:22.380
clears coming through.

06:18:22.439 --> 06:18:25.860
Or maybe you have a headache because you

06:18:25.860 --> 06:18:27.540
just got whacked in the head with a mop

06:18:27.540 --> 06:18:27.959
handle.

06:18:28.020 --> 06:18:30.240
Kinkaju suggested it sensibly.

06:18:30.299 --> 06:18:34.200
No, it's, I think it's some danger in the

06:18:34.200 --> 06:18:36.060
kingdom of the sea, Moon said.

06:18:36.180 --> 06:18:38.400
Her worried eyes met turtles.

06:18:38.459 --> 06:18:40.680
Cold terror ran through him.

06:18:40.740 --> 06:18:43.919
Was anemone really going back home, right

06:18:43.919 --> 06:18:46.080
now, to kill mother and steal the

06:18:46.080 --> 06:18:46.380
throne?

06:18:46.500 --> 06:18:48.299
She wouldn't do that.

06:18:48.360 --> 06:18:49.439
He thought.

06:18:49.500 --> 06:18:53.159
And at the same moment, this new anemone

06:18:53.159 --> 06:18:53.459
might.

06:18:53.520 --> 06:18:56.700
This anemone who wants everything, who

06:18:56.700 --> 06:18:59.639
believes it should be hers, this anemone

06:18:59.639 --> 06:19:01.680
who uses her magic for selfish reasons

06:19:01.680 --> 06:19:04.919
who wants to impress dark stalker, this

06:19:04.919 --> 06:19:07.799
anemone, who acts as though her soul is

06:19:07.799 --> 06:19:08.819
damaged after all.

06:19:08.880 --> 06:19:12.240
The enchantment Dark Stalker did on her

06:19:12.240 --> 06:19:12.659
necklace.

06:19:12.720 --> 06:19:14.099
What if it was a lie?

06:19:14.159 --> 06:19:16.380
What if it didn't protect her soul?

06:19:16.439 --> 06:19:18.720
What if she'd been losing it bit by bit

06:19:18.720 --> 06:19:20.759
with each spell she cast?

06:19:20.819 --> 06:19:24.060
Including the one I asked her to cast on

06:19:24.060 --> 06:19:24.779
Kinkachu?

06:19:24.840 --> 06:19:26.520
Turtle thought with a wince.

06:19:26.580 --> 06:19:30.180
If that was true, the same thing could be

06:19:30.180 --> 06:19:31.799
happening to anemone that happened to

06:19:31.799 --> 06:19:34.680
albatross, their murderous ancestor all

06:19:34.680 --> 06:19:37.139
those centuries ago, and she could be

06:19:37.139 --> 06:19:39.419
flying home to follow in his footsteps

06:19:39.419 --> 06:19:40.139
right now.

06:19:40.200 --> 06:19:44.819
Chapter 19.

06:19:45.000 --> 06:19:50.040
I have to go after her, Turtle said, my

06:19:50.040 --> 06:19:51.299
tribe, my family.

06:19:51.360 --> 06:19:54.299
Kingaju took a step toward him.

06:19:54.360 --> 06:19:55.919
The dark stalker was already folding his

06:19:55.919 --> 06:19:57.180
wings around her and moon.

06:19:57.240 --> 06:20:02.220
Now, let's go see the gardens. he said

06:20:02.220 --> 06:20:04.619
and put all this unpleasantness behind

06:20:04.619 --> 06:20:04.979
us.

06:20:05.040 --> 06:20:08.040
But what if anemone does something

06:20:08.040 --> 06:20:11.220
terrible, Moon said to him, shouldn't we

06:20:11.220 --> 06:20:11.580
follow her?

06:20:11.639 --> 06:20:14.340
He looked down at her with sad eyes.

06:20:14.400 --> 06:20:17.099
In all the futures, I see.

06:20:17.159 --> 06:20:19.080
Following her only makes it worse.

06:20:19.139 --> 06:20:22.259
You and I are the last dragons she wants

06:20:22.259 --> 06:20:22.860
to see right now.

06:20:22.919 --> 06:20:26.040
But there's a good chance, she'll get

06:20:26.040 --> 06:20:27.479
tired after half a day of flying.

06:20:27.540 --> 06:20:30.419
Stop at Jade Mountain and stay there, safe

06:20:30.419 --> 06:20:31.439
and harmless.

06:20:31.500 --> 06:20:33.779
I think that's the most likely future.

06:20:33.900 --> 06:20:36.900
Turtles pounding heart disagreed.

06:20:36.959 --> 06:20:39.779
What if everything Dark Stalker said to

06:20:39.779 --> 06:20:41.759
her was a spell, and I didn't recognize

06:20:41.759 --> 06:20:41.939
it.

06:20:42.000 --> 06:20:45.119
What if Darkstalker has enchanted anemone

06:20:45.119 --> 06:20:45.720
to kill mother?

06:20:45.840 --> 06:20:48.959
To punish us all, for being Fathom's

06:20:48.959 --> 06:20:49.380
descendants.

06:20:49.500 --> 06:20:52.680
If that's true, there's no way I can stop

06:20:52.680 --> 06:20:52.919
her.

06:20:53.040 --> 06:20:55.560
There's almost certainly no way I can

06:20:55.560 --> 06:20:56.279
stop her anyhow.

06:20:56.400 --> 06:20:58.500
But I'm the only one who can even try.

06:20:58.560 --> 06:21:02.939
Stay with him, Turtle said to Kinkachu

06:21:02.939 --> 06:21:04.319
although his voice was shaking.

06:21:04.380 --> 06:21:06.000
You have to watch him.

06:21:06.060 --> 06:21:07.619
I'll go after anemone.

06:21:07.680 --> 06:21:09.779
By yourself?

06:21:09.840 --> 06:21:11.700
His mind screamed.

06:21:11.759 --> 06:21:13.319
Do you want everyone to die?

06:21:13.380 --> 06:21:16.439
He didn't have time to write to Kibley

06:21:16.439 --> 06:21:17.939
and Kibley wouldn't be able to help him

06:21:17.939 --> 06:21:18.419
anyway.

06:21:18.479 --> 06:21:20.939
Neither Kibley nor Kinkaju could follow

06:21:20.939 --> 06:21:21.840
him into the ocean.

06:21:21.900 --> 06:21:24.360
If that was really where anemone was

06:21:24.360 --> 06:21:26.880
headed, only Sea Wings could go as far

06:21:26.880 --> 06:21:28.500
underwater as the Deep Palace.

06:21:28.560 --> 06:21:31.500
He stepped onto the balcony and glanced

06:21:31.500 --> 06:21:31.740
back.

06:21:31.799 --> 06:21:34.979
Another part of him was screaming, don't

06:21:34.979 --> 06:21:35.880
leave Kinkaju here.

06:21:35.939 --> 06:21:36.779
It's not safe.

06:21:36.840 --> 06:21:39.240
What if he notices there's a spell on

06:21:39.240 --> 06:21:39.479
her?

06:21:39.540 --> 06:21:41.819
What if she's not the same when I get

06:21:41.819 --> 06:21:41.939
back?

06:21:42.000 --> 06:21:44.639
The 3 dragons were heading out through

06:21:44.639 --> 06:21:45.779
the main doors of the room.

06:21:45.840 --> 06:21:48.779
At the same moment, Kinkachu turned to

06:21:48.779 --> 06:21:49.619
look back at him.

06:21:49.680 --> 06:21:52.020
She gave him a reassuring smile and

06:21:52.020 --> 06:21:54.299
flared her wings, letting them turn pink

06:21:54.299 --> 06:21:55.080
along the edges.

06:21:55.139 --> 06:21:57.599
Then she followed Moon out the door, and

06:21:57.599 --> 06:21:57.900
was gone.

06:21:57.959 --> 06:22:02.759
And Turtle was aloft, flying, flying

06:22:02.759 --> 06:22:05.159
higher, beating his wings as hard and

06:22:05.159 --> 06:22:06.659
fast as he'd ever flown before.

06:22:06.720 --> 06:22:08.939
Could he catch anemone?

06:22:09.000 --> 06:22:11.040
If he did, could he stop her from

06:22:11.040 --> 06:22:12.119
whatever she was planning?

06:22:12.180 --> 06:22:15.540
She was smaller than him, but fast, and

06:22:15.540 --> 06:22:17.099
she might use her magic to make herself

06:22:17.099 --> 06:22:17.520
faster.

06:22:17.639 --> 06:22:20.939
Below him, the night wing city fell away

06:22:20.939 --> 06:22:23.819
and the mountains whipped past, craggy

06:22:23.819 --> 06:22:26.880
and jagged, like a dragon's spine, peaks

06:22:26.880 --> 06:22:28.619
reaching out like claws to snag his

06:22:28.619 --> 06:22:28.919
wings.

06:22:28.979 --> 06:22:31.319
The air currents were strange in these

06:22:31.319 --> 06:22:34.560
mountains, falling away in odd places, and

06:22:34.560 --> 06:22:36.240
he had to concentrate more than usual to

06:22:36.240 --> 06:22:36.779
stay aloft.

06:22:36.840 --> 06:22:39.779
Why couldn't he see her in the sky up

06:22:39.779 --> 06:22:40.080
ahead?

06:22:40.200 --> 06:22:41.939
Because she was too small?

06:22:42.000 --> 06:22:44.580
Because she blended in with a pale gray

06:22:44.580 --> 06:22:45.360
blue clouds?

06:22:45.419 --> 06:22:46.500
Where was she?

06:22:46.619 --> 06:22:49.680
He burst out of the mountains and veered

06:22:49.680 --> 06:22:52.200
east, following the same route they'd

06:22:52.200 --> 06:22:52.799
taken that morning.

06:22:52.860 --> 06:22:55.439
His wings were tiring already at this

06:22:55.439 --> 06:22:55.740
pace.

06:22:55.799 --> 06:22:58.619
There was no way he could keep it up all

06:22:58.619 --> 06:22:59.939
the way back to the kingdom of the sea.

06:23:00.000 --> 06:23:01.439
The sea.

06:23:01.500 --> 06:23:04.200
Turtle looked down at the dark waves

06:23:04.200 --> 06:23:06.299
pounding the beach below him.

06:23:06.360 --> 06:23:07.860
Maybe he could swim part of the way

06:23:07.860 --> 06:23:08.099
home.

06:23:08.159 --> 06:23:10.380
Maybe that's what anemone was doing.

06:23:10.439 --> 06:23:13.619
He tucked himself into a dive, plunging

06:23:13.619 --> 06:23:15.840
into the water, and nearly caving in his

06:23:15.840 --> 06:23:17.819
skull on an underwater boulder.

06:23:17.880 --> 06:23:21.840
Careful, careful, be more careful.

06:23:21.900 --> 06:23:23.700
Mustn't die before I get there.

06:23:23.759 --> 06:23:26.700
Although I might die when I get there.

06:23:26.759 --> 06:23:29.819
He found a rip current moving swiftly

06:23:29.819 --> 06:23:32.400
east and slipped into it, spreading his

06:23:32.400 --> 06:23:34.439
wings to catch as much of its speed as

06:23:34.439 --> 06:23:34.799
possible.

06:23:34.860 --> 06:23:37.560
Would anemone actually kill me?

06:23:37.619 --> 06:23:38.880
Her own brother.

06:23:38.939 --> 06:23:42.000
Killing Queen Coral was one thing.

06:23:42.060 --> 06:23:44.759
That was the only way for the next queen

06:23:44.759 --> 06:23:46.919
to take the throne, so every princess

06:23:46.919 --> 06:23:48.900
grew up without possibility in her mind.

06:23:49.020 --> 06:23:50.759
With the rest of the family?

06:23:50.819 --> 06:23:53.639
If she attacked them, that would have to

06:23:53.639 --> 06:23:56.279
mean she'd lost her soul, or she was

06:23:56.279 --> 06:23:57.720
under dark stalker's control.

06:23:57.779 --> 06:23:59.400
My family.

06:23:59.459 --> 06:24:02.700
Turtle thought, powering himself forward

06:24:02.700 --> 06:24:05.400
with talons and tail, my mother.

06:24:05.459 --> 06:24:09.000
Coral had never loved him or been at all

06:24:09.000 --> 06:24:11.040
interested in him, but he still loved

06:24:11.040 --> 06:24:11.580
her.

06:24:11.639 --> 06:24:14.159
The idea of her, and the stories she

06:24:14.159 --> 06:24:14.520
wrote.

06:24:14.580 --> 06:24:16.319
My brothers.

06:24:16.439 --> 06:24:19.500
The whole restless wrestling, teasing

06:24:19.500 --> 06:24:20.040
pack of them.

06:24:20.099 --> 06:24:23.700
Ants, and uncles, and cousins, my

06:24:23.700 --> 06:24:25.979
littlest sister, tiny Aucklet.

06:24:26.040 --> 06:24:28.680
He couldn't imagine anyone hurting a

06:24:28.680 --> 06:24:29.880
dragonette so small.

06:24:29.939 --> 06:24:32.459
Don't do this, anemone.

06:24:32.520 --> 06:24:34.560
Should he use his magic?

06:24:34.619 --> 06:24:35.340
Now?

06:24:35.400 --> 06:24:36.779
Should he try to stop her?

06:24:36.840 --> 06:24:39.479
Dark stalker might think he was sensing

06:24:39.479 --> 06:24:41.939
anemones magic, but what if he realized

06:24:41.939 --> 06:24:42.599
it wasn't?

06:24:42.659 --> 06:24:44.400
What if it made him suspicious?

06:24:44.520 --> 06:24:47.459
Drum beats of panic were thudding around

06:24:47.459 --> 06:24:49.200
and around in Turtle's head.

06:24:49.259 --> 06:24:50.700
He knew this feeling.

06:24:50.759 --> 06:24:53.099
He hated this feeling.

06:24:53.159 --> 06:24:55.680
The pressure pounded in rhythm with his

06:24:55.680 --> 06:24:56.400
wing strokes.

06:24:56.459 --> 06:25:00.599
Everything is resting on me, on me, on me

06:25:00.599 --> 06:25:04.020
and I will fail again, again, again.

06:25:04.080 --> 06:25:06.779
Searching and searching for Snapper

06:25:06.779 --> 06:25:09.840
knowing his father was waiting, knowing

06:25:09.840 --> 06:25:12.479
his father was counting on him, knowing

06:25:12.479 --> 06:25:15.000
he couldn't do it, knowing now what his

06:25:15.000 --> 06:25:17.159
father's disappointed face looked like

06:25:17.159 --> 06:25:19.680
and how all that disappointment would

06:25:19.680 --> 06:25:21.419
crush turtle into a nobody.

06:25:21.479 --> 06:25:24.180
This was exactly the same.

06:25:24.299 --> 06:25:27.060
Except the disappointed faces would be

06:25:27.060 --> 06:25:30.360
moons, and Kinkajoos, and Kibleys, and

06:25:30.360 --> 06:25:32.700
the dragons who died because of him would

06:25:32.700 --> 06:25:33.779
be his entire family.

06:25:33.840 --> 06:25:34.919
Maybe more.

06:25:34.979 --> 06:25:37.799
Maybe everyone, if anemone couldn't be

06:25:37.799 --> 06:25:38.040
stopped.

06:25:38.159 --> 06:25:41.040
The current veered north, and he went

06:25:41.040 --> 06:25:43.439
with it, realizing he couldn't see land

06:25:43.439 --> 06:25:44.459
off to his left anymore.

06:25:44.520 --> 06:25:46.560
I want to run away.

06:25:46.619 --> 06:25:48.299
I want to hide forever.

06:25:48.360 --> 06:25:50.099
But he had no choice.

06:25:50.220 --> 06:25:53.040
Anemone was his responsibility.

06:25:53.099 --> 06:25:56.279
Anemone was his biggest mistake.

06:25:56.340 --> 06:26:00.840
Once a year, in the kingdom of the sea.

06:26:00.959 --> 06:26:03.900
Every 2 year old dragon in the tribe is

06:26:03.900 --> 06:26:05.400
brought together for a particular

06:26:05.400 --> 06:26:08.700
ceremony, at least, it is called a

06:26:08.700 --> 06:26:12.060
ceremony, the talons of power ceremony.

06:26:12.119 --> 06:26:14.580
But really, it is a test.

06:26:14.639 --> 06:26:16.740
And smart dragonettes who've been

06:26:16.740 --> 06:26:18.599
listening closely, know that's what it

06:26:18.599 --> 06:26:18.779
is.

06:26:18.840 --> 06:26:22.259
Smart dragonettes also know exactly what

06:26:22.259 --> 06:26:23.340
the ceremony is looking for.

06:26:23.400 --> 06:26:26.759
When he was 2 years old, a week before

06:26:26.759 --> 06:26:29.340
the ceremony, Prince Turtle went out and

06:26:29.340 --> 06:26:31.799
caught 2 large fish and a talon full of

06:26:31.799 --> 06:26:32.159
shrimp.

06:26:32.279 --> 06:26:34.740
He flew them to a rocky ledge on a

06:26:34.740 --> 06:26:37.319
deserted island, and left them to rot in

06:26:37.319 --> 06:26:37.680
the sun.

06:26:37.740 --> 06:26:41.580
Five days later, he returned and ate them

06:26:41.580 --> 06:26:44.159
holding his nose, and forcing them down

06:26:44.159 --> 06:26:44.639
his throat.

06:26:44.639 --> 06:26:48.000
The night before the ceremony, Prince

06:26:48.000 --> 06:26:51.419
Turtle was dramatically violently ill in

06:26:51.419 --> 06:26:53.099
the dining room of the Deep Palace.

06:26:53.159 --> 06:26:54.779
It was pretty horrifying.

06:26:54.840 --> 06:26:57.720
No one wanted to go anywhere near the

06:26:57.720 --> 06:26:58.560
vomiting prints.

06:26:58.619 --> 06:27:00.959
He was sent to recover on a small island

06:27:00.959 --> 06:27:04.080
far away from civilized society, which

06:27:04.080 --> 06:27:06.119
meant, of course, that he missed the

06:27:06.119 --> 06:27:08.220
talons of power ceremony that year.

06:27:08.279 --> 06:27:10.380
Queen Coral wasn't concerned.

06:27:10.439 --> 06:27:12.479
He was just one of her many little

06:27:12.479 --> 06:27:15.000
princes, and if he really had any magic

06:27:15.000 --> 06:27:17.520
in his claws, which was, statistically

06:27:17.520 --> 06:27:18.360
very unlikely.

06:27:18.419 --> 06:27:20.580
Someone would figure it out sooner or

06:27:20.580 --> 06:27:20.759
later.

06:27:20.880 --> 06:27:23.639
She decreed that he could be included in

06:27:23.639 --> 06:27:25.439
the ceremony the following year when he

06:27:25.439 --> 06:27:25.799
was three.

06:27:25.919 --> 06:27:29.520
But the year Turtle turned 3 was the year

06:27:29.520 --> 06:27:30.599
his father went missing.

06:27:30.659 --> 06:27:33.659
Captured by the Sky Wings, according to

06:27:33.659 --> 06:27:36.419
Coral's spies, Queen Coral had spent

06:27:36.419 --> 06:27:38.099
every moment of that year guarding her

06:27:38.099 --> 06:27:40.319
new egg, so that a princess could finally

06:27:40.319 --> 06:27:41.459
hatch unharmed.

06:27:41.520 --> 06:27:45.540
She got her wish, a living daughter, but

06:27:45.540 --> 06:27:46.619
she lost her husband.

06:27:46.680 --> 06:27:49.979
The talons of power ceremony was canceled

06:27:49.979 --> 06:27:50.459
that year.

06:27:50.520 --> 06:27:53.040
So Prince Turtle was four.

06:27:53.099 --> 06:27:55.259
By the time the next talons of power

06:27:55.259 --> 06:27:56.400
ceremony rolled around.

06:27:56.459 --> 06:27:58.979
No one had said anything to him about it

06:27:58.979 --> 06:27:59.639
in over a year.

06:27:59.700 --> 06:28:01.919
He believed they'd forgotten about

06:28:01.919 --> 06:28:03.900
testing him, because why bother?

06:28:03.959 --> 06:28:06.659
If he were an animus dragon, someone

06:28:06.659 --> 06:28:07.799
would have noticed by then.

06:28:07.860 --> 06:28:10.680
At least, that's what everyone thought.

06:28:10.740 --> 06:28:13.500
On the day of the ceremony.

06:28:13.560 --> 06:28:15.180
Turtle was on his way out of the Summer

06:28:15.180 --> 06:28:18.119
Palace, with a pearl gathering party, when

06:28:18.119 --> 06:28:20.040
a dark green dragon blocked his path.

06:28:20.099 --> 06:28:24.479
Prince Turtle, the dragon said, in an

06:28:24.479 --> 06:28:25.139
oily voice.

06:28:25.259 --> 06:28:27.419
Whirlpool.

06:28:27.479 --> 06:28:30.119
Turtle answered evenly, hiding his

06:28:30.119 --> 06:28:30.599
dislike.

06:28:30.659 --> 06:28:33.840
Queen Carl adored this particular advisor

06:28:33.840 --> 06:28:36.360
and Turtle couldn't figure out why, except

06:28:36.360 --> 06:28:39.060
perhaps that Whirlpool was an expert at

06:28:39.060 --> 06:28:40.680
fawning over everything Coral did.

06:28:40.740 --> 06:28:43.740
Have you forgotten what today is?

06:28:43.799 --> 06:28:45.540
Whirlpool asked.

06:28:45.659 --> 06:28:48.599
Your presence is required at the talons

06:28:48.599 --> 06:28:49.619
of power ceremony.

06:28:49.680 --> 06:28:52.680
Turtle's heart thudded hard against the

06:28:52.680 --> 06:28:53.459
walls of his chest.

06:28:53.520 --> 06:28:54.959
Me?

06:28:54.959 --> 06:28:55.799
he said.

06:28:55.860 --> 06:28:58.200
Isn't it pretty clear by now that I'm not

06:28:58.200 --> 06:28:58.860
an animus?

06:28:58.919 --> 06:29:01.979
Still, said Whirlpool.

06:29:02.040 --> 06:29:04.979
Every sea wing must undergo the test

06:29:04.979 --> 06:29:07.380
especially those in the royal family.

06:29:07.439 --> 06:29:10.200
If animus power should happen to

06:29:10.200 --> 06:29:13.500
resurface now, when it is so direly

06:29:13.500 --> 06:29:13.919
needed.

06:29:13.979 --> 06:29:17.040
We cannot let it slip past our noses, can

06:29:17.040 --> 06:29:17.279
we?

06:29:17.340 --> 06:29:19.439
Does he know?

06:29:19.500 --> 06:29:20.939
Turtle wondered.

06:29:21.000 --> 06:29:23.639
But Whirlpool always sounded like a know

06:29:23.639 --> 06:29:26.819
it all, even, maybe especially, when he

06:29:26.819 --> 06:29:27.180
knew nothing.

06:29:27.299 --> 06:29:30.659
All right, he said with a shrug.

06:29:30.720 --> 06:29:32.520
Seems like a waste of time is all.

06:29:32.580 --> 06:29:34.619
I thought the Queen really wanted these

06:29:34.619 --> 06:29:36.240
pearls for Anemone's new necklace.

06:29:36.299 --> 06:29:39.360
The test will be over by midday.

06:29:39.419 --> 06:29:42.900
Plenty of time for pearl gathering after

06:29:42.900 --> 06:29:45.000
that, Whirlpool said.

06:29:45.060 --> 06:29:47.279
Ushering turtle into the tunnel that led

06:29:47.279 --> 06:29:48.119
out of the pavilion.

06:29:48.180 --> 06:29:51.119
Turtle swam along beside him, his mind

06:29:51.119 --> 06:29:52.380
paddling frantically.

06:29:52.439 --> 06:29:54.360
There had to be some way out of this.

06:29:54.419 --> 06:29:56.040
He couldn't take that test.

06:29:56.099 --> 06:29:58.200
He couldn't let them find out what he

06:29:58.200 --> 06:29:58.439
was.

06:29:58.500 --> 06:30:01.020
If his mother found out.

06:30:01.080 --> 06:30:02.220
What would she make him do?

06:30:02.279 --> 06:30:05.759
Turtle had read every scroll he could

06:30:05.759 --> 06:30:06.959
find on animus magic.

06:30:07.020 --> 06:30:08.459
There weren't many.

06:30:08.520 --> 06:30:10.919
And most of the ones that existed were

06:30:10.919 --> 06:30:13.380
about albatross, his ancestor from

06:30:13.380 --> 06:30:14.040
centuries ago.

06:30:14.099 --> 06:30:17.520
Albatross, the one who built the summer

06:30:17.520 --> 06:30:18.540
palace with his power.

06:30:18.659 --> 06:30:23.040
Albatross, who went mad, and massacred

06:30:23.040 --> 06:30:24.659
half his family before he was stopped.

06:30:24.720 --> 06:30:28.139
Turtle had often tried to imagine what it

06:30:28.139 --> 06:30:30.419
would be like if everyone knew he was an

06:30:30.419 --> 06:30:30.900
animus.

06:30:31.020 --> 06:30:33.000
Would they be terrified of him?

06:30:33.060 --> 06:30:35.759
Would they always be wondering if he'd

06:30:35.759 --> 06:30:38.220
suddenly snap and start killing dragons?

06:30:38.279 --> 06:30:41.400
Or would they think he could be a useful

06:30:41.400 --> 06:30:43.619
tool in the great war that was raging

06:30:43.619 --> 06:30:44.340
across the sea?

06:30:44.400 --> 06:30:47.400
What if Queen Coral forced him to use his

06:30:47.400 --> 06:30:48.720
magic against her enemies?

06:30:48.779 --> 06:30:51.840
What if she wanted him to do something he

06:30:51.840 --> 06:30:52.500
didn't want to do?

06:30:52.560 --> 06:30:55.680
What if he tried to do it and failed?

06:30:55.740 --> 06:30:58.619
And dragons died because of him?

06:30:58.680 --> 06:31:00.599
One thing was for sure.

06:31:00.659 --> 06:31:02.939
Everyone would know who he was.

06:31:03.000 --> 06:31:06.299
Everyone would always be looking at him.

06:31:06.360 --> 06:31:09.060
He'd never be able to hide or blend in.

06:31:09.119 --> 06:31:12.299
He would always have eyes on him, waiting

06:31:12.299 --> 06:31:15.360
and judging, and expecting.

06:31:15.419 --> 06:31:18.720
That scared him a lot more than the idea

06:31:18.720 --> 06:31:19.560
of losing his soul.

06:31:19.619 --> 06:31:22.080
He wasn't terribly worried about that.

06:31:22.139 --> 06:31:23.759
His soul felt fine.

06:31:23.819 --> 06:31:25.919
He certainly didn't feel like killing

06:31:25.919 --> 06:31:27.060
anyone, ever.

06:31:27.119 --> 06:31:29.400
He wasn't even sure he believed the

06:31:29.400 --> 06:31:31.860
theory that animus dragons lost their

06:31:31.860 --> 06:31:34.020
souls when they used their magic too

06:31:34.020 --> 06:31:34.200
much.

06:31:34.259 --> 06:31:37.139
Maybe Albatross had been naturally crazy

06:31:37.139 --> 06:31:39.360
and homicidal all along, but nobody

06:31:39.360 --> 06:31:39.720
noticed.

06:31:39.840 --> 06:31:43.080
Still, better safe than sorry.

06:31:43.139 --> 06:31:46.680
Better a quiet nobody than a big deal

06:31:46.680 --> 06:31:49.020
center of attention dragon than everyone

06:31:49.020 --> 06:31:50.220
thought would do great things.

06:31:50.340 --> 06:31:54.000
I'll have to fool the test, Turtle

06:31:54.000 --> 06:31:54.479
realized.

06:31:54.540 --> 06:31:56.220
He was 4 now.

06:31:56.279 --> 06:31:57.840
Surely he was smart enough to do that.

06:31:57.900 --> 06:32:01.740
Whirlpool led him a long way to an island

06:32:01.740 --> 06:32:03.060
where Turtle had never been before.

06:32:03.119 --> 06:32:06.180
As they approached, he saw other dragons

06:32:06.180 --> 06:32:07.080
swimming toward it.

06:32:07.139 --> 06:32:10.200
Parents with their 2 and 3 year olds, or

06:32:10.200 --> 06:32:12.240
members of Queen Coral's council who had

06:32:12.240 --> 06:32:12.659
come to watch.

06:32:12.720 --> 06:32:14.459
He wasn't sure why.

06:32:14.520 --> 06:32:16.979
There hadn't been an animus dragon found

06:32:16.979 --> 06:32:19.259
in the tribe in centuries, as far as he

06:32:19.259 --> 06:32:19.439
knew.

06:32:19.500 --> 06:32:21.599
Surely it would be a very boring

06:32:21.599 --> 06:32:22.259
ceremony.

06:32:22.319 --> 06:32:24.900
The dragonettes were gathered on a beach

06:32:24.900 --> 06:32:26.939
on the eastern side of the island.

06:32:27.000 --> 06:32:29.759
As Turtle waded up onto the sand, he

06:32:29.759 --> 06:32:31.860
realized with surprise that there were

06:32:31.860 --> 06:32:34.439
dragon made structures around him, the

06:32:34.439 --> 06:32:36.299
remains of an old pier jutted into the

06:32:36.299 --> 06:32:36.599
water.

06:32:36.659 --> 06:32:39.119
Most of the wooden walkway had rotted

06:32:39.119 --> 06:32:42.299
away, but a few of the pylons still stood

06:32:42.299 --> 06:32:43.919
and it clearly led out to where a

06:32:43.919 --> 06:32:46.200
pavilion had once balanced over the sea.

06:32:46.259 --> 06:32:49.740
Farther up the beach, overgrown by jungle

06:32:49.740 --> 06:32:52.439
vines, ruins rose out of the greenery

06:32:52.439 --> 06:32:55.799
walls, a tower, here and there a dragon

06:32:55.799 --> 06:32:56.340
statue.

06:32:56.459 --> 06:32:58.439
What is this place?

06:32:58.500 --> 06:33:00.299
Turtle asked Whirlpool.

06:33:00.360 --> 06:33:03.180
Oh, don't you know?

06:33:03.240 --> 06:33:06.060
Whirlpool said, in his insufferably

06:33:06.060 --> 06:33:09.599
superior way, what do your tutors spend

06:33:09.599 --> 06:33:10.799
their time on, I wonder?

06:33:10.919 --> 06:33:13.680
Use your brain, little prince.

06:33:13.740 --> 06:33:16.200
Don't you remember anything about an

06:33:16.200 --> 06:33:19.380
ancient sea wing palace abandoned nearly

06:33:19.380 --> 06:33:20.939
2000 years ago?

06:33:21.000 --> 06:33:23.340
Turtle looked around again.

06:33:23.400 --> 06:33:26.159
Resisting the urge to smack whirlpool in

06:33:26.159 --> 06:33:29.040
the snout with his tail. 2000 years ago.

06:33:29.099 --> 06:33:31.319
That was around the time of the

06:33:31.319 --> 06:33:31.979
massacre.

06:33:32.040 --> 06:33:35.700
The island palace, he breathed.

06:33:35.759 --> 06:33:38.159
It's the island.

06:33:38.279 --> 06:33:41.819
Oh, said Whirlpool, realizing what Turtle

06:33:41.819 --> 06:33:42.180
had said.

06:33:42.240 --> 06:33:44.459
Yes, that's correct.

06:33:44.520 --> 06:33:46.919
With a faint air of disappointment.

06:33:46.979 --> 06:33:49.380
He oozed off toward the top of the beach

06:33:49.380 --> 06:33:51.779
where Turtle's Uncle Shark was pacing and

06:33:51.779 --> 06:33:52.680
glowering at everyone.

06:33:52.799 --> 06:33:55.680
This was where the massacre had taken

06:33:55.680 --> 06:33:55.919
place.

06:33:55.979 --> 06:33:58.979
Turtle felt an eerie chill flood through

06:33:58.979 --> 06:33:59.459
his scales.

06:33:59.520 --> 06:34:01.979
Nine dragons had died here.

06:34:02.040 --> 06:34:05.340
The victims of albatross's magic, most of

06:34:05.340 --> 06:34:07.439
them members of the royal family, his

06:34:07.439 --> 06:34:08.040
ancestors.

06:34:08.099 --> 06:34:10.680
If anywhere in the kingdom was haunted

06:34:10.680 --> 06:34:11.700
this would be the place.

06:34:11.819 --> 06:34:15.360
He imagined restless ghosts, stepping

06:34:15.360 --> 06:34:17.340
through puddles of blood on the verandas

06:34:17.340 --> 06:34:19.979
reaching with translucent talons toward

06:34:19.979 --> 06:34:20.400
the living.

06:34:20.459 --> 06:34:24.240
Hey, Octopus said, breaking turtles

06:34:24.240 --> 06:34:26.159
trance, what's she doing here?

06:34:26.220 --> 06:34:28.860
Queen Coral came swooping down from the

06:34:28.860 --> 06:34:29.759
sky?

06:34:29.819 --> 06:34:31.799
The turtle knew that she wasn't the she

06:34:31.799 --> 06:34:32.700
his brother meant.

06:34:32.759 --> 06:34:35.099
Octopus was talking about their sister

06:34:35.099 --> 06:34:38.639
little princess anemone, the dragonette

06:34:38.639 --> 06:34:41.220
clinging to Coral's neck, a harness bound

06:34:41.220 --> 06:34:42.000
the 2 of them together.

06:34:42.060 --> 06:34:43.979
Turtle had never seen them without it.

06:34:44.040 --> 06:34:46.740
She goes everywhere, mother goes.

06:34:46.799 --> 06:34:49.139
Cerulean whispered, you know that.

06:34:49.200 --> 06:34:51.299
They're here to watch the ceremony, like

06:34:51.299 --> 06:34:52.020
everyone else.

06:34:52.080 --> 06:34:54.000
But he was wrong about that.

06:34:54.060 --> 06:34:57.419
Coral landed on the sand, shook her wings

06:34:57.419 --> 06:34:59.279
and looked around triumphantly at the

06:34:59.279 --> 06:35:00.659
assembled council members.

06:35:00.720 --> 06:35:04.439
I want anemone to be tested with the

06:35:04.439 --> 06:35:06.599
other dragonettes today, she announced.

06:35:06.659 --> 06:35:08.819
Anemone?

06:35:08.880 --> 06:35:11.639
protested Turtle's cousin Moray, who was

06:35:11.639 --> 06:35:14.279
old and on the council, she's not even

06:35:14.279 --> 06:35:17.580
one year old yet, Queen Coral smiled

06:35:17.580 --> 06:35:18.479
fondly at her daughter.

06:35:18.540 --> 06:35:22.080
Yes, but she's very precocious, and I

06:35:22.080 --> 06:35:23.939
have a feeling about her.

06:35:24.000 --> 06:35:26.400
I just know how the story should go.

06:35:26.459 --> 06:35:29.759
Princess Anemone slid off the queen's

06:35:29.759 --> 06:35:32.099
back, in a move that was almost graceful

06:35:32.099 --> 06:35:34.380
except she got tangled up in the harness

06:35:34.380 --> 06:35:36.240
and ended up flopping onto her side in

06:35:36.240 --> 06:35:39.540
the sand, growling softly, she struggled

06:35:39.540 --> 06:35:41.220
to her feet, and wrestled the harness

06:35:41.220 --> 06:35:41.939
back out of her way.

06:35:42.000 --> 06:35:45.060
Next to Turtle, a three-year-old

06:35:45.060 --> 06:35:47.220
dragonette twitched forward. as if he

06:35:47.220 --> 06:35:49.139
wanted to go help her, but he wasn't sure

06:35:49.139 --> 06:35:51.599
he was allowed to, his scales were

06:35:51.599 --> 06:35:53.939
grayish blue, and there was a nick on one

06:35:53.939 --> 06:35:55.740
of his ears, which Turtle recognized.

06:35:55.799 --> 06:35:58.619
That was Pike, who had a reputation for

06:35:58.619 --> 06:36:01.020
fighting too hard in training classes, and

06:36:01.020 --> 06:36:02.340
hurting himself by accident.

06:36:02.459 --> 06:36:04.439
All right.

06:36:04.500 --> 06:36:06.180
Here we go.

06:36:06.240 --> 06:36:09.840
Whirlpool said smacking his front talons

06:36:09.840 --> 06:36:10.439
together wetly.

06:36:10.500 --> 06:36:13.799
A coconut for each dragonette, please.

06:36:13.919 --> 06:36:16.560
A few older dragons moved between the

06:36:16.560 --> 06:36:18.779
dragonettes, passing out coconuts.

06:36:18.840 --> 06:36:21.360
Turtle looked warily down at his.

06:36:21.419 --> 06:36:24.540
This could be the instrument of my

06:36:24.540 --> 06:36:26.220
destruction, he thought.

06:36:26.279 --> 06:36:29.340
This harmless looking snack could betray

06:36:29.340 --> 06:36:31.200
me and change my life forever.

06:36:31.259 --> 06:36:36.599
We'll start on this end, Whirlpool said

06:36:36.599 --> 06:36:37.979
stepping over to the line of

06:36:37.979 --> 06:36:38.759
dragonettes.

06:36:38.819 --> 06:36:42.419
You three, loud and clear.

06:36:42.479 --> 06:36:45.419
Tell your coconuts to float into the air

06:36:45.419 --> 06:36:47.400
then return to your claws.

06:36:47.520 --> 06:36:50.459
The 3 dragonettes on the end dutifully

06:36:50.459 --> 06:36:52.740
spoke in unison, issuing commands to

06:36:52.740 --> 06:36:53.520
their coconuts.

06:36:53.580 --> 06:36:54.840
Nothing happened.

06:36:54.900 --> 06:36:56.819
You may go.

06:36:56.939 --> 06:36:58.799
Whirlpool dismissed them.

06:36:58.860 --> 06:37:01.020
As they slipped back into the water with

06:37:01.020 --> 06:37:03.119
their parents, Turtle felt his heart

06:37:03.119 --> 06:37:04.560
racing as fast as his mind.

06:37:04.619 --> 06:37:07.439
Whirlpool would be looking right at him.

06:37:07.500 --> 06:37:09.419
He'd have to say exactly what he'd been

06:37:09.419 --> 06:37:11.099
commanded to say.

06:37:11.159 --> 06:37:12.000
How could he fool the test?

06:37:12.060 --> 06:37:15.479
Enchant it now, he thought. before he

06:37:15.479 --> 06:37:15.779
gets here.

06:37:15.900 --> 06:37:18.659
He sank his claws into the coconut

06:37:18.659 --> 06:37:19.020
shell.

06:37:19.080 --> 06:37:20.220
Coconut?

06:37:20.279 --> 06:37:20.759
he thought.

06:37:20.819 --> 06:37:21.840
Don't move.

06:37:21.900 --> 06:37:24.599
No matter what I or anyone else says to

06:37:24.599 --> 06:37:26.880
you, you are now a completely normal

06:37:26.880 --> 06:37:28.979
coconut who can never be enchanted.

06:37:29.040 --> 06:37:30.659
Without work?

06:37:30.720 --> 06:37:33.119
He had experimented so little with his

06:37:33.119 --> 06:37:35.040
power, because of the need to keep it

06:37:35.040 --> 06:37:35.400
secret.

06:37:35.459 --> 06:37:37.500
He knew he could enchant things by

06:37:37.500 --> 06:37:39.299
thinking about it, without having to

06:37:39.299 --> 06:37:42.060
speak aloud, but he wasn't sure if spoken

06:37:42.060 --> 06:37:44.400
spells were stronger and might overpower

06:37:44.400 --> 06:37:45.540
a thought spell.

06:37:45.659 --> 06:37:48.240
He also wasn't sure it was possible to

06:37:48.240 --> 06:37:50.459
enchant an object to be enchantment

06:37:50.459 --> 06:37:51.060
resistant.

06:37:51.119 --> 06:37:53.939
What else can I do to distract them?

06:37:54.000 --> 06:37:57.720
His gaze fell on anemone, sitting up the

06:37:57.720 --> 06:37:58.919
beach beside their mother.

06:37:58.979 --> 06:38:02.459
She held a coconut too, studying it, and

06:38:02.459 --> 06:38:04.259
turning it between her talons like a

06:38:04.259 --> 06:38:05.099
large opal.

06:38:05.159 --> 06:38:07.860
Queen Coral was watching her, as though

06:38:07.860 --> 06:38:10.139
anemone had been carved out of sea glass

06:38:10.139 --> 06:38:12.599
perfect and shimmering and sharp.

06:38:12.659 --> 06:38:14.580
Her eyes were full of all the things

06:38:14.580 --> 06:38:15.659
turtle feared.

06:38:15.720 --> 06:38:19.439
Grand plans, dreams, ambitions

06:38:19.439 --> 06:38:20.700
expectations.

06:38:20.759 --> 06:38:23.819
In Queen Coral's story of the world.

06:38:23.880 --> 06:38:26.040
Of course, her one surviving daughter

06:38:26.040 --> 06:38:26.939
would be magical.

06:38:27.000 --> 06:38:29.700
Of course, she would be the 1st animus

06:38:29.700 --> 06:38:32.340
dragon to hatch in 100s of years, she

06:38:32.340 --> 06:38:33.119
would be chosen.

06:38:33.180 --> 06:38:35.279
She would be a savior for the whole

06:38:35.279 --> 06:38:35.819
tribe.

06:38:35.880 --> 06:38:37.200
That's it.

06:38:37.259 --> 06:38:39.900
An idea hit turtle like a lightning

06:38:39.900 --> 06:38:40.200
bolt.

06:38:40.259 --> 06:38:42.840
If the tribe already has an animus.

06:38:42.900 --> 06:38:44.220
Then they won't need me.

06:38:44.279 --> 06:38:47.340
As quickly as it had struck, his

06:38:47.340 --> 06:38:48.180
excitement faded.

06:38:48.240 --> 06:38:50.340
The type of enchantment he was

06:38:50.340 --> 06:38:51.000
imagining.

06:38:51.060 --> 06:38:53.580
No one had ever tried it before, as far

06:38:53.580 --> 06:38:54.000
as he knew.

06:38:54.060 --> 06:38:57.000
It was probably impossible, almost

06:38:57.000 --> 06:38:59.939
certainly impossible, insane, in fact

06:38:59.939 --> 06:39:03.119
especially since he couldn't touch her or

06:39:03.119 --> 06:39:03.840
speak out loud.

06:39:03.900 --> 06:39:06.299
It would have to be a thought spell from

06:39:06.299 --> 06:39:07.919
a distance, and those were difficult

06:39:07.919 --> 06:39:10.500
enough, even when they weren't immensely

06:39:10.500 --> 06:39:11.220
powerful requests.

06:39:11.279 --> 06:39:14.459
But the words were forming in his head

06:39:14.459 --> 06:39:17.459
unbidden, and he realized he was going to

06:39:17.459 --> 06:39:17.880
try.

06:39:17.939 --> 06:39:20.759
If it was impossible, it wouldn't work

06:39:20.759 --> 06:39:22.680
and he'd be in the same current as

06:39:22.680 --> 06:39:22.979
before.

06:39:23.040 --> 06:39:24.599
If it did work.

06:39:24.659 --> 06:39:26.520
Whirlpool would be happy.

06:39:26.580 --> 06:39:29.639
Anemone would be even more special, Queen

06:39:29.639 --> 06:39:32.700
Coral would be ecstatic, and Turtle would

06:39:32.700 --> 06:39:33.240
be safe.

06:39:33.299 --> 06:39:37.799
I enchant my sister anemone. to become an

06:39:37.799 --> 06:39:39.000
animus dragon too.

06:39:39.060 --> 06:39:43.319
Anemone, become an animus dragon.

06:39:43.380 --> 06:39:46.319
I enchant you to have talons of power.

06:39:46.380 --> 06:39:48.779
Turtle!

06:39:48.840 --> 06:39:50.459
Whirlpool barked in his ear.

06:39:50.520 --> 06:39:53.279
Turtle jerked back, catching his tail

06:39:53.279 --> 06:39:55.200
painfully on a giant conch shell.

06:39:55.259 --> 06:39:57.060
Sorry, Turtle said.

06:39:57.119 --> 06:39:57.479
What?

06:39:57.540 --> 06:40:00.060
It's your turn.

06:40:00.119 --> 06:40:02.520
Whirlpool nodded at the coconut.

06:40:02.580 --> 06:40:04.259
And then at the 2 dragons beside him.

06:40:04.319 --> 06:40:08.040
Pike and octopus are waiting.

06:40:08.099 --> 06:40:09.840
Oh, yes.

06:40:09.900 --> 06:40:12.479
Turtle fumbled his coconut out in front

06:40:12.479 --> 06:40:14.159
of him and took a deep breath.

06:40:14.220 --> 06:40:16.619
He heard the other 2 mumbling along as he

06:40:16.619 --> 06:40:17.159
spoke to it.

06:40:17.220 --> 06:40:20.400
Coconut, float into the air, and then

06:40:20.400 --> 06:40:21.419
return to my claws.

06:40:21.540 --> 06:40:24.000
Was the coconut trembling?

06:40:24.060 --> 06:40:26.220
Or was that his own fear traveling

06:40:26.220 --> 06:40:27.000
through his arms?

06:40:27.060 --> 06:40:30.060
Did it feel lighter in his talons as if

06:40:30.060 --> 06:40:31.080
it was about to lift off?

06:40:31.139 --> 06:40:33.840
Oh, please, anemone?

06:40:33.900 --> 06:40:34.860
Use your magic.

06:40:34.919 --> 06:40:36.720
Turtle wished desperately.

06:40:36.840 --> 06:40:39.959
A piercing shriek suddenly cut the air

06:40:39.959 --> 06:40:42.360
making half the dragonettes jump and drop

06:40:42.360 --> 06:40:43.139
their coconuts.

06:40:43.200 --> 06:40:44.580
It was Moray.

06:40:44.639 --> 06:40:46.979
One talon outstretched to point at

06:40:46.979 --> 06:40:50.220
anemone, and a coconut that was slowly

06:40:50.220 --> 06:40:52.020
drifting up into the air over her head.

06:40:52.080 --> 06:40:55.860
Whirlpool turned to stare, and Turtle

06:40:55.860 --> 06:40:57.479
took the moment to grip his coconut

06:40:57.479 --> 06:40:58.439
forcefully once more.

06:40:58.500 --> 06:41:01.680
Stop moving, you hairy idiot.

06:41:01.740 --> 06:41:04.500
I enchant you to be a normal coconut, a

06:41:04.500 --> 06:41:06.419
coconut that would never float anywhere

06:41:06.419 --> 06:41:07.680
by all the whales.

06:41:07.740 --> 06:41:11.939
The coconut seemed to nestle closer, warm

06:41:11.939 --> 06:41:14.099
and heavy and still in his claws.

06:41:14.159 --> 06:41:16.380
I was right.

06:41:16.439 --> 06:41:17.880
Queen Kroll cried.

06:41:17.939 --> 06:41:20.819
Anemone, you're an Adamus, you really

06:41:20.819 --> 06:41:21.060
are.

06:41:21.119 --> 06:41:25.139
No one looked more surprised than anemone

06:41:25.139 --> 06:41:27.299
who stared up at the coconut in awe.

06:41:27.419 --> 06:41:30.479
With the sun shining behind it, it seemed

06:41:30.479 --> 06:41:33.060
to be glowing, and so did all the pinkish

06:41:33.060 --> 06:41:35.040
white and pale blue scales all over

06:41:35.040 --> 06:41:35.939
anemone.

06:41:36.060 --> 06:41:39.000
I'm magic, she whispered.

06:41:39.060 --> 06:41:42.299
The test is over, Carl called.

06:41:42.419 --> 06:41:44.939
Whirlpool, we found our animus.

06:41:45.000 --> 06:41:45.360
Look.

06:41:45.419 --> 06:41:47.819
But shouldn't we?

06:41:47.880 --> 06:41:50.220
We'll pull gestured faintly at the

06:41:50.220 --> 06:41:52.200
remaining dragonettes, then shrugged.

06:41:52.259 --> 06:41:55.259
Quite right, your majesty.

06:41:55.319 --> 06:41:57.479
All of you are dismissed.

06:41:57.540 --> 06:42:00.360
Turtle exhaled softly.

06:42:00.419 --> 06:42:02.040
He couldn't believe it.

06:42:02.099 --> 06:42:03.299
It worked.

06:42:03.360 --> 06:42:06.900
He'd turned his sister into an animus

06:42:06.900 --> 06:42:07.200
dragon.

06:42:07.259 --> 06:42:09.119
So now he was safe.

06:42:09.180 --> 06:42:11.220
His magic was his own.

06:42:11.279 --> 06:42:13.919
He could keep being quiet, ordinary

06:42:13.919 --> 06:42:14.880
turtle on the outside.

06:42:15.000 --> 06:42:17.580
But had he done the right thing?

06:42:17.639 --> 06:42:20.700
What if he had ruined Anemone's life by

06:42:20.700 --> 06:42:21.479
protecting himself?

06:42:21.540 --> 06:42:24.659
He hesitated at the edge of the water

06:42:24.659 --> 06:42:26.099
watching his sister.

06:42:26.159 --> 06:42:28.139
She certainly looked pretty happy.

06:42:28.259 --> 06:42:30.900
Queen Coral threw her wings around

06:42:30.900 --> 06:42:33.720
anemone as her council crowded closer

06:42:33.720 --> 06:42:34.860
murmuring excitedly.

06:42:34.919 --> 06:42:37.560
Would the queen have reacted the same way

06:42:37.560 --> 06:42:39.959
to finding out he was an animus?

06:42:40.020 --> 06:42:42.419
Would he suddenly be the one she loved

06:42:42.419 --> 06:42:44.340
the center of attention all the time?

06:42:44.400 --> 06:42:46.919
Would he have ended up with a harness

06:42:46.919 --> 06:42:47.880
like anemones?

06:42:47.939 --> 06:42:50.759
He shook a crab off one of his talons.

06:42:50.819 --> 06:42:53.819
Remember, that's exactly what I don't

06:42:53.819 --> 06:42:55.680
want, he told himself.

06:42:55.740 --> 06:42:58.259
This would have been anemone's life

06:42:58.259 --> 06:42:58.619
anyway.

06:42:58.680 --> 06:43:01.200
Really, it wouldn't be any different.

06:43:01.259 --> 06:43:03.599
She'd still be special and beloved.

06:43:03.659 --> 06:43:06.479
She'd probably adore having animus

06:43:06.479 --> 06:43:06.900
powers.

06:43:06.959 --> 06:43:09.000
What about her soul?

06:43:09.060 --> 06:43:10.740
A part of him whispered.

06:43:10.799 --> 06:43:12.599
He pushed away the guilt.

06:43:12.659 --> 06:43:14.639
Probably a myth.

06:43:14.759 --> 06:43:17.819
He told himself. someone will make sure

06:43:17.819 --> 06:43:19.259
she's careful with her magic.

06:43:19.319 --> 06:43:20.520
He told himself.

06:43:20.580 --> 06:43:21.840
She'll be fine.

06:43:21.900 --> 06:43:23.580
He told himself.

06:43:23.639 --> 06:43:27.419
Turtle slipped into the water quietly

06:43:27.419 --> 06:43:29.700
unnoticed by anyone, and swam away

06:43:29.700 --> 06:43:32.520
leaving barely a ripple on the surface of

06:43:32.520 --> 06:43:32.939
the ocean.

06:43:33.000 --> 06:43:37.380
Chapter 20.

06:43:37.680 --> 06:43:42.240
Turtle thought of Kinkajou, of Kibley and

06:43:42.240 --> 06:43:45.540
Winter, of peril, as he flew and swam

06:43:45.540 --> 06:43:47.340
flew and swam without stopping.

06:43:47.400 --> 06:43:49.560
He wished he had his friends with him.

06:43:49.619 --> 06:43:52.380
Peril would be able to stop anemone

06:43:52.380 --> 06:43:54.779
either with her fire scales, or her blunt

06:43:54.779 --> 06:43:55.319
honesty.

06:43:55.380 --> 06:43:58.619
Kibley would have some brilliant plan, or

06:43:58.619 --> 06:43:59.819
winter would be able to fight her.

06:43:59.880 --> 06:44:01.319
Not him.

06:44:01.380 --> 06:44:04.860
He had no plan, no fighting skills, no

06:44:04.860 --> 06:44:05.700
fire scales.

06:44:05.700 --> 06:44:07.680
I could try honesty.

06:44:07.740 --> 06:44:10.259
I've never given anemone the truth

06:44:10.259 --> 06:44:10.560
before.

06:44:10.619 --> 06:44:13.560
I'm not sure she'd be very grateful for

06:44:13.560 --> 06:44:13.680
it.

06:44:13.740 --> 06:44:16.560
The current took him north to a river

06:44:16.560 --> 06:44:19.080
which turned out to be Winding Tail River

06:44:19.080 --> 06:44:20.580
snaking through the mountains.

06:44:20.580 --> 06:44:22.919
Whenever it was too shallow to swim, he

06:44:22.919 --> 06:44:23.279
flew.

06:44:23.400 --> 06:44:26.040
When the night unleashed brutal gusting

06:44:26.040 --> 06:44:27.299
winds, he swam.

06:44:27.360 --> 06:44:30.419
The windstorm was still going when he had

06:44:30.419 --> 06:44:31.740
to leave the river sometime the next

06:44:31.740 --> 06:44:32.159
day.

06:44:32.159 --> 06:44:34.080
It was hard to tell whether it was

06:44:34.080 --> 06:44:36.180
morning or afternoon, with the sun

06:44:36.180 --> 06:44:38.759
swallowed up by clouds, and only a dim

06:44:38.759 --> 06:44:41.040
gray light filling the sky from horizon

06:44:41.040 --> 06:44:41.759
to horizon.

06:44:41.819 --> 06:44:44.520
The landscape below him was equally

06:44:44.520 --> 06:44:45.240
monotonous.

06:44:45.299 --> 06:44:48.599
This was the mud kingdom, dreary and

06:44:48.599 --> 06:44:50.400
swampy and bog riddled.

06:44:50.459 --> 06:44:53.279
He let himself stop for a moment in a

06:44:53.279 --> 06:44:56.040
grove of mist shrouded trees, so he could

06:44:56.040 --> 06:44:58.020
use his healing stone on his exhausted

06:44:58.020 --> 06:44:58.500
wings.

06:44:58.560 --> 06:45:01.080
Then he replaced it in his pouch and flew

06:45:01.080 --> 06:45:01.259
on.

06:45:01.319 --> 06:45:04.020
He was starving, but he couldn't stop to

06:45:04.020 --> 06:45:04.259
eat.

06:45:04.319 --> 06:45:05.759
He had to catch his sister.

06:45:05.819 --> 06:45:09.360
Another night passed in flying, and the

06:45:09.360 --> 06:45:11.279
next morning, Turtle found himself over

06:45:11.279 --> 06:45:14.400
the ocean, sunlight sparkling on waves as

06:45:14.400 --> 06:45:16.080
blue as tsunami's scales.

06:45:16.139 --> 06:45:18.840
Gratefully he dove into the warm water

06:45:18.840 --> 06:45:20.700
and found a current that was going in the

06:45:20.700 --> 06:45:22.080
direction of the deep palace.

06:45:22.080 --> 06:45:24.659
As it swept him along, he was able to

06:45:24.659 --> 06:45:27.659
catch a fish hurtling by, and eat it in 2

06:45:27.659 --> 06:45:28.560
snaps of his jaws.

06:45:28.680 --> 06:45:32.099
A sense of enormous relief washed over

06:45:32.099 --> 06:45:34.139
him as he came in sight of the deep

06:45:34.139 --> 06:45:34.619
palace.

06:45:34.680 --> 06:45:38.099
For one thing, it was home, familiar and

06:45:38.099 --> 06:45:40.740
comforting in every twist and crevice, for

06:45:40.740 --> 06:45:42.900
another, it did not look like the sight

06:45:42.900 --> 06:45:44.099
of an ongoing massacre.

06:45:44.159 --> 06:45:47.759
Sea wings swam peacefully, busily, in and

06:45:47.759 --> 06:45:49.319
out of the various entrances.

06:45:49.560 --> 06:45:51.599
Dragonettes played around the fins of the

06:45:51.599 --> 06:45:53.340
soldiers in the gardens.

06:45:53.400 --> 06:45:55.500
The usual glow of aquatic conversations

06:45:55.500 --> 06:45:57.720
danced over the coral and reflected

06:45:57.720 --> 06:45:58.680
through the palace windows.

06:45:58.740 --> 06:46:02.040
No clouds of blood rising from the palace

06:46:02.040 --> 06:46:04.200
no dragons fleeing in panic.

06:46:04.860 --> 06:46:07.259
If anemone was here, she hadn't started

06:46:07.259 --> 06:46:07.799
killing yet.

06:46:07.860 --> 06:46:10.200
What if she isn't here?

06:46:10.200 --> 06:46:11.220
he thought.

06:46:11.340 --> 06:46:13.380
Touching down at the main palace

06:46:13.380 --> 06:46:13.740
entrance.

06:46:13.799 --> 06:46:16.680
He'd look like kind of an idiot if he'd

06:46:16.680 --> 06:46:18.060
chased her all the way back home for no

06:46:18.060 --> 06:46:18.360
reason.

06:46:18.419 --> 06:46:21.659
But then everyone would be safe, and he

06:46:21.659 --> 06:46:23.099
wouldn't mind looking like an idiot to

06:46:23.099 --> 06:46:23.639
make that true.

06:46:23.700 --> 06:46:26.279
One of his older brothers was swimming

06:46:26.279 --> 06:46:28.200
out of the palace as turtle approached

06:46:28.200 --> 06:46:30.299
Finn blinked in surprise when he saw a

06:46:30.299 --> 06:46:30.659
turtle.

06:46:30.720 --> 06:46:33.779
I thought you'd gone off to fancy hugging

06:46:33.779 --> 06:46:36.240
school, he joked, with flashing scales.

06:46:36.299 --> 06:46:37.740
I did.

06:46:37.799 --> 06:46:40.319
I'm just stopping by to say hi, Turtle

06:46:40.319 --> 06:46:40.500
said.

06:46:40.619 --> 06:46:43.319
He couldn't stop himself from adding, and

06:46:43.319 --> 06:46:44.040
what does that even mean?

06:46:44.099 --> 06:46:45.240
Hugging school.

06:46:45.360 --> 06:46:48.360
Where all the tribes of pyrhea will learn

06:46:48.360 --> 06:46:50.700
to hug out their problems, of course, said

06:46:50.700 --> 06:46:53.279
Finn, grinning like a comedic barracuda.

06:46:53.340 --> 06:46:55.319
Who are you here to say hi to?

06:46:55.439 --> 06:46:57.119
Nobody's even noticed you're gone?

06:46:57.180 --> 06:47:00.119
He laughed, and thumped Turtle's shoulder

06:47:00.119 --> 06:47:01.860
hard enough to make turtles spin in the

06:47:01.860 --> 06:47:02.279
water.

06:47:02.520 --> 06:47:04.680
Oh, thanks very much.

06:47:04.740 --> 06:47:07.319
Total responded, riding himself.

06:47:07.380 --> 06:47:09.240
Have you seen anemone today?

06:47:09.299 --> 06:47:10.860
Here?

06:47:10.919 --> 06:47:12.599
Finn looked alarmed.

06:47:12.659 --> 06:47:14.220
She's supposed to be with you.

06:47:14.279 --> 06:47:16.619
Do not tell me Pike has lost her.

06:47:16.680 --> 06:47:19.080
Mother will pop off all his scales one by

06:47:19.080 --> 06:47:19.319
one.

06:47:19.380 --> 06:47:21.180
No, no.

06:47:21.240 --> 06:47:22.259
Turtle said.

06:47:22.319 --> 06:47:24.900
She snuck away from school, and I thought

06:47:24.900 --> 06:47:25.680
she might have come here.

06:47:25.740 --> 06:47:27.119
But you haven't seen her?

06:47:27.240 --> 06:47:29.340
Finn shook his head.

06:47:29.400 --> 06:47:30.599
Where's mother?

06:47:30.659 --> 06:47:31.919
Turtle asked.

06:47:31.979 --> 06:47:33.599
Maybe he should warn her.

06:47:33.659 --> 06:47:35.639
Although he didn't want her to kill

06:47:35.639 --> 06:47:37.919
anemone on sight, which would be the

06:47:37.919 --> 06:47:38.639
logical reaction.

06:47:38.759 --> 06:47:40.979
Could he explain everything that had

06:47:40.979 --> 06:47:41.279
happened?

06:47:41.400 --> 06:47:43.319
Dark stalker and everything else?

06:47:43.380 --> 06:47:47.639
In Auckland's favorite place, Finn said

06:47:47.639 --> 06:47:49.740
rolling his eyes and nodding at one of

06:47:49.740 --> 06:47:50.939
the gardens beyond the palace.

06:47:51.000 --> 06:47:53.939
As usual, he spread his wings to swim

06:47:53.939 --> 06:47:54.240
away.

06:47:54.299 --> 06:47:57.299
Finn, turtles started.

06:47:57.360 --> 06:47:59.459
His brother turned to look at him.

06:47:59.520 --> 06:48:02.580
If you do see anemone in the next day or

06:48:02.580 --> 06:48:02.819
two.

06:48:02.880 --> 06:48:06.240
Maybe keep your distance, just in case.

06:48:06.299 --> 06:48:09.060
You're freaking me out, little brother

06:48:09.060 --> 06:48:10.860
Finn said, frowning.

06:48:10.919 --> 06:48:13.740
I'm worried about her soul, Turtle

06:48:13.740 --> 06:48:15.720
admitted, but I hope I'm wrong.

06:48:15.779 --> 06:48:19.080
Finn blanched, no doubt remembering all

06:48:19.080 --> 06:48:20.580
the albatross stories as well.

06:48:20.639 --> 06:48:23.340
I've been meaning to do a mapping

06:48:23.340 --> 06:48:25.319
excursion to the outer aisles, he said.

06:48:25.380 --> 06:48:27.360
Maybe now would be a good time for that.

06:48:27.479 --> 06:48:31.979
Maybe, Turtle said, adding the sequence

06:48:31.979 --> 06:48:33.779
of glowing scales that indicated high

06:48:33.779 --> 06:48:34.619
anxiety.

06:48:34.680 --> 06:48:36.900
Maybe take our brothers with you.

06:48:36.959 --> 06:48:38.939
All of them?

06:48:39.000 --> 06:48:40.680
Three moons.

06:48:40.740 --> 06:48:43.080
Finn flashed, a shadow of a grin

06:48:43.080 --> 06:48:44.220
reappearing on his face.

06:48:44.279 --> 06:48:46.740
It'll be more like an invasion than a

06:48:46.740 --> 06:48:47.279
scouting trip.

06:48:47.340 --> 06:48:49.380
The grin vanished again.

06:48:49.439 --> 06:48:50.759
Thanks, turtle.

06:48:50.880 --> 06:48:54.119
He swam off at top speed and turtle

06:48:54.119 --> 06:48:55.319
headed for Aucklett's garden.

06:48:55.380 --> 06:48:58.979
As he got closer, he realized why this

06:48:58.979 --> 06:48:59.880
spot was our favorite.

06:48:59.939 --> 06:49:03.299
Here, a few vents in the ocean floor sent

06:49:03.299 --> 06:49:05.459
jets of warm bubbles shooting toward the

06:49:05.459 --> 06:49:05.759
surface.

06:49:05.819 --> 06:49:08.759
When he was a little dragonette, he loved

06:49:08.759 --> 06:49:09.540
playing in them too.

06:49:09.599 --> 06:49:12.900
Queen Coral sat beside the bubble sprays

06:49:12.959 --> 06:49:14.880
watching her littlest daughter with a

06:49:14.880 --> 06:49:15.720
smile on her face.

06:49:15.779 --> 06:49:18.659
She held a slate loosely in her talons

06:49:18.659 --> 06:49:20.700
but she wasn't riding on it.

06:49:20.759 --> 06:49:22.740
At the end of her harness, Aucklet was

06:49:22.740 --> 06:49:25.080
somersaulting and giggling and pouncing

06:49:25.080 --> 06:49:26.340
at the bubbles as they shot by.

06:49:26.400 --> 06:49:31.139
Mother, turtle flashed as he sidled up

06:49:31.139 --> 06:49:31.680
beside her.

06:49:31.740 --> 06:49:36.180
Oh, hello, she flashed back, glancing at

06:49:36.180 --> 06:49:36.599
him briefly.

06:49:36.659 --> 06:49:39.659
She didn't seem to recognize him as the

06:49:39.659 --> 06:49:40.919
prince who was supposed to be at Jade

06:49:40.919 --> 06:49:41.279
Mountain.

06:49:41.340 --> 06:49:44.639
Turtle sat down beside her, at a loss for

06:49:44.639 --> 06:49:44.880
words.

06:49:44.939 --> 06:49:46.740
Where should he start?

06:49:46.799 --> 06:49:49.080
Would it be wise to warn her about

06:49:49.080 --> 06:49:49.680
anemone?

06:49:49.740 --> 06:49:52.080
What if his sister wasn't really planning

06:49:52.080 --> 06:49:52.919
to challenge her?

06:49:52.979 --> 06:49:55.919
After all, she should have easily gotten

06:49:55.919 --> 06:49:56.639
here before he did.

06:49:56.700 --> 06:49:58.259
So where was she?

06:49:58.319 --> 06:50:00.840
Maybe Dark Stalker was right.

06:50:00.900 --> 06:50:03.060
An anemone was back at the Jade Mountain

06:50:03.060 --> 06:50:05.700
Academy right now, eating fish and

06:50:05.700 --> 06:50:07.200
bossing the other sea wings around.

06:50:07.259 --> 06:50:10.020
If so, he didn't want to get her in

06:50:10.020 --> 06:50:10.860
trouble with a queen.

06:50:10.919 --> 06:50:14.580
But if Coral and Aucklet were in danger.

06:50:14.639 --> 06:50:16.139
Shouldn't he warn them?

06:50:16.200 --> 06:50:19.080
He looked up at the dark ocean overhead

06:50:19.080 --> 06:50:21.900
wondering if a soulless anemone was out

06:50:21.900 --> 06:50:24.060
there somewhere, circling like a shark.

06:50:24.119 --> 06:50:26.520
Isn't she perfect?

06:50:26.580 --> 06:50:28.080
His mother flashed.

06:50:28.139 --> 06:50:31.080
It took total a moment to realize she was

06:50:31.080 --> 06:50:32.159
talking about Aucklet.

06:50:32.220 --> 06:50:34.259
The queen nodded at the Happy

06:50:34.259 --> 06:50:35.040
Dragonette.

06:50:35.099 --> 06:50:37.740
I was convinced I was cursed.

06:50:37.799 --> 06:50:40.319
I thought I'd never get even one living

06:50:40.319 --> 06:50:40.799
daughter.

06:50:40.860 --> 06:50:42.299
And now I have 3.

06:50:42.479 --> 06:50:45.540
She caught a wayward bubble in her talons

06:50:45.540 --> 06:50:46.080
and smiled.

06:50:46.139 --> 06:50:48.060
And I'm not afraid anymore.

06:50:48.119 --> 06:50:50.159
That's the most amazing part.

06:50:50.220 --> 06:50:53.279
I know the assassin is gone, so I can

06:50:53.279 --> 06:50:57.000
just be happy to be with Aucklet, instead

06:50:57.000 --> 06:50:59.099
of being terrified every minute, that I'm

06:50:59.099 --> 06:50:59.700
about to lose her.

06:50:59.759 --> 06:51:02.759
I never told you how sorry I was.

06:51:02.819 --> 06:51:04.740
Turtle blurted.

06:51:04.799 --> 06:51:06.720
He clapped his wings shut.

06:51:06.840 --> 06:51:09.060
This was not at all what he had meant to

06:51:09.060 --> 06:51:09.299
say.

06:51:09.360 --> 06:51:10.979
For what?

06:51:11.040 --> 06:51:12.240
The queen asked.

06:51:12.299 --> 06:51:15.419
For the eggs that died, he said

06:51:15.419 --> 06:51:16.080
miserably.

06:51:16.139 --> 06:51:19.020
When I was looking for Snapper, when the

06:51:19.020 --> 06:51:21.119
other guard got sick, and I couldn't find

06:51:21.119 --> 06:51:23.880
Snapper anywhere, and dad was so upset

06:51:23.880 --> 06:51:24.240
with me.

06:51:24.299 --> 06:51:26.639
That was you?

06:51:26.700 --> 06:51:29.819
She looked at him more closely, and he

06:51:29.819 --> 06:51:30.479
flinched back.

06:51:30.540 --> 06:51:33.720
But it wasn't anger in her eyes, or even

06:51:33.720 --> 06:51:34.380
disappointment.

06:51:34.439 --> 06:51:36.900
Was it pity?

06:51:37.020 --> 06:51:40.979
Your father felt terrible about that, she

06:51:40.979 --> 06:51:41.279
said.

06:51:41.340 --> 06:51:44.880
Especially once we found out that Snapper

06:51:44.880 --> 06:51:46.860
had snuck off to the Summer Palace and

06:51:46.860 --> 06:51:47.459
wasn't even here.

06:51:47.520 --> 06:51:51.240
Oh, I made sure her death was a little

06:51:51.240 --> 06:51:52.560
extra painful for that.

06:51:52.619 --> 06:51:54.479
What?

06:51:54.599 --> 06:51:57.119
Turtle wasn't sure he'd followed her

06:51:57.119 --> 06:51:58.259
aquatic correctly.

06:51:58.319 --> 06:52:01.200
Snapper wasn't, what?

06:52:01.259 --> 06:52:04.080
She was supposed to stay in the deep

06:52:04.080 --> 06:52:06.779
palace in case she was needed, but she

06:52:06.779 --> 06:52:08.700
left, Queen Coral said.

06:52:08.759 --> 06:52:10.860
That's why you couldn't find her here.

06:52:10.919 --> 06:52:12.479
Didn't you know that?

06:52:12.540 --> 06:52:15.299
No, Turtle said.

06:52:15.360 --> 06:52:17.580
No one ever told me that.

06:52:17.639 --> 06:52:20.520
I thought Gil was going to tell you.

06:52:20.580 --> 06:52:21.900
Coral mused.

06:52:21.959 --> 06:52:24.360
Maybe he didn't get a chance before.

06:52:24.419 --> 06:52:26.400
She trailed off.

06:52:26.459 --> 06:52:30.240
Turtle's mind was spinning, as if it was

06:52:30.240 --> 06:52:31.319
caught in a whirlpool.

06:52:31.380 --> 06:52:34.020
He couldn't have found Snapper that day

06:52:34.020 --> 06:52:36.900
not in time to help his father, if she

06:52:36.900 --> 06:52:38.279
was all the way at the summer palace.

06:52:38.340 --> 06:52:39.959
It wasn't his fault.

06:52:40.020 --> 06:52:42.840
It wasn't his failure, and his father

06:52:42.840 --> 06:52:44.279
knew it before he died.

06:52:44.340 --> 06:52:46.740
Maybe he forgave me.

06:52:46.799 --> 06:52:48.180
Turtle thought.

06:52:48.240 --> 06:52:50.459
The 1st hopeful thought he'd had about

06:52:50.459 --> 06:52:51.419
his father in years.

06:52:51.479 --> 06:52:54.060
Sorry nobody told you.

06:52:54.119 --> 06:52:56.400
His mother said unexpectedly.

06:52:56.459 --> 06:52:59.700
You were such a little dragonette, and

06:52:59.700 --> 06:53:00.540
you tried so hard.

06:53:00.599 --> 06:53:04.979
And then, even more unexpectedly, she put

06:53:04.979 --> 06:53:07.439
one wing around his shoulders and pulled

06:53:07.439 --> 06:53:07.860
him closer.

06:53:07.919 --> 06:53:10.740
Turtle's heart was definitely going to

06:53:10.740 --> 06:53:11.279
explode.

06:53:11.340 --> 06:53:13.439
What's your name again?

06:53:13.500 --> 06:53:14.580
She asked.

06:53:14.639 --> 06:53:17.520
Which almost wrecked the moment, except

06:53:17.520 --> 06:53:18.779
that nothing could do that.

06:53:18.840 --> 06:53:21.119
Turtle, he said.

06:53:21.180 --> 06:53:22.919
It's turtle.

06:53:22.979 --> 06:53:24.840
She smiled down at him.

06:53:24.900 --> 06:53:26.639
I'll remember it this time.

06:53:26.759 --> 06:53:28.500
He smiled back.

06:53:28.560 --> 06:53:32.040
Holy mother of scavengers, she knows who

06:53:32.040 --> 06:53:32.400
I am.

06:53:32.459 --> 06:53:36.360
She cares about my feelings, and I didn't

06:53:36.360 --> 06:53:37.200
even have to be a hero.

06:53:37.259 --> 06:53:38.819
I'm just me.

06:53:38.880 --> 06:53:40.259
Turtle.

06:53:40.319 --> 06:53:42.840
Her dragonette, who tried his best.

06:53:42.959 --> 06:53:46.259
He leaned into her, and thought about

06:53:46.259 --> 06:53:48.540
heroes, and stories, and

06:53:48.540 --> 06:53:49.560
misunderstandings.

06:53:49.619 --> 06:53:52.319
He knew he still had to go find anemone

06:53:52.319 --> 06:53:54.959
to do something heroic, and possibly

06:53:54.959 --> 06:53:55.439
impossible.

06:53:55.500 --> 06:53:58.139
He knew Dark Stalker was still out there

06:53:58.139 --> 06:54:01.020
and he hadn't yet tried his best to stop

06:54:01.020 --> 06:54:02.099
him, but he would.

06:54:02.159 --> 06:54:06.360
But for now, for this moment, he let

06:54:06.360 --> 06:54:08.880
himself just be turtle, under his

06:54:08.880 --> 06:54:11.040
mother's wing, where he'd always wanted

06:54:11.040 --> 06:54:11.520
to be.

06:54:11.580 --> 06:54:16.139
Chapter 21.

06:54:16.439 --> 06:54:20.880
All too soon, a sea wing messenger came

06:54:20.880 --> 06:54:22.919
from the palace looking for Queen Coral.

06:54:22.979 --> 06:54:25.560
A dragon from the talons of peace is here

06:54:25.560 --> 06:54:27.000
to see you, he reported.

06:54:27.060 --> 06:54:29.700
News about changes in the sky kingdom, he

06:54:29.700 --> 06:54:29.939
says.

06:54:30.000 --> 06:54:32.700
The queen made a face at Turtle and

06:54:32.700 --> 06:54:33.240
Aucklet.

06:54:33.299 --> 06:54:35.819
Official business, she said.

06:54:35.880 --> 06:54:37.560
We have to get back to the palace

06:54:37.560 --> 06:54:38.040
outlet.

06:54:38.159 --> 06:54:39.599
Okay.

06:54:39.659 --> 06:54:41.819
The little dragonette spun through the

06:54:41.819 --> 06:54:44.040
bubbles one last time and swam over to

06:54:44.040 --> 06:54:44.400
her mother.

06:54:44.459 --> 06:54:48.060
Turtle, she cried, recognizing him.

06:54:48.119 --> 06:54:50.159
Aucklett threw her arms around his neck

06:54:50.159 --> 06:54:51.119
and hugged him tight.

06:54:51.180 --> 06:54:54.000
He hugged her back, thinking, I won't let

06:54:54.000 --> 06:54:55.740
anyone hurt you, little sister.

06:54:55.799 --> 06:54:57.959
See you soon.

06:54:58.020 --> 06:54:59.340
His mother flashed.

06:54:59.459 --> 06:55:01.799
Turtle watched them swim inside.

06:55:01.860 --> 06:55:04.619
His heart ached, but his wings felt

06:55:04.619 --> 06:55:05.400
stronger than ever.

06:55:05.459 --> 06:55:08.220
He was going to find anemone and stop her

06:55:08.220 --> 06:55:09.540
no matter what it took.

06:55:09.599 --> 06:55:11.759
I know the truth now.

06:55:11.819 --> 06:55:14.279
The coral was trying to take me to

06:55:14.279 --> 06:55:14.819
Snapper.

06:55:14.880 --> 06:55:16.979
It only seemed like it didn't work

06:55:16.979 --> 06:55:18.900
because it was trying to get to the

06:55:18.900 --> 06:55:19.619
summer palace.

06:55:19.680 --> 06:55:21.659
The coral.

06:55:21.720 --> 06:55:23.880
He could use that to figure out where

06:55:23.880 --> 06:55:24.900
anemone was.

06:55:24.959 --> 06:55:26.939
A thought that really should have

06:55:26.939 --> 06:55:29.340
occurred to him a couple of days and a

06:55:29.340 --> 06:55:30.180
very long flight ago.

06:55:30.240 --> 06:55:32.520
He prayed that it would point south

06:55:32.520 --> 06:55:34.200
toward Jane Mountain.

06:55:34.259 --> 06:55:36.180
Maybe it would lead him all the way back

06:55:36.180 --> 06:55:37.319
to the safety of school.

06:55:37.380 --> 06:55:40.500
The tiny red tree felt fragile and

06:55:40.500 --> 06:55:42.599
brittle in his talons, as though it might

06:55:42.599 --> 06:55:43.500
snap at any moment.

06:55:43.560 --> 06:55:47.639
Anemone, he whispered to it, where is my

06:55:47.639 --> 06:55:47.939
sister?

06:55:48.000 --> 06:55:51.360
It wriggled in his talons, pointing up

06:55:51.360 --> 06:55:53.700
and away from the deep palace, but not

06:55:53.700 --> 06:55:54.000
south.

06:55:54.060 --> 06:55:56.459
He let it pull him into one of the swift

06:55:56.459 --> 06:55:58.319
currents that spiraled out to the

06:55:58.319 --> 06:55:58.680
islands.

06:55:58.799 --> 06:56:01.919
For a while he swam steadily, and his

06:56:01.919 --> 06:56:04.319
spirits rose with every wing stroke away

06:56:04.319 --> 06:56:04.919
from the palace.

06:56:04.979 --> 06:56:07.799
She wasn't lurking there, lying in wait

06:56:07.799 --> 06:56:08.159
for his mother.

06:56:08.220 --> 06:56:10.259
Whatever anemone was up to.

06:56:10.319 --> 06:56:11.759
Maybe no one had to die.

06:56:11.819 --> 06:56:13.500
Left.

06:56:13.560 --> 06:56:16.680
The curls suddenly insisted, tugging him

06:56:16.680 --> 06:56:19.380
up out of the current and up, up, up to

06:56:19.380 --> 06:56:19.740
the surface.

06:56:19.799 --> 06:56:22.319
Turtle had to pinwheel fast with his

06:56:22.319 --> 06:56:23.819
wings and tail to stay with it.

06:56:23.939 --> 06:56:27.180
Cascades of green blue bubbles exploded

06:56:27.180 --> 06:56:27.540
around him.

06:56:27.599 --> 06:56:29.580
It was leading him to an island.

06:56:29.700 --> 06:56:32.040
He could see the shape of the land ahead

06:56:32.040 --> 06:56:33.779
of him, but he didn't recognize it.

06:56:33.840 --> 06:56:36.659
Not until he popped out of the water and

06:56:36.659 --> 06:56:38.639
saw the ruins jutting out of the jungle.

06:56:38.700 --> 06:56:41.819
The island palace, the place where the

06:56:41.819 --> 06:56:44.580
animus test had taken place, where he'd

06:56:44.580 --> 06:56:46.139
cursed his little sister with his own

06:56:46.139 --> 06:56:48.000
power, so he could stay hidden.

06:56:48.119 --> 06:56:51.599
And there was anemone, digging a hole in

06:56:51.599 --> 06:56:53.580
the beach with her claws, muttering

06:56:53.580 --> 06:56:56.459
furiously to herself, wet sand covered

06:56:56.459 --> 06:56:58.860
her webbed talons, and plastered her tail

06:56:58.860 --> 06:57:01.020
so she looked half mud wing.

06:57:01.020 --> 06:57:03.959
Turtle floundered forward in the surf as

06:57:03.959 --> 06:57:06.119
the waves tried alternately to toss him

06:57:06.119 --> 06:57:08.340
onto the sand, or to drag him back into

06:57:08.340 --> 06:57:09.180
their arms.

06:57:09.240 --> 06:57:11.639
The sun was unexpectedly bright in his

06:57:11.639 --> 06:57:11.880
eyes.

06:57:11.939 --> 06:57:14.819
Somehow, he'd expected to confront

06:57:14.819 --> 06:57:17.340
anemone deep underwater, or in the rain.

06:57:17.400 --> 06:57:20.400
This idyllic beach scene didn't fit his

06:57:20.400 --> 06:57:22.020
idea of an animist showdown.

06:57:22.080 --> 06:57:23.819
Anemone.

06:57:23.880 --> 06:57:26.340
He gasped, staggering onto the beach.

06:57:26.400 --> 06:57:28.799
The coral practically dragged him forward

06:57:28.799 --> 06:57:30.959
so it could tap Anemone's tail.

06:57:31.020 --> 06:57:34.020
His sister whirled around, her face

06:57:34.020 --> 06:57:35.340
contorted with fury.

06:57:35.400 --> 06:57:38.939
You boring lump of kelp, she yelled at

06:57:38.939 --> 06:57:39.240
him.

06:57:39.299 --> 06:57:40.560
You ruin everything.

06:57:40.619 --> 06:57:42.299
Why can't you leave me alone?

06:57:42.360 --> 06:57:46.020
You're my sister, he said.

06:57:46.080 --> 06:57:48.720
He let his wings rest on the sand and

06:57:48.720 --> 06:57:50.759
tried to catch his breath as he tucked

06:57:50.759 --> 06:57:51.540
the coral away.

06:57:51.599 --> 06:57:53.520
I'm worried about you.

06:57:53.580 --> 06:57:55.200
Are you?

06:57:55.259 --> 06:57:57.479
she scoffed, or are you worried about

06:57:57.479 --> 06:57:58.200
what I might do?

06:57:58.259 --> 06:58:01.560
Um, he said, that too.

06:58:01.680 --> 06:58:05.159
Well, you can't stop me, she said

06:58:05.159 --> 06:58:05.880
mockingly.

06:58:05.939 --> 06:58:07.740
So there's really no point in you being

06:58:07.740 --> 06:58:07.979
here.

06:58:08.040 --> 06:58:10.740
Go back to your loser friends and your

06:58:10.740 --> 06:58:11.880
hypnotized girlfriend.

06:58:11.939 --> 06:58:15.000
You're the one who put that spell on her

06:58:15.000 --> 06:58:16.139
turtle flared.

06:58:16.200 --> 06:58:17.279
I didn't ask you to.

06:58:17.340 --> 06:58:20.580
Because you're a wimp, who's afraid to

06:58:20.580 --> 06:58:21.779
even try for what he wants.

06:58:21.840 --> 06:58:24.299
Anemone said, but I'm not like you.

06:58:24.360 --> 06:58:26.700
I'm getting exactly what I want and

06:58:26.700 --> 06:58:28.560
deserve, and I'm getting it today.

06:58:28.619 --> 06:58:30.900
She turned back to her digging.

06:58:30.959 --> 06:58:32.580
What are you looking for?

06:58:32.639 --> 06:58:33.840
Turtle asked.

06:58:33.900 --> 06:58:36.540
Something Whirlpool said he hid for me

06:58:36.540 --> 06:58:36.779
here.

06:58:36.840 --> 06:58:37.799
She said.

06:58:37.860 --> 06:58:38.939
Go away, turtle.

06:58:39.000 --> 06:58:41.220
Anemone, he said.

06:58:41.279 --> 06:58:43.799
I'm afraid dark stalkers put a spell on

06:58:43.799 --> 06:58:43.979
you.

06:58:44.040 --> 06:58:45.900
She laughed bitterly.

06:58:45.959 --> 06:58:48.360
Well, that would be ironic.

06:58:48.479 --> 06:58:51.479
I mean, I think he's enchanted you to

06:58:51.479 --> 06:58:53.880
kill mother, and maybe Aucklet and the

06:58:53.880 --> 06:58:54.479
rest of our family.

06:58:54.540 --> 06:58:56.700
Turtle explained.

06:58:56.759 --> 06:58:59.939
Oh, she said, and laughed again.

06:59:00.000 --> 06:59:02.340
I don't need to be enchanted to want to

06:59:02.340 --> 06:59:03.599
do that, big brother.

06:59:03.720 --> 06:59:06.119
I think anyone who met you all would feel

06:59:06.119 --> 06:59:06.659
the same way.

06:59:06.720 --> 06:59:10.860
But I think this is his vengeance, Turtles

06:59:10.860 --> 06:59:13.139
said desperately, for what Fathom did to

06:59:13.139 --> 06:59:13.319
him.

06:59:13.380 --> 06:59:17.040
Maybe, Anemone said with a shrug.

06:59:17.159 --> 06:59:19.979
But if I do it, I'll be queen of the sea

06:59:19.979 --> 06:59:21.840
wings, and then he'll have to respect

06:59:21.840 --> 06:59:22.200
me.

06:59:22.259 --> 06:59:24.240
And if that's what he was hoping for

06:59:24.240 --> 06:59:25.860
maybe he'll be proud of me too.

06:59:25.919 --> 06:59:28.500
How can you not care?

06:59:28.560 --> 06:59:29.880
Turtle demanded.

06:59:29.939 --> 06:59:31.380
Is it your soul?

06:59:31.439 --> 06:59:33.840
Maybe he didn't enchant that necklace to

06:59:33.840 --> 06:59:34.740
protect it after all?

06:59:34.799 --> 06:59:37.860
Maybe, you've been losing it all along

06:59:37.860 --> 06:59:39.180
piece by piece.

06:59:39.240 --> 06:59:41.939
That whole idea of the soul is

06:59:41.939 --> 06:59:42.419
ridiculous.

06:59:42.479 --> 06:59:44.099
Anemone snapped.

06:59:44.159 --> 06:59:46.799
Good dragons do bad things, and bad

06:59:46.799 --> 06:59:48.599
dragons do good things all the time.

06:59:48.659 --> 06:59:51.779
Nobody has an entirely good soul to start

06:59:51.779 --> 06:59:52.020
with.

06:59:52.139 --> 06:59:54.419
It's just stupid to think that it's like

06:59:54.419 --> 06:59:56.700
a block of stone, and my magic is

06:59:56.700 --> 06:59:58.139
chipping away at it.

06:59:58.200 --> 06:59:58.799
It doesn't make sense.

06:59:58.860 --> 07:00:01.979
She smashed her tail into the sand

07:00:01.979 --> 07:00:04.200
cracking seashells and frightening small

07:00:04.200 --> 07:00:05.819
crabs in every direction.

07:00:05.880 --> 07:00:07.319
Where is it?

07:00:07.380 --> 07:00:10.860
If he was lying to me, I swear, I'm going

07:00:10.860 --> 07:00:13.020
to hunt down Whirlpool's drifting corpse

07:00:13.020 --> 07:00:13.919
and kill him again.

07:00:13.979 --> 07:00:15.900
Again?

07:00:16.020 --> 07:00:18.240
Turtles' ears twitched.

07:00:18.299 --> 07:00:19.259
What?

07:00:19.380 --> 07:00:20.279
Again.

07:00:20.340 --> 07:00:22.139
Anemone, what do you mean?

07:00:22.200 --> 07:00:25.020
I'm the one who killed him the 1st time.

07:00:25.080 --> 07:00:27.060
She gave him a scornful look.

07:00:27.119 --> 07:00:30.419
Did you really think he accidentally fell

07:00:30.419 --> 07:00:31.740
into that pool of eels?

07:00:31.799 --> 07:00:33.900
We figured out that he'd been trying to

07:00:33.900 --> 07:00:34.799
kill tsunami.

07:00:34.860 --> 07:00:37.619
And then he realized how powerful I was

07:00:37.619 --> 07:00:39.240
and he was going to tell mother and

07:00:39.240 --> 07:00:39.779
blister.

07:00:39.840 --> 07:00:41.220
She shrugged.

07:00:41.279 --> 07:00:42.540
So I took care of him.

07:00:42.599 --> 07:00:45.119
Three moons.

07:00:45.180 --> 07:00:47.759
Turtle had been worrying about anemone

07:00:47.759 --> 07:00:49.919
all this time, worrying about what she

07:00:49.919 --> 07:00:52.319
might do, about how the magic he'd given

07:00:52.319 --> 07:00:53.220
her might affect her.

07:00:53.279 --> 07:00:56.099
And yet, when she did do something big

07:00:56.099 --> 07:00:58.319
and terrible, he'd missed it completely.

07:00:58.380 --> 07:01:03.419
Oh, she said, spotting a gleam of metal

07:01:03.419 --> 07:01:05.939
in the sand underfoot, she pounced on it

07:01:05.939 --> 07:01:09.000
digging furiously, and finally reared

07:01:09.000 --> 07:01:11.580
back with a triumphant, aha.

07:01:11.639 --> 07:01:15.000
In her talons, was a dagger as long as

07:01:15.000 --> 07:01:18.060
her forearm, curved like a claw, and

07:01:18.060 --> 07:01:20.159
gleaming wickedly sharp along every edge

07:01:20.220 --> 07:01:25.020
3 moons, turtle whispered, anemone.

07:01:25.080 --> 07:01:28.740
Whirlpool wanted to be king pretty badly

07:01:28.740 --> 07:01:31.380
she said, turning the dagger to catch the

07:01:31.380 --> 07:01:31.799
sunlight.

07:01:31.860 --> 07:01:34.919
I think he was hoping to shape me into a

07:01:34.919 --> 07:01:37.619
darker dragon by making me cast all those

07:01:37.619 --> 07:01:39.119
practice spells.

07:01:39.180 --> 07:01:42.000
He wanted me to go evil and try for the

07:01:42.000 --> 07:01:42.240
throne.

07:01:42.360 --> 07:01:44.580
He told me he'd hidden a perfect weapon

07:01:44.580 --> 07:01:46.799
here, ready for whenever I needed it.

07:01:46.860 --> 07:01:49.080
For whenever I wanted to challenge

07:01:49.080 --> 07:01:49.560
mother.

07:01:49.680 --> 07:01:51.360
She smiled at it.

07:01:51.419 --> 07:01:54.479
I think it'll work fine on little sisters

07:01:54.479 --> 07:01:55.439
too, don't you?

07:01:55.500 --> 07:01:57.840
And big ones, for that matter.

07:01:57.900 --> 07:02:00.299
But you can't.

07:02:00.419 --> 07:02:03.959
Turtle said, feeling sick, all through

07:02:03.959 --> 07:02:05.819
his scales and bones and muscles.

07:02:05.880 --> 07:02:10.200
Sure I can. she said, widening her blue

07:02:10.200 --> 07:02:10.799
eyes at him.

07:02:10.860 --> 07:02:13.560
I won't make orca's mistakes.

07:02:13.619 --> 07:02:16.740
I'll enchant this thing right now to be a

07:02:16.740 --> 07:02:17.759
perfect killing machine.

07:02:17.819 --> 07:02:19.020
It'll never miss.

07:02:19.139 --> 07:02:21.599
It'll go straight from mother's throat

07:02:21.599 --> 07:02:26.159
first, then Aucklet, tsunami, you.

07:02:26.279 --> 07:02:28.380
Her eyes narrowed.

07:02:28.439 --> 07:02:29.939
Moon?

07:02:30.000 --> 07:02:32.099
Maybe Kinkaju too.

07:02:32.159 --> 07:02:32.759
Why not?

07:02:32.819 --> 07:02:35.819
He did say anyone who gets in my way.

07:02:35.880 --> 07:02:37.860
This was it.

07:02:37.919 --> 07:02:39.840
This was the breaking point.

07:02:39.900 --> 07:02:41.759
His speeches weren't working.

07:02:41.819 --> 07:02:43.259
He had to do something.

07:02:43.319 --> 07:02:46.020
Even if it meant Dark Stalker found out

07:02:46.020 --> 07:02:46.380
about him.

07:02:46.439 --> 07:02:47.700
He had to do something.

07:02:47.759 --> 07:02:50.939
His talons closed around the nearest

07:02:50.939 --> 07:02:54.180
seashell, fan shaped, pale pink and white

07:02:54.180 --> 07:02:55.560
like anemones scales.

07:02:55.619 --> 07:02:58.680
I enchant you to break every spell.

07:02:58.740 --> 07:03:01.139
Dark Stalker has cast on anemone the

07:03:01.139 --> 07:03:03.900
moment you touch her. he said, and flung

07:03:03.900 --> 07:03:05.340
the seashell with all his might.

07:03:05.400 --> 07:03:08.220
It bounced off Anemone's side, and she

07:03:08.220 --> 07:03:10.439
jumped back, blinking and startled.

07:03:10.500 --> 07:03:13.740
What the anemone yelped, are you out of

07:03:13.740 --> 07:03:14.099
your mind?

07:03:14.159 --> 07:03:15.959
Necklace?

07:03:15.959 --> 07:03:18.119
he said, reaching out one arm.

07:03:18.180 --> 07:03:19.020
Come to me.

07:03:19.080 --> 07:03:22.319
The silver collar around Anemone's neck

07:03:22.319 --> 07:03:24.599
snapped off and flew into his talons.

07:03:24.659 --> 07:03:27.659
I enchant you to be powerless from now on

07:03:27.659 --> 07:03:30.540
he said to it, and threw the necklace as

07:03:30.540 --> 07:03:31.680
far out to sea as he could.

07:03:31.740 --> 07:03:34.439
Anemone's claws went to her throat.

07:03:34.500 --> 07:03:37.380
But she said, how?

07:03:37.439 --> 07:03:41.220
Dagger, turtle commanded, turn to sand

07:03:41.220 --> 07:03:41.700
forever.

07:03:41.759 --> 07:03:45.119
The dagger collapsed in anemones, talons

07:03:45.119 --> 07:03:46.080
and scattered into the wind.

07:03:46.139 --> 07:03:48.360
Anemone stared at him.

07:03:48.540 --> 07:03:51.299
I'm an animus too, said Turtle.

07:03:51.360 --> 07:03:53.459
I'm sorry, I should have told you

07:03:53.459 --> 07:03:53.759
sooner.

07:03:53.819 --> 07:03:56.220
That's ridiculous.

07:03:56.279 --> 07:03:57.540
Anemone cried.

07:03:57.599 --> 07:03:58.319
You?

07:03:58.380 --> 07:03:59.400
You're nobody.

07:03:59.459 --> 07:04:01.259
I'm the sea wing animus.

07:04:01.319 --> 07:04:02.759
You are.

07:04:02.819 --> 07:04:05.759
But that's because of me, Turtles said.

07:04:05.819 --> 07:04:08.040
I'm so sorry, Anemone.

07:04:08.099 --> 07:04:10.139
I'm the one who made you an animus.

07:04:10.200 --> 07:04:13.139
Right here, the day of the talons of

07:04:13.139 --> 07:04:13.979
power ceremony.

07:04:14.040 --> 07:04:16.380
I didn't want anyone to find out about me

07:04:16.380 --> 07:04:19.860
so I distracted them with you, and

07:04:19.860 --> 07:04:21.180
everything that's happened to you since

07:04:21.180 --> 07:04:22.680
then is all my fault.

07:04:22.740 --> 07:04:26.040
No, Anemone screamed.

07:04:26.099 --> 07:04:27.419
It's my power.

07:04:27.479 --> 07:04:28.860
You can't just take it?

07:04:28.919 --> 07:04:30.540
You can't just say it's yours.

07:04:30.599 --> 07:04:32.220
You did not create me.

07:04:32.279 --> 07:04:35.220
She launched herself at Turtle and

07:04:35.220 --> 07:04:36.900
slammed him onto his back in the waves.

07:04:36.959 --> 07:04:39.840
Her claws slashed the side of his throat

07:04:39.840 --> 07:04:42.299
and pain blistered through his gills.

07:04:42.360 --> 07:04:44.520
You didn't make me, and you can't stop

07:04:44.520 --> 07:04:44.880
me.

07:04:44.939 --> 07:04:47.400
I can still kill her, she yelled.

07:04:47.459 --> 07:04:49.979
I can kill her with my bare claws.

07:04:50.040 --> 07:04:51.000
I can kill her with anything.

07:04:51.060 --> 07:04:53.819
I can make daggers out of seashells.

07:04:53.880 --> 07:04:55.860
I can poison the drops of water around

07:04:55.860 --> 07:04:56.580
her snout.

07:04:56.639 --> 07:04:59.880
I can enchant her pearls to choke her, or

07:04:59.880 --> 07:05:02.400
her stupid narwhal horn to stab her in

07:05:02.400 --> 07:05:02.700
the heart.

07:05:02.759 --> 07:05:04.439
In shock.

07:05:04.500 --> 07:05:06.840
Turtle fought back, throwing her off

07:05:06.840 --> 07:05:07.080
him.

07:05:07.139 --> 07:05:10.080
She skidded onto the beach, and he leaped

07:05:10.080 --> 07:05:12.060
after her, pinning her down into the

07:05:12.060 --> 07:05:13.020
sand.

07:05:13.080 --> 07:05:17.040
This is what Moon saw, he realized, this

07:05:17.040 --> 07:05:17.520
fight.

07:05:17.580 --> 07:05:20.520
A jolt of relief made his heart pulse

07:05:20.520 --> 07:05:21.000
wildly.

07:05:21.060 --> 07:05:22.919
But I haven't lost my soul.

07:05:22.979 --> 07:05:25.259
I still don't want to hurt anemone.

07:05:25.319 --> 07:05:28.619
Her scales were slippery under his claws

07:05:28.619 --> 07:05:30.599
and sand sprayed up into his eyes

07:05:30.599 --> 07:05:32.340
stinging and blinding him.

07:05:32.400 --> 07:05:34.860
She sank her teeth into one of the webs

07:05:34.860 --> 07:05:37.319
on his front talons, and he roared with

07:05:37.319 --> 07:05:37.560
pain.

07:05:37.619 --> 07:05:40.860
He'd thought breaking dark stalker's

07:05:40.860 --> 07:05:41.759
spells would change her.

07:05:41.819 --> 07:05:44.040
He'd thought he was setting her free.

07:05:44.099 --> 07:05:45.599
Why didn't it work?

07:05:45.659 --> 07:05:48.720
Anemone thrashed and stabbed at his

07:05:48.720 --> 07:05:51.299
underbelly, sending more fiery bolts of

07:05:51.299 --> 07:05:52.380
agony along his scales.

07:05:52.439 --> 07:05:56.099
Knock my brother off me, anemone shouted

07:05:56.099 --> 07:05:58.139
flinging one talon out at something

07:05:58.139 --> 07:05:59.159
behind turtle.

07:05:59.220 --> 07:06:02.099
He turned, and saw a huge rock lever

07:06:02.099 --> 07:06:03.240
itself out of the sand.

07:06:03.299 --> 07:06:05.819
It shot toward him like an attacking sky

07:06:05.819 --> 07:06:08.400
wing, turtle ducked, and rolled off

07:06:08.400 --> 07:06:10.619
anemone, covering his head.

07:06:10.680 --> 07:06:13.799
Disappear, he shouted at the rock, with

07:06:13.799 --> 07:06:16.139
an odd thudding sound, the boulder

07:06:16.139 --> 07:06:17.040
vanished out of the air.

07:06:17.099 --> 07:06:19.740
Anemone leaped to her feet, with her

07:06:19.740 --> 07:06:20.459
wings spread.

07:06:20.520 --> 07:06:23.040
All the crabs on this beach, she

07:06:23.040 --> 07:06:23.520
shouted.

07:06:23.580 --> 07:06:25.319
Attack turtle, do it now.

07:06:25.380 --> 07:06:29.279
The sand erupted, as 100s of crabs came

07:06:29.279 --> 07:06:31.799
swarming out of their burrows, from tiny

07:06:31.799 --> 07:06:34.919
hermit crabs, up to massive talon sized

07:06:34.919 --> 07:06:37.680
red monsters, with snapping claws.

07:06:37.740 --> 07:06:40.259
Blue gray pincers popped out of the sand

07:06:40.259 --> 07:06:43.020
right below him, and clamped down sharply

07:06:43.020 --> 07:06:45.180
on one of his front talons.

07:06:45.240 --> 07:06:47.520
Turtle yowled and jumped back and felt

07:06:47.520 --> 07:06:50.459
more explosions of pain as claws dug in

07:06:50.459 --> 07:06:51.060
along his tail.

07:06:51.119 --> 07:06:54.180
Waves, he called desperately.

07:06:54.240 --> 07:06:56.040
Wash these crabs out to sea.

07:06:56.099 --> 07:06:59.340
The sea pulled back, as if mildly

07:06:59.340 --> 07:07:01.860
offended by the order, then came rushing

07:07:01.860 --> 07:07:04.560
in all at once in a huge tidal wave.

07:07:04.619 --> 07:07:08.220
Turtle felt himself slammed to the sand

07:07:08.220 --> 07:07:10.080
and through the water, he saw anemone

07:07:10.080 --> 07:07:11.279
clawing to stay on the beach.

07:07:11.340 --> 07:07:14.040
All the crabs were caught up and tumbled

07:07:14.040 --> 07:07:16.680
about and carried away, sucked out into a

07:07:16.680 --> 07:07:18.000
hissing, foaming ocean.

07:07:18.060 --> 07:07:20.580
He didn't have a moment to catch his

07:07:20.580 --> 07:07:23.580
breath before seashells began pelting him

07:07:23.580 --> 07:07:25.619
each one aiming to stab between his

07:07:25.619 --> 07:07:26.040
scales.

07:07:26.099 --> 07:07:30.479
Death by 1000 cuts, he thought, trying to

07:07:30.479 --> 07:07:31.919
wipe away the blood running into his

07:07:31.919 --> 07:07:32.220
eyes.

07:07:32.279 --> 07:07:35.580
Turtle tried to duck away, scrabbling

07:07:35.580 --> 07:07:36.779
through the sand for something he could

07:07:36.779 --> 07:07:39.180
work with, here, and here.

07:07:39.240 --> 07:07:41.700
Two sand dollars washed up by the wave.

07:07:41.759 --> 07:07:44.819
Protect me from the shells, he said to

07:07:44.819 --> 07:07:47.580
them, and they shot into the air, warding

07:07:47.580 --> 07:07:49.560
off the attacking seashells like tiny

07:07:49.560 --> 07:07:50.639
flying shields.

07:07:50.700 --> 07:07:52.020
Anemone.

07:07:52.080 --> 07:07:53.459
I don't want to fight you.

07:07:53.520 --> 07:07:54.599
He yelled.

07:07:54.720 --> 07:07:57.060
Then you shouldn't say stupid things that

07:07:57.060 --> 07:07:59.159
make me want to kill you, she yelled

07:07:59.159 --> 07:07:59.400
back.

07:07:59.459 --> 07:08:00.720
Swallow him up.

07:08:00.779 --> 07:08:03.840
The sand suddenly collapsed under him

07:08:03.840 --> 07:08:06.360
dropping him into a sinkhole, and then

07:08:06.360 --> 07:08:08.099
immediately began pouring back over his

07:08:08.099 --> 07:08:08.340
head.

07:08:08.400 --> 07:08:11.040
Turtle flailed around in a panic.

07:08:11.099 --> 07:08:13.619
He did not want to die by drowning in

07:08:13.619 --> 07:08:13.919
sand.

07:08:13.979 --> 07:08:16.020
He did not want to be buried and

07:08:16.020 --> 07:08:18.419
forgotten here on this beach, leaving

07:08:18.419 --> 07:08:20.819
Aucklet, and mother unprotected from

07:08:20.819 --> 07:08:22.799
anemone, and the rest of my friends

07:08:22.799 --> 07:08:26.099
enchanted by dark stalker, and Kingaju

07:08:26.099 --> 07:08:27.659
under that awful spell forever.

07:08:27.720 --> 07:08:30.779
He reached out with his magic, and

07:08:30.779 --> 07:08:32.880
wrenched an entire palm tree out of the

07:08:32.880 --> 07:08:33.060
ground.

07:08:33.119 --> 07:08:35.759
It came skidding across the sand toward

07:08:35.759 --> 07:08:38.040
him, nearly plowing through anemone

07:08:38.040 --> 07:08:40.560
before she jumped out of the way, and

07:08:40.560 --> 07:08:42.659
stopped, with its fronds hanging over the

07:08:42.659 --> 07:08:42.900
hole.

07:08:43.020 --> 07:08:45.900
Turtle sank his claws into the sharp

07:08:45.900 --> 07:08:48.180
edged leaves and dragged himself out

07:08:48.180 --> 07:08:49.619
talon over talon.

07:08:49.680 --> 07:08:53.400
The sand behind him made an ominous glorp

07:08:53.400 --> 07:08:55.740
sound, and tried to suck him back down.

07:08:55.799 --> 07:08:57.060
Let me go.

07:08:57.119 --> 07:08:58.919
Turtles shouted at it.

07:08:58.979 --> 07:09:02.040
A flurry of sand exploded upward, then

07:09:02.040 --> 07:09:04.439
settled into a normal non-carnivorous

07:09:04.439 --> 07:09:05.099
beach dune.

07:09:05.220 --> 07:09:07.979
Turtle clutched the trunk of the palm

07:09:07.979 --> 07:09:09.180
tree, panting heavily.

07:09:09.240 --> 07:09:11.220
This fight was uneven.

07:09:11.279 --> 07:09:13.860
She was willing to use lethal force, and

07:09:13.860 --> 07:09:14.520
he was not.

07:09:14.580 --> 07:09:16.860
He refused to kill his little sister.

07:09:16.919 --> 07:09:19.860
A faint whistling in the air warned him

07:09:19.860 --> 07:09:20.279
to look up.

07:09:20.340 --> 07:09:22.979
Something enormous was crashing down

07:09:22.979 --> 07:09:25.500
toward him, a piece of stone wall from

07:09:25.500 --> 07:09:27.119
the ruins of the island palace.

07:09:27.180 --> 07:09:28.560
Crush him!

07:09:28.680 --> 07:09:30.180
Anemone screamed.

07:09:30.299 --> 07:09:31.860
Don't stop until you hit him.

07:09:31.919 --> 07:09:33.119
Stop.

07:09:33.180 --> 07:09:34.560
Turtles shouted.

07:09:34.619 --> 07:09:37.380
The projectile wobbled for a moment, but

07:09:37.380 --> 07:09:38.040
it didn't stop.

07:09:38.099 --> 07:09:40.619
It kept coming faster and faster.

07:09:40.680 --> 07:09:42.060
Shield me.

07:09:42.119 --> 07:09:44.159
Turtle cried to the palm tree.

07:09:44.220 --> 07:09:45.959
He leaped off and covered his head.

07:09:46.020 --> 07:09:49.680
There was a muffled, smashing cracking

07:09:49.680 --> 07:09:50.040
sound.

07:09:50.099 --> 07:09:52.680
And when Turtle looked up, he saw pieces

07:09:52.680 --> 07:09:54.240
of tree raining down around him.

07:09:54.299 --> 07:09:57.060
The wall rebounded off the broken palm

07:09:57.060 --> 07:09:58.200
and leaped for him again.

07:09:58.259 --> 07:10:00.779
It won't stop until it hits me.

07:10:00.840 --> 07:10:01.799
That's the spell.

07:10:01.860 --> 07:10:04.500
Turtle grabbed the nearest thing he could

07:10:04.500 --> 07:10:06.959
read, a shell that once housed a hermit

07:10:06.959 --> 07:10:09.599
crab, and whispered, make my scales as

07:10:09.599 --> 07:10:10.439
hard as diamonds.

07:10:10.500 --> 07:10:12.240
Make my bones unbreakable.

07:10:12.299 --> 07:10:15.240
Make me impossible to hurt, no matter how

07:10:15.240 --> 07:10:16.619
hard that thing lands on me.

07:10:16.680 --> 07:10:19.500
He wrapped his claws around the shell, and

07:10:19.500 --> 07:10:21.779
crouched, with his eyes screwed shut.

07:10:21.840 --> 07:10:23.099
I'm going to die.

07:10:23.159 --> 07:10:24.180
I'm going to die.

07:10:24.240 --> 07:10:24.900
I'm going to die.

07:10:24.959 --> 07:10:27.900
The block of stone slammed into him with

07:10:27.900 --> 07:10:30.299
such force that it left an imprint in the

07:10:30.299 --> 07:10:30.540
sand.

07:10:30.599 --> 07:10:33.540
It felt like the entire deep palace

07:10:33.540 --> 07:10:34.259
landing on him.

07:10:34.319 --> 07:10:36.360
For a moment, he couldn't breathe.

07:10:36.479 --> 07:10:39.840
But he felt no pain, and he was still

07:10:39.840 --> 07:10:40.139
alive.

07:10:40.259 --> 07:10:44.220
Get off me.

07:10:44.279 --> 07:10:46.919
He croaked at the stone block when he

07:10:46.919 --> 07:10:47.700
could form words again.

07:10:47.759 --> 07:10:49.979
Its original mission complete.

07:10:50.040 --> 07:10:52.619
The block obligingly lifted away and

07:10:52.619 --> 07:10:54.779
clunked down in the sand beside him.

07:10:54.840 --> 07:10:58.439
Seaweed, turtle thought dizzily, wondering

07:10:58.439 --> 07:11:01.139
if he was about to lose consciousness, go

07:11:01.139 --> 07:11:03.540
wrap anemone's mouth shut, so she cannot

07:11:03.540 --> 07:11:06.720
cast any more animus spells, neither by

07:11:06.720 --> 07:11:08.700
voice or thought, as long as you are

07:11:08.700 --> 07:11:10.740
touching her, but make sure she can still

07:11:10.740 --> 07:11:11.099
breathe.

07:11:11.159 --> 07:11:13.919
From the muffled shrieks he could hear.

07:11:13.979 --> 07:11:16.919
He guessed that his spell succeeded, but

07:11:16.919 --> 07:11:17.819
he couldn't move yet.

07:11:17.880 --> 07:11:20.340
He had to lie there, waiting for

07:11:20.340 --> 07:11:22.500
everything in his body to realize that it

07:11:22.500 --> 07:11:22.919
still worked.

07:11:22.979 --> 07:11:26.700
A moment later, Claws raked viciously

07:11:26.700 --> 07:11:29.459
across his nose, and he jerked up to find

07:11:29.459 --> 07:11:30.779
anemones standing over him.

07:11:30.840 --> 07:11:33.840
She had so much seaweed wrapped around

07:11:33.840 --> 07:11:35.700
her snout that she couldn't see over it.

07:11:35.759 --> 07:11:38.400
She kept turning her head from side to

07:11:38.400 --> 07:11:40.919
side, to glare at him with one eye and

07:11:40.919 --> 07:11:41.220
then the other.

07:11:41.279 --> 07:11:44.220
Only her nostrils were still visible, and

07:11:44.220 --> 07:11:45.779
they were flaring with fury.

07:11:45.840 --> 07:11:48.779
She clawed at him again, and he stumbled

07:11:48.779 --> 07:11:51.119
back, before realizing that he'd barely

07:11:51.119 --> 07:11:51.540
felt them.

07:11:51.599 --> 07:11:54.959
He blinked down at his scales, which were

07:11:54.959 --> 07:11:56.880
a mess of blood from the seashell cuts.

07:11:56.939 --> 07:11:59.700
His sister leaped forward again and tried

07:11:59.700 --> 07:12:02.400
to slice her claws across his throat, but

07:12:02.400 --> 07:12:05.099
they ricocheted off as though, as though

07:12:05.099 --> 07:12:06.779
my scales are hard as diamonds.

07:12:06.840 --> 07:12:09.659
Turtles' talons were empty.

07:12:09.720 --> 07:12:12.720
Where was the shell he'd enchanted?

07:12:12.779 --> 07:12:15.419
Why was the spell still working on him if

07:12:15.419 --> 07:12:16.080
he wasn't holding it?

07:12:16.139 --> 07:12:18.720
Because I wasn't that specific?

07:12:18.779 --> 07:12:20.099
He realized.

07:12:20.159 --> 07:12:23.159
With most of his spells, he worded the

07:12:23.159 --> 07:12:24.900
enchantment to work as long as he was

07:12:24.900 --> 07:12:27.479
holding, Or touching, or wearing, the

07:12:27.479 --> 07:12:28.680
animus touched object.

07:12:28.740 --> 07:12:32.159
But with this one, I just told it to make

07:12:32.159 --> 07:12:33.119
me impossible to hurt.

07:12:33.180 --> 07:12:36.659
It was like the healing spell on Kinkachu

07:12:36.659 --> 07:12:39.180
or the feather that fixed Flame's scar.

07:12:39.240 --> 07:12:41.520
The effects were permanent, no matter

07:12:41.520 --> 07:12:43.200
what happened to the object afterward.

07:12:43.259 --> 07:12:45.479
He'd never really thought about the

07:12:45.479 --> 07:12:46.200
difference before.

07:12:46.259 --> 07:12:49.680
His mind spun to the spells Dark Stalker

07:12:49.680 --> 07:12:52.139
had cast on his night wings, they were

07:12:52.139 --> 07:12:53.520
all object dependent.

07:12:53.520 --> 07:12:55.919
If Dark Stalker took away their objects

07:12:55.919 --> 07:12:58.319
his subjects would lose those powers.

07:12:58.380 --> 07:13:01.860
He must know he could make them permanent

07:13:01.860 --> 07:13:03.299
but he's choosing not to.

07:13:03.360 --> 07:13:06.779
With a sickening lurch in his stomach, he

07:13:06.779 --> 07:13:08.880
tried to remember how anemone had worded

07:13:08.880 --> 07:13:09.959
the spell on Kinkaju.

07:13:10.020 --> 07:13:12.779
Did she say, as long as she has this

07:13:12.779 --> 07:13:13.200
rock?

07:13:13.259 --> 07:13:15.959
Or did she just say, make her love

07:13:15.959 --> 07:13:16.500
turtle?

07:13:16.560 --> 07:13:19.259
Was the enchantment permanent?

07:13:19.319 --> 07:13:21.959
Even if Kingaju took off the Skyfire?

07:13:21.959 --> 07:13:23.639
He couldn't remember.

07:13:23.700 --> 07:13:27.720
I'm so sorry, Kinkachu, he thought, with

07:13:27.720 --> 07:13:28.799
a wrench of agony.

07:13:28.860 --> 07:13:31.860
Turtle realized that anemone was

07:13:31.860 --> 07:13:32.700
glowering at him.

07:13:32.759 --> 07:13:35.819
Her sides were heaving, slick with sweat

07:13:35.819 --> 07:13:37.500
and sand and seawater.

07:13:37.560 --> 07:13:39.119
Anemone.

07:13:39.180 --> 07:13:42.060
He said carefully, please listen to me.

07:13:42.119 --> 07:13:45.419
She gestured to her snout like, have you

07:13:45.419 --> 07:13:46.259
given me any choice?

07:13:46.319 --> 07:13:50.459
I'm not going to kill you, he said, and I

07:13:50.459 --> 07:13:52.139
would really like you to not kill me.

07:13:52.259 --> 07:13:54.540
Can we talk without attacking each

07:13:54.540 --> 07:13:55.080
other?

07:13:55.139 --> 07:13:57.240
He sidled a step toward her.

07:13:57.299 --> 07:13:59.819
I'd like to think we can work this out

07:13:59.819 --> 07:14:02.220
with words instead of violence or magic.

07:14:02.279 --> 07:14:05.580
She rolled her eyes at him, which wasn't

07:14:05.580 --> 07:14:06.900
a very reassuring yes.

07:14:06.959 --> 07:14:09.360
All right, he said.

07:14:09.419 --> 07:14:10.740
Let's try this.

07:14:10.799 --> 07:14:12.060
Seaweed.

07:14:12.119 --> 07:14:14.580
I want you to wrap around anemones arm

07:14:14.580 --> 07:14:14.939
instead.

07:14:15.000 --> 07:14:17.520
But still, as long as you're touching

07:14:17.520 --> 07:14:18.299
her.

07:14:18.360 --> 07:14:20.759
She cannot use her magic in any way, and

07:14:20.759 --> 07:14:22.619
stay put until I remove you.

07:14:22.680 --> 07:14:24.180
He added hurriedly.

07:14:24.240 --> 07:14:27.720
The long strands of dark wet seaweed

07:14:27.720 --> 07:14:29.520
began smoothly unrolling from his

07:14:29.520 --> 07:14:32.159
sister's snout and transferring to one of

07:14:32.159 --> 07:14:33.419
her forearms instead.

07:14:33.659 --> 07:14:36.180
Anemone scowled down at the makeshift

07:14:36.180 --> 07:14:37.919
handcuff, as though she was thinking

07:14:37.919 --> 07:14:39.419
about cutting off her arm to get her

07:14:39.419 --> 07:14:39.959
magic back.

07:14:40.020 --> 07:14:43.139
You are so annoying.

07:14:43.259 --> 07:14:45.900
She snapped at Turtle, as soon as she

07:14:45.900 --> 07:14:46.439
could speak again.

07:14:46.560 --> 07:14:50.639
And you're very powerful, he said, but I

07:14:50.639 --> 07:14:53.279
can't let you go kill mother, or Aucklet

07:14:53.279 --> 07:14:54.659
or Tsunami, or anyone else.

07:14:54.720 --> 07:14:56.759
I don't believe you're that kind of

07:14:56.759 --> 07:14:57.180
dragon.

07:14:57.299 --> 07:15:00.000
Anemone threw her wings up in the air.

07:15:00.060 --> 07:15:01.380
Of course I am.

07:15:01.439 --> 07:15:02.580
I have to be.

07:15:02.639 --> 07:15:04.919
It's my stupid destiny to kill the

07:15:04.919 --> 07:15:05.279
queen.

07:15:05.340 --> 07:15:07.319
That's what princesses do.

07:15:07.380 --> 07:15:10.919
And I'm even worse, because I'm an animus

07:15:10.919 --> 07:15:13.619
so I'm going to turn evil anyway, no

07:15:13.619 --> 07:15:14.340
matter what I do.

07:15:14.400 --> 07:15:17.939
I should just do it and be evil and be

07:15:17.939 --> 07:15:18.840
done with it already.

07:15:18.900 --> 07:15:22.919
You don't have to be evil, Turtle cried

07:15:22.919 --> 07:15:23.819
appalled.

07:15:23.880 --> 07:15:25.740
Not every animus is evil.

07:15:25.799 --> 07:15:27.000
I'm not evil.

07:15:27.060 --> 07:15:30.060
But you will be, anemone said

07:15:30.060 --> 07:15:30.599
accusingly.

07:15:30.659 --> 07:15:31.979
We both will be.

07:15:32.040 --> 07:15:34.979
That's what happens to animus dragons

07:15:34.979 --> 07:15:37.439
unless you're dark stalker, and you're so

07:15:37.439 --> 07:15:38.580
smart.

07:15:38.580 --> 07:15:42.240
Fathom wasn't evil, Turtle pointed out.

07:15:42.299 --> 07:15:45.119
We don't know that, Anemone said.

07:15:45.180 --> 07:15:48.000
First of all, what he did to Dark Stalker

07:15:48.000 --> 07:15:50.099
wasn't exactly the kindest thing in the

07:15:50.099 --> 07:15:52.020
world, and then he disappears from

07:15:52.020 --> 07:15:52.439
history.

07:15:52.500 --> 07:15:54.419
Who knows what else he did with his

07:15:54.419 --> 07:15:54.659
power?

07:15:54.720 --> 07:15:58.259
There were lots of animus ice wings who

07:15:58.259 --> 07:15:59.040
didn't go evil either.

07:15:59.099 --> 07:16:01.080
Turtles said stubbornly.

07:16:01.139 --> 07:16:03.720
And the sandwing from 1000s of years ago

07:16:03.720 --> 07:16:04.500
who disappeared?

07:16:04.560 --> 07:16:08.220
Jerboa, as far as we know anyhow, and

07:16:08.220 --> 07:16:09.060
stone mover.

07:16:09.119 --> 07:16:12.599
So my choices are evil, missing, or

07:16:12.599 --> 07:16:13.619
fossilized?

07:16:13.680 --> 07:16:14.880
Anemone said.

07:16:14.939 --> 07:16:16.139
That's appealing.

07:16:16.200 --> 07:16:19.139
I think a spell to protect your soul

07:16:19.139 --> 07:16:21.000
could work, Turtle said.

07:16:21.060 --> 07:16:23.580
I just don't trust Dark Stalker to cast

07:16:23.580 --> 07:16:23.939
it for you.

07:16:24.000 --> 07:16:25.919
It won't work.

07:16:25.979 --> 07:16:28.439
It's already too late for me.

07:16:28.500 --> 07:16:30.479
Anemone shook her head.

07:16:30.540 --> 07:16:34.259
Ever since Whirlpool died, I see him all

07:16:34.259 --> 07:16:37.799
the time, in my dreams, in the faces of

07:16:37.799 --> 07:16:39.659
strange dragons, everywhere.

07:16:39.720 --> 07:16:42.479
I keep seeing those eels going after

07:16:42.479 --> 07:16:42.779
him.

07:16:42.840 --> 07:16:45.540
I see all the dragons I've hurt.

07:16:45.659 --> 07:16:47.520
Now moon's there too.

07:16:47.580 --> 07:16:50.639
And I hate what I did to her, but I also

07:16:50.639 --> 07:16:51.900
feel proud of it.

07:16:51.959 --> 07:16:53.159
Isn't that twisted?

07:16:53.220 --> 07:16:56.700
Whatever soul I had, it's long gone.

07:16:56.759 --> 07:16:58.979
So protecting it wouldn't be much use.

07:16:59.040 --> 07:17:03.119
Maybe losing your soul isn't the right

07:17:03.119 --> 07:17:03.840
way to describe it.

07:17:03.959 --> 07:17:05.159
Turtle said.

07:17:05.279 --> 07:17:08.580
Maybe it's more like, the more you use

07:17:08.580 --> 07:17:09.840
your power for bad things.

07:17:09.900 --> 07:17:12.180
The more you feel like you're entitled to

07:17:12.180 --> 07:17:13.380
use your power for anything.

07:17:13.439 --> 07:17:15.659
It makes it harder to go back.

07:17:15.720 --> 07:17:18.900
Only forward, into more bad things.

07:17:18.959 --> 07:17:20.279
He hesitated.

07:17:20.400 --> 07:17:23.459
But, I think you can go back.

07:17:23.520 --> 07:17:26.819
I think anyone can choose to do good or

07:17:26.819 --> 07:17:29.159
be good, no matter what happened before.

07:17:29.220 --> 07:17:31.919
I think you just have to try really

07:17:31.919 --> 07:17:32.400
hard.

07:17:32.459 --> 07:17:35.400
And that means stopping yourself before

07:17:35.400 --> 07:17:37.020
you do even worse things.

07:17:37.139 --> 07:17:39.540
She growled softly.

07:17:39.599 --> 07:17:42.900
I suppose you mean like killing a bunch

07:17:42.900 --> 07:17:43.740
of family members?

07:17:43.799 --> 07:17:46.439
Well, yeah, he said.

07:17:46.500 --> 07:17:47.700
That's one example.

07:17:47.759 --> 07:17:50.220
She looked down at her talons.

07:17:50.340 --> 07:17:52.500
So what do I do instead?

07:17:52.560 --> 07:17:54.959
What if I can't stop myself?

07:17:54.959 --> 07:17:57.540
and you're not here next time to wrap me

07:17:57.540 --> 07:17:58.680
in enchanted seaweed?

07:17:58.799 --> 07:18:00.419
He hesitated.

07:18:00.540 --> 07:18:03.000
Do you want me to take it away again?

07:18:03.060 --> 07:18:04.680
Your power?

07:18:04.680 --> 07:18:07.680
I don't know if it'll work, but I could

07:18:07.680 --> 07:18:07.919
try.

07:18:07.979 --> 07:18:10.259
If you don't want to be an animus

07:18:10.259 --> 07:18:10.500
anymore.

07:18:10.560 --> 07:18:13.439
But then what would I be?

07:18:13.500 --> 07:18:17.040
She spread her wings and talons, leaving

07:18:17.040 --> 07:18:18.779
a trail of droplets from the dripping

07:18:18.779 --> 07:18:19.319
seaweed.

07:18:19.439 --> 07:18:22.319
Animus dragons are rare and special.

07:18:22.439 --> 07:18:24.599
I like knowing that I'm powerful.

07:18:24.720 --> 07:18:26.939
I want to be that powerful.

07:18:26.939 --> 07:18:29.459
Who would give away their own magic like

07:18:29.459 --> 07:18:29.700
that?

07:18:29.759 --> 07:18:32.279
I'm just...

07:18:32.279 --> 07:18:33.419
Scared of it too.

07:18:33.479 --> 07:18:36.360
I know, he said.

07:18:36.419 --> 07:18:37.979
I feel the same way.

07:18:38.040 --> 07:18:39.720
Really?

07:18:39.779 --> 07:18:40.680
She said.

07:18:40.740 --> 07:18:43.500
Because you don't act like you want to be

07:18:43.500 --> 07:18:43.860
powerful.

07:18:43.919 --> 07:18:47.279
Turtle opened his mouth to answer, then

07:18:47.279 --> 07:18:47.880
closed it again.

07:18:47.939 --> 07:18:49.259
She was right.

07:18:49.319 --> 07:18:51.119
He didn't act that way.

07:18:51.180 --> 07:18:53.459
But he did want to be an animus.

07:18:53.520 --> 07:18:55.680
It was the one thing that made him

07:18:55.680 --> 07:18:58.259
special, even if only in secret.

07:18:58.319 --> 07:18:59.880
He'd never give it up either.

07:18:59.939 --> 07:19:03.599
I've cast a spell to hide myself from

07:19:03.599 --> 07:19:05.220
Dark Stalker, he said.

07:19:05.279 --> 07:19:08.220
I think we should do the same for you, in

07:19:08.220 --> 07:19:09.900
case he does try to enchant you to do

07:19:09.900 --> 07:19:10.560
something evil.

07:19:10.619 --> 07:19:13.619
Oh, she said.

07:19:13.740 --> 07:19:15.599
That explains a lot.

07:19:15.659 --> 07:19:19.139
I mean, I was like, sure, turtle is

07:19:19.139 --> 07:19:21.720
boring, but Dark Stalker really acts like

07:19:21.720 --> 07:19:22.619
he doesn't exist at all.

07:19:22.680 --> 07:19:23.880
So weird.

07:19:23.939 --> 07:19:25.619
Now I get it.

07:19:25.680 --> 07:19:28.919
Aren't I less boring now that you know

07:19:28.919 --> 07:19:29.819
I'm inanimous?

07:19:29.939 --> 07:19:31.080
Turtle protested.

07:19:31.139 --> 07:19:33.779
He poked at his armband to pop out one of

07:19:33.779 --> 07:19:35.220
the last Skyfire rocks.

07:19:35.279 --> 07:19:37.919
You'll need this too. so he can't read

07:19:37.919 --> 07:19:38.279
your mind.

07:19:38.340 --> 07:19:41.700
She took the rock and held it up so the

07:19:41.700 --> 07:19:43.259
deep sparkles in it could catch the

07:19:43.259 --> 07:19:43.500
light.

07:19:43.560 --> 07:19:46.319
There was a strange twitch in the air

07:19:46.319 --> 07:19:48.659
like someone pinching the world around

07:19:48.659 --> 07:19:48.900
them.

07:19:48.959 --> 07:19:51.479
Turtle glanced up at the sky nervously.

07:19:51.540 --> 07:19:54.900
Maybe we should also enchant something to

07:19:54.900 --> 07:19:57.180
make Dark Stalker forget about our

07:19:57.180 --> 07:19:59.040
explosion of animus spells.

07:19:59.099 --> 07:20:01.080
He must be wondering what's going on.

07:20:01.139 --> 07:20:05.459
He, is that how he always catches me

07:20:05.459 --> 07:20:06.119
doing magic?

07:20:06.180 --> 07:20:09.060
Anemone trailed off with a shiver.

07:20:09.119 --> 07:20:12.360
He can sense animus spells being cast

07:20:12.360 --> 07:20:14.279
Turtle said, nodding.

07:20:14.340 --> 07:20:17.580
Then let's do that first, Anemone said

07:20:17.580 --> 07:20:18.299
alarmed.

07:20:18.360 --> 07:20:20.040
She grabbed a palm frond.

07:20:20.099 --> 07:20:23.340
Hey, leaves, erase all the yikes.

07:20:23.400 --> 07:20:25.680
She shrieked, as the entire beach

07:20:25.680 --> 07:20:27.659
shuddered violently underneath them.

07:20:27.720 --> 07:20:30.900
Erase all our spells from Dark Stalker's

07:20:30.900 --> 07:20:31.080
memory.

07:20:31.200 --> 07:20:33.180
She shouted as fast as she could.

07:20:33.240 --> 07:20:36.000
The air was suddenly pressing in on them

07:20:36.000 --> 07:20:38.099
as though they were being squeezed into

07:20:38.099 --> 07:20:39.240
an invisible chest.

07:20:39.299 --> 07:20:42.360
Turtle's ears popped painfully, and he

07:20:42.360 --> 07:20:43.439
staggered toward anemone.

07:20:43.500 --> 07:20:44.759
Did it work?

07:20:44.819 --> 07:20:45.959
She yelled.

07:20:46.020 --> 07:20:49.259
And Turtle realized there was a dark, high

07:20:49.259 --> 07:20:51.540
pitched whistling sound drowning out all

07:20:51.540 --> 07:20:52.259
other noises.

07:20:52.380 --> 07:20:54.299
I don't know.

07:20:54.360 --> 07:20:55.680
I don't see why.

07:20:55.740 --> 07:20:56.939
It should.

07:20:57.060 --> 07:20:59.639
Turtle's gaze fell from the gathering

07:20:59.639 --> 07:21:02.520
clouds to his sister, and he was hit by a

07:21:02.520 --> 07:21:03.540
sinking realization.

07:21:03.599 --> 07:21:06.479
The seaweed, he cried.

07:21:06.599 --> 07:21:09.360
He leaped forward and sliced through the

07:21:09.360 --> 07:21:11.159
wrapping of seaweed around Anemone's

07:21:11.159 --> 07:21:11.340
arm.

07:21:11.400 --> 07:21:13.740
It didn't work because your magic was

07:21:13.740 --> 07:21:14.040
blocked.

07:21:14.099 --> 07:21:17.340
There seemed to be infinite, thick, sticky

07:21:17.340 --> 07:21:19.380
layers of seaweed and they wouldn't come

07:21:19.380 --> 07:21:21.840
off fast enough, no matter how he stabbed

07:21:21.840 --> 07:21:22.619
and peeled at them.

07:21:22.680 --> 07:21:24.419
You do this, Belle.

07:21:24.479 --> 07:21:26.939
Anemone shouted, but the wind was now

07:21:26.939 --> 07:21:29.400
screaming along with a sound, and sand

07:21:29.400 --> 07:21:31.860
was blowing fiercely in their faces, like

07:21:31.860 --> 07:21:33.720
the entire beach was rising up to attack

07:21:33.720 --> 07:21:34.020
them.

07:21:34.139 --> 07:21:37.740
Turtle clasped his sister's talons, folded

07:21:37.740 --> 07:21:39.900
his wings around her, and held on tight.

07:21:39.959 --> 07:21:42.900
Suddenly, there was a bending, warping

07:21:42.900 --> 07:21:45.419
feeling to the universe, and Turtle heard

07:21:45.419 --> 07:21:48.299
Dark Stalker's voice as clearly as if he

07:21:48.299 --> 07:21:49.500
were standing right next to them.

07:21:49.560 --> 07:21:53.880
Bring them here, Dark Stalker growled.

07:21:53.939 --> 07:21:56.759
Every animous dragon in all the 7

07:21:56.759 --> 07:21:57.360
tribes.

07:21:57.419 --> 07:22:00.479
Bring them here to my throne room, right

07:22:00.479 --> 07:22:00.840
now.

07:22:00.900 --> 07:22:05.040
The world collapsed inward, into darkness

07:22:05.040 --> 07:22:07.979
and unfolded again into pale sunlight

07:22:07.979 --> 07:22:10.139
streaming through tall, narrow windows

07:22:10.139 --> 07:22:12.240
across a vast black marble hall.

07:22:12.299 --> 07:22:15.720
Outside the windows, the mountains of the

07:22:15.720 --> 07:22:19.139
night kingdom, inside the hall, staring

07:22:19.139 --> 07:22:22.560
down at them, dark stalker, wearing a

07:22:22.560 --> 07:22:24.900
crown made of twisted metal with sharp

07:22:24.900 --> 07:22:25.680
points.

07:22:25.979 --> 07:22:30.060
Chapter 22.

07:22:30.299 --> 07:22:34.380
Turtle gave a startled gasp and glanced

07:22:34.380 --> 07:22:34.619
around.

07:22:34.740 --> 07:22:37.560
All the way across the continent.

07:22:37.680 --> 07:22:40.500
He just summoned us, like a tray of

07:22:40.500 --> 07:22:40.979
shrimp.

07:22:41.040 --> 07:22:43.860
There were still cracks of darkness in

07:22:43.860 --> 07:22:44.159
the air.

07:22:44.220 --> 07:22:46.919
Like it was a scroll that had been folded

07:22:46.919 --> 07:22:49.020
and wrinkled too many times.

07:22:49.080 --> 07:22:51.540
The cracks hissed and sparked, spitting

07:22:51.540 --> 07:22:54.840
out turtle, anemone, stone mover, and

07:22:54.840 --> 07:22:57.540
right behind dark stalker, and unfamiliar

07:22:57.540 --> 07:22:58.139
sandwing.

07:22:58.200 --> 07:23:01.740
The sandwing met turtle's eyes, her face

07:23:01.740 --> 07:23:04.560
a mask of startled terror, and then she

07:23:04.560 --> 07:23:06.419
vanished again in less than a heartbeat.

07:23:06.479 --> 07:23:09.659
She was gone so quickly, the turtle

07:23:09.659 --> 07:23:11.159
thought he might have hallucinated her

07:23:11.159 --> 07:23:13.439
that perhaps she was a double image

07:23:13.439 --> 07:23:16.080
accidentally reflected by the teleporting

07:23:16.080 --> 07:23:18.419
cracks, especially since no one else

07:23:18.419 --> 07:23:20.040
acted as if they'd seen her too.

07:23:20.099 --> 07:23:22.020
Was that real?

07:23:22.080 --> 07:23:24.900
He sat down, rubbing his eyes.

07:23:24.959 --> 07:23:27.479
A splitting headache, was trying to

07:23:27.479 --> 07:23:29.340
splinter his skull into small pieces.

07:23:29.400 --> 07:23:33.959
I enchant this room so that no one can

07:23:33.959 --> 07:23:36.360
cast any spills while they're in here

07:23:36.360 --> 07:23:37.020
except me.

07:23:37.139 --> 07:23:39.360
Dark stalker growled.

07:23:39.419 --> 07:23:41.279
He loomed over anemone.

07:23:41.340 --> 07:23:43.319
Where is your neck band?

07:23:43.319 --> 07:23:44.159
he asked.

07:23:44.220 --> 07:23:46.619
I lost it, she said.

07:23:46.680 --> 07:23:47.639
I'll make another one.

07:23:47.700 --> 07:23:48.360
Don't worry.

07:23:48.419 --> 07:23:53.279
Someone gave you Skyfire, I see, he said

07:23:53.279 --> 07:23:55.080
tapping the top of her skull.

07:23:55.139 --> 07:23:57.299
Did you kill your mother?

07:23:57.360 --> 07:24:00.779
Turtle guessed from his tone that he

07:24:00.779 --> 07:24:01.619
already knew the answer.

07:24:01.740 --> 07:24:05.819
No, Anemone said, lifting her chin

07:24:05.819 --> 07:24:06.299
defiantly.

07:24:06.360 --> 07:24:07.919
What do you care anyway?

07:24:07.979 --> 07:24:10.139
Why'd you drag me back here after you

07:24:10.139 --> 07:24:11.340
just ordered me to go away?

07:24:11.459 --> 07:24:13.799
Dark Stalker hissed.

07:24:13.860 --> 07:24:16.020
Who are you fighting anemone?

07:24:16.080 --> 07:24:17.340
He asked.

07:24:17.400 --> 07:24:19.080
Turtle flinched guiltily.

07:24:19.139 --> 07:24:21.840
A scratch behind her ear was bleeding, and

07:24:21.840 --> 07:24:23.520
there were scratches along her sides from

07:24:23.520 --> 07:24:24.720
turtle's claws.

07:24:25.080 --> 07:24:27.060
No one important, she said.

07:24:27.119 --> 07:24:29.220
I was winning until you interrupted

07:24:29.220 --> 07:24:30.000
though, by the way.

07:24:30.060 --> 07:24:34.799
Those were battling animus spells, Dark

07:24:34.799 --> 07:24:35.520
Stalker said.

07:24:35.580 --> 07:24:38.340
And every animus in Pyria should be

07:24:38.340 --> 07:24:38.580
here.

07:24:38.639 --> 07:24:40.680
Which means...

07:24:40.680 --> 07:24:43.139
He whipped his head toward stone mover.

07:24:43.200 --> 07:24:45.779
The night wing lay awkwardly on his side

07:24:45.779 --> 07:24:48.659
still encased in stone, but looking very

07:24:48.659 --> 07:24:50.279
odd without his cave around him.

07:24:50.340 --> 07:24:53.580
His talent twitched feebly, as though he

07:24:53.580 --> 07:24:55.740
might be trying to right himself.

07:24:55.799 --> 07:24:58.919
Stone mover, Dark Stalker said.

07:24:58.979 --> 07:25:01.979
He tipped Stone Mover onto his talons and

07:25:01.979 --> 07:25:03.659
leaned over to hiss in his ear.

07:25:03.720 --> 07:25:05.639
Tell me the truth.

07:25:05.700 --> 07:25:09.180
How many dragons are in this room right

07:25:09.180 --> 07:25:09.659
now?

07:25:09.720 --> 07:25:13.020
Turtle tried to wave frantically to get

07:25:13.020 --> 07:25:15.959
his attention, to hold up 3 claws, or

07:25:15.959 --> 07:25:18.779
mine to keep his secret or something, but

07:25:18.779 --> 07:25:21.479
he wasn't fast enough, or a stone mover

07:25:21.479 --> 07:25:22.080
was too slow.

07:25:22.139 --> 07:25:27.119
For, Stone Mover said, sounding puzzled.

07:25:27.180 --> 07:25:28.619
I knew it.

07:25:28.680 --> 07:25:30.540
Dark stalker cried.

07:25:30.599 --> 07:25:31.740
There's another one.

07:25:31.799 --> 07:25:34.500
There's someone hiding from me.

07:25:34.560 --> 07:25:37.139
He seized a sword that was hanging on the

07:25:37.139 --> 07:25:37.319
wall.

07:25:37.380 --> 07:25:39.180
Bring me a dragon.

07:25:39.240 --> 07:25:41.939
Our hidden animus cares about very much.

07:25:42.060 --> 07:25:44.279
Alive for now.

07:25:44.340 --> 07:25:48.360
No, Turtle cried, but the sword was

07:25:48.360 --> 07:25:49.500
already whipping out the door.

07:25:49.560 --> 07:25:50.700
What can I do?

07:25:50.759 --> 07:25:52.799
I can't cast any spells in here.

07:25:52.860 --> 07:25:54.419
Do I have anything I can use?

07:25:54.479 --> 07:25:58.020
He scrabbled open his pouch, all banged

07:25:58.020 --> 07:26:00.119
up and covered with sand and searched

07:26:00.119 --> 07:26:01.619
inside, trying to think.

07:26:01.680 --> 07:26:04.919
The coral finder, the slate, the healing

07:26:04.919 --> 07:26:07.860
stone, his hiding stick, the slate

07:26:07.860 --> 07:26:09.119
Kibley.

07:26:09.180 --> 07:26:11.220
He pulled it out and wrote as quickly as

07:26:11.220 --> 07:26:11.580
he could.

07:26:11.639 --> 07:26:15.419
Dark Stalker knows about me, trapped in

07:26:15.419 --> 07:26:16.500
the Nightwing Palace.

07:26:16.560 --> 07:26:17.099
Help.

07:26:17.159 --> 07:26:20.340
As soon as he'd written it, he erased

07:26:20.340 --> 07:26:20.520
it.

07:26:20.580 --> 07:26:22.919
He couldn't risk dark stalker finding out

07:26:22.919 --> 07:26:24.060
he'd sent a message.

07:26:24.119 --> 07:26:26.220
Please see it soon, Kibley.

07:26:26.279 --> 07:26:27.240
He prayed.

07:26:27.299 --> 07:26:29.459
Hidden?

07:26:29.520 --> 07:26:31.919
Stone Mover coughed, bewildered.

07:26:31.979 --> 07:26:34.919
Yes, said Dark Stalker.

07:26:34.979 --> 07:26:37.020
One of the dragons you can see is a

07:26:37.020 --> 07:26:37.439
coward.

07:26:37.500 --> 07:26:39.720
Planning against me in secret.

07:26:39.779 --> 07:26:42.119
I think he's smart.

07:26:42.180 --> 07:26:43.860
Anemone said sharply.

07:26:43.919 --> 07:26:45.659
He knew right away not to trust you.

07:26:45.720 --> 07:26:47.939
He knew there was something seriously

07:26:47.939 --> 07:26:48.419
wrong with you.

07:26:48.479 --> 07:26:51.180
You think everything you do is right.

07:26:51.240 --> 07:26:53.819
You think you're so perfect, that you

07:26:53.819 --> 07:26:55.380
don't even care about the dragons around

07:26:55.380 --> 07:26:55.619
you.

07:26:55.680 --> 07:26:58.200
You're the only one who gets to decide

07:26:58.200 --> 07:26:59.580
what happens to everyone else.

07:26:59.700 --> 07:27:02.819
By all the moons.

07:27:02.939 --> 07:27:04.560
Dark Stalker growled.

07:27:04.619 --> 07:27:06.180
He pointed an anemone.

07:27:06.240 --> 07:27:08.580
Enchant this dragon to obey my every

07:27:08.580 --> 07:27:09.000
command.

07:27:09.060 --> 07:27:11.639
Now shut up, he barked at her.

07:27:11.759 --> 07:27:14.159
Anemone's mouth snapped closed.

07:27:14.220 --> 07:27:16.919
She touched her snout, looking startled

07:27:16.919 --> 07:27:19.619
and outraged and terrified all at once.

07:27:19.680 --> 07:27:23.880
No, Turtle felt the cold marble hall

07:27:23.880 --> 07:27:24.900
pressing in on him.

07:27:24.959 --> 07:27:27.479
That's the same spell he put on his

07:27:27.479 --> 07:27:27.720
father.

07:27:27.779 --> 07:27:30.720
He can make anemone do anything he wants

07:27:30.720 --> 07:27:31.080
now.

07:27:31.139 --> 07:27:35.340
That's better, Dark Stalker said.

07:27:35.400 --> 07:27:37.259
He paced around her slowly.

07:27:37.319 --> 07:27:40.500
You know, I've always had so many

07:27:40.500 --> 07:27:42.000
questions about anima's power.

07:27:42.060 --> 07:27:45.840
Maybe now, with you and Stone Mover both

07:27:45.840 --> 07:27:46.680
under my control.

07:27:46.740 --> 07:27:49.200
I can test out some of my theories.

07:27:49.259 --> 07:27:52.799
For instance, is there a limit to how

07:27:52.799 --> 07:27:54.659
many spells one can cast in a day?

07:27:54.720 --> 07:27:58.619
What happens when 2 animus dragons try to

07:27:58.619 --> 07:28:00.119
enchant something at the same time?

07:28:00.180 --> 07:28:01.979
And of course.

07:28:02.040 --> 07:28:05.939
How many spells does it take for a dragon

07:28:05.939 --> 07:28:07.020
to turn evil?

07:28:07.080 --> 07:28:10.500
He stopped in front of anemone, smiling

07:28:10.500 --> 07:28:11.040
down at her.

07:28:11.099 --> 07:28:13.319
For you, my dear.

07:28:13.380 --> 07:28:15.840
I'm guessing it won't be very many more.

07:28:15.900 --> 07:28:18.840
Turtle was transfixed with horror.

07:28:18.959 --> 07:28:21.299
This was exactly what he'd been trying to

07:28:21.299 --> 07:28:22.500
save anemone from.

07:28:22.560 --> 07:28:25.439
It hadn't even occurred to him that Stone

07:28:25.439 --> 07:28:27.659
Mover was one of Dark Stalker's puppets

07:28:27.659 --> 07:28:27.959
already.

07:28:28.020 --> 07:28:29.939
Maybe.

07:28:30.000 --> 07:28:32.400
That's what he meant when he said his

07:28:32.400 --> 07:28:33.599
talents weren't his own.

07:28:33.659 --> 07:28:36.779
Maybe he sensed Dark Stalker taking them

07:28:36.779 --> 07:28:36.959
over.

07:28:37.020 --> 07:28:39.360
Oh, anemone.

07:28:39.419 --> 07:28:40.619
How can I save you?

07:28:40.680 --> 07:28:43.500
A clattering sound came from the hall

07:28:43.500 --> 07:28:45.779
outside, and they all could hear a voice

07:28:45.779 --> 07:28:46.500
coming closer.

07:28:46.619 --> 07:28:49.979
This better be important, summoning a

07:28:49.979 --> 07:28:51.959
dragon with a sword in the middle of

07:28:51.959 --> 07:28:52.680
suntime?

07:28:52.740 --> 07:28:55.080
I mean, someone has the manners of an

07:28:55.080 --> 07:28:55.799
orangutan.

07:28:55.860 --> 07:28:57.659
I am moving.

07:28:57.720 --> 07:28:59.700
Quit pointing that, yourself at me.

07:28:59.759 --> 07:29:03.299
Oh, no, turtle thought.

07:29:03.360 --> 07:29:06.119
This bear poured over him like wet sand.

07:29:06.180 --> 07:29:10.080
Kinkaju bounded into the throne room, with

07:29:10.080 --> 07:29:12.119
a sword hovering menacingly in the air

07:29:12.119 --> 07:29:13.020
behind her.

07:29:13.080 --> 07:29:16.139
She was indignantly tangerine from horns

07:29:16.139 --> 07:29:18.540
to tail, and turtle's heart leaped at the

07:29:18.540 --> 07:29:18.840
side of her.

07:29:18.900 --> 07:29:22.919
Hello, King Bossy, she said to Dog

07:29:22.919 --> 07:29:24.779
Stalker, flicking her wings back.

07:29:24.840 --> 07:29:27.060
You could have sent a dragon to ask me

07:29:27.060 --> 07:29:28.200
nicely.

07:29:28.200 --> 07:29:30.479
It's pretty rude to wake someone up with

07:29:30.479 --> 07:29:31.259
sharp weapons.

07:29:31.319 --> 07:29:32.340
I have to say.

07:29:32.400 --> 07:29:35.880
Dog stalker slid over, and stared at her

07:29:35.880 --> 07:29:36.779
thoughtfully for a moment.

07:29:36.840 --> 07:29:38.580
Really?

07:29:38.580 --> 07:29:39.900
he said.

07:29:39.959 --> 07:29:44.040
Somebody cares about this dragon.

07:29:44.099 --> 07:29:47.040
Hey, Kinkachu squeaked.

07:29:47.099 --> 07:29:48.659
That's so unnecessary.

07:29:48.779 --> 07:29:50.759
All right.

07:29:50.819 --> 07:29:52.740
Dark Stalker said with a shrug.

07:29:52.799 --> 07:29:57.119
Cowardly animus, he said, raising his

07:29:57.119 --> 07:29:57.299
voice.

07:29:57.419 --> 07:30:01.080
You see that I have your unimpressive

07:30:01.080 --> 07:30:02.040
little rain wing.

07:30:02.099 --> 07:30:04.259
Kinkachu scowled at him.

07:30:04.319 --> 07:30:07.020
So now would be a good time to reveal

07:30:07.020 --> 07:30:07.380
yourself.

07:30:07.439 --> 07:30:10.619
Unless you want to see her sliced to

07:30:10.619 --> 07:30:10.919
pieces.

07:30:10.979 --> 07:30:14.580
He hooked the sword out of the air and

07:30:14.580 --> 07:30:16.919
swept it around to point at Kinkachu's

07:30:16.919 --> 07:30:18.599
throat in one graceful move.

07:30:18.720 --> 07:30:22.740
No, Turtle shouted, taking a step toward

07:30:22.740 --> 07:30:22.919
her.

07:30:22.979 --> 07:30:25.860
Don't do it, Kinkachu said.

07:30:25.979 --> 07:30:27.240
She closed her eyes.

07:30:27.299 --> 07:30:28.799
Stay hidden.

07:30:28.860 --> 07:30:29.939
You can stop him.

07:30:30.000 --> 07:30:31.200
You have to stop him.

07:30:31.259 --> 07:30:33.360
Not by myself.

07:30:33.419 --> 07:30:35.580
Turtle said, not without you.

07:30:35.639 --> 07:30:38.400
Yes, without me, she said.

07:30:38.459 --> 07:30:40.139
I know you can.

07:30:40.200 --> 07:30:42.540
Oh, monkey brains.

07:30:42.599 --> 07:30:45.419
Does this mean I'm the hapless sidekick?

07:30:45.479 --> 07:30:47.520
Blorg, that is so lame.

07:30:47.580 --> 07:30:50.279
Better than the wailing victim who needs

07:30:50.279 --> 07:30:50.939
rescuing, though.

07:30:51.060 --> 07:30:53.520
Make sure nobody writes me that way when

07:30:53.520 --> 07:30:55.500
this story becomes an epic poem, all

07:30:55.500 --> 07:30:55.740
right?

07:30:55.799 --> 07:30:58.020
And I would definitely like to be the

07:30:58.020 --> 07:30:59.040
hero next time, please.

07:30:59.159 --> 07:31:02.099
She glanced down at the sword and

07:31:02.099 --> 07:31:03.000
shivered slightly.

07:31:03.060 --> 07:31:06.119
I mean, in my next life, I guess.

07:31:06.180 --> 07:31:08.340
Kinkajoo.

07:31:08.400 --> 07:31:10.139
Turtle couldn't breathe.

07:31:10.200 --> 07:31:12.840
Was this what drowning felt like for

07:31:12.840 --> 07:31:13.619
other dragons?

07:31:13.680 --> 07:31:16.139
The story doesn't make sense without

07:31:16.139 --> 07:31:16.380
you.

07:31:16.439 --> 07:31:19.139
You're the whole point of it for me.

07:31:19.200 --> 07:31:22.619
Do please stop talking.

07:31:22.680 --> 07:31:24.659
Dark Stalker said to her.

07:31:24.720 --> 07:31:27.360
Last chance, animus.

07:31:27.419 --> 07:31:30.599
In 10 seconds, this babbling dragonette

07:31:30.599 --> 07:31:31.380
dies.

07:31:31.439 --> 07:31:34.020
Turtle took his hiding stick out of his

07:31:34.020 --> 07:31:34.439
pouch.

07:31:34.500 --> 07:31:37.799
And it was so ordinary, unremarkable

07:31:37.799 --> 07:31:39.060
boring.

07:31:39.119 --> 07:31:42.419
Nothing anyone would ever notice, kind of

07:31:42.419 --> 07:31:42.900
like him.

07:31:42.959 --> 07:31:45.779
But it held some of the most powerful

07:31:45.779 --> 07:31:46.799
magic in this room.

07:31:46.860 --> 07:31:49.200
And it was the only thing that might

07:31:49.200 --> 07:31:50.759
still be able to save the world.

07:31:50.819 --> 07:31:54.599
This wasn't the heroic story he dreamed

07:31:54.599 --> 07:31:55.560
of as a dragonette.

07:31:55.619 --> 07:31:58.080
He wasn't standing at the gates to the

07:31:58.080 --> 07:32:00.419
palace, fighting off attacking hordes

07:32:00.419 --> 07:32:00.959
with a spear.

07:32:01.020 --> 07:32:03.720
He wasn't defending his kingdom with

07:32:03.720 --> 07:32:04.680
valiant strength.

07:32:04.740 --> 07:32:07.439
And he might still be the idiot who died

07:32:07.439 --> 07:32:09.779
while the real heroes saved the day.

07:32:09.840 --> 07:32:11.580
But this was his chance.

07:32:11.639 --> 07:32:14.639
A chance to be a different kind of hero

07:32:14.639 --> 07:32:18.000
one who stood in the way, one who got

07:32:18.000 --> 07:32:20.220
noticed, so that someone else could

07:32:20.220 --> 07:32:20.880
live.

07:32:21.240 --> 07:32:23.880
Heroes don't have to stab the bad guy in

07:32:23.880 --> 07:32:25.860
the heart, or save the whole world.

07:32:25.979 --> 07:32:27.659
Maybe it was enough.

07:32:27.720 --> 07:32:31.380
More than enough, to save his sister and

07:32:31.380 --> 07:32:32.159
Kinkaju.

07:32:32.220 --> 07:32:35.700
All he had to do was stop hiding.

07:32:35.759 --> 07:32:39.119
Anemone, he said urgently.

07:32:39.180 --> 07:32:42.180
I don't know if this will work, but if it

07:32:42.180 --> 07:32:44.400
does, get out of here as fast as you

07:32:44.400 --> 07:32:44.520
can.

07:32:44.639 --> 07:32:46.919
Go find Kibley and make him help you.

07:32:46.979 --> 07:32:50.220
He closed his claws around the stick and

07:32:50.220 --> 07:32:50.939
took a deep breath.

07:32:51.000 --> 07:32:53.459
I'm not going to leave you in danger

07:32:53.459 --> 07:32:56.639
anymore while I hide, but it means you

07:32:56.639 --> 07:32:57.599
have to be the hero now.

07:32:57.659 --> 07:33:00.720
Turtle glanced down at the stick again.

07:33:00.779 --> 07:33:03.540
His heart was pounding, and his insides

07:33:03.540 --> 07:33:05.279
were threatening to dissolve into sand

07:33:05.279 --> 07:33:08.040
but he couldn't hide anymore, for

07:33:08.040 --> 07:33:09.840
Kinkachu, for anemone.

07:33:09.959 --> 07:33:11.159
For everyone.

07:33:11.220 --> 07:33:13.979
He tossed the stick through the air to

07:33:13.979 --> 07:33:14.459
his sister.

07:33:14.520 --> 07:33:18.360
For a moment, as it was airborne, dark

07:33:18.360 --> 07:33:19.799
stalker's head snapped up.

07:33:19.860 --> 07:33:23.279
Perhaps a 1000 new futures were crowding

07:33:23.279 --> 07:33:23.759
into his mind.

07:33:23.819 --> 07:33:26.700
Perhaps he knew for a moment what was

07:33:26.700 --> 07:33:28.860
about to happen, and he saw what he was

07:33:28.860 --> 07:33:31.139
about to lose. and where it might lead.

07:33:31.200 --> 07:33:34.319
But then Anemone caught the stick in her

07:33:34.319 --> 07:33:37.979
front talons, and then, Dark Stalker saw

07:33:37.979 --> 07:33:38.340
turtle.

07:33:38.400 --> 07:33:40.439
And whatever future he had been looking

07:33:40.439 --> 07:33:43.439
at was forgotten as his eyes flashed with

07:33:43.439 --> 07:33:43.860
fury.

07:33:43.919 --> 07:33:47.220
Fathom, he snarled.

07:33:47.279 --> 07:33:49.680
A blast of flame shot out of his mouth

07:33:49.680 --> 07:33:53.279
and enveloped turtle in fire, blistering

07:33:53.279 --> 07:33:54.900
heat scorched over turtle.

07:33:54.959 --> 07:33:56.939
He threw himself to the ground with his

07:33:56.939 --> 07:33:57.779
wings over his head.

07:33:57.840 --> 07:34:00.419
I'm not fathom, he shouted.

07:34:00.479 --> 07:34:01.500
I'm turtle.

07:34:01.560 --> 07:34:04.439
Kinkachu screamed, and leaped at Dark

07:34:04.439 --> 07:34:06.959
Stalker's head, her talons wrapped around

07:34:06.959 --> 07:34:09.840
his snout, her wings beat at his ears, and

07:34:09.840 --> 07:34:12.659
she reared back, opening her mouth wide.

07:34:12.720 --> 07:34:15.720
Jets of black venom shot from her fangs

07:34:15.720 --> 07:34:19.259
and landed splat, sizzle. across Dark

07:34:19.259 --> 07:34:20.939
Stalker's face, and in one of his eyes.

07:34:21.000 --> 07:34:24.540
Dark Stalker roared and threw her off.

07:34:24.599 --> 07:34:27.479
Kinkaju landed on the floor and skidded

07:34:27.479 --> 07:34:28.319
halfway across the room.

07:34:28.439 --> 07:34:32.639
Oh, moonfire and star vomit.

07:34:32.700 --> 07:34:35.220
Dark Stalker shouted, clutching his

07:34:35.220 --> 07:34:35.639
face.

07:34:35.700 --> 07:34:37.619
Heel by all the snakes.

07:34:37.740 --> 07:34:41.099
He lifted his talons away, and Turtle saw

07:34:41.099 --> 07:34:43.680
that his scales were undamaged, but there

07:34:43.680 --> 07:34:45.599
was a black hole where his eyeball had

07:34:45.599 --> 07:34:45.779
been.

07:34:45.840 --> 07:34:49.439
A moment later, it filmed over and a new

07:34:49.439 --> 07:34:51.180
eye started to grow into the spot.

07:34:51.240 --> 07:34:54.959
My accidental invulnerability spell

07:34:54.959 --> 07:34:55.500
worked too.

07:34:55.560 --> 07:34:58.319
Turtle realized, stretching out his

07:34:58.319 --> 07:34:58.799
wings.

07:34:58.860 --> 07:35:00.479
The fire had not burned him.

07:35:00.540 --> 07:35:01.919
He was unharmed.

07:35:01.979 --> 07:35:03.900
He stood up and looked around

07:35:03.900 --> 07:35:04.619
frantically.

07:35:04.680 --> 07:35:06.360
Anemone was gone.

07:35:06.419 --> 07:35:10.139
She'd escaped in a chaos, small enough to

07:35:10.139 --> 07:35:11.520
fit out one of the narrow windows.

07:35:11.580 --> 07:35:14.340
He hoped she was on her way to Jade

07:35:14.340 --> 07:35:16.680
Mountain right now, clutching his stick

07:35:16.680 --> 07:35:18.840
erased from dark stalker's memory.

07:35:18.900 --> 07:35:20.639
He hoped it would keep her safe.

07:35:20.700 --> 07:35:23.520
If Dark Stalker didn't know she existed

07:35:23.520 --> 07:35:24.779
he couldn't control her.

07:35:24.840 --> 07:35:27.479
As long as she stayed hidden, she could

07:35:27.479 --> 07:35:27.959
still be free.

07:35:28.020 --> 07:35:31.319
He also hoped he could trust her.

07:35:31.380 --> 07:35:34.139
Would she do the right thing, now that

07:35:34.139 --> 07:35:34.619
she was free?

07:35:34.680 --> 07:35:37.200
Would she know what the right thing was?

07:35:37.259 --> 07:35:40.560
He darted over to Kinkaju, who was

07:35:40.560 --> 07:35:41.580
struggling back to her feet?

07:35:41.639 --> 07:35:43.259
Are you all right?

07:35:43.319 --> 07:35:45.360
he asked, trying to help her up.

07:35:45.419 --> 07:35:48.299
Oh, you're not a pile of ash.

07:35:48.360 --> 07:35:49.139
She said.

07:35:49.200 --> 07:35:51.180
She collapsed to the floor again.

07:35:51.240 --> 07:35:53.459
That is such a relief.

07:35:53.520 --> 07:35:55.799
I'm going to lie here and be relieved for

07:35:55.799 --> 07:35:56.220
a minute.

07:35:56.279 --> 07:35:57.000
Don't mind me.

07:35:57.119 --> 07:35:59.759
I wish you would stop getting yourself

07:35:59.759 --> 07:36:01.560
hurt, Turtle whispered.

07:36:01.619 --> 07:36:03.900
Me too, she said.

07:36:03.959 --> 07:36:05.279
Talk to the bad guys.

07:36:05.340 --> 07:36:06.840
Tell them to stop hurting me.

07:36:06.900 --> 07:36:09.419
She tried to move one of her wings and

07:36:09.419 --> 07:36:10.020
winced.

07:36:10.080 --> 07:36:11.939
Ow, ow, ow.

07:36:12.060 --> 07:36:15.659
Here, Turtle said, giving her the healing

07:36:15.659 --> 07:36:15.959
rock.

07:36:16.020 --> 07:36:17.040
This might help.

07:36:17.099 --> 07:36:20.279
He glanced over his shoulder, saw that

07:36:20.279 --> 07:36:21.900
Dark Stalker was still holding his eyes

07:36:21.900 --> 07:36:24.360
shut, and pressed the entire pouch into

07:36:24.360 --> 07:36:24.959
her talons.

07:36:25.020 --> 07:36:28.080
Pretend this is yours, he whispered.

07:36:28.139 --> 07:36:29.880
Maybe something in here can help.

07:36:29.939 --> 07:36:33.419
I'm scared for you, she whispered back.

07:36:33.479 --> 07:36:36.299
Just making sure you get to be more than

07:36:36.299 --> 07:36:38.459
the dead sidekick, he said.

07:36:38.520 --> 07:36:40.200
You're a lot more than that to me.

07:36:40.259 --> 07:36:43.619
I love you, turtle, she whispered.

07:36:43.680 --> 07:36:46.200
Softer than ripples in a still pool.

07:36:46.259 --> 07:36:50.340
You don't really, he said. feeling his

07:36:50.340 --> 07:36:51.240
heart break a little more.

07:36:51.299 --> 07:36:54.060
Anemone put a spell on you to love me.

07:36:54.119 --> 07:36:55.259
I'm so sorry.

07:36:55.319 --> 07:36:57.840
Oh, she said.

07:36:57.959 --> 07:37:00.180
That's not cool.

07:37:00.240 --> 07:37:02.279
But I feel like I love you.

07:37:02.340 --> 07:37:05.400
And I'm afraid this is our tragic goodbye

07:37:05.400 --> 07:37:06.659
so don't argue with me.

07:37:06.779 --> 07:37:09.779
My apologies, Kinkachu.

07:37:09.840 --> 07:37:12.419
Dark Stalker rumbled behind Turtle.

07:37:12.479 --> 07:37:14.040
I didn't mean to hurt you.

07:37:14.099 --> 07:37:17.220
Although in my defense, you did melt my

07:37:17.220 --> 07:37:17.639
eyeball.

07:37:17.700 --> 07:37:20.880
Turtle turned and found himself face to

07:37:20.880 --> 07:37:22.380
face with Dark Stalker.

07:37:22.439 --> 07:37:25.380
Those black eyes were seeing him for the

07:37:25.380 --> 07:37:28.200
1st time, since dark stalker swarmed out

07:37:28.200 --> 07:37:28.680
of the mountain.

07:37:28.740 --> 07:37:31.919
It's all coming back to me.

07:37:31.979 --> 07:37:33.959
Dark Stalker rumbled.

07:37:34.080 --> 07:37:35.459
Turtle.

07:37:35.580 --> 07:37:36.720
Yes.

07:37:36.779 --> 07:37:38.400
Moon's friend.

07:37:38.459 --> 07:37:40.680
Fathom's descendant.

07:37:40.740 --> 07:37:42.840
You look exactly like him.

07:37:42.900 --> 07:37:45.419
I believe I had a whole plan for you

07:37:45.419 --> 07:37:48.000
before you muddled it up by hiding like

07:37:48.000 --> 07:37:48.180
that.

07:37:48.240 --> 07:37:51.419
He tapped turtle lightly on the nose.

07:37:51.479 --> 07:37:55.439
Surprisingly clever, especially for you.

07:37:55.500 --> 07:37:57.659
I would never have guessed you had it in

07:37:57.659 --> 07:37:57.840
you.

07:37:57.900 --> 07:38:01.439
Whatever you're going to do to me, Turtle

07:38:01.439 --> 07:38:03.840
said, please, let Kinkaju go.

07:38:03.959 --> 07:38:05.939
Dog Stalker chuckled.

07:38:06.000 --> 07:38:08.639
I would never hurt a ball of fluff like

07:38:08.639 --> 07:38:08.880
her.

07:38:08.939 --> 07:38:11.159
Ball of fluff?

07:38:11.220 --> 07:38:12.419
Kingaju protested.

07:38:12.479 --> 07:38:13.860
I just melted your eye.

07:38:13.919 --> 07:38:15.419
I am totally terrifying.

07:38:15.479 --> 07:38:17.520
Kingajoush.

07:38:17.580 --> 07:38:20.099
Turtle said, nudging her sharply.

07:38:20.159 --> 07:38:23.939
No, I promised Moon I wouldn't hurt her

07:38:23.939 --> 07:38:24.299
friends.

07:38:24.360 --> 07:38:27.720
Dog stalker said thoughtfully, and she's

07:38:27.720 --> 07:38:28.619
very fond of both of you.

07:38:28.680 --> 07:38:31.799
Of course, she doesn't know where you are

07:38:31.799 --> 07:38:33.419
he said to Turtle.

07:38:33.479 --> 07:38:37.080
So, for the time being, let's stick you

07:38:37.080 --> 07:38:39.599
in the dungeon until I decide how you can

07:38:39.599 --> 07:38:40.020
be useful.

07:38:40.080 --> 07:38:43.139
Dark Stalker bent down and took

07:38:43.139 --> 07:38:45.540
Kinkachu's chin in his talons, looking

07:38:45.540 --> 07:38:46.200
into her eyes.

07:38:46.259 --> 07:38:48.119
As for you.

07:38:48.180 --> 07:38:50.939
I enchant you to forget about everything

07:38:50.939 --> 07:38:52.919
that happened in this throne room today.

07:38:52.979 --> 07:38:56.400
You'll wake up from your suntime in an

07:38:56.400 --> 07:38:59.279
hour, and carry on with your day, as

07:38:59.279 --> 07:39:01.740
though everything is normal, and turtle

07:39:01.740 --> 07:39:02.400
is not here.

07:39:02.459 --> 07:39:05.340
Kinkachu went very still.

07:39:05.459 --> 07:39:08.279
Her eyes flicked from dark stalker to

07:39:08.279 --> 07:39:08.639
turtle.

07:39:08.700 --> 07:39:10.740
His spells don't work on her.

07:39:10.799 --> 07:39:12.479
Turtle remembered.

07:39:12.599 --> 07:39:15.000
This might be the one thing he'd done

07:39:15.000 --> 07:39:15.599
right.

07:39:15.659 --> 07:39:18.299
She nodded slowly and took a step back.

07:39:18.360 --> 07:39:20.939
Her expression was full of questions.

07:39:21.000 --> 07:39:23.279
The turtle knew she couldn't ask any of

07:39:23.279 --> 07:39:25.380
them without giving away that Dark

07:39:25.380 --> 07:39:27.060
Stalker's spell hadn't worked.

07:39:27.060 --> 07:39:30.360
Go on now, Dark Stalker said.

07:39:30.419 --> 07:39:33.659
Turtle and I need to have a little talk.

07:39:33.720 --> 07:39:37.439
Kinkaju gave Turtle an agonized look

07:39:37.439 --> 07:39:39.479
bowed her head, and flew away.

07:39:39.540 --> 07:39:42.000
She still had turtle's pouch.

07:39:42.000 --> 07:39:44.040
Maybe something in there would help her

07:39:44.040 --> 07:39:45.779
if she could figure out what any of it

07:39:45.779 --> 07:39:46.619
did.

07:39:46.680 --> 07:39:48.840
It's unfortunate for you.

07:39:48.900 --> 07:39:52.200
Dark Stalker said to Turtle, that you

07:39:52.200 --> 07:39:53.580
look so much like Fathom.

07:39:53.639 --> 07:39:56.580
He spread one wing around Turtle, and

07:39:56.580 --> 07:39:57.840
steered him toward one of the side

07:39:57.840 --> 07:39:58.319
doors.

07:39:58.439 --> 07:40:00.840
I have very good reasons to hate him, you

07:40:00.840 --> 07:40:01.020
know.

07:40:01.080 --> 07:40:03.119
It's going to make it hard to look at

07:40:03.119 --> 07:40:03.240
you.

07:40:03.299 --> 07:40:06.299
Although I suppose if you're locked away

07:40:06.299 --> 07:40:09.599
deep in my darkest dungeon, we can avoid

07:40:09.599 --> 07:40:09.959
that problem.

07:40:10.020 --> 07:40:13.680
When we leave the room, I can cast a

07:40:13.680 --> 07:40:15.060
spell, Turtle thought.

07:40:15.119 --> 07:40:15.900
But what?

07:40:15.959 --> 07:40:17.520
Something to help me escape.

07:40:17.580 --> 07:40:19.380
His mind raced.

07:40:19.439 --> 07:40:22.560
But just before they reached the exit

07:40:22.560 --> 07:40:25.979
Dark Stalker paused and regarded Turtle

07:40:25.979 --> 07:40:26.759
pensively for a moment.

07:40:26.819 --> 07:40:30.180
I wouldn't normally do this, he said.

07:40:30.240 --> 07:40:32.700
I always think an animus could be useful

07:40:32.700 --> 07:40:34.740
in some way, if handled correctly.

07:40:34.860 --> 07:40:38.220
But you managed to trick me once, and

07:40:38.220 --> 07:40:39.599
that makes me a bit nervous about you.

07:40:39.659 --> 07:40:42.000
So, I'm sorry.

07:40:42.060 --> 07:40:45.060
Dark Stalker kept his talons around

07:40:45.060 --> 07:40:45.900
Turtle's face.

07:40:45.959 --> 07:40:49.500
And chant this dragon to lose all his

07:40:49.500 --> 07:40:52.979
animus power right now, he said, so that

07:40:52.979 --> 07:40:54.840
he shall never be able to cast a spell

07:40:54.840 --> 07:40:55.380
again.

07:40:55.439 --> 07:40:58.979
Turtle caught his breath and caught it

07:40:58.979 --> 07:40:59.279
again.

07:40:59.340 --> 07:41:01.020
Gasping with disbelief.

07:41:01.080 --> 07:41:04.200
A strange sensation scraped over his

07:41:04.200 --> 07:41:06.720
scales, like a powerful scrubbing brush

07:41:06.720 --> 07:41:07.740
scouring him clean.

07:41:07.799 --> 07:41:09.599
It was gone.

07:41:09.659 --> 07:41:13.200
The faint tingling in his claws that had

07:41:13.200 --> 07:41:14.939
been there from the 2nd he hatched.

07:41:15.000 --> 07:41:16.860
He'd never even known what it was.

07:41:16.919 --> 07:41:19.680
Never guessed, that it was a sign of

07:41:19.680 --> 07:41:22.740
animus magic, and now it had vanished

07:41:22.740 --> 07:41:22.979
forever.

07:41:23.040 --> 07:41:25.560
He'd always thought he was ordinary.

07:41:25.680 --> 07:41:28.439
But he'd never been completely ordinary

07:41:28.439 --> 07:41:29.340
until this moment.

07:41:29.400 --> 07:41:33.659
Don't be too sad, Dark Stalker said.

07:41:33.720 --> 07:41:36.479
To be the most powerful animus in the

07:41:36.479 --> 07:41:36.659
world.

07:41:36.720 --> 07:41:39.659
You have to be the smartest, and that was

07:41:39.659 --> 07:41:41.159
never going to be you anyway, was it?

07:41:41.220 --> 07:41:43.919
Now all the pressure is off.

07:41:43.979 --> 07:41:46.259
You don't have to come up with something

07:41:46.259 --> 07:41:47.279
brilliant to stop me.

07:41:47.340 --> 07:41:49.500
Isn't that a bit of a relief?

07:41:49.560 --> 07:41:50.220
Really?

07:41:50.279 --> 07:41:54.180
Turtle's tail dragged on the floor as 2

07:41:54.180 --> 07:41:55.799
nightwing guards led him away to the

07:41:55.799 --> 07:41:56.279
dungeon.

07:41:56.340 --> 07:42:00.779
Caught by dark stalker, imprisoned, just

07:42:00.779 --> 07:42:02.580
as he had feared his story would end for

07:42:02.580 --> 07:42:03.000
so long.

07:42:03.060 --> 07:42:06.360
And worst of all, stripped of his magic

07:42:06.360 --> 07:42:06.779
as well.

07:42:06.840 --> 07:42:09.119
But anemone was safe.

07:42:09.240 --> 07:42:12.299
Turtle had finally atoned for the talons

07:42:12.299 --> 07:42:14.159
of power curse he gave her on the beach.

07:42:14.220 --> 07:42:18.360
And Kinkaju was safe, and Kibli was out

07:42:18.360 --> 07:42:19.799
there, ready to help.

07:42:19.799 --> 07:42:23.220
Between the 3 of them, maybe they could

07:42:23.220 --> 07:42:24.419
stop Dark Stalker.

07:42:24.479 --> 07:42:27.000
He had to cling to the thin hope that

07:42:27.000 --> 07:42:27.659
they could.

07:42:27.720 --> 07:42:30.900
Because if they didn't, there was no one

07:42:30.900 --> 07:42:31.139
else.

07:42:31.200 --> 07:42:35.880
Epilogue.

07:42:35.939 --> 07:42:40.259
In the kingdom of sand, 3 explosions

07:42:40.259 --> 07:42:43.259
rocked the markets at 3 different oases

07:42:43.259 --> 07:42:45.119
timed to go off simultaneously.

07:42:45.180 --> 07:42:47.880
Dragons wearing black hoods and gold

07:42:47.880 --> 07:42:50.400
medallions, stamped with a bird symbol

07:42:50.400 --> 07:42:51.840
were spotted fleeing the scenes.

07:42:51.900 --> 07:42:54.779
In the streets and tents and towns of the

07:42:54.779 --> 07:42:55.080
kingdom.

07:42:55.200 --> 07:42:57.540
Sandwings muttered and growled to one

07:42:57.540 --> 07:42:57.840
another.

07:42:57.840 --> 07:42:59.220
Who is doing this?

07:42:59.279 --> 07:43:01.979
Why isn't Queen Thorn keeping us safe?

07:43:02.040 --> 07:43:04.259
In the kingdom of the sea.

07:43:04.319 --> 07:43:06.840
A class of young dragonettes on an

07:43:06.840 --> 07:43:08.939
overnight trip was terrified half to

07:43:08.939 --> 07:43:11.819
death by a pale phantom that dove from

07:43:11.819 --> 07:43:12.180
the sky.

07:43:12.240 --> 07:43:15.000
It swept around the island where they

07:43:15.000 --> 07:43:18.240
were camped, hissing and snapping, and at

07:43:18.240 --> 07:43:20.819
least 5 of the dragonettes swore, it

07:43:20.819 --> 07:43:22.619
glared at them with beady black eyes.

07:43:22.680 --> 07:43:25.619
Rumors spread quickly that the tribe was

07:43:25.619 --> 07:43:28.020
being haunted, by the vengeful ghost of

07:43:28.020 --> 07:43:28.919
albatross.

07:43:28.979 --> 07:43:32.459
And far to the north, in the ice kingdom

07:43:32.459 --> 07:43:33.959
in the midst of a blizzard.

07:43:34.020 --> 07:43:36.419
Winter's brother hailstorm stood before

07:43:36.419 --> 07:43:38.520
the wall of rankings, shivering with

07:43:38.520 --> 07:43:38.819
fever.

07:43:38.880 --> 07:43:42.000
His claws brushed over the last spot

07:43:42.000 --> 07:43:44.400
where Winter's name had been not long

07:43:44.400 --> 07:43:44.819
ago.

07:43:44.880 --> 07:43:47.700
Why is this happening to our tribe?

07:43:47.759 --> 07:43:50.880
Are we being punished for what happened

07:43:50.880 --> 07:43:52.380
between me and winter?

07:43:52.439 --> 07:43:55.200
A dragon trudged through the snow toward

07:43:55.200 --> 07:43:58.139
him, but had to stop halfway, his body

07:43:58.139 --> 07:44:00.599
racked with deep, lung churning coughs.

07:44:00.659 --> 07:44:02.279
Is there news?

07:44:02.340 --> 07:44:03.779
Hillstorm asked.

07:44:03.840 --> 07:44:05.159
Are my parents any better?

07:44:05.220 --> 07:44:08.880
No, the other ice wing wheezed.

07:44:08.939 --> 07:44:09.900
They're getting worse.

07:44:10.020 --> 07:44:11.700
But there's something else.

07:44:11.759 --> 07:44:13.080
Someone else.

07:44:13.200 --> 07:44:16.560
Hailstorm waited through another storm of

07:44:16.560 --> 07:44:17.040
coughs.

07:44:17.099 --> 07:44:18.479
What is it?

07:44:18.540 --> 07:44:19.680
He said finally.

07:44:19.740 --> 07:44:20.639
What's happened?

07:44:20.700 --> 07:44:23.819
It's Queen Glacier. said the other

07:44:23.819 --> 07:44:24.240
dragon.

07:44:24.299 --> 07:44:27.479
She got the plague 1st. 3 days ago.

07:44:27.540 --> 07:44:30.419
I know, said Hailstorm.

07:44:30.479 --> 07:44:32.700
The world was swimming before his eyes.

07:44:32.759 --> 07:44:35.819
Heat blurred his vision, pounded through

07:44:35.819 --> 07:44:36.119
his blood.

07:44:36.180 --> 07:44:38.279
I'm sorry, sir.

07:44:38.279 --> 07:44:41.340
It's over, said the messenger.

07:44:41.400 --> 07:44:44.700
Snow covered his wings, his tail.

07:44:44.759 --> 07:44:47.759
Snow piled up around his talons, consuming

07:44:47.759 --> 07:44:48.599
him from all sides.

07:44:48.720 --> 07:44:51.659
He bowed his head, as though he was ready

07:44:51.659 --> 07:44:54.119
to sink into it, and become a part of the

07:44:54.119 --> 07:44:55.319
frozen landscape forever.

07:44:55.380 --> 07:44:59.639
The queen of the ice wings is dead.

07:44:59.700 --> 07:45:06.599
